title: Diurnal and circadian-regulated genes (I)
description: Analysis of plant molecular response to day/night cycling. Samples taken at 6 hour intervals throughout the day. Identification of genes that cycle with either a diurnal or a circadian pattern.

title: Germline development and function
description: Identification and kinetics of sperm-enriched, oocyte-enriched and germline-intrinsic patterns of gene expression. Identifies genes that participate in biological functions that make the germline unique.

title: Type 1 diabetes gene expression profiling
description: Examination of spleen and thymus of type 1 diabetes nonobese diabetic (NOD) mouse, four NOD-derived diabetes-resistant congenic strains and two nondiabetic control strains.

title: Bone marrow stromal cell lines
description: Examination of two functionally distinct human bone marrow stromal cell lines, HS-27a and HS-5. Four independent RNA samples from each cell line analyzed.

title: Heat shock from various temperatures to 37°C
description: Samples collected 20 min after temperature shift from either 17°C, 21°C, 25°C, 29°C or 33°C to 37°C. Included as part of a detailed characterization of global expression programs triggered by environmental stress.

title: Heat shock from 25°C to 37°C time course
description: Heat shock from 25°C to 37°C. Samples collected at several time points up to 80 minutes. Included as part of a detailed characterization of global expression programs triggered by stress.

title: Hydrogen peroxide response
description: Samples collected 20 minutes after exposure to 0.3 mM hydrogen peroxide. Wild type and mutant strains examined. Included as part of a detailed characterization of global expression programs triggered by environmental stress.

title: Stationary phase time course (y12)
description: Analysis of stationary phase. Culture grown to OD600 0.3 after which samples collected at various time points up to 13 days. Included as part of a detailed characterization of global expression programs triggered by environmental stress.

title: Nitrogen depletion time course
description: Samples grown in minimal medium without amino acids or adenine, low ammonium sulfate and collected at various time points up to 3 days. Included as part of a detailed characterization of global expression programs triggered by stress.

title: Hyper-osmotic shock time course
description: Samples grown in YPD supplemented with 1 M sorbitol and collected at several time points up to 60 minutes. Included as part of a detailed characterization of global expression programs triggered by stress.

title: Carbon sources
description: Samples grown in YP media supplemented with 2% weight to volume of glucose, raffinose, galactose, fructose, sucrose or ethanol as carbon source. Included as part of a detailed characterization of global expression programs triggered by stress.

title: Homeobox otd/Otx2 transcription factor action
description: Analysis of the effects of overexpression of orthodenticle homeobox genes otd (Drosophila) and Otx2 (human) reveals evolutionary conservation.  The otd/Otx2 homeobox genes play a role in embryogenesis of the head and brain.

title: Ume6 regulon (Ye6100subA)
description: Examination of wild type and ume6-deleted diploids during vegetative growth in glucose and acetate in order to expand the profile of ume6-regulated genes.

title: Diamide treatment time course
description: Diamide (1.5 mM) added to culture, and samples recovered at several time points up to 90 minutes. Included as part of a detailed characterization of global expression programs triggered by stress.

title: Dithiothrietol exposure time course (y13)
description: Dithiothrietol (DTT; 2.5 mM) added to culture and samples recovered at several time points up to 180 minutes. Included as part of a detailed characterization of global expression programs triggered by stress.

title: Hypo-osmotic shock time course
description: Cells resuspended in YPD medium without sorbitol. Samples recovered at 5, 15, 30, 45 and 60 minutes. Included as part of a detailed characterization of global expression programs triggered by stress.

title: Heat shock from 37°C to 25°C time course
description: Heat shock from 37°C to 25°C. Samples collected at 15, 30, 45, 60 and 90 minutes. Included as part of a detailed characterization of global expression programs triggered by environmental stress.

title: Heat shock, mild, at variable osmolarity
description: Heat shock from 29°C to 33°C, with or without addition of 1 M sorbitol. Samples collected at 5, 15 and 30 minutes. Included as part of a detailed characterization of global expression programs triggered by environmental stress.

title: Heat shock from 29°C to 33°C time course
description: Heat shock from 29°C to 33°C. Samples collected at 5, 15, 30 and 90 minutes. Included as part of a detailed characterization of global expression programs triggered by environmental stress.

title: Diauxic shift time course
description: Gene expression patterns accompanying the metabolic shift from anaerobic fermentation to aerobic respiration. Samples taken at several time points up to 20.5 h.

title: Cell cycle, alpha-factor block-release time course
description: Culture synchronized by alpha factor arrest, then samples taken every 7 minutes as cells went through cell cycle. Included as part of a comprehensive identification of cell cycle-regulated genes.

title: Cell cycle, elutriation time course
description: Culture synchronized by elutriation and samples removed at several time points up to 6.5 h. Included as part of a comprehensive identification of cell cycle-regulated genes.

title: Cardiac development, maturation and aging
description: Benchmark gene expression profile of heart ventricle at various ages to monitor changes in cardiac development. Examined embryonic stages through adolescence and adulthood.

title: Cochlear hair cell line differentiation time course (Mu11K-A)
description: Gene expression profile of differentiation of inner ear hair cell precursors in vitro. A conditionally immortal cell line derived from the mouse cochlea, UB/OC-1, examined from 0 to 14 days.

title: E2F1-regulated genes
description: Identification of E2F1-regulated genes that modulate the transition from quiescence into DNA synthesis, or have roles in apoptosis, signal transduction, membrane biology, and transcription repression.

title: Granulosa cell tumorigenesis  (Mu11K-A)
description: Comparison of global changes in ovarian transcriptomes uniquely associated with either granulosa cell tumors or luteomas, and identification of new markers for this tumor phenotype. Luteinizing hormone hypersecreting mice studied.

title: Granulosa cell tumorigenesis (Mu11K-B)
description: Comparison of global changes in ovarian transcriptomes uniquely associated with either granulosa cell tumors or luteomas, and identification of new markers for this tumor phenotype. Luteinizing hormone hypersecreting mice studied.

title: Congenital heart disease (Mu11K-A)
description: Use of E9.5 Csx/Nkx2.5 mutant embryos to identify downstream target genes and affected pathways of Nkx2.5 which has a function in cardiac differentiation.

title: Congenital heart disease (Mu11K-B)
description: Use of E9.5 Csx/Nkx2.5 mutant embryos to identify downstream target genes and affected pathways of Nkx2.5 which has a function in cardiac differentiation.

title: Cochlear hair cell line differentiation time course (Mu11K-B)
description: Gene expression profile of differentiation of inner ear hair cell precursors in vitro. A conditionally immortal cell line derived from the mouse cochlea, UB/OC-1, examined from 0 to 14 days.

title: Bone marrow B cell precursors (Mu11K-B)
description: Gene expression profiles of five consecutive stages of B cell development. Flow-cytometrically purified or ex vivo-isolated cells examined.

title: CD34+ cell analysis
description: Comparison of gene expression in CD34+ cells from bone marrow and G-CSF-mobilized peripheral blood to investigate why the latter are optimal for allogeneic transplant recipients.

title: Allergic response to ragweed in lung (U74Av2)
description: Analysis of allergic response to an immunogenic protein of ragweed pollen in lung. Determination of the temporal relationship between gene expression and airway allergen challenge.

title: Allergic response to ragweed in lung (U74Bv2)
description: Analysis of allergic response to an immunogenic protein of ragweed pollen in lung. Determination of the temporal relationship between gene expression and airway allergen challenge.

title: Lung hypertension recovery (U74Bv2)
description: Analysis of vascular remodeling following pulmonary hypertension. Lungs of normoxic and hypoxic treated animals analyzed. Hypoxia induces vasoconstriction then hypertrophy/hyperplasia of pulmonary vascular smooth muscle and endothelial cell proliferation.

title: Allergic response to ragweed in lung (U74Cv2)
description: Analysis of allergic response to an immunogenic protein of ragweed pollen in lung. Determination of the temporal relationship between gene expression and airway allergen challenge.

title: Lung hypertension recovery (U74Cv2)
description: Analysis of vascular remodeling following pulmonary hypertension. Lungs of normoxic and hypoxic treated animals analyzed. Hypoxia induces vasoconstriction then hypertrophy/hyperplasia of pulmonary vascular smooth muscle and endothelial cell proliferation.

title: Sex differences in immune response
description: Gene expression in lungs of males 15 and 40 days post-infection with Seoul hantavirus compared with females. Part of an investigation into whether sex steroid hormones modulate sex differences in host immune response.

title: Spinal cord injury and regeneration time course: at T9 (RG-U34A)
description: Temporal analysis of molecular mechanisms of spinal cord degeneration and repair. Analyzed spinal cord at thoracic vertebrae T9 at various time points up to 28 days post injury. Mild, moderate and severe injury examined.

title: Lung ventilation
description: Analysis of the separate and combined effects of large tidal volume ventilation and hyperoxia in the lungs of anesthetized animals, using 21 or 100% oxygen.

title: Copper regulon
description: Differential gene expression under growth conditions of excess copper or copper deficiency, regulated by Mac1 or Ace1 transcriptional activators.

title: Macrophages infected with Salmonella (SHAD2)
description: Identification of host pathways affected by the Salmonella virulence transcription factor phoP. phoP found to play a role in Salmonella-induced human macrophage cell death.

title: Macrophages infected with Salmonella (SHAI2)
description: Identification of host pathways affected by the Salmonella virulence transcription factor phoP. phoP found to play a role in Salmonella-induced human macrophage cell death.

title: Macrophages infected with Salmonella (SHS)(I)
description: Identification of host pathways affected by the Salmonella virulence transcription factor phoP. phoP found to play a role in Salmonella-induced human macrophage cell death.

title: Serum stimulation time course (10k_print2)
description: Temporal transcriptional program of primary fibroblasts in response to serum. Samples taken at various time points up to 24 hours.

title: Serum stimulation time course (10k_print1)
description: Analysis of a temporal transcriptional program in the response of primary fibroblast cultures to serum. Samples taken at 15 minutes and 2 hours.

title: Cancer cell lines (10k_print2)
description: Analysis of cell lines used in the National Cancer Institute's screen for anti-cancer drugs. Gene expression is linked to phenotypic properties and drug sensitivity profiles of the cell lines.

title: Transcriptional regulation (I)
description: Genetic linkage analysis of global expression levels in a cross between two budding yeast strains. Identification of cis-acting and trans-acting loci that modulate a total of 570 genes.

title: Transcriptional regulation (I)(dye-swap)
description: Genetic linkage analysis of global expression levels in a cross between two budding yeast strains. Identification of cis-acting and trans-acting loci that modulate a total of 570 genes.

title: Transcriptional regulation (II)
description: Genetic linkage analysis of global expression levels in a cross between two budding yeast strains. Identification of cis-acting and trans-acting loci that modulate a total of 570 genes.

title: Transcriptional regulation (II)(dye-swap)
description: Genetic linkage analysis of global expression levels in a cross between two budding yeast strains. Identification of cis-acting and trans-acting loci that modulate a total of 570 genes.

title: Tryptophan metabolism (ecoli_3.0)
description: Analysis of changes in gene expression elicited by perturbations of tryptophan metabolism using strains with mutations that affect tryptophan metabolism.

title: Tryptophan metabolism (ecoli_4.3)
description: Analysis of changes in gene expression elicited by perturbations of tryptophan metabolism using strains with mutations that affect tryptophan metabolism.

title: UV exposure time course (ecoli_4.3)
description: Time course of UV-responsive genes and their role in cellular recovery. MG1655 wild type strains analyzed.

title: UV exposure time course (ecoli_8.0)
description: Time course of UV-responsive genes and their role in cellular recovery. lexA SOS-deficient strains analyzed.

title: Sporulation time course
description: Temporal analysis of the developmental program of sporulation, which consists of meiosis and spore morphogenesis. Seven distinct temporal patterns of induction are observed. Samples recovered at several time points up to 11 hours.

title: Snf/Swi mutants (v1_2.2)
description: Whole-genome expression analysis of mutants deleted for a gene encoding one conserved (Snf2) or one unconserved (Swi1) Snf/Swi component.  The Snf/Swi complex controls transcription and chromatin structure.

title: Snf/Swi mutants (384_F_v1.0)
description: Whole-genome expression analysis of mutants deleted for a gene encoding one conserved (Snf2) or one unconserved (Swi1) Snf/Swi component.  The Snf/Swi complex controls transcription and chromatin structure.

title: Menadione exposure time course
description: Superoxide-generating drug menadione bisulphate (1 mM) added to culture and samples removed at several time points up to 160 minutes. Included as part of a detailed characterization of global expression programs triggered by environmental stress.

title: Cyclin overexpression
description: Cells arrested in G1 for CLN3 overexpression. Included as part of a comprehensive identification of cell cycle-regulated genes.

title: Steady-state temperature (y14)
description: Samples collected from cells grown continuously at 15°C, 17°C, 21°C, 25°C, 29°C, 33°C and 36°C. Included as part of a detailed characterization of global expression programs triggered by stress.

title: Heat shock from 30°C to 37°C time course
description: Cultures shifted from 30°C to 37°C and samples collected at 0, 5, 15, 30 and 60 minutes. Included as part of a detailed characterization of global expression programs triggered by environmental stress.

title: Dithiothrietol exposure time course (y14)
description: 2.5 mM dithiothrietol (DTT) added to culture and samples collected at several time points up to 480 minutes. Included as part of a detailed characterization of global expression programs triggered by environmental stress.

title: Amino acid and adenine starvation time course
description: Cells grown in minimal medium lacking amino acids and adenine. Samples taken at 0, 0.5, 1, 2, 4 and 6 hours. Included as part of a detailed characterization of global expression programs triggered by environmental stress.

title: Diurnal and circadian-regulated genes (II)
description: Analysis of plant molecular response to day/night cycling. Samples taken at 6 hour intervals throughout the day. Identification of genes that cycle with either a diurnal or a circadian pattern.

title: SBF-MBF genomic distribution (ORF_intergenic_v1.0) (I)
description: Identification of genomic binding sites of the sequence-specific transcription factors SBF and MBF. Provides understanding of the parallel but distinct functions of SBF and MBF in the mitotic cell cycle.

title: SBF-MBF genomic distribution (ORF_intergenic_v1.0) (II)
description: Identification of genomic binding sites of the sequence-specific transcription factors SBF and MBF. Provides understanding of the parallel but distinct functions of SBF and MBF in the mitotic cell cycle.

title: SBF-MBF genomic distribution (intergenic_v1.0) (I)
description: Identification of genomic binding sites of the sequence-specific transcription factors SBF and MBF. Provides understanding of the parallel but distinct functions of SBF and MBF in the mitotic cell cycle.

title: SBF-MBF genomic distribution (intergenic_v1.0) (II)
description: Identification of genomic binding sites of the sequence-specific transcription factors SBF and MBF. Provides understanding of the parallel but distinct functions of SBF and MBF in the mitotic cell cycle.

title: Cardiac hypertrophy, exercise-induced
description: Effects of chronic conditioning by swimming which increases left ventricular mass and induces myocyte hypertrophy. 8 week old FVB mice swum in tanks 7 days a week for 4 weeks. Animals sacrificed at several time points up to 28 days.

title: Serum stimulation with cycloheximide time course
description: Analysis of the transcriptional program in the response of human fibroblasts to serum. Serum added to fibroblasts in the presence of cycloheximide and samples taken at 0, 0.5, 2 and 4 hours.

title: Muscle function and aging (HG-U95A)
description: Comparison of gene expression in vastus lateralis skeletal muscle biopsies in healthy young (21-31 year old) and older (62-77 year old) men. Sample RNAs isolated from individuals and pooled into groups of 8.

title: Type 2 diabetes and insulin resistance (HuGeneFL)
description: Analysis of gene expression in pooled vastus lateralis muscle samples from insulin-sensitive and insulin-resistant equally obese, non-diabetic Pima Indians. A search for susceptibility genes for type 2 diabetes.

title: Type 2 diabetes and insulin resistance (Hu35k-A)
description: Analysis of gene expression in pooled vastus lateralis muscle samples from insulin-sensitive and insulin-resistant equally obese, non-diabetic Pima Indians. A search for susceptibility genes for type 2 diabetes.

title: Type 2 diabetes and insulin resistance (Hu35k-B)
description: Analysis of gene expression in pooled vastus lateralis muscle samples from insulin-sensitive and insulin-resistant equally obese, non-diabetic Pima Indians. A search for susceptibility genes for type 2 diabetes.

title: Type 2 diabetes and insulin resistance (Hu35k-C)
description: Analysis of gene expression in pooled vastus lateralis muscle samples from insulin-sensitive and insulin-resistant equally obese, non-diabetic Pima Indians. A search for susceptibility genes for type 2 diabetes.

title: Type 2 diabetes and insulin resistance (Hu35k-D)
description: Analysis of gene expression in pooled vastus lateralis muscle samples from insulin-sensitive and insulin-resistant equally obese, non-diabetic Pima Indians. A search for susceptibility genes for type 2 diabetes.

title: Shock and adaptive response to injury
description: C57/B6 mice subjected either to sham laparotomy or cecal ligation and puncture (CLP) and spleen samples taken 24 hours post surgery. Effort to increase understanding of shock and the adaptive response to injury at the level of the entire genome.

title: Autoimmune disease mechanisms
description: Examination of medullary thymic epithelial cells from aire-deficient mice. aire is autoimmune regulator gene. Aim to understand autoimmune disease mechanisms, esp.  autoimmune polyendocrinopathy candidiasis ectodermal dystrophy (APECED).

title: Dietary effects of long chain polyunsaturated fatty acids (Mu11K-A)
description: Dietary effects of long chain polyunsaturated fatty acids from arachidonate-rich fungal oil and fish oil on hepatic and hippocampal gene expression. Identified broad-spectrum effects on  major lipid metabolism transcription factors.

title: Dietary effects of long chain polyunsaturated fatty acids (Mu11K-B)
description: Dietary effects of long chain polyunsaturated fatty acids from arachidonate-rich fungal oil and fish oil on hepatic and hippocampal gene expression. Identified broad-spectrum effects on major lipid metabolism transcription factors.

title: Tumor suppressor protein p53 gene dosage effects
description: Analysis of tumor suppressor protein p53 gene dosage effects in HCT116 colorectal carcinoma-derived cell lines p53 -/-, +/- and +/+ at 0 and 12 hours. Cells with different numbers of functional TP53 alleles can be distinguished by gene expression profile.

title: HIV viral infection time course
description: Gene expression profile of proliferating normal peripheral blood mononuclear cells (PBMC) infected with HIV type 1 RF. Assessed at 0, 12, 24, 48, and 72 hours postinfection and compared with those of matched uninfected PBMC.

title: SIV disease progression
description: Analysis of SIV MAC 251 disease progression in Rhesus Macaque peripheral blood mononuclear cells (PBMC). Slow, typical and fast progression groups examined at baseline, 3 and 7 weeks post-infection.

title: Spermatogenesis regulation
description: Analysis of gene expression in follicle-stimulating hormone (FSH) treated Sertoli cells. Sertoli cells from 20 day rats were cultured in the presence of 25 ng/ml ovine FSH and gene expression monitored 0, 2, 4, 8 and 24 hours after addition of FSH.

title: Cytomegalovirus strain comparison
description: Human foreskin fibroblasts (HFF) infected with cytomegalovirus strains fhCMV-H (rapid spread in vitro) and fhCMV-T (slow spread in vitro). UV-inactivated viruses also examined to control for response to coat glycoprotein B and active viral infection.

title: Large-scale analysis of the human transcriptome (HG-U95A)
description: Gene expression profiles from a diverse array of tissues, organs, and cell lines, from the normal physiological state. Represents a preliminary description of the normal mammalian transcriptome.

title: Large-scale analysis of the mouse transcriptome (MG-U74A)
description: Gene expression profiles from a diverse array of tissues, organs, and cell lines, from the normal physiological state. Represents a preliminary description of the normal mammalian transcriptome.

title: Bladder tumor stage classification
description: Identification of clinically relevant subclasses of bladder carcinoma. Three major stages identified, Ta, T1 and T2-4. Ta tumors further classified into subgroups. A 32-gene molecular classifier was built.

title: Progesterone effects on uterus time course
description: Analysis of effects of progesterone on uterus tissue gene expression. 14 days after ovariectomy, mice injected subcutaneously with progesterone in sesame oil. Uterine horns removed for analysis at several time points up to 24 hours after injection.

title: Progesterone and Hoxa-10 relationship
description: Hoxa-10 +/+ and Hoxa-10 -/- littermates injected 14 days after ovariectomy with either progesterone in sesame oil, or just sesame oil. Uterine horns removed for analysis 6 hours after injection.

title: Wing imaginal disc spatial gene expression
description: Discovery of genes with restricted expression patterns in wing disc and potential roles in wing disc development. Wing imaginal discs dissected to generate body wall and wing/hinge fragments. Three biological replicates of each examined.

title: Inflammatory myopathy
description: Molecular profiles of muscle tissue in patients with inflammatory myopathies.

title: Mefloquine treatment of NG108 neuroblastoma cells
description: Neuroblastoma cells NG108 exposed to a physiological dose (4400 ng/ml) of antimalarial mefloquine (Lariam), or 0.25% DMSO (control), for 2 hours. Mefloquine appears to disrupt neuronal function through disrupted calcium homeostasis and ER stress.

title: Contextual fear conditioning paradigm
description: Mice subject to novel spatial context with 0.5 mA shock, shock alone or control. Alzheimer's mice (50% C57BL/6, 50% SJL) and MK-801-injected mice also examined. Dentate gyrus and CA1 hippocampus tissue examined 1, 2, 4 or 6 hours after treatment.

title: Interferon induction by small hairpin RNA
description: Embryonic lung fibroblasts (HLF) infected with control lentivirus, or lentivirus expressing MRG15 and MRGX small hairpin RNAs from the H1 polIII promoter. The MRG15 shRNA induces an interferon response that is unrelated to silencing of MRG15.

title: Cold stress time course in sugarcane
description: Expression profile of sugarcane plantlet leaves exposed to cold for 0, 3, 6, 12, 24 and 48 hours. Thirty-four cold-induced ESTs identified, of which 23 were novel cold-responsive genes that had not previously been reported as being cold-inducible.

title: Mammary tissue profile
description: Variety of bovine tissues hybridized against the bovine mammary (BMAM) array. Reference is bovine macrophage (BovMac) cell line. Contribution towards development of a mammary gland gene expression profile.

title: Congestive heart failure
description: Analysis of canine tachycardia-induced cardiomyopathy caused by several weeks of rapid ventricular pacing.  Left ventricular free wall samples from control dogs and dogs with pacing-induced heart failure compared.

title: Duchenne muscular dystrophy (MuscleChip)
description: Examination of muscle biopsies from Duchenne muscular dystrophy patients and normal subjects of various age groups.  Both mixed groups of patients (5 patient biopsies per group) and individual biopsies analyzed.

title: Juvenile dermatomyositis muscle profile (MuscleChip)
description: Examination of skeletal muscle from juvenile dermatomyositis (JDM) patients, a common pediatric inflammatory myopathy. Muscle biopsies processed singly or in mixed groups of two. Patients genotyped for TNFalpha which is associated with prolonged disease.

title: Microarray technology comparison (3OPHs version 1)
description: Part of a comparison of spotted long oligonucleotide arrays with in situ synthesized 25-mer arrays. Examination of amplified and unamplified K562 erythroleukemia RNA and Stratagene Universal Human Reference RNA.

title: Microarray technology comparison (HG-U95A)
description: Part of a comparison of spotted long oligonucleotide arrays with in situ synthesized 25-mer arrays. Examination of amplified and unamplified K562 erythroleukemia RNA and Stratagene Universal Human Reference RNA.

title: Platform type/amplification method cross comparison (16K cDNA)(I)
description: Part of a cross comparison of DNA microarray platforms and linear amplification methods. Double and single round amplified liver and spleen RNA analyzed on a cDNA array.

title: Platform type/amplification method cross comparison (16K cDNA)(II)
description: Part of a cross comparison of DNA microarray platforms and linear amplification methods. Single round amplified liver, spleen and universal RNA analyzed on a cDNA array.

title: Platform type/amplification method cross comparison (U74Av2)
description: Part of a cross comparison of DNA microarray platforms and linear amplification methods. Single round amplified liver and spleen RNA analyzed on Affymetrix array.

title: Medulloblastoma metastasis
description: Identification of genes causing medulloblastoma tumors to metastasize. Analyzed 23 primary medulloblastomas clinically designated as either metastatic or non-metastatic.

title: Muscle regeneration (U74Av1)
description: Cardiotoxin injected into mouse gastrocnemius muscle to induce muscle regeneration. Muscles profiled at 27 time points (0-40 days) post-injection. Transcriptional regulatory pathways defined.

title: Muscle regeneration (U74Av2)
description: Cardiotoxin injected into gastrocnemius muscle to induce muscle regeneration. Muscles profiled at 27 time points (0-40 days) post-injection. Transcriptional regulatory pathways defined.

title: Dystrophin-deficient mdx muscle regeneration
description: Examination of mdx mouse, Duchenne muscular dystrophy model. 16 week regenerating mdx muscle analyzed in search for salvage pathways that maintain skeletal muscle integrity in the absence of functional dystrophin protein.

title: Skin tumors and vitamin A supplements
description: Analysis of gene expression in skin of rats subjected to electron irradiation and the effect of dietary vitamin A supplements.

title: Ozone effect on airways hyperpermeability
description: Ozone is an environmental pollutant associated with  exacerbation of cardiopulmonary diseases like asthma. HeJ (Tlr4 mutant) and OuJ (wild type) exposed continuously to air or 0.3 ppm of ozone, and lungs  examined.

title: Alternatively activated macrophages
description: Study of IL-4 dependent alternatively activated macrophages (AAM). AAM implicated in pulmonary diseases like allergic asthma and nematode infections. Macrophages extracted from peritoneal cavity of wildtype and mutant (IL4--) mice infected with nematode.

title: Alveoli destruction time course
description: Temporal study of lung alveoli destruction induced by caloric restriction. Alveoli number and surface area are linked to oxygen consumption, and calorie restriction lowers oxygen consumption.

title: Alveolar septation (U74Av2)
description: Study of alveolar septation using the Mg-delta strain of fibrillin-1 deficient mice which display an early defect in alveolar septation, and serve as a model for Marfan syndrome and emphysema.

title: Alveolar septation (U74Bv2)
description: Study of alveolar septation using the Mg-delta strain of fibrillin-1 deficient mice which display an early defect in alveolar septation, and serve as a model for Marfan syndrome and emphysema.

title: Alveolar septation (U74Cv2)
description: Study of alveolar septation using the Mg-delta strain of fibrillin-1 deficient mice which display an early defect in alveolar septation, and serve as a model for Marfan syndrome and emphysema.

title: Allergen-induced goblet cells
description: A-J mice treated intratracheally with saline or IL13. Airway epithelial cells analyzed as they differentiate into goblet cells. Goblet cells increase mucus production which is a characteristic phenotype of allergic asthma.

title: Hypoxia
description: Analysis of the effects of intermittent hypoxia on brain, heart, lung and muscle tissue. Included as part of a sleep apnea study.

title: Hyperoxic lung injury (U74Av2)
description: Lung tissue from wild type and Nrf2 knock out mice examined after treatment with 100% oxygen to induce injury. Nrf2 mutant mice have increased susceptibility to hyperoxic lung injury. Search for downstream effector genes regulated by Nrf2.

title: Hyperoxic lung injury (U74Bv2)
description: Lung tissue from wild type and Nrf2 knock out mice examined after treatment with 100% oxygen to induce injury. Nrf2 mutant mice have increased susceptibility to hyperoxic lung injury. Search for downstream effector genes regulated by Nrf2.

title: Hyperoxic lung injury (U74Cv2)
description: Lung tissue from wild type and Nrf2 knock out mice examined after treatment with 100% oxygen to induce injury. Nrf2 mutant mice have increased susceptibility to hyperoxic lung injury. Search for downstream effector genes regulated by Nrf2.

title: Alveoli septation inhibition and protection
description: Analysis of how dexamethasone (DEX) inhibits normal lung septation and alveoli formation, and mechanism by which retinoic acid (ATRA) protects against DEX. Three day old mice treated with ATRA or control. On day 4, half of each group administered DEX.

title: Pulmonary fibrosis
description: Determination of genetic basis of sensitivity to pulmonary fibrosis induced by bleomycin by comparing susceptible (C57BL6/J) and resistant (Balb/c) strains. C57BL6/J experience inflammatory response then progressive lung disease, Balb/c do not.

title: Lung hypertension recovery (U74Av2)
description: Analysis of vascular remodeling following pulmonary hypertension. Lungs of hypoxic treated animals analyzed. Hypoxia induces vasoconstriction then hypertrophy/hyperplasia of pulmonary vascular smooth muscle and endothelial cell proliferation.

title: Methylprednisolone effect on liver: time course
description: Expression profiling of liver from animals treated with methylprednisolone. Liver examined at various time points up to 72 hours following methylprednisolone treatment. Results provide insight into prednisone pharmacodynamics.

title: Muscle, normal extraocular, profile
description: Molecular definition of extraocular muscles (EOM). EOM are anatomically and physiologically distinct from other skeletal muscles.

title: Cocaine effect on brain
description: Comparison of gene expression in brain of cocaine-treated and saline control animals. Amygdala, caudate putamen, nucleus acumbens, prefrontal cortex, and ventral tegmental area analyzed.

title: Pharmacogenomic effect of corticosteroid in skeletal muscle
description: Temporal analysis of skeletal muscle response to corticosteroid methylprednisolone. Wistar rats  injected with methylprednisolone and skeletal muscle analyzed at various time points up to 72 hours.

title: Juvenile dermatomyositis muscle profile (HuGeneFL)
description: Examination of skeletal muscle from juvenile dermatomyositis (JDM) patients, a common pediatric inflammatory myopathy. Muscle biopsies processed singly or in mixed groups of two. Patients genotyped for TNFalpha which is associated with prolonged disease.

title: Spinal cord injury and regeneration time course: at T9 (RG-U34B)
description: Temporal analysis of molecular mechanisms of spinal cord degeneration and repair. Analyzed spinal cord at thoracic vertebrae T9 at various time points up to 28 days post injury. Mild, moderate and severe injury examined.

title: Asthma exacerbatory factors
description: Comparison of epithelial cells derived from asthmatic and normal bronchial airways, and examination of factors that enhance inflammatory and immunologic responses which exacerbate asthma. Effects of ozone and rhinovirus examined.

title: Duchenne muscular dystrophy (HG-U95A)
description: Examination of muscle biopsies from Duchenne muscular dystrophy patients and normal subjects of various age groups. Both mixed groups of patients (5 patient biopsies per group) and individual biopsies analyzed.

title: Duchenne muscular dystrophy (HG-U95D)
description: Examination of muscle biopsies from Duchenne muscular dystrophy patients and normal subjects of various age groups. Both mixed groups of patients (5 patient biopsies per group) and individual biopsies analyzed.

title: Duchenne muscular dystrophy (HG-U95E)
description: Examination of muscle biopsies from Duchenne muscular dystrophy patients and normal subjects of various age groups. Both mixed groups of patients (5 patient biopsies per group) and individual biopsies analyzed.

title: Asthma and atopy (HG-U133A)
description: Investigation of CD4+ lymphocytes from patients with and without atopy, in combination with asthma.

title: Asthma and atopy (HG-U133B)
description: Investigation of CD4+ lymphocytes from patients with and without atopy, in combination with asthma.

title: Obesity and fatty acid oxidation
description: Identification of proteins involved in fatty acid oxidation in skeletal muscle. Fat oxidation may be reduced in morbidly obese individuals. Provides understanding of how obesity contributes to cardiovascular disease via insulin resistance.

title: Duchenne muscular dystrophy (HG-U95B)
description: Examination of muscle biopsies from Duchenne muscular dystrophy patients and normal subjects of various age groups. Both mixed groups of patients (5 patient biopsies per group) and individual biopsies analyzed.

title: Hypoxia and glucose metabolism
description: Analysis of the relationship between intermittent hypoxia (similar to what occurs with sleep apnea) and improvements in glucose tolerance.

title: Hepatocellular carcinoma metastasis
description: Generation of a molecular signature for metastatic hepatocellular carcinoma (HCC) and identification of genes relevant to metastasis and patient survival. Osteopontin identified as molecular marker for defining metastatic potential.

title: Muscle profiles
description: Examination of control adult rat extraocular muscle, cardiac muscle, leg gastroc-soleus muscle and smooth muscle from stomach wall.

title: Muscle response to acute resistance exercise
description: Trancriptionally and translationally-regulated gene expression underlying skeletal muscle hypertrophy induced by acute maximally activated eccentric contractions. Total RNA or polysomal RNA examined at one and six hours post contraction.

title: Diet induced changes in liver
description: Examination of gene expression profiles from liver of C57BL/6 wild type mice and LDL receptor deficient mice fed on either a low fat diet or a high fat, western-style diet for 12 weeks.

title: Cytokine treatment effect on liver
description: Liver mRNA profiles following intraperitoneal cytokine injection. Strains interferon gamma -/-, albumin-cre(-) Socs3(w/fl) and albumin-cre(+) Socs3(-/fl) injected with either PBS, interferon gamma, or interleukin 6, and liver examined at 4 hours.

title: Heat shock, kin82 mutant
description: Temporal analysis of wild type and kin82 mutant strains after heat shock from 25°C to 37°C. Samples collected at several time points up to 1 hour.

title: Hypo-osmotic shock, ppt1 mutant
description: Temporal analysis of wild type and ppt1 mutant strains after hypo-osmotic shock. Cultures grown with 1M sorbitol for ~20 hours, then cells resuspended in YPD after which samples collected at several time points up to 1 hour.

title: Stationary phase, ypl230w mutant
description: Temporal analysis of wild type and ypl230w mutant strains in stationary phase. Cultures were grown to OD600 of 0.27 (ypl230w) and 0.4 (wild-type), then samples collected at various time points up to 24 hours.

title: Ethynyl estradiol estrogen effect in uterus
description: Temporal examination of ethynyl estradiol (EE) in uterus of immature, ovariectomized C57BL/6. 0.1 mg/kg EE or vehicle administered and uteri harvested at 0, 2, 8, 12, or 24 hours, or three daily doses administered and uteri harvested at 72 hours.

title: Muscle function and aging - male (HG-U133A)
description: Comparison of gene expression in vastus lateralis skeletal muscle biopsies in healthy young (21-27 year old) and older (67-75 year old) men

title: Muscle function and aging - male (HG-U133B)
description: Comparison of gene expression in vastus lateralis skeletal muscle biopsies in healthy young (21-27 year old) and older (67-75 year old) men.

title: Chronic obstructive pulmonary disease
description: Study of the signaling mechanisms responsible for diaphragm muscle transformation from fast-to-slow fiber type in chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD) patients.

title: Oxygen-regulated gene expression in proteobacterium
description: Expression profiles of wild-type anoxygenic phototrophic proteobacterium grown under 0%, 3% and 30% oxygen tensions, and relationship to production of the photosystem.

title: Ligand screen in B cells: 2-methyl-thio-ATP
description: Temporal analysis of effects induced by 100 uM 2-methyl-thio-ATP in male c57BL/6 B cells. Cells incubated in culture with ligand and samples removed at several time points up to 4 hours. Spleen from male c57BL/6 used as reference.

description: Temporal analysis of effects induced by 120 nM macrophage inflammatory protein-3 in male c57BL/6 B cells. Cells incubated in culture with ligand and samples removed at several time points up to 4 hours. Spleen from male c57BL/6 used as reference.

description: Temporal analysis of effects induced by 1 uM neuropeptide Y in male c57BL/6 B cells. Cells incubated in culture with ligand and samples removed at several time points up to 4 hours. Spleen from male c57BL/6 used as reference.

description: Temporal analysis of effects induced by 100 nM platelet activating factor in male c57BL/6 B cells. Cells incubated in culture with ligand and samples removed at several time points up to 4 hours. Spleen from male c57BL/6 used as reference.

description: Temporal analysis of effects induced by 0.3 uM sphingosine-1-phosphate in male c57BL/6 B cells. Cells incubated in culture with ligand and samples removed at several time points up to 4 hours. Spleen from male c57BL/6 used as reference.

description: Temporal analysis of effects induced by 6 nM stromal cell derived factor-1 in male c57BL/6 B cells. Cells incubated in culture with ligand and samples removed at several time points up to 4 hours. Spleen from male c57BL/6 used as reference.

description: Temporal analysis of effects induced by 1.5 nM secondary lymphoid-organ chemokine in male c57BL/6 B cells. Cells incubated in culture with ligand and samples removed at several time points up to 4 hours. Spleen from male c57BL/6 used as reference.

description: Temporal analysis of effects induced by 10 uM terbutaline in male c57BL/6 B cells. Cells incubated in culture with ligand and samples removed at several time points up to 4 hours. Spleen from male c57BL/6 used as reference.

title: Ligand screen in B cells: transforming growth factor-beta
description: Temporal analysis of effects induced by 0.4 nM transforming growth factor-beta in male c57BL/6 B cells. Cells incubated in culture with ligand and samples removed at several time points up to 4 hours. Spleen from male c57BL/6 used as reference.

title: Ligand screen in B cells: tumor necrosis factor-alpha
description: Temporal analysis of effects induced by 6 nM tumor necrosis factor-alpha in male c57BL/6 B cells. Cells incubated in culture with ligand and samples removed at several time points up to 4 hours. Spleen from male c57BL/6 used as reference.

title: Ligand screen in B cells: untreated
description: Temporal analysis of untreated male c57BL/6 B cells. Spleen from male c57BL/6 used as reference.

title: Hypothalamus response to lipopolysaccharide and restraint stress
description: Analysis of gene expression profiles in the paraventricular nucleus of the hypothalamus in male C57BL6. Mice subjected to either bacterial lipopolysaccharide (LPS) challenge, restraint stress or a saline control for 1 or 3 hours.

title: Macrophage response to IL-6, and SOCS3 effect
description: Bone marrow-derived macrophages from mice that had received fetal liver cells from SOCS3+/+ or SOCS3-/- embryos analyzed. Macrophages either unstimulated, or stimulated for 100 or 400 minutes with 10 ng/ml IL-6.

title: DNA repair mechanisms in mycobacteria
description: Molecular analysis of DNA repair mechanisms. Bacteria exposed to 0.2 ug/ml mitomycin C, variable UV irradiation or 4 mM hydrogen perxoxide treatment for up to 12 hours.

title: Photosynthesis in proteobacteria
description: Molecular investigation of photosynthesis and the effect of varying illumination in proteobacteria. Bacteria illuminated with either lumiline bulbs at 10 W/m2 or tungsten bulbs at 100 W/m2.

title: Colon carcinoma response to butyrate and aspirin
description: Temporal analysis of colon carcinoma cell line CC531 response to 4.5 mM butyrate or 3 mM aspirin. Samples taken at 2, 6, 12, 16 and 24 hours.

title: Telomerase overexpression
description: Effect of overexpression of the telomerase catalytic subunit (TERT) in mammary epithelial cells (HMEC).  Findings imply that ectopic telomerase expression modulates growth-controlling genes and enhances cell proliferation.

title: Spinal cord injury and regeneration time course: at T9 (RG-U34C)
description: Temporal analysis of molecular mechanisms of spinal cord degeneration and repair. Analyzed spinal cord at thoracic vertebrae T9 at various time points up to 28 days post injury. Mild, moderate and severe injury examined.

title: Chitin synthesis
description: Investigation into chitin synthesis in wildtype BY4741 and mutant fks1 (elevated chitin). Cells exposed to chitin-inducing glucosamine either for 2 hours, or continuous steady state.

title: Aldosterone response
description: Identification of early aldosterone-responsive genes after 1 hour exposure in inner medullary collecting duct cell line, mIMCD-3. Aldosterone is major regulator of Na(+) and acid-base balance and control of blood pressure.

title: Serotonergic hallucinogen effect in somatosensory cortex
description: Effect of 5-HT2A seratonin receptor agonist (±)2,5-dimethoxy 4-iodoamphetamine (DOI) in somatosensory cortex. 129Sv mice injected with DOI (2 mg/kg or 10 mg/kg), 1 hour. Abnormal 5-HT2A receptor function implicated in depression and schizophrenia.

title: Dendritic cell subtypes
description: Profiling of murine splenic CD11c high dendritic cell subtypes. CD4+, CD8+ and CD8- CD4- cells analyzed both directly after sorting and after 2 hours cultivation.

title: Dermal burn wounds
description: Investigation into dermal burn wound healing. Thermal dermal injury induced. Skin excised at 0 hours, 2 hours, 3 days and 14 days post-injury.

title: Lithium response in yeast
description: Wild type CEN.PK113-7D grown with 20 g/L galactose. LiCl (10 mM, therapeutically relevant) added and samples analyzed at 0, 20, 40, 60 and 140 minutes after LiCl addition. Lithium inhibits phosphoglucomutase, affecting galactose uptake and growth.

title: Calorie restriction and aging (Mu11K-A)
description: Investigation of the effect of calorie restriction on the aging process. Gene expression profiles generated for control-fed 5 month, control-fed 30 month and calorie restricted 30 month C57BL/6 mice. Kidney tissue analyzed.

title: Calorie restriction and aging (Mu11K-B)
description: Investigation of the effect of calorie restriction on the aging process. Gene expression profiles generated for control-fed 5 month, control-fed 30 month and calorie restricted 30 month C57BL/6 mice. Kidney tissue analyzed.

title: Leprosy lesions
description: Molecular characterization of lepromatous leprosy (LL) and borderline tuberculoid (BT) leprosy skin lesions.

title: Glaucoma and aqueous humor outflow
description: Glaucoma study investigating molecular basis of increase in aqueous humor outflow when human ciliary muscle or human trabecular meshwork cells are treated with prostaglandin analogs latanoprost free acid or prostaglandin F2alpha.

title: Breast cancer and docetaxel treatment
description: Breast cancer core biopsies taken from patients found to be resistant (greater than 25% residual tumor volume) or sensitive (less than 25% residual tumor volume) to docetaxel treatment.

title: Aging in yeast
description: Wild type and sgs1 null yeast grown with or without DNA damaging agent methyl methanesulfonate (MMS). sgs1 homologous genes linked with Bloom's and Werner's aging syndromes in humans. sgs1 mutants have high sensitivity to MMS.

title: Anesthetic effect on brain
description: Analysis of effect of single or repetitive exposure to halothane or isoflurane inhalation anesthetics on whole brain tissue. Male Sprague Dawley rats examined.

title: Necrotizing enterocolitis development
description: Rodent model of necrotizing enterocolitis (NEC) used to study effect of formula feeding and hypoxia on NEC development. Newborn rats either breast fed, or formula-fed with hypoxic stress. Three pups sacrificed daily for 5 days. Terminal ileum examined.

title: Skeletal repair in non-union fractures (HG-U95A)
description: Identification of mechanisms leading to lack of skeletal repair in non-union fractures. Non-union fractures do not heal six months after injury and may cause advanced arthritis or loss of limb function. Normal and non-union callous bone samples examined.

title: Skeletal repair in non-union fractures (HG-U95B)
description: Identification of mechanisms leading to lack of skeletal repair in non-union fractures. Non-union fractures do not heal six months after injury and may cause advanced arthritis or loss of limb function. Normal and non-union callous bone samples examined.

title: Skeletal repair in non-union fractures (HG-U95C)
description: Identification of mechanisms leading to lack of skeletal repair in non-union fractures. Non-union fractures do not heal six months after injury and may cause advanced arthritis or loss of limb function. Normal and non-union callous bone samples examined.

title: RNA quantity effect
description: Analysis of the effect of varying starting quantity of RNA.  Three different amounts, 20 ug, 40 ug and 80 ug total Kc167 RNA used in homotypic labelings to determine optimal quantity of RNA.

title: Germination and gibberellin inhibitor
description: Analysis of effect of uniconazole-P, a gibberellin biosynthetic inhibitor, on wild type and pickle (pkl) germinating seeds. pkl mutants are defective in repressing embryonic differentiation characteristics. Gibberellins promote germination of seeds.

title: Congenital heart disease - E12.5 (Mu11K-A)
description: Examination of whole heart of embryonic day 12.5 Csx/Nkx2.5 heterozygous and homozygous embryos to identify downstream target genes and affected pathways of Nkx2.5. Nkx2.5 is a cardiogenic marker with critical function in cardiac differentiation.

title: Congenital heart disease - E12.5 (Mu11K-B)
description: Examination of whole heart of embryonic day 12.5 Csx/Nkx2.5 heterozygous and homozygous embryos to identify downstream target genes and affected pathways of Nkx2.5. Nkx2.5 is a cardiogenic marker with critical function in cardiac differentiation.

title: Arthritis synoviocyte response to TNF alpha
description: Temporal analysis of arthritic synovial biopsies treated with TNF alpha at 0, 4 and 24 hours.

title: Cardiac remodeling (Mu11K-A)
description: Evaluation of in vivo models of cardiac remodeling.  Mice underwent transverse aortic constriction (TAC); myocardial infarction (MI) or sham operation. Left ventricle free wall and septum tissues examined 1 week later.

title: Cardiac remodeling (Mu11K-B)
description: Evaluation of in vivo models of cardiac remodeling. Mice underwent transverse aortic constriction (TAC); myocardial infarction (MI) or sham operation. Left ventricle free wall and septum tissues examined 1 week later.

title: Colon cancer
description: Examination of transition from normal intestinal epithelia to adenomas and carcinomas in the multiple intestinal neoplasia adenomatous polyposis coli mutant mouse, APC(Min/+).

title: Idiopathic thrombocytopenic purpura
description: Idiopathic thrombocytopenic purpura (ITP) is an autoimmune hematologic disorder. CD3+ cells were studied in duplicate from healthy controls, patients with active ITP and patients with ITP in remission.

title: Muscle eccentric and isometric contraction
description: Tibialis anterior muscle eccentric contraction (EC) and isometric contraction (IC) comparison. Mice subjected to 50 EC or 50 IC using non-invasive model, and sacrificed 48 hours later.

title: Biomaterial engineering
description: Temporal gene expression analysis of fetal lung fibroblast cell line IMR-90 seeded onto collagen/chondroitin sulfate tissue engineering scaffold mesh material. Integration of genomic information with biomaterial engineering.

title: Cardiac aging
description: Comparison of young (3-4 month) and aged (20-22 month) male Fischer-344 heart ventricle. Reduced adrenergic signaling in the aged heart investigated.

title: DNA damage and UV radiation
description: Temporal analysis of differences in WS1 human skin fibroblast gene expression response to low (10 J/m2; induces transient cellular replicative arrest) or high (50 J/m2; induces apoptosis) doses of short wavelength UV radiation (UVC; 254 nm).

title: Spermatogenesis time course (MG-U74A)
description: Analysis of C57BL/6 testis from day 1 to adult. Determination of transcripts expressed specifically by male germ cells late in spermatogenesis (postmeiotic) reveals many candidates for contraceptive targeting and fertilization participants.

title: Type 2 diabetes and renal function
description: Kidney tissue from a genetic model of non-insulin-dependent diabetes mellitus (NIDDM) type 2 diabetic db/db mice compared with control nondiabetic db/m littermates. 8 and 16 week old mice examined. Renal failure is common with diabetes.

title: Circadian oscillations and cardiovascular function
description: Examination of molecular basis of circadian oscillation system in aorta. After 2 week acclimation to 12/12 hour light/dark regimen, C57Bl6 mice subjected to 36 hours constant darkness. Aortae subsequently harvested at 4 hour intervals to 48 hours.

title: Hepatocyte growth factor-treated kidney cells
description: Cultured Madin-Darby canine kidney (MDCK) cells treated with hepatocyte growth factor (HGF) for 0, 3 and 24 hours.

title: Spermatogenesis time course (MG-U74B)
description: Analysis of C57BL/6 testis from day 1 to adult. Determination of transcripts expressed specifically by male germ cells late in spermatogenesis (postmeiotic) reveals many candidates for contraceptive targeting and fertilization participants.

title: Spermatogenesis time course (MG-U74C)
description: Analysis of C57BL/6 testis from day 1 to adult. Determination of transcripts expressed specifically by male germ cells late in spermatogenesis (postmeiotic) reveals many candidates for contraceptive targeting and fertilization participants.

title: Heart failure and rescue (Mu11K-A)
description: Analysis of left ventricular (LV) gene expression to uncover genomic changes associated with cardiomyopathy and/or its phenotypic rescue by the beta-adrenergic receptor kinase, betaARKc.

title: Amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (Lou Gehrig's Disease)
description: Identification of amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (ALS) associated genes. Post mortem spinal cord grey matter from sporadic and familial ALS patients compared with controls. Attempt to identify mechanisms by which ALS destroys motor neurons.

title: Circadian rhythm in Clock and Cry mutants
description: Identification of CLOCK and CRY-regulated genes expressed in circadian manner in liver. Wild-type, Clock mutant and Cry-deficient C57BL/6 8-10 week old male mice examined at circadian times (CT) 14 and 2.

title: Ethylene treatment in seedlings
description: Effect of ethylene treatment on 3 day old etiolated wild type Columbia-0 Arabidopsis seedlings.

title: Photoperiodic gene expression
description: Comparison of short day and long day growth conditions in adult wild type Columbia-0 Arabidopsis apices. Plants grown under short day conditions for 30 days then shifted to long day for 0 or 7 days.

title: Leaf, stem and flower gene expression
description: Analysis of Columbia-0 leaf, stem and flowers grown in greenhouse or growth chamber. Expanding leaves harvested 15 days post germination. Expanding upper 2" of stem and developed flowers/unopened buds harvested 29 days post germination.

title: Disease resistance in callose synthase mutant
description: Examination of disease resistance mechanisms in powdery mildew resistant 4 (pmr4), a mutant lacking pathogen-induced callose. Infected and uninfected pmr4-1 and wildtype plants examined. Activation of salicylic acid signal transduction pathway implied.

title: Leaf morphogenesis control by JAW microRNA
description: Investigation of the molecular basis of jaw-D uneven leaf shape and curvature phenotype. Aerial parts of two week old jaw-d mutant and control plants examined. JAW microRNA guides mRNA cleavage of several TCP genes controlling leaf development.

title: Severe combined immunodeficiency (HG-U133A)
description: Investigation of molecular basis for immunodeficiency in severe combined immunodeficiency (SCID) patient. Thymocytes isolated from SCID patient compared with control subject.

title: Severe combined immunodeficiency (HG-U95A)
description: Investigation of molecular basis for immunodeficiency in severe combined immunodeficiency (SCID) patient. Thymocytes isolated from SCID patient compared with control subject.

title: Normal human tissue expression profiling (HG-U95A)
description: Analysis of gene expression in a variety of normal tissues. Samples typically composed of a pool of 10-25 individuals. Included as part of the GeneNote project.

title: Normal human tissue expression profiling (HG-U95B)
description: Analysis of gene expression in a variety of normal tissues. Samples typically composed of a pool of 10-25 individuals. Included as part of the GeneNote project.

title: Normal human tissue expression profiling (HG-U95C)
description: Analysis of gene expression in a variety of normal tissues. Samples typically composed of a pool of 10-25 individuals. Included as part of the GeneNote project.

title: Normal human tissue expression profiling (HG-U95D)
description: Analysis of gene expression in a variety of normal tissues. Samples typically composed of a pool of 10-25 individuals. Included as part of the GeneNote project.

title: Normal human tissue expression profiling (HG-U95E)
description: Analysis of gene expression in a variety of normal tissues. Samples typically composed of a pool of 10-25 individuals. Included as part of the GeneNote project.

title: Heart failure and rescue (Mu11K-B)
description: Analysis of left ventricular (LV) gene expression to uncover genomic changes associated with cardiomyopathy and/or its phenotypic rescue by the beta-adrenergic receptor kinase, betaARKc.

title: Stem cell self renewal and Bmi-1 (MG-U74A)
description: Molecular basis of renewal properties in Bmi-1-deficient central and peripheral nervous system stem cells. Bmi-1 is a polycomb transcriptional repressor. Forebrain and gut neurospheres cultured from postnatal day 0  Bmi-1 -/- and wild type mice compared.

title: Stem cell self renewal and Bmi-1 (MG-U74B)
description: Molecular basis of renewal properties in Bmi-1-deficient central and peripheral nervous system stem cells. Bmi-1 is a polycomb transcriptional repressor. Forebrain and gut neurospheres cultured from postnatal day 0 Bmi-1 -/- and wild type mice compared.

title: Stem cell self renewal and Bmi-1 (MG-U74C)
description: Molecular basis of renewal properties in Bmi-1-deficient central and peripheral nervous system stem cells. Bmi-1 is a polycomb transcriptional repressor. Forebrain and gut neurospheres cultured from postnatal day 0 Bmi-1 -/- and wild type mice compared.

title: MHC class II transactivator targets (MG-U74Av2)
description: Identification of new targets of major histocompatibility complex class II transactivator CIITA in dendritic cells (DC). Day 10 bone marrow-derived DC isolated from B6 background CIITA-deficient, MHC class II-deficient and wild type mice examined.

title: MHC class II transactivator targets (MG-U74Av1)
description: Identification of new targets of major histocompatibility complex class II transactivator CIITA in dendritic cells (DC). Day 10 bone marrow-derived DCs isolated from B6 background CIITA-deficient, MHC class II-deficient and wild type mice examined.

title: CD8+ effector and central memory T cells (MG-U74A)
description: Identification of mechanisms by which activated mast cells induce chemotaxis of antigen-experienced CD8+ effector (TEFF) but not central (TCM) memory T cells. Leukotriene B4 (LTB4) implicated in recruitment of TEFF cells to sites of allergic inflammation.

title: Embryonic stem cell cholesterol metabolism mutants
description: Transcriptional profiling of embryonic stem (ES) cell lines with mutations affecting cholesterol transport and metabolism. Abca1 +/- and Cdk4 +/- ES lines compared with controls.

title: CD8+ effector and central memory T cells (MG-U74B)
description: Identification of mechanisms by which activated mast cells induce chemotaxis of antigen-experienced CD8+ effector (TEFF) but not central (TCM) memory T cells. Leukotriene B4 (LTB4) implicated in recruitment of TEFF cells to sites of allergic inflammation.

title: CD8+ effector and central memory T cells (MG-U74C)
description: Identification of mechanisms by which activated mast cells induce chemotaxis of antigen-experienced CD8+ effector (TEFF) but not central (TCM) memory T cells. Leukotriene B4 (LTB4) implicated in recruitment of TEFF cells to sites of allergic inflammation.

title: Heart transplants
description: Examination of immunologic tolerance induction achieved in cardiac allografts from BALB/c to C57BL/6 mice by daily intraperitoneal injection of anti-CD80 and anti-CD86 monoclonal antibodies (mAbs).

title: Intraspecific variation - Canton S
description: Analysis of intraspecific expression differentiation shows that gene expression in males evolves more rapidly than in females. Canton S, Oregon R, Hikone R, a St. Louis-derived isofemale strain and four Zimbabwe-derived lines examined.

title: Intraspecific variation - Canton S (dye-swap)
description: Analysis of intraspecific expression differentiation shows that gene expression in males evolves more rapidly than in females. Canton S, Oregon R, Hikone R, a St. Louis-derived isofemale strain and four Zimbabwe-derived lines examined.

title: Intraspecific variation - Zimbabwe53
description: Analysis of intraspecific expression differentiation shows that gene expression in males evolves more rapidly than in females. Canton S, Oregon R, Hikone R, a St. Louis-derived isofemale strain and four Zimbabwe-derived lines examined.

title: Intraspecific variation - Zimbabwe53 (dye-swap)
description: Analysis of intraspecific expression differentiation shows that gene expression in males evolves more rapidly than in females. Canton S, Oregon R, Hikone R, a St. Louis-derived isofemale strain and four Zimbabwe-derived lines examined.

title: Midgut metamorphosis time course
description: Temporal analysis of midgut development. Examined 11 time points between 18 hours before puparium formation (BPF) to 12 hours after puparium formation (APF) as larval midgut is replaced by adult midgut in Canton S strain.

title: Larval tissue-specific transcripts
description: Identification of transcripts enriched in 5 differentiated larval tissue types. Epidermis with attached muscle, salivary gland, wing disc, midgut, and central nervous system tissues examined at 18 hours before puparium formation (BPF) in Canton S strain.

title: Cardiac hypertrophy and phosphoinositide 3-kinase
description: Analysis of the relationship between cardiac hypertrophy/cell size regulation with phosphoinositide 3-kinase (PI3K) signaling pathway. Constitutively active (caPI3K - hearts 20% larger) and dominant-negative (dnPI3K - hearts 17% smaller) mice examined.

title: Cell cycle and Tat transactivation
description: Analysis of effect of Tat transactivation during cell cycle. HeLa CD4+ cells transfected with epitope-tagged Tat plasmid or parental vector pCEP4. Cells synchronized with cell cycle blocker hydroxyurea or nocodazole and sampled at 0, 3, 6 and 9 hours.

title: Flower development (AtGenome1)
description: Dissection of flowering pathways using photoperiod floral induction of plants that have combinations of different FRIGIDA (FRI) and FLOWERING LOCUS C (FLC) alleles. Shoot apex examined at 0, 2 and 4 days after floral induction.

title: Flower development (ATH1)
description: Dissection of flowering pathways using photoperiod floral induction in Landsberg erecta or Columbia plants with combinations of different CONSTANS, FLOWERING LOCUS T and LEAFY alleles. Shoot apex examined at 0, 3, 5 and 7 days after floral induction.

title: Oxidative stress induced by allylamine
description: Analysis of Sprague Dawley thoracic aorta response to repreated oxidative stress induced via administration of 35 or 70 mg/kg allylamine for 20 days.

title: Thyroid hormone effect on cardiomyocytes
description: Analysis of effect of 48 hours exposure to thyroid hormone triiodothyronine (T3) and structural analogues DITPA and CGS on primary culture cardiomyocytes prepared from 18 day old fetus. Thyroid hormone may be useful in treatment of heart failure.

title: Thyroid hormone effect on cardiomyocytes (dye-swap)
description: Analysis of effect of 48 hours exposure to thyroid hormone triiodothyronine (T3) and structural analogues DITPA and CGS on primary culture cardiomyocytes prepared from 18 day old fetus. Thyroid hormone may be useful in treatment of heart failure.

title: Cervical cancer
description: Expression profiling of normal and cancerous cervix tissue samples at stages 1B, 2A, 2B and 3B.

title: Malaria resistance
description: Examination of molecular basis of malaria resistance. Spleens from malaria resistant recombinant congenic strains AcB55 and AcB61 compared with malaria susceptible A/J mice.

title: Muscle function and aging - female (HG-U133A)
description: Comparison of gene expression in vastus lateralis skeletal muscle biopsies in healthy young (20-29 year old) and older (65-71 year old) women

title: Muscle function and aging - female (HG-U133B)
description: Comparison of gene expression in vastus lateralis skeletal muscle biopsies in healthy young (20-29 year old) and older (65-71 year old) women

title: HCMV infection of foreskin fibroblasts
description: Expression profiles of foreskin fibroblasts at 12 time points beginning 30 minutes after infection by human cytomegalovirus (HCMV) and continuing until 48 hours after infection.

title: Coxsackievirus B3 pathogenesis (I)
description: Temporal analaysis of an in vitro model of coxsackievirus B3 (CVB3) infection. HeLa cells infected with either CVB3 or control PBS and samples examined at 0, 0.5, 1, 3, 5, 7 and 9 hours following treatment.

title: Coxsackievirus B3 pathogenesis (II)
description: Temporal analysis of in vitro model of coxsackievirus B3 (CVB3) infection. HeLa cells infected with either CVB3, CVB3 and U0126 (blocks cytokines and metalloproteinases) or control PBS, and samples examined at 0, 0.5, 3 and 9 hours after treatment.

title: Ionizing radiation effect on lymphoblastoid cells
description: Temporal analysis of effect of 3 Gy and 10 Gy ionizing radiation (IR) exposure on lymphoblastoid cells. Various time points up to 24 hours examined.

title: Auxin (6 varieties)  effect on seedlings
description: Analysis of the effect of 20 minute treatment with 6 different auxins on Columbia-0 seedlings.

title: Indole-3-acetic acid time course
description: Temporal analysis of effect of auxin indole-3-acetic acid (IAA) on Columbia-0 seedlings. 20, 40 and 60 minute time points examined.

title: DACH1-responsive genes
description: Analysis of effect of DACH1 in breast cancer cell line MDA-MB-231. DACH1 induced by ponasterone A treatment for 0, 18 or 36 hours.  DACH1 may regulate aberrant TGF beta signals that have role in breast cancer progression.

title: Uterine fibroid and normal myometrial tissue
description: Comparison of normal myometrium and uterine leiomyomas obtained from fibroid afflicted patients.

title: Rheumatoid arthritis and TNFalpha
description: Analysis of rheumatoid arthritis synovial fibroblasts (RASF) expressing dominant negative form of inhibitor of nuclear factor kappa B (Ik-B). Ik-B blocks TNFalpha. Cells treated with TNFalpha at 18 hours. TNFalpha known to increase progression of RA.

title: Cardiomyopathy, severe dilated
description: Examination of ventricles of 10 week mice overexpressing dominant-negative (dn) small GTP binding protein p21ras. dn-p21ras mice show severe cardiac dilation and decreased contractility. p21ras implicated in hypertrophic response of cardiomyocytes.

title: Myocardial infarction time course
description: Temporal analysis of acute myocardial infarction (AMI) induced by left coronary artery ligation. Left ventricle above and below left anterior descending (LAD) artery examined at 1 hour to 8 week time points.

title: Toxicosis induced by endophyte infected fescue seed
description: Characterization of fescue toxicosis in luteal tissue. Heifers fed endophyte free fescue seed (EF), endophyte infected fescue seed (EI) or EI supplemented with domperidone (EID). Fescue toxicosis thought to affect dopamine signaling pathways.

title: Cystic fibrosis pathology and 4-phenylbutyrate (HG-U133A)
description: Effect of 1mM 4-phenylbutyrate (PBA) at 0, 12 and 24 hours in cystic fibrosis bronchial epithelial model cell line IB3-1. PBA modulates heat shock protein and promotes trafficking of deltaF508 cystic fibrosis transmembrane conductance regulator (CFTR).

title: Cystic fibrosis pathology and 4-phenylbutyrate (HG-U133B)
description: Effect of 1mM 4-phenylbutyrate (PBA) at 0, 12 and 24 hours in cystic fibrosis bronchial epithelial model cell line IB3-1. PBA modulates heat shock protein and promotes trafficking of deltaF508 cystic fibrosis transmembrane conductance regulator (CFTR).

title: Angiogenesis
description: Temporal analysis of human umbilical cord vein endothelial cell (HUVEC) isolates treated with angiogenic factors vascular endothelial growth factor-A (VEGF-A) and placental growth factor (PlGF) in low or high serum media.

title: Inflammatory cytokine effect on primary lung endothelial cells
description: Examination of gene expression induced by interferon gamma (IFNg), tumor necrosis factor alpha (TNFa) and interleukin 4 (IL4) inflammatory cytokines on primary lung endothelial cells.

title: Inflammatory cytokine effect on primary aortic endothelial cells
description: Examination of gene expression induced by interferon gamma (IFNg), tumor necrosis factor alpha (TNFa) and interleukin 4 (IL4) inflammatory cytokines on primary aortic endothelial cells.

title: Inflammatory cytokine effect on primary dermal endothelial cells
description: Examination of gene expression induced by interferon gamma (IFNg), tumor necrosis factor alpha (TNFa) and interleukin 4 (IL4) inflammatory cytokines on primary dermal endothelial cells.

title: Inflammatory cytokine effect on primary colon endothelial cells
description: Examination of gene expression induced by interferon gamma (IFNg), tumor necrosis factor alpha (TNFa) and interleukin 4 (IL4) inflammatory cytokines on primary colon endothelial cells.

title: Pulmonary arterial hypertension and PBMC
description: Analysis of peripheral blood mononuclear (PBMC) cells in patients with pulmonary arterial hypertension (PAH). Altered gene expression patterns in PAH PBMCs may allow disease subgroup identification and prediction of treatment response.

title: Renal clear cell carcinoma (HG-U133A)
description: Investigation into mechanisms of renal clear cell carcinogenesis (RCC). Comparison of renal clear cell tumor tissue and adjacent normal tissue isolated from the same surgical samples.

title: Renal clear cell carcinoma (HG-U133B)
description: Investigation into mechanisms of renal clear cell carcinogenesis (RCC). Comparison of renal clear cell tumor tissue and adjacent normal tissue isolated from the same surgical samples.

title: Denervation effect on lacrimal gland
description: Analysis of lacrimal gland (LG) 7 days after greater superficial petrosal nerve sectioning. LG ipsilateral to the experimental side, sham operated and unoperated controls included. LG denervation results in severe dry eye like symptoms.

title: Fracture healing timecourse and the effect of age
description: Temporal analysis of gene expression following femoral fracture. Female Sprague-Dawleys at 6 (young), 26 (adult) and 52 (older) weeks of age at time of fracture. Samples analyzed at 0, 3 days, 1, 2, 4, and 6 weeks after fracture.

title: Multiple sclerosis and vitamin D
description: Examination of effect of 200 ng 1,25-dihydroxyvitamin D3 (1alpha,25-(OH)2D3) on B10.PL mice with severe (stage 2.5-3) experimental autoimmune encephalomyelitis (EAE), a model of multiple sclerosis (MS). Spinal cord tissue examined.

title: Postmortem skeletal muscle
description: Transcriptional profile of normal skeletal muscle collected at autopsy compared to surgical specimens.

title: Familial combined hyperlipidemia and USF1 haplotype
description: Comparison of subcutaneous adipose tissue from individuals with familial combined hyperlipidemia (FCHL) exhibiting either upstream transcription factor 1 (USF1) susceptibility or protective haplotype. USF1 regulates glucose and lipid metabolism genes.

title: Autoimmune disease and Nrf2
description: Analysis of spleen and liver tissue of 5 month old male and female transcription factor nuclear factor E2-related factor 2 (Nrf2) double knockouts. Nrf2-deficient female mice develop lupus-like autoimmune nephritis.

title: LEAFY transcription factor targets
description: Analysis of gene expression in 9 day old LEAFY-GR, 35S::LFY or Landsberg erecta seedlings treated with dexamethasone and/or cycloheximide identifies LFY targets which likely initiate changes required for vegetative to reproductive switch.

title: Diet study: yeast effect time course
description: Temporal analysis of gene expression in response to nutrition factors. Yeast-fed and yeast-restricted adults sampled at 12 hourly intervals. Genes and networks regulating insulin ligand and receptor activity characterized.

title: YODA MAPKK kinase characterization
description: Comparison of gene expression in vegetative rosettes of wild type and yda-2 (YODA MAPKK kinase) plants. YODA promotes extra-embryonic cell fates in basal lineage. Results suggest YODA is involved with a novel developmental signal transduction pathway.

title: Hepatocarcinogenesis induced by clofibric acid
description: Analysis of mechanisms of clofibric acid (CLO) induced hepatocarcinogenesis. Whole liver and early pre-neoplastic foci isolated by laser capture microdissection (LCM) examined.

title: Astrocyte response to beta amyloid peptide 25-35
description: Temporal analysis of cortical type I astrocytes cultured on beta amyloid peptide 25-35 fragment (bAP(25-35)). Samples examined at 12 hours, 1, 3, and 5 days. Amyloid plaques of Alzheimer's disease are composed of beta amyloid.

title: Hippocampal aging and cognitive impairment
description: Identification of aging-dependent cognitive decline gene expression. Hippocampal CA1 tissue collected from 4, 14, and 24 month old male Fischer 344 rats after 7 days training on water maze and object memory task.

title: Intestinal tract gene expression (MG-U74A)
description: Analysis of regional differences in gene expression profiles along the intestinal tract. Duodenum, jejunum, ileum, and colon of 8 week-old male Hsd:ICR(CD-1) mice examined.

title: Intestinal tract gene expression (MG-U74B)
description: Analysis of regional differences in gene expression profiles along the intestinal tract. Duodenum, jejunum, ileum, and colon of 8 week-old male Hsd:ICR(CD-1) mice examined.

title: Intestinal tract gene expression (MG-U74C)
description: Analysis of regional differences in gene expression profiles along the intestinal tract. Duodenum, jejunum, ileum, and colon of 8 week-old male Hsd:ICR(CD-1) mice examined.

title: Extraocular and limb muscle comparison
description: Molecular definition of extraocular muscle (EOM). Autopsy superior rectus EOM compared with biopsy limb quadriceps femoris muscle.

title: Syracuse high and low avoidance learning comparison
description: Comparison of hippocampus tissue from Syracuse High Avoidance (SHA) and Syracuse Low Avoidance (SLA) learning rats.  Syracuse strains provide model for studying anxiety.

title: Colorectal tumor cell response to X radiation (19K 3 Part A)
description: Evaluation of colorectal tumor cell line (HCT116) response to X radiation (XR). XR sensitive HCT116-CloneK cells treated at 4 Gy for 10 minutes, 6 hours, and 24 hours.

title: Colorectal tumor cell response to X radiation (19K 3 Part B)
description: Evaluation of colorectal tumor cell line (HCT116) response to X radiation (XR). XR sensitive HCT116-CloneK cells treated at 4 Gy for 10 minutes, 6 hours, and 24 hours.

title: Oxidative stress and glutaredoxin 5-deficient mutant
description: Transcriptome analysis of glutaredoxin 5-deficient (grx5) mutant, a model for continuous moderate oxidative stress. Respiratory petite (pet117) mutants and wild type also examined.

title: Multiple myeloma and bone lesions
description: Comparison of gene expression in bone marrow plasma cells of multiple myeloma patients with and without bone lesions. Osteolytic lesions increase in multiple myeloma patients.

title: Hydrostatic pressure-responsive genes in optic nerve head astrocytes
description: Temporal analysis of how astrocytes in the optic nerve head (ONH) respond to changes in intraocular pressure (IOP). ONH astrocytes exposed to 60 mm Hg hydrostatic pressure for 6, 24, and 48 hours. Lends understanding to pathogenesis of glaucoma.

title: Uterine smooth muscle tumor characterization
description: Comparison of gene expression in uterine smooth muscle tumors. Normal myometrium, benign uterine leiomyoma, malignant uterine and extra-uterine leiomyosarcoma examined.

title: Smoking-induced changes in airway transcriptome
description: Analysis of cigarette smoking-induced changes in  bronchial epithelia, and reversibility of effects when smoking is discontinued. May provide insight to molecular events leading to chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD) and lung cancer.

title: Prostate cancer antiandrogen resistance
description: Analysis of mechanisms of prostate cancer resistance to antiandrogen therapy. Isogenic hormone-sensitive and drug-resistant hormone-refractory xenograft pairs examined.

title: Androgen receptor antagonist to agonist conversion
description: Examination of antagonist to agonist conversion in androgen receptor-expressing hormone-sensitive LNCaP prostate cancer cells. Cells challenged with increasing doses of R1881, or bicalutamide.

title: DNA methylation and histone deacetylation in neural stem cells
description: Examination of DNA methylation and histone deacetylation in neural stem cells. Neurospheres from bcl2 transgene E14.5 forebrains treated with 150 nM trichostatin A (histone deacetylase inhibitor) or 500 nM 5-aza-2'-deoxycytidine (demethylating agent).

title: Essential thrombocythemia megakaryocytes
description: Malignant bone marrow CD34+ thrombopoietin-treated megakaryocytes from essential thrombocythemia (ET) patients compared with normal megakaryocytes.

title: Mesangioblast stem cell clone comparison (MG-U74A)
description: Comparison of mesangioblast clone lines D16 and D351 derived from E9.5 C57BL6 embryo dorsal aorta. Mesangioblast vessel-associated stem cells have possible use in therapy of primary myopathies.

title: Mesangioblast stem cell clone comparison (MG-U74B)
description: Comparison of mesangioblast clone lines D16 and D351 derived from E9.5 C57BL6 embryo dorsal aorta. Mesangioblast vessel-associated stem cells have possible use in therapy of primary myopathies.

title: Mesangioblast stem cell clone comparison (MG-U74C)
description: Comparison of mesangioblast clone lines D16 and D351 derived from E9.5 C57BL6 embryo dorsal aorta. Mesangioblast vessel-associated stem cells have possible use in therapy of primary myopathies.

title: Extraocular muscle layer profiles (HG-U133A)
description: Analysis of adult monkey whole medial and lateral rectus extraocular muscle (EOM), and microdissected medial rectus global and orbital EOM layers.

title: Extraocular muscle layer profiles (HG-U133B)
description: Analysis of adult monkey whole medial and lateral rectus extraocular muscle (EOM), and microdissected medial rectus global and orbital EOM layers.

title: Inflammatory bowel disease (HG-U133A)
