description: Investigation into inflammatory bowel disease gene expression. Terminal ileum and colon transversum biopsies from Crohn´s disease, ulcerative colitis and control patients examined.

title: Inflammatory bowel disease (HG-U133B)
description: Investigation into inflammatory bowel disease gene expression. Terminal ileum and colon transversum biopsies from Crohn´s disease, ulcerative colitis and control patients examined.

title: Osteopontin overexpression
description: Investigation into effect of constitutive overexpression of osteopontin (OPN) in breast carcinoma cell line 21NT.

title: Bone cell tissue culture on amino acid conjugated surfaces
description: Evaluation of osteosarcoma TE85 cell tissue culture on a variety of amino acid conjugated surfaces at 6 and 32 hours. Study holds potential applications for bone tissue engineering.

title: Duchenne muscular dystrophy (II) (HG-U95A)
description: Search for modifying factors and pathogenic pathways involved in Duchenne muscular dystrophy (DMD). Quadricep skeletal muscle biopsies from 12 DMD patients and 11 unaffected control patients examined.

title: Sex specific transcription in hypothalamus
description: Examination of sex specific transcription in hypothalamus using postmortem samples from individuals averaging 70 years of age.

title: Sex specific transcription in somatic and reproductive tissues
description: Analysis of sex specific transcription in somatic and reproductive tissues. Hypothalamus, liver, kidney, ovary, and testis tissues pooled from 10 different animals examined.

title: Cystic fibrosis pancreatic gene expression
description: Analysis of pancreas from 8 week male CFTR-/- and CFTR+/+ mice. The abnormally acidic duodenum in CF increases signaling from intestine to pancreas to stimulate bicarbonate ion secretion, leading to pancreatic stress and inflammation.

title: Erythroid differentiation: G1E model
description: Analysis of erythroid differentiation using G1E ER4 clone cells. Estradiol addition induces Gata-1 triggering synchronous differentiation. 30 hour time course corresponds to late burst-forming unit-erythroid stage through orthochromatic erythroblast stage.

title: Renal function and dietary salt
description: Examination of kidney tissue from Sprague Dawley and Dahl salt sensitive (SS/Jr) rats fed 10 day diet of either 0.3% or 8.0% NaCl. Results provide insight into salt adaptation and pathogenesis of hypertension.

title: Retinoblastoma-deficient prostate epithelial cells, and effect of serum
description: Comparison of retinoblastoma-deficient (Rb-/-) and control wild type prostate epithelial cell lines maintained in RPMI-1640 medium supplemented with 5% fetal bovine serum, or without serum for 48 hours.

title: Gastric mucosa ECL cell hyperplasia and neoplasia
description: Analysis of gastric mucosa from rodent with predisposition for gastric carcinoids derived from enterochromaffin-like (ECL) cells. Animals treated with hypergastrinemia-inducing loxtidine for 8 weeks (hyperplasia) or 16 weeks (neoplasia).

title: Gastric mucosa ECL cell carcinoid
description: Analysis of enriched gastric mucosa enterochromaffin-like (ECL) cell populations obtained from rodent with predisposition for ECL cell carcinoids. Animals treated with loxtidin for 8 or 16 weeks. Spontaneous ECL cell carcinoid included in analysis.

title: Preimplantation development
description: Dynamics of global gene expression changes during preimplantation development. Unfertilized eggs, fertilized egg, 2-cell embryos, 4-cell embryos, 8-cell embryos, morulae and blastocysts examined.

title: Zygotic gene activation
description: Characterization of zygotic gene activation (ZGA)  and influence of maternal transcripts. Embryos cultured until 2-cell stage with inhibitors of transcription (α-amanitine), DNA replication (aphidicolin) and protein synthesis (cycloheximide).

title: Glomerulonephropathy
description: Gene expression profiling of anti-glomerular basement membrane (GBM) glomerulonephropathy model. Analysis of kidney tissue of BALB/c mice injected with anti-GBM antibody for 1, 3, 7, 11 or 16 days.

title: Aging and oxidative stress in fly heads
description: Analysis of effect of aging and oxidative stress in male w1118 fly heads. Aging examined using young (3 day) and adult (47 day) flies. Oxidative stress examined using sucrose-fed and 15 mM paraquat-fed flies.

title: Aging time course, normal adult
description: Examination of normal adult aging using synchronized populations at 0 - 144 hours. Employed CF512 fer-15(b26) II; fem-1 (hc17) IV mutant strain, which has defective spermatids thus eliminating contributions from embryonic transcripts.

title: Heat stress time course
description: Examination of effect of heat stress. Adult CF512 cultured at 25°C, then switched to 30°C and sampled over 12 hour time period.

title: Myogenic differentiation timecourse (MG-U74A)
description: Analysis of early stages of myogenesis. C2C12 myoblasts induced to differentiate and examined during cell proliferation (days -2 to -1), at cell cycle withdrawal (day 0) and during myogenic fusion and maturation of multinucleated myotubes (days 2 to 10).

title: Myogenic differentiation timecourse (MG-U74C)
description: Analysis of early stages of myogenesis. C2C12 myoblasts induced to differentiate and examined during cell proliferation (days -2 to -1), at cell cycle withdrawal (day 0) and during myogenic fusion and maturation of multinucleated myotubes (days 2 to 10).

title: Cystic fibrosis and small intestine
description: Analysis of small intestine from 40 day old CFTR-/- and CFTR+/+ mice. The CFTR null mouse has a severe intestinal phenotype serving as model for cystic fibrosis related growth deficiency, meconium ileus, and distal intestinal obstructive syndrome.

title: Multiple normal tissue gene expression across strains
description: Examination of normal physiological gene expression  in 11 peripheral and 15 brain regions in three common out-bred rat strains, Sprague Dawley, Wistar, and Wistar Kyoto.

title: Tetracycline transactivator expression in heart
description: Determination of effects of tetracycline transactivator (tTA) expression in cardiac ventricle of FVBN mice.

title: Large-scale analysis of the mouse transcriptome (GNF1M)
description: Gene atlas of mouse protein-encoding transcriptome. Gene expression profiles from 61 physiologically normal tissues. Samples generated from adult (10-12 week old) C57BL/6 mice (4 male, 3 female) by dissection.

title: Large-scale analysis of the human transcriptome (GNF1b)
description: Gene atlas of human protein-encoding transcriptome. Examined gene expression profiles from 79 physiologically normal tissues obtained from various sources.

title: Large-scale analysis of the human transcriptome (HG-U133A)
description: Gene atlas of human protein-encoding transcriptome. Examined gene expression profiles from 79 physiologically normal tissues obtained from various sources.

title: Cardiac hypertrophy: comparison of various induction models
description: Analysis of heart left ventricle tissue in several models of cardiac hypertrophy. Hypertrophy induced by aortic banding, myocardial infarction, an arteriovenous fistula, or hormone (angiotensin 2 or thyroxin analog) infusion.

title: Burn injury: liver metabolic and inflammatory response
description: Temporal analysis of metabolic and inflammatory response to burn injury. Livers from male Sprague-Dawleys examined at 1, 4, 8, and 24 hours following 20% total burn surface area scald-burn injury.

title: Deubiquitinating enzyme UBP10 inactivation
description: Comparison of ubp10 null mutant, sir4 null mutant, ubp10sir4 double null mutant, and the isogenic wild type strain W303-1A gives insight into mechanisms underlying deubiquitinating enzyme UBP10 function.

title: X-ray induced cell death in embryos
description: Analysis of X-ray induced cell death in stage 9-11 (irradiation sensitive) and stage 13-15 embryos (irradiation resistant) provides insight into molecular mechanisms of irradiation induced apoptosis.

title: Neurofibromatosis and neurodevelopment
description: Examination of hippocampus from 10 to 32 day old NF1 heterozygotes. NF1+/- mice develop learning and memory difficulties mimicking cognitive deficits in human neurofibromatosis.

title: Spermatogenesis and  testis development time course (MG-U74A)
description: Spermatogenesis time course generated from BL/6-129 testis collected from birth through adulthood. Provides insight into genes implicated in maturation, maintenance, and function of testis and the integrated process of spermatogenesis.

title: Spermatogenesis and testis development time course (MG-U74B)
description: Spermatogenesis time course generated from BL/6-129 testis collected from birth through adulthood. Provides insight into genes implicated in maturation, maintenance, and function of testis and the integrated process of spermatogenesis.

title: Spermatogenesis and testis development time course (MG-U74C)
description: Spermatogenesis time course generated from BL/6-129 testis collected from birth through adulthood. Provides insight into genes implicated in maturation, maintenance, and function of testis and the integrated process of spermatogenesis.

title: Filamentous-form growth on solid media
description: Temporal analysis of wild type diploid cells shifted from yeast-form growth in SHAD liquid (plentiful glucose and ammonium) to filamentous-form growth on SLAD agar (low ammonium). Filamentous-form cells collected hourly for 10 hours.

title: Duchenne muscular dystrophy (II) (HG-U95B)
description: Search for modifying factors and pathogenic pathways involved in Duchenne muscular dystrophy (DMD). Quadricep skeletal muscle biopsies from DMD patients and unaffected control patients examined.

title: Duchenne muscular dystrophy (II) (HG-U95C)
description: Search for modifying factors and pathogenic pathways involved in Duchenne muscular dystrophy (DMD). Quadricep skeletal muscle biopsies from DMD patients and unaffected control patients examined.

title: Duchenne muscular dystrophy (II) (HG-U95D)
description: Search for modifying factors and pathogenic pathways involved in Duchenne muscular dystrophy (DMD). Quadricep skeletal muscle biopsies from DMD patients and unaffected control patients examined.

title: Duchenne muscular dystrophy (II) (HG-U95E)
description: Search for modifying factors and pathogenic pathways involved in Duchenne muscular dystrophy (DMD). Quadricep skeletal muscle biopsies from DMD patients and unaffected control patients examined.

title: Dystrophin-deficient mdx extraocular muscle development time course
description: Analysis of extraocular muscle (EOM) from dystrophin-deficient mdx mice, a Duchenne muscular dystrophy (DMD) model. Postnatal ages 14, 28, 56, and 112 days examined. EOM is unaffected in DMD, so results provide insight into mdx EOM protective mechanisms.

title: Cerebral cortex regional expression
description: Analysis of medial, dorsal, lateral, rostral, and occipital regions from strain ICR embryo day 16.5 cerebral cortex provides insight into molecular mechanisms of neocortical area and layer formation.

title: Rapid alkalinization factor overexpression
description: Analysis of the effect of overexpression of polypeptide hormone rapid alkalinization factor RALF1-1 in 1 week old seedlings. RALF has role in regulating growth and development.

title: Lung injury after hemorrhage
description: Temporal analysis of response of lung tissue to hemorrhagic shock. Male Sprague-Dawleys subjected to hemorrhage and lung tissue examined at various time points up to 72 hours.

title: Extraocular and hindlimb muscle development
description: Analysis of hindlimb and extraocular muscle (EOM) between birth and postnatal day 45. Dissecting allotype-specific regulatory mechanisms may help explain differential muscle group sensitivity to a variety of metabolic and neuromuscular diseases.

title: Endothelial cell microenvironment effect  (1.2I)
description: Comparison of high endothelial venules endothelial cells (HEVEC) freshly isolated from tonsils with dedifferentiated HEVEC cultured ex vivo for 48 hours identifies gene expression controlled by tissue microenvironment.

title: Endothelial cell microenvironment effect (1.2II)
description: Comparison of high endothelial venules endothelial cells (HEVEC) freshly isolated from tonsils with dedifferentiated HEVEC cultured ex vivo for 48 hours identifies gene expression controlled by tissue microenvironment.

title: Endothelial cell microenvironment effect (cardiovascular array)
description: Comparison of high endothelial venules endothelial cells (HEVEC) freshly isolated from tonsils with dedifferentiated HEVEC cultured ex vivo for 48 hours identifies gene expression controlled by tissue microenvironment.

title: Gastric mucosa immune response to Helicobacter pylori
description: Examination of gastric mucosa inflammatory response to Helicobacter pylori infection. Gastric biopsies from healthy and H. pylori-infected patients compared. Infection can lead to cellular hyperproliferation and malignant transformation.

title: Cardiac development in embryo
description: Analysis of strain C57BL/6 embryo heart development from E (embryonic day) 10.5 to E18.5, which encompass stages of septation of atrial and ventricular chambers as well as cardiac outflow tract. Atrial and ventricular chambers analyzed separately.

title: Microphthalmia induction by ocular teratogen: dose response
description: Dose response analysis of ocular teratogen 2-chloro-2'deoxyadenosine (2CdA) exposure and induction of microphthalmia (small eye syndrome). Pregnant 8 days post coitum CD-1 dams exposed to 5, 2.5, 1.25 or 0.625 mg/kg 2CdA, and embryos examined at 3 hours.

title: Microphthalmia induction by ocular teratogen: time course
description: Temporal analysis of ocular teratogen 2-chloro-2'deoxyadenosine (2CdA) exposure and induction of microphthalmia (small eye syndrome). Pregnant 8 days post coitum CD-1 dams exposed to 2.5 mg/kg 2CdA, and embryonic headfold examined at 3, 4.5, and 6 hours.

title: Microphthalmia induction by ocular teratogen: PK11195 intervention
description: Temporal analysis of ocular teratogen 2-chloro-2'deoxyadenosine (2CdA) exposure in developing embryos, intervention with PK11195, and induction of microphthalmia (small eye syndrome). Embryonic headfold examined at 3, 4.5, and 6 hours.

title: Fetal minamata disease induction by methylmercury: dose response
description: Dose response analysis of methylmercury (MeHg) exposure in embryos. Pregnant 9 days post coitum CD-1 dams injected with 10, 5, 2.5, or 1.25 mg/kg MeHg. Embryonic forebrain examined after 3 hours. MeHg induces symptoms of fetal minamata disease (FMD).

title: Fetal minamata disease induction by methylmercury: time course
description: Temporal analysis of methylmercury (MeHg) exposure in embryos. Pregnant 9 days post coitum CD-1 dams injected with 5.0 mg/kg MeHg. Embryonic forebrain examined at 1.5 - 24 hours post-treatment. MeHg induces symptoms of fetal minamata disease (FMD).

title: Fetal minamata disease induction by methylmercury: PK11195 intervention
description: Temporal analysis of methylmercury (MeHg) exposure, and PK11195 intervention. Pregnant 9 days post coitum CD-1 dams injected with 5.0 mg/kg MeHg. Embryonic forebrain examined at 3, 4.5 and 6 hours. MeHg induces symptoms of fetal minamata disease (FMD).

title: Dystrophin-deficient mdx diaphram muscle development time course
description: Temporal analysis of diaphram muscle from dystrophin-deficient mdx mice, a Duchenne muscular dystrophy (DMD) model. Postnatal ages 7 to 112 days examined. Results provide insight into mechanisms of muscular dystrophy pathogenesis.

title: Dystrophin-deficient mdx hindlimb muscle development time course
description: Temporal analysis of hindlimb gastrocnemius/soleus muscle from dystrophin-deficient mdx mice, a Duchenne muscular dystrophy (DMD) model. Postnatal ages 7 to 112 days examined. Results provide insight into mechanisms of muscular dystrophy pathogenesis.

title: Germ-free gastrointestinal tract
description: Analysis of germ-free and conventional corpus, jejunum, descending colon and rectum. Findings identify important interaction between commensal microbiota and gastrointestinal tract transcriptome.

title: Dystrophin-deficient mdx, mdx5cv and wild type skeletal muscle profiles
description: Analysis of diaphragm, extensor digitorum longus, gastroc, soleus, quadricep, and tibialis anterior muscle in 8 week old male dystrophin-deficient mdx, mdx5cv, and C57BL10 wild type provides insight into pathogenesis of muscular dystrophy.

title: Aging of cultured myotubes and glucose metabolism
description: Examination of aging myotubes from a muscle biopsy incubated in glucose.  Myotubes in 25 mM glucose at 2, 3, 4, 5, and 7 weeks, and in 10 mM glucose at 4 weeks examined in reference to 0 mM glucose control at 1 week.

title: Insulin-like growth factor receptor overexpression in heart
description: Characterization of ventricles from transgenics with an overexpressed IGF1R, and from double transgenics with an overexpressed IGF1R and either a constitutively active phosphatidylinositol-3-kinase (PI3K) or a dominan

title: Inflammatory response of interleukin-1-stimulated endothelial cells
description: Temporal analysis of human umbilical vein endothelial cell (HUVEC) inflammatory response to interleukin-1 (IL-1) stimulation for 0, 0.5, 1, 2.5, and 6 hours. Immediate-early to early gene expression program characterized.

title: Heart  failure arising from different etiologies
description: Examination of left ventricle in idiopathic dilated and ischemic cardiomyopathy.  Diseased ventricles examined in reference to normal.

title: Wax inducer 1 transcription factor overexpression
description: Analysis of leaves strongly and moderately overexpressing wax inducer 1 (WIN1), an ethylene response factor-like transcription factor. WIN1 activates several wax biosynthesis pathway genes leading to epidermal wax accumulation.

title: Neurotransmitter-specific neuronal gene expression
description: Examination of neurotransmitter-specific gene expression using FACS-isolated cholinergic neurons or neurons expressing glutamic acid decarboxylase 1 (Gad1). Neurons dissociated from nervous system or generated by culturing neural progenitor cells.

title: Cardiac hypertrophy induced by exercise
description: Analysis of heart left ventricles from animals subjected to 7 weeks treadmill exercise compared with sedentary controls. Provides insight into molecular mechanisms of left ventricular hypertrophy.

title: Retina injury response time course
description: Examination of injured retinas from male Sprague-Dawleys. Retinas scraped and examined at 4 hours, 1, 3, 7, and 30 days post-injury. Results help characterize distinct phases of retinal injury response.

title: Ligament healing and effect of hindlimb unloading
description: Examination of effect of hindlimb unloading on healing of medial collateral ligaments 3 weeks after injury. Hindlimb unloading alters gene expression patterns in wound healing ligaments leading to delayed healing response.

title: Thymocyte selection by agonist
description: Analysis of CD8 alpha beta cells in reaggregation thymic organ culture (RTOC) selected by natural ligands, CD8 alpha beta RTOC cells selected by low-dose agonist (100 nM Smcy), and CD8 alpha alpha RTOC cells selected by high-dose agonist (10 mM Smcy).

title: Spinal cord development
description: Comparison of L4-L6 spinal cord sections of 2 and 12 day old animals.  Results provide insight into development of motoneurons and their synaptic inputs.

title: Testis developmental time course: embryonic (MG-U74A)
description: Time course of gene expression in BL/6-129 embryonic testis from the time of the indifferent gonad (11.5 days post coitum) to birth (18.5 days post coitum).

title: Testis developmental time course: embryonic (MG-U74B)
description: Time course of gene expression in BL/6-129 embryonic testis from the time of the indifferent gonad (11.5 days post coitum) to birth (18.5 days post coitum).

title: Testis developmental time course: embryonic (MG-U74C)
description: Time course of gene expression in BL/6-129 embryonic testis from the time of the indifferent gonad (11.5 days post coitum) to birth (18.5 days post coitum).

title: Ovary developmental time course: embryonic (MG-U74A)
description: Time course of gene expression in BL/6-129 embryonic ovary from the time of the indifferent gonad (11.5 days post coitum) to birth (18.5 days post coitum).

title: mRNA splicing factor mutant at permissive and restrictive temperatures
description: Analysis of mutant defective in dU2AF50 (large subunit of pre-mRNA splicing factor U2AF).  Mutant examined after growth at permissive (25°C) and restrictive (30°C) temperatures in reference to wild type.

title: Ovary developmental time course: embryonic (MG-U74B)
description: Time course of gene expression in BL/6-129 embryonic ovary from the time of the indifferent gonad (11.5 days post coitum) to birth (18.5 days post coitum).

title: Ovary developmental time course: embryonic (MG-U74C)
description: Time course of gene expression in BL/6-129 embryonic ovary from the time of the indifferent gonad (11.5 days post coitum) to birth (18.5 days post coitum).

title: mRNA splicing factor knock-down and nucleo-cytoplasmic mRNA distribution
description: Examination of cytoplasmic and nuclear mRNA distribution in D.mel2 cell line after RNAi knock-down of dU2AF50 (large subunit of pre-mRNA splicing factor U2AF).  dU2AF50 knock-down analyzed in reference to non-specific RNAi knock-down.

title: Indole acetic acid treatment time course (ATH1)
description: Analysis of 10-12 day Columbia-O seedlings treated with 0.1 uM indole acetic acid (IAA) auxin for 1 and 3 hours.  Treated seedlings analyzed in reference to untreated control. Part of a study comparing AG and ATH1 arrays.

title: Emphysema lung tissue expression profiling
description: Expression profiling of lung tissue from normal individuals, and patients with either 'usual' emphysema or alpha-1 antitrypsin (AAT) deficiency-related emphysema. Global reduction in gene expression observed in emphysemic lungs.

title: Indole acetic acid treatment time course (AG)
description: Analysis of 10-12 day Columbia-O seedlings treated with 0.1 uM indole acetic acid (IAA) auxin for 1 and 3 hours. Treated seedlings analyzed in reference to untreated control. Part of a study comparing AG and ATH1 arrays.

title: Indole acetic acid treatment: dose response and  time course
description: Analysis of 10-12 day Columbia-O seedlings treated with either 0.1 uM or 1.0 uM indole acetic acid (IAA) auxin for 1 and 3 hours.  Treated seedlings analyzed in reference to untreated control.  Part of a study assessing the performance of the ATH1 array.

title: 4-nonylphenol effect on liver
description: Analysis of FVB/NJ liver treated with 45 mg/kg/day 4-nonylphenol (4-NP) for 32 weeks. 4-NP is an industrial waste and elicits estrogen-like responses.  Results provide insight into molecular events altered by 4-NP.

title: Osteogenesis induced by bone morphogenic protein 2
description: Response of calvarial MC3T3-1b cells to osteogenic stimulus (beta-glycerophosphate (GP), ascorbic acid (AA) and bone morphogenic protein 2 (BMP-2)) for 0, 1 and 3 days. Notch, Wnt and TGF-β signaling pathways are activated in osteogenesis.

title: Oxygen deprivation expression profiling of various mutants
description: Examination of K-12 MG1655 deletion strains grown in either aerobic or anaerobic conditions.  Strains deleted for transcriptional regulators in oxygen response.  Results used to validate a computational model of transcriptional and metabolic networks.

title: Down syndrome and brain (MG-U74A)
description: Analyses of six Ts1Cje (Down syndrome) and six normal brains at postnatal day 0. Dosage-dependent over-expression of genes in trisomic region of Ts1Cje observed.

title: Down syndrome and brain (MG-U74B)
description: Analyses of six Ts1Cje (Down syndrome) and six normal brains at postnatal day 0. Dosage-dependent over-expression of genes in trisomic region of Ts1Cje observed.

title: Oxidative stress and Snell dwarf liver
description: Time course of long-lived Snell dwarf (Pit1 mutation) and wild type response to oxidative stress induced by 3-nitropropionic acid (3-NPA). Livers examined at several time points up to 42 hours.

title: T regulatory and T effector cells in prediabetic lesion
description: Comparison of T regulatory (CD4+CD25+CD69-) and T effector (CD4+CD25lo/-CD69+/-) cells isolated from the pancreatic lesion of 3-4 week old BDC2.5 transgenic NOD mice before type 1 diabetes onset.

title: YODA MAPKK inactivation and constitutive activation effect on stomata
description: Examination of gene expression in 7 days post-germination seedlings with either an inactive or a constitutively active YODA MAPKK.  Inactivating YODA results in excess stomata, and constitutively activating YODA eliminates stomata.

title: Store-operated calcium entry in HEK-293 cells
description: Comparison of HEK-293-derived monoclonal cell lines with high or low levels of store-operated Ca2+ entry (SOCE). Levels of SOCE confirmed by monitoring thapsigargin-stimulated Ba2+ entry.

title: Dermal papilla-induced epithelial stem cell differentiation
description: Analysis of dermal papilla (DP) induced epithelial stem cell differentiation. Keratinocyte stem cells from bulge area of telogen hair follicle co-cultured with DP over a 5 day period.

title: Intestinal epithelial cell immune response
description: Analysis of intestinal epithelial cell immune response. 14 day old colon adenocarcinoma cell lines Caco-2 and T84 stimulated 4 hours with flagellin, or lymphotoxin beta or TNF alpha cytokines.

title: AtMYB23 MYB transcription factor target down-regulation
description: Examination of rosette leaves from 2 week old Columbia-0 transgenic seedlings expressing AtMYB23SRDX, a chimeric AtMYB23 MYB transcription factor with an SRDX repression domain. Seedlings expressing AtMYB23SRDX are defective in trichome development.

title: Cardiac and aortic endothelial cells
description: Gene expression profiles of endocardial (EE) and aortic (AE) endothelial cells. EE and AE genetic diversity in culture reflects in vivo physiological diversity.

title: Cardiac myocyte hypertrophy induced by fibronectin
description: Examination of neonatal ventricular myocytes plated on fibronectin coated dishes. Fibronectin elicits a hypertrophic response by clustering integrin receptors.  Results provide insight into molecular events underlying cardiac hypertrophy.

title: Spermatogonial stem cell activity time course under various culture conditions (RAE230A)
description: Temporal analysis of stem cell activity examined in laminin binding testis germ cells cultured on either STO fibroblasts for 0 to 20 days or MSC-1 Sertoli cells for 20 days.  Results provide insight into maintenance of stem cell activity.

title: Spermatogonial stem cell activity time course under various culture conditions (RAE230B)
description: Temporal analysis of stem cell activity examined in laminin binding testis germ cells cultured on either STO fibroblasts for 0 to 20 days or MSC-1 Sertoli cells for 20 days.  Results provide insight into maintenance of stem cell activity.

title: Spermatogonial stem cell activity in testis laminin binding germ cells (MG-U74A)
description: Comparison of cultured laminin binding to non-binding germ cells from testes of 19-day-old neonates.  Laminin binding germ cells are enriched in spermatogonial stem cells.  Results provide insight into molecular events underlying stem cell activity.

title: Spermatogonial stem cell activity in testis laminin binding germ cells (MG-U74B)
description: Comparison of cultured laminin binding to non-binding germ cells from testes of 19 day old neonates.  Laminin binding germ cells are enriched in spermatogonial stem cells.  Results provide insight into molecular events underlying stem cell activity.

title: Extraocular, limb, and masticatory muscle comparison
description: Comparison of extraocular (EOM), masticatory (masseter), and hindlimb (gastrocnemius/soleus) muscle in 8 week old mice. EOM defined by distinct gene expression profile.

title: Dystrophin-deficient mdx extraocular and leg muscle
description: Analysis of extraocular (EOM) and hindlimb (gastrocnemius/soleus) muscle in mdx (dystrophin-deficient; Duchenne muscular dystrophy model) mice at postnatal day 56.5. Highly specific changes observed between dystrophic (leg) and spared (EOM) muscle.

title: Spermatogonial stem cell activity in testis laminin binding germ cells (MG-U74C )
description: Comparison of cultured laminin binding to non-binding germ cells from testes of 19 day old neonates.  Laminin binding germ cells are enriched in spermatogonial stem cells.  Results provide insight into molecular events underlying stem cell activity.

title: RENT1 nonsense-mediated mRNA decay component knockdown
description: Analysis of mRNA abundance changes in Hela cells following knockdown of nonsense-mediated mRNA decay component RENT1 using RNAi.   Results identify transcripts potentially regulated by RENT1.

title: Aging brain: frontal cortex expression profiles at various ages
description: Analysis of gene expression profiles obtained from the postmortem frontal cortex of 18 normal males and 12 normal females at 26 to 106 years of age.  Results provide insight into molecular events underlying the onset of brain aging.

title: HIV integration sites and gene transcription activity
description: Correlation of HIV integration sites to gene activity in SupT1 (T cell), PBMC (peripheral blood mononuclear cell), and IMR90 (lung fibroblast) cell lines infected with an HIV-based vector.  Results provide insight into sites preferred in HIV integration.

title: Enterocyte differentiation time course
description: Enterocyte differentiation analyzed using colonic adenocarcinoma cell line Caco-2 BBe as a model.  Cells examined at 2, 8, and 15 days in culture: these are in the proliferating, postproliferative nondifferentiated, and differentiated stages respectively.

title: Hippocampus ischemic tolerance time course
description: Comparison of temporal expression patterns in hippocampi of hypoxia tolerant and sensitive animals.  Microdissected hippocampus CA1 regions analyzed 0, 1, 3, 12, 24, and 48 hours after ischemia operation.  Results offer insight into cell death in hypoxia.

title: Juvenile rheumatoid arthritis expression profiles in mononuclear cells
description: Examination of peripheral blood and synovial fluid mononuclear cells in pauciarticular and polyarticular rheumatoid arthritis, and in juvenile spondyloarthropathy.  Results identify disease subtypes and provide insight into disease mechanisms.

title: Huntingtons disease and combination drug therapy
description: Whole brain hemispheres from Huntingtons disease model R6/2 transgenic mice treated with creatine, tacrine and moclobemide from 5 weeks of age. Drug therapy was aimed at boosting neurotransmitter levels and improve cognitive functions.

title: Phototrophic anoxygenic proteobacterium response to blue light under semi-aerobic conditions
description: The phototrophic anoxygenic proteobacterium Rhodobacter sphaeroides 2.4.1 grown under 10% O2 semi-aerobic conditions in the dark, then illuminated with blue light for 5, 45 or 135 minutes before harvesting.

title: Prostate adenocarcinoma response to radiation (HG-U95A)
description: Time course of androgen-independent LNCaP C4-2 prostate adenocarcinoma cells following ionizing radiation (IR) to a dose of 10 Sv. Cells harvested 6 or 24 hours after IR. Dose applied in 1 or 4 fractions.

title: Prostate adenocarcinoma response to radiation (HG-U95B)
description: Time course of androgen-independent LNCaP C4-2 prostate adenocarcinoma cells following ionizing radiation (IR) to a dose of 10 Sv. Cells harvested 6 or 24 hours after IR. Dose applied in 1 or 4 fractions.

title: Prostate adenocarcinoma response to radiation (HG-U95C)
description: Time course of androgen-independent LNCaP C4-2 prostate adenocarcinoma cells following ionizing radiation (IR) to a dose of 10 Sv. Cells harvested 6 or 24 hours after IR. Dose applied in 1 or 4 fractions.

title: Prostate adenocarcinoma response to radiation (HG-U95D)
description: Time course of androgen-independent LNCaP C4-2 prostate adenocarcinoma cells following ionizing radiation (IR) to a dose of 10 Sv. Cells harvested 6 or 24 hours after IR. Dose applied in 1 or 4 fractions.

title: Prostate adenocarcinoma response to radiation (HG-U95E)
description: Time course of androgen-independent LNCaP C4-2 prostate adenocarcinoma cells following ionizing radiation (IR) to a dose of 10 Sv. Cells harvested 6 or 24 hours after IR. Dose applied in 1 or 4 fractions.

title: Kidney transplant rejection expression profiling
description: Analysis of kidney transplant rejection by expression profiling of kidney biopsies and peripheral blood lymphocytes from patients. Results identify expression profiles unique to rejection, dysfunction without rejection, and well-functioning transplants.

title: Prostate adenocarcinoma and ionizing radiation
description: Time course of androgen-independent LNCaP C4-2 prostate adenocarcinoma cells following a dose of 10 Sv ionizing radiation (IR). Cells harvested at several time points up to 24 hours after IR.

title: Renin-angiotensin system inhibition effect on cerebral capillaries
description: Examination of cerebral capillaries in stroke-prone spontaneously hypertensives (SHRSP) treated with either an angiotensin II receptor (AT1R) antagonist or an angiotensin converting enzyme (ACE) inhibitor. Renin-angiotensin system inhibition reduces stroke in SHRSP.

title: CD8 T cell development (Mu11K-A)
description: Expression profiling of naïve and memory CD8 T cells from female RAG1-deficient transgenics expressing B6.2.16 T cell receptors specific for the human Y antigen.  Genes protecting against programmed cell death upregulated in memory CD8 T cells.

title: Leukotriene LTD4 effect on macrophage and endothelial cells
description: Examination of gene expression in MonoMac6 macrophage and umbilical vein endothelial cells treated with 100 nM leukotriene LTD4 for 1 hour.  Results offer insight into autocrine action of LTD4 on macrophages and its paracrine action on endothelial cells.

title: Malpighian tubule expression profiling
description: Expression profiling of 7 day adult Oregon R Malpighian tubules in reference to whole organisms.  Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying renal function.

title: Thiazolidinedione treatment of 3T3-L1 adipocytes
description: Expression profiling of 3T3-L1 adipocytes treated with the thiazolidinediones (TZD) pioglitazone, rosiglitazone, and troglitazone, at 20 uM, 1 uM, and 20 uM respectively.  TZDs increase sensitivity of cells to insulin in patients with type II diabetes.

title: High fat diet effect on aorta: time course
description: Comparison of gene expression in aortas of C57BL/6 and C3H/HeJ fed identical high fat diets at 0, 4, 8, 24, and 40 weeks.  C57BL/6 has a greater tendency than C3H/HeJ to develop atherosclerotic aortic lesions when both fed identical high fat diets.

title: Lung tissue from smokers with severe emphysema
description: Comparison of lung tissue from smokers with severe emphysema (removed at lung volume reduction surgery) and  smokers with mild or no emphysema. Study provides insights into the pathogenesis of chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD).

title: Intervertebral disc cells and osmotic loading
description: Gene expression profiles of intervertebral disc cells (IVD) exposed to iso-osmotic, hyper-osmotic and hypo-osmotic conditions. Under physiological conditions, IVD are subject to osmotic stress.

title: Orofacial development in embryo
description: Developmental gene expression profiling of fetal orofacial tissue from gestation day (GD) 12-14 embryos.

title: Chromosomally stable and unstable isogenic clone comparison
description: Expression profiling of 2 pools of chromosomally unstable Chinese hamster-human hybrid GM10115 clones referenced to an isogenic stable clone RT210B.  Clone Fe10-3 pooled with 10-56-11, and LS12 with 10-107-9. Chromosome instability induced by radiation.

title: Compensated and decompensated hypertrophies induced by monocrotaline
description: Analysis of compensated and decompensated hypertrophies induced by monocrotaline in Wistar.   Left and right heart ventricles examined 14 days after monocrotaline injection.  Decompensated hypertrophy is a prelude to chronic heart failure.

title: Brassinosteroid effects on wild type and yucca mutant seedlings
description: Analysis of brassinolide treatment on 10 day old light-grown Columbia-O wild type and yucca mutant seedlings. Yucca mutants overproduce auxin. Brassinosteroids (BRs) promote cell expansion.

title: Auxin effects on seedlings
description: Analysis of effects of indole-3-acetic acid (IAA, auxin) treatment on 5 day old light-grown Columbia-0 seedlings. Auxins promote cell expansion.

title: Beta-catenin S37A mutant effect on gene expression
description: Expression profiling of 293T cells infected with RCAS vector carrying beta-catenin S37A mutant.  Beta-catenin S37A mutant is oncogenic and more stable than the corresponding wild type protein.

title: HAC1 transcription and unfolded protein response
description: Strains expressing HAC1 under various promoters were grown at 30°C, or shifted from 23°C to 37°C, and treated with 6mM DTT or tunicamycin for 60 minutes. DTT and tunicamycin activate the unfolded protein response (UPR) which is regulated by Hac1p.

title: Natural killer cell expression profiling
description: Expression profiling of CD56dimCD16+, CD56brightCD16-, and in vitro activated CD56+CD16+ natural killer (NK) cells.  NK cells derived from purified peripheral blood  pooled from 9 healthy donors.

title: Blastocyst dormancy and activation comparison
description: Comparison of gene expression in dormant and active blastocysts. Dormancy induced by ovariectomy and maintained by progesterone injections. Dormant blastocysts activated by estradiol-17 beta injections.  Results provide insight into delayed implantation.

title: CD8 T cell development (Mu11K-B)
description: Expression profiling of naïve and memory CD8 T cells from female RAG1-deficient transgenics expressing B6.2.16 T cell receptors specific for the human Y antigen. Genes protecting against programmed cell death upregulated in memory CD8 T cells.

title: Colon cancer progression
description: Comparison of gene expression in SW480, a primary tumor colon cancer cell line, to that in SW620, an isogenic metastatic colon cancer cell line.  Cell lines derived from one individual.  Results provide insight the progression of cancer from primary tumor growth to metastasis.

title: Pre-mRNA splicing factor mutants at restrictive temperature: time course
description: Analysis of gene expression in temperature sensitive pre-mRNA splicing factor mutants prp17 null, prp17-1, and prp22-1 at various time points following a shift from the permissive temperature of 23°C to the restrictive temperature of 37°C.  Results identify substrates of Prp17p and Prp22p.

title: Essential thrombocythemia expression profiling
description: Expression profiling of malignant megakaryocytes (MK) from 6 donors with essential thrombocythemia (ET).  MK derived from bone marrow CD34+ hematopoietic progenitor cells.  Progenitors induced to differentiate into MK by treatment with 100 ng/ml thrombopoietin.  Apoptotic pathway is impaired in ET.

title: Fatty liver disease induced by orotic acid: time course
description: Expression profiling of livers from inbred Kyotos and outbred Wistars fed a diet with 1% orotic acid to induce fatty liver disease.  Profiles examined at various time points up to 14 days. Results used together with NMR spectroscopic analysis of the liver to identify perturbed metabolic pathways.

title: Osteoclastogenesis regulation by c-Fos and Nfat
description: Analysis of the role of c-Fos and Nfat in osteoclastogenesis by expression profiling of osteoclastogenic splenocytes lacking c-Fos but with an active Nfatc4.  Active Nfatc4 introduced into cells by retroviral gene transfer.  Osteoclastogenesis restored by active Nfatc4 in splenocytes lacking c-Fos.

title: RNA-dependent serine/threonine protein kinase PKR overexpression (Mu11K-A)
description: Analysis of gene expression in NIH3T3 overexpressing RNA-dependent serine/threonine protein kinase (PKR) controlled by a tetracycline repressible promoter.  PKR repressed in 1 ug/ml tetracycline and overexpressed upon tetracycline removal.  PKR promotes cell survival before inducing cell death.

title: RNA-dependent serine/threonine protein kinase PKR overexpression (Mu11K-B)
description: Analysis of gene expression in NIH3T3 overexpressing RNA-dependent serine/threonine protein kinase (PKR) controlled by a tetracycline repressible promoter.  PKR repressed in 1 ug/ml tetracycline and overexpressed upon tetracycline removal.  PKR promotes cell survival before inducing cell death.

title: Glioma cell migration: comparison of fast and slow invading cells
description: Analysis of glioma migration by comparing expression profiles of fast and slow invading C6 glial cells. Fast and slow cells separated using monolayer migration assay and by extent of migration of transplants in nude mice brains. Results provide insight into mechanisms underlying glioma invasion.

title: Long-lived daf-2 insulin/IGF-1 receptor mutant expression profiling
description: Analysis of gene expression in long-lived daf-2 mutants for the insulin/IGF-1 receptor.  daf-2(e1370) and daf-2(m577) alleles each examined as single and as double mutations with the daf-16(df50) allele.  DAF-2 regulates DAF-16, a transcription factor.  Results provide insight into longevity.

title: Hematopoietic stem cell proliferation after 5-fluorouracil treatment: time course
description: Expression profiling of bone marrow Sca+ SP hematopoeitic stem cells (HSC) and fetal liver HSCs of C57BL/6.  Bone marrow HSCs examined at various time points up to 30 days after treating mice with 150 mg/kg 5-fluorouracil. Results identify signatures for quiescent and proliferating HSCs.

title: Histone deacetylase RPD3 deletion and histone mutations effect on gene regulation
description: Analysis of gene regulation by expression profiling of single mutants for histone deacetylase RPD3, histones H3 and H4, and double mutants for either RPD3 and H3 or RPD3 and H4.  Histone mutants defective in amino terminal tails, which are acetylated and deacetylated in transcription regulation.

title: Retinoic acid teratogenic effect on cranial neural crest: time course
description: Expression profiling of cranial neural crest exposed to 1 uM retinoic acid (RA) at various lengths of time up to 48 hours.  Neural crest obtained from 8.5 days postcoitum ICR embryos.  Results provide insight into developmental pathways affected upon exposure to teratogenic concentrations of RA.

title: Typical and atypical antipsychotic drugs effect on brain
description: Examination of brains from 13 week ddY males treated for 28 days with an antipsychotic: either the typical drugs chlorpromazine and thioridazine (25 mg/kg each) or the atypical drugs olanzapine (1.25 mg/kg) and quetiapine (18.75 mg/kg). Results provide insight into schizophrenia negative symptoms.

title: Interferon-alpha effect on monocytes primed with interferon-gamma
description: Expression profiling of monocytes cultured for 2 days with 150 pg/ml interferon (IFN) gamma and then stimulated with 25 ng/ml of IFN-alpha.  Monocytes obtained from 3 donors.  Results provide insight into mechanisms underlying the enhanced response of IFN primed monocytes to cytokines.

title: Nutrient limitation under aerobic and anaerobic conditions effect on gene expression
description: Expression profiling of MATa CEN.PK113-7D chemostat cultures grown either aerobically or anaerobically in media limited for either glucose, nitrogen, phosphorous, or sulfur.  Results provide insight into the interaction between oxygen and nutrient responsive pathways.

title: Aerobic running capacity: expression profiling of heart ventricles from various strains (RG-U34A)
description: Expression profiling of heart left ventricles from 15 week old inbred COP, DA, and COP x DA F1 offspring (low, high, and intermediate performers respectively). Results provide insight into mechanisms underlying aerobic capacity.

title: Aerobic running capacity: expression profiling of heart ventricles from various strains (RG-U34B)
description: Expression profiling of heart left ventricles from 15 week old inbred COP, DA, and COP x DA F1 offspring (low, high, and intermediate performers respectively). Results provide insight into mechanisms underlying aerobic capacity.

title: Aerobic running capacity: expression profiling of heart ventricles from various strains (RG-U34C)
description: Expression profiling of heart left ventricles from 15 week old inbred COP, DA, and COP x DA F1 offspring (low, high, and intermediate performers respectively). Results provide insight into mechanisms underlying aerobic capacity.

title: CD14 cells from granulocyte colony stimulating factor mobilized peripheral blood: expression profile
description: Expression profiling of CD14+ cells isolated from granulocyte colony stimulating factor (G-CSF) mobilized peripheral blood mononuclear cells (G-PBMC). Cells collected from normal donors after 3 days of G-CSF stimulation. G-PBMCs may confer a survival advantage to allogeneic transplant recipients.

title: Lung apical membrane protein T1alpha null mutant effect on pulmonary development
description: Expression profiling of lungs from apical membrane protein T1alpha null mutants at 18.5 days post coitum and at birth.  Lung alveolar epithelial type I cell differentiation is blocked in T1alpha null mutants.  Results provide insight into mechanisms controlling alveolar type I cell differentiation.

title: CD4+ T cell differentiation (HG-133A)
description: Analysis of CD4+ T cell differentiation by expression profiling of subpopulations of CD4+ cells representing 5 successive stages of differentiation: intrathymic T progenitors, double positive thymocytes, single positive thymocytes, naïve T cells from cord blood, and naïve T cells from adult blood.

title: CD4+ T cell differentiation (HG-133B)
description: Analysis of CD4+ T cell differentiation by expression profiling of subpopulations of CD4+ cells representing 5 successive stages of differentiation: intrathymic T progenitors, double positive thymocytes, single positive thymocytes, naïve T cells from cord blood, and naïve T cells from adult blood.

title: Presenilin 1 and 2 conditional double knockout effect on brain cerebral cortex
description: Expression profiling of brain cerebral cortex from presenilin (PS) 1 and 2 conditional double knockout (cDKO) mutant at 6 months of age.  PS inactivation is restricted to the forebrain. PS1 and PS2 mutations cause familial Alzheimer's disease. Inflammatory markers upregulated in PS cDKO.

title: Interferon signaling in PIAS1 null mutants: time course
description: Expression profiling of bone marrow derived macrophages of PIAS1 null mutants treated with 500 U/ml interferon (IFN)-beta or 10 ng/ml IFN-gamma for 2 and 4 hours.  IFN activates the STAT pathway, which is negatively regulated by PIAS1.  Antiviral activity of IFN is enhanced in PIAS1 nulls.

title: Keratinocyte differentiation promoted by Notch1 signaling
description: Comparison of gene expression in keratinocytes from embryos at 15.5 days of gestation to that from 2 day newborns infected with an adenovirus expressing a constitutively activate Notch1. Results indicate that Notch1 promotes differentiation in part through caspase 3.

title: Estrogen receptor beta knockout effect on skeletal muscle
description: Comparison of expression profiles of soleus muscles from 5 to 6 month old C57BL/6 males to those of estrogen receptor beta (ERbeta) knockout male littermates. Male ERbeta knockout muscles are more resistant to fatigue than male wild type muscles.

title: Cardiac hypertrophy progression: time course
description: Expression profiling of hearts from FVB males subjected to cardiac pressure overload by transverse aortic constriction (TAC). TAC performed on 3 month old males.  Hearts examined 2, 10, and 21 days after surgery.  Results provide insight into the progression of cardiac hypertrophy.

title: Smooth muscle cell differentiation induced by retinoic acid: time course
description: Expression profiling of A404 cells at 48 and 96 hours following 1 umol/L all trans-retinoic acid (RA) treatment to induce differentiation into smooth muscle cells (SMCs).  A set of cells treated with RA for 96 hours was subsequently treated with 0.5 ug/ml puromycin to enrich for SMCs.

title: Estrogen positive breast cancer recurrence during tamoxifen therapy: whole tissue tumor
description: Expression profiling of estrogen positive primary breast cancer tumors from 60 patients.  Patients subsequently treated with tamoxifen for 5 years, and tumors classified according to whether cancer recurred.  Results identify gene markers of disease-free survival that include HOXB13 and IL17BR.

title: Estrogen positive breast cancer recurrence during tamoxifen therapy: microdissected tumor
description: Expression profiling of microdissected estrogen positive primary breast cancer tumors from 60 patients.  Patients later treated with tamoxifen for 5 years, and tumors grouped according to whether cancer recurred.  Results identify markers of disease-free survival that include HOXB13 and IL17BR.

title: Heart ischemia protection: comparison of pharmacologic and ischemic preconditioning
description: Comparison of Wistar heart left ventricles preconditioned against ischemia by pharmacologic treatment with isoflurane to those preconditioned by exposure to sublethal ischemia.   Expression profiles examined in preconditioned hearts either perfused alone or subjected to ischemia and then reperfused.

title: Alpha-secretase cleaved amyloid precursor protein effect on hippocampus
description: Expression profiling of hippocampal slice cultures treated with 1 nM  alpha-secretase cleaved amyloid precursor protein (sAPPalpha) for 24 hours.  Hippocampi obtained from 15 day postnatal C57B6/SJL males.  Results provide insight into the neuroprotective activity of sAPPalpha.

title: Alzheimer's disease at various stages of severity
description: Expression profiling of brain hippocampi from 22 postmortem subjects with Alzheimer's disease (AD) at various stages of severity.  7, 8, and 7 subjects diagnosed with incipient, moderate, and severe AD respectively.  Results provide insight into mechanisms underlying the early pathogenesis of AD.

title: Amyloid precursor protein mutant overexpression in strain resistant to neuronal cell loss
description: Expression profiling of brain left hippocampi from 12 month old Tg2576 transgenics overexpressing the amyloid precursor protein with the Swedish mutation (APPSw).  APPSw linked to the early-onset Alzheimer's disease.  Tg2576 express neuroprotective genes that prevent neuronal cell loss.

title: Preimplantation embryo development (MG-U74A)
description: Expression profiling of CF-1 x B6D2F1/J preimplantation embryos.  Oocytes and embryos at the 1-cell, 2-cell, 8-cell, and blastocyst stages examined. Results provide insight into mechanisms underlying the major transitions in preimplantation development.

title: Preimplantation embryo development (MOE430A)
description: Expression profiling of CF-1 x B6D2F1/J preimplantation embryos.  Oocytes and embryos at the 1-cell, 2-cell, 8-cell, and blastocyst stages examined.  Results provide insight into mechanisms underlying the major transitions in preimplantation development.

title: Preimplantation embryo development (MOE430B)
description: Expression profiling of CF-1 x B6D2F1/J preimplantation embryos.  Oocytes and embryos at the 1-cell, 2-cell, 8-cell, and blastocyst stages examined.  Results provide insight into mechanisms underlying the major transitions in preimplantation development.

title: Breast cancer cell expression profiles (HG-U95A)
description: Expression profiling of breast cancer cell lines HCC 1954 and MDA-MB-436 in reference to mammary epithelial cells.  Results used to validate a method of comparing data generated from Affymetrix arrays to that from cDNA arrays.  The method uses DNA sequence to match probes between platforms.

title: Breast cancer cell expression profiles (HG-U133A)
description: Expression profiling of breast cancer cell lines HCC 1954 and MDA-MB-436 in reference to mammary epithelial cells. Results used to validate a method of comparing data generated from Affymetrix arrays to that from cDNA arrays. The method uses DNA sequence to match probes between platforms.

title: Breast cancer cell expression profiles (HG-U133B)
description: Expression profiling of breast cancer cell lines HCC 1954 and MDA-MB-436 in reference to mammary epithelial cells. Results used to validate a method of comparing data generated from Affymetrix arrays to that from cDNA arrays. The method uses DNA sequence to match probes between platforms.

title: Breast cancer cell expression profiles (G4100A)
description: Expression profiling of breast cancer cell lines HCC 1954 and MDA-MB-436 in reference to mammary epithelial cells.  Results used to validate a method of comparing data generated from cDNA arrays to that from Affymetrix arrays.  The method uses DNA sequence to match probes between platforms.

title: Erythroid differentiation of erythroleukemia cell line induced by hemin: time course
description: Expression profiling of K562 erythroleukemia cells induced to differentiate into erythroid-like cells by hemin.  K562 cells examined at various time points up to 72 hours following treatment with 50 uM hemin.  Results provide insight into mechanisms underlying hemoglobinization.

title: Acute ethanol administration effect on Toll-like receptor 3 signaling in macrophages
description: Analysis of peritoneal macrophages from 8 to12 week-old C57BL/6xC3H females treated with 100 ug poly(I:C) and 6 g/kg ethanol.  Poly(I:C) mimics viral dsRNA by binding Toll-like receptor 3.  Results provide insight into the suppression of innate immunity by ethanol.

title: Insulitis: comparison of innocuous and destructive forms
description: Analysis of CD4+ automimmune T and CD45+ hematopoeitic cells from non-obese diabetic (NOD) and C57BL/6-H-2 g7 transgenics with the BDC2.5 T cell receptor (TCR) from a diabetogenic T cell.  BDC2.5 TCR in NOD and in C57BL/6-H-2 g7 results in innocuous and destructive insulitis respectively.

title: Alternative pre-mRNA splicing in various tissues and cell lines (Rosetta/Merck Splicing Chip 1)
description: Monitoring of mRNA splice variants for more than 10,000 multi-exon genes using arrays with oligonucleotide probes positioned at exon-exon junctions.  mRNA from 52 tissues and cell lines examined.  Results provide tissue distribution of splice variants and identify novel splice variants.

title: Alternative pre-mRNA splicing in various tissues and cell lines (Rosetta/Merck Splicing Chip 2)
description: Monitoring of mRNA splice variants for more than 10,000 multi-exon genes using arrays with oligonucleotide probes positioned at exon-exon junctions. mRNA from 52 tissues and cell lines examined. Results provide tissue distribution of splice variants and identify novel splice variants.

title: Alternative pre-mRNA splicing in various tissues and cell lines (Rosetta/Merck Splicing Chip 3)
description: Monitoring of mRNA splice variants for more than 10,000 multi-exon genes using arrays with oligonucleotide probes positioned at exon-exon junctions. mRNA from 52 tissues and cell lines examined. Results provide tissue distribution of splice variants and identify novel splice variants.

title: Alternative pre-mRNA splicing in various tissues and cell lines (Rosetta/Merck Splicing Chip 4)
description: Monitoring of mRNA splice variants for more than 10,000 multi-exon genes using arrays with oligonucleotide probes positioned at exon-exon junctions. mRNA from 52 tissues and cell lines examined. Results provide tissue distribution of splice variants and identify novel splice variants.

title: Alternative pre-mRNA splicing in various tissues and cell lines (Rosetta/Merck Splicing Chip 5)
description: Monitoring of mRNA splice variants for more than 10,000 multi-exon genes using arrays with oligonucleotide probes positioned at exon-exon junctions. mRNA from 52 tissues and cell lines examined. Results provide tissue distribution of splice variants and identify novel splice variants.

title: Sindbis virus-induced cell death
description: Comparison of 293 cells that are resistant to Sindbis virus-induced cell death (clones 9, 43) versus cells that are sensitive to Sindbis virus-induced cell death (wild type 293).

title: Spermatogonia in Zfp145 knockout (MG-U74A)
description: Expression analysis of spermatogonia, mitotic germ cells of the testis, in 1 week old wild type or Zfp145 (Plzf) knockout. PLZF plays role in maintenance of spermatogonial stem cells.

title: Spermatogonia in Zfp145 knockout (MG-U74B)
description: Expression analysis of spermatogonia, mitotic germ cells of the testis, in 1 week old wild type or Zfp145 (Plzf) knockout. PLZF plays role in maintenance of spermatogonial stem cells.

title: Spermatogonia in Zfp145 knockout (MG-U74C)
description: Expression analysis of spermatogonia, mitotic germ cells of the testis, in 1 week old wild type or Zfp145 (Plzf) knockout. PLZF plays role in maintenance of spermatogonial stem cells.

title: Imatinib effects on chronic myelogenous leukemia CD34+ cells
description: Comparison of purified bone marrow CD34+ cells from imatinib-treated chronic myelogenous leukemia (CML) patients and healthy donors.

title: Hair follicle stem cell characterization
description: Analysis of hair follicle stem cells (FACS-isolated Keratin1-15-EGFP-positive keratinocytes) from bulge cell population of 50-60 day old female B6SJL/F1 transgenics. Results provide targets for the treatment of hair loss and other disorders of skin and hair.

title: Adult acute myeloid leukemia: bone marrow and peripheral blood expression profiles (SHCO)
description: Part of a study profiling 54 bone marrow and 65 peripheral blood samples from 116 adults with acute myeloid leukemia (AML). Results identify distinct gene expression signatures that correlate with clinical outcomes. Signatures used to construct a clinical outcome predictor using 133 genes.

title: Adult acute myeloid leukemia: bone marrow and peripheral blood expression profiles (SHDJ)
description: Part of a study profiling 54 bone marrow and 65 peripheral blood samples from 116 adults with acute myeloid leukemia (AML). Results identify distinct gene expression signatures that correlate with clinical outcomes. Signatures used to construct a clinical outcome predictor using 133 genes.

title: Peri-implantation embryo development
description: Gene expression changes during peri-implantation conceptus development. Small spherical (1-5 mm), large spherical (6-11 mm), tubular (13-45 mm) and filamentous (>100 mm) embryos analyzed.

title: Breast cancer cell line ME16C response to chemotherapeutics: time course
description: Analysis of the response of the basal epithelium derived breast cancer line ME16C to either doxorubicin or 5-fluorouracil.  Cells examined 12, 24, and 36 hours following treatment.  Results provide insight into the response of breast cancers derived from different cell types to chemotherapeutics.

title: Breast cancer cell line HME-CC response to chemotherapeutics: time course
description: Analysis of the response of basal epithelium derived breast cancer line HME-CC to either doxorubicin or 5-fluorouracil. Cells examined 12, 24, and 36 hours following treatment. Results provide insight into the response of breast cancers derived from different cell types to chemotherapeutics.

title: Breast cancer cell line MCF-7 response to chemotherapeutics: time course
description: Analysis of the response of luminal epithelium derived breast cancer line MCF-7 to either doxorubicin or 5-fluorouracil. Cells examined 12, 24, and 36 hours following treatment. Results provide insight into the response of breast cancers derived from different cell types to chemotherapeutics.

title: Breast cancer cell line ZR-75-1 response to chemotherapeutics: time course
description: Analysis of the response of luminal epithelium derived breast cancer line ZR-75-1 to either doxorubicin or 5-fluorouracil. Cells examined 12, 24, and 36 hours following treatment. Results provide insight into the response of breast cancers derived from different cell types to chemotherapeutics.

title: Hereditary spastic paraparesis
description: Analysis of gene expression in skeletal muscle of three patients affected by hereditary spastic paraplegia (HSP) caused by mutations of spastin (SPG4). SPG4 is an ubiquitously expressed protein involved in microtubule regulation and vesicle traffic.

title: Extraocular muscle: comparison of global and orbital layers
description: Expression profiling of microdissected global and orbital layers of the rectus extraocular muscle (EOM) from 2 adult Sprague-Dawleys. By identifying molecular differences between the 2 layers, results provide insight into the possible specialized function of each muscle layer.

title: Alveolar epithelial cell line A549 response to acute lung injury causing stimuli: time course
description: Examination of alveolar epithelial A549 cells in models of pulmonary parenchymal cell activation: exposure to tumor necrosis factor-alpha (TNF-alpha), lipopolysaccharide (LPS), or cyclic stretch. Cells examined 1 and 4 hours after exposure to each acute lung injury-causing stimulus.

title: Erythroid and non-erythroid granulocyte-monocyte progenitor cells
description: Expression profiling of FACS-isolated erythroid progenitor and non-erythroid granulocyte-monocyte progenitor cells from 10-16 week old C57BL/6-S129Ola. Results provide insight into erythropoiesis and identify an expression pattern unique to erythroid progenitors.

title: Transforming growth factor beta effect on acute myelogenous leukemia cells
description: Analysis of M091 acute myelogenous leukemia cells after treatment with 200 pM transforming growth factor beta (TGFbeta) for 2 and 4 hours. Part of a study comparing M091 to hematopoietic stem cells. Reveals cytostatic role of TGFbeta in hematopoiesis and identifies p57 as a possible tumor suppressor

title: Transforming growth factor beta effect on CD34+ hematopoietic stem cells
description: Analysis of CB-CD34 CD34+ hematopoietic stem cells after treatment with 200 pM TGFbeta for 2 and 4 hours. Part of a study comparing CB-CD34 cells to acute myelogenous leukemia cells. Reveals cytostatic role of TGFbeta in hematopoiesis and identifies p57 as a possible tumor suppressor.

title: Fibrillin-1 deficiency effect on heart mitral valves
description: Expression profiling of heart mitral valve from homozygous and heterozygous C1039G fibrillin-1 mutants at 6.5 postnatal days. Fibrillin-1 deficient mutants are models for acquired myxomatous mitral valve disease and Marfan syndrome.

title: Corneal stromal cell differentiation
description: Expression profiling of cultured keratocyte, fibroblast, and myofibroblast cells of the corneal stroma. Cultured cells compared to cornea from adults and 10 day postnatals.  Keratocytes maintain the transparent corneal stroma, and upon injury differentiate into fibroblasts and myofibroblasts.

title: Mucoid and motile Pseudomonas aeruginosa infected lung epithelial cell comparison
description: Comparison of lung epithelial Calu-3 cells infected with the mucoid alginate-producing FRD1 strain to those infected with the isogenic motile flagellin-producing FRD440 strain of Pseudomonas aeruginosa. Mucoid and motile strains are associated with chronic and acute lung infections, respectively.

title: Peroxisome proliferator-activated receptor-gamma target genes in aorta
description: Analysis of aorta isolated from adult male C57BL/6J treated for 21 days with a peroxisome proliferator-activated receptor-gamma (PPARgamma) agonist rosiglitazone or vehicle. Diminished activity of PPARgamma may play role in pathogenesis of hypertension and vascular dysfunction.

title: Endothelin-1 effect on fibroblasts
description: Cultured primary lung fibroblasts incubated 4 hours in the presence or absence of 100 nM endothelin-1 (ET-1). Results suggest that ET-1 is involved in matrix synthesis and connective tissue deposition during wound repair and in pulmonary fibrosis.

title: Sex-dependent and growth hormone-dependent gene expression (MWG Rat 5K Array)
description: Investigation of regulatory role of growth hormone (GH) in sexually dimorphic gene expression. Liver tissue from adult male and female rats untreated or treated with GH by 7 day continuous infusion examined.

title: Sex-dependent and growth hormone-dependent gene expression (MWG Rat Liver Array)
description: Investigation of regulatory role of growth hormone (GH) in sexually dimorphic gene expression. Liver tissue examined from adult male and female rats untreated or treated with GH by 7 day continuous infusion.

title: Spatial gene expression in flowers (oligo array)
description: Comparison of gene expression profiles of inflorescences of the floral homeotic mutants apetala1, apetala2, apetala3, pistillata, and agamous with that of wild type plants. Several genes predicted to have floral organ-specific expression patterns.

title: Spatial gene expression in flowers (oligo array; dye-swap)
description: Comparison of gene expression profiles of inflorescences of the floral homeotic mutants apetala1, apetala2, apetala3, pistillata, and agamous with that of wild type plants. Several genes predicted to have floral organ-specific expression patterns.

title: MPSS transcriptome analysis project
description: Large scale transcriptome analysis using massively parallel signature sequencing (MPSS) technology. The focus of this project is to generate a reference tissue expression dataset for C57BL/6J.

title: Spinal cord injury and regeneration time course: below T9 (RG-U34A)
description: Temporal analysis of molecular mechanisms of spinal cord degeneration and repair. Analyzed spinal cord below thoracic vertebrae T9 at various time points up to 28 days post injury. Mild, moderate and severe injury examined.

title: Spinal cord injury and regeneration time course: below T9 (RG-U34B)
description: Temporal analysis of molecular mechanisms of spinal cord degeneration and repair. Analyzed spinal cord below thoracic vertebrae T9 at various time points up to 28 days post injury. Mild and severe injury examined.

title: Spinal cord injury and regeneration time course: below T9 (RG-U34C)
description: Temporal analysis of molecular mechanisms of spinal cord degeneration and repair. Analyzed spinal cord below thoracic vertebrae T9 at various time points up to 28 days post injury. Mild and severe injury examined.

title: Spinal cord injury and regeneration time course: above T9 (RG-U34A)
description: Temporal analysis of molecular mechanisms of spinal cord degeneration and repair. Analyzed spinal cord above thoracic vertebrae T9 at various time points up to 28 days post injury. Mild, moderate and severe injury examined.

title: Spinal cord injury and regeneration time course: above T9 (RG-U34B)
description: Temporal analysis of molecular mechanisms of spinal cord degeneration and repair. Analyzed spinal cord above thoracic vertebrae T9 at various time points up to 28 days post injury. Mild and severe injury examined.

title: Spinal cord injury and regeneration time course: above T9 (RG-U34C)
description: Temporal analysis of molecular mechanisms of spinal cord degeneration and repair. Analyzed spinal cord above thoracic vertebrae T9 at various time points up to 28 days post injury. Mild and severe injury examined.

title: Alveolar type I and type II cell comparison
description: Expression profiling of freshly isolated alveolar type I (TI) and type II (TII) cells, and cultured alveolar TII cells grown in vitro for 7 days.  Results provide insight into the functional differences between TI and TII cells.

title: MPSS analysis of BLK CL.4 and liver cells
description: Massively parallel signature sequencing (MPSS) analysis of C57BL/6J BLK CL.4 cells and liver cells. Total mRNA, nuclear mRNA and post-nuclear mRNA examined.

title: X-linked hypophosphatemia and low phosphate diet
description: Examination of kidney from normal or X-linked hypophosphatemic (Hyp) 5 week old mice fed either control (1.0% P) or low phosphate diet (0.03% P) for 3 or 5 days. Results provide insight into mechanism of renal adaptation to low phosphate diet.

title: Visceral adiposity resulting from poor fetal nutrition
description: Expression profiling of visceral adipose tissue of 130 day old adult male Wistars that had been subjected to poor nutrition during fetal development caused by maternal protein restriction. Results indicate that poor fetal nutrition predisposes to visceral obesity.

title: Breast cancer and selective estrogen receptor modulators
description: Analysis of gene stimulation and inhibition by the selective estrogen receptor modulators (SERMs) trans-hydroxytamoxifen (TOT) and raloxifene (Ral) or ICI 182,780 (ICI) and by estradiol (E2) in estrogen receptor-containing MCF-7 breast cancer cells. Cells were treated for 8 or 48 hours.

title: Neuromedin U effect on type-2 Th cells: time course
description: Analysis of type-2 Th cell line D10.G4.1 after treatment with 10 nM neuromedin U (NmU) for various times up to 12 hours. NmU is a neuropeptide that binds to its receptor on D10.G4.1 cells, eliciting the release of cytokines. This effect suggests a role for NmU in immune response and inflammation.

title: Lipopolysaccharide-induced gene expression mediated by Schistosome soluble egg antigen
description: IL10-/- dendritic cells (DC) pulsed for 6 hours with soluble antigen molecules from the eggs of the helminth parasite Schistosoma mansoni (SEA), lipopolysaccharide (LPS), or SEA/LPS to compare changes in LPS-induced gene expression mediated by SEA, and the anti-inflammatory properties of SEA.

title: Estradiol effect on osteosarcoma cells expressing estrogen receptor alpha or beta: time course
description: Expression profiling of U2OS osteosarcoma cells after treatment with 17beta-estradiol (E2) for various lengths of time up to 48 hours.  U2OS transfected with either estrogen receptor (ER) alpha or beta.  Results identify signaling pathways in bone regulated by E2 through ERalpha and ERbeta.

title: Tumor cell response to topoisomerase poison camptothecin
description: HeLa tumor cells treated with 10 uM topoisomerase poison camptothecin (CPT) for 8 hours. This dose and time are sufficient to induce rapid apoptosis. Results identify potential targets for adjuvant cancer therapy.

title: Diabetic nephropathy: models of type 1 and type 2 diabetes
description: Examination of kidneys from streptozotocin-induced diabetic C57BL/6J and db/db animals, which are models for type I and type II diabetes, respectively. Results identify HSD3-beta 4 and OPN as classifiers for the mesangial matrix expansion phenotype, an indicator for end-stage renal disease.

title: Schwann cell development: neural crest stem cells to mature Schwann cells
description: Expression profiling of neural crest stem cells at embryonic day (E) 9.5 and developing Schwann cells (SC) at E12, E14, E16, E18, and mature SCs at birth. Cells isolated by FACS from proteolipid-GFP transgenics. Results provide insight into stem cell regulation and Schwann cell development.

title: Synaptic acetylcholinesterase overexpression in prefrontal cortex
description: Gene expression profiles from prefrontal cortex of female FVB/N mice and female mice overexpressing human synaptic acetylcholinesterase (AChE).

title: GATA3 ectopic expression in 293T cells
description: Examination of 293T epithelial kidney cells stably transfected with either wild type GATA3 or R367L mutant GATA3. GATA3 can be highly expressed in breast tumors. GATA3 variants may contribute to tumorigenesis.

title: GATA3 ectopic expression in 293T cells (dye-swap)
description: Examination of 293T epithelial kidney cells stably transfected with either wild type GATA3 or R367L mutant GATA3. GATA3 can be highly expressed in breast tumors. GATA3 variants may contribute to tumorigenesis.

title: Skeletal muscle response to exercise and circadian rhythms
description: Analysis of effects of resistance exercise (RE) and time of day in skeletal muscle. Biopsies of male vastus lateralis muscle obtained 6 and 18 hours after acute RE, or no RE. Results suggest that RE may directly modulate circadian rhythms in skeletal muscle.

title: Aquaporin-1 knockout kidney inner medulla profile (I)
description: Gene expression profiles of kidney inner medulla from aquaporin-1 (AQP1) null and wild type mice compared against a wild type common reference. AQP1 null mice manifest a severe defect in urinary concentrating ability.

title: Aquaporin-1 knockout kidney inner medulla profile (II)
description: Gene expression profiles of kidney inner medulla from aquaporin-1 (AQP1) null and wild type mice compared against a AQP1 null common reference. AQP1 null mice manifest a severe defect in urinary concentrating ability.

title: Estrogen receptor alpha L540Q mutation effect on gene induction by estradiol: time course
description: Analysis of breast cancer cell line 231/ERalpha expressing L540Q mutant estrogen receptor after 1 or 2 hour estradiol treatment. Mutant receptor is defective in binding steroid receptor coactivator (SRC) proteins. Results identify estrogen-regulated genes that require SRCs for expression.

title: Pyridine activator of myocyte hypertrophy effect on ventricular myocytes
description: Analysis of ventricular myocytes cultured 48 hours in 1 uM of pyridine activator of myocyte hypertrophy (PAMH) or 20 uM phenylephrine (PE). PAMH activates a modulator of calcineurin, and is as effective as phenylephrine in promoting hypertrophy. PAMH and PE treated cells exhibit similar expression.

title: Pancreatic beta cell lines overexpressing wild type MODY genes or mutant HNF1b alleles
description: Analysis of gene expression in pancreatic beta cell line INS-1 overexpressing the transcription factors HNF1b, HNF4a2, HNF6, or mutant forms of HNF1b, which were introduced by FRT/FLP recombination.  Dysfunction of these transcription factors cause maturity onset diabetes of the young (MODY).

title: Bladder smooth muscle cell response to mechanical stretch
description: Expression profiling of cultured bladder smooth muscle cells subjected to repetitive mechanical stimulation for 4 hours.  Chronic overdistension results in bladder wall thickening, associated with loss of muscle contractility. Results identify genes whose expression is altered by mechanical stimuli.

title: Macrophage inflammatory protein-1alpha disruption effect on olfactory epithelium
description: Expression profiling of the olfactory epithelium (OE) from macrophage inflammatory protein-1alpha disrupted (Mip-1alpha-/-) 6 week old C57BL/6 males. Effect of injecting wild type Mip-1alpha into the OE of Mip-1alpha-/- males examined. Results provide insight into OE remodeling.

title: Xylose metabolism
description: Strain YSX3 engineered for D-xylose utilization and respiration-deficient mutant FPL-YSX3P were grown under full aeration or oxygen limitation, with glucose or xylose as a carbon source.

title: Alternative splicing in five tissues
description: Detection of tissue-specific regulation of alternative splicing for 316 genes in five normal tissues (brain, muscle, liver, bone marrow, testes) using array containing oligonucleotides spanning individual exons and splice junctions.

title: Alternative splicing in five tissues (dye-swap)
description: Detection of tissue-specific regulation of alternative splicing for 316 genes in five normal tissues (brain, muscle, liver, bone marrow, testes) using array containing oligonucleotides spanning individual exons and splice junctions.

title: Growth-arrested cell: serum deprivation and contact inhibition growth-arrest comparison
description: Expression profiling of T98G cancer cells in growth-arrest induced by 3 days of either serum deprivation or contact inhibition. Results show that targets of the p130- E2F4 repressor complex are downregulated under the two growth-arrest conditions.

title: Hair follicle development: time course
description: Expression profiling of back skin excised from CB6F1 animals at various ages up to 1 year.  Difference between synchronously and asynchronously growing hair used to identify hair cycle genes.  Results provide insight into the mechanisms regulating hair follicle morphogenesis.

title: DNA damage from ultraviolet and ionizing radiation effect on peripheral blood lymphocytes
description: Analysis of peripheral blood lymphocytes exposed to ultraviolet (10 J/m^2) or ionizing radiation (5 Gy). Lymphocytes obtained from 15 healthy individuals from ages 21 to 36 years and immortalized with Epstein-Barr virus. Results provide insight into transcriptional response to DNA damage.

title: Metabolic syndrome response to exercise intervention (HG-95A)
description: Analysis of skeletal muscle from overweight males with metabolic syndrome. Individuals subjected to chronic exercise training. Muscles examined prior to training, and after 1 and 14 days of recovery following 9 months training. Provides insight into effects of exercise intervention.

title: Ewing family tumor histogenetic origin
description: Human embryonic kidney cells HEK293 transfected with the Ewing family tumor (EFT)-specific EWS-FLI1 fusion protein to investigate the histogenetic origin of EFTs. The observed EFT-specific gene expression profile supports the concept of a neural crest and endothelial origin of EFT stem cells.

title: Whole blood RNA isolation and leukocyte RNA purification: comparison of methods
description: Comparison of RNA isolation from whole blood using the PAXgene system to that from leukocytes using the buffy coat procedure.  Blood of healthy subjects and trauma patients examined.  Results indicate that RNA isolated from whole blood produced more noise than that from leukocytes.

title: Ewing family tumor cells: effect of transfection
description: Analysis of Ewing family tumor (EFT) cell line A673 response to interleukin-2 (IL-2) transfection to assess possible undesirable effects (e.g. tumor stimulation) of in vitro manipulation. Results impact the potential use of IL-2 transfection as an in vivo immunotherapy for EFT patients.

title: Cytosine methylase inactivation and histone deacetylase inhibition effect on expression
description: Analysis of 16 day old Columbia plantlets grown in media with 7 ug/ml 5-aza-2'deoxycytosine (aza-dC) to block cytosine methylation (Cm) or 0.5 uM trichostatin A (TSA) to block histone deacetylation (HD) or both. Results provide insight into the interaction between Cm and HD in gene regulation.

title: Cytosine methylase inactivation and histone deacetylase inhibition effect on expression (dye-swap)
