description: Analysis of 16 day old Columbia plantlets grown in media with 7 ug/ml 5-aza-2'deoxycytosine (aza-dC) to block cytosine methylation (Cm) or 0.5 uM trichostatin A (TSA) to block histone deacetylation (HD) or both. Results provide insight into the interaction between Cm and HD in gene regulation.

title: TOR2-controlled transcription
description: Comparison of total transcription profiles for temperature-sensitive TOR2 mutant strain SH121 to its isogenic wild type counterpart SH100. Results indicate that TOR2 inactivation leads to enhanced transcription of Gcn4-controlled target genes.

title: Myotube starvation model of atrophy
description: Expression profiling of starved skeletal muscle C2C12 myotubes. Starvation induced by witholding differentiation medium containing 2% horse serum for 4 days. Results show that the expression profile of starved myotubes differs to that of whole muscle atrophy.

title: Photosynthesis and photosystem I mutant
description: Comparison of expression profiles of psad1 mutant lacking D subunit of photosystem I (PSI-D) and wild type. Photosynthetic electron flow and growth are affected in psad1 mutant.

title: Erythroid progenitor erythropoiesis
description: Analysis of three distinct stages of late erythroid progenitor cell development. Developmentally synchronized erythroid progenitor cells (EPCs) were prepared from splenocytes at 80, 100 and 120 hours after thiamphenical withdrawal.

title: Osteoblasts and microgravity-induced bone loss
description: Identification of gravisensitive gene expression in 2T3 pre-osteoblast cells exposed to 3 days of simulated microgravity. Microgravity causes bone loss possibly due to decreased bone formation by osteoblasts. Results provide insight into similar pathologic conditions such as osteoporosis.

title: Stress response in brain
description: Examination of brain from fish stressed with netting and confinement for 1, 3 or 5 days.

title: Stress response in brain (dye-swap)
description: Examination of brain from fish stressed with netting and confinement for 1 or 3 days.

title: Stress response in kidney
description: Examination of kidney from fish stressed with netting and confinement for 1, 3 or 5 days.

title: Stress response in kidney (dye-swap)
description: Examination of kidney from fish stressed with netting and confinement for 1, 3 or 5 days.

title: Kaposi sarcoma-associated herpesvirus infection of primary human dermal endothelial cells
description: Primary human dermal endothelial cells (HDMEC) were infected with isolated Kaposi sarcoma-associated herpesvirus (KSHV) for 7 days. Infection of HDVECs with KSHV results in upregulation of lymphatic lineage-specific genes and downregulation of blood vascular genes.

title: Skeletal myoblast cell line KM109 differentiation: time course (I)
description: Expression profiling of primary myoblast cell line KM109 obtained from muscle biopsy of a healthy individual and induced to differentiate by serum deprivation.  Cells examined at various time points up to 14 days following serum deprivation.  Results provide insight into late myogenesis.

title: Skeletal myoblast cell line KM109 differentiation: time course (I, dye-swap)
description: Expression profiling of primary myoblast cell line KM109 obtained from muscle biopsy of a healthy individual and induced to differentiate by serum deprivation. Cells examined at various time points up to 14 days following serum deprivation. Results provide insight into late myogenesis.

title: Skeletal myoblast cell line KM109 differentiation: time course (II)
description: Expression profiling of primary myoblast cell line KM109 obtained from muscle biopsy of a healthy individual and induced to differentiate by serum deprivation. Cells examined at various time points up to 14 days following serum deprivation. Results provide insight into late myogenesis.

title: Skeletal myoblast cell line KM109 differentiation: time course (II, dye-swap)
description: Expression profiling of primary myoblast cell line KM109 obtained from muscle biopsy of a healthy individual and induced to differentiate by serum deprivation. Cells examined at various time points up to 14 days following serum deprivation. Results provide insight into late myogenesis.

title: Familial combined hyperlipidemia
description: Expression profiling of lymphoblastic cell lines derived from the peripheral blood lymphocytes of patients with familial combined hyperlipidemia (FCHL), the most common form of genetically determined dyslipidemia.  Results provide insight into the pathophysiology of FCHL.

title: Lacrimal gland and cornea burn: time course (SMCmou8400A)
description: Examination of the effect of stimulation stress produced by chemical burn to the cornea in the lacrimal gland over a 0.5 to 360 hour time course in comparison with the non-stimulated controls.

title: Lacrimal gland and cornea burn: time course (SMCmou6600Av1)
description: Examination of the effect of stimulation stress produced by chemical burn to the cornea in the lacrimal gland over a 0.5 to 24 hour time course in comparison with the non-stimulated controls.

title: Lacrimal gland and cornea burn: time course (SMCmou6600Av2)
description: Examination of the effect of stimulation stress produced by chemical burn to the cornea in the lacrimal gland over a 1 to 360 hour time course in comparison with the non-stimulated controls.

title: Hormone-induced adipogenesis suppressed by 2,3,7,8-tetrachlorodibenzo-p-dioxin and EGF
description: Analysis of differentiated C3H10T1/2 fibroblasts treated with 10 nM 2,3,7,8-tetrachlorodibenzo-p-dioxin (TCDD) and/or 10 nM EGF. Prior to treatment, cells induced to differentiate into adipocytes with IDMB hormone. EGF increases effectiveness of TCDD in suppressing hormone-induced adipogenesis.

title: Embryonic lung: branching and non-branching regions
description: Transcriptional profiles of distal branching and proximal non-branching regions of lung at embryonic day E11.5. During development, the proximal and distal regions of respiratory tract undergo distinct processes that give rise to conducting airways and alveoli.

title: Ketogenic diet effect on brain hippocampus
description: Expression profiling of brain hippocampi of animals fed the ketogenic diet (KD).  KD is an anticonvulsant treatment used to manage medically intractable epilepsies.   Results provide insight into the anticonvulsant action of KD.

title: Early-life kainite-induced seizure effect on brain hippocampus: time course
description: Analysis of early-life kainite induced seizures by expression profiling of brain hippocampi from animals at postnatal day 15. Hippocampi examined at various time points up to 240 hours following kainite treatment. Results provide insight into molecular effects of early childhood convulsions.

title: Dopamine neurons from substantia nigra pars compacta and ventral tegmental area
description: Expression profiling of dopaminergic neurons of the substantia nigra pars compacta (SNc) and the ventral tegmental area.  Neurons from normal animals isolated using laser capture microdissection.  SNc dopaminergic neurons degenerate in Parkinson's disease.

title: Asthma and interleukin 13 (MOE430A)
description: Expression profiling of lung tissue from interleukin 13 (IL-13) knockout mice treated with house dust mite allergen. IL-13 mediates the development of asthma by causing hyperreactivity of the airway and mucus overproduction in the lung.

title: Asthma and interleukin 13 (MOE430B)
description: Expression profiling of lung tissue from interleukin 13 (IL-13) knockout mice treated with house dust mite allergen. IL-13 mediates the development of asthma by causing hyperreactivity of the airway and mucus overproduction in the lung.

title: Estrogen effect on lung: time course
description: Expression profiling of lungs from ovariectomized animals 3 and 6 hours following estrogen treatment.  Estrogen prevents diminished alveoli formation in ovariectomized immature animals, and reverses the loss of alveoli in ovariectomized adults.

title: Diabetic nephropathy
description: Comparison of glomeruli from kidneys with diabetic nephropathy (DN) and glomeruli from kidneys of healthy individuals. Progression of DN may be due to diminished tissue repair capability.

title: Peripheral blood mononuclear cells and the effect of exercise
description: Peripheral blood mononuclear cells (PBMC) were isolated from blood samples taken from healthy male subjects before, immediately after, and 60 minutes after 30 minutes of exercise. Brisk activation and deactivation of genes associated with stress, inflammation, and tissue repair observed.

title: Macular degeneration and dermal fibroblast response to sublethal oxidative stress
description: Expression profiling of dermal fibroblasts from patients with macular degeneration.  Fibroblasts subjected to sublethal oxidative stress.  This study tests the hypothesis that patients with macular degeneration have an abnormal response to cellular injury in sites other than the eye.

title: Methylprednisolone effect on kidney: time course (RAE230A)
description: Expression profiling of kidneys from animals treated with methylprednisolone.  Kidneys examined at various time points up to 72 hours following methylprednisolone treatment.  Results provide insight into prednisone pharmacodynamics.

title: Methylprednisolone effect on kidney: time course (RG-U34A)
description: Expression profiling of kidneys from animals treated with methylprednisolone.  Kidneys examined at various time points up to 6 hours following methylprednisolone treatment.  Results provide insight into prednisone pharmacodynamics.

title: Adventitious root development
description: Analysis of hypocotyls treated with auxin to induce adventitious root formation. Hypocotyls were harvested at day 0, day 3 (cell expansion), day 6 (when root primordia are formed), day 9 (when root meristems are formed), day 12 (when roots are fully developed), and day 33 (root elongation).

title: Glycine receptor beta subunit mutant model for hyperekplexia
description: Analysis of spinal cords from glycine receptor beta subunit mutants with alleviating or severe spastic symptoms. Mutants at various ages up to 6 months examined. Results provide insight into the basis for tendency of hyperekplexia (startle disease) symptoms to alleviate with age.

title: Radiation therapy toxicity association with abnormal transcriptional response to DNA damage
description: Analysis of UV and IR irradiated lymphoblastoid cell lines derived from the peripheral blood of patients with acute radiation toxicity.  Samples taken 2 months after the completion of radiation therapy.  Results provide insight into the role of the response to DNA damage in radiation toxicity.

title: Bone marrow prolonged storage effects
description: Analysis of impact of pre-analytical handling of bone marrow (BM). Time delays of 0, 24, or 48 hours between sample aspiration and RNA extraction examined. Storage of BM has dramatic effects on mRNA expression of individual transcripts.

title: Bile ductular differentiation of embryonic hepatoblasts: time course
description: Temporal analysis of hepatoblast cell line 3 (HBC-3) cells grown on Matrigel to induce in vitro bile ductular differentiation. HBC-3 line is derived from liver diverticulum on day 9.5 of gestation.

title: Rhabdomyosarcoma and Ewing's sarcoma comparison
description: Comparison of gene expression in 12 pediatric rhabdomyosarcomas (RMS) to that in 11 pediatric Ewing's sarcomas (EWS).   3 embryonic and 9 alveolar RMS tumors examined.  RMS and EWS appear similar in routine histology.  Results identify expression profiles that distinguish RMS from EWS.

title: Methylprednisolone effect on liver: time course (RAE230A)
description: Expression profiling of liver from animals treated with methylprednisolone. Liver examined at various time points up to 168 hours following methylprednisolone treatment. Results provide insight into prednisone pharmacodynamics.

title: Flagellar export apparatus component FlhA inactivation effect on virulence
description: Comparison of the V26 attenuated strain to the V1 strain with a component of the flagellar export apparatus FlhA inactivated.  FlhA inactivation decreases virulence.  Results show that the expression profile of V1 with FlhA inactivated is similar to that of V26.

title: Flagellar export apparatus component FlhA inactivation effect on virulence (dye-swap)
description: Comparison of the V26 attenuated strain to the V1 strain with a component of the flagellar export apparatus FlhA inactivated.  FlhA inactivation decreases virulence.  Results show that the expression profile of V1 with FlhA inactivated is similar to that of V26.

title: Uterine response to physiologic and plant-derived estrogen: time course
description: Temporal analysis of immature Alpk:APfCD-1 uterus response up to 72 hours after a single dose of physiologic estrogen 17beta-estradiol (E2) or phytoestrogen genistein (GEN).

title: Uterine response to physiologic, plant-derived, and synthetic estrogen
description: Analysis of immature Alpk:APfCD-1 uterus 72 hours after 3 daily injections of physiologic estrogen 17beta-estradiol (E2), phytoestrogen genistein (GEN), or synthetic estrogen diethylstilbestrol (DES). Similarity in gene expression indicates synthetic estrogen may not pose unique threat to health.

title: Abscisic acid and gibberellin effect on calluses
description: Analysis of calluses treated for 3 days with 50 uM of abscisic acid (ABA) or gibberellin (GA).  ABA promotes seed dormancy, while GA promotes seed germination.  Results provide insight into the crosstalk between ABA and GA regulated signaling pathways.

title: Abscisic acid and gibberellin effect on calluses (dye-swap)
description: Analysis of calluses treated for 3 days with 50 uM of abscisic acid (ABA) or gibberellin (GA).  ABA promotes seed dormancy, while GA promotes seed germination.  Results provide insight into the crosstalk between ABA and GA regulated signaling pathways.

title: Kidney transplant response to calcineurin inhibitor-free immunosuppression using sirolimus
description: Analysis of kidneys from adult renal transplant recipients subjected to calcineurin inhibitor-free immunosuppression using sirolimus. Patients treated with sirolimus have a lower prevalence of chronic allograft nephropathy compared to those treated with cyclosporine, a calcineurin inhibitor.

title: Kaposi's sarcoma-associated herpesvirus LANA overexpression in B lymphoid cells: time course
description: Expression profiling of B lymphoid cell lines overexpressing the latency-associated nuclear antigen (LANA) of Kaposi's sarcoma-associated herpesvirus. B cells made to express LANA from a tetracycline inducible promoter.  Expression examined at various time points up to 48 hours after induction.

title: Kaposi's sarcoma-associated herpesvirus and Epstein-Barr virus infected cell lines
description: Expression profiling of cell lines BCBL-1 and BC-3 infected by Kaposi's sarcoma-associated herpesvirus (KSHV), Raji infected by the Epstein-Barr virus (EBV), and BC-1 infected by both viruses.  Results identify expression patterns specific to KSHV-infected primary effusion lymphoma derived cells.

title: Phosphomannose isomerase PMI40 deletion strain response to excess mannose
description: Expression profiling of a phosphomannose isomerase PMI40 deletion strain growing on media with various mannose concentrations up to 5 g/liter.  Results provide insight into the cause of slow growth exhibited by the PMI40 deletion strain in media with excess mannose.

title: Endoplasmic reticulum membrane-associated genes in breast cancer cell line MCF-7
description: Identification of genes whose mRNA are translated from the endoplasmic reticulum (ER) in the breast cancer cell line MCF-7.  Secreted and membrane-bound proteins are preferentially translated in the ER.  Results provide insight into the association of membrane-bound proteins and breast cancer.

title: Naive CD8+ T cells proliferative response to lymphopenia: time course
description: Analysis of OT-I CD8+ T cells from lymphopenic C57BL/6s. OT-I CD8+ T cells transferred into C57BL/6s, irradiated to induce lymphopenia.  OT-I CD8+ T cells examined at various time points up to 115 days after transfer. Results provide insight into mechanisms regulating homeostatic proliferation.

title: Segmental trisomy Ts1Cje model for Down syndrome
description: Expression profiling of brain cerebella from Ts1Cje males at postnatal days 0, 15, and 30.  RNA pooled from 3 males at each developmental stage. Results provide insight into the molecular changes contributing to the pathogenesis of Down syndrome.

title: Vitamin E deficiency effect on distal colon
description: Expression profiling of distal colons from 8 Hooded Lister males fed a vitamin E deficient diet for 12 weeks. Vitamin E deficiency is associated with inflammatory bowel disease and colon cancer. Results provide insight into the contribution of vitamin E deficiency to colon pathologies.

title: DNase II and type I interferon receptor double null mutation effect on fetal liver
description: Analysis of fetal livers of E14.5 embryos lacking DNaseII (DNase2-/-) and type I interferon receptor (Ifnar-/-) or DNaseII alone. DNase2-/- embryos exhibit dysregulated interferon target genes and die in utero. DNase2-/-, Ifnar-/- embryos exhibit normal interferon target gene regulation and survive.

title: Transcription factor CHOP null mutation effect on fibroblasts subjected to ER stress: time course
description: Expression profiling of embryonic fibroblasts deleted for the transcription factor CHOP.  Fibroblast treated with 2 ug/ml tunicamycin for 4 or 8 hours to induce endoplasmic reticulum (ER) stress. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms regulating the response to ER stress.

title: Treacher Collins' syndrome Tcof1 gene overexpression and knockdown effect on neuroblastoma cells
description: Expression profiling of neuroblastoma N1E-115 cells with the Treacher Collins' syndrome (TCS) Tcof1 gene overexpressed or inactivated.  TCS is an autosomal dominant dysostosis of the face and lower jaw. Results provide insight into the role of Tcof1 in neuroblastoma cell proliferation.

title: Bronchoalveolar lavage cells of lung transplant recipients with acute rejection
description: Expression profiling of bronchoalveolar lavage cells of lung transplant recipients with acute rejection. Rejection status determined from biopsies. Results identify possible gene markers of lung transplant rejection.

title: Na,K-ATPase alpha 1 isoform reduced expression effect on hearts
description: Expression profiling of hearts from 8 to 16 week old adult males lacking one copy of the Na,K-ATPase alpha 1 isoform.  Na,K-ATPase alpha 1 isoform expression is reduced by half in heterozygous null mutants.  Results provide insight into the role of the Na,K-ATPase alpha 1 isoform in the heart.

title: Lung response to urban particulate matter: time course
description: Analysis of lungs from hypersensitive males exposed to urban particulate matter.  Males exposed to 10 mg Ottawa dust sample EHC-93 per kg of body weight.  Lungs examined at various time points up to 40 hours after exposure.  Results provide insight into the molecular effects of exposure to dust.

title: Embryogenesis and early fetal development: time course
description: Expression profiling of embryos at various days of gestation up to 21 days and fetuses and fetal membranes at 27 and 28 days of gestation.   Results provide insight into the regulation of embryonic, fetal, and fetal membrane differentiation.

title: Male and female salivary gland comparison
description: Expression profiling of 9 week old BALB/c male and female submandibular, sublingual, and parotid salivary glands.  Lacrimal and meibomian glands also examined.  Results provide insight into the differences between male and female salivary glands.

title: Bone marrow and muscle Side Population cell comparison
description: Expression profiling of Side Population (SP) cells from bone marrow and muscle of 4 to 5 week old C57BL/10SnJ males.  Main Population from bone marrow and muscle also examined.  Results provide insight into the similarities and differences between SP cells from different tissues.

title: Essential hypertension BPH model
description: Expression profiling of adrenal glands from blood pressure high (BPH) males at the prehypertensive stage. BPH males examined at 5 weeks of age. Results compared to gene expression in SHR rat model, and provides insight into mechanisms of hypertension shared across species.

title: Idiopathic and scleroderma-associated pulmonary fibrosis derived fibroblasts response to TGFbeta
description: Analysis of adult lung fibroblasts treated with 4 ng/ml TGFbeta cytokine for 4 hours. Fibroblasts obtained from patients with idiopathic or scleroderma-associated pulmonary fibrosis. Results provide insight into the role of TGFbeta in pulmonary fibrosis.

title: IFH1 overexpression: time course
description: Analysis of overexpression of essential ribosomal protein activator IFH1. Cells engineered to express IFH1 from a galactose inducible promoter. Expression examined at various time points up to 60 minutes following galactose addition.  Results indicate that IFH1 regulates ribosomal protein genes.

title: Serum response factor SRF overexpression in embryonic stem cells
description: Expression profiling of embryonic stem (ES) cells overexpressing serum response factor SRF.  SRF transiently transfected into ES cells disrupted for both copies of SRF.  RNA examined 72 hours after transfection.  Results identify potential transcriptional targets of SRF.

title: Serum response factor SRF induction in embryonic stem cells: time course
description: Expression profiling of embryonic stem (ES) cells following stimulation with fetal bovine serum at various time points up to 180 minutes.  Expression in wild type ES cells compared to that in Srf homozygous mutants with or without an SRF transgene.  Results identify potential targets of SRF.

title: Hypoxic-ischemic injury response to erythropoietin pretreatment
description: Analysis of 7 day old forebrains pretreated with erythropoietin (EPO) and then subjected to hypoxic-ischemic injury (HI). HI induced by ligation of the common carotid artery and confinement in hypoxic chambers for 50 minutes. Results provide insight into the neuroprotective effect of EPO.

title: Brain hippocampal neurons response to brief preconditioning seizures
description: Expression profiling of brain hippocampal CA1 and CA3 neurons of Sprague Dawleys subjected to brief preconditioning seizures. Dentate gyrus granule cells also examined. CA1 and CA3 neurons subjected to preconditioning seizures are less vulnerable to subsequent prolonged seizures.

title: Skeletal muscle response to voluntary running: time course
description: Analysis of plantaris muscle following a bout of voluntary running for 12 hours.  Gene expression examined at various time points up to 24 hours following cessation of running.  Results provide insight into molecular events occuring during the early phase of adaptation to endurance training.

title: Post-traumatic stress disorder development
description: Expression profiling of peripheral mononuclear blood cells (PMBC) from patients with post-traumatic stress disorder. PMBC samples obtained from patients a few hours and 4 months after exposure to psychological stress.

title: Lung pneumocyte response to Pseudomonas aeruginosa type III secretion system mutants
description: Analysis of A549 lung pneumocytes after infection with Pseudomonas aeruginosa (PA) PAK mutants deleted for various components of the type III secretion system (TTSS).  Mutants in TTSS effectors and translocators studied.  PA causes serious respiratory infections in cystic fibrosis patients.

title: Hematopoietic stem cell engraftment in goat
description: Human-goat chimerism achieved by transplanting human CD34+Lin- cord blood cells into fetal goats. Markers indicate human genes expressed in goat liver and blood. Human/goat hematopoietic stem cell (HSC) xenogeneic model allows analysis of HSC transplantation, expansion and differentiation in vivo.

title: Sulfur mustard effect on lungs: dose response and time course
description: Analysis of lungs from Sprague Dawley males following injection with 1, 3, or 6 mg/kg of sulfur mustard (SM) bis-(2-chloroethyl) sulfide, a carcinogenic alkylating agent. Lungs examined at various time points up to 24 hours postinjection. Results provide insight into SM-induced lung injury.

title: Severe acute respiratory syndrome expression profile
description: Expression profiling of peripheral blood mononuclear cells (PBMC) from 10 adult patients with severe acute respiratory syndrome (SARS). Results provide insight into the host immune response to the SARS coronavirus.

title: IL-21 and IL-15 synergistic effect on naïve CD8+ T cells
description: Expression profiling of naïve CD8+ T cells stimulated with IL-15 or IL-21 or both cytokines for 4 hours.  100 ng/ml of each cytokine used.  Results provide insight into the synergistic effect of IL-21 and IL-15 on T cell homeostasis and effector functions.

title: Coxsackievirus B3 infection effect on hearts: time course
description: Expression profiling of hearts from 4 to 5 week old A/J males after infection with coxsackievirus B3 (CVB3).  Hearts examined at various time points up to 30 days postinfection.  CVB3 infection leads to cardiac inflammation and fibrosis within 9 days of infection.

title: fhl1 and ifh1 deletion mutants
description: Expression profiling of fhl1 single deletion mutant and ifh1 fhl1 double deletion mutant.  Mutants generated from W303 strain.  Results indicate that Ifh1p and Fhl1p function together to regulate the transcription of ribosomal protein genes.

title: Microglial cell response to interferon-gamma: time course
description: Expression profiling of microglial cells obtained from 4 different samples following treatment with 200 u/ml interferon-gamma (IFN-gamma).  Cells examined 1, 6, and 4 hours after treatment.  Results provide insight into the regulation of immune functions in microglia by IFN-gamma.

title: Embryonic lung side population CD45+ and CD45- cell comparison
description: Expression profiling of CD45+ and CD45- side population (SP) cells from embryonic 17.5-day lungs.  CD45+ and CD45- main population cells also examined.  Results provide insight into the role of CD45+ and CD45- SP cells in lung development.

title: Adenylate cyclase activator forskolin effect on pheochromocytoma cell line (RAE230A)
description: Expression profiling of PC12 pheochromocytoma cells treated with 10 uM forskolin for 1 hour. Forskolin activates adenylate cyclase.  Effect of 1,9 dideoxy forskolin, an inactive analog of forskolin, also examined. Results identify genes whose expression responds to changes in cAMP levels.

title: Adenylate cyclase activator forskolin effect on pheochromocytoma cell line (RAE230B)
description: Expression profiling of PC12 pheochromocytoma cells treated with 10 uM forskolin for 1 hour.  Forskolin activates adenylate cyclase.  Effect of 1,9 dideoxy forskolin, an inactive analog of forskolin, also examined.  Results identify genes whose expression responds to changes in cAMP levels.

title: Macrophage response to lipopolysaccharide: time course
description: Expression profiling of RAW264.7 macrophage cells exposed to 100 ng/ml of lipopolysaccharide (LPS) for 2 and 12 hours.  Macrophages secrete proinflammatory cytokines in response to LPS.  Results provide insight into trafficking and secretion of cytokines in macrophages.

title: Auxin signaling inhibitors effect on seedlings
description: Expression profiling of 7 day old Columbia-O seedlings treated for 1 hour with auxin and with either compound A or B. Both compounds identified in a screen for small chemical inhibitors of auxin signaling. Results provide insight into the regulation of the auxin-signaling network.

title: Vernalization independence vip5 and vip6 mutants
description: Expression profiling of 3 week old vernalization independence (VIP) vip5 and vip6 mutants.  VIP genes repress flowering by activating the MADSbox gene FLC.  Results provide insight into the role of VIP genes in flowering and development.

title: Lymphoblastoid cell lines from CEPH/Utah families
description: Expression profiling of lymphoblastoid cell lines from 15 CEPH/Utah families.  Cell lines from 3 generations examined.  Results provide insight into the heritability of gene expression traits in segregating human populations.

title: Terminal heart failure model
description: Expression profiling of left ventricles of 7 week old double transgenics overexpressing human angiotensin and renin. Double transgenics exhibiting cardiac hypertrophy compared to those exhibiting terminal heart failure with cachexia. Double transgenics treated with losartan also examined.

title: Valproic acid effect on theca cells (HG-U133A)
description: Analysis of normal theca cells treated with 500 uM valproic acid (VPA), an anti-epilipetic that induces polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS)-like symptoms. Theca cells from PCOS patients also examined. Results provide insight into the underlying mechanisms contributing to VPA-induced PCOS-like symptoms.

title: Valproic acid effect on theca cells (HG-U133B)
description: Analysis of normal theca cells treated with 500 uM valproic acid (VPA), an anti-epilipetic that induces polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS)-like symptoms. Theca cells from PCOS patients also examined. Results provide insight into the underlying mechanisms contributing to VPA-induced PCOS-like symptoms.

title: Growth hormone receptor mutants
description: Analysis of liver of 42 day old male mutants expressing growth hormone receptor (GHR) proteins truncated at amino acid residues 569 or 391. Receptors truncated at residue 569 have residues 539 and 545 replaced with phenylalanine. Results provide insight into the function of regions of GHR.

title: Iron deficiency effect on duodenum: time course (RAE230A)
description: Analysis of effect of dietary iron deprivation on duodenum. Sprague Dawleys examined at various post-natal ages up to 36 weeks. Results identify iron-responsive genes, which include those involved in intestinal iron transport, during the course of post-natal development.

title: Iron deficiency effect on duodenum: time course (RAE230B)
description: Analysis of effect of dietary iron deprivation on duodenum. Sprague Dawleys examined at various post-natal ages up to 36 weeks. Results identify iron-responsive genes, which include those involved in intestinal iron transport, during the course of post-natal development.

title: Type 1 diabetes model response to cyclophosphamide: time course
description: Analysis of pancreatic islets from BDC2.5/NOD transgenics after treatment with 200 mg/kg cyclophosphamide (CY) at various time points up to 3 days.  CY induces diabetes in BDC2.5/NOD transgenics.  Results provide insight into molecular events accompanying the progression from insulitis to diabetes.

title: Structural bone autograft and allograft comparison
description: Expression profiling of autografted and allografted femurs of 8 week old C57BL/6 animals. Allografts obtained from ICR animals and grafted onto C57BL/6 femurs. Bone remodeling and vascularization in autografts is superior to that in allografts. Results identify genes important in autograft healing.

title: Uterus response to 17beta-estradiol: time course
description: Analysis of uteri of immature 19 to 20 day old Alpk:APfCD-1 females given a single injection of 400 ug/kg 17beta-estradiol (E2). Gene expression examined at various time points up to 72 hours following treatment. Results provide insight into mechanisms underlying E2-induced uterine growth.

title: Acute myeloid leukemia response to chemotherapy
description: Analysis of mononuclear cells from 54 chemotherapy treated patients less than 15 years of age with acute myeloid leukemia (AML). Mononuclear cells taken from peripheral blood or bone marrow. Results identify expression patterns associated with complete remission and relapse with resistant disease.

title: Squamous cell carcinoma of the oral cavity with lymph node metastasis
description: Expression profiling of 18 primary squamous cell carcinomas of the oral cavity with or without lymph node metastasis. Expression in lymph node metastasis also examined. Results used to identify gene expression signature in primary tumors that indicates the presence of lymph node metastasis.

title: Primary effusion lymphomas and associated viral infections
description: Analysis of Kaposi's sarcoma-associated herpesvirus (KSHV) positive mononuclear cells from 3 patients with primary effusion lymphoma (PEL), 9 KSHV positive PEL cell lines, and 3 KSHV negative cell lines from lymphomatous effusions.  Effect of concomittant Epstein-Barr virus infection also examined.

title: Acute myeloid leukemia subclasses
description: Expression profiling of bone marrow from 43 patients with various forms of acute myeloid leukemia (AML): 10 promyelocytic leukemias with t(15;17), 4 AMLs with inv(16), 7 monocytic leukemias, and 22 nonmonocytic leukemias.  Results identify expression signatures unique to each AML subclass.

title: Mitochondrial encephalomyopathies associated with mitochondrial DNA mutations
description: Analysis of muscle from 12 patients with various forms of mitochondrial encephalomyopathies associated with mitochondrial DNA mutations: 8 patients with a A3243G mutation, and 4 patients with a 4977 base pair deletion. Results identify possible expression signature for mitochondrial disorders.

title: Plasma cell dyscrasias
description: Expression profiling of plasma cells from patients with plasma cell dyscrasias: 7 with monoclonal gammopathy of undetermined significance, 39 with multiple myeloma (MM), and 6 with plasma cell leukemia.  Results provide insight into the neoplastic transformation of plasma cells in MM.

title: Wing imaginal disc proneural cluster cells of the peripheral nervous system
description: Expression profiling of wing imaginal disc proneural cluster cells (PNCs) of the peripheral nervous system (PNS). PNS PNCs adopt the sensory organ precursor cell fate. PNCs purified by fluorescence-activated cell sorting. Results provide insight into the function of proneural genes in neurogenesis.

title: Platelet derived growth factor effect in the presence of Src family kinase inhibitors (MG-U74A)
description: Analysis of NIH3T3 fibroblasts treated with platelet-derived growth factor (PDGF) and one of several Src family kinase (SFK) small molecule inhibitors. Inhibitors of SFKs, MEK1/2, and phosphotidylinositol 3-kinase used. Results provide insight into the role of SFKs in PDGF signaling.

title: Platelet derived growth factor effect in the presence of Src family kinase inhibitors (MOE430A)
description: Analysis of NIH3T3 fibroblasts treated with platelet-derived growth factor (PDGF) and one of several Src family kinase (SFK) small molecule inhibitors. Inhibitors of SFKs, MEK1/2, and phosphotidylinositol 3-kinase used. Results provide insight into the role of SFKs in PDGF signaling.

title: Heat shock transcription factor 1 mutant response to heat stress
description: Analysis of a heat shock transcription factor 1 (HSF1) temperature sensitive mutant strain subjected to heat stress at 33 degrees C. HSF1 mutant contains an arginine to serine and a phenylalanine to serine substitution at residues 206 and 256 respectively. Results identify novel targets of HSF1.

title: AML1-ETO fusion protein effect on CD34+ hematopoietic cells
description: Analysis of CD34+ hematopoietic cells expressing the AML1-ETO fusion protein which is formed in acute myeloid leukemia (AML) from translocation t(8;21). CD34+ cells isolated from peripheral blood progenitor and cord blood cells. Results provide insight into the role of AML1-ETO in leukemogenesis.

title: Corticospinal motor neuron development
description: Analysis of corticospinal motor neurons (CSMN) of C57BL/6 at embryonic day 18 to postnatal day 14. CSMN degeneration contributes to amyotrophic lateral sclerosis. CSMN compared to callosal projection and corticotectal projection neurons. Results provide insight into CSMN development.

title: Hematopoietic stem cells from different recombinant inbred strains
description: Expression profiling of Lin- Sca-1+ c-kit+ hematopoietic stem cells (HSC) from 22 different BXD recombinant inbred (RI) strains. Each RI strain is homozygous for alleles at about 98% of loci. Results combined with QTL mapping to identify candidate genes for the control of HSC function.

title: E2F-1 overexpression effect on melanoma cells
description: Expression profiling of SKMEL-2 melanoma cells overexpressing the transcription factor E2F-1. E2F-1 overexpression induces apoptosis in many tumor cells. Results provide insight into the mechanisms underlying E2F-1 induced apoptosis in melanoma cells.

title: Age effect on myoblast progenitors
description: Analysis of primary myoblast progenitor (MP) cultures from 8 and 23 month old DBA/2JNIA females. MPs are responsible for the growth, repair, and maintenance of skeletal muscle. Results provide insight into age-related alterations in MP function that contribute to changes in muscle composition.

title: Manganese superoxide dismutase deficiency effect on hearts
description: Analysis of hearts from C57BL/6 mutants lacking manganese superoxide dismutase (MnSOD). MnSOD deficiency confined to heart and muscle. Mutants developed progressive congestive heart failure with dilated cardiomyopathy. Results provide insight into the effect of excess oxidative stress on the heart.

title: Brain, heart, and lung expression profiles of individuals from different natural populations
description: Analysis of brains, hearts, and lungs of 9 individuals, 3 each collected from Maine, New Jersey, and Georgia. 192 metabolic genes examined. Results provide insight into the variation in tissue-specific gene expression among outbred individuals and among different natural populations of a species.

title: Homeobox Dlx1/2 mutations effect on embryonic telencephalon
description: Expression profiling of cortex and basal ganglia from embryonic telencephalon of homozygous and heterozygous Dlx1/2 mutants. Mutants examined at embryonic day 14.5. Dlx homeobox transcription factors are implicated in regulating the function of inhibitory neurons.

title: Normal tissues of diverse types (SHBW)
description: Expression profiling of 115 samples from 35 different types of normal tissues. Samples obtained by surgery or autopsy, and evaluated by pathologists. Results provide insight into the molecular organization of diverse cell types, and provide a baseline for comparison to diseased tissues.

title: Normal tissues of diverse types (SHDP)
description: Expression profiling of 115 samples from 35 different types of normal tissues. Samples obtained by surgery or autopsy, and evaluated by pathologists. Results provide insight into the molecular organization of diverse cell types, and provide a baseline for comparison to diseased tissues.

title: NADH-cytochrome P450 reductase deletion effect on liver
description: Analysis of liver from male 3 month old hepatic NADH-cytochrome P450 reductase null mutants (POR). Results provide insight into the central role of POR and the P450 system in controlling hepatic homeostasis.

title: Estrogen receptor alpha/beta heterodimer action in response to estrogen and tamoxifen
description: Expression profiling of U2OS osteosarcoma cell line expressing estrogen receptor/alpha heterodimer after treatment with 10 nM 17beta-estradiol (E2) or 10 nM 4-OH tamoxifen (4HT) for 24 hours. Results provide insight into the role of estrogen receptor/alpha heterodimer in gene regulation.

title: Hematopoeitic stem cells of various types
description: Expression profiling of Lin-CD34-, Lin-CD34+, and Lin+CD34+ peripheral blood hematopoeitic stem cells (HSCs). Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the association of CD34 expression with self-renewal and lineage commitment in HSCs.

title: Normal tissues of various types
description: Expression profiling of 36 types of normal tissue. Each RNA tissue sample pooled from several donors.  Results identify tissue specific genes and provide baselines for interpreting gene expression in cancer.

title: Carbon source quality effect on gene expression
description: Analysis of MG1655 cells grown aerobically in several media each with a different carbon source.  Carbon sources used in decreasing order of quality were glucose, glycerol, succinate, L-alanine, acetate, and L-proline. Results provide insight into the response of cells to carbon source quality.

title: leu3 mutant expression profiles
description: Analysis of leu3 mutant grown in either limited ethanol or limited ammonium media. Leu3p regulates a gene involved in nitrogen assimilation and six genes involved in branched chain amino acid metabolism. Results provide insight into the role of Leu3p in gene regulation.

title: Anti-sigma factor ChrR deletion mutant expression profile
description: Expression profiling of anti-sigma factor ChrR deletion mutant grown aerobically in 30% oxygen. Binding of ChrR to sigma(E) blocks sigma(E)-dependent transcription.

title: Blastocyst response to various MAPK pathway inhibitors  (MOE430A)
description: Expression profiling of blastocysts following inhibition of JNK, p38 MAPK, or ERK signaling. JNK, p38 MAPK, and ERK signaling inhibited by SP600125, SB203580, and U0126 respectively. Results provide insight into the role of MAPK pathways in preimplantation development.

title: Blastocyst response to various MAPK pathway inhibitors (MOE430B)
description: Expression profiling of blastocysts following inhibition of JNK, p38 MAPK, or ERK signaling. JNK, p38 MAPK, and ERK signaling inhibited by SP600125, SB203580, and U0126 respectively. Results provide insight into the role of MAPK pathways in preimplantation development.

title: Blastocyst response to various MAPK pathway inhibitors (MOE430 2.0)
description: Expression profiling of blastocysts following inhibition of JNK, p38 MAPK, or ERK signaling. JNK, p38 MAPK, and ERK signaling inhibited by SP600125, SB203580, and U0126 respectively. Results provide insight into the role of MAPK pathways in preimplantation development.

title: Patched heterozygous model of medulloblastoma
description: Analysis of granule cell precursors, pre-neoplastic cells, and tumor cells obtained from 7 day old, 6 week old, and 10 to 25 week old patched heterozygous animals, respectively. Results provide insight into the mechanisms of pathogenesis of medulloblastoma at the early stage.

title: RNA binding protein HuD overexpression effect on hippocampus
description: Analysis of hippocampus of 60 day old C57BL/6 males overexpressing the RNA binding protein HuD. HuD overexpressor mice exhibit learning deficits and abnormalities in prepulse inhibition.

title: Glaucomatous astrocytes from the optic nerve head
description: Expression profiling of astrocytes taken from the optic nerve head (ONH) of patients with glaucoma. The ONH is the site of damage in glaucomatous optic neuropathy. Studies suggest that damage in glaucoma is mediated by reactive astrocytes.

title: CD4+ T cells expressing transcription factor Foxp3 and various amounts of CD25
description: Analysis of CD4+/CD25lo, CD4+/CD25+, and CD4+/CD25hi T cells expressing the forkhead transcription factor Foxp3. FACS used to sort CD4+ cells based on Foxp3 GFP fusion protein and CD25 expression. Results provide insight into the role of Foxp3 in regulatory T cell development and function.

title: Genetic variation in gene expression among parents and progenies
description: Expression profiling of parental strains and haploid progenies from a cross of strain BY4716 and the wild wine strain RM11-1a. Results used to find linkage between gene expression levels, which are treated as quantitative traits, and genetic markers.

title: Genetic variation in gene expression among parents and progenies (dye-swap)
description: Expression profiling of parental strains and haploid progenies from a cross of strain BY4716 and the wild wine strain RM11-1a. Results used to find linkage between gene expression levels, which are treated as quantitative traits, and genetic markers.

title: Lung cancer cell line response to motexafin gadolinium: time course
description: Expression profiling of lung cancer cell line A549 following treatment with 50 uM of the metal cation-containing chemotherapeutic drug motexafin gadolinium (MGd). Cells examined at 4, 12, and 24 hours following treatment. Results provide insight into the mechanism of action of MGd.

title: Ssl1 mutant for a subunit of TFIIH response to methyl methanesulfonate
description: Analysis of Ssl1 mutant for a subunit of TFIIH treated with methyl methanesulfonate (MMS). Ssl1 mutant contains C406A substitution and is sensitive to DNA damaging agents such as MMS. Results provide insight into the relationship between transcription and DNA repair.

title: Sarcoma and hypoxia
description: Expression profiling of soft tissue sarcoma samples. Hypoxic regions often develop in tumors as they increase in size. Results provide insight into the expression of hypoxia-related genes in sarcomas.

title: Gastric cancer
description: Expression profiling of 22 primary advanced gastric cancer tissues. Whole gastric cancer tissues examined in the presence of metastasis and according to histological type. Results provide insight into the progression and diversity of gastric cancer.

title: mTert overexpression
description: Expression profiling of embryonic fibroblasts overexpressing mTert, the catalytic subunit of telomerase. Results identify potential downstream targets of telomerase.

title: Tumor necrosis factor effect in the absence of NF-kappaB activity: time course
description: Temporal analysis of the effect of tumor necrosis factor (TNF)  on gene expression in HeLa cells with NF-kappaB inactivated. NF-kappaB inactivated with 2 ug/ml doxycycline. Cells examined at various time points following stimulation with 25 ng/ml TNF. Results identify potential targets of NF-kappaB.

title: Intermittent hypoxia effect on liver
description: Examination of chronic intermittent hypoxia (CIH) effect on liver gene expression in leptin deficient (ob/ob) mice. CIH in the presence of pre-existent obesity may cause an increase in gene expression of enzymes of lipid biosynthesis. CIH is a component of obstructive sleep apnea (OSA).

title: rnt1 null mutant expression profile
description: Expression profiling of isogenic strains lacking Rnt1p, a member of the RNase III family of double-stranded RNA endonucleases. Results identify potential Rnt1p mRNA targets.

title: Acute myeloblastic leukemia cells response to all trans retinoic acid and valproic acid
description: Analysis of acute myeloblastic leukemia (AML) cell line, OCI/AML-2, following treatment with valproic acid (VPA) and all trans retinoic acid (ATRA). VPA inhibits histone deacetylase. Results provide insight into the responsiveness of AML cells to ATRA when VPA is present.

title: Insulin receptor substrate inactivation effect on brown preadipocytes
description: Expression profiling of brown preadipocytes derived from insulin receptor substrate (IRS) knockout animals.The IRS family of insulin signaling mediators is composed of IRS-1, IRS-2, IRS-3, and IRS-4. Results provide insight into the regulation of brown adipocyte differentiation.

title: Malignant pleural mesothelioma
description: Expression profiling of malignant pleural mesothelioma (MPM) tumors. MPM is a highly lethal malignancy associated with asbestos exposure. Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of MPM.

title: Chronic myelogenous leukemia response to imatinib
description: Analysis of peripheral blood and bone marrow of chronic myelogenous leukemia (CML) patients prior to imatinib (Gleevec) treatment. Imatinib induces complete cytogenetic response (CCR) in most CML patients. This study attempts to determine transcriptional signature of imatinib non-responders.

title: Mammary tumorigenesis in MMTV-neu model
description: Analysis of cancer progression by profiling of preneoplastic mammary glands and tumors of MMTV-neu animals. Activated neu allele placed under the control of mammary tumor virus promoter to enable mammary specific expression. Results provide insight into the early events of Neu induced tumorigenesis.

title: White adipose tissue remodeling: response to β3-adrenergic receptor activation
description: Temporal analysis of epididymal white adipose tissue of 3-4 month old males treated with β3-adrenergic receptor (Adrb3) agonist CL-316,243 for 0 to 6 days. Adrb3 agonists exert anti-diabetes and anti-obesity properties.

title: White adipose tissue remodeling: role of peroxisome proliferator-activated receptor alpha
description: Temporal analysis of epididymal white adipose tissue during remodeling induced by the β3-adrenergic receptor (Adrb3) agonist CL-316,243 in peroxisome proliferator-activated receptor alpha (Ppara) knockouts. Ppara is upregulated by CL-316,243.

title: Dietary supplement Boswellia serrata effects on liver
description: Hepatic gene expression analysis in Swiss-Webster mice fed diet supplemented with hexane or methanol extracts of Boswellia serrata for 21 days. Extracts from Boswellia serrata may have anti-inflammatory activity.

title: Heart failure and nitric oxide
description: Analysis of hearts from 21 month old endothelial nitric oxide synthase (eNOS) knockout males. These animals exhibit cardiac dysfunction with age and 50% mortality at 21 month. Results provide clues to molecular mechanisms leading to heart failure.

title: Hematopoietic stem cell and progenitor cell comparison (HG-U133A)
description: Comparison of CD34+CD33-CD38-Rho(lo)c-kit+ cells, enriched for hematopoietic stem/progenitor cells (HSC), to CD34+CD33-CD38-Rho(hi) cells, enriched for committed hematopoietic progenitor cells (HPC). Cells obtained from umbilical cord blood and bone marrow. Provides insight into control of HSC fate.

title: Hematopoietic stem cell and progenitor cell comparison (HG-U133B)
description: Comparison of CD34+CD33-CD38-Rho(lo)c-kit+ cells, enriched for hematopoietic stem/progenitor cells (HSC), to CD34+CD33-CD38-Rho(hi) cells, enriched for committed hematopoietic progenitor cells (HPC). Cells obtained from umbilical cord blood and bone marrow. Provides insight into control of HSC fate.

title: Liver X receptor alpha increase effect on livers of LDLR knockouts fed a high-cholesterol high-fat diet
description: Analysis of the effect of increasing liver X receptor (LXR) alpha in livers of low-density lipoprotein receptor (LDLR) knockouts fed a high-cholesterol, high-fat diet. LXR alpha improves the serum lipid profile of LDLR nulls fed the unhealthy diet. Effect of T0901317, an LXR alpha agonist, examined.

title: Dysferlin deficiency effect on proximal and distal muscles
description: Comparison of the proximal quadriceps femoris muscle to the distal tibialis anterior muscle of 3 week old dysferlin deficient mutants. Dysferlin mutations can result in the neuromuscular disorders Limb-Girdle muscular dystrophy type 2B and Myoshi myopathy.

title: Fibroblast growth factor receptor 3 K650E mutation for type II thanatophoric dysplasia
description: Analysis of PC12 cells expressing fibroblast growth factor receptor 3 (FGFR3) K650E mutant responsible for thanatophoric dysplasia (TD) type II. Mutant receptor expressed as a chimera of FGFR3 and platelet derived growth factor receptor. Results provide insight into TD type II pathogenesis.

title: Pediatric acute lymphoblastic leukemia subtypes
description: Expression profiling of bone marrow from pediatric patients with acute lymphoblastic leukemia (ALL). 10 B-cell ALL, 5 T-cell ALL, and 3 B-cell ALL, with the MLL/AF4 chromosomal rearrangement, patients examined. Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of childhood ALL.

title: Huntingtin exon 1 protein overexpression
description: Analysis of Htt14A2.5 cell line expressing a truncated form of huntingtin (Htt) exon 1 protein controlled by a promoter inducible by ponasterone (PA). Expression examined 48 hours after treatment with 5 uM PA. Htt expression in Htt14A2.5 results in protein aggregation.

title: Promyelocytic cell response to Anaplasma phagocytophilum infection
description: Expression profiling of NB4 promyelocytic leukemic cells infected with Anaplasma phagocytophilum, an obligate intracellular bacterium that causes granulocytic anaplasmosis. NB4 is a model for neutrophil maturation. Results provide insight into host cellular pathways affected by A. phagocytophilum.

title: Spinal cord contusion
description: Expression profiling of contused spinal cords of Fischer animals. Spinal cords examined 35 days following contusion at the thoracic 8 segment. Results identify potential targets for therapeutic intervention following spinal cord injury.

title: Inflammatory lung injury and effect of simvastatin
description: Analysis of effect of simvastatin in LPS-induced inflammatory model of acute lung injury. Male C57BL/6J administered simvastatin 24 hours prior to and concomitant with LPS. Simvastatin is a 3-hydroxy-3-methylglutaryl (HMG)-CoA reductase inhibitor that mediates endothelial cell barrier protection.

title: Ventilator-induced lung injury (mouse)
description: Investigation of deleterious effects of mechanical ventilation (MV) on lung gene expression in model of ventilator-induced lung injury. MV, a treatment of acute lung injury, can augment injury in some patients.

title: Ventilator-induced lung injury (rat)
description: Investigation of deleterious effects of mechanical ventilation (MV) on lung gene expression in model of ventilator-induced lung injury. MV, a treatment of acute lung injury, can augment injury in some patients.

title: Neuroblastoma differentiation induced by retinoic acid: time course
description: Temporal analysis of neuroblastoma Neuro2a cell differentiation induced by retinoic acid. Gene expression examined at several time points up to 24 hours following treatment with 20 uM all-trans-retinoic acid. Provides insight into the role of mKIAA genes in the early stages of neurite outgrowth.

title: Phosgene effect on lungs: time course
description: Analysis of lungs exposed to the toxic industrial compound carbonyl chloride (phosgene). Phosgene exposure results in pulmonary edema and acute lung injury. Lungs examined at several time points up to 72 hours after exposure. Provides insight into molecular events affected in phosgene-injured lungs.

title: GATA-1 knockdown effect on magakaryocytes
description: Analysis of megakaryocytes lacking the transcription factor GATA-1. GATA-1 is required for the development of megakaryocytes and erythroid cells. Megakaryocytes obtained from 13.5 day C57BL/6 mutant embryos. Results provide insight into the role of GATA-1 in megakaryopoiesis.

title: Dysferlin deficiency effect on skeletal and cardiac muscles
description: Comparison of skeletal and cardiac muscles of dysferlin deficient SJL/J animals. Dysferlin deficiency results in skeletal muscle weakness, but does not affect the heart. Dysferlin mutations can result in the neuromuscular disorders Limb-Girdle muscular dystrophy type 2B and Myoshi myopathy.

title: Telomere dysfunction effect on male germ cells
description: Expression profiling of male germ cells lacking the telomerase RNA component, Terc, or the DNA repair/telomere binding protein, Ku86, or both. Germ cells obtained from seminiferous tubules of 3 to 5 month old males. Results identify processes affected by dysfunctional telomeres.

title: Toll-like receptor agonists synergistic effect on dendritic cells: time course
description: Temporal analysis of monocyte-derived dendritic cells (DCs) treated with lipopolysaccharide (LPS), an agonist for toll-like receptor (TLR) 4, the synthetic imidazoquinoline resiquimod R848, an agonist for TLR8, or both. Provides insight into the synergistic effect of TLR agonists in activating DCs.

title: Atypical ductal hyperplasia and breast cancer
description: Comparison of atypical ductal hyperplasia (ADH) tissues from patients with and without a history of breast cancer. Incidence of invasive breast cancer is high in ADH patients. Results identify putative markers of invasive breast cancer.

title: Acute hypotension effect on kidneys
description: Expression profiling of kidneys of 12 week old normotensive Wistar-Kyoto males subjected to acute hypotension by withdrawing 3 ml of blood. Results provide insight into vasoregulatory mechanisms and the genetics and physiology of blood pressure regulation.

title: Idiopathic pulmonary fibrosis
description: Expression profiling of lung tissues from patients with idiopathic pulmonary fibrosis (IPF), a progressive and lethal disorder characterized by the abnormal formation of fibrous scar tissue in the lungs. Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of IPF.

title: Pituitary adenoma subtypes
description: Expression profiling of 4 pituitary adenoma subtypes. Growth hormone (GH), prolactin (PRL), and adrenocorticotrophin (ACTH) secreting pituitary adenomas, and non-functioning pituitary adenoma examined. 5 specimens pooled and examined for each subtype. Results provide insight into tumor pathogenesis.

title: SOCS3 inactivation effect on embryonic stem cells
description: Expression profiling of embryonic stems (ES) cells deleted for SOCS3, a regulator of cytokine signaling. SOCS3 null ES cells derived from blastocysts of SOCS3 heterozygous mutants. Results provide insight into the role of SOCS3 in ES cell biology.

title: Hexamethylene diisocyanate effect on lungs: time course
description: Analysis of lungs from C57BL/6J males exposed to hexamethylene diisocyanate biuret trimer (HDI-BT) for 5 hours. HDI-BT is a major component of polyurethane spray paints and HDI-BT inhalation is a cause of occupational lung disease. Lungs examined at various time points up to 90 hours after exposure.

title: IFN-gamma inflammatory effect on bronchial epithelial cells modulated by dexamethasone: time course
description: Analysis of bronchial epithelial cells treated with interferon (IFN) gamma, or dexamethasone (dex), or both. IFN-gamma plays a role in lung inflammatory responses and corticosteroids such as dex are used as treatments for inflammation. Cells examined 8 or 24 hours after treatment.

title: Sickle cell plasma effect on pulmonary artery endothelial cells (HG-U133A)
description: Expression profiling of pulmonary artery endothelial cells exposed to plasma from sickle cell disease (SCD) patients with sickle acute chest syndrome or from SCD patients at steady state. Results provide insight into the role of extra-erythrocytic factors in sickle cell vasoocclusion.

title: Sickle cell plasma effect on pulmonary artery endothelial cells (HG-U133B)
description: Expression profiling of pulmonary artery endothelial cells exposed to plasma from sickle cell disease (SCD) patients with sickle acute chest syndrome or from SCD patients at steady state. Results provide insight into the role of extra-erythrocytic factors in sickle cell vasoocclusion.

title: GH/IGF-1 signaling disruption and caloric restriction additive effect
description: Analysis of livers from growth hormone/insulin-like growth factor-1 signaling defective Ames dwarfs (DF) subjected to caloric restriction (CR). DF and CR in combination additively extend life span. Results provide insight into the mechanisms underlying this additive effect.

title: Dukes B colon cancer recurrence
description: Expression profiling of previously resected frozen primary tumors from patients with Dukes' stage B colon cancer that recurred in 5 years. Results identify potential prognostic markers for tumor relapse.

title: Left ventricular hypertrophy in spontaneously hypertensive model: time course
description: Analysis of progressive left ventricular hypertrophy (LVH) in spontaneously hypertensive (SHR) males at 12, 16, and 20 months of age. LVH impairs diastolic relaxation, which decreases cardiac output and leads to heart failure (HF). Provides insight into pathogenesis of hypertrophy and LV remodeling.

title: Oocyte development (MOE430A)
description: Analysis of oocytes from follicles at the primordial to large antral stages of development, collected from B6SJLF1 animals at 2 to 22 days of age. Provides insight into the development of eggs of high meiotic and developmental competence.

title: Oocyte development (MOE430B)
description: Analysis of oocytes from follicles at the primordial to large antral stages of development, collected from B6SJLF1 animals at 2 to 22 days of age. Provides insight into the development of eggs of high meiotic and developmental competence.

title: Cigarette smoking effect on alveolar macrophage
description: Analysis of alveolar macrophages from 15 cigarette smokers, 15 non-smokers and 15 asthmatics. Results suggest that alveolar macrophage activation induced by smoking contributes to emphysema.

title: SPT10 global transcription regulator null mutant
description: Expression profiling of mutants lacking Spt10p. Spt10p binds the upstream activating sequences in all major core histone promoters. Results provide insight into the mechanism by which Spt10p acts as a global regulator of transcription.

title: Macrophage response to viral infection
description: Analysis of macrophages from C57BL/6J males infected with Sendai virus (SeV). Macrophages avoid virus-induced death and remove virus-infected, apoptotic cells. Provides insight into the mechanism controlling the viability of macrophages in viral infections.

title: Luteinizing hormone overexpression effect on mammary gland
description: Analysis of thoracic mammary gland from luteinizing hormone (LH) overexpressing transgenic virgins at 16 weeks of age. LH overexpression results in the development of spontaneous mammary tumors in the absence of p53 mutations.

title: Amoxicillin effect on small intestine and colon development: time course
description: Analysis of small intestine and colon of Sprague-Dawleys treated with 100 mg/kg/day of amoxicillin from 7 days of age until day 17 or day 21. Results provide insight into the effect of antibiotics on gut barrier function maturation.

title: Vitamin A deficiency effect on liver
description: Analysis of liver of 74 day old Sprague-Dawley males fed a vitamin A (retinol) deficient diet for 53 days. The liver is the major storage organ for vitamin A, is involved in vitamin A homeostasis, and expresses retinoic acid-regulated transcription factors.

title: 17beta-estradiol and genistein effect on thymus: time course
description: Analysis of thymus of ovariectomized C57BL/6 treated with 17beta-estradiol (estrogen; E2) or genistein, an E2 analog. Thymus tissue examined at various intervals up to 6 days after treatment. Provides insight into E2-mediated regulation of thymic development and immune function.

title: Inflammatory lung injury and mechanical ventilation
description: Analysis of lungs of C57BL/6 based model of lung inflammation and injury. The model develops acute lung injury (ALI) after concurrent exposure to low-dose lipopolysaccharide (LPS) and mechanical ventilation (MV). MV may contribute to ALI in critically ill patients.

title: Obliterative bronchiolitis and  tracheal allograft
description: Analysis of tracheal grafts from BALB/c donors transplanted into MHC incompatible C57BL/6 recipients. Allografts examined up to 25 days after transplantation. Provides insight into pathogensis of allograft rejection and associated obliterative bronchiolitis development.

title: Age effect on laryngeal muscle
description: Expression profiling of laryngeal posterior cricoarytenoid muscle from animals 6, 18, and 30 months of age. Results provide insight into the effect of age and sarcopenia on non-locomotive muscles.

title: Age effect on extraocular muscles
description: Expression profiling of extraocular muscle (EOM) from animals 6, 18, and 30 months of age. Extensor digitorum longus (EDL) muscles also examined. Results provide insight into the effect of age on EOM.

title: Age effect on central and peripheral nervous systems
description: Comparison of gene expression in the oculomotor nucleus (OMN) to that in the spinal cord. Animals 6, 18, and 30 months of age examined. Provides insight into the mechanisms underlying the divergent effects of age on the central and peripheral nervous systems.

title: Clear cell sarcoma of the kidney
description: Expression profiling of clear cell sarcoma of the kidney (CCSK). Wilms' tumors and fetal kidney control samples also examined. Objective is to reveal diagnostic markers and insight into the pathogenesis of CCSK.

title: Multiple myeloma molecular classification
description: Analysis of CD138+ plasma cells purified from bone marrow of multiple myeloma (MM) patients. Results used to classify MM cases into translocation/cyclin (TC) groups based on cyclin D expression and presence of translocations in the immunoglobulin heavy chain locus at 14q32.

title: Macrophage response to lipopolysaccharide and CstF-64 overexpression
description: Analysis of RAW 264.7 macrophages treated with 100 ng/ml lipopolysaccharide (LPS) for 18 hours, or overexpressing polyadenylation factor CstF-64. LPS treatment increases CstF-64 expression. Results provide insight into post-transcriptional mechanisms affected by LPS in macrophages.

title: Esophageal cell response to low pH: time course
description: Analysis of esophageal cell line SKGT4 following exposure to low pH 6.5. Cells examined at various time points up to 2 hours following exposure. Results provide insight into role of gastric acid in pathogenesis of gastro-esophageal reflux disease (GORD) and esophagus adenocarcinoma.

title: Bone mineral density and circulating monocytes
description: Comparison of circulating monocytes from pre- and postmenopausal females with low or high bone mineral density (BMD). Circulating monocytes are progenitors of osteoclasts, and produce factors important to bone metabolism. Results provide insight into the role of monocytes in osteoporosis.

title: Mesenchymal precursor cells derived from embryonic stem cells
description: Comparison of mesenchymal stem cells (MSC) and undifferentiated embryonic stem cells (ESC). ESC plated on a monolayer of OP9 stromal cells in the presence of 20% heat inactivated fetal bovine serum in alpha MEM medium to induce differentiation into MSC.

title: TNFalpha effect on epidermal keratinocytes in the presence of NF-kappa B inhibitor: time course
description: Analysis of epidermal keratinocytes treated with TNFalpha in the presence of 10 uM parthenolide, an NF-kappa B inhibitor. Cells examined at various time points up to 48 hours following TNFalpha treatment. Results identify NF-kappa B-dependent subset of TNFalpha-regulated genes.

title: CD4+ lymphocyte polarization into Th1 and Th2 cells in the presence of TGFbeta: time course (HG-U95A)
description: Analysis of CD4+ lymphocyte induced to differentiate into Th1 and Th2 by treatment with IL-12 and IL-4 respectively in the presence of TGFbeta. Cells examined at various time points up to 48 hours after treatment. Results provide insight into the mechanisms regulating CD4+ cell polarization.

title: Spinal cord injury effect on supraspinal tracts: time course (RG-U34A)
description: Temporal analysis of Sprague-Dawley males subjected to moderate spinal cord injury (SCI) at vertebral T9. Raphe magnus and sensorimotor cortex examined at various time points up to 3 months following trauma. Analysis of areas indirectly affected by injury helps understanding the mechanisms of SCI.

title: Spinal cord injury effect on supraspinal tracts: time course (RG-U34B)
description: Temporal analysis of Sprague-Dawley males subjected to moderate spinal cord injury (SCI) at vertebral T9. Raphe magnus and sensorimotor cortex examined at various time points up to 3 months following trauma. Analysis of areas indirectly affected by injury helps understanding the mechanisms of SCI.

title: Spinal cord injury effect on supraspinal tracts: time course (RG-U34C)
description: Temporal analysis of Sprague-Dawley males subjected to moderate spinal cord injury (SCI) at vertebral T9. Raphe magnus and sensorimotor cortex examined at various time points up to 3 months following trauma. Analysis of areas indirectly affected by injury helps understanding the mechanisms of SCI.

title: Lethal congenital contracture syndrome
description: Analysis of spinal cord from fetuses with lethal congenital contracture syndrome (LCCS). LCCS is autosomal recessive, causes death in 32nd gestational week, and involves degeneration of anterior horn motor neurons in spinal cord. Results provide insight into pathways active in motoneuron disease.

title: Fibroblast adipogenesis induced by EBF-1 and PPARgamma2 overexpression: time course
description: Analysis of NIH-3T3 embryonic fibroblasts induced to differentiate into adipocytes by overexpression of early B cell factor (EBF)-1 or peroxisome proliferator-activated receptor (PPAR)gamma2 transcription factors. Cells examined at various time points up to 10 days following overexpression.

title: Genotoxic stress
description: Analysis of BY4730 cells treated with DNA-reactive compounds cisplatin, methyl methanesulfonate (MMS), and bleomycin to induce genotoxic stress. Effect of genotoxic compounds compared to cytotoxic compounds, NaCl and ethanol. Results identify an expression signature unique to genotoxic stress.

title: Hyperlipidemic model of adaptive immunity in aorta during atherogenesis
description: Expression profiling of 32 week old aorta in an apolipoprotein  E deficient (apoE(-/-)) strain.  Results provide insight into a major site of immune cell accumulation during atherosclerosis progression.

title: Cardiovascular response to chronic voluntary exercise
description: Expression profiling of the aorta of spontaneously hypertensive (SHR) females after 5 weeks of wheel-cage running. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying improved cardiovascular health associated with exercise.

title: 2,3,7,8-tetrachlorodibenzo-p-dioxin effect on cardiovascular development
description: Analysis of gestational day (GD) 17.5 fetal hearts isolated from pregnant C57BL/6Ns treated at GD 14.5 with up to 6.0 ug/kg 2,3,7,8-tetrachlorodibenzo-p-dioxin (TCDD). TCDD, a cardiovascular teratogen, inhibits cardiomyocyte proliferation, a process that peaks between GD 14.5 to 17.5.

title: Aldosterone effect on heart: time course
description: Analysis of heart from C57BL/6 males injected with 10 ug/kg aldosterone. Hearts examined at various time points up to 12 hours after injection. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying the adverse effects of aldosterone on the heart.

title: Cigarette smoking effect on small airway epithelium
description: Analysis of phenotypically normal 10th to 12th order small airway bronchial epithelia from cigarette smokers. Cigarette smoking is the most common cause of chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD). Results provide insight into the early pathogenesis of COPD.

title: Pax6 mutation effect on brain development
description: Analysis of forebrain and hindbrain of Small eye homozygous Pax6 mutants at embryonic day 12.5. Pax6 is a transcription factor important in the development of the brain, where it affects cell fate, cell proliferation, and patterning. Results identify targets of Pax6 in the developing brain.

title: MAP kinase activation effect on heart: time course
description: Analysis of adult hearts after induction of activated transgene mutants of Ras, MKK3, or MKK7, which are specific upstream activators of the MAP kinases ERK, p38, and JNK respectively. Hearts examined at various time points up to 4 weeks following each transgene induction using tamoxifen.

title: Various high fat diets effect on liver
description: Expression profiling of liver from Wistar males fed for 12 weeks with one of 4 different high fat diets, each differing in fatty acid composition. The different fat sources used were lard, olive oil, coconut fat, and cod liver oil.

title: Myotube response to hydrogen peroxide
description: Expression profiling of myotubes following treatment with hydrogen peroxide at various concentrations up to 1000 uM. Myotubes derived from C2C12 myoblasts. Results provide insight into the response of muscle to reactive oxygen species.

title: Neonatal mononuclear cell response to lipopolysaccharide
description: Analysis of neonatal mononuclear cells from cord blood incubated with 5 ug/ml lipopolysaccharide (LPS). Effect of LPS on adult mononuclear cells from peripheral blood compared. Results provide insight into the molecular basis for increased susceptibility of neonates to sepsis.

title: Age effect on lipopolysaccharide-induced neuroinflammation and sickness behavior
description: Analysis of aged brain after activation of the peripheral innate immune system by intraperitoneal injection of E. coli lipopolysaccharide (LPS).  Results provide insight into molecular events underlying severe behavioral deficits (delirium) common in older adults with systemic infections.

title: Squamous lung cancer
description: Expression profiling of squamous lung cancer biopsy specimens and paired normal specimens from 5 patients. Differentially expressed genes integrated with protein interaction maps. Results suggest that differentially expressed genes are highly connected through protein interactions.

title: GFAP-negative lamina cribrosa cell response to TGF-beta1
description: Analysis of glial fibrillary acidic acid (GFAP)-negative lamina cribrosa (LC) glial cell response to 10 ng/ml TGF-beta1 for 24 hours. This is a model for primary open-angle glaucoma (POAG) in which TGF-beta levels are elevated in human LC tissue.

title: Malignant melanoma cell lines
description: Expression profiling of MelJUSO, A375, 607B, 518A2, and Skmel 28 malignant melanoma cell lines. Results correlated with regions of chromosomal breakpoints, and indicate an association between chromosomal breakpoints and altered gene expression.

title: Immune response to suppressive vs. stimulatory immunomodulators
description: Analysis of bone marrow-derived dendritic cells (DC) treated with lipid-transfected, double-stranded DNA or CpG oligonucleotides for 4 hours.  Double-stranded DNA is an immunosuppressive agent (ISD), CpG oligo an immunostimulant.  Results provide insight into differential immune response.

title: GATA-1 variant role in Down syndrome megakaryocytic leukemias
description: Analysis of megakaryocytes and their progenitors from mutant E12.5 embryo liver expressing truncated transcription factor GATA-1. Results provide insight into the role of variant GATA-1 (GATA1s) in megakaryocyte hyperproliferation and Down syndrome (DS)-associated leukemias (TMD, DS-AMKL/DS-AML M7).

title: Umbilical vein endothelial cell response to shear stress and intraluminal pressure
description: Analysis of endothelial cells (HUVEC) isolated from umbilical veins subjected to high shear stress or high intraluminal pressure. Umbilical veins exposed to each stimuli using a vascular ex vivo perfusion system. Results suggests that response to shear stress differs from response to pressure.

title: Hormone-sensitive lipase inactivation effect on muscle
description: Expression profiling of soleus muscle from females lacking the hormone-sensitive lipase (HSL) gene. HSL is a key enzyme in fatty acid mobilization in adipocytes and found to be active in skeletal muscle. Results provide insight into the role of HSL in muscle lipid metabolism.

title: Lineage-specific regulatory network specified by PAL-1
description: Various C blastomere mutant embryos analyzed to deconvolve C blastomere lineage-specific expression patterns specified by the PAL-1 homeodomain protein. Embryonic tissue examined at various time points from the 4-cell stage (0 minutes) to 186 minutes.

title: Scott syndrome B lymphoblast response to calcium ionophore
description: Analysis of Scott B lymphoblasts after calcium ionophore A23187 treatment. Lymphoblasts derived from a patient with Scott syndrome, a hemorrhagic disease. Results provide insight into the mechanisms underlying the apoptotic effect of A23187, and susceptibility of Scott B lymphoblasts to apoptosis.

title: Barrett's metaplasia progression to adenocarcinoma
description: Expression profiling of normal esophageal epithelium, premalignant Barrett's metaplasia, and esophageal adenocarcinoma samples. Tissue samples of each type obtained from 8 patients by transhiatal esophagectomy. Results identify potential markers of disease progression.

title: Hair follicle and skin molecular signatures
description: Comparison of hair follicle matrix, outer root sheath, dermal papilla cells, melanocytes, and a dermal fraction enriched in fibroblasts were FACS-isolated from 4 day old Lef1-RFP/K14-H2BGFP backskins. Contributes to molecular dissection of mesenchymal-epithelial interactions in the hair follicle.

title: T-cell acute lymphoblastic leukemia with CALM-AF10 fusion
description: Analysis of T-cell acute lymphoblastic leukemia (ALL) samples containing t(10;11)(p13;q14-21) translocation that fuses the clathrin-assembly protein-like lymphoid-myeloid leukemia gene CALM to the transcription factor AF10. Results provide insight into the consequences of CALM-AF10 expression.

title: Telomerase reverse transcriptase overexpression effect on CD4+ lymphocytes
description: Analysis of CD4+ T cells overexpressing green fluorescent protein telomerase reverse transcriptase fusion protein (GFP-hTERT). hTERT encodes catalytic reverse transcriptase subunit of telomerase. Provides insight into long-term consequences of hTERT overexpression in T lymphocytes.

title: Breast cancer cells reexpressing estrogen receptor alpha response to 17beta-estradiol
description: Analysis of the response of estrogen receptor (ER) negative MDA-MB-231 breast cancer cells infected with full-length ER alpha adenoviral constructs to treatment with 17beta-estradiol (E2). Results provide insight into the anti-proliferative effect of E2 on breast cancer cells reexpressing ER.

title: Lens epithelial and lens cortical fiber cell comparison
description: Comparison of lens epithelial cells to lens cortical fiber cells. Cells microdissected from lenses of post mortem donors. Results identify genes that may play roles in maintaining the specialized functions of each cell type and provides insight into potential mechanisms of lens cell differentiation.

title: Asthma model of prostaglandin E receptor EP3 effect on allergic inflammation
description: Analysis of lung treated with prostaglandin E2 (PGE2) receptor subtype EP3 agonist, ONO-AE-248 (AE-248), after ovalbumin (OVA)-sensitization and challenge. OVA induces allergic asthma. Results identify inhibitory role of PGE2-EP3 pathway in allergic inflammation and allergy-related gene expression.

title: Molecular apocrine breast tumors
description: Analysis of tumors of 49 breast cancer patients. Tumors classified into luminal and basal classes, and a novel molecular apocrine class. Apocrine tumors are estrogen receptor negative (ER-) and androgen receptor positive (AR+), while luminal tumors are ER+ and AR+, and basal tumors are ER- and AR-.

title: Crohn disease and ulcerative colitis comparison
