description: Expression profiling of mucosal biopsy samples from sigmoid colons of 10 patients with Crohn disease (CD) and 10 patients with ulcerative colitis (UC). CD and UC are two forms of inflammatory bowel disease. Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of CD and UC.

title: Huntington's disease: peripheral blood expression profile (HG-U133A)
description: Analysis of blood samples of 5 presymptomatic and 12 symptomatic Huntington's disease (HD) patients. Studies suggest that gene expression may be altered in a variety of tissues in HD, including peripheral blood. Results identify potential markers for HD.

title: Huntington's disease: peripheral blood expression profile (Codelink Uniset 20K)
description: Analysis of blood samples of 5 presymptomatic and 12 symptomatic Huntington's disease (HD) patients. Studies suggest that gene expression may be altered in a variety of tissues in HD, including peripheral blood. Results identify potential markers for HD.

title: Duchenne Muscular Dystrophy response to oxandrolone (HG-U133A)
description: Analysis of gastrocnemius muscle biopsy specimens from Duchenne muscular dystrophy (DMD) patients before and after 3 months of treatment with 0.1mg/kg/day oxandrolone, a synthetic anabolic steroid. Results provide insight into mechanisms underlying the beneficial effect of oxandrolone in DMD.

title: Duchenne Muscular Dystrophy response to oxandrolone (HG-U133B)
description: Analysis of gastrocnemius muscle biopsy specimens from Duchenne muscular dystrophy (DMD) patients before and after 3 months of treatment with 0.1mg/kg/day oxandrolone, a synthetic anabolic steroid. Results provide insight into mechanisms underlying the beneficial effect of oxandrolone in DMD.

title: Juvenile hormone III effect on anterior midgut: time course
description: Analysis of anterior midguts of males after topical application of juvenile hormone III (JHIII). Midguts examined 24 hours after phloem feeding, and at various time points up to 16 hours after treatment. JHIII is a sesquiterpenoid involved in the regulation of insect development and reproduction.

title: T cell anergy induction regulation by Egr-2 and Egr-3 (MG-U74A)
description: Analysis of pooled mRNA (2, 4, 6 hours) from A.E7 T cell clones activated in conditions that promote (anti-TCR) or inhibit (anti-TCR + CsA or PKCi or Combo) anergy induction.  Results identify the early growth response gene 2 (Egr-2) and Egr-3 as key positive regulators of T cell anergy induction.

title: T cell anergy induction regulation by Egr-2 and Egr-3 (MG-U74B)
description: Analysis of pooled mRNA (2, 4, 6 hours) from A.E7 T cell clones activated in conditions that promote (anti-TCR) or inhibit (anti-TCR + CsA or PKCi or Combo) anergy induction.  Results identify the early growth response gene 2 (Egr-2) and Egr-3 as key positive regulators of T cell anergy induction.

title: T cell anergy induction regulation by Egr-2 and Egr-3 (MG-U74C)
description: Analysis of pooled mRNA (2, 4, 6 hours) from A.E7 T cell clones activated in conditions that promote (anti-TCR) or inhibit (anti-TCR + CsA or PKCi or Combo) anergy induction.  Results identify the early growth response gene 2 (Egr-2) and Egr-3 as key positive regulators of T cell anergy induction.

title: Exercise effect on aged muscle
description: Expression profiling of vastus lateralis muscles from 6 healthy, elderly, sedentary males after 3 months of exercise at 80% of maximal capacity.  Results provide insight into the molecular changes induced by exercise in sedentary skeletal muscles.

title: Forelimb and hindlimb embryonic autopod comparison (MG-430A)
description: Analysis of forelimb and hindlimb autopod tissues at embryonic day 12.5. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms regulating the formation of forelimbs and hindlimbs.

title: Forelimb and hindlimb embryonic autopod comparison (MG-430B)
description: Analysis of forelimb and hindlimb autopod tissues at embryonic day 12.5. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms regulating the formation of forelimbs and hindlimbs.

title: Papillary renal cell carcinoma classification
description: Analysis of renal tumors from 34 papillary renal cell carcinoma (PRCC) cases. Results identify 2 molecular signatures that correlate with the morphologic classification of PRCC. Molecular class type 1 tumors correlate with excellent survival, while type 2 tumors correlate with poor survival.

title: Bruton's tyrosine kinase mutant models of X-linked agammaglobulinemia
description: Analysis of splenic B cells from mutants with a knockout of Bruton's tyrosine kinase (Btk) or a R28C missense mutation in Btk. Btk mutations cause a block in B cell differentiation and lead to X-linked agammaglobulinemia (XLA). Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of XLA.

title: Neurogenic potential of mesenchymal stem cells
description: Comparison of mesenchymal stem cells (MSC) treated with  dimethylsulphoxide and butylated hydroxyanisole (DMSO/BHA) for 6 or 48 hours to fetal brain (positive control) or adult liver (negative control). Results raise doubts about the DMSO/BHA protocol for generating neural cells from MSCs.

title: Cigarette smoke effect on bronchial epithelial cells: time course
description: Analysis of cultured normal bronchial epithelial cells 4 and 24 hours after exposure to 15 minutes of cigarette smoke in order to better understand molecular impact of tobacco exposure.

title: NADPH-cytochrome P450 reductase-loss transgenic models: hepatic expression profiling
description: Analysis of liver in two NADPH-cytochrome P450 reductase (CPR)-loss transgenic models: liver-Cpr-null (liver-specific Cpr deletion) and Cpr-low (global Cpr suppression). Results provide insight into potential mechanisms underlying altered hepatic gene expression related to CPR-deficiency.

title: SIR2 knockout effect on virulence gene family silencing and activation
description: Expression profiling of 3D7 silent information regulator 2 homolog (Sir2) knockout at ring stage, 8 hours post-invasion. Results identify Sir2-mediated, reversible heterochromatin silencing as one tier of epigenetic regulation of the antigenic variation var gene family.

title: Gastrin target genes in parietal cells
description: Analysis of gastrin knockout parietal cells isolated from the stomach fundus by flow cytometry. Results identify gastrin responsive genes and provide insight into the critical components of the acid secretory system.

title: Neuromuscular junction
description: Analysis of the neuromuscular junction (NMJ), a regionally specialized area of myofibers. NMJ regions isolated using laser capture microdissection. Results provide insight into the formation and maintenance of the NMJ.

title: Glucocorticoid effect on lens epithelial cells: time course
description: Analysis of cultured immortalized lens epithelial cells (LEC) 4 and 16 hours after treatment with 1 uM dexamethasone, a glucocorticoid steroid hormone. Long-term glucocorticoid use can induce cataract formation. Results identify glucocorticoid targets and short-term effects of glucocorticoid on LECs

title: Cirrhosis and liver endothelial cells
description: Analysis of liver endothelial cells (LECs) from male Wistars exposed to carbon tetrachloride to induce cirrhosis. Studies suggest that LECs play a role in the decrease of hepatic vascular compliance in cirrhosis. Results identify endothelial-specific pathways for therapeutic targeting.

title: Muscle response to low frequency electrical stimulation: time course
description: Expression profiling of tibialis anterior muscle after 3 hours of low frequency electrical stimulation using a pacer. Muscle tissues harvested at various time points up to 24 hours following stimulation.

title: Conjugated linoleic acid delipidative effect on obese line: time course (dye-swap)
description: Analysis of epididymal adipose tissue from M16 polygenic obese animals fed diet containing 1% trans-10 cis-12-conjugated linoleic acid (CLA). Body weight was 12% lower by day 14 on CLA diet. Adipose examined at 5 and 14 days. Results provide insight to mechanisms underlying CLA delipidative effect.

title: Conjugated linoleic acid delipidative effect on obese line: time course
description: Analysis of epididymal adipose tissue from M16 polygenic obese animals fed diet containing 1% trans-10 cis-12-conjugated linoleic acid (CLA). Body weight was 12% lower by day 14 on CLA diet. Adipose examined at 5 and 14 days. Results provide insight to mechanisms underlying CLA delipidative effect.

title: Testosterone effect on meibomian gland
description: Analysis of meibomian glands from orchiectomized BALB/c adults treated with testosterone for 14 days. Androgen deficiency associated with glandular dysfunction and evaporative dry eye. Lacrimal and submandibular glands included. Results suggest pathways regulated by androgens in meibomian glands.

title: Ischemic and nonischemic cardiomyopathy comparison
description: Analysis of myocardial tissues from nonischemic (NICM) and ischemic cardiomyopathy (ICM) patients. NICM and ICM, major forms of dilated cardiomyopathy leading to congestive heart failure, have similar presentations but differ in pathophysiology, prognosis, and response to therapy.

title: N-methyl-N-nitrosourea-induced breast cancer model
description: Analysis of N-methyl-N-nitrosourea (NMU)- induced primary mammary tumors from Wistar-Furth females. Results compared to expression profiles of human breast carcinomas, and found similar to profiles of ER-positive, low to intermediate grade breast cancer.

title: IFN-gamma primed macrophage response to IFN-gamma restimulation: time course
description: Analysis of CD14+ monocytes primed with 3 U/ml (subactivating dose) IFN-gamma for 48 hours and restimulated with 100 U/ml (saturating dose) IFN-gamma for various time point up to 24 hours. Results provide insight into the influence of IFN-gamma priming on IFN-gamma induced transcriptional responses.

title: Androgen effect on spermatogenesis
description: Analysis of testis from Sertoli cell-selective androgen receptor knockouts (SCARKO) at postnatal day 10. Results provide insight into molecular consequences of selective absence of androgen action in Sertoli cells at onset of spermatogenesis.

title: Androgen effect on spermatogenesis: time course
description: Analysis of testis from Sertoli cell-selective androgen receptor knockouts (SCARKO) between postnatal day 8 and 20. Results provide insight into molecular consequences of selective absence of androgen action in Sertoli cells at onset of spermatogenesis.

title: Autophagy effect on the MHC class II antigenic peptide repertoire
description: Analysis of Awells B-lymphoblastoid cell line after 6 and 24 hours of starvation-induced autophagy. Results identify the influence of autophagy on the MHC-II ligandome, in promoting MHC-II presentation of antigens from intracellular source proteins, and on the MHC-II antigen-processing machinery.

title: Peripheral myelin protein 22 gene dosage and point mutation effect on sciatic nerve
description: Analysis of sciatic nerve from postnatal day 4 and 60 mutants overexpressing peripheral myelin protein 22 (PMP22), lacking PMP22, or expressing the Trembler PMP22 point mutation. Results provide insight into normal function of PMP22, myelination, and neuropathies caused by PMP22 misexpression.

title: Bone morphogenic protein 2 effect on idiopathic pulmonary arterial hypertension
description: Analysis of pulmonary artery smooth muscle cells (PASMC) from patients with idiopathic pulmonary arterial hypertension (IPAH). PASMC treated with 200 nM bone morphogenic protein 2 (BMP-2) for 24 hours. BMP signaling dysfunction has been implicated in IPAH.

title: Peroxisome proliferator-activated receptor subtype activation effect on liver cell
description: Analysis of HepG2 cells expressing peroxisome proliferator-activated receptor (PPAR) alpha, beta/delta, gamma 1, or gamma 2. Cells expressing PPARs treated with fenofibric acid, GW501516, or ciglitizone to activate alpha, beta/delta, or gamma subtypes respectively. PPARs regulate lipid homeostasis.

title: Stearoyl-CoA desaturase 1 null mutation effect on liver
description: Analysis of liver of 6 week old stearoyl-CoA desaturase 1 (SCD1) knockout females. SCD1 is a lipogenic enzyme that catalyzes the synthesis of monosaturated fatty acids. SCD1 null mutants have reduced body adiposity, increased insulin sensitivity, and are resistant to diet-induced weight gain.

title: Cutaneous malignant melanoma
description: Expression profiling of primary malignant melanoma, benign skin nevi, and normal skin samples. Results identify potential molecular markers for lymph node staging assays, and provide insight into melanoma tumorigenesis.

title: Essential thrombocythemia
description: Analysis of platelets from patients with essential thrombocythemia (ET). ET is a myeloproliferative disorder resulting in an abnormal increase in the number of blood platelets. Results indicate that distinct expression patterns of 17beta-hydroxysteroid dehydrogenases are associated with ET.

title: Hypoxia response
description: Analysis of wild type, hif-1-deficient, and vhl-1-deficient strains cultured for 4 hours in 21% oxygen (normoxia) or 0.1% oxygen (hypoxia). Results provide insight into pathways for adaptation to oxygen deprivation.

title: Glioblastoma pseudopalisading cells
description: Analysis of pseudopalisading cells obtained by laser capture microdissection from glioblastoma tumors. The presence of pseudopalisading cells is associated with aggressive malignant gliomas. Results identify putative prognostic markers for glioblastoma.

title: Carboplatin sensitive and resistant ovarian carcinoma
description: Comparison of carboplatin sensitive and resistant ovarian cancer cells. Carboplatin is a chemotherapy drug. Cancer cells prepared from primary cultures of ovarian papillary serous adenocarcinomas. Results identify potential markers for carboplatin responsiveness in ovarian carcinoma.

title: mRNA translation and dehydration stress
description: Evaluation of proportion of individual mRNAs in polysomal complexes in leaves under control and mild dehydration stress (DS) conditions. DS reduces level of mRNA in polysomes (ribosome loading) for most genes. Results suggest transcript sequence features that regulate differential mRNA translation.

title: Salinity stress response
description: Analysis of crown and growing point of salt-tolerant (FL478) and salt-sensitive (IR29) genotypes under control and salinity-stressed conditions during vegetative growth. Results provide insight into the genetic basis of salt tolerance in rice.

title: c-Myb and its oncogenic variant v-Myb
description: Analysis of transcriptional activity in MCF7 cells infected with control adenovirus versus adenovirus expressing c-Myb, oncogenic variant v-Myb, or a 3MutC hybrid construct. Results indicate that v-Myb is a distinct transcriptional regulator with a unique set of activities.

title: Hepatocellular carcinoma induced by choline-deficient L-amino acid-defined diet
description: Analysis of hepatocellular carcinoma (HCC) tumors, surrounding non-cancerous tissue, and normal liver from Fischer 344 males. HCC formation induced by a choline-deficient L-amino acid-defined (CDAA) diet for 70 weeks. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying progression of HCC.

title: B-cell chronic lymphocytic leukemia progression
description: Analysis of primary lymphocytes from B-cell chronic lymphocytic leukemia (B-CLL) patients. Lymphocytes from patients with indolent B-CLL compared to those with progressive B-CLL. Results identify putative gene markers of B-CLL progression from a stable to an aggressive state.

title: 1alpha,25-dihydroxyvitamin D3 suppressive effect on IFN-gamma activated macrophages
description: Analysis of wild type and vitamin D receptor (Vdr) knockout primary bone marrow-derived macrophages following treatment with IFN-gamma and/or 1alpha,25-dihydroxyvitamin D3 (1alpha,25(OH)2D3). Results indicate that 1alpha,25(OH)2D3 suppresses effector functions of IFN-gamma-activated macrophages.

title: Prostate cancer progression after androgen ablation
description: Analysis of prostate cancer progression following androgen ablation treatment. 10 treated androgen-independent primary prostate tumors compared to 10 untreated androgen-dependent primary  prostate tumors. Results provide insight into progression of prostate cancer to aggressive androgen-independent

title: Myelodysplastic syndrome
description: Analysis of bone marrow CD34+ progenitor cells from normal-karyotype, low-blast-count, early, low-risk myelodysplastic syndrome (MDS) patients, age-matched controls, and patients with non-MDS anemia. Results provide insight into pathogenesis of MDS and identify putative markers of MDS.

title: Type 1 diabetes mellitus model of erectile dysfunction
description: Analysis of F344 penile cavernosal tissue after 10 weeks of streptozotocin (STZ)-induced Type 1 diabetes. Results provide insight into molecular events associated with pathophysiology of diabetes-induced erectile dysfunction (ED).

title: D-penicillamine-induced autoimmunity model of idiosyncratic drug reactions
description: Analysis of Brown Norway males 6 hours after treatment with 150 mg/kg of D-penicillamine. Some rheumatoid arthritis patients treated with D-penicillamine develop idiosyncratic drug reactions (IDR). Results provide insight into mechanisms underlying IDR.

title: Viral infection: time course
description: Expression profiling of Oregon R males 24 and 48 hours after drosophila C virus infection. Results provide insight into the response of the innate immune system to viral infections.

title: Multipotent neural progenitor cells
description: Analysis of multipotent neural progenitor cells (NPCs) propagated by growth on media containing cystatin C and fibroblast growth factor-2. NPCs isolated from hippocampus neural stem cells. Results provide insight into the frequency of L1 element retrotransposition events in multipotent NPCs.

title: T cells infected with an HIV-based vector
description: Analysis of Jurkat T cells infected with an HIV-based vector transducing green fluorescent protein. Expression of genes hosting HIV integration events examined. Results provide insight into how expression from the HIV type 1 promoter is affected by the integration site of the provirus.

title: Coritical neuron response to inhalational anesthetics
description: Expression profiling of primary cortical neuron cultures exposed to 1 or 3% halothane or 4% isoflurane for 6 hours. Cells allowed to recover for an additional 6 hours. Results provide insight into effect of inhaled anesthetics on global gene expression.

title: DNA adenine methyltransferase and mismatch repair mutants
description: Analysis of mutants lacking DNA adenine methyltransferase Dam, or mismatch repair protein MutS, or both. Results help elucidate the global changes resulting from Dam deficiency and the role of mismatch repair in producing these changes.

title: Cisplatin effect on DNA adenine methyltransferase and mismatch repair mutants
description: Analysis of mutants lacking DNA adenine methyltransferase Dam, or mismatch repair protein MutS, or both after treatment with cisplatin. dam mutants are hypersensitive to cisplatin, while dam mutS double mutants display wild type resistance to cisplatin.

title: CD34+ hematopoietic cells expanded in artificial matrix of fibrillar collagen I
description: Analysis of CD34+ hematopoietic stem/progenitor cells (HSC) expanded for 7 days in an artificial matrix of fibrillar collagen I, the major matrix component of bone. Results provide insight into the limitations of ex vivo expansion to increase the number of transplantable HSCs from cord blood.

title: Various normal pure cell cultures
description: Expression profiling of various pure normal epithelial, endothelial, fibroblast, stromal, and muscle cell cultures. Data provide baseline for understanding cellular mechanisms for maintenance of stable cell types and for studying pathways to terminally differentiated state.

title: Regenerating retina: time course
description: Expression profiling of lesioned retina at various time points up to 14 days after injury. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms that enable the regeneration of injured retinas in adult anamniotes.

title: Pulmonary type II cell differentiation
description: Analysis of epithelial cells isolated from 13 fetal lungs (13-20 wks old) and cultured in dexamethasone/cyclic AMP/isobutylmethylxanthine (DCI) for 72 hrs to promote type II cell differentiation. Mature alveolar type II cells that produce surfactant are critical for adaptation to extrauterine life.

title: Brain regions of various inbred strains
description: Analysis of 7 brain regions of 6 inbred strains. 7 week old males from 129S6/SvEvTac, A/J, C3H/HeJ, C57BL/6J, DBA/2J, and FVB/NJ strains examined. Results correlated with behavioral phenotypes and identify candidate genes for anxiety-like behavior.

title: Leukocyte inflammatory responses to lipopolysaccharide
description: Analysis of whole blood following 4 hour treatment with lipolysaccharide (LPS). Leukocytes from individuals with high and low responses to LPS examined. LPS response assessed by measuring cytokine production. Results provide insight into the variability of LPS responses between individuals.

title: Auxin response factors ARF6 and ARF8
description: Analysis of stage 1-14 flowers from wild type Columbia, arf6/arf6 ARF8/arf8, and arf6 arf8 plants after 30 minute treatment with 10 uM indole-3-acetic acid (IAA). Results provide insight into early flower development and identify genes that respond rapidly to auxin in an ARF6/ARF8-dependent manner.

title: cAMP/protein kinaseA effect on cell-cycle regulation: timecourse
description: Analysis of wild type and Kin- S49 lymphoma cell line treated with 8-(4-chlorophenylthio)-cAMP (8-CPT-cAMP), a PKA-selective cAMP analog, for 2, 6, or 24 hours. Kin- S49 cells lack protein kinase A (PKA). Results identify the global impact of cAMP/PKA on transcriptional networks, particularly the ce

title: HCaRG overexpression in kidney cells
description: Analysis of HCaRG9, a stably-transfected HEK293 embryonal kidney cell line over-expressing the hypertension-related, calcium-regulated gene (HCaRG). Results identify a role for HCaRG in kidney repair involving increased renal cell migration and transforming growth factor-alpha (TGF-α) expression.

title: Hormone replacement therapy effect on whole blood
description: Comparison of whole blood samples from 42 postmenopausal women on hormone replacement therapy (HRT) to those of 47 postmenopausal women not on HRT. Subjects are part of the Norwegian Women and Cancer Study (NOWAC).

title: Lipid peroxidation product 4-hydroxy-2-nonenal effect on cells: time course
description: Analysis of RKO colorectal carcinoma cell line at 6 and 24 hours following exposure to subcytotoxic and cytotoxic amounts of 4-hydroxy-2-nonenal (HNE). HNE is an abundant product of polyunsaturated fatty acid oxidation and decomposition and reacts extensively with DNA and proteins.

title: Candoxin effect on glial cells: time course
description: Analysis of glial cell line Hs683 at various time points up to 48 hours following exposure to 300 nM of candoxin (CDX) snake venom. CDX is a neurotoxin that inhibits post-synaptic neuromuscular and neuronal alpha7nACh-receptors, and delays cell death in glial cells.

title: Classical Hodgkin's lymphoma: T cell expression profile
description: Expression profiling of CD3+ T cells isolated from peripheral blood samples of untreated patients with classical Hodgkin's lymphoma. CD3+ T cells from healthy donors and patients with sarcoidosis also examined.

title: Regular exercise effect on heart
description: Analysis of left heart ventricle of Sprague Dawley males without access to exercise, with access to hour-long twice a week of activity, or with access to a running wheel every other day. Regimen imposed from 3 weeks until 16 months of age. Results identify putative markers of cardiovascular health.

title: Parous mammary gland response to N-methyl-N-nitrosourea
description: Analysis of mammary gland from parous or virgin Lewis animals 3 weeks after treatment with 50 mg/kg of N-methyl-N-nitrosourea, a carcinogen. Full-term pregnancy early in life is associated with a reduced chance of developing breast cancer.

title: Lunasin effect on prostate epithelial cells
description: Expression profiling of normal prostate epithelial RWPE1 cells and tumorigenic prostate cancer RWPE2 cells treated with 2 uM lunasin for 24 hours. Lunasin is a soybean peptide shown to suppress carcinogenesis. Results provide insight into the chemopreventive properties of lunasin.

title: Folic acid deficiency effect on colon cancer cells
description: Analysis of HT-29 colon cancer cells cultured in pteroylglutamic acid or methyl-tetrahydrofolate at concentrations of 10 or 100 ng/ml each. Studies suggest that folate deficiency can have an inhibitory effect on the progression of established colonic tumor cells.

title: c-Myb and oncogenic variant v-Myb transcriptional activities
description: Analysis of monocytes infected with adenovirus expressing c-Myb or its oncogenic variant v-Myb, a mutated (11 AA substitutions) and truncated (N- and C-termini) version of c-Myb. Results identify dramatic, qualitative changes in the transcriptional acitivity of c-Myb caused by oncogenic mutations.

title: Various anti-cancer drugs effect on liver: time course and dose-response
description: Analysis of livers of Sprague-Dawley males treated with the anticancer drug carmustine, methotrexate, or thioguanine. Animals treated daily with various doses and livers examined at various time points up to 5 days. Results combined with clinical pathology assessments in a chemogenomics database.

title: Olfactory bulbectomy effect on olfactory eptithelium: time course
description: Analysis of the olfactory epithelium at various time points up to 5 days following olfactory bulbectomy. Olfactory bulbectomy performed to force the replacement of olfactory sensory neurons. Results provide insight into the cellular events involved in olfactory neurogenesis.

title: Transcription factor p63 null mutation effect on skin (MG-U74A)
description: Analysis of skin from transcription factor p63 homozygous null mutants at embryonic age E18.5. Without p63, the epidermis fails to commit to stratification, resulting in aborted skin development. Results identify p63 target genes and provide insight into early events in epidermal morphogenesis.

title: Transcription factor p63 null mutation effect on skin (MG-U74B)
description: Analysis of skin from transcription factor p63 homozygous null mutants at embryonic age E18.5. Without p63, the epidermis fails to commit to stratification, resulting in aborted skin development. Results identify p63 target genes and provide insight into early events in epidermal morphogenesis.

title: Cigarette smoking effect on alveolar macrophages
description: Anlaysis of alveolar macrophages of 5 phenotypically normal smokers who consume ~20 packs cigarettes/year. Smoking is the leading cause of respiratory diseases collectively known as chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD). Provides insight into early events in molecular pathogenesis of COPD.

title: Kidneys removed by laparoscopic donor nephrectomy
description: Analysis of kidneys removed by laparoscopic donor nephrectomy (LDN), a minimally invasive procedure that involves several hours of carbon dioxide pneumoperitoneum. Renal cortices of kidneys recovered by LDN compared to those removed by open donor nephrectomy.

title: Prostate cancer progression
description: Expression profiling of prostate cancer tumors that are benign, clinically localized, or metastatic and refractory to hormones. Results compared to those obtained from immunoblotting to identify concordant changes in mRNA and protein levels.

title: Melanoma cell lines treated with a DNA methylase inhibitor
description: Analysis of a poorly tumorigenic melanoma cell line and its 3 highly aggressive derivative lines after treatment with 2'-deoxy-5-azacytidine (DAC), a DNA methyltransferase inhibitor. Results suggest multiple markers for melanoma progression that are regulated by DNA methylation.

title: PPARα  agonist ciprofibrate effect on liver
description: Analysis of primate livers exposed to ciprofibrate at various doses for 4 or 15 days. Peroxisome proliferator-activated receptor-α (PPARα) agonists such as ciprofibrate cause hepatocarcinogenesis in rodents but not in primates. Results identify species differences in response to PPARα agonist.

title: Type 2 diabetes susceptibility: role of hepatic lipogenic capacity
description: Analysis of adipose tissue, liver, skeletal muscle, and pancreatic islets from non-diabetic (C57BL/6J (B6)) and severely diabetic (BTBR) strains of obese (ob/ob), 14 week old males.  Results correlate increased hepatic lipogenic gene expression in B6-ob/ob with type 2 diabetes resistance.

title: Obesity and type 2 diabetes: role of adipogenic gene expression (Mu11K-A)
description: Analysis of lean (C57BL/6J (B6), BTBR, F1 (B6xBTBR)), obese (B6-ob/ob), and obese-diabetic (F2 (B6xBTBR)-ob/ob [increasingly hyperglycemic], BTBR-ob/ob [severely diabetic]) strains. Results identify decreased adipogenic gene expression in obesity and further changes in the progression to diabetes.

title: Transcription factor Oct-1 deficient fibroblast response to ionizing radiation (430A)
description: Expression profiling of Oct-1 deficient 3T3-immortalized embryonic fibroblasts exposed to gamma radiation. Oct-1 is a POU domain transcription factor. Results provide insight into the role of Oct-1 in the adaptation to cellular stress.

title: Transcription factor Oct-1 deficient fibroblast response to ionizing radiation (430B)
description: Expression profiling of Oct-1 deficient 3T3-immortalized embryonic fibroblasts exposed to gamma radiation. Oct-1 is a POU domain transcription factor. Results provide insight into the role of Oct-1 in the adaptation to cellular stress.

title: Bronchial epithelial cell response to vanadium and zinc
description: Analysis of bronchial epithelial cells after 4 hours of exposure to 50 uM vanadium (V) or zinc (Zn). Excessive V and Zn in the air can arise from the burning of heavy fuel and during welding and smelting operations, respectively. Results identify biomarkers that distinguish V from Zn exposure.

title: Anoxia and sucrose effect on seedlings
description: Analysis of ecotype Columbia glabra seedlings subjected to anoxia for 6 hours in the presence or absence of 90 uM sucrose. Exogenous sucrose enhances the tolerance of seedlings to anoxia. Results identify candidate genes that enhance the tolerance of sucrose treated seedlings to anoxia.

title: HIV-1 infection effect on peripheral blood mononuclear cells
description: Analysis of peripheral blood mononuclear cells from HIV-1 seropositive and seronegative individuals. Results used to identify a 10-gene signature used for determining HIV-1 serostatus, and a 6-gene signature to identify seropositive individuals exhibiting changes in CD4+ T cell counts.

title: Hypoxia effect on seedlings
description: Expression profiling of 7 day old wild type Ler seedlings subjected to 12 hours of hypoxia under low light conditions. Total RNA and mRNA extracted from large polyribosomes  compared. Results provide insight into the role of translational regulation in the response to hypoxia.

title: Toxicants effect on liver: pooled and individual sample comparison
description: Analysis of livers of Sprague-Dawley males at various time points up to 168 hours after treatment with clofibrate, diethylhexylphthalate, or valproic acid. Expression profiles from pooled and individual samples compared. Results provide insight into the impact of pooling on experimental analysis.

title: Mammary gland response to retinoic X receptor ligand: pooled and individual sample comparison
description: Analysis of mammary glands from Wistar Furth females fed a diet supplemented with the retinoic X receptor ligand LG100268. Expression profiles from pooled and individual samples compared. Results provide insight into the impact of pooling on experimental analysis.

title: Camptothecin effect on renal epithelial cell line and HIV transduction
description: Analysis of renal epithelial cell line 293T following treatment with 2 uM camptothecin, which boosts transduction of cells by HIV. Camptothecin induces DNA damage and arrests cell cycle at G2/M. Results provide insight into the mechanisms underlying HIV transduction boost induced by camptothecin.

title: Motoneuron characterization
description: Analysis of lateral and medial motoneurons (MNs) from lumbar segments and sympathetic preganglionic motoneurons located in the thoracic intermediolateral nucleus. MNs isolated by laser capture microdissection. Results provide insight into the molecular differences between adult MN types.

title: Obesity and type 2 diabetes: role of adipogenic gene expression (Mu11K-B)
description: Analysis of lean (C57BL/6J (B6), BTBR, F1 (B6xBTBR)), obese (B6-ob/ob), and obese-diabetic (F2 (B6xBTBR)-ob/ob [increasingly hyperglycemic], BTBR-ob/ob [severely diabetic]) strains. Results identify decreased adipogenic gene expression in obesity and further changes in the progression to diabetes.

title: Essential hypertension SHR model
description: Comparison of adrenal gland from spontaneously hypertensive (SHR) males at 4 weeks of age, a prehypertensive stage, and normotensive Wistar-Kyoto. Results compared to gene expression in hypertensive BPH mouse model, and provides insight into mechanisms of hypertension shared across species.

title: IFN-gamma and host genetic background effect on Yersinia enterocolitica infected macrophages
description: Analysis of bone marrow derived macrophages from resistant C57BL/6 or susceptible BALB/c animals, with or without IFN-gamma pretreatment, infected with Yersinia enterocolitica. Results provide insight into the impact of host genetic background and IFN-gamma on Y. enterocolitica infections.

title: DICER-LIKE 4 mutant
description: Analysis of rosette leaf and inflorescence tissues from the DICER-LIKE (DCL) 4 mutant dcl4-2. DCL genes have specialized functions in small RNA biogenesis for RNA interference-related processes. Results provide insight into the role of DCL4 in the trans-acting siRNA pathway.

title: TGF-beta-activated kinase 1 deficient B cell response to B cell receptor stimulation
description: Analysis of TGF-beta activated kinase 1 (TAK1)-deficient B cells following B cell receptor (BCR) activation by anti-IgM treatment for 4 hours. Results provide insight into how TAK1 regulates BCR-mediated proliferative responses.

title: Neuromuscular degeneration mutant spinal cord response to neural stem cell transplantation
description: Analysis of neuromuscular degeneration mutant (nmd) spinal cords transplanted with ALDHhiSSClo neural stem cells. nmd is a model for spinal muscular atrophy with respiratory distress type 1. Results provide insight into the mechanisms underlying neuromuscular improvements in stem cell recipients.

title: Oxidative stress effect on pyocin expression
description: Expression profiling of strain PA01 exposed to hydrogen peroxide, a reactive oxygen species, at a sublethal concentration of 1 mM. Results identify upregulation of pyocin (bacteriocin) genes as a potentially novel defensive scheme in response to oxidative attack by infected host cells.

title: Transcription factor Spotted-dick knockdown
description: Expression profiling of cultured S2 cells following inactivation of spotted-dick, a gene encoding a zinc finger transcriptional activator of S phase genes. RNAi used to inactivate spotted-dick. Results identify potential downstream targets of Spotted-dick.

title: Transcription factor Tcf1 knockout effect on pancreatic islets (MG-U74A)
description: Analysis of pancreatic islets from 6 to 8 week old Tcf1 knockouts. Mutations in Tcf1 lead to a subtype of type 2 diabetes called maturity-onset diabetes of the young (MODY) in humans. Results identify potential targets of Tcf1 that may be responsible for mediating pancreatic beta cell growth.

title: Transcription factor Tcf1 knockout effect on pancreatic islets (MG-U74B)
description: Analysis of pancreatic islets from 6 to 8 week old Tcf1 knockouts. Mutations in Tcf1 lead to a subtype of type 2 diabetes called maturity-onset diabetes of the young (MODY) in humans. Results identify potential targets of Tcf1 that may be responsible for mediating pancreatic beta cell growth.

title: Rho/CRIK signaling modulation effect on keratinocyte
description: Analysis of keratinocytes expressing activated Rho or Citron kinase (CRIK), or treated with C3 transferase. Rho plays a positive role during early differentiation, CRIK is a Rho effector, and C3 is a Rho inhibitor. Results provide insight into the role of Rho/CRIK in later stages of differentiation.

title: Uterine fibroids with fumarate hydratase mutations
description: Analysis of 7 uterine fibroids carrying fumarate hydratase (FH) mutations. FH catalyzes hydration of fumarate in the Krebs tricarboxylic acid cycle. Results provide insight into the connection between the disruption of mitochondrial metabolic pathways and neoplasia.

title: Transcription factor FoxM1 inactivation effect on breast cancer cell
description: Expression profiling of BT-20 breast cancer cells 48 hours after transfection with FoxM1 siRNA. Elevated expression of FoxM1 has been observed in hepatocellular carcinoma, basal cell carcinoma, and breast cancer. Results provide insight into the role of FoxM1 in cancer cell growth.

title: Intestinal epithelial cell response to probiotic Escherichia coli strain Nissle 1917
description: Analysis of Caco-2 intestinal epithelial cells cocultured for 6 hours with the probiotic Escherichia coli strain Nissle 1917 (EcN). A controlled clinical trial suggests that EcN is effective in remission maintenance of ulcerative colitis. Results provide insight into EcN-host interactions.

title: Carcinoma in situ lesions of the urinary bladder
description: Analysis of bladder biopsies of superficial transitional cell carcinomas with or without surrounding carcinoma in situ (CIS) lesions and muscle invasive carcinomas (mTCC). CIS is a common mTCC precursor. Results provide insight into which tumors in early stage bladder cancer are likely to progress.

title: Obesity: preadipocyte expression profile (HG-U133A)
description: Analysis of cultured abdominal subcutaneous preadipocytes from 7 male and 7 female non-diabetic obese Pima Indians. The prevalence of obesity in Pima Indians is among the highest of any population. Results provide insight into the role of preadipocytes in obesity and obesity-related inflammation.

title: Obesity: preadipocyte expression profile (HG-U133B)
description: Analysis of cultured abdominal subcutaneous preadipocytes from 7 male and 7 female non-diabetic obese Pima Indians. The prevalence of obesity in Pima Indians is among the highest of any population. Results provide insight into the role of preadipocytes in obesity and obesity-related inflammation.

title: Anticarcinogen 3H-1, 2-dithiole-3-thione effect on liver
description: Analysis of livers of animals treated with 3H-1, 2-dithiole-3-thione (D3T). D3T blocks carcinogenesis through induction of phase 2 enzymes that enhance the detoxification of xenobiotic compounds. Results provide insight into the regulatory pathways affected by D3T.

title: Gpr1 receptor and Gpa2 G protein alpha subunit deletion mutants
description: Expression profiling of mutants lacking the Gpr1 receptor or the Gpa2 G protein alpha subunit. Results provide insight into the role of the Gpr1 receptor and the Gpa2 G protein alpha subunit in the maintenance and modulation of cell size in response to glucose.

title: Serum response factor null mutation effect on neonatal cardiomyocytes
description: Analysis of serum response factor (SRF)-null neonatal cardiomyocytes. SRF is a transcriptional regulator required for mesodermal development and implicated in myogenesis. Results provide insight into the role of SRF in regulating genetic programs important for controlling cardiomyocyte function.

title: Intermediate filament protein GFAP transgene overexpression effect on olfactory bulb: time course
description: Analysis of olfactory bulb of 23 day and 4 month old transgenics overexpressing human intermediate filament protein GFAP. GFAP missense mutations result in Alexander disease, a neurodegenerative disease. GFAP overexpression results in an encephalopathy similar to that resulting from GFAP mutations.

title: Growth hormone effect on adipocytes: time course
description: Analysis of cultured 3T3-F442A adipocytes treated with 500 nM growth hormone (GH). Adipocytes examined at various time points up to 48 hours following treatment with GH. Chronic GH treatment induces metabolic changes consistent with insulin resistance in 3T3-F442A adipocytes.

title: Neural tissue profiling
description: Expression profiling of 24 neural tissues and 10 body regions from adult A/J, C57BL/6J, C3H/HeJ, DBA/2J, and 129S6/SvEvTac males. Relationship of regional gene expression in the brain to architecture and organization of the brain examined.

title: Calcineurin overexpression effect on astrocytes
description: Analysis of primary hippocampal culture cells overexpressing an activated form of calcineurin that lacks part of its C terminus and an autoinhibitory domain. The hippocampal cultures contain neurons and astroglia. Results provide insight into the role of calcineurin in astrocyte activation.

title: Bleomycin effect on lungs: dose response and time course
description: Comparison of lungs from C57BL/6J and C3H/HeJ strains, 3 and 6 weeks after treatment with 80, 100, or 125 units of bleomycin/kg. C57BL/6Js are susceptible to bleomycin-induced pulmonary fibrosis, while C3H/HeJs are resistant. Results identify candidate genes underlying fibrosis susceptibility.

title: RyhB small regulatory RNA effect on global iron use
description: Analysis of derivatives of strain MG1655: wild-type, fur mutant, and wild-type with added FeSO4, induced to overexpress RyhB. RyhB is a noncoding RNA regulated by the Fur repressor protein. Results suggest that RyhB plays a major role in the regulation of iron metabolism.

title: Obesity: adipocyte expression profile (HG-U95B)
description: Analysis of cultured abdominal subcutaneous mature adipocytes from 9 male and 10 female non-diabetic obese Pima Indians. The prevalence of obesity in Pima Indians is among the highest of any population. Results provide insight into the role of adipocytes in obesity and obesity-related inflammation.

title: Obesity: adipocyte expression profile (HG-U95C)
description: Analysis of cultured abdominal subcutaneous mature adipocytes from 9 male and 10 female non-diabetic obese Pima Indians. The prevalence of obesity in Pima Indians is among the highest of any population. Results provide insight into the role of adipocytes in obesity and obesity-related inflammation.

title: Obesity: adipocyte expression profile (HG-U95D)
description: Analysis of cultured abdominal subcutaneous mature adipocytes from 9 male and 10 female non-diabetic obese Pima Indians. The prevalence of obesity in Pima Indians is among the highest of any population. Results provide insight into the role of adipocytes in obesity and obesity-related inflammation.

title: Obesity: adipocyte expression profile (HG-U95E)
description: Analysis of cultured abdominal subcutaneous mature adipocytes from 9 male and 10 female non-diabetic obese Pima Indians. The prevalence of obesity in Pima Indians is among the highest of any population. Results provide insight into the role of adipocytes in obesity and obesity-related inflammation.

title: Hepatocyte nuclear factor 1beta mutant overexpression effect on embryonic kidney cells
description: Analysis of HEK293 embryonic kidney cells overexpressing wild type hepatocyte nuclear factor (HNF) 1beta or HNF1alpha, or the HNF1beta A263insGG mutant. Results identify gene targets of HNF1 beta, and provide insight into the functional differences between HNF1beta and HNF1alpha.

title: Mechanical stress effect on fibroblasts from various fetal tissues (MG-430A)
description: Expression profiling of fetal fibroblasts from tendon, skin, and cornea following mechanical stimulation by fluid flow. Fibroblasts isolated from embryos at 19 days post conception. Results provide insight into differences among fibroblasts from different tissues and response to linear shear stress.

title: Mechanical stimulation effect on fibroblasts from various fetal tissues (MG-430B)
description: Expression profiling of fetal fibroblasts from tendon, skin, and cornea following mechanical stimulation by fluid flow. Fibroblasts isolated from embryos at 19 days post conception. Results provide insight into differences among fibroblasts from different tissues and response to linear shear stress.

title: Inducer of CBF expression 1 mutant response to cold stress: time course
description: Analysis of inducer of CBF expression 1 (ICE1) mutant seedlings exposed to 0 C for up to 24 hours. Transcription factor ICE1 is required for chilling/freezing tolerance. Results identify a major role for ICE1 in controlling the expression of many cold-responsive genes during cold stress.

title: Hutchinson-Gilford progeria syndrome: fibroblast (HG-U133A)
description: Expression profiling of three fibroblast cell lines derived from Hutchinson-Gilford progeria syndrome (HGPS) patients. Identified changes in gene expression may provide clues to potential risk factors or factors influencing disease progression.

title: Hutchinson-Gilford progeria syndrome: fibroblast  (HG-U133B)
description: Expression profiling of three fibroblast cell lines derived from Hutchinson-Gilford progeria syndrome (HGPS) patients. Identified changes in gene expression may provide clues to potential risk factors or factors influencing disease progression.

title: Cultured skin substitute
description: Comparison of cultured skin substitute (CSS), cultured keratinocytes, cultured fibroblasts, and native skin. CSS contains fibroblasts and keratinocytes, and can facilitate wound healing. Results provide insight into physiological and molecular differences between CSS and native skin.

title: Transcription factor HNF4 null mutation effect on fetal colon
description: Analysis of epithelial cells from colon lacking hepatocyte nuclear factor 4 (HNF4) from embryos at E18.5. HNF4 encodes a nuclear hormone receptor transcription factor required for hepatocyte differentiation and liver development. Results provide insight into the role of HNF4 in colon development.

title: Leptin effect on gallbladder
description: Expression profiling of gallbladders from 12 leptin-deficient obese females following daily treatment with 5 ug/g recombinant leptin for 4 weeks. Studies indicate that leptin plays a role in gallbladder motility. Results provide insight into the role of leptin in gallstone disease.

title: Tamoxifen effect on normal endometrial epithelium
description: Analysis of normal endometrial epithelial cells following treatment with oestrogen or tamoxifen (TMX).  Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the association of TMX treatment of breast cancer with an increased incidence of endometrial cancer.

title: Transcription factor RUNX1 knockout
description: Expression profiling of RUNX1 null mutant embryos at E8.5 and E12. RUNX1 is necessary for normal development of all hematopoietic lineages, and is implicated in acute leukemias.

title: Embryonal carcinoma cell line response to retinoic acid or trichostatin A
description: Analysis of embryonal carcinoma cell line F9 following treatment with all-trans retinoic acid or trichostatin A, a histone deacetylase inhibitor (HDACI). Retinoic acid and HDACIs may be critical regulators of tissue homeostatis and are being tested in clinical trials for a variety of cancers.

title: Neonatal brains from X-monosomic females
description: Analysis of neonatal brains of X-monosomic females that inherited either a maternal or a paternal X chromosome. X-monosomy is the basis of Turner's syndrome (TS). Expressivity of TS phenotypes depends partly on the parental origin of the single X. This expressivity may be due to imprinted X genes.

title: Interferon-gamma tolerogenic effect on CD8+ dendritic cells
description: Analysis of splenic CD8+ dendritic cells (DCs) rendered tolerogenic by interferon (IFN)-γ, which activates indoleamine 2,3-dioxygenase (IDO) thereby initiating immunosuppression. Results suggest the IDO-dependent tolerogenic program requires tight co-modulation of a very restricted set of genes.

title: Lateral root initiation model of auxin-induced cell division: time course
description: Analysis of the root of early auxin signaling mutant slr1 treated with auxin species alpha-naphthaleneacetic acid for up to 6 hours. Auxin triggers lateral root initiation (LRI), marked by cell divisions in the pericycle. LRI is absent in slr1. Results provide insight into the early events of LRI.

title: Probiotic Lactobacillus GG soluble factors effect on intestinal epithelial cells
description: Analysis of YAMC colonic intestinal epithelial cell line following treatment with Lactobacillus GG (LGG) conditioned media. LGG is a probiotic bacterium used to treat acute and rotavirus diarrhea. Results provide insight into the mechanisms underlying the cytoprotective effect of LGG.

title: Stearoyl-CoA desaturase 1-deficient mutants on a very low-fat, high-carbohydrate diet: liver expression profile
description: Analysis of liver from stearoyl-CoA desaturase 1 (SCD1) deficient mutants maintained on a very low-fat, high-carbohydrate (VLF-HC) diet. SCD1-deficient mutants on VLF-HC develop severe hypercholesterolemia, have reduced high-density lipoprotein cholesterol, and hepatic dysfunction.

title: Ureteric bud epithelia response to non-branching and branching growth promoting factors
description: Analysis of isolated ureteric buds (UBs) cultured in the presence of non-branching growth factor heregulin (HRG) or branching growth factor pleiotrophin (PTN). HRG and PTN purified from BSN cell conditioned medium. Results provide insight into how HRG induces non-branching growth.

title: Fibroblasts induced to an antiviral state by interferon-beta
description: Analysis of wildtype embryo fibroblasts (MEFs) induced to an antiviral state with interferon IFN-β. IFN-β plays a crucial role in host defense by modulating gene expression and inducing antiviral activity. Results identify IFN-induced genes believed responsible for the antiviral action of IFN.

title: Mast cell activation via the Fc(epsilon)RI
description: Analysis of umbilical cord blood-derived mast cells 2 hours post stimulation by high-affinity IgE receptor (FcεRI). Cells incubated with myeloma IgE and IL-4 prior to stimulation. Cells activated via FcεRI with anti-IgE antibody to induce release of antihistamines and other inflammation mediators.

title: Heat shock transcription factor 1 C-terminal domain mutant
description: Expression profiling of heat shock factor 1 (HSF1) C-terminal domain mutant (hsf1-ba1). The hsf1-ba1 mutation inhibits the heat-induced hyperphosphorylation of Hsf1. Results identify genes whose transcriptional response to heat shock is reduced by the hsf1-ba1 mutation.

title: Forebrain neuronal subtypes
description: Analysis of 12 distinct neuronal subpopulations from 5 regions of the adult forebrain. Results identify highly heterogeneous expression profiles that likely underlie the fundamental differences observed between neuronal classes and between glutamatergic and GABAergic neurons within a given class.

title: Ovarian cancer cell lines
description: Analysis of 10 ovarian cancer cell lines: 4 ovarian serous adenocarcinomas, 1 paclitaxel/cisplatin resistant ovarian adenocarcinoma cell line derivative, 5 ovarian clear cell adenocarcinomas. Expression profile of each cell line compared to its sensitivity to paclitaxel and cisplatin.

title: Heterochromatin protein HP-1 depletion effect on third instar larvae
description: Analysis of male and female 3rd instar larvae following depletion of heterochromatin protein 1 (HP1) using a Gal4-induced RNA interference system. Results provide insight into the function of HP1 during development and a sex-specific role.

title: Heat shock factor HSF1 null mutant fibroblast response to heat shock: time course
description: Expression profiling of embryonic fibroblasts lacking heat shock factor 1 (HSF1) at various time points up to 8 hours of heat shock. Results provide insight into the role of HSF1 in the regulation of gene expression during heat shock.

title: Embryonic fibroblast response to adenoviral vector infection (Mu11K-A)
description: Analysis of primary C57BL/6 embryonic fibroblasts infected with a 1st generation adenoviral (Ad) vector. Ad vectors are known to induce certain genes and impact innate response networks. Results provide insight into the innate immune response of cells to Ad transduction.

title: Embryonic fibroblast response to adenoviral vector infection (Mu11K-B)
description: Analysis of primary C57BL/6 embryonic fibroblasts infected with a 1st generation adenoviral (Ad) vector. Ad vectors are known to induce certain genes and impact innate response networks. Results provide insight into the innate immune response of cells to Ad transduction.

title: Fibroblast response to cytomegalovirus infection: time course
description: Analysis of fibroblasts infected with cytomegalovirus (CMV) AD169 strain or a derivative lacking the CMV chemokine receptor US28. Cells examined at 50, 72, and 98 hours post-infection. Results identify pathways affected by CMV and provide insight into the role of US28 in the late phase of infection.

title: Chito-oligomer effect on seedlings
description: Analysis of 14-day-old Columbia-0 seedlings treated with hydrolyzed crab-shell chitin or chito-octamer. Chitin is a major component of fungal walls and insect exoskeletons. Results provide insight into the signaling pathways involved in activating defense genes in response to chito-oligomers.

title: Alternative oxidase anti-sense silencing effect on leaves
description: Analysis of leaves of Columbia-0 plants transformed with an anti-sense mitochondrial alternative oxidase (AOX) construct to silence AOX. Results provide insight into the role of AOX in limiting the formation of reactive oxygen species and in the acclimation to oxidative stress.

title: Type 1 diabetes mellitus progression model
description: Analysis of pancreas of 3-week-old BDC2.5 transgenics that express a diabetogenic T cell receptor on the NOD or NOD.scid genetic background. BDC2.5/NOD has severe insulitis. BDC2.5/NOD.scid has severe insulitis and type 1 diabetes (T1D). Result provides insight into the pathogenesis of T1D.

title: DNA-binding protein SPT10 mutants
description: Analysis of spt10 null deletion and spt10(C388S) mutants. SPT10 encodes a putative histone acetyltranferase implicated as a global transcription regulator and is involved in chromatin maintenance. The C388S mutation disrupts a predicted zinc finger that may be part of the DNA-binding domain.

title: Exercise effect on diabetic skeletal muscle: time course
description: Analysis of experimental type 1 diabetic skeletal muscle subjected to endurance training. Diabetic muscle atrophy is accompanied by changes in the extracellular matrix (ECM). Results suggest the diabetes-induced decrease in gene expression of ECM proteins is partially attenuated by training.

title: Tumor necrosis factor effect on macrovascular umbilical vein endothelial cells
description: Analysis of macrovascular umbilical vein endothelial cells (HUVEC) stimulated with tumor necrosis factor (TNF)-alpha for 5 hours. TNF is a potent inflammatory stimulus. Results provide insight into the relevance of the diversity of endothelial cell subtypes for the response to inflammatory stimuli.

title: Tumor necrosis factor effect on microvascular endothelial cells
description: Analysis of microvascular endothelial cells (HMEC) stimulated with tumor necrosis factor (TNF)-alpha for 5 hours. TNF is a potent inflammatory stimulus. Results provide insight into the relevance of the diversity of endothelial cell subtypes for the response to inflammatory stimuli.

title: Ionizing radiation effect on lymphoid tissue of ATM protein kinase deficient mutants
description: Analysis of lymph nodes from ATM-deficient males exposed to ionizing radiation (IR). ATM regulates the cellular network induced by DNA double-strand breaks and is often mutated in lymphoid tumors. Results identify parallel induction of ATM-dependent pro- and antiapoptotic signals in response to IR.

title: Salt sensitive hypertension: kidney (RG-U34A)
description: Comparison of kidneys from a hypertensive salt-sensitive strain and a congenic salt-resistant strain, with much lower blood pressure (BP). Expression of genes located in the 2.4 cM BP quantitative trait locus (QTL) interval on chromosome 9 examined.

title: Salt sensitive hypertension: kidney (RG-U34B)
description: Comparison of kidneys from a hypertensive salt-sensitive strain and a congenic salt-resistant strain, with much lower blood pressure (BP). Expression of genes located in the 2.4 cM BP quantitative trait locus (QTL) interval on chromosome 9 examined.

title: Salt sensitive hypertension: kidney (RG-U34C)
description: Comparison of kidneys from a hypertensive salt-sensitive strain and a congenic salt-resistant strain, with much lower blood pressure (BP). Expression of genes located in the 2.4 cM BP quantitative trait locus (QTL) interval on chromosome 9 examined.

title: Neuroblastoma cell lines
description: Analysis of four cell lines initially established as neuroblastomas. Results indicate that the SK-N-MC cell line expresses all of the Ewing Family Tumor (EFT) signature genes. EFTs are small round blue cell tumors that show features of neuroectodermal differentiation.

title: Estrogen effect on estrogen receptor alpha positive breast cancer cell lines
description: Expression profiling of estrogen receptor positive breast cancer cell lines treated with estradiol for 24 hours. MCF-7, T47-D, and BT-474 breast cancer cell lines examined. Results identify candidate genes involved in estrogen stimulated breast cancer growth.

title: RNA polymerase II associated protein Paf1 depletion: time course
description: Analysis of cells depleted of Paf1, an RNA polymerase II associated protein. Cells were examined at various time points up to 8 hours following the inactivation of Paf1 expression from a tetracycline-regulated promoter using doxycyline (DOX). Results identify the primary targets of Paf1.

title: paf1 and ctr9 null mutants
description: Expression profiling of paf1 and ctr9 null mutants. Paf1p and Ctr9p are part of the Paf1 complex (Paf1C) of RNA polymerase II associated proteins. Results provide insight into the role of Paf1C in gene expression.

title: Mycobacterium tuberculosis clinical isolates
description: Analysis of 10 clinical isolates and 2 laboratory strains of Mycobacterium tuberculosis. Intraspecies genetic diversity is important in the pathogenicity and epidemiology of several pathogens. Results provide insight into the variability in gene expression among clinical isolates of M. tuberculosis.

title: Fullerene effect on vascular endothelial cells
description: Analysis of umbilical vein endothelial cells (ECs) treated with hydroxyl fullerene, a major nanomaterial. Nanomaterials are known to translocate into the circulation and may thus directly affect vascular ECs. Results provide insight into the effects of fullerenes on endothelial injury and toxicity.

title: Glycerol kinase knockout effect on liver
description: Expression profiling of livers of 4 male glycerol kinase knockout mutants. Glycerol kinase deficiency (GKD) is an X-linked inborn error of metabolism with metabolic and neurologic crises. Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of GKD.

title: Atrial and ventricular myocardium comparison (HG-U133B)
description: Analysis of right atria and left ventricles of hearts. While both the ventricle and atrium contract, the atrium is also a source and target for neurohumoral signals. Results provide insight into the molecular basis for the ultrastructural and functional differences between the atrium and ventricle.

title: Permanent atrial fibrillation (HG-U133B)
description: Analysis of atrium from patients with permanent atrial fibrillation (AF). AF is associated with extensive structural, contractile, and electrophysiological remodeling. Results identify adoption of a ventricular-like genomic signature as a general feature of the fibrillating atrium.

title: Beta-catenin activation effect on skin: time course
description: Analysis of skin of deltaNB-cateninER transgenics following the activation of beta-catenin for up to 7 days. Onset and duration of beta-catenin activation in deltaNB-cateninER transgenics controlled by 4-hydroxytamoxifen. Results provide insight into how beta-catenin induces hair follicle growth.

title: Alveolar rhabdomyosarcoma
description: Analysis of 14 tumor biopsies from children affected by alveolar rhabdomyosarcoma (ARMS). Seven patients were positive for the PAX3-FKHR fusion gene, which indicates an unfavorable prognosis. Results identify expression signatures that differentiate PAX3-FKHR positive from PAX3-FKHR negative ARMS.

title: Host response to malaria
description: Analysis of whole blood from Kenyan children with acute malaria or other febrile illnesses, both at hospital admission and after recovery. Samples collected during July September 2002. Results provide a perspective of the host response to malaria and further insight into processes of pathogenesis.

title: Thymocyte response to anti-T cell receptor antibody stimulation
description: Analysis of CD4+CD8+ double positive thymocytes following engagement of T cell receptor (TCR) with anti-α-chain (aVα2) or β-chain (aVβ5) antibody. Results suggest aVα does not induce gene expression changes, whereas aVβ activates a transcriptional program that mimics positive thymic selection.

title: Fibroblast response to serum: time course
description: Analysis of fibroblasts at various time points up to 36 hours after serum stimulation. The fibroblast serum response represents a wound healing program; cancer progression is likened to wound healing gone awry. Results provide insight into the significance of the wound healing process in cancer.

title: haa1 null mutant response to copper availability
description: Expression profiling of haa1 null mutants cultured in the presence of 100 uM copper sulfate or 100 uM bathocuproine sulfonate, a copper chelator. Haa1 is a homolog of Ace1, a copper-binding transcription factor. Results provide insight into the function of Haa1.

title: Embryonic kidney: ureteric bud and metanephric mesenchyme  (RG-U34A)
description: Analysis of ureteric buds (UBs) and metanephric mesenchyme (MM) from E13.5 kidneys. UB-secreted factors induce conversion of adjacent MM cells into nephrons. Results identify as potential regulators a set of 20 secreted molecules specific to the UB and conserved between species.

title: Endotoxin effect on leukocytes: time course (U133 2.0)
description: Analysis of leukocytes from 6 healthy subjects intravenously administered bacterial endotoxin. Leukocytes examined at various time points up to 6 hours post-infusion. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms involved in the propagation and resolution of the inflammatory response.

title: Lens epithelium-derived growth factor knockdown
description: Expression profiling of 293T cells depleted for lens epithelium-derived growth factor (LEDGF/p75). LEDGF/p75 binds to HIV integrase. Results identify LEDGF/p75 regulated genes, which may be preferential targets of HIV integration.

title: Embryonic kidney: ureteric bud and metanephric mesenchyme (RG-U34B)
description: Analysis of ureteric buds (UBs) and metanephric mesenchyme (MM) from E13.5 kidneys. UB-secreted factors induce conversion of adjacent MM cells into nephrons. Results identify as potential regulators a set of 20 secreted molecules specific to the UB and conserved between species.

title: Embryonic kidney: ureteric bud and metanephric mesenchyme (RG-U34C)
description: Analysis of ureteric buds (UBs) and metanephric mesenchyme (MM) from E13.5 kidneys. UB-secreted factors induce conversion of adjacent MM cells into nephrons. Results identify as potential regulators a set of 20 secreted molecules specific to the UB and conserved between species.

title: Embryonic kidney: ureteric bud and metanephric mesenchyme (MOE430 2.0)
description: Analysis of ureteric bud (UB) tips and stalks and metanephric mesenchyme (MM) from E12.5 kidneys. UB-secreted factors induce conversion of adjacent MM cells into nephrons. Results identify as potential regulators a set of 20 secreted molecules specific to the UB and conserved between species.

title: Oral squamous cell carcinoma
description: Analysis of oral squamous cell carcinoma (OSCC) cells from 16 patients. OSCC cells isolated from tumors by laser capture microdissection. Results identify a strong correlation between gene expression profile and tumor invasiveness in OSCC.

title: Follicular dendritic cell enriched splenocytes (MG U74A)
description: Analysis of follicular dendritic cell (FDCs) enriched splenocytes. FDCs are important in the formation of lymphoid germinal centers (GCs), where rapid B-cell proliferation and differentiation occur. Results identify transcripts that are overrepresented in cells associated with FDC networks in GCs.

title: p38 inhibitor PD169316 effect on embryonic stem derived differentiated cells (U74A Version 1)
description: Analysis of embryonic stem cells differentiated in the presence of PD169316, an inhibitor of p38 that blocks apoptosis without altering differentiation. Results identify gene families whose transcriptional regulation correlates with cell fate: differentiation with or without apoptosis.

title: p38 inhibitor PD169316 effect on embryonic stem derived differentiated cells (U74 Version 2)
description: Analysis of embryonic stem cells differentiated in the presence of PD169316, an inhibitor of p38 that blocks apoptosis without altering differentiation. Results identify gene families whose transcriptional regulation correlates with cell fate: differentiation with or without apoptosis.

title: Coronary artery atherosclerosis
description: Analysis of 51 coronary artery segments from the explanted hearts of 22 cardiac patients. Results provide insight into the pathogenesis and progression of atherosclerotic disease.

title: Follicular dendritic cell enriched splenocytes (MG U74B)
description: Analysis of follicular dendritic cell (FDCs) enriched splenocytes. FDCs are important in the formation of lymphoid germinal centers (GCs), where rapid B-cell proliferation and differentiation occur. Results identify transcripts that are overrepresented in cells associated with FDC networks in GCs.

title: Follicular dendritic cell enriched splenocytes (MG U74C)
description: Analysis of follicular dendritic cell (FDCs) enriched splenocytes. FDCs are important in the formation of lymphoid germinal centers (GCs), where rapid B-cell proliferation and differentiation occur. Results identify transcripts that are overrepresented in cells associated with FDC networks in GCs.

title: Ionizing radiation effect on monocytic leukemia cells
description: Analysis of leukemia THP-1 moncytes exposed to ionizing radiation (IR). IR exposure is associated with thrombotic vascular occlusion. Thrombosis in cancer is associated with poor prognosis. Results provide insight into the effect of IR on the expression of tissue factor, an activator of coagulation.

title: Dual specificity phosphatase 1-deficient spleen response to lipopolysaccharide
description: Analysis of spleens from dual specificity phosphatase 1 (DUSP1)-deficient mutants 6 hours after lipopolysaccharide (LPS) challenge. Mutants injected intraperitoneally with LPS. Results provide insight into the role of DUSP1 in the innate immune response to LPS endotoxin shock.

title: Muscle glycogen content effect on skeletal muscle
description: Analysis of skeletal muscles of MGSKO and GSL30 lines which lack or over-accumulate muscle glycogen, respectively. Liver was also analyzed in MGSKO to assess whether muscle glycogen loss has indirect effects on liver. The two largest glycogen stores in mammals are in skeletal muscle and liver.

title: Cocaine addiction effect on reward-related brain regions
description: Analysis of reward-related brain regions from Wistar males with restricted (1 h) or extended (6 h) daily access to cocaine. Escalated cocaine intake (ESC) developed in subjects with extended access. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying the transition to compulsive drug use.

title: Inbred Long Sleep and Inbred Short Sleep model of ethanol sensitivity: cerebellum (MG-430A)
description: Comparison of cerebella of Inbred Long Sleep (ILS) and Inbred Short Sleep (ISS) animals. ILS animals are more sensitive than ISS animals to ethanol. Initial sensitivity to ethanol is a predictor of alcohol abuse. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of differential ethanol sensitivity.

title: Inbred Long Sleep and Inbred Short Sleep model of ethanol sensitivity: cerebellum (MG-430B)
description: Comparison of cerebella of Inbred Long Sleep (ILS) and Inbred Short Sleep (ISS) animals. ILS animals are more sensitive than ISS animals to ethanol. Initial sensitivity to ethanol is a predictor of alcohol abuse. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of differential ethanol sensitivity.

title: Nonsense-mediated mRNA decay factor upf1 null mutant response to global transcription inhibition: time course
description: Analysis of wild type and mutant upf1 strains up to 60 minutes after treatment with 10 ug/ml thiolutin, a global transcription inhibitor. Upf1 is an RNA helicase required for nonsense-mediated mRNA decay (NMD). Results identify genes with differential expression over time between the two strains.

title: Hypothalamoneurohypophyseal system response to dehydration
description: Analysis of the hypothalamoneurohypophyseal system (HNS) in fluid-deprived males. The HNS components examined were hypothalamic paraventricular and supraoptic nuclei and neurointermediate lobe of the pituitary. Results identify candidate genes of HNS activity and remodeling induced by dehydration.

title: Ulcerative colitis and Crohn's disease comparison: peripheral blood mononuclear cells
description: Analysis of peripheral blood mononuclear cells (PBMCs) from Crohn's disease (CD) and ulcerative colitis (UC) patients. Results identify a PBMC expression signature that distinguishes between CD and UC, suggesting that diagnosis of these two inflammatory bowel diseases (IBD) using PBMCs is possible.

title: Akt kinase constitutive activation effect on embryonic stem cells
description: Analysis of embryonic stem (ES) cells expressing a myristoylated, active form of Akt (myr-Akt) kinase. Myr-Akt expression maintains pluripotency of ES cells even in the absence of leukemia inhibitory factor (LIF). Results demonstrate Akt signaling is sufficient to maintain ES cell pluripotency.

title: Motexafin gadolinium and zinc effect on Ramos B-cell lymphoma line
description: Analysis of Ramos B-cell lymphoma cultures following 4 hour treatment with anticancer agent motexafin gadolinium (MGd), zinc acetate (25 or 50 uM), or combinations of MGd and zinc. Results provide insight into the molecular changes that accompany the disruption of intracellular zinc homeostasis.

title: Lymph node and tonsil comparison
description: Analysis of lymph node (sinuses) and tonsil (no sinuses), highly similar secondary lymphoid organs. Metastatic tumor cells are preferentially arrested in the lymph node sinuses. Results identify signature genes that are prime candidates for mediating adhesion of tumor cells to sinusoidal cells.

title: Abiotic stress-inducing agents effect on suspension cell cultures
description: Analysis of suspension cell cultures subjected to various abiotic stress-inducing agents. Results indicate that expression of components of the phosphorylating respiratory chain and TCA cycle remained largely constant, but that of alternative components varied in response to the various treatments.

title: c-Jun N-terminal kinase pathway activation and suppression effect on aortic vascular smooth muscle cells
description: Analysis of aortic vascular smooth muscle cells following c-Jun N-terminal kinase (JNK) activation or JNK suppression with H202 treatment to induce oxidative stress (OS). OS is linked to abdominal aortic aneurysm (AAA) and activates JNK. Results provide insight into the role of JNK in AAA.

title: Arginine deprivation effect on tumorigenic hepatic cells
description: Analysis of neoplastic hepatic cells subjected to arginine deprivation. Results identify arginine responsive genes that become unresponsive to arginine in tumorigenic cells.

title: Environmental enrichment effect on hippocampus subjected to early-life seizures
description: Analysis of hippocampi of animals that were injected with kainic acid at postnatal day (P) 20 to induce early-life seizures and then housed in an enriched environment until P30. Results provide insight into the efficacy of environmental enrichment in reversing early-life seizure-induced changes.

title: Breast cancer cell lines response to chemotherapeutic drugs: time course
description: Analysis of 4 breast cell lines treated for up to 36 hrs with the chemotherapeutic agents 5-fluorouracil (5FU), doxorubicin (DOX), or etoposide (ETOP), a drug mechanistically similar to DOX. Expression profiles for DOX- and 5FU-treated cells were used to successfully predict the response to ETOP.

title: Immortalized suprachiasmatic nucleus cell line across circadian cycles: time course
description: Analysis of suprachiasmatic nucleus (SCN) immortalized cell line SCN2.2 at 6 hour intervals over 2 circadian cycles. The master clock responsible for the regulation of circadian rhythms in the body is located in the SCN. Results indicate that SCN2.2 retains intrinsic rhythm-generating properties.

title: Immortalized endothelial cell line response to atorvastatin
description: Analysis of EA.hy926, an immortalized umbilical vein endothelial cell (HUVEC) line, and its primary cell counterpart following treatment with HMG-CoA reductase inhibitor atorvastatin to inhibit the mevalonate pathway. Results suggest EA.hy926 cells have retained endothelial cell-specific features.

title: Osteoblast differentiation (MG-U74A)
description: Analysis of FACS-sorted bone cells 7 and 17 days following induction of differentiation. Cells sorted based on GFP expression from a promoter that becomes active in the preosteoblastic stage between days 5 and 7 or from one that remains inactive until the osteoblastic stage between days 15 and 17.

title: Osteoblast differentiation (MG-U74B)
description: Analysis of FACS-sorted bone cells 7 and 17 days following induction of differentiation. Cells sorted based on GFP expression from a promoter that becomes active in the preosteoblastic stage between days 5 and 7 or from one that remains inactive until the osteoblastic stage between days 15 and 17.

title: Osteoblast differentiation (MG-U74C)
description: Analysis of FACS-sorted bone cells 7 and 17 days following induction of differentiation. Cells sorted based on GFP expression from a promoter that becomes active in the preosteoblastic stage between days 5 and 7 or from one that remains inactive until the osteoblastic stage between days 15 and 17.

title: Nodose and dorsal root ganglia comparison (MG-U74A)
description: Comparison of whole nodose ganglia (NG) and dorsal root ganglia (DRG) vs. the population of laser-captured visceral sensory neurons. Results identify striking differences and the need for microdissection when studying visceral sensory neurons because of dilution of signal by somatic sensory neurons.

title: Nodose and dorsal root ganglia comparison (MG-430 2.0)
description: Analysis of laser-captured neurons of the nodose (NG) and dorsal root ganglia (DRG). Vagal afferents arise from NG and convey mostly physiological information, while spinal afferents arise from DRG and transmit noxious signals. Results elucidate molecular identities for these different properties.

title: Patulin cytotoxic effect
description: Expression profiling of S288C cells treated with 50 ppm patulin for 2 hours. Patulin is a toxic and colorless crystalline antibiotic produced by several molds that can grow naturally on fruits and vegetables. Results provide insight into the mechanisms underlying the cytotoxicity of patulin.

title: Oncogene-induced sensescence in vitro model
description: Analysis of transformed cell lines that either exhibit oncogene-induced senescence (OIS) triggered by MEK activation or bypass OIS. Senescent cells exist in premalignant tumors but not in malignant ones. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of OIS.

title: Ikaros mutant thymic tumors
description: Analysis of thymic tumors or premalignant thymocytes that contains the hypomorphic Ikaros mutation (IkL/L). Ikaros is a tumor suppressor in T cells. Results provide insight into the molecular changes involved in Ikaros-dependent tumor development.

title: Myocilin over-secretion effect on the retina
description: Analysis of retinas of transgenics that secret high levels of myocilin (MYOC) into the aqueous humor of the eye. Results provide insight into the role of myocilin in the pathogenesis of glaucoma.

title: Dopaminergic neurons from the substantia nigra pars compacta and ventral tegmental area
description: Analysis of dopaminergic neurons of the substantia nigra pars compacta (SNc) and the ventral tegmental area (VTA) from normal animals. SNc dopaminergic neurons are more susceptible to degeneration in Parkinson's disease than VTA dopaminergic neurons.

title: Kainate-induced status epilepticus effect on immature hippocampus: time course
description: Analysis of hippocampi of immature animals up to 10 days following kainite (KA) induced status epilepticus (SE). Unlike adults, KA-induced SE in immature animals causes neither cell death nor recurrent spontaneous seizures. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of this difference.

title: VTS1 deletion mutant
description: Analysis of a strain lacking Vts1p. Vts1p is a putative post-transcriptional regulator that uses a sterile alpha motif (SAM) domain to bind an RNA hairpin termed the Smaug recognition element (SRE). Results identify genes that may be regulated by Vts1p and contain one or more copies of the SRE.

title: Nitric oxide effect on soluble guanylate cyclase deficient cells
description: Analysis of soluble guanylate cyclase-deficient U937 cells exposed to the nitric oxide (NO) donor S-nitrosoglutathione. Cells treated in the presence of dibutyryl-cAMP (Bt2cAMP) to block signaling due to NO-induced decreases in cAMP. Results provide insight into the cGMP-independent effects of NO.

title: HIV-1 burden effect on mononuclear cell response to co-infection with Neisseria gonorrhoeae
