description: Analysis of peripheral blood mononuclear cells infected with various titers of HIV-1 and exposed to a single infectious dose of Neisseria gonorrhoeae (Gc). Results provide insight into the role of viral burden in defining the cellular contribution to host immune response to co-infection with Gc.

title: RPE65 null mutant model of Leber's congenital amaurosis
description: Analysis of retinas of RPE65 null mutants at 2, 4 and 6 months of age. RPE65 is highly expressed in retinal pigment epithelial cells. Mutations in REP65 cause 10-15% of Leber's congenital amaurosis (LCA) cases, a severe form of retinal dystrophy. Results provide insight into early LCA progression.

title: Hypoxia effect on HIF-1 alpha null hepatocytes
description: Analysis of hypoxia-inducible factor-1alpha (HIF-1alpha) null mutant hepatocytes subjected to hypoxic conditions for 8 hours. The HIF-1alpha transcription factor is a key regulator of oxygen homeostasis. Results provide insight into hepatocyte gene expression changes induced by short-term hypoxia.

title: Urethane-induced lung tumor model of pulmonary adenocarcinoma
description: Analysis of lung tumors that develop following treatment with urethane. Urethane-induced lung tumors exhibit similar histological appearance and molecular changes to human pulmonary adenocarcinoma (AC). Results compared with those from human AC (GDS1650).

title: Pulmonary adenocarcinoma
description: Analysis of pulmonary adenocarcinomas (AC). Carcinogen exposure is responsible for the majority of ACs. Results compared with those obtained from a urethane-induced lung tumor model in the mouse (GDS1649), and provide insight into the conserved pathways underlying the development of AC.

title: POU-domain transcription factor Brn3a knockout effect on embryonic ganglia (MG-U74A)
description: Analysis of embryonic day 13.5 trigeminal ganglia of Brn3a knockout mutants. Brn3a encodes a POU-domain transcription factor. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying the essential role of the Brn3a protein in normal axon growth and neuronal survival.

title: POU-domain transcription factor Brn3a knockout effect on embryonic ganglia (MG-U74B)
description: Analysis of embryonic day 13.5 trigeminal ganglia of Brn3a knockout mutants. Brn3a encodes a POU-domain transcription factor. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying the essential role of the Brn3a protein in normal axon growth and neuronal survival.

title: Linker histone H1 depletion
description: Analysis of embryonic stem (ES) cells from histone H1c, H1d, H1e triple null mutants. The triple-H1 null ES cells have close to a 50% reduction in H1 content. Results provide insight into the mechanisms by which linker H1 affects chromatin structure and gene transcription in vivo.

title: Dendritic cell subpopulations: spleen (MG-U74A)
description: Analysis of three dendritic cell (DC) subpopulations from BALB/c spleens: interferon-producing killer DCs (IKDCs), plasmacytoid DCs (PDCs), and conventional DCs (cDCs). Results identify IKDCs as a distinct DC lineage and provide insight into the role of IKDCs in linking innate and adaptive immunity.

title: Medullary thymic epithelial cells
description: Comparison of medullary thymic epithelial cells (TECs) to cortical TECs, dendritic cells, and macrophages. Aberrent expression of tissue-restricted antigens, called promiscuous gene expression (PGE), is a property of the thymic stroma. Results provide insight into the scope of PGE in the thymus.

title: Dendritic cell subpopulations: spleen (MG-U74B)
description: Analysis of three dendritic cell (DC) subpopulations from BALB/c spleens: interferon-producing killer DCs (IKDCs), plasmacytoid DCs (PDCs), and conventional DCs (cDCs). Results identify IKDCs as a distinct DC lineage and provide insight into the role of IKDCs in linking innate and adaptive immunity.

title: Dendritic cell subpopulations: spleen (MG-U74C)
description: Analysis of three dendritic cell (DC) subpopulations from BALB/c spleens: interferon-producing killer DCs (IKDCs), plasmacytoid DCs (PDCs), and conventional DCs (cDCs). Results identify IKDCs as a distinct DC lineage and provide insight into the role of IKDCs in linking innate and adaptive immunity.

title: Fetal alcohol exposure effect on hippocampus
description: Analysis of hippocampi of 5-day-old animals subjected to fetal alcohol exposure (FAE) with 5% ETOH. FAE affects the development and function of the hippocampus.

title: Transcription factor Egr3 expression effect on primary myotubes (MG-430A)
description: Analysis of primary myotubes expressing wild-type or inactive truncated Egr3. Transcription factor Egr3 activity is critical for the development of muscle spindles, skeletal muscle stretch receptors that mediate axial and limb proprioception.

title: Enigma mitochondrial protein knockdown
description: Analysis of Kc-167 cells following knockdown of Enigma (Egm) using RNAi. Egm is a mitochondrial protein with homology to enzymes of the beta-oxidation of fatty acids. Results provide insight into the mechanisms underlying the increased oxidative stress tolerance conferred by decreased Egm levels.

title: Expression data from different research centers
description: Comparison of expression data from the Translational Genomics Research Institute to that from the Children's National Medical Center in Washington, DC. Data consists of normal kidney, liver, and spleen expression profiles.

title: Parathyroid hormone-related protein knockdown effect on breast cancer cells
description: Analysis of MDA-MB-231 breast cancer cells depleted for parathyroid hormone-related protein (PTHrP) using siRNA. PTHrP affects the proliferative and invasive activities of breast cancer cells and regulates their sensitivity to apoptotic stimuli. Results identify PTHrP-regulated tumor-relevant genes.

title: Papillary thyroid carcinoma
description: Analysis of papillary thyroid carcinoma (PTC) tumors from 9 patients. PTC accounts for about 80% of all thyroid cancers. These results, together with those obtained from custom miRNA chips, indicate the involvement of several miRNAs and the receptor tyrosine kinase KIT in PTC pathogenesis.

title: Staphylococcus aureus response to oxidative stress: time course
description: Analysis of Staphylococcus aureus cells exposed for 10 or 20 minutes to hydrogen peroxide to induce oxidative stress. Macrophages and other lymphocytes use reactive oxygen species such as H2O2 to destroy the bacteria. Results provide insight into mechanisms involved in S. aureus-host interactions.

title: Head and neck squamous cell carcinoma tumors harboring human papillomavirus
description: Analysis of 8 head and neck squamous cell carcinoma (HNSCC) tumors positive for human papilloma virus (HPV). 28 HNSCC HPV negative tumors examined. Between 15% and 35% of HNSCCs harbor HPV DNA. Results provide insight into the effect of HPV infection in HNSCC.

title: Respiratory burst oxidase homologs effect on wound responsiveness
description: Analysis of systemic leaves from mutant plants with antisense-mediated reduction in respiratory burst oxidase homologs (Rboh) activity. Rboh are homologs of gp91phox, the catalytic subunit of the phagocytic NADPH oxidase. Results provide insight into the role of Rboh in the wound response.

title: Keratinocyte stem cell–enriched hair follicle bulge cells
description: Comparison of outer root sheath (ORS) cells of the hair follicle bulge with other defined ORS cell subpopulations within the follicle. Results provide insight into the biological distinctiveness of hair follicle bulge cells, suggesting the bulge is a repository for keratinocyte stem cells (KSCs).

title: Non-diseased lung tissue
description: Analysis of non-diseased lungs from 23 multi-organ donors.  Upper and lower lobe peripheral sections of the lung were examined. Donors varied in age, sex, smoking history, and ethnicity. Results provide a reference for microarray studies of pulmonary disease.

title: Histone H3 and H4 amino terminal deletions
description: Expression profiling of H3 and H4 amino terminal deletion mutants grown under conditions of amino acid starvation, which induce Gcn4p activated transcription. Results provide insight into the contribution of histone amino termini modifications to gene expression.

title: Werner syndrome protein and poly(ADP-ribose) polymerase-1 null mutants
description: Analysis of embryonic fibroblast cells lacking Werner syndrome (WS) protein (Wrn), or poly(ADP-ribose) polymerase-1 (PARP-1), or both. Mutations in Wrn or PARP-1 result in genomic instability. Results provide insight into tumor progression, senescence, oxidative stress and aging.

title: T cell leukemia cell response to human herpesvirus 6 infection: time course
description: Analysis of an adult T cell leukemia cell line (TaY) following infection with human herpesvirus type 6B strain OK. Cells examined up to 5 days post-infection. Chronically-infected TaY cells were also examined. Results identify candidate genes that regulate the immune response during viral infection.

title: Cumulus oocyte complex during ovulation: time course
description: Analysis of cumulus oocyte complexes (COCs) isolated from ovaries prior to ovulation or from the oviduct after ovulation. Follicular growth stimulated using equine chorionic gonadotropin (CG) and ovulation induced using human CG. Results identify candidate genes in COCs that impact ovulation.

title: Quercetin effect on hepatic cytochrome P-450 oxidoreductase null mutants
description: Analysis of cytochrome-P450 oxidoreductase (POR) null mutants at 24 hours following consumption of anti-carcinogenic flavonoid, quercetin. Results identify a diminished transcriptomic response in KO compared to WT in all tissues examined and provide insight into the bioactive nature of quercetin.

title: Exhaustive endurance exercise effect on skeletal muscle: time course
description: Expression profiling of vastus lateralis muscles 3 and 48 hours after a 75-minute bout of high-intensity cycling. Results identify transcriptional pathways activated in skeletal muscles recovering from endurance exercise.

title: Dendritic cell response to measles virus infection: time course
description: Analysis of dendritic cells (DCs) for up to 24 hours after infection with measles virus (MV). MV induces immunosuppression followed by lasting immunity. DCs appear to play a role in this effect. Results provide insight into MV-DC interactions and suggest mechanisms for MV-modulated immune response.

title: Cardiac allograft rejection: time course
description: Expression profiling of endomyocardial tissues from 3 subjects before, during, and after a rejection episode.  Cardiac allograft rejection is a significant clinical problem in the early phase after heart transplantation and requires frequent surveillance with endomyocardial biopsy.

title: Hereditary gingival fibromatosis
description: Analysis of gingival tissues from a patient with hereditary gingival fibromatosis (HGF). HGF is a benign disorder characterized by a slow progressive enlargement of the gingiva. This hypertrophic overgrowth of the gingiva may completely cover the teeth.

title: Sleep deprivation effect on the brain: time course
description: Analysis of brain of Canton-S females deprived of sleep by perturbations during their normal sleep period. Perturbation effect also assessed during their active period to control for its effect during sleep deprivation. Results suggest processes altered during prolonged wakefulness and during sleep.

title: Low-shear modeled microgravity effect
description: Analysis of wild type BY4743 cells grown in a low-shear modeled microgravity environment (LSMMG). LSMMG environment produced using a high aspect rotating vessel. Results provide insight into the response to the microgravity environment experienced during space flight.

title: Various lung cancer cell lines
description: Expression profiling of a set of 29 lung cancer cell lines consisting of 10 non-small cell adenocarcinoma, 10 small cell cancer, and 9 squamous cell cancer lines.  Gene expression results analyzed in relation to the sensitivity of each cell line to commonly used anti-cancer agents.

title: Hypocotyl response to phototropic and gravitropic stimulation
description: Analysis of localized expression patterns in hypocotyl tissue flanks from etiolated seedlings following mock, 2h phototropic, or 2h gravitropic stimulation. Results identify genes exhibiting differential expression between opposing flanks of tropically stimulated seedlings.

title: Notch receptors and Delta ligand interaction effect
description: Analysis of cell mixtures consisting of cultured S2 cells expressing the full length (NFull) or C-terminal truncated Notch (NDCterm) and S2 cells expressing the ligand Delta. NFull and Delta interaction induce epidermal differentiation, while NDCterm and Delta induce neuronal differentiation.

title: Plakoglobin mutant heart response to endurance training
description: Analysis of arrhythmogenic right ventricle from plakoglobin heterozygous mutants subjected to endurance training. Mutations in plakoglobin, a component of the desmosome, result in arrhythmogenic right ventricular cardiomyopathy (ARVC). Results identify transcriptional response induced by training.

title: Agrobacterium tumefaciens infection effect on cells: time course
description: Analysis of LER cells up to 48 hours after infection with oncogenic Agrobacterium tumefaciens (A.t.). Unlike all known bacterial phytopathogens, broadly-infectious A.t. lacks the hypersensitive response-inducing HRP genes. Results identify the host transcriptional response to this unusual pathogen.

title: Transcription factor Nrl deficiency effect on photoreceptor development
description: Analysis of photoreceptors (PRs) from wild type and Nrl deficient retinas at various developmental stages. PRs isolated based on transgene GFP expression from an Nrl promoter. Nrl ablation leads to cones at the expense of rods. Results provide insight into the regulation of PR development.

title: Altered mitochondrial alternative oxidase expression effect on leaves
description: Analysis of five-week-old leaves under non-stress conditions from wild type gl1 and two transgenic lines that overexpress (S5) or inhibit (A1-1) mitochondrial alternative oxidase (AOX) synthesis. Results provide insight into the role of AOX in regulating reactive oxygen species (ROS) in leaves.

title: Self-renewing memory B cell
description: Analysis of plasma, germinal center, and memory B cells (mBCs) from animals immunized with the T-dependent antigen, NP-CGG. MBC, memory T (mTCs), and long-term hematopoietic stem cells (Lt-HSCs) undergo self-renewal. Results indicate mBCs share a transcriptional program with mTCs and Lt-HSCs.

title: Nanosecond pulsed electric fields effect: time course
description: Expression profiling of Jurkat cells 30min and 60min after exposure to nanosecond pulsed electric fields (nsPEFs) for two consecutive 10 ns pulses at 280kV/cm. Results provide insight into the early response genes to DNA damage caused by electric field radiation.

title: DNA methyltransferase inhibitor 5-aza-2'-deoxycytidine effect on prostate cancer cell lines
description: Analysis of prostate cancer cell lines after treatment with the DNA methyltransferase inhibitor 5-Aza-2'-deoxycytidine (5-aza-dC). Aberrant DNA methylation is an early event in the development of prostate cancer. Results identify hypermethylated genes whose expression is induced by 5-aza-dC.

title: Androgen sensitive and insensitive prostate cancer cell lines: expression profiles
description: Analysis of androgen sensitive (AS) and insensitive (AI) prostate cancer cell lines. Despite the wide use of these cell lines as model systems, a global genotypic characterization of these cell lines is currently lacking. Results identify differences in gene expression profiles.

title: Anemia induced by acute renal rejection: peripheral blood lymphocytes
description: Analysis of peripheral blood lymphocytes from 4 renal allograft recipients with acute rejection and concurrent anemia. Compromised renal function after renal allograft transplantation often results in anemia. Results provide insight into the molecular events underlying anemia in acute rejection.

title: Endothelial progenitor cells in fetal liver
description: Analysis of endothelial progenitor cells (EPCs) from fetal liver (LEPs). EPCs have a high angiogenic capacity at sites of tissue injury and, thus, significant therapeutic potential. Results show that LEPs within the CD31+Sca1+ stem cell subset possess the endothelial progenitor activity.

title: Dark-grown phytochrome phyA phyB double mutants
description: Analysis of dark-grown Col phytochrome mutants given 1 hour of white light to induce germination, followed by 3 days in darkness. Phytochromes mediate a profound developmental shift upon light exposure. Results reveal signaling network paths between photoreceptors and target developmental genes.

title: Dark-grown phytochrome and cryptochrome mutants
description: Analysis of dark grown Ler seedlings mutant for phytochromes A and B, or cryptochromes cry1 and cry2, or both. Results provide insight into the structure of the signaling network between the photoreceptor families and the target developmental genes that respond to light.

title: Dark-grown phytochrome phyA phyB single and double mutants
description: Analysis of dark-grown Col phytochrome mutants given 1 hour of white light to induce germination, followed by 3 days in darkness. Phytochromes mediate a profound developmental shift upon light exposure. Results reveal signaling network paths between photoreceptors and target developmental genes.

title: MyD88-deficient macrophage response to lipopolysaccharide and E. coli
description: Analysis of MyD88 null mutant macrophages treated with LPS or live E. coli. MyD88 transduces cell signaling events downstream of Toll-like receptors, a key component of host defense. Results suggest most of the host response to endotoxin or live bacteria is actually regulated independently of MyD88.

title: MyD88-deficient macrophage response to lipopolysaccharide and E. coli (dye swap)
description: Analysis of MyD88 null mutant macrophages treated with LPS or live E. coli. MyD88 transduces cell signaling events downstream of Toll-like receptors, a key component of host defense. Results suggest most of the host response to endotoxin or live bacteria is actually regulated independently of MyD88.

title: Aldosterone effect on kidney cortical collecting cell line: time course
description: Analysis of kidney epithelial cortical collecting duct cells treated with aldosterone for 1 or 6 hours. Aldosterone stimulates Na+ transport in tight epithelia. Results identify candidate genes that regulate Na+ transport via the epithelial Na+ channel and mediate the early response to aldosterone.

title: Transcriptional regulator PpsR overexpressing and mutant strains
description: Analysis of PpsR overexpressing and mutant strains grown at normal 20% oxygen. Expression examined in wild type cells at 0.5% oxygen. PpsR represses the transcription of a subset of biosynthetic genes in photosystem (PS) formation. Results suggest that PpsR is a master regulator of PS development.

title: bHLH transcription factor MyoD knockdown effect on myoblast differentiation
description: Analysis of C2C12 myoblast cell line following RNAi knockdown of the bHLH transcription factor MyoD. RNA prepared from cells after 1, 3, and 6 days of myogenic differentiation in DMEM medium supplemented with 2% horse serum. Results identify targets of MyoD.

title: Heat shock stress response: time course
description: Expression profiling of wild type JN54 cells following heat shock treatment at 43 degrees C for 30 and 60 minutes.  Results compared to expression profile of ssa1 ssa2 double deletion mutant.  Ssa1p and Ssa2p are cytosolic molecular chaperones.

title: 2,4-dibencilaminoquinazoline effect on various cancer cell lines
description: Analysis of breast HTB26, colon HT29, and bladder T24 cancer cell lines after treatment with 2,4-dibencilaminoquinazoline, which exhibits cytostatic and apoptotic effects. Gene expression examined after 2,4-dibencilaminoquinazoline induces caspase activation or DNA fragmentation.

title: Ewing family tumor and neuroblastoma comparison
description: Analysis of Ewing family tumor (EFT) and neuroblastoma (NB) samples. Distinguishing EFTs from other small round blue cell tumors (SRBCTs), such as NBs, by histologic methods is often difficult. Results identify EF-associated genes that enable molecular discrimination between EFTs and other SRBCTs.

title: Bleomycin effect on mutagen-sensitive lymphoblastoid cell lines
description: Analysis of mutagen-sensitive lymphoblastoid cell lines after exposure to bleomycin. Mutagen-sensitive cells exhibit a high number of bleomycin-induced chromatid breaks. Mutagen sensitivity (MS) reflects an individual's susceptibility to sporadic cancers. Results identify genes involved in MS.

title: Transcription factors Mixer and Sox17beta expression effect on naïve ectodermal tissue
description: Analysis of naïve ectodermal tissue excised from embryos injected with Mixer or Sox17beta mRNA. Mixer and Sox17beta are important in endoderm specification during embryogenesis. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying the regulation of endoderm development.

title: SOD1-G93A transgenic model of amyotrophic lateral sclerosis: oculomotor nucleus
description: Analysis of oculomotor motor neurons (OMNs) of SOD1-G93A transgenic model of amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (ALS) at 6 and 10 weeks of age. ALS spares the ocular neurons suggesting they are intrinsically protected against ALS. Results instead suggest OMNs actively adapt to the ALS-inducing mutation.

title: Thyroid hormone triiodothyronine effect on tadpole brain: time course
description: Analysis of brains of NF stage 54 (NF54) premetamorphic tadpoles treated with thyroid hormone (TH) triiodothyronine (T3) for 24 or 48 hours. Premetamorphic brain ventricle cells proliferate and differentiate in response to TH. Results identify genes involved in the TH-induced proliferation pathway.

title: Thyroid hormone triiodothyronine effect on tadpole limb bud: time course
description: Analysis of limb buds of NF stage 54 (NF54) premetamorphic tadpoles treated with thyroid hormone (TH) triiodothyronine (T3) for 14, 24 or 48 hours. Premetamorphic limb buds proliferate and differentiate in response to TH. Results identify genes involved in the TH-induced proliferation pathway.

title: Thyroid hormone triiodothyronine effect on tadpole tail: time course
description: Analysis of tails of NF stage 54 (NF54) premetamorphic tadpoles treated with thyroid hormone (TH) triiodothyronine (T3) up to 48 hours. NF61 tadpoles were in 0.1xMMR till they reached NF62. Premetamorphic tails are resorbed in response to TH. Results identify genes involved in TH-induced resorption.

title: Abscisic acid effect on small GTPase rop10-1 mutant seedlings
description: Analysis of small GTPase rop10-1 knockout mutant seedlings following treatment with 1 uM abscisic acid (ABA). ROP10 is involved in the negative regulation of ABA responses. Results provide insight into the mechanisms underlying the regulation of the ROP10-mediated ABA signaling network.

title: Gonadal somatic cells during the critical period of sex determination: time course
description: Analysis of gonadal somatic cells from male and female embryos at 10.5 and 11.5 days post coitum (dpc), which span the critical period of male sex determination. Results provide insight into sex determination and gonad differentiation, and identify candidate genes for sexual dysgenesis syndromes.

title: HIV encephalitis: brain frontal cortex
description: Analysis of brain frontal cortex of HIV-seropositive patients with HIV encephalitis (HIVE). HIVE affects >40% of AIDS patients, promoting neurodegeneration and cognitive impairment. Results suggest HIV-mediated dysregulation of genes involved in neuronal maintenance might play an important role.

title: UV-B radiation effect on UV resistance locus 8 and transcription factor HY5 mutant leaves
description: Analysis of leaves of UV resistance locus 8 uvr8-1 and transcription factor hy5-1 mutants following exposure to a physiological dose of UV-B. Results provide insight into the role of UVR8 and HY5 in the response to UV-B radiation and into the mechanisms of UV-B perception and signal transduction.

title: DBA/2J model of glaucoma: retina
description: Analysis of retinas from strain DBA/2J with elevated intraocular pressure (IOP). A model for glaucoma, DBA/2J has mutations that lead to iris atrophy and pigment dispersion. These conditions result in increased IOP. Results provide insight into the molecular changes associated with IOP elevation.

title: MicroRNA miR-122 antisense inhibition effect on livers
description: Analysis of liver from C57BL/6 adult males treated with an antisense oligonucleotide (ASO) targeting liver-specific microRNA (miRNA) miR-122. miR-122 is expressed at high levels in the adult liver, making up 70% of all miRNA. Results provide insight into the role of miR-122 in the adult liver.

title: Autocrine platelet-derived growth factor inhibition effect on malignant gliomas
description: Analysis of U87 glioblastoma (GBM) cell clones overexpressing a dominant-negative form of platelet-derived growth factor (PDGF) A subunit to inactive the PDGF autocrine signaling loop. The autocrine PDGF loop is a hallmark of GBM. Results identify genes regulated by oncogenic PDGF signaling.

title: Caerulein effect on transcription factor Mist1 null pancreas
description: Analysis of pancreas from transcription factor Mist1 knockouts (Mist1KO) injected with caerulein.  Mist1KOs exhibit disrupted cell morphology in adult pancreatic acini; caerulein induces acute pancreatitis. Results identify genes that may contribute to susceptibility and initiation of pancreatitis.

title: Papillary thyroid cancer
description: Expression profiling of 7 papillary thyroid carcinoma (PTC) samples. PTC is the most common type of thyroid cancer, representing up to 80% of all malignant thyroid tumors. Results provide insight into potential molecular markers for PTC.

title: Heat shock transcription factor HSF1 depleted cells response to heat shock: time course
description: Analysis of HSF1-depleted HeLa cells at various time points up to 24 hours following heat shock treatment at 43 degrees C. Heat shock transcription factor HSF1 silenced using RNA interference (siHSF1_1, siHSF1_2). Results provide insight into the structure and function of the HSF1 signaling network.

title: Sucrose effect on dark-grown seedlings
description: Analysis of Columbia glabra (gl1-1) seedlings grown in the dark at 23°C for 4 days then treated with 90 mM sucrose for 6h. Sugar status regulates mechanisms controlling growth and development of plants. Results identify sucrose-modulated genes and provide insight into sugar sensing mechanisms.

title: Vdelta1 and Vdelta2 gamma delta T cells response to non-TCR agonist  stimulation
description: Analysis of Vdelta1 (Vd1) and Vdelta2 (Vd2) gamma delta (gd) T cells following stimulation with a non-TCR mediated agonist, PMA/ionomycin. Vd1 and Vd2 cells differ in tissue tropism, TCR usage, and agonist response. Results provide insight into the functional differences between Vd1 and Vd2 cells.

title: Arachidonic acid effect on prostate cancer cells
description: Analysis of PC-3 prostate cancer cells incubated with arachidonic acid (AA).  AA is an omega-6 fatty acid shown to induce cancer cell proliferation. Results suggest AA plays an important role in stimulation of growth-related genes and proliferation via phosphatidylinositol 3-kinase (PI3K) signaling.

title: Primary mesodermal cells from various mutants perturbed for muscle development
description: Analysis of primary mesodermal cells from mutant embryos perturbed for the development of founder cells, fusion-competent myoblasts, or both myoblast types. 12 mutant genotypes examined. Results identify candidate myoblast subpopulation-specific genes and provide insight into embryonic myogenesis.

title: Vier F-Box VFB triple mutant seedlings
description: Expression profiling of 10-day-old light-grown Vier F-Box (VFB) triple mutant seedlings. F-box proteins are receptors for the plant growth hormone auxin and are involved in ubiquitin-mediated protein degradation.

title: MADS-box FBP7 mutant seedlings
description: Expression profiling of 5-day-old light-grown fbp7-3 mutant seedlings. FLORAL BINDING PROTEIN 7 (FBP7) is a MADS-box protein that is necessary and sufficient to determine ovule identity. Results provide insight into the molecular control of ovule development.

title: COP9 signalosome subunit 4 CSN4 mutant seedlings
description: Expression profiling of 7-day-old light-grown csn4-1 mutant seedlings. CSN4 is subunit 4 of the COP9 signalosome (CSN), a multifunctional protein complex of the ubiquitin-proteasome pathway. CSN is essential for development, but little is known about the specific role of its eight subunits.

title: Succinate semialdehyde dehydrogenase deficiency effect on the brain
description: Analysis of brain hippocampi, cerebella, and cortices of succinate semialdehyde dehydrogenase (SSADH)-deficient mutants at 3 weeks of age, when fatal seizures occur. Results indicate that SSADH deficiency results in the dysregulation of genes involved in myelin structure and compaction.

title: Primary epithelial cell cultures from prostate tumors
description: Analysis of epithelial cell cultures from prostate tumor explants. Results identify an epithelial-restricted transcription profile that can be integrated with tumor grade and clinical information with the aim of discriminating indolent and aggressive prostate tumors that are histologically similar.

title: SOD1-G93A transgenic model of amyotrophic lateral sclerosis: spinal cord
description: Analysis of spinal cord from SOD1-G93A transgenic model of amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (ALS) at 75 or 110 days of age. Cu/Zn superoxide dismutase mutations are a cause of ALS. Gene expression results, together with proteomic data, provide insight into functional changes underlying ALS progression.

title: Homeobox Lim1 mutant nephron-deficient kidneys
description: Analysis of embryonic day 14.5 and 18.5 kidneys from Lim1 conditional mutants. Lim1 is a homoebox gene that is essential for nephrogenesis. The mutant is ablated for Lim1 in the metanephric mesenchyme, resulting in nephron deficient kidneys. Results identify genes expressed in developing nephrons.

title: Mantle cell lymphoma cell lines (HG-U133A)
description: Expression profiling of 4 mantle cell lymphoma (MCL) cell lines. MCL has the worst prognosis among B-cell lymphomas. Gene expression results combine with genomic profiling results to identify genes that are relevant to MCL pathogenesis and that could also represent possible therapeutic targets.

title: Steady-state culture response to transient perturbations in carbon source: time course
description: Analysis of steady state cultures growing on galactose following a pulse of 0.2 or 2 grams of glucose per liter. Gene expression examined at various time points up to 4 hours after glucose addition. Results provide insight into the dynamics of the transcriptional response to changing environments.

title: Colchicine anti-inflammatory effect: time course and dose response
description: Analysis of umbilical vein endothelial cell line HUVEC at various time points up to 24 hours following treatment with 100 ng/ml or 1 ug/ml of colchicine. Colchicine is an alkaloid used to alleviate rheumatic complaints like gout and to prevent acute attacks of familial Mediterranean fever.

title: CAG repeat knock-in model of spinocerebellar ataxia type 1 progression
description: Analysis of cerebellum and forebrain tissue of knock-in mice carrying 154 CAG repeats in the spinocerebellar ataxia type 1 (SCA1) locus at 4 and 12 weeks of age. Results provide insight into the pathophysiology of the neurodegenerative disease SCA1.

title: Diurnal cycle effect in leaves: time course
description: Analysis of Col-0 leaves at various time points in a normal day-night cycle. Col-0 plants grown in 12-hour light 12-hour dark rhythm at 20 degrees C. Leaves collected 4, 8, and 12 h into the light period and into the night. Results identify genes that undergo diurnal changes of expression.

title: Pterygium
description: Expression profiling of primary pterygium tissue. Pterygium, a common ocular surface disorder, is a fibrovascular overgrowth from the conjunctiva onto the cornea. Results provide insight into pterygium pathogenesis.

title: Retinas under a light-dark cycle and in constant dim light: time course
description: Analysis of retinas under a light-dark cycle at Zeitgeber times (ZT) 6 and 18 or in constant dim light at circadian times (CT) 6 and 18. Gene expression in retinas compared to that in pineal glands.

title: Telomerase reverse transcriptase immortalizing effect on fibroblasts and endothelial cells: time-course
description: Analysis of normal fibroblasts and endothelial cells, at various population doubling levels (PDLs), following human telomerase reverse transcriptase (hTERT) transfection. hTERT mediates cellular immortalization. Results identify cell-type specific transcriptional responses during immortalization.

title: NCI60 cancer cell lines
description: Analysis of 60 cell lines (the NCI60) derived from tumors from a variety of tissues and organs. Such cell lines are used extensively as experimental models of neoplastic disease. Results identify variation in gene expression patterns in the cell lines and their relationships to tumors in vivo.

title: Cell culture model of extra-embryonic endoderm
description: Analysis of blastocyst-derived extra-embryonic endoderm (XEN) cell lines and an embryonic stem (ES) cell line. Results identify independent XEN cell lines that express markers of extra-embryonic endoderm, but not those of the epiblast, and thus represent a new model of an early mammalian lineage.

title: Various oxidative stress-inducing agents effect on mycelia: time course
description: Analysis of mycelia at various timepoints up to 9 hours after exposure to diamide, H2O2, or menadione. Specific cell functions are involved in the resistance to each oxidative stress-inducing agent. Results identify transcriptional responses unique to diamide, H2O2, and menadione.

title: Extraocular and hindlimb skeletal muscle cell differentiation: time course (MG-430A)
description: Analysis of cell lines derived from extraocular (EOM) and gastrocnemius skeletal muscle allotypes at various time points up to 48 hours following induction of myogenesis. Results provide insight into the early developmental mechanisms underlying the formation of skeletal muscle classes.

title: Extraocular and hindlimb skeletal muscle cell differentiation: time course (MG-430B)
description: Analysis of cell lines derived from extraocular (EOM) and gastrocnemius skeletal muscle allotypes at various time points up to 48 hours following induction of myogenesis. Results provide insight into the early developmental mechanisms underlying the formation of skeletal muscle classes.

title: Zucker diabetic fatty model of type 2 diabetes: various insulin-sensitive tissues
description: Analysis of adipose, skeletal muscle, and liver tissues of Zucker diabetic fatty animals at pre-diabetic and diabetic stages. ZDF animals have a mutated leptin receptor. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms responsible for insulin resistance and progression to type 2 diabetes.

title: Platelet-derived growth factor effect on fibroblasts: time course
description: Expression profiling of AG01518 foreskin fibroblasts at various time points up to 24 hours following stimulation with 10 ng/ml platelet-derived growth factor (PDGF). PDGF is a potent mitogen for fibroblasts and other cells of mesenchymal origin. Results identify genes regulated by PDGF.

title: Fast-twitch muscle response to denervation: time course
description: Analysis of tibialis anterior muscle at various time points up to 14 days after denervation. Sciatic nerve transected at the level of the trochanter. Results provide insight into the mechanisms leading to atrophy and fiber phenotype change after denervation in fast-twitch muscles.

title: MicroRNA miR-430 effect on maternal-zygotic (MZ) dicer mutant embryos
description: Analysis of maternal-zygotic (MZ) dicer mutant embryos that lack miR-430 and mutants rescued with miR-430. MZdicer mutants cannot generate mature miRNAs; miR-430 accumulates during maternal-to-zygotic transition and regulates morphogenesis during early development. Results identify miR-430 targets.

title: Hypoxia effect on vhl and p53 null mutants
description: Analysis of cell lines lacking VHL or p53 following exposure to hypoxia. VHL is the gene responsible for degrading transcription factor HIF-1. p53 null mutants examined to identify genes whose expression under hypoxia depends on p53. Results identify genes regulated by HIF-1.

title: B-form DNA transfection effect on TBK1 and IKKi deficient embryonic fibroblasts
description: Analysis of embryonic fibroblast deficient in kinases TBK1, IKKi (Ikbke), or both following transfection with B-form DNA. B-DNA transfection triggers interferon-beta production via TBK1 and IKKi. Results provide insight into the mechanisms of intracellular recognition of DNA during infection.

title: Chronic hepatitis C infection response to Agaricus blazei medicinal extract: peripheral blood cells
description: Analysis of peripheral blood cells from chronic hepatitis patients following oral administration of Agaricus blazei Murill (AbM) extract 3 times daily for 1 week. AbM extracts are used as a non-prescription remedy for cancer and infections, including hepatitis.

title: B3 domain transcription factor LEC2 induction effect on seedlings: time course
description: Analysis of 8-day-old seedlings at 1 or 4 hours following induction of the B3 domain transcription factor LEAFY COTYLEDON2 (LEC2). LEC2 induced from a 35S:LEC2-glucocorticoid receptor transgene using dexamethasone. Results provide insight into the role of LEC2 in embryogenesis.

title: Colon tubular adenoma and carcinoma cells
description: Analysis of colon tubular adenoma and carcinoma cells microdissected from formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded sections of colon tubular adenomas containing focal adenocarcinomas. Results provide insight into the progression of colon cancers from pre-existing adenomas.

title: Alpha2-laminin deficient dy/dy model of muscular dystrophy: diaphragm
description: Analysis of diaphragms of alpha2-laminin deficient dy/dy animals. Alpha-2 laminin is important in muscle cell attachment, and its deficiency underlies classical congenital muscular dystrophy. Results provide insight into the events that link alpha2-laminin deficiency with muscle fiber necrosis.

title: Hypoxia effect on astrocytes
description: Analysis of purified primary astrocytes exposed to hypoxia for 24 hours. Gene expression in HeLa cells also examined. Astrocytes play critical roles in the proper functioning of the brain. Results provide insight into the molecular events underlying the astrocytic responses to hypoxia.

title: Colorectal cancer progression: polysomal mRNA profiles
description: Comparison of polysomal RNA from isogenic cell lines established from a colorectal cancer (CRC) patient. SW480 and SW620 cells derived from the primary tumor and a lymph node metastasis, respectively. The cell lines constitute a cellular model of CRC transition from invasive carcinoma to metastasis.

title: Vascular smooth muscle response to voltage-dependent and store-operated calcium channel activation
description: Analysis of cerebral vascular smooth muscle cells after activation of voltage-dependent (VDCCs) or store-operated calcium channels (SOCCs). VDCCs activated by K+ depolarization and SOCCs by thapsigargin. Results provide insight into the effect of different calcium signals on gene expression.

title: Protein kinase B alpha knockout effect on adipogenesis: time course
description: Analysis of protein kinase B alpha (PKBalpha) knockout embryonic fibroblasts (MEFs) following treatment with a standard induction cocktail to induce differentiation into adipocytes. Cells examined up to 48 hours following treatment. Results provide insight into the role of PKBalpha in adipogenesis.

title: pen3 mutant response to nonhost fungal pathogen
description: Analysis of pen3 mutants after inoculation with barley powdery mildew, Blumeria graminis f. sp hordei (B. g. hordei). pen3 mutations allows increased epidermal cell invasion by B. g. hordei. Results provide insight into the mechanisms underlying the lack of nonhost resistance in pen3 mutants.

title: Microarray-assisted positional cloning of TOM-1 and UNC-43
description: Analysis of tom-1 and unc-43 mutants. Many mutations found in screens are nonsense mutations which give rise to rapidly-degraded mRNAs, thus making them detectable by microarray. Results support the use of arrays to facilitate identification of mutations from genetic screens.

title: Protein tyrosine kinase Src R388A mutant rescue by imidazole in living cells: time course
description: Analysis of protein tyrosine kinase Src R388A mutant protein in living cells at 1 and 12 hours after chemical rescue with imidazole. Rapid and reversible activity stimulation is an advantage chemical rescue has over inducible transcriptional systems and temperature-sensitive mutants.

title: Wilms' tumor
description: Expression profiling of Wilms' tumor tissue after pre-operative chemotherapy. Stratagene Universal Reference RNA also examined. Results are part of a cross-platform evaluation and compared to data generated from Serial Analysis of Gene Expression.

title: Gastric tubular adenoma and carcinoma
description: Analysis of gastric tubular adenoma and carcinoma cells microdissected from formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded sections of gastric biopsies. Early lesions are small and detectable only with a microscope. Results indicate that routinely processed biopsy specimens may be useful in expression profiling.

title: Homeodomain interacting protein kinase 2 dominant-negative form effect on trigeminal ganglion
description: Analysis of the trigeminal ganglia of transgenics expressing a dominant-negative form of homeodomain interacting protein kinase 2 (HIPK2). HIPK2 is a downstream target of Brn-3.2, a class IV POU domain transcription factor that controls a developmental program regulating axon pathfinding.

title: Chronic stress effect on the amygdala and hippocampus
description: Analysis of the amygdalae (Amy) and hippocampi (Hipp) of animals subjected to chronic stress induced by daily handling sessions for 14 days. Studies indicate that chronic stress produce a response in Hipp that is opposite of that in Amy.

title: Traumatic brain injury: time course
description: Analysis of cortices and hippocampi of animals 4 and 24 hours after mild or severe traumatic brain injury (TBI). TBI induced by lateral fluid percussion. Gene expression in tissues ipsi- and contralateral to the injury examined.

title: Prostacylin receptor agonist and indomethacin effect on interleukin-1 beta activated synovial fibroblasts
description: Analysis of interleukin-1 beta activated synovial fibroblasts following treatment with indomethacin, a non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drug, alone or in combination with iloprost, a prostacyclin (PGI) receptor agonist. Results provide insight into the role of PGI in rheumatoid arthritis.

title: TCDD effect on regenerating fin: time course
description: Analysis of 2,3,7,8-tetrachlorodibenzo-p-dioxin (TCDD) exposed caudal fins at various time points up to 5 days post amputation. TCDD prevents caudal fin regeneration. Results provide insight into the pathways required for fin regeneration and the mechanisms of TCDD toxicity.

title: CBF3 and ABF3 overexpressing transgenic leaves tolerative response to drought
description: Analysis of transgenic leaves from plants constitutively expressing Arabidopsis CBF3 or ABF3 following exposure to drought. CBF3 and ABF3 function in distinct stress-response pathways. Results demonstrate ectopic expression of CBF3 or ABF3 enhances stress tolerance.

title: Potassium chloride depolarizing effect on cortical neurons
description: Expression profiling of cortical neurons depolarized by treatment with 25 mM potassium chloride for 4 hours. Cortical neurons obtained from 17-day-old embryos and grown for 14 days in vitro prior to treatment. Results identify genes that are differentially expressed upon depolarization.

title: Sodium arsenate effect on Azucena and Bala varieties
description: Expression profiling of 1-week-old roots from varieties Azucena and Bala following treatment with 1 ppm sodium arsenate. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of arsenate tolerance exhibited by the Bala variety.

title: DNA methyltransferase inhibitor 5-aza-2-deoxycytidine effect on RAS-transformed fibroblasts
description: Expression profiling of HRAS oncogene transformed fibroblasts after treatment with the DNA methyltransferase inhibitor 5-aza-2-deoxycytidine for 96 hours. Results provide insight into the role of DNA methylation in oncogenic signaling pathways.

title: Sodium butyrate effect on colonic epithelial cells: time course
description: Analysis of colonic epithelial cells treated with sodium butyrate. Gene expression examined at various time points up to 24 hours following treatment. Results provide insight into the mechanisms underlying the ability of sodium butyrate to induce cell growth arrest and differentiation.

title: Age effect on hematopoietic stem cells
description: Analysis of highly purified long-term hematopoietic stem cells from young and old C57BL/6s at 2 to 3 months and 22 to 24 months of age, respectively.  Results provide insight into the cellular and molecular changes underlying hematopoietic stem cell aging.

title: Heat shock factor sigma32 overexpression: time course
description: Expression profiling of cells at various time points up to 10 minutes following induction by IPTG of alternative sigma factor, sigma32, from an inducible promoter. Sigma32 mediates the heat shock response. Results identify genes regulated by sigma32.

title: Lactating mammary gland response to diets with varying amounts of fat: time course
description: Analysis of mammary glands from FVBs fed a diet with 8%, 16%, or 40% fat. Gene expression examined at pregnancy day 12 to lactation day 9. Results provide insight into whether multiple metabolic control points are involved in activating lipid and lactose synthesis at the onset of lactation.

title: Modeled microgravity effect on activated T lymphocytes
description: Analysis of activated T-cells subjected to modeled microgravity. The study seeks to identify microgravity sensitive genes involved in apoptosis and the immune response. Microgravity is an environment of little net gravitational force that is experienced in spaceflight and by free-falling objects.

title: Hypoxia effect on B lymphocyte cell line
description: Expression profiling of B lymphocyte P493-6 cells subjected to hypoxia. Cells incubated in 0.1% oxygen for 29 hours, the point of highest expression of hypoxia-inducible factor 1 (HIF-1).  Results identify hypoxia responsive genes in P493-6 cells.

title: Candidate calorie restriction mimetic drugs effect on the liver
description: Analysis of livers of long-lived B6C3F1 animals fed a diet containing metformin, glipizide, rosiglitazone, or soy isoflavone extract. Results compared to hepatic gene expression profile produced by long-term caloric restriction. Caloric restriction extends the life span of laboratory animals.

title: Graded HoxA10 expression effect on Lin(-) Sca1(+) c-kit(+) bone marrow cells
description: Analysis of HoxA10 transgenic Lin(-) Sca1(+) c-kit(+) bone marrow cells following treatment with 0, 0.1 or 0.5 ug/ml doxycycline. In this model, doxycycline induces the expression of HoxA10 in a dose dependent manner.  Results provide insight into the role of HoxA10 in early hematopoiesis.

title: Surgical model of acute lymphedema induction
description: Expression profiling of lymphedematous tail skin. Lymphedema is the swelling of subcutaneous tissue due to faulty lymphatic drainage. It is a common consequence of surgical and radiation treatment of certain types of cancers. Lymph vessels were surgically blocked to induce acute lymphedema.

title: HPV16 integration and episomal loss effect on cervical keratinocytes
description: Analysis of high-risk human papillomavirus (HRHPV) HPV16-containing cervical keratinocyte W12 cells selected for integrated HPV16. Results show that HRHPV integration and episome loss are key events in cervical neoplastic progression.

title: Glial brain tumors
description: Analysis of 50 glial brain tumors of various histogenesis. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying gliomagenesis and define biological pathway maps associated with gliomagenesis as well as distinct glioma subtypes.

title: Pulsatile shear stresses at various frequencies effect on endothelial cells
description: Analysis of aortic endothelial cells subjected to a mean shear stress of 7.5 or 15 dyn/cm^2 in vitro. 3 sinusoidal waveforms at 1, 2, and 3 Hz tested at each mean shear stress level. Results shed light on how in vivo arterial shear forces affect vascular endothelial gene expression.

title: High-grade gliomas (HG-U133A)
description: Analysis of high-grade glioma (HGGs) samples from cases of WHO grade III and IV astrocytomas. Results classify HGGs into molecular subclasses with prognostic value that predict survival and disease progression. The molecular subclasses resemble key stages of neurogenesis.

title: High-grade gliomas (HG-U133B)
description: Analysis of high-grade glioma (HGGs) samples from cases of WHO grade III and IV astrocytomas. Results classify HGGs into molecular subclasses with prognostic value that predict survival and disease progression. The molecular subclasses resemble key stages of neurogenesis.

title: Muscle cell survival mediated by transcriptional coactivator p300
description: Analysis of insulin growth factor II deficient C2AS12 myoblasts expressing wild type or protein interaction domain mutant p300 at 0 and 24 hours after a switch to low serum media. Wild type but not the mutant p300 prevents the progressive cell death induced by serum withdrawal.

title: Transcription factors Nanog and Oct4 knockdown effect on embryonic stem cells
description: Analysis of embryonic stem (ES) cells following RNA interference-mediated depletion of Nanog or Oct4. Nanog and Oct4 are required to maintain the pluripotency and self-renewal of ES cells. Differentially expressed genes scanned for the presence of binding sites for Nanog and Oct4.

title: Virulent and non-virulent Entamoeba species comparison
description: Expression profiling of virulent and non-virulent Entamoeba strains and species. Entamoeba histolytica is a protozoan parasite that causes colitis and liver abscesses. Results identify expression patterns indicative of a virulence phenotype.

title: Adenovirus vector effect on complement system deficient mutant livers
description: Analysis of livers from complement-deficient C3 knockout mutants injected with a first generation LacZ adenovirus (Ad) vector. Ad vectors are used in gene delivery. Results provide insight into the role of the complement system in elaborating multiple Ad-associated acute inflammatory responses.

title: Steady-state external pH effect on enteric bacteria
description: Analysis of enteric bacteria K-12 strain W3110 cells grown aerobically and exposed to low, neutral, or high pH. Enteric bacteria encounter a wide range of external pHs in the human digestive tract, their natural habitat. Results provide insight into the acid and base response.

title: Chemoresistant glioblastomas: expression profile
description: Expression analysis of cell lines derived from primary and recurrent glioblastomas with resistance to O6-alkylating agents, BCNU and TMZ. Chemoresistance to these widely-used drugs is a major obstacle to tumor treatment. Results identify a transcriptomic signature of resistance to alkylating agents.

title: Testosterone effect on female lacrimal, meibomian, and submandibular glands
description: Expression profiling of lacrimal, meibomian, and submandibular glands from BALB/c females. Females ovariectomized at 8 weeks and allowed to recover from surgery for 10 days prior to testosterone treatment. Results compared to the response of male glands to testosterone.

title: Testosterone effect on the female submandibular gland
description: Expression profiling of submandibular glands from BALB/c females. Females ovariectomized at 8 weeks and allowed to recover from surgery for 10 days prior to testosterone treatment. Results compared to the response of male glands to testosterone.

title: Various cell lines and Universal Reference RNA (II)
description: Analysis of individual cell lines representing different tissues against a Universal Reference RNA (URR). URR prepared from pooled RNA from the individual cell lines. Results indicate the individual cell lines contribute their own unique set of genes, thereby diversifying gene representation in URR.

title: Androgen insensitivity syndrome: genital fibroblast response to dihydrotestosterone
description: Analysis of genital fibroblasts from 46,XY females with complete androgen insensitivity syndrome (AIS). Response of cells to dihydrotestosterone examined. Most AIS affected individuals have mutated androgen receptors (AR). Results provide insight into the role of AR in genital differentiation.

title: c-Raf inhibitor GW5074 anti-apoptotic effect on cerebellar granule neurons: time course
description: Analysis of cultured cerebellar granule neurons in low potassium medium 3 and 6 hours following treatment with the c-Raf inhibitor GW5074. GW5074 blocks low potassium induced cell death. Results provide insight into the neuroprotective action of GW5074.

title: Skeletal muscle synaptic region
description: Analysis of synaptic regions of diaphragm muscles from 16-day-old animals. Results identify genes preferentially expressed in the synaptic region of muscles. Such genes are candidates for muscle-derived retrograde signals that regulate the differentiation of motor axon terminals.

title: Follicular lymphomas and response to rituximab
description: Analysis of lymph node biopsies from 24 follicular lymphoma patients. Biopsies obtained before any systemic therapy. Results analyzed together with the subsequent response of patients to rituximab, a monoclonal antibody directed against the B cell antigen, CD20.

title: Denervation effect on somatosensory cortex: time course
description: Analysis of the adult somatosensory cortex at the forepaw/lower jaw border at various time points up to 28 days after partial paw denervation. The adult somatosensory cortex undergoes reorganization in response to changes in peripheral input, such as limb usage patterns or denervation.

title: Chronic endoplasmic reticulum stress imposed by misfolded surfactant protein C (HG-U133A)
description: Analysis of cells that constitutively express misfolded surfactant protein C, which induces chronic endoplasmic reticulum (ER) stress and cytotoxicity. Results provide evidence for an NF-kB-dependent adaptive response to the chronic ER stress imposed by the misfolded protein.

title: Ethanol effect on heads
description: Analysis of heads from animals exposed to 50% ethanol vapor for 40 minutes once or five times. The multiple treatments were interspersed with exposures to 10% ethanol vapor. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying the development of fast and chronic ethanol tolerance.

title: Cystic fibrosis transmembrane conductance regulator CFTR deficiency effect on lungs: time course
description: Expression profiling of lungs from animals lacking the cystic fibrosis transmembrane conductance regulator gene (CFTR). Animals examined at 3, 6, and 11 weeks of age. Mutations in CFTR cause cystic fibrosis, an autosomal recessive monogenic disorder.

title: Cystic fibrosis transmembrane conductance regulator CFTR transgene overexpression effect on lungs
description: Analysis of lungs of adult Cftr+/+ animals overexpressing the normal human cystic fibrosis transmembrane conductance regulator gene (CFTR) under control of the Sftpc promoter in respiratory epithelial cells. Homozygous transgenic, heterozygous transgenic and wild type mice were compared.

title: Retinitis pigmentosa 1 gene knockout effect on retinas: time course
description: Analysis of retinas of animals disrupted for the retinitis pigmentosa 1 (RP1) gene. Animals examined up to postnatal day 21. Results provide insight into mechanisms underlying autosomal dominant progressive RP caused by RP1 mutations and identify molecules involved early in the disease process.

title: Interferon gamma effect on keratinocytes: time course
description: Analysis of keratinocytes treated with interferon gamma (IFN-gamma) for up to 48 hours. IFN-gamma is a multifunctional, immunomodulatory cytokine with cell type-specific antiviral activities. Results provide insight into molecular processes regulated by IFN-gamma in keratinocytes.

title: Vitamin D effect on intestinal epithelial cells
description: Analysis of intestinal epithelial Caco-2 cells following treatment with 1,25-dihydroxyvitamin D3 for 24 hours. 1,25-dihydroxyvitamin D3 stimulated calcium absorption in the intestine. Results provide insight into the additional effects of vitamin D on intestinal epithelial cells.

title: High temperature adapted strains
description: Analysis of 3 strains derived by growing the ancestral Bc251 strain for 2,000 generations at 41.5 degrees C. Cells grown to mid log-phase at 41.5 degrees C. Results provide insight into the role of heat-inducible genes in the genetic adaptation to long-term temperature stress.

title: Intestine-adapted bacterial symbiont response to polysaccharide and simple sugar diets
description: Analysis of Bacteroides thetaiotaomicron (BT) from the ceca of mice on polysaccharide or simple sugar diets. BT is involved in the breakdown of plant polysaccharides. BT-colonized mice is a human gut ecosystem model. Results identify genes that may endow flexibility in adapting to dietary changes.

title: Carious pulpal tissue
description: Expression profiling of core pulpal tissue from carious teeth. RNA pooled from 11 carious teeth. Results provide insight into the molecular events that occur during the progression of dental caries.

title: Cold and subsequent immobilization stress effect on adrenal medulla
description: Analysis of the adrenal medulla of animals exposed to cold stress for 28 days and subsequently subjected to immobilization stress.  Effect of cold stress exposure for 1 and 7 days examined. Adaptation to cold stress leads to sensitization to a different stressor.

title: siRNA knockdown and transcriptional response to DNA damage
description: Analysis of HEK293 cells following siRNA knockdown of p53, RelA, or ATM, and subsequent treatment with neocarzinostatin, a radiomimetic drug that induces DNA double-strand breaks. Results indicate RNAi combined with expression profiling is a powerful method for dissecting transcriptional networks.

title: Intramedullary nail and internal plate fixation treated diaphyseal femoral fractures: time course
description: Comparison of healing diaphyseal femoral fractures treated with intramedullary nail fixation or with internal plate fixation. Expression profiles examined at various time points up to 6 weeks post-treatment. Results provide insight into the effect of fracture fixation technique on fracture repair.

title: Postnatal day 7 and adult cerebellum: glycoconjugate expression profile
description: Analysis of cerebellums of postnatal day 7 (P7) and adult animals using an array focusing on glycoconjugates. P7 was chosen for comparison as many differentiation events are peaking at this time. Glycoconjugates are widely distributed throughout the CNS and play an essential role in its development.

title: Four-amino analog of tetrahydrobiopterin effect on cardiac allografts
description: Analysis of cardiac allografts from transplant recipients treated with four-amino analog of tetrahydrobiopterin (ABH4), a nitric oxide synthase inhibitor shown to prolong allograft survival. The effect of tetrahydrobiopterin (BH4), N6-(iminoethyl)-L-lysine (L-NIL), and cyclosporin A also examined.

title: Rheumatoid arthritis: synovial tissues
description: Expression profiling of synovial tissues of patients with rheumatoid arthritis (RA). RA is a chronic inflammatory disease characterized by pain, stiffness, swelling, and destruction of joints. Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of RA.

title: Various miRNA transfections: time course
description: Analysis of HeLa cells at 12 or 24 hours after transfection with wild type or mutant miR-1 or miR-124. miR-1 is preferentially expressed in heart and skeletal muscle, while miR-124 is preferentially expressed in brain. Results suggest that metazoan miRNAs can reduce the levels of target transcripts.

title: Adrenalectomized mice skeletal muscle response to cortisol: time course (MG-U74A)
description: Expression profiling of gastrocnemius muscle of adrenalectomized C57BL6 males at 3 and 24 hours following intraperitoneal injection of cortisol. Results compared with those from SAGE (GSE2122) to assess the reproducibility of SAGE experiments.

title: Antiepileptic drugs levetiracetam and phenytoin effect on the brain
description: Analysis of the brainstem, frontal cortex, and hippocampus of animals chronically treated for 90 days with levetiracetam or phenytoin. Levetiracetam inhibits epileptogenesis in the kindling model of epilepsy. Phenytoin's antiepileptic activity involves the inhibition of sodium channels.

title: Chondrocyte differentiation: time course
description: Analysis of micromass cultures derived from limb bud mesenchymal cells and cultured for 15 days in differentiating conditions (beta-glycerophosphate and ascorbic acid). Cultures examined every 3 days, up to day 15. Results provide insight into the mechanisms regulating chondrocyte differentiation.

title: Heregulin and forskolin mitogenic effect on cultured Schwann cells
description: Analysis of passage 1 and passage 3 Schwann cell cultures obtained from four donors and maintained in the presence of the heregulin and forskolin. Heregulin and forskolin synergistically drive Schwann cell proliferation in vitro.

title: Adrenalectomized liver at light and dark periods of the circadian cycle
description: Expression profiling of livers of adrenalectomized C57BL/6 males 2 hours into the light or dark periods of a 12:12 hour light cycle. Results identify genes regulated by endogenous glucocorticoids in a circadian manner.

title: Interleukin-10 deficiency model of inflammatory bowel disease
description: Analysis of colons of C3H/HeJBir and C57BL/6J strains following interleukin-10 (IL-10) gene disruption. IL-10 disruption leads to colitis in C3H/HeJBir strain but not in C57BL/6J. Results used to reduce the number of candidate genes associated with colitogenic quantitative trait loci regions.

title: CCAAT/enhancer-binding proteins C/EBP alpha, beta, delta, and epsilon induction
description: Analysis of NIH 3T3 cells following induction of CCAAT/enhancer-binding protein (C/EBP) alpha, beta, delta, or epsilon from zinc inducible expression vectors. The C/EBP family of transcription factors regulate growth and differentiation in numerous cell types. Results identify C/EBP targets.

title: Antiestrogen and aromatase inhibitor effect on breast cancer cells
description: Analysis of estrogen receptor positive, aromatase transfected MCF-7 cells after treatment with an antiestrogen (AE) or an aromatase inhibitor (AI). AEs and AIs are used to treat estrogen-dependent breast cancer. Cells also treated with androgen which is converted to estrogen by aromatase.

title: Integrin beta-6 deficiency model of emphysema: alveolar macrophage
description: Analysis of alveolar macrophages of integrin beta-6 (Itgb6) deficient animals treated with doxycycline. Itgb6 mutants develop emphysema. Effect of TGFbeta transgene induction to suppress the effect of the Itgb6 mutation also examined.

title: Host cell response to HIV-1 Vpr-induced cell cycle arrest: time course
description: Analysis of cell lines expressing wild-type or mutant HIV-1 Vpr protein at various timepoints following doxycycline induction. Vpr advances HIV pathogenesis by inhibiting the cell cycle at G2/M. Results identify changes in cellular gene expression associated with Vpr-mediated cell cycle arrest.

title: slbo mutant migratory cells of the ovary
description: Analysis of slbo mutant border and centripetal migratory cells in the ovary. SLBO, a C/EBP family transcriptional activator, is required for the switch from stationary to migratory behavior. Results identify genes involved in cell migration and downstream targets of SLBO.

title: Myotube response to PGC-1alpha induced mitochondrial biogenesis: time course (MG-U74A)
description: Analysis of C2C12 myoblast-derived myotubes transduced with transcriptional coactivator PGC-1alpha to induce mitochondrial proliferation in the muscle cells. Cells examined up to 3 days post-transduction. Results combined with other genome-scale datasets to identify mitochondrial proteins.

title: Myotube response to PGC-1alpha induced mitochondrial biogenesis: time course (MG-U74B)
description: Analysis of C2C12 myoblast-derived myotubes transduced with transcriptional coactivator PGC-1alpha to induce mitochondrial proliferation in the muscle cells. Cells examined up to 3 days post-transduction. Results combined with other genome-scale datasets to identify mitochondrial proteins.

title: Myotube response to PGC-1alpha induced mitochondrial biogenesis: time course (MG-U74C)
description: Analysis of C2C12 myoblast-derived myotubes transduced with transcriptional coactivator PGC-1alpha to induce mitochondrial proliferation in the muscle cells. Cells examined up to 3 days post-transduction. Results combined with other genome-scale datasets to identify mitochondrial proteins.

title: Mono-(2-ethylhexyl) phthalate effect on prepubertal testes: time course
description: Analysis of testes of postnatal day 28 animals at various time points up to 12 hrs after acute exposure to mono-(2-ethylhexyl) phthalate. Phthalate plasticizers can damage fetal and prepubertal testis.   Results provide insight into mechanisms of prepubertal phthalate-induced testicular injury.

title: Embryonic fibroblast-independent embryonic stem cell differentiation
description: Analysis of CGR8 embryoid bodies differentiating for 3 or 10 days. Culturing of most embryonic stem (ES) cells require embryonic fibroblast (MEF) feeder cells which may affect their gene expression profiles. CGR8 cells are MEF-independent and represent a powerful model of ES cell differentiation.

title: Sodium tungstate regenerative effect on diabetic pancreas
description: Analysis of pancreas of diabetic animals after treatment with sodium tungstate, which induces beta cell mass growth. Diabetes induced by streptozotocin. Results provide insight into the mechanisms underlying the regenerative effect of sodium tungstate on the pancreas of models of diabetes.

title: Testes of various subspecies
description: Expression profiling of testes from subspecies castaneus, domesticus, musculus, and a strain from Iran (BID).

title: Moderate hypothermia effect in vitro
description: Analysis of acute monocytic leukemia THP-1 cells exposed to moderate hypothermia (MH) at 32 degrees C for 24 hours. THP-1 cell line is an in vitro system for analyzing the effects of hypothermia. MH has therapeutic applications. Results show substantial changes in gene expression in response to MH.

title: Rectal cancer cells and radiotherapy response
description: Analysis of rectal cancer cells from patients prior to preoperative radiotherapy. Response to radiotherapy determined by histopathologic examination of resected specimens. Results identify gene markers for the characterization and prediction of the response to radiotherapy in rectal cancer.

title: Hoxc13 overexpression effect on the skin
description: Analysis of skins of post-natal day 5 transgenics overexpressing the homeobox (Hox) gene Hoxc13. Hox genes are implicated in hair follicle differentiation, and Hoxc13 overexpression in transgenics leads to hair shaft defects, alopecia, and epidermal abnormalities.

title: Glucosamine and high glucose effect on renal mesangial cells
description: Analysis of renal mesangial MES-13 cells treated with high glucose or glucosamine. Mesangial cells play an important role in the development of diabetic glomerulosclerosis and renal failure. Glucosamine and high glucose mimic the hyperglycemic and hemodynamic insults of diabetic kidney disease.

title: TGF-beta1 effect on renal mesangial cells
description: Analysis of renal mesangial MES-13 cells following treatment with TGF-beta1. TGF-beta1 has been identified as a mediator of renal hypertrophy and accumulation of extracellular matrix proteins in the diabetic glomerular mesangium.

title: Strains exhibiting low or high freezing in response to fear: amygdala and hippocampus
description: Analysis of the amygdalae and hippocampi of strains exhibiting low or high freezing behavior in response to fear.  Previous work identified alleles that contribute to the variability in freezing behavior, and the chromosomal location of these alleles.

title: Cyanobacterial metabolite apratoxin A cytotoxic effect on colon adenocarcinoma cells: time course and dose response
description: Analysis of colon adenocarcinoma HT29 cells at various time points up to 12 hours following treatment with 2 or 10 nM of the cyanobacterial metabolite apratoxin A. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying the cytotoxic effect of apratoxin A on tumor cells.

title: Classical fear conditioning effect on amygdala and hippocampus
description: Comparison of amygdalae and hippocampi of animals subjected to classical fear conditioning (CFC), which consists of a 3-minute exposure to the conditioning chamber, a 30-second exposure to tone, and a 2-second, 1.5-mA footshock. CFC induced greater gene expression changes in the amygdala.

title: Various wild-type tissues: glycogene expression profile
description: Analysis of various wild type murine tissues using a glycogene array. Glycosylation is the most common posttranslational modification of proteins. Results used to determine whether glycogene expression profiles could be used for the analysis of glycan synthesis and function.

title: Ovarian germ line stem cells expanded by Dpp overexpression and bam mutation
description: Analysis of purified ovarian germ line stem cells (GSCs) expanded by overexpression of the bone morphogenetic protein Dpp or by mutating the bam gene. Kc tissue culture cells also examined. Dpp represses bam transcription. Results provide insight into the mechanisms of GSC maintenance and function.

title: Ovarian germ line stem cell differentiation and reversion: time course
description: Analysis of Dpp expanded germ line stem cells (GSCs) at various time points up to 50 hours following transient bam gene induction. GSCs differentiate into cystocytes 20 hours following bam induction. Cystocytes revert to GSCs 30 hours later. Results identify candidate GSC-specific genes.

title: Hydrogen peroxide response: time course
description: Expression profiling of oxyR deletion mutant and wild type cells following treatment with 1 mM hydrogen peroxide. OxyR is a transcription factor that senses oxidative stress. Results provide insight into the mechanisms involved in oxidative stress tolerance.

title: Iron starvation effect on PA2384 null mutant
description: Analysis of PAO1 strain PA2384 null mutant grown under iron-limiting conditions. PA2384 is responsive to iron limitation and is weakly similar to the ferric uptake regulator fur. RNA extracted from cells at various stages of growth. Results provide insight into the function of PA2384.

title: Piper nigrum seed extract and pyrethrum insecticidal effect
description: Analysis of Oregon R animals treated with an ethylacetate extract from Piper nigrum seeds, natural pyrethrum, or both. Pyrethrum is an insecticide. The P. nigrum extract has insecticidal properties. The study examines the synergistic effect of both agents on gene expression.

title: X-linked recessive dystonia-parkinsonism
description: Expression profiling of the caudate nucleus and nucleus accumbens from the brain of a patient with X-linked recessive dystonia-parkinsonism (XDP). XDP is an adult onset disorder characterized by dystonia and parkinsonism. Result provide insight into the pathogenesis of XDP.

title: Streptozotocin-induced diabetic muscle response to vanadyl sulfate
description: Expression profiling of rear leg muscles of diabetic Wistars treated with vanadyl sulfate. Diabetes induced with streptozotocin (STZ). Studies show that vanadyl sulfate relieves diabetic hyperglycemia.

title: Salinity stress effect on seedling shoot tissues: time course
description: Temporal analysis of shoot tissue from 17-day-old Morex seedlings subjected to salinity stress. Gene expression in shoot tissue examined following exposure to 100 mM NaCl at various lengths of time up to 27 hours. Results provide insight into the ion-specific effects of salinity on gene expression.

title: Hepatocyte nuclear factor 4 alpha knockout effect on the small intestine
description: Expression profiling of small intestines lacking hepatocyte nuclear factor 4 alpha (HNF4alpha). Cre/Lox system used to knock out Hnf4a in the small intestine. HNF4alpha is a member of the nuclear receptor family of ligand-dependent transcription factors.

title: Hepatocyte nuclear factor 4 alpha knockout effect on the embryonic liver
description: Analysis of embryonic day 18.5 livers lacking hepatocyte nuclear factor 4 alpha (HNF4alpha). Cre/lox system used to knock out Hnf4a in liver. HNF4alpha is a nuclear hormone transcription factor. Results provide insight into the role of HNF4alpha in hepatogenesis.

title: Cerebellar cortex in schizophrenia
description: Analysis of cortical samples corresponding to the crus I/VIIa area of the cerebellum from schizophrenia patients. A study indicates that targets of the RNA-binding ELAV-like protein HuD are overexpressed in the prefrontal cortex of patients with schizophrenia.

title: Inhibitor-1 knockout effect on the hippocampus
description: Analysis of the hippocampi of inhibitor-1 knockout animals. Inhibitor-1 is an inhibitor of protein phosphatase-1 (PP1) and regulates several PP1-dependent signaling pathways, such as pathways involved in learning and memory.

title: High and low level freezing in response to fear: amygdala and hippocampus
description: Analysis of the amygdalae and hippocampi of lines exhibiting high or low freezing behavior in response to fear. The amygdala and hippocampus are brain regions important in fear behavior. Results provide insight into the genetic basis of fear behavior.

title: Angiopoietin-1 and vascular endothelial growth factor angiogenic effect on aortic rings (RAE230A)
description: Analysis of aortic rings treated with angiopoietin-1 (Ang-1) or vascular endothelial growth factor (VEGF). Aortic rings can generate neovessels ex vivo after angiogenic factor stimulation. Results identify transcriptional events associated with angiogenesis in VEGF and Ang-1 stimulated aortic rings.

title: Angiopoietin-1 and vascular endothelial growth factor angiogenic effect on aortic rings (RAE230B)
description: Analysis of aortic rings treated with angiopoietin-1 (Ang-1) or vascular endothelial growth factor (VEGF). Aortic rings can generate neovessels ex vivo after angiogenic factor stimulation. Results identify transcriptional events associated with angiogenesis in VEGF and Ang-1 stimulated aortic rings.

title: ErbB2/Neu and luteinizing hormone overexpression effect on the mammary gland: time course
description: Analysis of mammary glands of 5 and 10-week-old bitransgenics overexpressing oncogenic ErbB2/Neu and luteinizing hormone (LH). Results provide insight into the effect of chronic trophic maintenance of the mammary epithelial cells, induced by LH, on ErbB2/Neu-initiated tumorigenesis.

title: Estrogen receptor alpha positive breast cancer cells response to hyperactivation of MAPK pathway
description: Analysis of estrogen receptor (ER) alpha positive MCF-7 breast cancer cells overexpressing constitutively active Raf-1, constitutively active MEK, constitutively active c-erbB-2, or ligand-activatable EGFR. Results indicate that increased MAPK activation results in loss of ER-alpha expression.

title: Leukotriene D4 and thrombin effect on endothelial cells: time course
description: Temporal analysis of umbilical vein endothelial cells (HUVEC) treated with leukotriene D4 (LTD4) and/or thrombin. LTD4 activates the cysteinyl leukotriene receptor cysLT2-R. Thrombin activates the protease-activated receptor PAR-1. cysLT2-R and PAR-1 may cooperate to augment vascular injury.

title: Compensated and decompensated right ventricular hypertrophy at onset: time course
description: Temporal analysis of right ventricles at the onset of compensated or decompensated right ventricular hypertrophy. Compensated and decompensated phenotypes induced by injection with 30 and 80 mg/kg monocrotaline, respectively. Results identify potential prognostic markers and therapeutic targets.

title: Growth hormone effect on bone: time course
description: Analysis of femurs and tibias of growth hormone (GH) deficient animals at 6 and 24 hours following treatment with 4 mg/kg body weight GH. Results provide insight into the insulin-like growth factor-I dependent and independent pathways that mediate the action of GH in bone.

title: Retinoblastoma-like p107 knockout effect on neurospheres (MG-430A)
description: Expression profiling of neurospheres cultured from the brain of embryonic day 13.5 p107 knockout embryos. p107 knockout animals exhibit enhanced stem cell self-renewal and have an increased number of stem cells.

title: Retinoblastoma-like p107 knockout effect on neurospheres (MG-430B)
description: Expression profiling of neurospheres cultured from the brain of embryonic day 13.5 p107 knockout embryos. p107 knockout animals exhibit enhanced stem cell self-renewal and have an increased number of stem cells.

title: Positively selected H-2b T cell receptor transgenic thymocytes (MG-U74A)
description: Analysis of positively selected T cell receptor (TCR) transgenic thymocytes from H-2b animals. T lymphocyte development involves TCR-mediated positive selection that ensures the survival of potentially useful T cells. Results provide insight into T lymphocyte development and selection.

title: Positively selected H-2b T cell receptor transgenic thymocytes (MG-U74B)
description: Analysis of positively selected T cell receptor (TCR) transgenic thymocytes from H-2b animals.
