T lymphocyte development involves TCR-mediated positive selection that ensures the survival of potentially useful T cells. Results provide insight into T lymphocyte development and selection.

title: Positively selected H-2b T cell receptor transgenic thymocytes (MG-U74C)
description: Analysis of positively selected T cell receptor (TCR) transgenic thymocytes from H-2b animals. T lymphocyte development involves TCR-mediated positive selection that ensures the survival of potentially useful T cells. Results provide insight into T lymphocyte development and selection.

title: Early embryo development
description: Analysis of early embryos at various stages of development: before zygotic transcription, during the slow and the fast phases of cellularization, and at the beginning and the end of gastrulation. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying the control of cellularization.

title: AMP-activated protein kinase gamma-3 knockout effect on skeletal muscle
description: Analysis of white portions of gastrocnemius muscles from AMP-activated protein kinase (AMPK) gamma-3 knockout mutants. AMPK gamma-3 is important in glucose uptake, glycogen synthesis, and fat oxidation. Results compared to those from AMPK gamma-3 R225Q transgenic mutant (GDS1939).

title: AMP-activated protein kinase gamma-3 R225Q mutation effect on skeletal muscle
description: Analysis of white portions of gastrocnemius muscles from AMP-activated protein kinase (AMPK) gamma-3 R225Q transgenic mutants. AMPK gamma-3 is important in glucose uptake, glycogen synthesis, and fat oxidation. Results compared to those from AMPK gamma-3 knockout mutant (GDS1938).

title: Eccentric exercise effect on skeletal muscle: time course
description: Analysis of vastus lateralis muscles of healthy subjects 3 and 48 hrs after a bout of resistance (RES) exercise of 300 single-leg maximal eccentric contractions (EC). EC is the lengthening of a muscle due to an external force while that muscle is contracting. EC commonly results in muscle damage.

title: Cystic fibrosis transmembrane conductance regulator deficiency in different genetic backgrounds
description: Analysis of lungs of C57BL/6J (B6) or BALB/c (BALB) animals deficient for cystic fibrosis transmembrane conductance regulator (CFTR). B6 background animals have a higher propensity to develop CF lung disease. Results suggest the variable severity of CF is controlled by multiple genetic factors.

title: Transgenic Krüppel-like factor 4 induction: time course
description: Analysis of RKO colon cancer cell line treated for up to 24 hours with ponasterone A to induce expression of a full-length, transgenic Krüppel-like factor 4 (KLF4). KLF4 is an epithelially-enriched, zinc finger transcription factor. Results provide insight into the biochemical function of KLF4.

title: Various tissues from somatic clones
description: Analysis of various tissues from somatically cloned neonates. Clones produced by injecting the nucleus of cumulus or Sertoli cells into enucleated mature oocytes. Results provide insight into how somatic clones differ from each other and from normal individuals produced by sexual reproduction.

title: Embryonic pituitary gland
description: Analysis of pituitary glands from day 17 embryos and post-hatch day 3 animals using a neuroendocrine system specific cDNA microarray. Major cell types in the anterior pituitary gland have differentiated at embryonic day 17. Results used to validate the method of amplifying RNA from pituitary glands.

title: Pituitary gland development
description: Analysis of embryonic pituitary glands at various ages from day 10 to day 17 using a neuroendocrine system specific cDNA microarray. Results identify genes potentially involved in the onset of thyroid-stimulating hormone beta-subunit, growth hormone, and prolactin gene transcription.

title: Various T7 RNA polymerase-based RNA amplification/labeling methods
description: Comparison of expression profiles generated using various T7 RNA polymerase-based in vitro transcription (IVT) RNA labeling methods. The length of the IVT reactions ranged from 4 to 16 hours. Results provide evidence for amplification method-dependent biases in gene expression data.

title: Fibroblast growth factor receptor 1 activation effect on mammary glands: time course
description: Temporal analysis of mammary glands from transgenic animals treated with dimerizing agent AP20187 to activate inducible fibroblast growth factor receptor 1 (iFGFR1). iFGFR1 dimerization induces proliferation in the mammary gland. Results provide insight into the early progression of tumorigenesis.

title: Various muscle diseases (HG-U133A)
description: Analysis of muscle biopsy specimens from patients with various muscle diseases. Results provide insight into the diagnosis and pathogenesis of muscle diseases.

title: Interferon gamma effect on suppressor of cytokine signaling-1 deficient livers: time course
description: Analysis of the effect of interferon gamma (IFNg) on the livers of animals lacking IFNg, or both suppressor of cytokine signaling-1 (SOCS1) and IFNg. Gene expression examined up to 48 hours following IFNg treatment. Results provide insight into the role of SOCS1 in regulating the response to IFNg.

title: Ischemic myocardium response to reperfusion
description: Analysis of ischemic heart ventricles 2 or 7 days after reperfusion. Ischemia induced by occlusion of the left anterior descending coronary artery. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms involved in the early and late inflammatory phases of acute myocardial infarction.

title: Testicular diffuse large B cell lymphoma
description: Analysis of testicular diffuse large B cell lymphoma (DLBCL) tissues with small homozygous HLA-DQ/HLA-DR deletions, larger hemizygous MHC complex deletions, or without deletions. Results provide insight into the significance of the downregulation of HLA class II expression in testicular DLBCL.

title: Glioma-derived stem cell factor effect on angiogenesis in the brain
description: Analysis of gliomas of different grades. Stem cell factor (SCF) is overexpressed by glioma cells but its role in gliomagenesis has been unclear. Results identify a positive correlation of SCF expression with increasing glioma grade which supports a role for SCF in tumor angiogenesis in the brain.

title: DNA gyrase inhibition effect on recA, topA, and dnaC mutants: time course
description: Analysis of recA, topA, and dnaC single mutants at various time points up to 20 minutes following treatment with norfloxacin to inhibit DNA gyrase. recA, topA, and dnaC mutants are deficient DNA repair, DNA relaxation and DNA replication, respectively.

title: Melanotransferrin effect on brain
description: Analysis of brain from melanotransferrin (MTf) knockout mutants. MTf or melanoma tumor antigen p97 is a membrane bound iron binding transferrin homolog highly expressed in melanomas and at lower levels in normal tissues. Results provide insight into the function of MTf.

title: Melanocyte to melanoma transformation
description: Expression profiling of normal melanocytes, primary melanoma cells, and metastatic melanoma cells. Results provide insight into changes in advanced melanoma relative to normal melanocytes and reveal new targets that can be used in assessing prognosis, staging, and therapy of melanoma patients.

title: Endothelial cell response to hypoxia and subsequent reoxygenation
description: Expression profiling of umbilical vein endothelial cells (HUVECs) subjected to hypoxia for 1 hour and subsequent reoxygenation for various lengths of time up to 24 hours.

title: Uncomplicated and complicated malaria: whole blood
description: Expression profiling of pooled whole blood from Gabonese children with uncomplicated or complicated malaria. The children with uncomplicated malaria present mild symptoms, while those with complicated or severe malaria have severe anemia.

title: RNAlater preservative effect on uterine myometrium: time course
description: Analysis of uterine myometrial tissue specimens stored in RNAlater preservative for 24 or 74 hours at room temperature. Results indicate RNALater did not contribute any systematic shift in quantitative RNA expression results relative to alternative tissue processing methods (fresh, snap-frozen).

title: Various prostate cell types
description: Analysis of basal, luminal secretory, stromal fibromuscular, and endothelial cells of the prostate. Cell types separated with magnetic cell sorting (MACS) based on cell-type specific cluster designation (CD) antigens. Results identify gene expression signatures at the level of individual cell types.

title: Keratinocyte response to GLI1 and GLI2 induction: time course
description: Analysis of keratinocyte HaCaT cells at 24 and 72 hours following induction of GLI1 or a constitutively active form of GLI2 from a tetracycline inducible promoter. GLI transcription factors mediate the hedgehog signal in development and carcinogenesis.

title: Gliomas of grades III and IV (HG-U133A)
description: Analysis of grades III and IV gliomas of various histologic types. Results used to develop a gene-expression based, histology independent-classification scheme, and provide insight into the biology of gliomas.

title: Gliomas of grades III and IV (HG-U133B)
description: Analysis of grades III and IV gliomas of various histologic types. Results used to develop a gene-expression based, histology independent-classification scheme, and provide insight into the biology of gliomas.

title: Retinal determination protein Eyeless ectopic expression
description: Analysis of leg, wing, and antenna imaginal discs ectopically expressing the retinal determination protein (RD) Eyeless (Ey) in the atonal wild-type or mutant background. Genes that depend on atonal for expression are involved in processes occurring after RD. Results identify targets of Ey.

title: Zinc-finger protein basonuclin knockdown effect on oocytes
description: Analysis of oocytes following RNAi knockdown of basonuclin (Bnc1), a zinc-finger protein found in abundance in oocytes. The Bnc1 gene qualifies as a maternal-effect gene because the source of pre-implantation embryonic Bnc1 is maternal. Results provide insight into the function of Bnc1.

title: Amyloid precursor protein intracellular domain effect on neural cells
description: Analysis of neural cells induced to express amyloid precursor protein (APP) intracellular domain (AICD) or the combination of AICD and its co-activator Fe65. Secretase processing of APP produces beta-amyloid, the main constituent of Alzheimer plaques, and AICD. Results identify target genes of AICD.

title: Endothelin-1 effect on dermal fibroblasts
description: Anlaysis of primary dermal fibroblasts treated with exogenous endothelin-1 (ET1) peptide for 24 hours. ET1 has been implicated in the pathogenesis of fibrotic and inflammatory diseases. Results suggest that stable silencing of Et1 is important for the phenotypic stability of dermal fibroblasts.

title: Ras-cAMP pathway perturbation
description: Analysis of cells following perturbation of the Ras-cAMP pathway by disrupting or constitutively activating cAMP signaling, or varying the concentration of cAMP. Results provide insight into the flow of information across a genome.

title: Heat-stress-associated 32-kD protein Hsa32 null mutant response to heat shock
description: Analysis of heat-stress-associated 32-kD protein (Hsa32) knockout mutant seedlings subjected to heat shock at 37 degrees C for 2 hours. Results provide insight into the role of Hsa32 in acquired thermotolerance.

title: Primary visual cortex response to visual input deprivation (MG-U74A)
description: Analysis of primary visual cortex (V1) under conditions of binocular deprivation by dark-rearing (DR) or monocular deprivation (MD). Animals subjected to DR from birth till postnatal day (P) 27 or to MD from P11-12 to P27. Results provide insight into the role of visual activity in V1 development.

title: Primary visual cortex response to visual input deprivation (MG-U74B)
description: Analysis of primary visual cortex (V1) under conditions of binocular deprivation by dark-rearing (DR) or monocular deprivation (MD). Animals subjected to DR from birth till postnatal day (P) 27 or to MD from P11-12 to P27. Results provide insight into the role of visual activity in V1 development.

title: Airway disease trait manifestation in various genetic backgrounds: lungs (MG-U74A)
description: Analysis of lungs of animals exhibiting extremes in airway hyperreactivity, goblet cell metaplasia, or both. Animals were derived from an intercross of an F1 hybrid strain, generated by crossing C57Bl/6J and Balb/cJ strains. Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of complex airway diseases.

title: Primary visual cortex response to visual input deprivation (MG-U74C)
description: Analysis of primary visual cortex (V1) under conditions of binocular deprivation by dark-rearing (DR) or monocular deprivation (MD). Animals subjected to DR from birth till postnatal day (P) 27 or to MD from P11-12 to P27. Results provide insight into the role of visual activity in V1 development.

title: Airway disease trait manifestation in various genetic backgrounds: lungs (MG-U74B)
description: Analysis of lungs of animals exhibiting extremes in airway hyperreactivity, goblet cell metaplasia, or both. Animals were derived from an intercross of an F1 hybrid strain, generated by crossing C57Bl/6J and Balb/cJ strains. Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of complex airway diseases.

title: Airway disease trait manifestation in various genetic backgrounds: lungs (MG-U74C)
description: Analysis of lungs of animals exhibiting extremes in airway hyperreactivity, goblet cell metaplasia, or both. Animals were derived from an intercross of an F1 hybrid strain, generated by crossing C57Bl/6J and Balb/cJ strains. Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of complex airway diseases.

title: Melanoma progression
description: Analysis of tissue specimens representing benign nevus, atypical nevus, melanoma in situ, vertical growth phase (VGP) melanoma, and metastatic growth phase (MGP) melanoma. Results identify expression signatures that distinguish benign and atypical nevi and melanomas in situ from VGPs and MGPs.

title: Mdr2 knockout model of hepatocellular carcinoma at precancerous stages
description: Analysis of livers of 3 and 12-month-old Mdr2 knockout (Mdr2-KO) mutants. Mdr2-KO mutants lack the liver P-glycoprotein responsible for phosphatidylcholine transport across the canalicular membrane, and develop hepatocellular carcinoma between the ages of 12 and 15 months.

title: Colon carcinoma cell line differentiation: transporter and ion channel expression profile
description: Analysis of colon carcinoma Caco-2 cells cultured for various lengths of time up to 3 weeks in flasks or on filters. An array focusing on transporters and ion channels was used. Results provide insight into the influence of cell differentiation on the mRNA expression of transporters and channels.

title: Age effect on healing femoral fractures: time course
description: Analysis of healing femurs of 6, 26, and 52-week-old Sprague-Dawley females at various time points up to 6 weeks after fracture. 6, 26, and 52-week-old animals regain normal skeletal biomechanics 4 weeks, 10 weeks, and 6 months after fracture, respectively.

title: Utrophin/dystrophin-deficient double mutant and dystrophin-deficient mdx mutant skeletal muscles
description: Comparison of skeletal muscles of utrophin/dystrophin double knockout (dko) mutants and dystrophin-deficient mdx mutants. dko and mdx mutants display skeletal muscle weakness and degeneration but only dko mutants display clinical features similar to Duchenne muscular dystrophy patients.

title: Metabolic state-dependent stress response to short-term anaerobiosis: time course
description: Analysis of catabolite-repressed (glucose) or derepressed (galactose) wildtype JM43 cells shifted from aerobiosis to anaerobiosis (2 generations). Results identify metabolic remodeling that occurs during acclimatization to short-term anaerobiosis in galactose but not in glucose.

title: Msn2/4 role in metabolic remodeling during short-term anaerobiosis: time course
description: Analysis of catabolite-derepressed (galactose) wildtype JM43 and isogenic msn2/4 mutant KKY8 cells shifted to short-term anaerobiosis (2 generations). Msn2 and 4 are key stress factors. Results suggest Msn2/4 involvement in metabolic remodeling during acclimatization to short-term anaerobiosis.

title: Lymphotoxin-beta receptor signaling inhibition effect on lymph nodes: time course (MG-430A)
description: Analysis of lymph nodes from animals treated with soluble lymphotoxin-beta receptor (LTbetaR)-immunoglobulin fusion protein (LTbetaR-Ig) for up to 35 days. LTbetaR-Ig inhibits LTbetaR activation, important in the differentiation of lymphoid germinal centers and follicular dendritic cells.

title: Lymphotoxin-beta receptor signaling inhibition effect on lymph nodes: time course (MG-430B)
description: Analysis of lymph nodes from animals treated with soluble lymphotoxin-beta receptor (LTbetaR)-immunoglobulin fusion protein (LTbetaR-Ig) for up to 35 days. LTbetaR-Ig inhibits LTbetaR activation, important in the differentiation of lymphoid germinal centers and follicular dendritic cells.

title: Thioredoxin interacting protein mutant model of hepatocellular carcinoma
description: Analysis of hepatocellular carcinoma  (HCC) tumors from thioredoxin interacting protein (Txnip) deficient mutants. Txnip deficiency leads to HCC in mice. Results provide insight into the role of Txnip in the pathogenesis of HCC.

title: Fibrosarcoma cell line response to various cytostatic drugs
description: Analysis of fibrosarcoma HT1080 cells following exposure to the cytostatic chemotherapeutic agents actinomycin D or vincristine for 24 hours, or doxorubicin for 6 and 24 hours. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying the cell death in response to cytotoxic therapies.

title: Sustained EGR1 expression in endothelial cells: time course (HG-U133A)
description: Analysis of umbilical vein endothelial cells (HUVEC) at various time points up to 48 hours following transfection with a recombinant adenovirus expressing early growth response-1 (EGR1). EGR1 is implicated in cell growth, apoptosis, and differentiation. Results identify potential EGR1 target genes.

title: Sustained EGR1 expression in endothelial cells: time course (HG-U133B)
description: Analysis of umbilical vein endothelial cells (HUVEC) at various time points up to 48 hours following transfection with a recombinant adenovirus expressing early growth response-1 (EGR1). EGR1 is implicated in cell growth, apoptosis, and differentiation. Results identify potential EGR1 target genes.

title: Wilms' tumor 1-associating protein knockdown
description: Analysis of umbilical vein endothelial cells (HUVEC) following siRNA knockdown of Wilms' tumor 1-associating protein, WTAP. WTAP interacts with Wilms' tumor 1 (WT1). The Wilms' tumor suppressor gene WT1 is important in the development of the genitourinary system.

title: Lupus-prone BWF1 males and females: spleen (MG-U74A)
description: Analysis of spleens from 4-month-old pre-lupus male and female BWF1 animals. The BWF1 strain is a model for systemic lupus erythematosus. BWF1 females are more prone to lupus than BWF1 males.

title: Lupus-prone BWF1 males and females: spleen (MG-U74B)
description: Analysis of spleens from 4-month-old pre-lupus male and female BWF1 animals. The BWF1 strain is a model for systemic lupus erythematosus. BWF1 females are more prone to lupus than BWF1 males.

title: Lupus-prone BWF1 males and females: spleen (MG-U74C)
description: Analysis of spleens from 4-month-old pre-lupus male and female BWF1 animals. The BWF1 strain is a model for systemic lupus erythematosus. BWF1 females are more prone to lupus than BWF1 males.

title: Ulcerative colitis
description: Expression profiling of colonic mucosa from patients with ulcerative colitis, a chronic inflammatory bowel disease of the colon. Colonic mucosa from patients with irritable bowel syndrome used as controls. Biopsies obtained during colonoscopy from region with macroscopically normal appearing mucosa.

title: Autoimmune regulator AIRE knockout effect on thymic epithelial cells
description: Expression profiling of thymic epithelial cells from autoimmune regulator AIRE knockout mutants. Mutations in the AIRE gene cause autoimmune polyendocrinopathy-candidiasis-ectodermal dystrophy, a rare autosomal recessive disease in humans.

title: Nodal, Mixer, and Sox17 inactivation effect on gastrula stage embryo
description: Analysis of stage 11 embryos inactivated for Nodal signaling, or depleted of Mixer or Sox17 proteins.  Microdissected animal caps and vegetal and equatorial regions of stage 11 embryos also examined. Nodal, Mixer, and Sox17 are key proteins of a pathway controlling endoderm formation.

title: Hypoxia-inducible factors-1 and -2 overexpression effect on embryonic kidney cells
description: Analysis of HEK293T embryonic kidney cells subjected to hypoxia or overexpressing hypoxia-inducible factor (HIF)-1, degradation resistant HIF-1, or HIF-2. Results provide insight into the respective roles of HIF-1 and HIF-2 in the cellular response to hypoxia.

title: Age effect on livers of long-lived Snell dwarf mutants
description: Analysis of livers from 6 and 22-month-old Snell dwarf mice which live 40% longer than wild types. Snell animals have a mutation in the Pit1 gene which prevents the development of anterior pituitary cells that produce growth hormone, thyroid stimulating hormone, and prolactin.

title: Midshaft fracture effect on the proximal femoral growth plate: time course
description: Analysis of proximal femoral growth plate at various time points up to 6 weeks following midshaft fracture in 4 week-old Sprague-Dawley females. Growth plates from fractured femora and intact contralateral femora compared. Midshaft femoral fracture stimulates linear growth of the bone.

title: Coronary smooth muscle cell response to beta-1 receptor blockers metoprolol and nebivolol
description: Expression profiling of coronary smooth muscle cells treated with metoprolol or nebivolol. Metoprolol and nebivolol are beta 1-receptor blockers. In a study of 155 patients with hypertension, adverse effects of metoprolol were higher than nebivolol (Uhlir et al. 1991).

title: Bronchial epithelial cell response to respiratory syncytial virus infection: time course
description: Expression profiling of bronchial epithelial cells at 4 and 24 hours following treatment with respiratory syncytial virus (RSV) at 1.0 MOI. RSV is the most common cause of bronchiolitis and pneumonia among infants.

title: Lung immune response to Nippostrongylus brasiliensis infection: time course
description: Analysis of lungs of SCID animals at various time points up to 12 days post infection with Nippostrongylus brasiliensis. SCID animals have no functional B or T cells but a fully functional innate immune system. Results provide insight into the immune response to helminth infection in the lung.

title: Myc activation and deactivation effect on pancreatic islet beta cells
description: Analysis of transgenic pancreatic islet beta cells after activation of Myc for up to 24 hours or activation for 21 days followed by deactivation for up to 6 days. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of Myc-driven tumorigenesis in vivo.

title: TSLC1/IGSF4 deficiency effect on testis
description: Analysis of whole testes of TSLC1/IGSF4 deficient animals. The TSLC1/IGSF4 protein belongs to the immunoglobulin superfamily of cell adhesion molecules. Results provide insight into the role of TSLC1/IGSF4 in spermatogenesis.

title: Nurr1 overexpression effect on neural stem cells
description: Expression profiling of neural stem cell lines overexpressing the orphan nuclear receptor Nurr1. Nurr1 is critical for the development of the ventral midbrain dopaminergic neurons, the cells primarily lost in Parkinson's disease.

title: Thymocytes of the NOD background response to activation by a mimotope peptide
description: Analysis of NOD or B6g7 strain BDC2.5 transgenic fetal thymic organ culture thymocytes after addition of a mimotope peptide that activates mature BDC2.5 T cells to inititate apoptosis. Results provide insight into the differential sensitivity to clonal deletion of this clonotype in the 2 strains.

title: Histone H2B N-terminal domain mutants
description: Analysis of histone H2B mutants that have a substitution of all acetylated N-terminal lysine (K) residues with glycine, or a deletion in the N-terminal domain. Results provide insight into the role of the histone NTD and histone lysine acetylation in transcriptional regulation.

title: Hoxa11/Hoxd11 null mutation effect on embryonic kidney development (MG-430A)
description: Analysis of kidneys from Hoxa11/Hoxd11 double null mutants at various embryonic ages up to E16.5. Hox11 genes play critical roles in kidney development. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms of Hox11 function in kidney development.

title: Hoxa11/Hoxd11 null mutation effect on embryonic kidney development (MG-430B)
description: Analysis of kidneys from Hoxa11/Hoxd11 double null mutants at various embryonic ages up to E16.5. Hox11 genes play critical roles in kidney development. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms of Hox11 function in kidney development.

title: Hoxa11/Hoxd11 null mutation effect on the metanephric mesenchyme
description: Analysis of metanephric mesenchyme (MM) dissected from the rudimentary kidney of embryonic day E11.5 Hoxa11 Hoxd11 null mutants and wild types. Gene expression in wild type ureteric bud (UB) examined. Hox11 genes are expressed in the early MM and are required for the induction of UB formation.

title: Prostate cancer cell line LNCaP response to synthetic androgen R1881: time course
description: Expression profiling of prostate cancer cell line LNCaP treated for up to 8 hours with the synthetic androgen R1881. LNCaP cells grow slowly in medium devoid of steroids but resume growth upon the addition of androgens. The study aims to identify direct targets of the androgen receptor.

title: Vectorless gravity effect on T cell activation
description: Analysis of T cells costimulated with concanavalin A and anti-CD28 antibody in a vectorless gravity environment, which approximates true freefall or microgravity experienced in spaceflight. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the altered immune function experienced by astronauts.

title: Macrophage response to hypoxia
description: Expression profiling of cultured macrophages subjected to hypoxia for 24 hours. Macrophages were derived from the mononuclear cells of 4 healthy donors.

title: Anesthesia and fear conditioning effect on amygdala
description: Analysis of basolateral amygdalae from animals following isoflurane treatment, pain treatment, or fear conditioning alone or in combination with isoflurane treatment. Fear conditioning leads to long-term memory formation. Isoflurane is a general anesthetic and amnestic agent.

title: Epstein-Barr virus nuclear antigen 2 activation
description: Analysis of Epstein-Barr virus (EBV) negative B-cell lines BL41K3 and BJABK3 following activation of EBV nuclear antigen 2 (EBNA-2). EBNA-2 fused to the hormone-binding domain of the estrogen receptor, and EBNA-2 activated upon estrogen binding. Results identify EBNA-2 target genes.

title: Endothelial cell morphogenesis (HG-U133A)
description: Analysis of microvascular endothelial cells stimulated to either proliferate or undergo tubulogenesis in vitro. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying the regulation of endothelial cell morphogenesis.

title: Endothelial cell morphogenesis (HG-U133B)
description: Analysis of microvascular endothelial cells stimulated to either proliferate or undergo tubulogenesis in vitro. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying the regulation of endothelial cell morphogenesis.

title: Type II activated macrophage
description: Analysis of type II activated macrophages (Mphi) generated by stimulation with lipopolysaccharide (LPS) in the presence of IgG immune complexes. Type II activated Mphi produce high levels of IL-10 and low levels of IL-12 relative to classically activated Mphi stimulated with LPS alone.

title: Celiac disease: intraepithelial cytotoxic T lymphocytes
description: Analysis of intraepithelial cytotoxic T lymphocytes (IE-CTLs), aberrantly expressing the cytolytic natural killer (NK) cell lineage receptor NKG2C, from celiac disease patients. Results provide insight into the role of IE-CTLs reprogrammed into NK-like cells in the pathogenesis of celiac disease.

title: Bisphenol A effect on testicular Sertoli cells: time course
description: Analysis of testicular Sertoli cells (TSCs) treated with bisphenol A (BPA) for up to 12 hours. BPA, an industrial chemical that acts as an environmental estrogen, induces TSC death. Results provide insight into the mechanisms underlying TSC injury, which is accompanied by ER stress, induced by BPA.

title: DNA demethylation effect on dermal fibroblasts
description: Analysis of primary dermal fibroblasts treated with the DNA methyltransferase inhibitor 5-aza-2'-deoxycytidine (Aza-dC) for 96 hours. This study seeks to identify developmental regulator genes whose expression in terminally differentiated cells is inhibited by DNA methylation.

title: Ductal carcinoma in situ to invasive ductal carcinoma progression (HG-U133A)
description: Analysis of preinvasive ductal carcinoma in situ (DCIS) and invasive ductal carcinoma (IDC) tumors. Pairs of patient-matched DCIS and IDC tumor specimens analyzed. Results provide insight into the mechanisms underlying the progression of DCIS to IDC.

title: Ductal carcinoma in situ to invasive ductal carcinoma progression (HG-U133 2.0)
description: Analysis of preinvasive ductal carcinoma in situ (DCIS) and invasive ductal carcinoma (IDC) tumors. Pairs of patient-matched DCIS and IDC tumor specimens analyzed. Results provide insight into the mechanisms underlying the progression of DCIS to IDC.

title: Lipopolysaccharide effect on macrophages pretreated with carbon monoxide: time course
description: Analysis of RAW 264.7 macrophages exposed to carbon monoxide (CO) for 3 hours and subsequently treated with lipopolysaccharide (LPS) for up to 4 hours. CO suppresses proinflammatory responses elicited by LPS. Results indicate that PPARgamma mediates the anti-inflammatory effects of CO.

title: Acute rotavirus infection: peripheral blood mononuclear cells
description: Expression profiling of peripheral blood mononuclear cells (PBMCs) from children with acute rotavirus diarrhea. Rotavirus is the most common cause of severe diarrhea in children.

title: Glycosylphosphatidylinositol-specific phospholipase D overexpression effect on hepatoma cells: time course
description: Analysis of hepatoma HepG2 cells 6 and 12 hours following transduction with a recombinant adenovirus expressing glycosylphosphatidylinositol-specific phospholipase D (GPI-PLD). Results provide insight into the role of GPI-PLD in hepatic lipid metabolism.

title: Antitumor agent azinomycin B cellular effect: dose response
description: Analysis of cells following treatment with 10 or 100 ug/ml of azinomycin B, a naturally occurring antitumor agent that forms interstrand crosslinks within the major groove of DNA. Results indicate that azinomycin B alters the expression of genes associated with DNA damage and repair.

title: Peritoneal mesotheliomas induced by o-nitrotoluene and bromochloracetic acid: dose response
description: Analysis of peritoneal mesotheliomas induced by various concentrations of o-nitrotoluene (o-NT) or bromochloracetic acid (BCA). o-NT is a high production chemical. BCA is a by-product of drinking water disinfection. Results provide insight into the mechanisms underlying mesothelioma formation.

title: Endometrium throughout the menstrual cycle
description: Analysis of the normal endometrium at distinct phases of the menstrual cycle. Results provide insight into whether molecular profiles of the endometrium can distinguish the different phases of the menstrual cycle.

title: 1-methyl-4-phenyl-1,2,3,6-tetrahydropyridine-lesioned substantia nigra: time course
description: Analysis of substantia nigrae (SN) injured by treatment with the dopaminergic neurotoxin 1-methyl-4-phenyl-1,2,3,6-tetrahydropyridine at 1 and 7 days postlesion. Parkinson's disease (PD) culminates in the loss of dopaminergic neurons of the SN. Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of PD.

title: Chronic endoplasmic reticulum stress imposed by misfolded surfactant protein C (HG-U133B)
description: Analysis of cells that constitutively express misfolded surfactant protein C, which induces chronic endoplasmic reticulum (ER) stress and cytotoxicity. Results provide evidence for an NF-kB-dependent adaptive response to the chronic ER stress imposed by the misfolded protein.

title: Skeletal muscle types (HG-U133A)
description: Analysis of tibialis anterior, deltoid, quadriceps, and gastrocnemius muscles obtained at autopsy from pediatric and geriatric subjects unaffected by neuromuscular disease. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the selective involvement of different muscles in muscular dystrophies.

title: Skeletal muscle types (HG-U133B)
description: Analysis of tibialis anterior, deltoid, quadriceps, and gastrocnemius muscles obtained at autopsy from pediatric and geriatric subjects unaffected by neuromuscular disease. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the selective involvement of different muscles in muscular dystrophies.

title: Androgen receptor modulator effect: time course (HG-U133A)
description: Analysis of LNCaP cells treated for 6 and 24 hours with RTI-018, an androgen receptor (AR) ligand with a mechanism of action different from that of canonical agonists. Results provide insight into the link between RTI-018 induced AR conformational changes and its ability to regulate gene expression.

title: Androgen receptor modulator effect: time course (HG-U133B)
description: Analysis of LNCaP cells treated for 6 and 24 hours with RTI-018, an androgen receptor (AR) ligand with a mechanism of action different from that of canonical agonists. Results provide insight into the link between RTI-018 induced AR conformational changes and its ability to regulate gene expression.

title: Transcription factor Egr3 expression effect on primary myotubes (MG-430B)
description: Analysis of primary myotubes expressing wild-type or inactive truncated Egr3. Transcription factor Egr3 activity is critical for the development of muscle spindles, skeletal muscle stretch receptors that mediate axial and limb proprioception.

title: Interleukin 2 deficient regulatory T cells expressing transcription factor Foxp3
description: Analysis of interleukin 2 (IL-2)-deficient, Foxp3-expressing regulatory T (Treg) cells. Foxp3+ Treg cells mediate dominant immune tolerance to self. Treg cells express IL-2 receptor alpha-chain CD25, but the role of IL-2 has been controversial to date. Results identify a role for IL-2 in Treg cells.

title: MicroRNA miR159a overexpression effect on flower
description: Analysis of stage 15 flowers from transgenics overexpressing miRNA miR159a. Most plant miRNAs have perfect or near-perfect complementarity with their targets. However, targets with up to five mismatches exist. Results provide insight into the mechanistic basis of target recognition by plant miRNA.

title: MicroRNA miR156b and miR164b overexpression effect on floral apex
description: Analysis of floral apices of transgenics overexpressing miRNA miR156b or miR164b. Most plant miRNAs have perfect or near-perfect complementarity with their targets. However, targets with up to 5 mismatches exist. Results provide insight into the mechanism of target recognition by plant miRNA.

title: MicroRNA miR164b and miR172a overexpression effect on vegetative apex
description: Analysis of vegetative apices of transgenics overexpressing miRNA miR164b or miR172a. Most plant miRNAs have perfect or near-perfect complementarity with their targets. However, targets with up to 5 mismatches exist. Results provide insight into the mechanism of target recognition by plant miRNA.

title: MicroRNA miR319a overexpression effect on the leaf
description: Analysis of leaves from transgenics overexpressing microRNA miR319a. Most plant miRNAs have perfect or near-perfect complementarity with their targets. However, targets with up to five mismatches exist. Results provide insight into the mechanistic basis of target recognition by plant miRNA.

title: Kruppel-like transcription factor 7 knockout effect on the olfactory epithelium
description: Analysis of olfactory epithelia from Kruppel-like transcription factor 7 (KLF7) knockout mutants. Kruppel-like transcription factors are important regulators of cell proliferation and differentiation in several organ systems. KLF7 knockout leads to impaired axon projection in the olfactory system.

title: Angiotensin II type 1 receptor antagonist effect on brain microvessels of hypertensive animals
description: Analysis of brain microvessels from hypertensive SHR males treated with candesartan, an angiotensin II type 1 receptor (AT1) antagonist, daily for 4 weeks. Blockade of angiotensin II AT1 receptors in cerebral microvessels protects against brain ischemia and inflammation.

title: Phenobarbital effect on nuclear receptor DHR96 null mutant
description: Analysis of DHR96 null mutant exposed to phenobarbital, a xenobiotic compound. DHR96 is an ortholog of the xenobiotic nuclear receptors pregnane X receptor and constitutive androstane receptor. Results provide insight into the role of DHR96 in mediating xenobiotic responses.

title: Nuclear receptor DHR96 ectopic expression effect on larvae
description: Analysis of transgenic larvae overexpressing the nuclear receptor DHR96, an ortholog of the xenobiotic nuclear receptors pregnane X receptor and constitutive androstane receptor. Results provide insight into the role of DHR96 in regulating xenobiotic responses.

title: Dietary iron-deficiency effect on jejunum (RAE230A)
description: Analysis of jejunum from iron (Fe)-deprived 12-week-old Sprague Dawleys. Results provide insight into the genetic response to Fe deprivation in the jejunum versus the duodenum (characterized earlier) and the role of distal gut segments in increasing Fe absorption in conditions of Fe-deficiency.

title: Dietary iron-deficiency effect on jejunum (RAE230B)
description: Analysis of jejunum from iron (Fe)-deprived 12-week-old Sprague Dawleys. Results provide insight into the genetic response to Fe deprivation in the jejunum versus the duodenum (characterized earlier) and the role of distal gut segments in increasing Fe absorption in conditions of Fe-deficiency.

title: Estren effect on the uterus: time course
description: Analysis of uteri from adult ovariectomized animals treated with estren, estradiol, dihydrotestosterone, or 19-nortestosterone for 2 or 24 hours. Estren is a synthetic steroid. Results provide insight into the molecular and physiological effects of estren on the uterus.

title: Estren effect on the estrogen receptor alpha null uterus: time course
description: Analysis of uteri from adult ovariectomized estrogen receptor alpha (ERalpha) null mutants treated with estren, estradiol, or 19-nortestosterone for 2 or 24 hours. Estren is a synthetic steroid. Results provide insight into the dependence of gene responses induced by estren in the uterus on ERalpha.

title: RNA-binding protein Nab3 inactivation
description: Analyis of nab3 temperature sensitive mutants subjected to the non-permissive temperature of 37 degrees C to inactivate Nab3. Nab3 is an RNA-binding protein involved in the transcription termination of nonpolyadenylated transcripts.

title: Early and late onset severe preeclampsia: placenta
description: Analysis of placentas from patients with early or late onset severe preeclampsia. Preeclampsia is a serious pregnancy-associated disorder characterized by hypertension and proteinuria. Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of preeclampsia.

title: Jun kinase inhibition effect on keratinocytes: time course
description: Analysis of keratinocytes at various time points up to 48 hours following treatment with the Jun kinase (JNK) inhibitor SP600125. SP600125 is a reversible ATP-competitive inhibitor specific for the three isoforms of JNK. Results identify JNK-regulated genes in epidermal keratinocytes.

title: Age effect on the hippocampus
description: Analysis of hippocampi of 2-month-old young and 15-month-old middle-aged animals. The hippocampal formation is one of the brain areas most affected by aging. Results provide insight into molecular changes accompanying the early stages of age-related memory decline.

title: Limb immobilization effect on skeletal muscle
description: Analysis of vastus lateralis muscle after knee immobilization for 48 hours. Limbs immobilized due to injury or illness experience significant muscle atrophy within 1 or 2 weeks. Results provide insight into the mechanisms regulating the rapid protein degradation in immobilized skeletal muscles.

title: Polycystic ovary syndrome: adipose tissue
description: Analysis of omental adipose tissues of morbidly obese patients with polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS). PCOS is a common hormonal disorder among women of reproductive age, and is characterized by hyperandrogenism and chronic anovulation. PCOS is associated with obesity.

title: Transcription factor p63 inactivation effect on squamous cells (HG-U133A)
description: Analysis of squamous cells following siRNA knockdown of the transcription factor p63, a homolog of the tumor suppressor p53. p63 encodes multiple isoforms that activate or repress transcription, and is critical for the development and maintenance of squamous epithelia.

title: Transcription factor p63 inactivation effect on squamous cells (HG-U133B)
description: Analysis of squamous cells following siRNA knockdown of the transcription factor p63, a homolog of the tumor suppressor p53. p63 encodes multiple isoforms that activate or repress transcription, and is critical for the development and maintenance of squamous epithelia.

title: Transcription factor p63 inactivation effect on squamous cells (HG-U133 2.0)
description: Analysis of squamous cell lines following siRNA knockdown of the transcription factor p63, a homolog of the tumor suppressor p53. p63 encodes multiple isoforms that activate or repress transcription, and is critical for the development and maintenance of squamous epithelia.

title: Skeletal muscle response to weight loss
description: Analysis of vastus lateralis muscles of morbidly obese patients before and after gastric bypass surgery. Surgical treatment of severe obesity such as gastric bypass provides the most dramatic reductions in body weight. Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of obesity.

title: Sphingosine 1-phosphate effect on glioblastoma cells
description: Analysis of glioblastoma cells treated with sphingosine 1-phosphate (S1P). S1P is a lysophospholipid involved in various cellular processes such as migration, proliferation, and survival. Results provide insight into the effect of S1P on glioblastoma angiogenesis and invasion.

title: DNA demethylation effect on terminally differentiated cells
description: Analysis of chondrocytes, fibroblasts, and osteoblasts treated with the DNA demethylating agent 5-aza-2'-deoxycytidine (5-aza-2dC). DNA methylation contributes to transcriptional silencing. Results identify genes whose expression is inhibited by DNA methylation in terminally differentiated cells.

title: Septic CD4+ splenocytes
description: Analysis of CD4+ splenocytes 6 hours after surgically induced sepsis. CD4+ splenocytes either undergo apoptosis or become Th2 polarized within 24 hours of the onset of sepsis.

title: Pregnane X receptor agonist effect on the liver (RAE230A)
description: Analysis of livers of animals treated with pregnenolone 16alpha-carbonitrile (PCN), a pregnane X receptor (NR1I2) agonist. NR1I2 is a member of the nuclear receptor family of ligand-activated transcription factors, and regulates the transcription of genes encoding xenobiotic metabolizing enzymes.

title: Pregnane X receptor agonist effect on the liver (RAE230B)
description: Analysis of livers of animals treated with pregnenolone 16alpha-carbonitrile (PCN), a pregnane X receptor (NR1I2) agonist. NR1I2 is a member of the nuclear receptor family of ligand-activated transcription factors, and regulates the transcription of genes encoding xenobiotic metabolizing enzymes.

title: Glucocorticoid receptor activation effect on breast cancer cells: time course (series 1)
description: Analysis of breast cancer MCF10A-Myc cells at various time points up to 24 hours following treatment with dexamethasone to activate the glucocorticoid receptor (GR). GR activation is critical in the stress response of virtually all cell types.

title: Glucocorticoid receptor activation effect on breast cancer cells: time course (series 2)
description: Analysis of breast cancer MCF10A-Myc cells at various time points up to 24 hours following treatment with dexamethasone to activate the glucocorticoid receptor (GR). GR activation is critical in the stress response of virtually all cell types.

title: Glucocorticoid receptor activation effect on breast cancer cells: time course (series 3)
description: Analysis of breast cancer MCF10A-Myc cells at various time points up to 24 hours following treatment with dexamethasone to activate the glucocorticoid receptor (GR). GR activation is critical in the stress response of virtually all cell types.

title: Testis development
description: Expression profiling of normal whole testes at various stages of development from gestation day 11 to postnatal day 2.

title: Bladders expressing fluorescent reporters
description: Expression profiling of postnatal day 1 transgenic bladders expressing enhanced green (EGFP) or yellow fluorescent proteins (EYFP).

title: Intestinal lymphoid tissues infected with Yersinia enterocolitica: time course
description: Analysis of Peyer's patches (PPs) and mesenteric lymph nodes (MLNs) infected with enteric pathogen Yersinia enterocolitica. PP and MLN removed from animals at various time points up to 7 days post oral infection. Results provide insight into the host response to pathogens within the PPs and MLNs.

title: Chitin oligomer chitooctaose effect on seedlings
description: Analysis of 14-day-old Col-0 seedlings treated with 1 uM chitooctaose for 3 minutes. Chitooctaose, a chitin oligomer, is released by plant enzymes from the cell wall of many plant fungal pathogens. Results provide insight into the plant defense response to fungal elicitors.

title: Pre-mRNA splicing factor sta1-1 mutant seedlings
description: Analysis of sta1-1 seedlings mutant for the pre-mRNA splicing factor STABILIZED1. sta1-1 mutant identified in a screen for mutants with enhanced stability of the normally unstable luciferase transcript. Results identify endogenous genes with enhanced transcript stability in the sta1-1 mutant.

title: Helicobacter-induced gastric cancer model
description: Analysis of cancerous stomach tissues of human gastrin overexpressing transgenic animals 6 months following infection with Helicobacter felis. Gastrin overexpression and H. felis infection synergistically accelerate gastric cancer in this model. Results identify gastric cancer-specific genes.

title: Prostaglandin J2 effect on neuroblastoma cell line: time course
description: Analysis of neuroblastoma SK-N-SH cells at various time points up to 24 hours following treatment with prostaglandin J2 (PGJ2), a neurotoxic product of inflammation. Results provide insight into mechanisms of PGJ2-induced accumulation/aggregation of ubiquitinated proteins and to neuronal cell death.

title: Staphylococcus aureus response to the disinfectant peracetic acid: time course
description: Analysis of Staphylococcus aureus cultures at 10 and at 20 minutes following treatment with 1 mM peracetic acid, an antimicrobial disinfectant. Results provide insight into the toxicogenomic response of S. aureus to a sublethal concentration of peracetic acid during the two growth states.

title: Lymphoblastoid cell lines from various CEPH pedigrees
description: Analysis of lymphoblastoid cell lines of 57 unrelated CEPH individuals from the International HapMap Project. Results used to find association between the expression phenotypes and SNP markers across the genome genotyped on the 57 individuals that belong to various CEPH pedigrees.

title: Long-term ethanol consumption effect on pancreas
description: Analysis of pancreas from Wistar males fed the ethanol containing Lieber-DeCarli diet for 8 weeks. Long-term ethanol consumption sensitizes the pancreas to subsequent insults. Results provide insight into the mechanisms underlying the ethanol-mediated sensitization of the pancreas to injury.

title: STN7 and STN8 protein kinase mutations effect on chloroplast gene expression
description: Analysis of protein kinase STN7 and STN8 mutants acclimated to fluctuating light using an array of nuclear chloroplast genes. The kinases regulate the distribution of absorbed solar energy between photosystems I and II. Results provide insight into the role of each in photosynthetic acclimation.

title: Adrenal gland across a 24-hour period
description: Analysis of whole adrenal glands collected at 4-hour intervals across a 24-hour period from adult females acclimated to a 12hr light, 12hr dark photoperiod. Results provide insight into the nature of oscillatory patterns of gene expression in the adrenal gland.

title: Azithromycin effect on Pseudomonas aeruginosa
description: Analysis of Pseudomonas aeruginosa cultures exposed to the macrolide azithromycin (AZM). P. aeruginosa infection is the major cause of morbidity and mortality in cystic fibrosis patients. Results provide insight into mechanisms underlying the beneficial role of AZM therapy in infection control.

title: Spermatogonial stem cell self-renewal: time course
description: Analysis of spermatogonial stem cells (SSCs) at various time points following withdrawal and replacement of glial cell line-derived neurotrophic factor (GDNF) and GDNF-family receptor alpha-1 (GFRalpha1). Results provide insight into the mechanisms of GDNF-supported in vitro self-renewal of SSCs.

title: Pheochromocytomas of various genetic origins
description: Analysis of 76 adrenal and extra-adrenal pheochromocytomas. These neural crest-derived tumors of uniform phenotype arise from inherited or sporadic mutations in at least six independent genes. Results provide insight into the molecular pathogenesis of pheochromocytomas.

title: Auxin response transcription factor ARF6 and ARF8 mutations effect on flower development
description: Analysis of mutant flowers heterozygous for arf6 but homozygous for arf8, and mutants double homozygous for both arf6 and arf8. Mutants examined at various stages of development. ARF6 and ARF8 are auxin response factors that coordinate the transition from immature to mature fertile flowers.

title: Developing mammary gland: terminal end buds and ducts
description: Comparison of terminal end buds (TEBs) and ducts from 5-week-old mammary glands. TEBs and ducts perform specialized functions for ductal invasion and branching. Results provide insight into the epithelial-stromal crosstalk that drives mammary morphogenesis.

title: Myelodysplastic syndromes: CD34+ cells
description: Analysis of CD34+ cells from 55 patients with myelodysplastic syndromes (MDSs). MDSs are a heterogeneous group of hematopoietic malignancies, characterized by blood cytopenias, ineffective hematopoiesis, and a hypercellular bone marrow. Results provide insight into the pathophysiology of MDS.

title: Adjudin effect on the testis: time course
description: Analysis of testis from Sprague-Dawleys 8 hours or 4 days after Adjudin treatment. Adjudin targets the Sertoli-germ cell adherens junction and causes germ cell depletion from the seminiferous epithelium. Results provide insight into the mechanisms that regulate junction restructuring in the testis.

title: Dominant negative thyroid hormone receptor overexpression effect on hind limb muscle development
description: Analysis of hind limbs of premetamorphic (NF55) and postmetamorphic (NF66) transgenics 2 or 6 weeks following transcriptional induction of a dominant negative thyroid hormone (TH) receptor transgene. Results provide insight into the role of TH in the maintenance of limb muscle during development.

title: Brown fat cell response to PGC-1alpha and PGC-1beta deficiency
description: Analysis of brown fat cells lacking PGC-1alpha or both PGC-1alpha and PGC-1beta. PGC-1alpha is required for the thermogenic function of brown fat cells, and PGC-1beta is the closest homolog of PGC-1alpha. Results provide insight into the specific roles of PGC-1alpha and PGC-1beta in brown fat cells.

title: ERK MAP kinase inactivation during G0/G1 to S phase transition: time course
description: Analysis of NIH3T3 cells treated with the ERK inhibitor U0126 before or after the addition of the ERK activator FGF. Cells stimulated with FGF for up to 12 hours. Results identify genes regulated by the ERK pathway during G0/G1 to S phase transition.

title: Methyl-CpG-binding protein 2 binding disruption during neuronal maturation
description: Analysis of SH-SY5Y cells undergoing PMA-induced neuronal maturational differentiation after transfection with a MeCP2 decoy to disrupt binding of MeCP2 to endogenous targets. Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of Rett syndrome, a neurodevelopmental disorder caused by mutations in MeCP2.

title: Rheumatoid arthritis: synovial tissues
description: Analysis of synovial tissues from patients with rheumatoid arthritis (RA) and osteoarthritis. RA is a chronic, inflammatory joint disease with pronounced inter-patient heterogeneity. Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of RA.

title: Diabetic cardiomyopathy progression model
description: Analysis of ventricles of streptozotocin-induced diabetic animals with early diabetic cardiomyopathy (DC) characterized by diastolic dysfunction (DD) or late DC characterized by DD and systolic dysfunction (SD). Results provide insight into mechanisms underlying DD and SD development in diabetes.

title: Alpha-tropomyosin mutant models of familial cardiac hypertrophy
description: Analysis of ventricles of mutants with mild ventricular disorganization and limited hypertrophy or with severe hypertrophy and fibrosis. Mutants possess familial cardiac hypertrophy (CH) associated mutations in alpha-tropomyosin. Results provide insight into mechanisms that mediate the onset of CH.

title: Prefrontal cortex postnatal development: time course
description: Analysis of prefrontal cortex (PFC) of animals at 2 to 10 weeks of age. Although the basic laminar structure of the PFC is established in utero, extensive remodeling continues into adolescence. Results map the overall pattern of changes in cortical gene transcripts during postnatal development.

title: Necrosis- and ethylene-inducing peptide effect on dicots
description: Analysis of dicot seedlings exposed for 30 minutes to necrosis- and ethylene-inducing peptide (Nep1) from fungal plant pathogen Fusarium oxysporum. Nep1 inhibited root and cotyledon growth and triggered cell death. Results provide insight into signaling networks involved in plant responses to Nep1.

title: Breast cancer cells resistant to green tea polyphenol epigallocatechin 3-gallate growth inhibition
description: Analysis of NF639 breast cancer cells resistant to growth inhibition by green tea polyphenol epigallocatechin 3-gallate (EGCG) after initial EGCG sensitivity. EGCG inhibits growth of NF639 cells by inhibiting Her-2/Neu signaling. Results provide insight into mechanisms underlying EGCG resistance.

title: UV irradiation effect on skin inactivated for tyrosine kinase receptor ErbB2: time course
description: Analysis of the dorsal skin of animals treated with the tyrosine kinase receptor Erbb2 inhibitor AG825 and subsequently exposed to UV radiation. Skin examined 6 and 12 hours after UV irradiation. Results provide insight into the role of Erbb2 in the response to UV and in UV-induced pathologies.

title: Protein kinase C alpha deficiency effect on small intestine
description: Analysis of small intestines of adult animals containing a homozygous null deletion of the gene for protein kinase C alpha (PKCa). PKCa knockouts show an elevated tendency to develop spontaneous intestinal tumors. Results provide insight into the role of the PKCa isoform in colorectal cancer.

title: Cystic fibrosis patients with mild and severe lung disease: nasal respiratory epithelium (HG-U133A)
description: Analysis of the nasal respiratory epithelium of cystic fibrosis (CF) patients with mild or severe lung disease. CF patients have identical homozygous deltaF508 CFTR genotypes but exhibit variability in pulmonary disease severity. Results provide insight into the basis of the phenotypic difference.

title: Cystic fibrosis patients with mild and severe lung disease: nasal respiratory epithelium (HG-U133B)
description: Analysis of the nasal respiratory epithelium of cystic fibrosis (CF) patients with mild or severe lung disease. CF patients have identical homozygous deltaF508 CFTR genotypes but exhibit variability in pulmonary disease severity. Results provide insight into the basis of the phenotypic difference.

title: Cochlear nucleus postnatal development
description: Analysis of cochlear nucleus (CN) at postnatal days 7 (P7), 14, and 21. Deprivation of auditory nerve input from P7 to P14 results in neuron death in the anteroventral CN. Results provide insight into the molecular basis underlying this critical period of susceptibility to loss of afferent input.

title: Congestive heart failure model
description: Analysis of the heart left ventricle 1 or 7 days after ligation of the left anterior descending coronary artery to induce myocardial infarction (MI). Animals subjected to MI had congestive heart failure (CHF) on day 7. Results identify genes involved in the progression to CHF.

title: Epidermal growth factor receptor activation effect on astrocytes: time course
description: Analysis of astrocytes 4 or 12 hours after epidermal growth factor (EGF) treatment to activate the EGF receptor (EGFR). EGFR is activated in astrocytes after various injuries to optic nerves. Results provide insight into the role of EGFR in the formation of reactive astrocytes after neural injury.

title: Bone morphogenic protein receptor 2 inactivation in smooth muscle effect on the lung: time course
description: Analysis of lungs 1 or 8 weeks following induction in smooth muscle of a dominant negative mutant form of type 2 bone morphogenic protein receptor (BMPR2). Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of hereditary pulmonary arterial hypertension (PAH), a disorder associated with BMPR2 mutations.

title: PGC-1alpha null brown adipocyte response to cAMP
description: Analysis of PGC-1alpha null brown adipocytes treated with cAMP for 4 hours. PGC-1alpha is required for the thermogenic function of brown fat cells, and cAMP plays a role in thermogenesis. Results provide insight into the role of PGC-1alpha in the global transcriptional response to cAMP.

title: Spleens of males and females at puberty
description: Comparison of male and female spleens at pre-puberty, puberty, and post-puberty. Results provide insight into the differences in immune responses between males and females during puberty.

title: RNA helicase p68/p72 knockdown effect on skeletal muscle cells (MG-430A)
description: Analysis of C2C12 skeletal muscle cells following shRNA knockdown of the RNA helicases p68 and p72. C2C12 myoblasts cultured in differentiation medium to induce differentiation into skeletal muscle cells. Results provide insight into the role of p68/p72 in skeletal muscle cell differentiation.

title: RNA helicase p68/p72 knockdown effect on skeletal muscle cells  (MG-430B)
description: Analysis of C2C12 skeletal muscle cells following shRNA knockdown of the RNA helicases p68 and p72. C2C12 myoblasts cultured in differentiation medium to induce differentiation into skeletal muscle cells. Results provide insight into the role of p68/p72 in skeletal muscle cell differentiation.

title: Dermatomyositis
description: Analysis of skeletal muscle biopsies of 5 patients with dermatomyositis (DM). DM is an idiopathic inflammatory myopathy characterized by muscle weakness and skin lesions. Results provide insight into the pathogenic pathways responsible for muscle fiber damage and dysfunction in myositis.

title: Inflammatory dilated cardiomyopathy
description: Analysis of parvovirus B19 positive endomyocardial biopsy (EMB) specimens from patients with inflammatory dilated cardiomyopathy (DCMi). Results report on a distinctive cardiac expression pattern in DCMi thereby providing insight into the pathogenesis of this DCM subtype.

title: BRG1 maternally depleted embryos
description: Analysis of two-cell stage embryos maternally depleted for BRG1, a catalytic subunit of SWI/SNF-related chromatin remodeling complexes. After fertilization, the embryo shifts from maternal to zygotic genome expression. Results provide insight into the role of Brg1 in this transition.

title: Mammary gland side population cells
description: Analysis of Hoechst dye 33342-effluxing side population cells (SPs) from the mammary glands of 4 to 6 week old C57/BL6 virgins. Results provide insight into the stem cell potential of mammary gland SPs.

title: Emery-Dreifuss muscular dystrophy model: regenerating skeletal muscle
description: Analysis of regenerating gastrocnemius muscles of emerin and lamin A/C knockout mutants at various time points up to 4 days following treatment with cardiotoxin to induce muscle injury. Mutations in emerin and lamin A/C cause Emery-Dreifuss muscular dystrophy (EDMD).

title: Spinal cord injury model: time course
description: Analysis of the T8 spinal cord segment up to 28 days after moderate contusion injury. Gene expression at the site of impact compared to that at the adjacent rostral and caudal regions. Results provide insight into the pathophysiology of secondary responses after moderate spinal cord injury (SCI).

title: CH1 domain deletions in p300 and CBP effect on hypoxic fibroblasts
description: Analysis of hypoxic fibroblasts bearing deletions in the CH1 domains of 1 allele of p300 and 2 alleles of CBP. CH1 domains interact with the C-TAD domain of hypoxia-inducible transcription factors HIF-1a and -2a. Results provide insight into the role of CH1 domains in the hypoxia response.

title: CH1 domain deletion, p300 and CBP heterozygous null mutant fibroblasts response to hypoxia
description: Analysis of hypoxic fibroblasts with deletions in the CH1 domains of p300 and CBP combined with a p300 or CBP allele knockout. CH1 domains interact with the C-TAD domain of hypoxia-inducible transcription factors HIF-1a and -2a. Results provide insight into the role for CH1 domains in hypoxia.

title: CH1 domain deletion, p300 and CBP heterozygous null mutant hypoxic fibroblasts response to trichostatin A
description: Analysis of trichostatin A (TSA)-treated hypoxic fibroblasts with deletions in CH1 domains of p300 and CBP, and a p300 or CBP allele knockout. TSA is a histone deacetylase inhibitor. Results provide insight into the role of deacetylase activity in CH1-independent hypoxia inducible transcription.

title: Paneth cell response to intestinal colonization
description: Analysis of Paneth cells harvested by LCM from germ-free animals and previously germ-free animals reconstituted with normal intestinal flora. Paneth cells are key effectors of small intestinal antimicrobial defense. Results provide insight into how intestinal surfaces cope with microbial challenges.

title: Simian immune deficiency virus Nef protein expression effect on CD4+ T cells
description: Analysis of Jurkat CD4+ T cells following induction of simian immune deficiency virus (SIV) Nef from an inducible promoter. The Nef protein is expressed early in HIV and SIV infections and plays a crucial role in disease progression. Results identify Nef-mediated changes in T cell gene expression.

title: Lung response to Influenza A virus and Streptococcus pneumoniae infections: time course
description: Analysis of female C57BL/6 lungs at various time points after influenza A virus or Streptococcus pneumoniae infection. Secondary bacterial infection during or after influenza recovery is common cause of pneumonia (PN). Results provide insight into molecular pathogenesis of severe infectious PN.

title: Activin ligand effect on LbetaT2 gonadotrope cell line: time course
description: Analysis of LbetaT2 pituitary gonadotrope cells at various time points up to 6 hours following treatment with activin. Activin, a member of the follicle stimulating hormone (FSH) beta superfamily of ligands, stimulates the secretion FSH from the gonadotrope cells of the anterior pituitary.

title: HIV viremia effect on monocytes
description: Analysis of CD14+ monocytes from 8 HIV patients at the aviremic state during highly active antiretroviral therapy (HAART) and at the viremic state after the cessation of HAART. Results provide insight into the impact of HIV infection and high-level HIV viremia on the function of monocytes.

title: Nuclear and extranuclear mutant huntingtin exon 1 protein effect on cerebellum
description: Analysis of cerebella of transgenics expressing mutant huntingtin (htt) exon 1 protein in nucleus only or in both nucleus and cytoplasm. The polyglutamine (polyQ) expansion in htt results in Huntington's disease (HD). Results provide insight into the impact of subcellular location of polyQ in HD.

title: Transcription factor IIF cofactor GAS41 overexpression
description: Analysis of SaoS2 cells overexpressing GAS41, a cofactor of the general transcription factor IIF. GAS41 expression from a tet-off vector was suppressed by the addition of doxycycline. Results provide insight into the role of GAS41 in eukaryotic transcription initiation.

title: Prostate adenocarcinomas of various Gleason patterns
description: Analysis of prostate adenocarcinoma specimens with Gleason patterns 3, 4, or 5. Adenocarcinoma specimens obtained by radical prostatectomy. Results identify molecular alterations underlying prostate cancer grades.

title: Pressure overload-induced cardiac hypertrophy effect on interleukin-18 null hearts
description: Analysis of left ventricles of interleukin (IL)-18 null mutants following surgical transaortic constriction (TAC) to induce cardiac hypertrophy (LVH) by pressure overload. IL-18 is a cardiotropic proinflammatory cytokine. Results provide insight into the role of IL-18 in the hypertrophic response.

title: Life-long exercise effect on the heart
description: Analysis of left heart ventricles of 16 month-old Sprague-Dawley females that had no access to physical activity, had access to twice-weekly one-hour physical activity, or had access to a running wheel.

title: Infarcted heart response to captopril and 3,5-diiodothyropropionic acid
description: Analysis of infarcted left heart ventricle of Spraque-Dawley males following treatment with thyroid hormone analog 3,5-diiodothyropropionic acid (DITPA), or captopril followed by DITPA. Results provide  insight into the effect of these drugs in congestive heart failure.

title: Cockayne syndrome group B protein-null fibroblast rescue (HG-U133A)
description: Analysis of Cockayne syndrome group B (CSB) protein-null fibroblasts rescued by expression of CSB cDNA. CS, a neurodegenerative disorder, arises mostly from CSB defects. Results provide insight into how CSB defects cause CS.

title: Cockayne syndrome group B protein-null fibroblast rescue  (HG-U133B)
description: Analysis of Cockayne syndrome group B (CSB) protein-null fibroblasts rescued by expression of CSB cDNA. CS, a neurodegenerative disorder, arises mostly from CSB defects. Results provide insight into how CSB defects cause CS.

title: Type 1 diabetes model: autoimmune target organs (MG-U74A)
description: Analysis of pancreata and submandibular and lacrimal glands from 6-, 9-, and 15-week-old NOD/scid animals, respectively, before the onset of autoimmune destruction of the tissues. The NOD/scid animal is a model for type 1 diabetes. The three organs examined are autoimmune targets in type 1 diabetes.

title: Type 1 diabetes model: autoimmune target organs (MG-U74B)
description: Analysis of pancreata and submandibular and lacrimal glands from 6-, 9-, and 15-week-old NOD/scid animals, respectively, before the onset of autoimmune destruction of the tissues. The NOD/scid animal is a model for type 1 diabetes. The three organs examined are autoimmune targets in type 1 diabetes.

title: Type 1 diabetes model: autoimmune target organs (MG-U74C)
description: Analysis of pancreata and submandibular and lacrimal glands from 6-, 9-, and 15-week-old NOD/scid animals, respectively, before the onset of autoimmune destruction of the tissues. The NOD/scid animal is a model for type 1 diabetes. The three organs examined are autoimmune targets in type 1 diabetes.

title: M-CSF and GM-CSF differentiated macrophages response to bacillus Calmette-Guerin (Subset A)
description: Analysis of granulocyte-macrophage colony-stimulating factor (CSF) or macrophage-CSF differentiated macrophages stimulated with bacillus Calmette-Guerin. The two macrophage types differ in their resistance to mycobacterial infection. Results identify host resistance or susceptibility genes.

title: Indole-3-acetic acid effect on
description: Escherichia coli
type: Analysis of Escherichia coli cells following treatment with indole-3-acetic acid (IAA). IAA is a ubiquitous molecule present in most living organisms and is the main plant growth hormone with auxin activity. Results provide insight into the function of IAA in E. coli.

title: M-CSF and GM-CSF differentiated macrophages response to bacillus Calmette-Guerin (Subset B)
description: Analysis of granulocyte-macrophage colony-stimulating factor (CSF) or macrophage-CSF differentiated macrophages stimulated with bacillus Calmette-Guerin. The two macrophage types differ in their resistance to mycobacterial infection. Results identify host resistance or susceptibility genes.

title: M-CSF and GM-CSF differentiated macrophages response to bacillus Calmette-Guerin (Subset C)
description: Analysis of granulocyte-macrophage colony-stimulating factor (CSF) or macrophage-CSF differentiated macrophages stimulated with bacillus Calmette-Guerin. The two macrophage types differ in their resistance to mycobacterial infection. Results identify host resistance or susceptibility genes.

title: Runt-related transcription factor 2 null mutation effect on the embryonal bone (MG-U74A)
description: Analysis of embryonic day 14.5 humeri of runt-related transcription factor 2 (Runx2) deficient animals. Runx2 is an essential factor for skeletogenesis and heterozygous loss causes cleidocranial dysplasia. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying skeletogenesis.

title: Runt-related transcription factor 2 null mutation effect on the embryonal bone (MG-U74B)
description: Analysis of embryonic day 14.5 humeri of runt-related transcription factor 2 (Runx2) deficient animals. Runx2 is an essential factor for skeletogenesis and heterozygous loss causes cleidocranial dysplasia. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying skeletogenesis.

title: Runt-related transcription factor 2 null mutation effect on the embryonal bone (MG-U74C)
description: Analysis of embryonic day 14.5 humeri of runt-related transcription factor 2 (Runx2) deficient animals. Runx2 is an essential factor for skeletogenesis and heterozygous loss causes cleidocranial dysplasia. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying skeletogenesis.

title: Triple-fusion reporter gene effect on embryonic stem cells
description: Analysis of embryonic stem (ES) cells stably-transduced with a triple-fusion (TF) construct consisting of fluorescence, bioluminescence, and positron emission tomography reporter genes. Results provide insight into the feasibility of using the TF construct to track cells in vivo.

title: Lung response to cigarette smoke: dose response and time course (PIQOR)
description: Analysis of lungs of animals exposed to 300 or 600 ug total particulate matter (TPM)/l of cigarette smoke (CS) for up to 13 weeks and allowed to recover 2, 6, or 20 hours after the last exposure. Results provide insight into mechanisms involved in the onset and development of CS-related diseases.

title: BRCA1/CtIP/ZBRK1 repressor complex depletion effect on mammary epithelial cells
description: Analysis of MCF10A mammary epithelial cells (MECs) in 3D culture following depletion of the BRCA1/CtIP/ZBRK1 repressor complex using BRCA1 or CtIP RNAi. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying the accelerated mammary tumor growth correlated with impaired BRCA1 function.

title: Bipolar disorder: dorsolateral prefrontal cortex
description: Analysis of postmortem dorsolateral prefrontal cortex from 30 adults with bipolar disorder. Results provide insight into the pathophysiology of the disease.

title: Bipolar disorder: orbitofrontal cortex
description: Analysis of postmortem orbitofrontal cortex from 10 adults with bipolar disorder. Results provide insight into the pathophysiology of the disease.

title: Titin mutation effect on embryonic muscles
description: Analysis of trunk and tail muscles of runzel (ruz) mutant embryos at 3.5 days post fertilization (dpf). Ruz mutants carry a mutation in the titin gene resulting in muscle degeneration and embryonic lethality. Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of titin muscular dystrophy.

title: Sry-related high mobility group box 4 knockdown effect on adenoid cystic carcinoma cells
description: Analysis of adenoid cystic carcinoma (ACC) derived cells (ACC3) following RNAi knockdown of Sry-related high mobility group box 4 (Sox4). Sox4 is one of the most upregulated genes in ACC. Results provide insight into the role of Sox4 in the pathogenesis of ACC.

title: Lung response to cigarette smoke: dose response (RAE230A)
description: Analysis of lungs of animals exposed to 300 or 600 ug total particulate matter (TPM)/l of cigarette smoke (CS) for 13 weeks and allowed to recover 2, 6, or 20 hours after the last exposure. Results provide insight into mechanisms involved in the onset and development of CS-related diseases.

title: Lung response to cigarette smoke: dose response (RAE230B)
description: Analysis of lungs of animals exposed to 300 or 600 ug total particulate matter (TPM)/l of cigarette smoke (CS) for 13 weeks and allowed to recover 2, 6, or 20 hours after the last exposure. Results provide insight into mechanisms involved in the onset and development of CS-related diseases.

title: Saponin treatment effect: time course
description: Analysis of yeast cells for up to 3 days after treatment with the saponins alpha-tomatine or tomatidine or the sterol biosynthesis inhibitor fenpropimorph. Saponins are glycoside compounds accumulated by many plant species, and possess antimicrobial activity and various pharmacological properties.

title: Trans-10, cis-12 conjugated linoleic acid delipidiative effect on white adipose tissues: time course
description: Analysis of retroperitoneal white adipose tissue (WAT) of C57BL/6J males fed a diet containing 0.5% trans-10 ,cis-12 conjugated linoleic acid (t10c12 CLA) for up to 17 days. Results provide insight into the mechanisms underlying the reduction in fat content of mice WAT in response to t10c12 CLA.

title: Non-melanoma skin cancer
description: Analysis of normal skin, actinic keratotic (AK) lesion, and squamous cell carcinoma (SCC) tumor biopsies from 5 patients with non-melanoma skin cancer (NMSC). Results provide insight into the molecular pathogenesis of NMSC.

title: Serrated and conventional adenocarcinomas
description: Comparison of serrated and conventional colorectal adenocarcinoma tumor samples. Results differentiate serrated from conventional colorectal carcinomas (CRC) and provide insight into the molecular pathogenesis of serrated CRC.

title: Epididymis development
description: Analysis of the epidididymis of animals at various ages from gestational day 12 to post-natal day 2. Results provide insight into the molecular events involved in testicular development.

title: Ovary development
description: Analysis of the ovary of animals at various ages from gestational day 12 to post-natal day 2. Results provide insight into the molecular events involved in ovary development.

title: Universal reference RNA in various amounts
description: Analysis of 1, 2, 5 or 10 ug of Stratagene universal human reference RNA as starting material. Results provide insight into the influence of starting RNA quantity on the subsequent gene expression signal measured from a microarray.

title: Dilated cardiomyopathy: left ventricle
description: Comparison of subendocardial left ventricular tissue samples from 7 patients with dilated cardiomyopathy (DCM) to those from 5 patients with non-failing (NF) hearts. DCM is a common cause of heart failure. Results contribute to the identification of a gene expression signature for DCM.

title: Dilated cardiomyopathy: septum
description: Comparison of septal myocardial tissue samples from 13 patients with dilated cardiomyopathy (DCM) to those from 15 patients with non-failing (NF) hearts. DCM is a common cause of heart failure. Results contribute to the identification of a gene expression signature for DCM.

title: Salicylic acid effect on leaves
description: Analysis of leaves 2 hours after treatment with salicylic acid (SA) which induces systemic acquired resistance (SAR). SA-induced genes examined for the presence of neighboring putative binding sites for the transcription factor TGA2. Results provide insight into role of TGA factors in triggering SAR

title: Estradiol effect on the uterus: time course
description: Expression profiling of uteri from ovariectomized C57BL/6 animals at various time points up to 24 hours following treatment with estradiol (E2). E2 plays a critical role in regulating the growth, differentiation, and secretory function of the uterus.

title: Spinal cord and dorsal root ganglion
description: Analysis of spinal cord (SC) and dorsal root ganglion (DRG). The central nervous system (CNS) comprises the brain and SC; the peripheral nervous system (PNS) includes spinal and cranial nerves along with their associated DRGs. Results identify gene expression differences between the CNS and the PNS.

title: Flagellin effect on toll-like receptor 5 deficient intestinal epithelial cells
description: Analysis of intestinal epithelial cells (IECs) from toll-like receptor 5 (TLR5) null animals stimulated with flagellin. TLR5 mediates the immune response to flagellin. Results provide insight into the role of IECs in the innate immune response mediated by TLR5.

title: Flagellin effect on toll-like receptor 5 deficient intestinal lamina propria cells
