title: Glucocorticoid sensitive and resistant acute lymphoblastic leukemia samples
description: Analysis of pretreatment acute lymphoblastic leukemia samples that are either sensitive or resistant to glucocorticoid (GC)-induced apoptosis in vitro. Results used to search a database of expression profiles of pharmacologic treatment of cells for small molecules that reverse the resistance to GCs.

title: Rapamycin effect on a glucorticoid-resistant T cell lymphoblastic leukemia cell line: time course
description: Analysis of the glucocorticoid (GC) resistant T cell lymphoblastic leukemia cell line CEM-c1 following treatment with rapamycin for 3 or 24 hours. Results compared to a GC sensitivity expression signature. Results provide insight into the feasibility of using rapamycin to reverse GC resistance.

title: Airway epithelium response to injury: time course
description: Analysis of airway epithelia from healthy individuals 7 and 14 days following injury by epithelial denudation. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying airway epithelial repair.

title: Lung response to carcinogens that test positive in two-year rodent bioassays
description: Analysis of lungs of B6C3F1 females 13 weeks following treatment with chemicals that test positive in two-year rodent cancer bioassays. Results provide insight into the feasibility of using expression signatures, as alternatives to standard two-year bioassays, to identify chemical carcinogens.

title: Liver response to carcinogens that test positive in two-year rodent bioassays
description: Analysis of livers of B6C3F1 females 13 weeks following treatment with chemicals that test positive in two-year rodent cancer bioassays. Results provide insight into the feasibility of using expression signatures, as alternatives to standard two-year bioassays, to identify chemical carcinogens.

title: TATA-binding protein Spt15 mutant response to ethanol and glucose stress
description: Analysis of spt15-300 mutant grown in conditions of ethanol and glucose stress. Mutant generated by global transcription machinery engineering (gTME) and bears 3 mutations in SPT15. Results provide insight into the applicability of gTME to alter cellular eukaryotic phenotypes.

title: Anti-cancer agent sapphyrin PCI-2050 effect on lung cancer cell line: dose response
description: Analysis of A549 lung cancer cells following treatment with anti-cancer agent sapphyrin PCI-2050 or transcription inhibitor actinomycin D. Hydrophilic sapphyrins localize to tumors, generate oxidative stress, and inhibit gene expression.

title: B-cell chronic lymphocytic leukemia cell type and prognosis
description: Analysis of B-cell chronic lymphocytic leukemia (B-CLL) cells that express or do not express zeta-associated protein (ZAP-70) and CD38. The prognosis of patients with ZAP-70-CD38- B-CLL cells is good, those with ZAP-70+CD38+ B-CLL cells is poor.

title: Pseudomonas aeruginosa response to airway epithelia
description: Analysis of Pseudomonas aeruginosa PAO1 or Type III secretion system (TTSS), rhamnolipid synthesis double mutant strain exposed to cultured airway epithelia. TTSS is a virulence factor in acute infections. Strains from chronic infections express decreased levels of TTSS or lack a functional TTSS.

title: Female reproductive tract response to male-derived molecules and sperm: time course
description: Analysis of the reproductive tracts of females up to 24 hours after mating. Male-derived accessory gland proteins transferred to females during mating affect reproductive physiology. Results provide insight into the response of female reproductive tissues to male-derived molecules and sperm.

title: DNA damage effect
description: Analysis of cells exposed to the radiomimetic enediyne antibiotics calicheamicin, esperamicin A1, and neocarzinostatin. These enediynes bind specifically to DNA and generate single- and double-strand DNA breaks. Results provide insight into the response to DNA damage.

title: Wilson’s disease model: liver
description: Analysis of livers of copper-transporting ATPase ATP7B null animals. Genetic inactivation of ATP7B causes Wilson’s Disease (WD), a severe metabolic disorder associated with intracellular copper overload. Results provide insight into the initial events of copper-dependent liver pathology in WD.

title: Brains of two strains (MG-U74A)
description: Comparison of whole brains from C57BL/6 and DBA/2 strains. These two strains differ in their preference for alcohol. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of this difference.

title: Nicotinamide effect on thrombopoietin-induced megakaryocyte differentiation in vitro
description: Analysis of thrombopoietin-cultured CD34+ cells at various time points up to 5 days following treatment with nicotinamide. Thrombopoietin induces CD34+ cells to differentiate into megakaryocytes. Results provide insight into the effect of nicotinamide on megakaryocyte differentiation.

title: Breast cancer formation in WAP-SVT/t transgenic animals
description: Analysis of mammary gland segments from WAP–SVT/t transgenic animals. These animals selectively synthesize the SV40 T/t antigen in mammary gland epithelial (ME) cells and develop breast cancer after the first lactation. Results provide insight into the role of SV40 T/t antigen in tumor formation.

title: Transcriptional coactivator PGC-1beta hypomorphic mutation effect on the skeletal muscle
description: Analysis of quadriceps muscles of animals bearing a hypomorphic PGC-1beta mutation. PGC-1beta is a transcriptional coactivator that stimulates mitochondrial biogenesis and respiration of cells. Results provide insight into the function of PGC-1beta in the skeletal muscle.

title: Interferons effect on endothelial cells
description: Analysis of endothelial cells treated with interferon (IFN) alpha, beta, or gamma for 5 hours.  The effect of IFNs on fibroblasts was also examined.  Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the antiangiogenic activity exhibited by IFNs.

title: Hyperhomocysteinemia model: heart
description: Analysis of hearts of animals given drinking water containing 10 g/L of L-methionine to induce chronic hyperhomocysteinemia (HHcy). HHcy is characterized by an elevation in plasma homocysteine, and is a risk factor for atherosclerosis. Results provide insight into the impact of HHcy on the heart.

title: Psoriatic plaques
description: Analysis of uninvolved and lesional skin of 13 patients with plaque-type psoriasis. Psoriasis vulgaris is characterized by hyperproliferation and incomplete terminal differentiation of epidermal keratinocytes. Results provide insight into the molecular pathogenesis of psoriasis.

title: Early-stage Parkinson’s disease: whole blood
description: Analysis of blood of 50 patients predominantly with early-stage Parkinson’s disease (PD). Results provide insight into the molecular processes perturbed in the cellular blood of patients with early-stage PD.

title: Head and neck squamous cell carcinoma
description: Analysis of paired normal tissues and tumor samples from patients with head and neck squamous cell carcinoma (HNSCC).  Results used to assess the effectiveness of using a combinatorial approach to analyze microarray data in identifying differentially expressed genes.

title: Megakaryocytes at successive stages of maturation
description: Analysis of primary megakaryocytes (MK) purified after 3 to 6 days in culture. MKs undergo sequential morphologic and functional transitions that culminate in platelet assembly in proplatelets.  Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying MK differentiation and platelet formation.

title: Pyocyanin treatment: dose response
description: Analysis of cells treated with 25 or 250 ug/ml of the blue metabolite pyocyanin for 6 hours. Pyocyanin, produced by Pseudomonas aeruginosa, kills cells by generating reactive oxygen species. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying the stress response to pyocyanin.

title: Leaf Response to Aphid Feeding
description: Analysis of rosette leaves subjected to aphid infestation.  To date, little is known about how plants perceive and defend themselves from phloem-feeding aphids. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of phloem-feeding insect-plant interactions and the development of control strategies.

title: Effect of gonadal steroids on sex differences in response to blood-stage malaria infection: time course
description: Analysis of white blood cells (WBCs) isolated from spleens of intact and gonadectomized (gdx) males and females up to 14 days after inoculation with Plasmodium chabaudi. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms mediating the sexual dimorphism in resistance to blood-stage malaria infection.

title: Foxp3 ablation effect on mature regulatory T cells
description: Analysis of mature regulatory T cells (Treg) ablated for the transcription factor Foxp3. Foxp3 is required for the development of Treg cells. Results provide insight into the role of Foxp3 in maintaining the transcriptional and functional program established during Treg cell development.

title: c-MYC depletion effect on carcinoma cell lines
description: Analysis of breast and cervix carcinoma cell lines depleted for c-MYC by siRNA knockdown. Abnormal activation of c-MYC contributes to breast and cervix carcinogenesis. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the developmental and oncogenic roles of MYC proteins.

title: Basal plate of the placenta from midgestation to term (HG-U133A)
description: Analysis of the basal plate of the placenta from midgestation to term. The basal plate is the region where maternal and fetal cells coexist. Its proper formation is required for pregnancy. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the unique cell-cell interactions in the basal plate.

title: Basal plate of the placenta from midgestation to term (HG-U133B)
description: Analysis of the basal plate of the placenta from midgestation to term. The basal plate is the region where maternal and fetal cells coexist. Its proper formation is required for pregnancy. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the unique cell-cell interactions in the basal plate.

title: Retinoblastomas with loss of heterozygosity at chromosome 16q
description: Analysis of 4 retinoblastomas with loss of heterozygosity (LOH) at chromosome 16q. In addition to RB1 gene mutations, retinoblastomas frequently show gains of 1q and 6p and losses of 16q. Results identify candidate tumor suppressors on 16q in retinoblastoma.

title: Antipsychotic agents clozapine and haloperidol effects on the brain (II)
description: Analysis of brains of animals treated for 12 weeks with the atypical antipsychotic clozapine or the typical antipsychotic haloperidol. Clozapine's use as an antipsychotic is limited by agranulocytosis. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of clozapine's therapeutic and toxic effects.

title: Model of decidualization and menstruation
description: Analysis of uterine tissues of decidualized animals for up to 84 hours after the withdrawal of progesterone to induce a process similar to menstruation. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying the remodeling and breakdown of the endometrium during the menstrual cycle.

title: Rap1 DNA-binding mutant
description: Analysis of temperature sensitive Rap1 mutant cells subjected to a temperature of 37 degrees C to dissociate the mutant protein from its DNA binding sites. Results provide insight into the contribution of this general regulatory factor to transcription genome-wide.

title: p63 depletion effect
description: Analysis of ME180 cervical carcinoma cells depleted for p63 isoforms by expression of a small hairpin RNA targeting the p63 oligomerization domain. p63 is a p53 homolog essential for stratified epithelial development. Results provide insight into the function of p63 in transcriptional regulation.

title: Vanadium pentoxide effect on lung fibroblasts: time course
description: Analysis of lung fibroblasts for up to 24 hours following exposure to vanadium pentoxide (V2O5). Exposure to V2O5 is a cause of occupational bronchitis. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms that contribute to airway remodeling associated with V2O5-induced bronchitis.

title: Nickel effect on endothelial cells
description: Analysis of human umbilical vein endothelial cells treated with nickel chloride. Nickel compounds, important carcinogens and inducers of contact allergy reactions, are activators of endothelial cells. Results provide insight into the signaling pathways mediating the cellular responses to nickel.

title: Antipsychotic agents clozapine and haloperidol effects on the brain (I)
description: Analysis of brains of animals treated for 4 weeks with the atypical antipsychotic clozapine or the typical antipsychotic haloperidol. Clozapine's use as an antipsychotic is limited by agranulocytosis. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of clozapine's therapeutic and toxic effects.

title: Activity-dependent neuroprotective protein null mutation effect on embryos
description: Analysis of E9 mutant embryos lacking the gene for the activity-dependent neuroprotective protein (ADNP). ADNP deficiency results in neural tube closure defects and death at E8.5 to E9.5. Results provide insight into the role of ADNP in embryogenesis at the molecular level.

title: Heart failure in obesity model
description: Analysis of left heart ventricles of 4 and 10-month old SHHF obese animals homozygous for leptin receptor (ObR) mutation. This mutant is obese at 4 months of age and prone to heart failure after 14 months. Results provide insight into molecular basis of the contribution of obesity to heart failure.

title: Metastatic prostate cancer (HG-U95A)
description: Analysis of metastatic prostate tumors and primary prostate tumors.  Normal tissue adjacent to the tumor and normal donor tissue also examined. Metastasis reflects the most adverse clinical outcome. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying the metastatic process.

title: Metastatic prostate cancer (HG-U95B)
description: Analysis of metastatic prostate tumors and primary prostate tumors.  Normal tissue adjacent to the tumor and normal donor tissue also examined. Metastasis reflects the most adverse clinical outcome. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying the metastatic process.

title: Metastatic prostate cancer (HG-U95C)
description: Analysis of metastatic prostate tumors and primary prostate tumors.  Normal tissue adjacent to the tumor and normal donor tissue also examined. Metastasis reflects the most adverse clinical outcome. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying the metastatic process.

title: Preeclampsia: uteroplacental tissues
description: Analysis of the deciduas, placentas, and fat tissues of preeclamptic women. The decidua and the placenta are two tissues of the uteroplacental unit. Results provide insight into the role of the uteroplacental renin-angiotensin system in the pathogenesis of preeclampsia.

title: Transcription factor DAF-19 deficient mutants
description: Analysis of mutants lacking DAF-19, a transcription factor that regulates genes involved in cilia function. Cilia defects are associated with a variety of human disorders, such as cystic kidney disease. Results provide insight into the mechanisms that regulate the formation and function of cilia.

title: Recycling factor p110 mutation effect on embryonic development
description: Analysis of 3 and 5-day egy mutant embryos, which contain a mutation in recycling factor p110. This mutation leads to microcephaly and thymus hypoplasia. U4/U6 snRNPs are disrupted in egy mutants. Results provide insight into the mechanisms underlying these developmental defects.

title: Small intestine response to Aeromonas caviae infection
description: Analysis of neonatal small intestines infected with Aeromonas caviae. A. caviae is associated with human gastrointestinal disease. Strains typically lack virulence factors. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of A. caviae's enteropathogenicity.

title: RNA-binding protein LARK overexpression effect on heads
description: Analysis of heads of animals overexpressing the RNA-binding protein LARK. Results provide insight into the identity of transcripts regulated by LARK in the neurons of the central nervous system.

title: Diffuse large B cell lymphoma model
description: Analysis of lymphomas of transgenics engineered to constitutively express the dual bromodomain protein Brd2, which causes a malignancy similar to diffuse large B cell lymphoma (DLCL). Results provide insight into the similarity of DLCL lymphomas to activated B cells at the molecular level.

title: Neurotoxin trimethyltin effect on neuronal cell line: dose response
description: Analysis neuronal PC12 cells treated with 1 or 5 uM trimethyltin (TMT). TMT induces neurodegeneration in the hippocampus and limbic system with a delayed onset. Results provide insight into the molecular and cellular mechanisms leading to TMT toxicity.

title: Embryonic retinal pigment epithelium
description: Analysis of microdissected embryonic retinas with or without the retinal pigment epithelium (RPE). The RPE is a thin layer of cells that underlies the neural retina and supports the function and development of photoreceptors. Results provide insight into the development of the RPE.

title: Octreotide effect on the oxyntic mucosa
description: Analysis of the oxyntic mucosa (OM) of animals treated with the long-acting release (LAR) formulation of octreotide (OCT), a somastostatin analog. OCT-LAR causes the regression of gastric ECL-cell carcinoids. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the antiproliferative effect of OCT.

title: Histone deacetylase inhibition effect on seeds (I)
description: Analysis of seeds imbibed for 3 days in the presence of trichostatin A, a specific inhibitor of histone deacetylase. Results provide insight into the role of histone acetylation in the regulation of gene expression during seed germination.

title: Cdk7 complex subunit menage-a-trois 1 deficiency effect on hearts
description: Analysis of 2 and 4 week old hearts ablated for menage-a-trois 1 (MAT1), a subunit of the cdk7/cyclin H/MAT1 heterotrimer. Results provide insight into the role of the cdk7/cyclin H/MAT1 complex in cardiac metabolism.

title: Prostate response to castration and subsequent hormone replacement
description: Analysis of prostate of animals following castration and subsequent hormone replacement with testosterone. Castration induces prostate involution, while hormone replacement induces regeneration. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms regulating prostatic involution and regeneration.

title: Cigarette smoking effect on T lymphocytes
description: Analysis of T lymphocytes of 3 male heavy smokers. Results provide insight into sensitivity of T lymphocytes to cigarette smoking.

title: Heat-inducible transcription factor HsfA2 null mutant response to heat shock
description: Analysis of HsfA2 null mutant following acclimative heat treatment at 37 degrees C for 1 hour, recovery at 24 degrees C for 2 days, and heat shock at 44 degrees C for 45 minutes. Results provide insight into role of HsfA2 in acquired thermotolerance induced by non-lethal heat treatment.

title: Endothelial cell response to ultrafine particles
description: Analysis of pulmonary artery endothelial cells HPAEC exposed to ultrafine particles for 4 hours. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the association of pollutant particle exposure to increased cardiovascular mortality and morbidity.

title: Bis(2-chloroethoxy)methane effect on hearts: time course
description: Analysis of hearts exposed to the heart toxin bis(2-chloroethoxy)methane (CEM) for 2 or 5 days. Toxicity occurs at day 2 of CEM dosing, and recovery at day 5 despite continued dosing. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of heart toxicity and recovery during the exposure to CEM.

title: Banded hedgehog effect on the pronephric nephron development
description: Analysis of pronephric explants dissected from embryos previously injected with banded hedgehog mRNA. Hedgehog suppresses the development of the pronephric kidney tubule but not that of the pronephric glomus. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of this inhibitory effect.

title: RNA polymerase II mutants (I)
description: Analysis of RNA polymerase II (RNAPII) RPB1 mutants that are sensitive to the nucleotide-depleting drug 6-azauracil (6AU). Results provide further insight into the mechanisms of RNAPII transcription.

title: RNA polymerase II mutants (II)
description: Analysis of RNA polymerase II (RNAPII) RPB1 mutants that are sensitive to the nucleotide-depleting drug 6-azauracil (6AU). Results provide further insight into the mechanisms of RNAPII transcription.

title: Bone morphogenic protein 6 effect on an endothelial cell line: time course
description: Analysis of endothelial cells treated for up to 24 hours with bone morphogenic protein 6 (BMP6). BMP proteins participate in the regulation of angiogenesis in physiological and pathological conditions. Results provide insight into the mechanisms that contribute to BMP-dependent angiogenic signaling.

title: Tocopherol deficient mutant seedlings
description: Analysis of 1 and 3 day old seedlings disrupted for tocopherol cyclase (vte1) or homogentisate phytyl transferase (vte2). Both mutants lack tocopherols, but vte1 mutants accumulate the tocopherol pathway intermediate DMPBQ. Results provide insight into seedling response to tocopherol deficiency.

title: Far-upstream element binding protein inactivation
description: Analysis of primary skin fibroblasts (Hs68) following siRNA knockdown of far-upstream element binding protein (FBP) 1, 2, or 3. Results provide insight into the function of each member of the FBP transactivator family.

title: Homeobox protein Hoxb1a deficiency effect on the embryonic hindbrain
description: Analysis of hindbrain rhombomere 4 tissues of embryos deficient for the homeobox protein Hoxb1a. Hoxb1a confers regional identity to rhombomere 4 in hindbrain development. Results provide insight into the mechanisms controlling the development of regional identity in the hindbrain.

title: Microgravity effect on osteoblasts
description: Analysis of 2T3 osteoblasts following 3 days of simulated microgravity using the rotating wall vessel (RWV). Weightlessness or microgravity of spaceflight induces bone loss due in part to decreased bone formation. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms regulating bone formation.

title: Regenerating liver and developing embryonic liver comparison
description: Comparison of regenerating liver to developing embryonic liver. Regenerating liver examined at time points up to 72 hours after partial hepatectomy. Developing liver examined up to 16.5 days post conception (dpc). Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms regulating renewal and repair.

title: Calcium chloride and glycerol wash effect: time course
description: Analysis of MG1655 cells after washing with 0.1 M calcium chloride and 15% glycerol and subsequent incubation on ice. Cells on ice examined at various time points up to 60 minutes. This is part of a study tracking transcriptional responses to over 30 chemical and physiological perturbations.

title: Ampicillin treatment: time course
description: Analysis of MG1655 cells at various time points up to 75 minutes following treatment with 100 ug/ml ampicillin.  Ampicillin added to cells grown in M9 media supplemented with glucose. This is part of a study tracking transcriptional responses to over 30 chemical and physiological perturbations.

title: Recovery from stationary phase: time course (I)
description: Analysis of MG1655 cells transferred from stationary phase LB culture into fresh LB media with 0.2% glucose to OD of 0.4. Recovering cells examined at various time points up to 90 minutes. This is part of a study tracking transcriptional responses to over 30 chemical and physiological perturbations.

title: Indole acrylate treatment: time course (I)
description: Analysis of MG1655 cells at various time points up to 60 minutes following treatment with 10 ug/ml indole acrylate. Indole acrylate added to cells growing in Bonner-Vogel media. This is part of a study tracking transcriptional responses to over 30 chemical and physiological perturbations.

title: Indole acrylate treatment: time course (II)
description: Analysis of MG1655 cells at various time points up to 60 minutes following treatment with 15 ug/ml indole acrylate. Indole acrylate added to cells growing in Bonner-Vogel media. This is part of a study tracking transcriptional responses to over 30 chemical and physiological perturbations.

title: Kanamycin treatment: time course
description: Analysis of MG1655 cells at various time points up to 75 minutes following treatment with 100 ug/ml kanamycin. Kanamycin added to cells grown in M9 media supplemented with glucose. This is part of a study tracking transcriptional responses to over 30 chemical and physiological perturbations.

title: Recovery from stationary phase: time course (II)
description: Analysis of MG1655 cells transferred from stationary phase LB culture into fresh LB media with 0.2% glucose. Recovering cells examined at various time points up to 1440 minutes. This is part of a study tracking transcriptional responses to over 30 chemical and physiological perturbations.

title: Recovery from stationary phase: time course (III)
description: Analysis of MG1655 cells transferred from stationary phase LB culture into fresh LB media with 0.2% glucose to OD of 1.0. Recovering cells examined at various time points up to 90 minutes. This is part of a study tracking transcriptional responses to over 30 chemical and physiological perturbations.

title: Recovery from stationary phase: time course (IV)
description: Analysis of MG1655 cells transferred from stationary phase culture into media with 10 mM sodium phosphate. Recovering cells examined at various time points up to 90 minutes. This is part of a study tracking transcriptional responses to over 30 chemical and physiological perturbations.

title: Recovery from stationary phase: time course (V)
description: Analysis of MG1655 cells at various time points up to 90 minutes following transfer from stationary phase culture into media with 10 mM sodium phosphate and 0.2% glucose to OD of 0.4. This is part of a study tracking transcriptional responses to over 30 chemical and physiological perturbations.

title: Anaerobic growth (I)
description: Analysis of MG1655 cells at various phases of growth up to stationary phase. Cells were grown anaerobically in M9 media with glucose. This is part of a study tracking transcriptional responses to over 30 chemical and physiological perturbations.

title: Anaerobic growth (II)
description: Analysis of MG1655 cells at various phases of growth up to stationary phase. Cells were grown anaerobically in M9 media containing glucose and fumarate. This is part of a study tracking transcriptional responses to over 30 chemical and physiological perturbations.

title: Anaerobic growth (III)
description: Analysis of MG1655 cells grown up to an OD of 1.27. Cells were grown anaerobically in M9 media containing glucose. This is part of a study tracking transcriptional responses to over 30 chemical and physiological perturbations.

title: Anaerobic growth (IV)
description: Analysis of MG1655 cells grown up to an OD of 1.29. Cells were grown anaerobically in M9 media containing glucose and fumarate. This is part of a study tracking transcriptional responses to over 30 chemical and physiological perturbations.

title: NOX overexpressing cells at various growth rates
description: Analysis of NOX overexpressing MG1655 cells at various growth rates during balanced growth in chemostat cultures. Cells with NOX recycle the excess NADH generated during rapid growth. OD600 of 0.13 to 0.4 examined. Part of a study tracking responses to chemical and physiological perturbations.

title: Wild type cells at various growth rates
description: Analysis of cells at various growth rates during balanced growth in chemostat. Results compared to those from cells overexpressing NOX. NOX allows cells to recycle the excess NADH during rapid growth. OD600 of 0.19 to 0.6 examined. Part of a study tracking responses to various perturbations.

title: Norfloxacin treatment: time course
description: Analysis of C600 cells at various time points up to 30 minutes following treatment with 50 ug/ml norfloxacin.  Norfloxacin added to cells grown in LB. This is part of a study tracking transcriptional responses to over 30 chemical and physiological perturbations.

title: gyrA parC double mutant response to norfloxacin treatment: time course (I)
description: Analysis of C600 gyrA parC double mutants at various time points up to 30 minutes following treatment with 15 ug/ml norfloxacin. gyrA parC double mutants are resistant to norfloxacin. This is part of a study tracking transcriptional responses to over 30 chemical and physiological perturbations.

title: gyrA parC double mutant response to norfloxacin treatment: time course (II)
description: Analysis of C600 gyrA parC double mutants at various time points up to 30 minutes following treatment with 50 ug/ml norfloxacin. gyrA parC double mutants are resistant to norfloxacin. This is part of a study tracking transcriptional responses to over 30 chemical and physiological perturbations.

title: Sodium azide treatment: time course
description: Analysis of W3110 cells in Bonner-Vogel medium supplemented with 50 ug/ml tryptophan at various time points up to 60 minutes following treatment with 0.01 M sodium azide. This is part of a study tracking transcriptional responses to over 30 chemical and physiological perturbations.

title: Gamma radiation treatment: time course
description: Analysis of MG1655 cells  in Davis medium at various time points up to 60 minutes following treatment with gamma radiation. This is part of a study tracking transcriptional responses to over 30 chemical and physiological perturbations.

title: Novobiocin treatment: dose response
description: Analysis of LE234 acrD- cells treated with novobiocin at various concentrations up to 200 ug/ml for 5 minutes. This is part of a study tracking transcriptional responses to over 30 chemical and physiological perturbations.

title: Stationary phase: time course
description: Analysis of stationary phase MG1655 cells at OD600 of 2.4, 2.8, and 3.1.  Cells at OD 3.1 in LB media examined at various time points up to 60 minutes. This is part of a study tracking transcriptional responses to over 30 chemical and physiological perturbations.

title: Alzheimer blood mononuclear cells
description: Analysis of blood mononuclear cells of sporadic Alzheimer disease (AD) and age- gender-matched normal controls. Results reveal insights into systemic nature of gene dys-regulation in sporadic AD and suggest novel pathways of beta-amyloid deposition.

title: COX-1 or COX-2 knockout effect in brain
description: Analysis of cortex and hippocampus in cyclooxygenase (COX)-1 and COX-2 knockouts. COX-1 and COX-2 produce prostanoids from arachidonic acid. Results indicate COX-1 and COX-2 differentially modulate brain gene expression, and give insight into therapeutic and toxicologic effects of COX inhibition.

title: Arsenite and p53 effect on G2 synchronized fibroblasts
description: Analysis of p53-expressing or p53-deficient fibroblasts exposed to arsenite (As) after release from G2 phase synchrony. p53 is activated in response to mitotic disruption by arsenic. Results provide insight into the role of p53 in the As-induced disruption of G2/M phase progression.

title: Asbestos effect on epithelial and mesothelial lung cell lines: time course
description: Analysis of epithelial and mesothelial lung cell lines at various time points up to 7 days after exposure to asbestos. Asbestos exposure causes lung diseases such as asbestosis, malignant mesothelioma, and lung cancer. Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of asbestos-associated diseases.

title: Niacin-bound chromium effect on the subcutaneous fat tissue of a model for type 2 diabetes with obesity
description: Analysis of subcutaneous fat tissues of type 2 Lepr(db/db) animals supplemented with niacin-bound chromium (NBC) for 10 weeks. The Lepr(db/db) animal is a model for type 2 diabetes with obesity. Results provide insight into the basis of the beneficial effect of NBC on diabetes and obesity.

title: Bronchial epithelial cell line response to various airway pathogens
description: Analysis of bronchial epithelial BEAS-2B cells exposed to UV-inactivated Staphylococcus aureus, Pseudomonas aeruginosa, or respiratory syncytial virus. Results provide insight into the common and specific molecular responses of bronchial epithelial cells to various airway pathogens.

title: Polyunsaturated fatty acids effect on cardiomyocytes
description: Analysis of primary cardiomyocyte cultures treated with eicosapentaenoic acid (EPA) or docosahexaenoic acid (DHA). EPA and DHA are n-3 polyunsaturated fatty acids (PUFAs). Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the cardioprotective effect of n-3 PUFAs.

title: Antipsychotic agent olanzapine effect on the brain frontal cortex
description: Analysis of brain frontal cortices of albino Sprague-Dawley males treated with olanzapine for 21 days. Olanzapine is a second generation antipsychotic agent. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the clinical response to olanzapine.

title: Early onset colorectal cancer: normal-appearing colonic mucosa
description: Analysis of normal-appearing colonic mucosa of early onset colorectal cancer (CRC) patients without a prior family history of CRC. Results provide insight into the molecular pathogenesis of early onset CRC.

title: Glycerol kinase deficiency effect on brown adipose tissue
description: Analysis of brown adipose tissues from glycerol kinase (GK) knockout mutants. GK is at the interface of fat and carbohydrate metabolism and has been implicated in insulin resistance and type 2 diabetes mellitus. Results provide insight into the role of GK in insulin resistance.

title: Interleukin-20 subfamily cytokines effect on epidermal keratinocytes
description: Analysis of cultured epidermal keratinocytes treated with various cytokines of the interleukin-20 (IL-20) subfamily. IL-20 cytokines are up-regulated in psoriatic skin. Results provide insight into the role of IL-20 cytokines in the pathogenesis of psoriasis.

title: Caloric restriction effect on aged skeletal muscle
description: Analysis of aged skeletal muscles of C57BL/6NHsd animals fed a calorie-restricted diet. Caloric restriction extends the life of this strain by 40%. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of mammalian aging.

title: Rett syndrome: brain frontal cortex
description: Analysis of brain frontal cortices of individuals with Rett syndrome (RTT). RTT is an X-linked neurodevelopmental disorder linked to heterozygous de novo mutations in MECP2, a gene encoding methyl-CpG-binding protein 2. Results provide insight into molecular pathogenesis of RTT.

title: miRNA-1-2 knockout effect on the heart
description: Analysis of hearts from miRNA-1-2 knockout mutants at postnatal day 10. miRNA-1-2 is a microRNA specific for cardiac and skeletal muscle. Results provide insight into the role of miRNA-1-2 in cardiac development.

title: Mucociliary differentiation of airway epithelial cells
description: Analysis of primary airway epithelial cells cultured at an air-liquid interface for up to 28 days to induce their differentiation into polarized, pseudostratified epithelia of ciliated and mucus-secreting cells. Results provide insight into the mechanisms underlying mucociliary differentiation.

title: Mammary epithelial cell response to genistein and soy proteins
description: Analysis of mammary epithelial cells of females fed a diet containing the soy isoflavone genistein or soy protein isolate. Soy consumption is associated with reduced breast cancer risk in women. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the beneficial effect of soy-rich diets.

title: Tumorigenic breast cancer cells (HG-U133A)
description: Analysis of breast cancer cells that have high tumorigenic capacity.  These cells express CD44 and low or undetectable levels of CD24. Results used to define a gene expression signature associated with metastasis.

title: Tumorigenic breast cancer cells (HG-U133B)
description: Analysis of breast cancer cells that have high tumorigenic capacity.  These cells express CD44 and low or undetectable levels of CD24. Results used to define a gene expression signature associated with metastasis.

title: Chromosome 4-specific protein Painting of fourth D119 mutant
description: Analysis of first instar larvae containing a chromosome 4 specific protein POF D119 mutation. POF is an autosome-specific protein that regulates gene expression in chromosome 4 in its entirety. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms that regulate chromosome 4 specific gene expression.

title: Epidermal growth factor effect on mammary epithelial cell line: time course
description: Analysis of mammary epithelial MCF10A cells following treatment with epidermal growth factor for various time points up to 480 minutes. Results provide insight into the dynamics of growth factor signaling.

title: Epidermal growth factor effect on cervical carcinoma cell line: time course
description: Analysis of cervical carcinoma HeLa cells following treatment with epidermal growth factor for various time points up to 480 minutes. Results provide insight into the dynamics of growth factor signaling.

title: Histone deacetylase-2 deficiency effect on the embryonic heart
description: Analysis of heart ventricles from histone deacetylase-2 (Hdac2) deficient embryos at embryonic day E17.5. The role of the HDAC family in cardiac myocyte homeostasis is complex. Results provide insight into the role of class I HDAC gene Hdac2 in cardiac development.

title: mRNA decapping activator edc3 null mutant
description: Analysis of edc3 null mutant cells. EDC3 encodes an mRNA decapping activator. Results provide insight into the role of Edc3p in mRNA decay.

title: Epidermal growth factor and heregulin effect on breast cancer cell line: dose response and time course
description: Analysis of MCF-7 breast cancer cells treated with various doses of epidermal growth factor (EGF) or heregulin (HRG) for up to 90 minutes. EGF and HRG induce distinct kinase kinetics and phenotypes of MCF-7 cells. Results provide insight into the linkage between signaling dynamics and cell fate.

title: Chromosome 4-specific protein Painting of fourth D2 mutant
description: Analysis of first instar larvae containing a chromosome 4 specific protein POF null mutation. POF is an autosome-specific protein that regulates gene expression in chromosome 4 in its entirety. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms that regulate chromosome 4 specific gene expression.

title: Vitamin D effect on bronchial smooth muscle cells
description: Analysis of bronchial muscle cells treated with 1alpha,25-dihydroxy-vitamin D3, the ligand for the vitamin D receptor (VDR). Genetic variants in VDR are associated with asthma. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of this association.

title: Epithelial transcription factor Get-1 deficiency effect on embryonic skin
description: Analysis of skins of embryos lacking Grainyhead-like epithelial transactivator (Get-1). Results provide insight into the role of Get-1 in epidermal differentiation.

title: Proapoptotic BH3-only protein Nix deficiency effect on the spleen
description: Analysis of spleens of mutants lacking Nix, a proapoptotic BH3-only factor that is transcriptionally induced during erythropoiesis. Erythropoiesis requires a critical balance between proapoptotic and antipaoptotic pathways. Results provide insight into the role of Nix in erythropoiesis.

title: Anoxia effect on rice coleoptiles
description: Analysis of coleoptiles of rice grown under anaerobic conditions. Rice seeds are capable of germinating in the absence of oxygen. Under anoxia, rice coleoptiles reach lengths greater than that of aerobically grown rice. Results provide insight into the control of anaerobic carbohydrate metabolism.

title: Cytokinin effect on rice roots and leaves: time course
description: Analysis of rice roots and leaves 30 and 120 minutes after treatment with the cytokinin trans-zeatin (tZ). Cytokinins (CKs) are a class of plant hormones that regulate the growth and development of plants. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms regulated by CK in rice.

title: Cytokinin-inducible type-A response regulator OsRR6 overexpression effect on rice leaves
description: Analysis of transgenic rice leaves overexpressing OsRR6, a cytokinin (CK)-inducible type-A response regulator. Results provide insight into the role of OsRR6 in CK signaling and further the understanding of the function of CK in rice.

title: Invasive ductal and lobular breast carcinomas
description: Analysis of invasive ductal carcinoma (IDC) cells, invasive lobular carcinoma (ILC) cells, and their normal counterparts. Cells obtained from postmenopausal breast cancer patients.  Results provide insight into the molecular differences between IDC and ILC.

title: Retinoschisis model
description: Analysis of retinas from postnatal day 7 mutants lacking retinoschisin (RS1h), an animal model for retinoschisis (RS). RS is a recessive retinal dystrophy accompanied by macular disease often resulting in early-onset vision loss. Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of RS.

title: Keratinocyte cell line response to a (56)Fe ion beam
description: Analysis of keratinocytes exposed to a (56)Fe ion beam. The (56)Fe ion beam is used as a surrogate for high-energy, heavy ion space radiation. Results provide insight into the risk at the cellular level to irradiation during space travel.

title: Uterus response to 17beta-estradiol: time course
description: Analysis of uteri from overiectomized animals at various lengths of time up to 24 hours following treatment with 17beta-estradiol (E2). Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the uterotrophic effect induced by a physiological dose of E2.

title: Aging and cognitive impairment: hippocampus
description: Analysis of hippocampi from aged learning-impaired animals on the last day of training in the Morris water maze (MWZ) or 21 days post-training. The MWZ task is a dorsal hippocampal-dependent task. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of aging-related cognitive impairment.

title: Multiple myeloma model
description: Analysis of multiple myeloma (MM) tumors and splenic B cells from transgenics overexpressing XBP-1s. XBP-1s is a spliced isoform of XBP-1, a factor that governs unfolded protein/ER stress response and plasma-cell development. Results provide insight into the role of XBP-1 in MM pathogenesis.

title: IRAK-4 kinase deficient fibroblast response to IL-1: time course
description: Analysis of embryonic fibroblasts from IRAK-4 kinase deficient mutants following stimulation with IL-1beta for 1 or 4 hours. Results provide insight into the role of IRAK-4 in the inflammatory responses mediated by the IL-1 receptor and Toll-like receptor 7.

title: Crohn’s disease and ulcerative colitis
description: Analysis of colonoscopic biopsies from patients with Crohn’s disease (CD) or ulcerative colitis (UC). CD and UC are inflammatory bowel diseases with variable, overlapping clinical features and complex pathophysiologies. Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of CD and UC.

title: Waldenstrom's macroglobulinemia: B lymphocytes and plasma cells
description: Analysis of B lymphocytes (BL) and plasma cells (PC) from patients with Waldenstrom's macroglobulinemia (WM), a B-lymphoproliferative disorder (BLPD). Results provide insight into differences between PC and BL from WM and their cell counterpart in chronic lymphocytic leukemia and multiple myeloma.

title: Homocysteine effect on cardiac neural crest cells
description: Analysis of cultured cardiac neural crest cells treated with homocysteine (HC). Elevated maternal HC increases the risk for congenital defects that result from abnormal development of the neural crest and neural tube. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of HC-induced dysmorphogenesis.

title: Asthma model: lungs
description: Comparison of whole lungs of wild-type and recombinase activating gene (RAG) deficient animals sensitized and then challenged with the allergen ovalbumin. RAG deficient animals do not develop allergic asthma. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the allergic asthmatic response.

title: Palmitate effect on myoblast cell line
description: Analysis of myoblasts treated with the saturated fatty acid palmitate. Muscle expression of PPAR coactivator 1 (PGC-1) is reduced in models of obesity. Palmitate decreases the expression of PGC-1. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the link between overnutrition, obesity, and PGC-1.

title: HIV infection effect on CD4+ and CD8+ T cells
description: Analysis of CD4+ and CD8+ T cells from HIV patients at different clinical stages and rates of disease progression. Changes in T-cell function are a hallmark of HIV infection. Results provide insight into the pathogenic mechanisms in HIV infections that lead to these changes in T-cell function.

title: Signal transduction adaptor MyD88 deficient lung response to Chlamydia pneumoniae infection
description: Analysis of lungs from MyD88 null mutants following Chlamydia pneumoniae infection. Toll-like receptors and key adaptor protein MyD88 play a critical role in inducing immunity against this microorganism. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying this MyD88-mediated induction.

title: Macrophage cell line response to Chlamydia pneumoniae infection
description: Analysis of ANA-1 macrophage cells infected with Chlamydia pneumoniae, an intracellular bacterium that causes pneumonia. Results provide insight into the contribution of the macrophage cell type in host defense against C. pneumoniae.

title: Neonatal brain response to docosahexaenoic acid supplemented formulas
description: Analysis of precentral gyri from neonates fed for 12 weeks with either a formula containing both 0.33% docosahexaenoic acid (DHA) and 0.67% arachidonic acid (ARA) or one with 1.0% DHA and 0.67% ARA. DHA and AHA are the major long chain polyunsaturated fatty acids of the central nervous system.

title: Sequestosome 1 and dipeptidylpeptidase III overexpression effect on neuroblastoma cell line
description: Analysis of IMR-32 neuroblastoma cells overexpressing sequestosome 1 (SQSTM1) or dipeptidylpeptidase III (DPP3). SQSTM1 and DPP3 activate the antioxidant response element (ARE). Results provide insight into mechanisms regulating the activation of the ARE.

title: Neurological aging models: retinas and hippocampi
description: Analysis of retinas and hippocampi of SAMP8 and SAMP10 animals at 3 and 16 months of age.  SAMP8 and SAMP10 are inbred animal models of accelerated neurological senescence. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying neurological aging.

title: Fetal and adult reticulocytes (HG-U133A)
description: Analysis of circulating blood reticulocytes from umbilical cords and normal adults. Reticulocytes are immature red blood cells containing residual RNA. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of terminal erythroid differentiation.

title: Fetal and adult reticulocytes (HG-U133B)
description: Analysis of circulating blood reticulocytes from umbilical cords and normal adults. Reticulocytes are immature red blood cells containing residual RNA. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of terminal erythroid differentiation.

title: miR-124 overexpression: time course
description: Analysis of HepG2 cells overexpressing miR-124 for up to 120 hours. Results combined with a computational method for predicting miRNA targets to identify targets of miR-124.

title: Histone deacetylase Sirt1 overexpression effect on the heart
description: Analysis of transgenic hearts overexpressing Sirt1, a class III histone deacetylase. Sirt1 protects against apoptosis and mediates the survival of cardiac myocytes and neurons under stress in vitro. Results provide insight into the in vivo function of Sirt1 in the heart.

title: Adipogenesis in vitro (Mu11K-A)
description: Analysis of differentiating 3T3-L1 preadipocytes at various time points up to 28 days after induction of adipogenesis using a standard differentiation cocktail of methylisobutylxanthine, dexamethasone, and insulin (MDI). Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms regulating adipogenesis.

title: Adipogenesis in vitro (Mu11K-B)
description: Analysis of differentiating 3T3-L1 preadipocytes at various time points up to 28 days after induction of adipogenesis using a standard differentiation cocktail of methylisobutylxanthine, dexamethasone, and insulin (MDI). Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms regulating adipogenesis.

title: Various adult tissues (Mu11K-A)
description: Analysis of various adult tissues, including in white adipose tissue (WAT). The differential expression of genes in WAT was compared to gene expression in differentiating 3T3-L1 preadipocytes (GDS2659).

title: Various adult tissues (Mu11K-B)
description: Analysis of various adult tissues, including in white adipose tissue (WAT). The differential expression of genes in WAT was compared to gene expression in differentiating 3T3-L1 preadipocytes (GDS2660).

title: Mre11 deficient sporulating cells
description: Analysis of Mre11 deficient cells at meiotic prophase during sporulation. Mre11 is important in homologous recombination, repair of DNA double strand breaks, activation of damage-induced checkpoint, and telomere maintenance. Results provide insight into the role of Mre11 in spore development.

title: Peripheral nerve injury effect on dorsal root ganglion: time course
description: Analysis of lumbar dorsal root ganglia at various time points up to 50 days following peripheral nerve injury inflicted by either partial sciatic nerve ligation or chronic constriction. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying neuropathic pain.

title: p53 mutant embryo response to radiation
description: Analysis of p53 mutant embryos exposed to gamma radiation. Within 90 minutes of radiation exposure, apoptosis is observed in embryonic and post-embryonic tissues of wild type but not p53 mutants. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of this p53-dependent apoptogenic response.

title: Embryonic R1 stem cell differentiation in vitro (MG-430A)
description: Analysis of R1 embryonic stem cells differentiating into embryoid bodies in vitro. Cells examined at various time points up to 14 days after inducing differentiation. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms that drive embryonic stem cell differentiation.

title: Embryonic R1 stem cell differentiation in vitro (MG-430B)
description: Analysis of R1 embryonic stem cells differentiating into embryoid bodies in vitro. Cells examined at various time points up to 14 days after inducing differentiation. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms that drive embryonic stem cell differentiation.

title: Embryonic J1 stem cell differentiation in vitro (MG-430A)
description: Analysis of J1 embryonic stem cells differentiating into embryoid bodies in vitro. Cells examined at various time points up to 14 days after inducing differentiation. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms that drive embryonic stem cell differentiation.

title: Embryonic J1 stem cell differentiation in vitro (MG-430B)
description: Analysis of J1 embryonic stem cells differentiating into embryoid bodies in vitro. Cells examined at various time points up to 14 days after inducing differentiation. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms that drive embryonic stem cell differentiation.

title: Embryonic V6.5 stem cell differentiation in vitro (MG-430A)
description: Analysis of V6.5 embryonic stem cells differentiating into embryoid bodies in vitro. Cells examined at various time points up to 14 days after inducing differentiation. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms that drive embryonic stem cell differentiation.

title: Embryonic V6.5 stem cell differentiation in vitro (MG-430B)
description: Analysis of V6.5 embryonic stem cells differentiating into embryoid bodies in vitro. Cells examined at various time points up to 14 days after inducing differentiation. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms that drive embryonic stem cell differentiation.

title: Pupariation
description: Analysis of animals before and after pupariation. A pulse of steroid hormone 20-hydroxyecdysone (20E) at late 3rd instar triggers puparium formation; a second 20E pulse after pupariation marks the prepupal-to-pupal transition. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms of 20E signaling.

title: 20-hydroxyecdysone effect on cultured larval organs
description: Analysis of cultured larval organs treated with 20-hydroxyecdysone (20E) alone or in combination with cycloheximide to distinguish primary responses to 20E signal. Organs dissected from third instar larvae. Results provide insight into the molecular events triggered by 20E during insect development.

title: Ecdysone receptor knockdown effect on larval metamorphosis
description: Analysis of ecdysone receptor (EcR) depleted animals 4 hours before to 4 hours after the start of pupariation. EcR is part of receptor complex for 20-hydroxyecdysone (20E), a hormone that triggers developmental transitions in insects. Results provide insight into the mechanisms regulated by 20E.

title: CD38-positive and CD38-negative chronic lymphocytic leukemia cells
description: Analysis of paired CD38(+) and CD38(-) chronic lymphocytic leukemia (CLL) cells from six patients. CD38 expression is an important prognostic marker in CLL with high levels of CD38 antigen associated with shorter overall survival. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of this association.

title: Capreomycin effect on Mycobacterium tuberculosis
description: Analysis of Mycobacterium tuberculosis cultures after treatment with capreomycin. Capreomycin is a drug used to treat multi-drug resistant tuberculosis (TB), and possesses bactericidal activity against non-replicating TB bacilli. Results provide insight into the spectrum of action of capreomycin.

title: Brain regions of humans and chimpanzees
description: Comparison of various human and chimpanzee brain regions. Results provide insight into the genetic basis of human specializations in brain organization and cognition.

title: Formaldehyde effect on nasal epithelium: dose response and time course
description: Analysis of nasal epithelia exposed to various doses of the carcinogenic pollutant formaldehyde for up to 19 days. Results used as a case study to validate a method that integrates benchmark dose calculations with gene ontology analysis to examine genomic dose-response data.

title: Caloric restriction effect on aged cochlea
description: Analysis of cochleas of 15 month old C57BL/6 (B6) animals on a calorie restricted diet. The B6 strain is a model of age-related hearing loss or presbycusis. Caloric restriction (CR) prevents late-onset presbycusis in B6. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of this effect of CR.

title: Conjunctiva and cornea comparison
description: Analysis of conjunctival (Cnj) and corneal (Co) epithelia, the main cellular components of the ocular surface. Cnj and Co epithelia are embryologically related but phenotypically and functionally disparate. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of these differences.

title: Terephthalate effect on Rhodococcus sp. strain RHA1
description: Analysis of Rhodococcus sp. strain RHA1 cells exposed to the pollutant phthalate (PTH) or terephthalate (TPA). Phthalate esters are used as plastic additives. RHA1 is able to degrade a wide range of aromatic compounds including PTH. Results provide insight into the ability of RHA1 to degrade TPA.

title: Nitrosomonas europaea response to chloromethane
description: Analysis of Nitrosomonas europaea cells treated with the pollutant chloromethane. N. europeaea is an ammonia oxidizer. Results provide insight into the molecular response of ammonia oxidizing bacteria to chlorinated aliphatic hydrocarbons.

title: Nitrosomonas europaea response to chloroform
description: Analysis of Nitrosomonas europaea cells treated with the pollutant chloroform. N. europeaea is an ammonia oxidizer. Results provide insight into the molecular response of ammonia oxidizing bacteria to chlorinated aliphatic hydrocarbons.

title: MyD88 deficient macrophage response to zymosan
description: Analysis of MyD88-deficient macrophages treated with fungal cell wall component zymosan. Zymosan-induced Toll-like receptor (TLR) signaling is transduced via adaptor protein MyD88. Results provide insight into the role of non-TLR innate immune signaling in response to zymosan and pathogenic fungi.

title: Kruppel-like factor 15 deficient liver and skeletal muscle response to fasting
description: Analysis of livers and quadriceps muscles of Kruppel-like factor 15 (KLF15) null mutants after an overnight fast. KLF15 nulls develop hypoglycemia after fasting. Gluconeogenesis (GLC) is essential for preventing hypoglycemia during fasting. Results provide insight into the role of KLF15 in GLC.

title: Skeletal muscle response to chronic corticosteroid exposure: time course
description: Analysis of skeletal muscles of adrenalectomized animals given methylprednisolone (MPL) at a constant rate of infusion for up to 7 days. Results compared to a time series experiment using a single dose of MPL. Results provide insight into the identity of genes regulated by MPL in both regimens.

title: Serine/threonine kinase Tao-1 dominant negative mutation effect on pole cells
description: Analysis of pole cells overexpressing a dominant negative Tao-1 mutation. Tao-1 is a member of a conserved family of ste20-related serine/threonine kinases that regulate fundamental cellular processes including apoptosis. Results identify genes regulated by Tao-1 in pole cells undergoing apoptosis.

title: p38alpha deficiency effect on the fetal liver
description: Analysis of embryonic day 13.5 and 15.5 fetal livers lacking p38alpha. p38alpha is a mitogen-activated kinase that controls inflammatory responses and cell proliferation. Results provide insight into the mechanisms underlying the enhanced proliferation of p38alpha-deficient hematopoietic cells.

title: Silent Information Regulator 2-related gene OsSRT1 knockdown effect on rice leaves
description: Analysis of rice leaves following RNAi knockdown of OsSRT1, a Silent Information Regulator 2 (SIR2)-related gene. Members of the SIR2 family are NAD(+)-dependent histone deacetylases. OsSRT1is one of the two SIR2-related genes found in rice. Results provide insight into the function of OsSRT1.

title: Teratozoospermia (HumanRef-8 BeadChip)
description: Analysis of sperm cells from males with consistent and severe teratozoospermia, a condition in which less than 4 percent of sperm cells are morphologically normal. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of a range of teratozoospermic presentations.

title: Teratozoospermia (Human-6 BeadChip)
description: Analysis of sperm cells from males with consistent and severe teratozoospermia, a condition in which less than 4 percent of sperm cells are morphologically normal. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of a range of teratozoospermic presentations.

title: Teratozoospermia (HG-U133 2.0 )
description: Analysis of sperm cells from males with consistent and severe teratozoospermia, a condition in which less than 4 percent of sperm cells are morphologically normal. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of a range of teratozoospermic presentations.

title: Synovial sarcoma model
description: Analysis of synovial sarcoma-like tumors from transgenics expressing the chimeric human SYT-SSX2 fusion protein. The presence of SYT-SSX transcript is diagnostic for synovial sarcoma. Results provide insight into the role of the SYT-SSX2 fusion protein in the pathogenesis of synovial sarcoma.

title: Mesenchymal and epithelial compartments of the developing intestine
description: Analysis of the mesenchymal and epithelial fractions of the embryonic small intestine. Crosstalk between the epithelium and the underlying mesenchyme is required for intestinal development. Results provide insight into the role of the mesenchyme in the determination of the epithelial phenotype.

title: Intestinal polyposis model
description: Analysis of intestinal polyps generated by the deletion of the phosphatase PTEN gene from the intestine. Intestinal polyposis results from an abnormal increase in the number of crypts, which contain stem cells. Results provide insight into the relationship between stem cells and polyp formation.

title: Contraction- and freeze-injured skeletal muscles: time course
description: Analysis of skeletal muscles at various time points up to 7 days following injury caused by eccentric contraction (CI) or by freezing (FI). Results provide insight into the molecular events accompanying the degeneration and repair phases of contraction- and trauma-induced muscle injuries.

title: Topoisomerase IIbeta deficiency effect on the developing embryonic brain
description: Anlaysis of brains from topoisomerase IIbeta (TopIIbeta) deficient embryos at various ages up to embryonic day 18.5. TopIIbeta null animals exhibit a perinatal death phenotype. Results provide insight into the role of TopIIbeta at the late stages of neuronal differentiation.

title: Transcription factor Klf9 deficiency effect on the intestine
description: Analysis of jejuna of Krüppel-like factor 9 (Klf9) null mutants. Klf9, a zinc-finger transcription factor, is involved in the control of cell proliferation, cell differentiation and cell fate. Results provide insight into role of Klf9 in intestine crypt-villus cell renewal and lineage determination

title: Transcription factor CHF1/Hey2 null smooth muscle cell response to platelet-derived growth factor: time course
description: Analysis of CHF1/Hey2 null aortic smooth muscle cells treated for up to 480 minutes with platelet-derived growth factor (PDGF). CHF1/Hey2 is a cardiovascular transcription factor. Results provide insight into the mechanisms regulated by CHF1/Hey2 in the response of smooth muscles to growth factors.

title: PPARgamma agonist and platinum-based drug effect on adenocarcinoma cell line
description: Analysis of NSCLC adenocarcinoma cells treated with rosiglitazone, carboplatin, or both. Rosiglitazone is an agonist of the nuclear receptor PPARgamma. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the synergy observed between rosiglitazone and platinum-based drugs in cancer models.

title: Philadelphia chromosome positive acute lymphoblastic leukemia cell lines response to imatinib mesylate
description: Analysis of Philadelphia chromosome (Ph) positive acute lymphoblastic leukemia cell lines BV173 and SUP-B15 treated with the anticancer drug imatinib mesylate (STI571). Ph encodes the oncogenic BCR-ABL1 kinase. Results provide insight into molecular basis of the transforming activity of BCR-ABL1.

title: Neuralized embryoid bodies response to Hedgehog agonist
description: Analysis of neuralized embryoid bodies (EBs) treated with a Hedgehog (Hh) agonist. EBs neuralized with retinoic acid. Hh signaling is mediated by Ci/Gli zinc finger domain-containing transcription regulators. Results used to identify gene targets of Gli.

title: Quercetin effect on cultured cardiomyocytes: time course
description: Analysis of cultured cardiomyocytes treated for up to 24 hours with the flavonoid quercetin. Consumption of food rich in quercetin is correlated with a decreased incidence of heart disease. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying the cardioprotective effects of quercetin.

title: Ventilator-associated lung induced injury resistant and sensitive strains
description: Analysis of lungs from 2 strains exposed to high tidal volume mechanical ventilation. Examined strains consist of one that is resistant to ventilator-associated lung injury (VALI) and another that is sensitive. Results provide insight into the genetic basis of susceptibility to VALI.

title: Salt-sensitive hypertension model: kidney
description: Analysis of kidneys from Dahl salt-sensitive males fed a high salt diet. The Dahl salt sensitive animal is used as a model of hypertension. Results combined with quantitative trait loci analyses to identify candidate genes that influence blood pressure levels.

title: Yeast response to dessication and subsequent rehydration (I)
description: Analysis of Saccharomyces cerevisiae BY4743 cells subjected to controlled air-drying and subsequent rehydration for up to 360 minutes. Results provide insight into the molecular response of yeast to water deficit.

title: Yeast response to dessication and subsequent rehydration (II)
description: Analysis of Saccharomyces cerevisiae BY4743 cells subjected to controlled air-drying and subsequent rehydration for up to 360 minutes. Results provide insight into the molecular response of yeast to water deficit.

title: Yeast response to dessication and subsequent rehydration (III)
description: Analysis of Saccharomyces cerevisiae BY4743 cells subjected to controlled air-drying and subsequent rehydration for up to 360 minutes. Results provide insight into the molecular response of yeast to water deficit.

title: Commercially prepared dry active yeast and dessicated laboratory yeast
description: Comparison of commercially prepared dry active yeast and desiccated preparations of the Saccharomyces cerevisiae laboratory strain BY4743. The yeast specimens were dried by different regimens. Results provide insight into the molecular response of yeast to water removal.

title: Polycomb group protein Ezh2 deficiency effect on lymph node T cells
description: Analysis of lymph node T cells lacking the polycomb group protein Ezh2. In B cells, Ezh2 is localized to the nucleus and is essential in histone H3 lysine 27 methylation. T lymphocytes also contain cytosolic Ezh2. Results provide insight into the function of Ezh2 in the T cell cytosol.

title: Transcription factor Zfx deficiency effect on embryonic and hematopoietic stem cells
description: Analysis of embryonic and hematopoietic stem cells (SCs) lacking the transcription factor Zfx. Zfx is a zinc finger protein of the Zfy family, whose members are highly conserved in vertebrates. Results provide insight into the role of Zfx in embryonic and adult SC self-renewal.

title: Embryonic gonad development
description: Analysis of male and female gonads at 11.5 to 18.5 days postcoitum (dpc). Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying the functional and structural changes in the developing male and female embryonic gonads.

title: Forkhead O deficiency effect on hematopoietic stem cells
description: Analysis of lineage-negative Sca-1+, c-Kit+ (LSK) cells lacking the Forkhead O transcription factors FoxO1, FoxO3, and FoxO4. The LSK cell population is enriched for hematopoietic stem cells (HSCs). Results provide insight into the role of FoxO family members in hematopoiesis.

title: Pubertal mammary gland development
description: Analysis of mammary glands of animals from pre-puberty to post-puberty. Results provide insight into the mechanisms underlying mammary gland development during puberty.

title: Barley cultivars response to salinity stress
description: Analysis of roots and shoots of barley cultivars Maythorpe and Golden Promise subjected to salinity stress. Golden Promise is a salt-tolerant spring barley closely related to Maythorpe. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of this difference in salt-tolerance.

title: Primary immunodeficiency syndrome: B cells
description: Analysis of immortalized B cells from 2 children with a primary immunodeficiency syndrome that is characterized by neutropenia, partial albinism, short stature, and B-cell and cytotoxic T-cell deficiencies. Results provide insight into the genetic basis of this syndrome.

title: Transcriptional regulators Bmi-1 and Mel-18 depletion effect on medulloblastoma cell line
description: Analysis of DAOY medulloblastoma cells following RNAi knockdown of Bmi-1, Mel-18, or both. Bmi-1 and Mel-18 belong to the Polycomb group (PcG) of transcriptional regulators. Results provide insight into the role of Bmi-1 and Mel-18 in the pathogenesis of medulloblastoma.

title: Conditionally immortalized astrocyte cell line response to T-antigen inactivation
description: Analysis of conditionally immortalized astrocyte RCG-12 cells induced to undergo growth arrest and differentiation by heat inactivation of a temperature-sensitive large T-antigen. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying cell growth arrest and differentiation.

title: Estrogen-related receptor alpha deficiency effect on the heart
description: Analysis of hearts from mutants lacking estrogen-related receptor alpha (ERRalpha), a nuclear receptor. ERRalpha is a regulator of mitochondrial biogenesis. Results provide insight into the role of ERRalpha in the heart.

title: CD133+ and CD133- glioblastoma-derived cancer stem cell lines
description: Comparison of CD133+ and CD133- glioblastoma-derived cancer stem cells (CSC). Both CSC subpopulations were derived from primary glioblastomas. Results provide insight into the role of CD133+ and CD133- CSCs in the pathogenesis of glioblastoma.

title: Cyclophosphamide-resistant chronic myelogenous leukemia cell line
description: Analysis of chronic myelogenous leukemia (CML) cells resistant to cyclophosphamide (CP), an alkylating anticancer drug. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of CP resistance in CML.

title: mRNA cap-binding protein ABH1 mutant response to abscisic acid
description: Analysis of abh1 mutants treated with abscisic acid (ABA). ABH1 encodes a nuclear mRNA cap-binding protein homolog. The abh1 mutant is hypersensitive to ABA, a plant hormone that regulates development and abiotic stress responses. Results provide insight into the role of ABH1 in ABA signaling.

title: Retinoblastoma binding protein RBP2 deficiency effect on embryonic fibroblasts
description: Analysis of embryonic fibroblasts lacking the retinoblastoma binding protein RBP2. RBP2 contains a histone demethylase signature motif, as well as other domains frequently found in transcriptional regulators. Results provide mechanistic insights into transcriptional regulation by RBP2.

title: 2-(3,4,5-trimethoxyphenylamino)-pyrrolo[2,3-d]pyrimidine effect on epidermal keratinocytes: time course
description: Analysis of epidermal keratinocytes at various time points up to 48 hours following treatment with 2-(3,4,5-trimethoxyphenylamino)-pyrrolo[2,3-d]pyrimidine (PP). PP induces the terminal differentiation of epidermal keratinocytes. Results provide insight into the mechanism of action of PP.

title: Cytosine arabinoside effect on Ewing’s sarcoma cell line: time course and dose response
description: Analysis of Ewing’s sarcoma A673 cells for up to 5 days after treatment with cytosine arabinoside (ARA-C) at EC50 or twice the EC50. ARA-C identified as a modulator of the Ewing’s sarcoma EWS/FLI fusion protein. Results provide insight into the specificity of the response of A673 cells to ARA-C.

title: DNA-associated protein Stonewall deficiency effect on ovaries
description: Comparison of ovaries from bag of marbles (bam) mutants and stonewall (stwl) bam double mutants. Stwl is a DNA-associated protein required for germline stem cell (GSC) maintenance; Bam is a key differentiation factor. Results provide insight into the role of Stwl in maintaining germ cell identity.

title: Metastatic melanoma: peripheral blood lymphocytes
description: Analysis of sorted peripheral blood lymphocytes (CD8 T cells, CD4 T cells, B cells, NK cells) from patients with melanoma. These subpopulations are involved in antitumor responses and negatively impacted by cancer. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms of immune dysfunction in cancer.

title: Malignant fibrous histiocytoma and various soft tissue sarcomas
description: Analysis of malignant fibrous histiocytoma (MFH) tumors and various soft tissue sarcomas (STSs). MFH is characterized by non-recurrent complex chromosomal aberrations, and overlapping histological and immunohistochemical phenotypes. Results provide insight into the similarities between MFH and STSs.

title: Endometriosis
description: Analysis of endometrial specimens from women with endometriosis. Endometrial gene expression examined at various phases of the menstrual cycle. Results provide insight into the molecular pathogenesis of endometriosis.

title: Ketogenic diet effect on the liver
description: Analysis of livers from animals fed a ketogenic diet (KD). KDs, diets that are high in fat and low in carbohydrates, are used as an approach to weight loss. Results provide insight into the KD-induced molecular mechanisms underlying the metabolic state congruous with weight loss.

title: Hyperplastic enlarged lobular units: epithelial cells
description: Analysis of epithelial cells isolated from hyperplastic enlarged lobular units (HELUs). HELUs arise from the enlargement of normal terminal duct lobular units by hyperplastic columnar epithelial cells and are the earliest histologically identifiable precursor of breast cancer.

title: Lengthening and shortening contractions effect on the muscle: time course
description: Analysis of skeletal muscles at various time points up to 24 hours after acute bouts of either lengthening (LCs) or shortening contractions (SCs). Resistance training using LCs results in greater increases in muscle size than SCs. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of this difference.

title: TCR-alpha/beta CD8-alpha/alpha intestinal intraepithelial lymphocytes
description: Analysis of TCR-alpha/beta CD8-alpha/alpha intestinal intraepithelial lymphocytes (IELs). Results provide insight into the function of TCR-alpha/beta CD8-alpha/alpha IELs in the mucosal immune system.

title: Type 1 diabetes mellitus model: mast cells
description: Analysis of mast cells isolated from the pancreatic lymph nodes of 60 day old prediabetic BioBiobreeding (BB) DR lyp/lyp animals. The BB DR lyp/lyp strain is a model for type 1 diabetes mellitus (T1DM). Results provide insight into the role of mast cells in the pathogenesis of T1DM.

title: Brown and white adipocyte differentiation
description: Comparison of brown and white preadipocytes at the undifferentiated and differentiating stages. Unlike white adipocytes, brown adipocytes have an abundance of mitochondria and are thus able to contribute to energy expenditure. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of this difference.

title: Dioxin effect on breast cancer cell line (HG-U133A)
description: Analysis of MCF-7 breast cancer cells treated with 100 nM dioxin. Although dioxin is causative for many types of cancers, low exposure to dioxin is associated with a decreased incidence of breast carcinoma. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of this protective effect.

title: Dioxin effect on breast cancer cell line (HG-U133B)
description: Analysis of MCF-7 breast cancer cells treated with 100 nM dioxin. Although dioxin is causative for many types of cancers, low exposure to dioxin is associated with a decreased incidence of breast carcinoma. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of this protective effect.

title: Lmna H222P homozygous and heterozygous mutant models of Emery-Dreifuss muscular dystrophy: hearts
description: Analysis of hearts of A-type lamin Lmna H222P homo-/heterozygous mutants. LMNA mutations lead to autosomal dominant and recessive Emery-Dreifuss muscular dystrophy which is characterized by dilated cardiomyopathy. Results provide insight into the role of LMNA in the development of cardiomyopathy.

title: Wilms’ tumor protein Wt1 deficiency effect on the urogenital ridge
description: Analysis of urogenital ridges from E11.5 embryos lacking the Wilms’ tumor protein Wt1. Wt1 is a transcription factor known to play an important role in urogenital development. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying Wt1 function in gonad and mesonephros development.

title: Homeodomain protein Lim1 deficiency effect on embryonic renal vesicles
description: Analysis of Lim1-null renal vesicles microdissected from embryonic day 12.5 kidneys. In Lim1 null embryos, the formation of comma shaped bodies from renal vesicles is interrupted. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of this developmental arrest.

title: Immature dendritic cell response to Aspergillus fumigatus infection in vitro
description: Analysis of dendritic cells (DCs) infected with Aspergillus fumigatus (AF) in vitro. DCs obtained from two healthy donors. AF is a ubiquitous mold and a common cause of invasive aspergillosis (IA) in immunocompromised patients. Results provide insight into DC involvement in antifungal defense.

title: Immature dendritic cell response to hypoxia in vitro
description: Analysis of immature dendritic cells (DCs) differentiated from monocytes under hypoxia for 4 days. DCs are antigen presenting cells whose development is influenced by the microenvironment. Hypoxia is an important constituent of the microenvironment of inflamed tissues.

title: Pocket protein ortholog lin-35 null mutant at various stages of development
description: Analysis of lin-35 null mutants at the embryonic stage, and L1 and L4 larval stages. LIN-35 is an ortholog of the mammalian pocket protein family members, pRb, p107, and p130. Results provide insight into the role of pocket proteins in development.

title: Interferon regulatory factor-1 effect on transformed cells
description: Analysis of myc/ras transformed cells expressing interferon regulatory factor-1 (IRF-1). IRF-1 mediates proliferation inhibition and reversion of the transformed phenotype of oncogenic cells. Results provide insight into the molecular alterations initiated by the action of IRF-1.

title: Enterohemorrhagic Escherichia coli biofilm response to 7-hydroxyindole and isatin
description: Analysis of enterohemorrhagic Escherichia coli biofilm treated with 7-hydroxyindole or oxidized indole (isatin). Many bacterial oxygenases readily convert indole, an interspecies biofilm signal, into oxidized compounds. Results provide insight into the role of oxidized indoles in biofilm formation.

title: Exhaustive exercise effect on peripheral blood mononuclear cells and T lymphocytes
description: Analysis of peripheral blood mononuclear cells and T lymphocytes from individuals before and after a bout of acute exhaustive exercise. White blood cell (WBC) subpopulations shift during physical activities. Results provide insight into the response of sorted WBC subpopulations to acute exercise.

title: miR-34 overexpression
