description: Analysis of HCT116 cells overexpressing miR-34, a microRNA. miR-34 is commonly deleted in human cancers. Results provide insight into the function of miR-34.

title: Measles: peripheral blood mononuclear cells
description: Analysis of peripheral blood mononuclear cells (PBMCs) from measles patients. PBMCs collected upon hospital admission, at discharge, and one month after discharge. Results provide insight into the immunological changes that occur during measles infections.

title: Retinoblastoma protein deficiency effect on fetal livers
description: Analysis of embryonic day 12.5 livers from retinoblastoma protein (Rb)-null mutants. Rb-null embryos exhibit defective fetal liver erythropoiesis. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the erythroblastic island defect in the Rb-null fetal liver.

title: Hypoxia and 2-oxoglutrate-dependent dioxygenase inhibition (HG-U133A)
description: Analysis of MCF-7 breast cancer cells exposed to hypoxia or treated with the non-specific 2-oxoglutarate (2-OG) dependent dioxygenase inhibitor dimethyloxalylglycine. Results provide insight into the role of 2-OG dioxygenases in the regulation of gene expression during hypoxia.

title: Hypoxia and 2-oxoglutrate-dependent dioxygenase inhibition (Human-6 BeadChip)
description: Analysis of MCF-7 breast cancer cells exposed to hypoxia or treated with the non-specific 2-oxoglutarate (2-OG) dependent dioxygenase inhibitor dimethyloxalylglycine. Results provide insight into the role of 2-OG dioxygenases in the regulation of gene expression during hypoxia.

title: Hypoxia-inducible factor depletion  (HG-U133 2.0)
description: Analysis of hypoxic MCF-7 breast cancer cells depleted for hypoxia-inducible factor (HIF)-1alpha, HIF-2alpha, or both HIF alpha subunits. Results provide insight into the extent of the role of HIF-1alpha and HIF-2alpha in the regulation of gene expression during hypoxia.

title: Hypoxia-inducible factor depletion (Human-6 BeadChip)
description: Analysis of hypoxic MCF-7 breast cancer cells depleted for hypoxia-inducible factor (HIF)-1alpha, HIF-2alpha, or both HIF alpha subunits. Results provide insight into the extent of the role of HIF-1alpha and HIF-2alpha in the regulation of gene expression during hypoxia.

title: Interferon receptor deficient lymph node B cell response to influenza infection
description: Analysis of lymph node B cells from interferon receptor (IFNR) null mutants infected with the influenza virus. Wild type B cells treated with IFN-beta also examined. Results provide insight into the role of IFNR signaling in the immune response mediated by B cells during influenza infections.

title: Polycystic lipomembranous osteodysplasia with sclerosing leukoencephalopathy: dendritic cells
description: Analysis of in vitro differentiated dendritic cells (DCs) from patients with PLOSL, an early onset dementia with bone cysts caused by mutations in DAP12 and TREM2 genes which encode important signaling molecules in DCs. Results provide further insight into mechanisms underlying PLOSL pathogenesis.

title: Pseudomonas aeruginosa response to 3,4-(di)hydroxy-heptyl-quinoline: time course
description: Analysis of Pseudomonas aeruginosa cells treated for up to 20 hours with 3,4-(di)hydroxy-heptyl-quinoline (PQS), a bacterial intercellular signaling molecule. Results provide insight into the role of PQS in the bacterial communication system termed quorum sensing.

title: Creatine effect on the brain
description: Analysis of brains of C57Bl/6J animals fed a creatine supplemented diet for 6 months. Creatine has a neuroprotective effect in animal models of neurodegenerative diseases. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of this neuroprotective effect.

title: Dominant negative cJun effect on apolipoprotein E deficient livers
description: Analysis of apolipoprotein E deficient livers from animals expressing a dominant negative cJun (dn-c-Jun). Lipoproteins transport cholesterol and other fats through the bloodstream. Results provide insight into the pathways involved in regulating plasma cholesterol that are affected by dn-c-Jun.

title: Blood response to various beverages: time course
description: Analysis of blood samples from 6 individuals at various time points up to 12 hours following the intake of water, ethanol, grape juice, or red wine. Results may contribute to elucidating the mechanisms underlying the cardioprotective effects of red wine.

title: Escherichia coli biofilm development
description: Analysis of Escherichia coli K-12 biofilms up to 24 hours of culturing. Biofilm bacteria predominate in nutrient-sufficient ecosystems. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying biofilm development.

title: Non-coding roX1 and roX2 RNA deficiency effect on larvae
description: Analysis of third instar larvae lacking noncoding RNAs roX1 and roX2. The roX RNAs are components of the male-specific lethal (MSL) ribonucleoprotein complex, required for equalization of X:A expression levels in males. Results provide insight into the role of roX RNAs in X-chromosome expression.

title: Estrogen effect on breast cancer cell line coexpressing estrogen receptors alpha and beta
description: Analysis of estrogen receptor (ER) alpha positive MCF-7 breast cancer cells following introduction of ERbeta and treatment with estrogen. The majority of breast cancers express both ERalpha and ERbeta. Results provide insight into the comodulatory effects of these two ERs.

title: Large airway epithelial cells from cigarette smokers with suspect lung cancer
description: Analysis of large airway epithelial cells from cigarette smokers without cancer, with cancer, and with suspect lung cancer. Results provide insight into the feasibility of using gene expression to detect early stage lung cancer in smokers.

title: Sevoflurane and propofol effect on the heart during off-pump coronary artery bypass graft surgery
description: Analysis of atrial biopsies from patients receiving the anesthetic gas sevoflurane or the intravenous anesthetic propofol during off-pump coronary artery bypass graft surgery. Anesthetic gases protect against myocardial ischemia. Results provide insight into the basis of this protective effect.

title: Endothelial cell response to chronic activation by tumor necrosis factor
description: Analysis of endothelial cells acutely activated by treatment with soluble tumor necrosis factor (TNF) or chronically activated by expression of an uncleavable form of the transmembrane TNF precursor. Results provide insight into the mechanisms mediating the effect of chronic endothelial activation.

title: Transcription factor Nurr1 overexpression induced by depolarization effect on midbrain neurons in vitro
description: Analysis of cultured midbrain neurons enriched for dopaminergic neurons following Nurr1 overexpression induced by depolarization. Nurr1 is a transcription factor essential for the generation of midbrain dopaminergic neurons. Results provide insight into the molecular pathways regulated by Nurr1.

title: Nuclear factor I-A deficiency effect on brain development
description: Analysis of embryonic (E18) and postnatal (P16) brains of mutants lacking the transcription/replication protein nuclear factor I-A (NFI-A). NFI-A null mutants exhibit neurological defects. Results provide insight into mechanisms regulated by NFI-A during brain development.

title: Bexarotene effect on gemcitabine resistant non-small lung cancer cell line
description: Analysis of gemcitabine (Gem)-resistant non-small lung cancer Calu3 cells treated with bexarotene (Bex). Acquired drug resistance is a major obstacle in cancer therapy. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying the ability of bexarotene to overcome Gem-resistance in Calu3 cells.

title: 1,2,4-benzenetriol effect on peripheral blood mononuclear cells in vitro
description: Analysis of cultured peripheral blood mononuclear cells treated with the benzene metabolite 1,2,4-benzenetriol. Benzene is an air pollutant and carcinogen. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of benzene cytotoxicity.

title: Lymphoblastoid cell lines from monozygotic twin pairs discordant for bipolar disorder
description: Analysis of lymphoblastoid cell lines derived from 3 monozygotic twin pairs discordant for bipolar disorder. Results provide insight into the molecular pathogenesis of bipolar disorder.

title: Heavy metals effect on liver cell line
description: Analysis of liver carcinoma HepG2 cells exposed to various heavy metals. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of heavy metal cytotoxicity.

title: Nonsense mediated decay factor UPF1 depletion
description: Analysis of HeLa cells depleted for the nonsense-mediated decay (NMD)-keys factor UPF1. NMD represents a key mechanism to control the expression of wild-type and aberrant mRNAs. Results provide insight into the extent of gene regulation mediated by UPF1 activity.

title: Androgen response element specific DNA-binding polyamide effect on dihydrotestoterone-stimulated prostate cell line
description: Analysis of DHT-stimulated LNCaP prostate cells treated with an androgen response (AR) element (ARE) specific DNA binding polyamide. Polyamide designed to target the sequence 5'-WGWWCW-3' and disrupt AR-mediated gene expression. Effects of the synthetic antiandrogen bicalutamide also examined.

title: Progesterone effect on cultured neonatal ovaries
description: Analysis of cultured neonatal ovaries treated with progesterone for 2 days. In the early postnatal period, groups of oocytes break down to form primordial follicles. This process is called follicle assembly. Results provide insight into the role of progesterone in follicle assembly.

title: Survey of various adult tissues
description: Analysis of eight distinct adult tissues in a model organism. Two larval tissues and whole organism also examined. Results provide insight into the degree of tissue specific gene expression at the adult stage.

title: Ovarian cancer tumors after neo-adjuvant chemotherapy
description: Analysis of malignant ovarian cancer tumors from patients receiving neo-adjuvant chemotherapy. Ovarian adenomas and untreated ovarian carcinomas also examined.  Results used to define gene expression signatures associated with clinical responses to chemotherapy.

title: Embryonic motor neurons
description: Analysis of embryonic motor neurons marked with an unc-4::GFP reporter transgene. UNC-4 is a homoedomain transcription factor expressed in 13 embryonic motor neurons. Results contribute to a comprehensive picture of gene expression in a subset of motor neurons.

title: LIM-only protein 4 induction effect on breast cancer cell line (HG-U133A)
description: Analysis of breast cancer MCF-7 cells following the induction of expression of nuclear LIM-only protein 4 (LMO4). LMO4 is upregulated in breast cancer. Results provide insight into the role of LMO4 in promoting tumor formation.

title: LIM-only protein 4 induction effect on breast cancer cell line (HG-U133B)
description: Analysis of breast cancer MCF-7 cells following the induction of expression of nuclear LIM-only protein 4 (LMO4). LMO4 is upregulated in breast cancer. Results provide insight into the role of LMO4 in promoting tumor formation.

title: LIM homeobox protein cofactor dominant negative form effect on breast cancer cell line
description: Analysis of breast cancer MCF-7 cells after the induction of expression of a dominant negative form of the cofactor of LIM domains (CLIM), a co-regulator of the nuclear LIM only protein 4 (LMO4). LMO4 is upregulated in breast cancer. Results provide insight into the role of LMO4 in tumor formation.

title: Skeletal muscle response to insulin infusion (HuGeneFL)
description: Analysis of skeletal muscles from non-diabetics after a 3 hour infusion of insulin. Glucose uptake by skeletal muscles in response to insulin is impaired in type 2 diabetes. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms regulating glucose homeostasis in response to insulin.

title: Skeletal muscle response to insulin infusion (HG-U133A)
description: Analysis of skeletal muscles from non-diabetics after a 2 hour infusion of insulin. Glucose uptake by skeletal muscles in response to insulin is impaired in type 2 diabetes. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms regulating glucose homeostasis in response to insulin.

title: T-cell acute lymphoblastic leukemia cell line response to Notch receptor inhibition
description: Analysis of T-cell acute lymphoblast leukemia (T-ALL) MOLT4 cells following gamma-secretase inhibitor (GSI) DAPT treatment. Gamma-secretase activity is required for Notch 1 receptor signaling. Results provide insight into the role of Notch signaling in T-ALL development.

title: Alzheimer's disease: neurofibrillary tangles
description: Analysis of entorhinal cortex neurons containing neurofibrillary tangles (NFT) from 10 mid-stage Alzheimer's disease (AD) patients. Comparison with histopathologically normal neurons from the same patients and brain region. Results provide insight into the formation of NFTs in AD.

title: Dexamethasone effect on fetal chondrocytes in vitro: time course
description: Analysis of primary cultured fetal chondrocytes treated with pharmacological doses of dexamethasone (DEX) for 6 and 24 hours. DEX is a synthetic glucorticoid (GC) receptor agonist. Results provide insight into the effects of pharmacological GC on chondrocytes.

title: Fluoxetine effect on the hippocampus
description: Analysis of hippocampi from DBA/2J males chronically treated with the antidepressant (AD) fluoxetine (Flx). ADs promote the proliferation and survival of neurons in the adult hippocampus. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the neuronal and behavioral responses to Flx treatment.

title: Quiescent stb3 null mutant response to glucose
description: Analysis of the response of quiescent stb3 null cells to glucose. STB3 encodes a protein that binds to the Ribosomal RNA Processing Element, a DNA sequence motif that regulates genes needed for growth. Results provide insight into Stb3’s role during the transition from quiescence to rapid growth.

title: Serum response factor deficient B cells
description: Analysis of IgM+ IgD+ B cells lacking the Serum response factor (SRF) gene. SRF is a MADS-box transcription factor that is essential in embryonic development and in neuron and muscle cell function. Results provide insight into the role of SRF in lymphocyte development.

title: Sepsis: neutrophils
description: Analysis of neutrophils from critically ill patients with sepsis. Results used to define a gene expression signature for sepsis and provides insight into the host response to sepsis.

title: Knee osteoarthritis model: chondrocytes
description: Analysis of articular condrocytes from osteoarthritic knees of Sprague-Dawley males. Osteoarthritis (OA) induced by surgery. Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of OA.

title: Organized and growth-arrested mammary acini: time course
description: Temporal analysis of two nonmalignant mammary epithelial cells (HMEC) grown in a laminin-rich extracellular matrix. Both HMECs transit from a disorganized to an organized state to form polarized acini. Results identify gene signatures with potential value for breast cancer prognosis prediction.

title: Estrogen-related receptor gamma deficiency effect on the fetal heart
description: Analysis of hearts from fetuses lacking ERRgamma, a gene expressed at high levels in fetal and postnatal heart. Results provide insight into the role of ERRgamma in the heart’s metabolic switch from a dependence on carbohydrates during fetal life to a dependence on postnatal oxidative metabolism.

title: Antimicrobial effect of Rhein
description: Analysis of Staphylococcus aureus ATCC25923 cultures treated with subinhibitory concentrations of rhein for 45 minutes. Rhein is an antimicrobial agent from rhubarb. Results provide insight into the efficacy of rhein against Staphylococcus aureus.

title: Brown and white adipose tissues
description: Comparison of brown and white adipose tissues. Brown fat cells are specialized to dissipate energy and can counteract obesity. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms controlling brown fat cell determination.

title: Berberine chloride effect on Staphylococcus aureus
description: Analysis of Staphylococcus aureus ATCC25923 cultures treated with berberine chloride. Results provide insight into the antimicrobial activity of berberine chloride against Staphylococcus aureus.

title: Morphine effect on the striatum
description: Analysis of striata from several inbred strains strains, with different opioid-related phenotypes, subjected to single and repeated morphine administrations. Results provide insight into the relationship between gene expression and behavioral response to the drug.

title: Ras-GRF1 deficiency effect on the hippocampus
description: Analysis of laser capture microdissected hippocampi of mutants lacking Ras-GRF1. Ras-GRF-1 is a guanine nucleotide exchange factor predominantly expressed in the central nervous system of mammals. Results provide insight into role of Ras-GRF1 in neural processes.

title: Nephronophthisis model
description: Analysis of kidneys of animals lacking Glis2. The GLIS2 gene, which encodes a Kruppel-like zinc finger transcription factor, is found in a region of chromosome 16 p linked to nephronophthisis (NPHP). Results provide insight into the role of Glis2 in the pathophysiology of NPHP.

title: Adipocytes and preadipocytes from subcutaneous and visceral fat depots
description: Analysis of adipocytes and stromovascular fraction containing preadipocytes taken from subcutaneous fat and intraabdominal fat. Individuals with peripheral subcutaneous obesity are at little risk of complications of obesity, while those with visceral obesity are prone to these complications.

title: Leukemic white blood cells and various RNA preparation protocols
description: Analysis of RNA samples prepared from leukemic white blood cells using 3 different protocols. Samples obtained from 27 pediatric patients with various subtypes of acute leukemia. Results provide insight into the impact of RNA preparation methods on the variation in gene expression data.

title: Cannabinoid receptor double knockout mutant response to contact allergen
description: Analysis of skins of mutants lacking 2 cannabinoid receptors after treatment with the contact allergen 2,4-dinitrofluorobenzene (DNFB). DNFB elicits a cutaneous T-cell mediated allergic response. Results provide insight into the role of the endocannabinoid system in allergic contact dermatitis.

title: Parkinson’s disease: substantia nigra
description: Analysis of substantia nigrae from postmortem brains of patients with Parkinson’s disease (PD). Neurons in the substantia nigra, which produces dopamine, degenerate in PD. Results provide insight into the molecular pathogenesis of PD.

title: Placental malaria
description: Analysis of inflamed placentas from patients with chronic placental malaria (PM). Chronic inflammation during PM is frequent in first time mothers and is associated with poor maternal and fetal outcomes. Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of chronic PM.

title: SOD1-G93A mutant model of amyotrophic lateral sclerosis: embryonic motor neurons
description: Analysis of spinal cord motor neurons from embryonic day 14 transgenics expressing the human superoxide dismutase 1 (SOD1) G93A mutant protein. The SOD1-G93A transgenic is a model for amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (ALS). Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of ALS.

title: Autism, fragile X syndrome, and 15q11-q13 duplication: lymphoblastoid cells
description: Analysis of lymphoblastoid cells from males with autism due to a fragile X mutation or a 15q11-q13 duplication. Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of autism spectrum disorders.

title: Benzalkonium chloride adapted E. coli K12
description: Analysis of E. coli K12 strains adapted to grow in benzalkonium chloride (BC). BC is a commonly used disinfectant and preservative. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of this resistance.

title: Sickle cell anemia model: brain response to naloxone
description: Analysis of brains of NY1DD transgenic animals treated with naloxone. The NY1DD strain is a model for sickle cell anemia. Naloxone is an opioid antagonist that possesses potent analgesic activity in NY1DD animals. Results provide insight into the mechanism of action of naloxone in this model.

title: ERalpha-negative ERbeta-positive breast carcinoma response to tamoxifen
description: Analysis of estrogen receptor (ER) alpha negative ERbeta-positive breast cancer tumors from patients treated with tamoxifen for 2 years. Unlike ERalpha-negative ERbeta-negative breast cancers, ERalpha-negative ERbeta-positive cancers respond favorably to tamoxifen treatment.

title: Strains resistant to environmental stresses
description: Analysis of several lines each selected for resistance to a different environmental stress factor. Results provide insight into the molecular and genetic mechanisms that promote adaptation to environmental stresses.

title: Primary graft dysfunction after lung transplantation
description: Analysis of donor lung biopsies from recipients that developed primary graft dysfunction after lung transplantation. Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of primary lung graft dysfunction.

title: Sphingosine-1-phosphate effect on embryonic stem cells
description: Analysis of embryonic stem cells (ESCs) after treatment with sphingosine-1-phosphate (S1P) which plays a role in regulation of fate in many cell types. ESCs grown on mouse embryo fibroblast feeder cells and under feeder-free conditions. Results provide insight into the role of S1P in ESC renewal.

title: Polyomavirus JCV resistant glial cell line (HG-U133A)
description: Analysis of SVGR2 glial cells resistant to the human polyomavirus JCV, the causative agent of progressive multifocal leukoencephalopathy. SVGR2 cells are derived from susceptible glial cells (SVG-A). Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying susceptibility to JCV infection.

title: Polyomavirus JCV resistant glial cell line (HG-U133B)
description: Analysis of SVGR2 glial cells resistant to the human polyomavirus JCV, the causative agent of progressive multifocal leukoencephalopathy. SVGR2 cells are derived from susceptible glial cells (SVG-A). Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying susceptibility to JCV infection.

title: Ovarian endometriosis
description: Comparison of endometriosis lesions to normal endometrial tissues obtained from the same patient at the same time. Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of endometriosis.

title: Abdominal aortic aneurysm
description: Analysis of aneurysmal abdominal aortas (AAAs). Abdominal aortic aneurysms are a common disorder and mortality from ruptured AAAs is high. Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of abdominal aortic aneurysm.

title: DNA electroporation effect on skeletal muscles: time course
description: Analysis of tibialis cranialis muscles at various time points up to 3 weeks following transfection with green fluorescent protein (GFP) using DNA electroporation. Results provide insight into the feasibility of introducing the DNA electrotransfer to muscle for clinical use.

title: Alcohol-preferring inbred strain: brain
description: Analysis of various CNS regions of inbred alcohol-preferring and non-alcohol preferring animals that have not been exposed to alcohol. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the difference in alcohol preference between the two strains.

title: Testicular seminoma progression
description: Analysis of testicular seminoma tumors at various stages of progression (pT1, pT2, pT3). Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of testicular seminoma.

title: Mammary gland development
description: Analysis of mammary glands during pregnancy, lactation, and involution. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms regulating mammary gland development.

title: MicroRNA miR-124 expression effect on neuronal cell line
description: Analysis of neuroblastoma CAD cells expressing neuron-specific microRNA miR-124.  MicroRNAs have been implicated in the development of the nervous system (NS). Results provide insight into the function of miR-124 in neuronal cells.

title: Anisomycin effect on leukemia cell line: time course
description: Analysis of myeloid leukemia U937 cells treated with anisomycin for various time points up to 6 hours. Anisomycin is a potent inducer of apoptosis. Results provide insight into the mechanism of action of anisomycin in inducing apoptosis.

title: Notch1 deficiency effect on hair follicles
description: Analysis of Notch1-deficient hair follicles from the skin of transgenic animals. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying the lowered mitotic index and increased apoptosis observed in Notch1-deficient hair follicles.

title: Brain trauma model: time course  (MG-U74A)
description: Analysis of brain at various time points up to 72 hours following lateral controlled cortical impact injury. Delayed cell death following trauma results in brain damage. Results provide insight into the mechanisms underlying brain damage after traumatic injury.

title: Brain trauma model: time course (RG-U34A)
description: Analysis of brain at various time points up to 21 days following lateral fluid percussion-induced brain injury.  Delayed cell death following trauma results in brain damage. Results provide insight into the mechanisms underlying brain damage after traumatic injury.

title: Interleukin 13 effect on bronchial cell line: time course
description: Analysis of bronchial A549 cells at various time points up to 24 hours following treatment with the cytokine interleukin 13 (IL-13). IL-13 contributes to the pathogenesis of asthma.

title: Low and high grade astrocytomas
description: Comparison of low and high grade astrocytoma brain tumors. Results provide insight into the molecular differences between the two types of tumors.

title: Myogenic transcription factor MyoD mutant expression effect on embryonic fibroblast: time course
description: Analysis of embryonic fibroblasts at various time points up to 24 hours following transcriptional induction of a mutant form of the myogenic transcription factor MyoD. MyoD altered at lysine residues 99, 102, and 104, rendering it not acetylatable.

title: Various muscle diseases (HG-U133B)
description: Analysis of muscle biopsy specimens from patients with various muscle diseases.  Results provide insight into the diagnosis and pathogenesis of muscle diseases.

title: Peripheral blood-derived monocytes response to lipopolysaccharide: time course
description: Analysis of peripheral blood-derived monocytes at various time points up to 24 hours following treatment with lipopolysaccharide. Results compared with those obtained from Massively Parallel Signature Sequencing.

title: Taf7l deficiency effect on the testis
description: Analysis of testes of animals lacking Taf7l. TAF7L is an X-linked germ cell-specific paralog of TAF7, which is a generally expressed component of TFIID. Results provide insight into the role of Taf7l in spermatogenesis.

title: Myeloid-related protein 8 and 14 effect on microvascular endothelial cells
description: Analysis of microvascular endothelial cells (ECs) treated with the myeloid-related protein 8 (MRP8) and 14 (MRP14), proteins that form heterodimers secreted by phagocytes at inflammatory sites. Results provide insight into the role of MRP8 and MRP14 in EC cell death during inflammation.

title: Splenocyte response to infection by virB mutant Brucella strains
description: Analysis of splenocytes from animals infected with virB mutant Brucella arbortus strains. The virB operon encodes a Type IV secretion system (T4SS) essential for the intracellular survival and persistent infection by Brucella species. Results provide insight into the role of T4SS in infections.

title: Aldosterone-producing adeonoma
description: Analysis of aldosterone-producing adenoma (APA) samples from patients with primary hyperaldosteronism (PA). The source of aldosterone in many patients with PA is unilateral APA. Results provide insight into the mechanisms causing elevated aldosterone production in APA.

title: X-Box binding protein overexpression effect on breast cancer cell line
description: Analysis of MCF7 breast cancer (BC) cells overexpressing spliced X-box binding protein-1 (XBP1), a transcription factor that participates in the unfolded protein response (UPR). Results provide insight into the role of XBP1 and the UPR in estrogen and antiestrogen responsiveness in breast cancer.

title: Hypothalamus during normal female sexual development
description: Analysis of hypothalami from juvenile, early pubertal, and late pubertal female animals. Results provide insight into the role of the hypothalamus in controlling the onset of puberty.

title: Tienilic acid effect on the liver: time course
description: Analysis of livers from animals 6 and 24 hours following treatment with tienilic acid. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of tienilic acid associated hepatotoxicity.

title: RhoGDIbeta depletion effect on breast cancer cell line
description: Analysis of MDA-MB-231 breast cancer cells following RhoGDIbeta knockdown. RhoGDIbeta is a Rho guanine nucleotide dissociation inhibitor (RhoGDI) expressed in tumor cells. RhoGDIs negatively regulate the activity of Rho GTPases.

title: Metastatic prostate tumor model
description: Comparison of poorly and highly metastatic prostate subcutaneous tumors derived from xenotransplanted human PC-3 prostate cancer cells. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms contributing to prostate cancer metastasis.

title: Monocyte-derived macrophages of chronic obstructive pulmonary disease patients response to fine and ultrafine particles
description: Analysis of monocyte-derived macrophages from chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD) patients after in vitro treatment with a mix of fine titanium dioxide (TiO2) and ultrafine Printex 90 particles, or lipopolysaccharide (LPS). TiO2 and Printex 90 are used in the manufacture of many products.

title: TAp63alpha-Q540L mutant protein expression
description: Analysis of H1299 cells expressing the TAp63alpha-Q540L mutant protein. TAp63alpha-Q540L is a form of p63 that contains a missense mutation in the SAM domain. Mutations in the SAM domain of p63 are associated with Hay-Wells syndrome.

title: Inadequate dietary protein intake effect on the skeletal muscle
description: Analysis of vastus lateralis skeletal muscle biopsies from older males and females (aged 55-80 years) before and during a diet inadequate in proteins. Results provide insight into the molecular changes in skeletal muscles brought about by inadequate dietary protein intake.

title: Pseudomonas aeruginosa from cystic fibrosis lungs
description: Analysis of Pseudomonas aeruginosa isolates from sputa of cystic fibrosis (CF) lungs following growth in minimal media. P. aeruginosa infected CF lungs are characterized by high cell density (HCD) replication of this pathogen. Results provide insight into the mechanisms sustaining HCD replication.

title: Pseudomonas aeruginosa cystic fibrosis isolate response to various sulfur sources
description: Analysis of Pseudomonas aeruginosa E601 grown in media containing various sources of sulfur. P. aeruginosa E601 is a cystic fibrosis isolate that exhibits mucin sulfatase activity. Results provide insight into the pathways that respond to the nature of the supply of sulfur.

title: Folate deficiency and arsenic effect on the skin
description: Analysis of skin from transgenic K6/ODC animals maintained on a folate deficient diet and exposed to 1 or 10 ppm sodium arsenate. K6/ODC mice develop skin tumors when exposed to sodium arsenite. Results provide insight into the combined effect of folate deficiency and arsenic on the skin.

title: Wip1 mutant embryonic fibroblast response to gamma radiation
description: Analysis of Wip1 mutant embryonic fibroblasts following 4 hour after 5 Gy of gamma irradiation. Wip1 is a p53-induced phosphatase overexpressed in several human tumor types.

title: D-3-phosphoglycerate dehydrogenase deficiency effect on the embryonic head
description: Analysis of embryonic head tissue lacking D-3-phosphoglycerate dehydrogenase (Phgdh). Mutations in human PHGDH gene cause serine deficiency disorders like congenital microcephaly and psychomotor retardation. Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of SDD.

title: Vaccine adjuvant monophosphoryl lipid A effect on the spleen
description: Analysis of spleens of animals treated with the vaccine adjuvant monophosphoryl lipid A (MPLA). MPLA is a low-toxicity derivative of lipopolysaccharide with useful immunostimulatory properties. Results provide insight into the mechanism of action of MPLA.

title: Chlamydia psittaci infection and host genetic background
description: Analysis of peritoneal lavage from inbred C57BL/6J and DBA/2J animals 3 days after intraperitoneal injection with Chlamydia psittaci. C57BL/6J are more resistant to C. psittaci infection than DBA/2J. Results provide insight into the genetic basis of this difference.

title: Inert particles effect on the lungs of pregnant females
description: Analysis of lungs from pregnant and non-pregnant BALB/c females following insufflation with inert titanium dioxide particles. Results provide insight into the mechanisms underlying the differences in response between pregnant and non-pregnant females to inhaled inert particles.

title: Enterohemorrhagic Escherichia coli response to epinephrine, norepinephrine, and indole
description: Analysis of enterohemmorhagic Escherichia coli (EHEC) O157:H7 treated with epinephrine (EP), norepinephrine (NE), and indole. During infection in the gastrointestinal tract, EHEC is exposed to a wide range of signaling molecules such as EP and NE, and bacterial signaling molecules such as indole.

title: Clear cell renal cell carcinoma (HG-U133A)
description: Analysis of patient matched normal and stage 1 or stage 2 clear cell renal cell carcinoma (cRCC) tumors. Results provide insight into the molecular pathogenesis of cRCC.

title: Clear cell renal cell carcinoma (HB-U133B)
description: Analysis of patient matched normal and stage 1 or stage 2 clear cell renal cell carcinoma (cRCC) tumors. Results provide insight into the molecular pathogenesis of cRCC.

title: Cerebral cortex and hypothalamus response to sleep and sleep deprivation: time course
description: Analysis of cerebral cortices (CCs) and hypothalami (HYs) of animals after various durations of sleep and sleep deprivation. The CC is a neuronal target for processes that control sleep; the HY is an important site of sleep regulatory processes. Results provide insight into the function of sleep.

title: LEDGF/p75 transcription factor deficiency effect on T-cell line
description: Analysis of Jurkat T-cells depleted for the LEDGF/p75 transcription factor. LEDGF/p75 is involved in targeting HIV DNA integration. Results provide insight into the mechanisms controlling HIV integration.

title: X-linked Emery-Dreifuss muscular dystrophy model and cardiomyopathy
description: Analysis of hearts of mutants lacking EMD, a gene encoding an A-type lamin. Mutations in EMD cause X-linked Emery-Dreifuss muscular dystrophy (EDMD). Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms involved in the development of cardiomyopathy in X-linked EDMD.

title: Fibroblast-like synoviocytes response to p38 MAPK inhibition and TGFalpha in vitro
description: Analysis of fibroblast-like synoviocytes (FLS) treated with TGFalpha alone or in combination with SB203580, an inhibitor of p38. FLS, targets of proinflammatory cytokines, are involved in rheumatoid arthritis (RA). Results provide insight into the role of the p38 pathway in RA pathogenesis.

title: PPARalpha activation effect on the small intestine
description: Analysis of small intestine of wild type and peroxisome proliferator-activated receptor alpha (PPARalpha) null animals after treatment with WY14643, an agonist of PPARalpha. PPARalpha is a fatty acid-activated transcription factor. Results provide insight into role of PPARalpha in small intestine.

title: Moderate stage Huntington's disease lymphocytes
description: Analysis of lymphocytes from patients with moderate stage Huntington's disease (HD). Results provide insight into the feasibility of using gene expression to identify biomarkers for moderate stage HD.

title: Air pollutant and oxidized lipid effect on microvascular endothelial cells: dose response
description: Analysis of microvascular endothelial cells treated at various concentrations of the model air pollutant diesel exhaust particles (DEP), an oxidized phospholipid (ox-PAPC), or both. Results provide insight into the synergistic effect of DEP and ox-PAPC in promoting vascular inflammation.

title: Rv3133c/dosR transcription factor mutant response to hypoxia
description: Analysis of Rv3133c/dosR transcription factor mutant cells subjected to hypoxia. Latency of Mycobacterium tuberculosis is linked to hypoxic conditions within the host. Rv3133c/DosR is induced by hypoxia. Results provide insight into the function of Rv3133c/DosR.

title: Optineurin depletion
description: Analysis of HeLa cells depleted for optineurin using RNAi knockdown. Mutations in the gene for optineurin are associated with open-angle glaucoma. Results provide insight into the function of optineurin and its role in the pathogenesis of open-angle glaucoma.

title: Response to low oxygen conditions
description: Analysis of Pseudomonas aeruginosa strain PAO1 grown with 2% or 0.4% oxygen (O2), or without O2 but with nitrate instead. In cystic fibrosis (CF) lungs, PAO1 grows to high densities in mucopurulent material depleted in O2. Results provide insight into mode of growth in CF lungs.

title: Stem development
description: Analysis of sections from 5 and 10 cm long ecotype Ler bolting stems. Different stages of vascular and interfascicular fiber differentiation can be identified along the axis of bolting stems. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms controlling this pattern of development.

title: Tsc2 tumor suppressor gene mutant kidney response to genotoxic and non-genotoxic carcinogens: time course
description: Analysis of kidneys of Eker males treated for up to 14 days with the genotoxic carcinogen aristolochic acid (AA) or the non-genotoxic carcinogen ochratoxin A (OTA). The Eker rat, heterozygous mutant for the tuberous sclerosis 2 (Tsc2) tumor suppressor gene, is a model to study renal carcinogenesis.

title: Hypoxia and lymphathic endothelial cells
description: Analysis of lymphatic endothelial cells (LECs) subjected to hypoxia or treated with conditioned media from lung carcinoma cells grown under hypoxic conditions. LECs contribute to tumor metastasis.

title: Immune-resistant cancer cell line
description: Analysis of a highly immune-resistant cancer cell line. The resistant cell line is produced by subjecting a susceptible cell line to multiple rounds of in vivo immune selection. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying tumor immune evasion.

title: Hematopoietic stem cell response to uridine triphosphate: time course
description: Analysis of CD34+ hematopoietic stem cells treated for up to 24 hours with uridine triphosphate.

title: Embryonic stem cells and embryoid bodies (MG-430A)
description: Comparison of J1 embyronic stem cells and J1 embryoid bodies. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms responsible for maintaining the embryonic stem cell phenotype.

title: Embryonic stem cells and embryoid bodies (MG-430B)
description: Comparison of J1 embyronic stem cells and J1 embryoid bodies. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms responsible for maintaining the embryonic stem cell phenotype.

title: T-cell prolymphocytic leukemia with inv(14)(q11q32)
description: Analysis of T-cell prolymphocytic leukemia (T-PLL) cells with the cytogenetic abnormality inv(14)(q11q32). T-PLL is a rare aggressive lymphoma derived from mature T cells. Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of T-PLL.

title: High fat diet effect on the small intestine of an obesity-prone strain
description: Analysis of small intestines of A/J and C57BL/6J animals on a low or high fat diet. The A/J strain is resistant to obesity, C57BL/6J is prone. Results provide insight into the factors contributing to the susceptibility to obesity.

title: Interspecies variations in response to environmental stresses: time course
description: Analysis of four closely related yeast species subjected to various durations of one of several environmental stresses. Results provide insight into the mechanisms driving the evolution of gene expression.

title: Huntington's disease models
description: Comparison of striatal cells harboring a mutant huntingtin protein with 111 glutamines to wild type striatal cells treated with 3-nitropropionic acid (3-NP). The size of the polyglutamine tract in huntingtin is correlated with mitochondrial function. 3-NP is a respiratory chain inhibitor.

title: Huntington's disease transgenic model: time course
description: Analysis of brains of R6/1 transgenic animals at 18 to 27 weeks of age. The R6/1 transgenic animal expresses exon 1 of the mutant human huntingtin gene that contains 115 CAG trinucleotide repeats. Results provide insight into the early pathogenesis of HD.

title: Diethylstilbestrol effect on pituitary glands of males of various inbred strains
description: Analyis of anterior pituitary glands of ACI, Copenhagen, and Brown Norway males following treatment with the synthetic estrogen diethylstilbestrol (DES).

title: Caffeine effect: time course and dose response
description: Analysis of cells treated with a low dose of caffeine at 2 mM or a high one at 20 mM for 5 , 15, or 90 minutes. Caffeine is a natural purine analogue that elicits pleiotropic effects leading to cell death.  Results provide insight into the mechanism of action of caffeine.

title: Aging liver
description: Analysis of livers of Fisher F344/N males at 32, 58, and 84 weeks of age. Results provide insight into age-associated changes in the capacity of the liver to metabolize xenobiotic compounds.

title: Liver reponse to an atherogenic diet and atorvastatin treatment
description: Analysis of livers of C57B/L females fed an atherogenic diet for 10 weeks, with the last 3 weeks of the diet combined with atorvastatin treatment. Atorvastatin is a statin used for lowering cholesterol.

title: Various brain regions of several inbred strains
description: Analysis of 5 different brain regions from 6 inbred strains. Results provide insight into strain-specific and brain region-specific patterns of gene expression.

title: Colorectal cancer markers in plasma
description: Analysis of blood plasma from patients with colorectal cancer. Results used to identify gene markers for colorectal cancer.

title: Tremorogenic chemical harmane effect on astrocytes
description: Analysis of astrocytes treated with the tremorogenic chemical harmane. Increased blood harmane concentration is associated with an increased risk of essential tremor. Astrocyte dysfunction is associated with neurodegenerative diseases.

title: Testosterone effect on skeletal muscles of HIV-infected males experiencing weight loss
description: Analysis of skeletal muscles of HIV-infected males experiencing weight loss after treatment with testosterone. HIV-associated wasting and weight loss are clinically significant concerns. Results provide insight into androgen action and the potential of anabolic therapies for wasting and sarcopenia.

title: Wilms' tumor suppressor (WT1) targets: time course
description: Analysis of U2OS osteosarcoma cells at various time points up to 12 hours following induction of a tetracycline-repressible Wilms' tumor 1 (WT1) gene encoding the -KTS isoform. WT1 encodes a zinc finger transcription factor that is involved in organ development.

title: Ascending aortic aneurysms
description: Analysis of aneurysmal tissue from ascending aortas of patients with normal tricuspid aortic valves or abnormal bicuspid aortic valves (BAVs). BAV is a congenital anomaly associated with an increased risk for ascending aortic aneurysm (AscAAs). Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of AscAA.

title: Testis response to histone deacetylase inhibitor trichostatin A: time course
description: Analysis of testes at various time points up to 10 hours following subcutaneous injection of the histone deacetylase inhibitor trichostatin A (TSA). TSA treatment is followed by infertility due to the apoptosis of pachytene spermatocytes.

title: Diethylstilbestrol effect on the prepubertal uterus: dose response
description: Analysis of uteri of prepubertal animals treated with diethylstilbestrol (DES) at doses of 1, 10, or 1000 ug/kg/day. DES treatment of neonates results in the development of uterine adenocarcinomas. Results provide insight into the mechanisms underlying the initiation of DES-induced carcinogenesis.

title: Various weak organic acids effect on anaerobic yeast chemostat cultures
description: Analysis of anaerobic chemostat cultures of Saccharomyces cerevisae exposed to one of several weak organic acids. Weak organic acids are used as preservatives in food and beverages. Yeasts are able to proliferate at the maximum legal dosage of such preservatives.

title: Megakaryocytic differentiation: time course
description: Temporal analysis of phorbol ester-treated CHRF-288-11 megakaryoblastic cells induced to undergo megakaryocytic (Mk) differentiation and primary Mk (PriMk) cells derived from cytokine-treated CD34+ peripheral blood cells. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying megakaryopoiesis.

title: 2,3,7,8-tetrachlorodibenzo-p-dioxin effect on the ovary: dose response (I)
description: Analysis of ovaries following exposure to 2,3,7,8-tetrachlorodibenzo-p-dioxin (TCDD) at concentrations of up to 100 parts per billion (ppb). TCDD is a reproductive toxicant and endocrine disruptor in vertebrates. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying TCDD toxicity.

title: 2,3,7,8-tetrachlorodibenzo-p-dioxin effect on the ovary: dose response (II)
description: Analysis of ovaries following exposure to 2,3,7,8-tetrachlorodibenzo-p-dioxin (TCDD) at concentrations of up to 100 parts per billion (ppb). TCDD is a reproductive toxicant and endocrine disruptor in vertebrates. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying TCDD toxicity.

title: Aging lungs and genetic background
description: Analysis of lungs of C57BL/6J and DBA/2J animals at up to 26 months of age. Aging lungs of C57BL/6J and DBA/2J strains differ in physiology and morphometry. Results provide insight into the influence of genetic background on the variability of age-dependent changes in lung structure and function.

title: Cis-urocanic acid effect on keratinocytes
description: Analysis of keratinocytes treated with cis-urocanic acid (UCA). UCA is an epidermal chromophore that undergoes trans to cis photoisomerization following ultraviolet radiation exposure. Results provide insight into the effect of cis-UCA on the cell-mediated immune response in the skin.

title: Rheumatoid arthritis and osteoarthritis: synovial fibroblasts
description: Comparison of synovial fibroblasts from patients with rheumatoid arthritis (RA) to those with osteoarthritis (OA). RA is characterized by chronic inflammation and destruction of multiple joints. OA is a degenerative disease resulting from the breakdown of cartilage.

title: TGF-beta effect on normal and tumor cell lines: time course
description: Analysis of normal lung epithelial HPL1D cells and lung adenocarcinoma A549 cells treated with TGF-beta for up to 12 hours. TGF-beta inhibits growth and promotes apoptosis in normal epithelial cells but acts as a pro-tumor cytokine by promoting tumour angiogenesis, immune-escape, and metastasis.

title: Gingival epithelial cell line response to commensal and opportunistic oral microbial species
description: Analysis of gingival epithelial HIGK cells co-cultured with the the oral commensal Streptococcus gordonii or the opportunistic commensal Fusobacterium nucleatum. Results provide insight into the mechanisms underlying the adaptation of hosts to commensals.

title: PPARalpha deficient small intestine response to fasting
description: Analysis of PPARalpha deficient small intestines after a 24 hour fast. PPARalpha is a fatty acid-activated transcription factor. Results provide insight into transport function and phase I/II metabolism in the small intestine during fasting and the role of PPARalpha in the response to fasting.

title: Allergic contact dermatitis: time course
description: Analysis of skin biopsies from nickel-allergic patients whose skins were exposed to nickel, a sensitizing hapten, for up to 96 hours to elicit allergic contact dermatitis (ACD). Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying the pathogenesis of ACD.

title: Neural retina leucine zipper deficiency effect on retinas: time course
description: Analysis of retinas of mutants lacking the rod photoreceptor-specific neural retina leucine zipper protein (Nrl), at up to 2 months of age. In the absence of Nrl, rods are missing and cones increase in number. Results provide insight into the differences between the two photoreceptor subtypes.

title: Olfactory marker protein deficiency effect on the olfactory epithelium
description: Analysis of heterozygous and homozygous olfactory marker protein (OMP) null olfactory epithelial cells. OMP is expressed only in mature olfactory sensory neurons (OSNs). Results provide insight into the function of OMP.

title: IFN-gamma and IL-1beta effect on thyroid epithelial cells (HG-U133A)
description: Analysis of thyroid epithelial cells (TECs) treated with IFN-gamma, IL-1beta, or both. Fas-mediated apoptosis plays a role in the pathogenesis of autoimmune thyroid diseases. TECs are resistant to Fas-mediated apoptosis, but the resistance is overcome by pretreatment with IFN-gamma and IL-1beta.

title: IFN-gamma and IL-1beta effect on thyroid epithelial cells (HG-U133A 2.0)
description: Analysis of thyroid epithelial cells (TECs) treated with IFN-gamma, IL-1beta, or both. Fas-mediated apoptosis plays a role in the pathogenesis of autoimmune thyroid diseases. TECs are resistant to Fas-mediated apoptosis, but the resistance is overcome by pretreatment with IFN-gamma and IL-1beta.

title: Dendritic cell response to TGF-beta1: time course
description: Analysis of dendritic cells (DCs) at various time points up to 36 hours following treatment with TGF-beta1. DCs derived from CD34+ hematopoietic progenitor cells induced to differentiate in vitro. Results provide insight into the role of TGF-beta1 in DC development.

title: Down syndrome: brain
description: Analysis of postmortem brains of individuals with Down syndrome. Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of Down syndrome.

title: Trib1-deficient macrophage response to lipopolysaccharide
description: Analysis of Trib1-deficient macrophages treated with lipopolysaccharide (LPS). Trib1 is a serine/threonine kinase-like protein. LPS activates toll-like receptors (TLRs) to stimulate host immune responses. Results provide insight into the function of Trib1 in TLR-mediated responses.

title: Islet amyloid polypeptide effect on pancreatic cell line: time course and dose response
description: Analysis of MIN6 pancreatic beta-cells treated for up to 24 hours with various concentrations of human islet amyloid polypeptide (IAPP). IAPP aggregration contributes to the development of islet amyloidosis in type 2 diabetes. IAPP oligomers are associated with pancreatic beta-cell apoptosis.

title: Diet-induced obesity model: epididymal fat tissue
description: Comparison of epididymal fat tissues from diet-induced obese (DIO) and lean animals. DIO animals were fed a high fat, high sucrose diet to induce obesity.

title: Colorectal adenoma formation
description: Analysis of colorectal adenomas and normal mucosas from 32 patients. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying the formation of colorectal adenomas.

title: Pancreatic development (MG-U74A)
description: Analysis of pancreatic tissues from NMRI animals from embryonic day E12.5 to E16.5. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying the development of the pancreas.

title: Pancreatic development (MG-U74B)
description: Analysis of pancreatic tissues from NMRI animals from embryonic day E12.5 to E16.5. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying the development of the pancreas.

title: Pancreatic development (MG-U74C)
description: Analysis of pancreatic tissues from NMRI animals from embryonic day E12.5 to E16.5. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying the development of the pancreas.

title: Hypoxia effect on peripheral blood lymphocytes
description: Analysis of peripheral blood lymphocytes (PBL) subjected to hypoxia in vitro. PBL were grown at 1% or 20% ambient oxygen.

title: Rheumatoid arthritis response to anti-tumor necrosis factor treatment: whole blood
description: Analysis of whole blood samples from rheumatoid arthritis (RA) patients following anti-tumor necrosis factor therapy. Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of RA and the molecular mechanisms associated with the response to anti-TNF treatment.

title: KIN10 kinase transcriptional induction effect on mesophyll cells
description: Analysis of mesophyll protoplasts following transcriptional induction of the KIN10 (At3g01090) kinase. Results provide insight into the function of KIN10.

title: Mycobacterium tuberculosis-derived lipopeptide effect on monocytes and dendritic cells: time course
description: Analysis of monocytes (MOs) and MO-derived dendritic cells (DCs) for up to 24 hours following Mycobacterium tuberculosis-derived lipopeptide treatment. Toll-like receptor activation by bacterial lipopeptides reduced the viability of M. tuberculosis in MOs and macrophages but not MO-derived DCs.

title: Estrogen-related receptor beta mutation effect on the stria vascularis
description: Analysis of the stria vascularis (SV) of estrogen-related receptor beta mutants (ERR-beta; NR3B2). Results provide insight into the role of ERR-beta in the development of endolymph-producing cells of the inner ear.

title: Roux-en-Y gastric bypass model
description: Analysis of subcutaneous abdominal fat and hypothalami of male Sprague-Dawleys that lost or regained weight after Roux-en-Y gastric bypass (RYGB) surgery. Obesity induced by diet prior to RYBG. Results provide insight into the mechanisms contributing to successful weight loss following RYBG.

title: Resting and activated natural killer cells
description: Analysis of resting and activated natural killer (NK) cells. Activated NK cells can use the granule exocytosis pathway to kill target cells upon recognition, resting NK cells are minimally cytotoxic. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the cytotoxicity displayed by NK cells.

title: Tumor suppressor PTEN depletion effect on various cell lines
description: Analysis of A431, HCC827, and SKBR-3 carcinoma cell lines depleted for the tumor suppressor PTEN. Inactivation of PTEN is a common genetic lesion in cancer. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the oncogenic phenotypes resulting from PTEN deficiency.

title: Granulocyte colony-stimulating factor mobilized leukocytes
description: Analysis of leukocytes from individuals before and after the administration of granulocyte colony-stimulating factor (G-CSF). G-CSF is used to boost granulocyte counts in immunocompromised patients. Results provide insight into the effect of G-CSF on the immune system.

title: Marfan syndrome: cultured skin fibroblasts
description: Analysis of cultured skin fibroblasts prepared from patients with Marfan syndrome (MFS). MFS is a heritable connective tissue disorder caused by mutations in the fibrillin-1 gene. Results provide insight into the molecular pathogenesis of MFS.

title: Male and female thymi response to aging and caloric restriction (A)
description: Analysis of thymi from 17 to 743 day-old males and females on a calorie-restricted or ad libitum diet. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the loss of thymic function with age and the influence of gender and diet on this loss.

title: Male and female thymi response to aging and caloric restriction (B)
description: Analysis of thymi from 17 to 743 day-old males and females on a calorie-restricted or ad libitum diet. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the loss of thymic function with age and the influence of gender and diet on this loss.

title: Vincristine-sensitive and resistant ovarian carcinoma cell lines
description: Analysis of the vincristine-sensitive SKOV3 ovarian carcinoma cell line and its vincristine-resistant derivative. Vincristine is a chemotherapeutic agent used for the treatment of cancer. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying the emergence of multidrug resistance.

title: Retinal pigment epithelium development
description: Analysis of retinal pigment epithelia (RPE) of E7 to E18 embryos. The RPE regulates transport between the neural retina and fenestrated capillaries of the choroid, a vascular layer between the retina and sclera. Results provide insight into the extent of remodeling of the RPE during development.

title: Embryonic heart response to retinoic acid and dioxin: time course
description: Analysis of hearts from embryos treated for up to 12 hours with retinoic acid (RA) or 2,3,7,8 tetrachlorodibenzo-p-dioxin (TCDD). Zebrafish embryos treated with RA or TCDD develop cardiac malformation and heart failure.

title: Resveratrol effect on lung carcinoma cell line
description: Analysis of lung carcinoma A549 cells treated with resveratrol. Resveratrol is a phytoestrogen found in red wine. Results provide insight into protective effect of resveratrol against lung cancer.

title: Bar1-deficient mating type a cells response to alpha mating factor: time course and dose response
description: Analysis of mating response of W303 bar1delta a-type cells treated for up to 150 minutes with various concentrations of alpha mating factor pheromone. BAR1 encodes an aspartyl protease that cleaves the alpha factor to inactivate it. The alpha factor induces the cell cycle arrest during mating.

title: Large intestine lacking intestinal flora
description: Analysis of large intestines of animals lacking intestinal flora. Results provide insight into the role of the intestinal flora in the development and function of the host immune system in the large intestine.

title: Polyamide-chlorambucil conjugate 1R-Chl effect on leukemia cell line
description: Analysis of leukemia K562 cells treated with the polyamide-chlorambucil conjugate 1R-Chl. 1R-Chl down-regulates transcription of the human histone H4c gene and inhibits the growth of several cancer cell lines in vitro.

title: Hemiasterlin analog HTI-286 effect on docetaxel-resistant prostate cancer cell line
description: Analysis of prostate cancer LNCaP cells treated with the chemotherapeutic agent docetaxel or the hemiasterlin analog HTI-286. Like docetaxel, HTI-286 disrupts microtubule dynamics. But unlike docetaxel, HT-286 exhibits reduced multidrug resistance.

title: Vitamin E supplementation effect on aged heart
description: Analysis of hearts of 30-month-old B6C3F1 animals fed a diet supplemented with alpha-tocopherol alone or in combination with gamma-tocopherol. Vitamin E supplementation initiated at 15 months of age.

title: Vitamin E supplementation effect on aged brain
description: Analysis of brains of aged (30-month-old) B6C3F1 animals fed a diet containing alpha-tocopherol alone or in combination with gamma-tocopherol. Both of these vitamin E homologs exhibit anti-inflammatory properties. Results provide insight into the effects of vitamin E supplementation on aged brain.

title: TGF-beta overexpression effect on the cornea
description: Analysis of corneas from transgenics overexpressing transforming growth factor-beta (TGF-beta). The transgenics developed corneas that were opaque, vascularized, and lacking sensory nerves. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying normal corneal development.

title: TGF-beta 1 effect on immortalized ovarian surface epithelial cell line: time course
description: Analysis of immortalized ovarian surface epithelial (IOSE) cells treated for up to 12 hours with transforming growth factor beta 1 (TGFb1). IOSE cells are derived from normal ovarian epithelial cells which, unlike ovarian cancer, respond to TGFb1-induced growth inhibition.

title: Ultrafine particles effect on ovalbumin-sensitized lungs
description: Analysis of lungs from ovalbumin-sensitized BALB/cJ animals exposed to ultrafine carbon particles (UCP). Ovalbumin-sensitized animals are models for allergic asthma. Results provide insight into the effect of ultrafine particle inhalation on development and progression of allergic asthma.

title: Host bladder urothelial response to intracellular bacterial communities
description: Analysis of urothelial cells distal to or proximal to sites of intracellular bacterial communities (IBCs) of uropathogenic Escherichia coli (UPEC) in infected bladders. UPEC is the primary cause of urinary tract infection in women. Results provide insight into localized urothelial responses to IBCs.

title: Multiple sclerosis: brain
description: Analysis of brains of individuals afflicted with multiple sclerosis (MS), a primary demyelinating disease of the central nervous system. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying MS pathogenesis.

title: T-dependent and T-independent germinal center B cells
description: Comparison of T-dependent (TD) and T-independent (TI) germinal center B cells from animals 4 days after immunization. The TD animals were carrier-primed 5 weeks earlier so that T-cell help was not limiting. Results provide insight into molecular differences between TD and TI germinal center B cells.

title: Embryos of various inbred lines: time course
description: Analysis of 5 and 8 hour embryos from 9 inbred lines. Results provide insight into the extent of gene expression variation in natural populations during early development.

title: CD11b-plus CD11c-minus macrophages of the intestinal lamina propria
description: Comparison of CD11b+ CD11c- macrophages of the small intestinal lamina propria and the spleen. The intestinal immune system responds robustly to pathogens yet remains tolerant to commensals and food antigens. Results provide insight into the role of intestinal macrophages in immune tolerance.

title: Triclosan effect on Staphylococcus aureus: time course
description: Analysis of Staphylococcus aureus cultures treated for 10 or 60 minutes with 0.05 uM triclosan. At this concentration, the antimicrobial agent caused growth inhibition for about 10 min. Results provide insight into the initial molecular response of Staphylococcus aureus to triclosan.

title: Beta-catenin inactivation effect on intestinal crypts
description: Analysis of intestinal crypts following inactivation of beta catenin. The mucosa of the intestine is composed of submucosal invaginations called intestinal crypts. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying crypt loss as a result of beta-catenin inactivation.

title: Comparison of Rho kinase inhibitor and atorvastatin effects on primary cell lines
description: Analysis of three primary cell lines treated with Rho kinase (ROCK) 2 inhibitor SLx-2119 or with atorvastatin. Effects of ROCK inhibitors overlap to some extent with the pleiotropic (nonlipid lowering) effects of statins. Results suggest possible synergistic effects between the two classes of drugs.

title: Paeoniflorin effect on lymphoma cell line: time course
description: Analysis of U937 lymphoma cells at various time points up to 6 hours following treatment with paeoniflorin (PF). PF, isolated from paeony roots, causes apoptosis and is a chemical heat shock protein (HSP) inducer. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms of action of this compound.

title: Small intestine postnatal development
description: Analysis of ilea from animals at postnatal days 4 to 32. During the early postnatal period, lymphocytes migrate into the small intestine. Results provide insight into the molecular response of small intestinal epithelial to postnatal lymphocytic migration into the small intestinal mucosa.

title: Cigarette smoking effect on full-term placenta
description: Analysis of full-term placentas exposed to maternal cigarette smoke. The placenta produces and metabolizes steroids and xenobiotics. Results provide insight into the effects of maternal cigarette smoking on the placenta at term, with a focus on xenobiotic- and steroid-metabolizing genes.

title: Hepatoerythropoietic porphyria model
description: Analysis of mutant larvae defective for uroporphyrinogen decarboxylase (UROD) at 56 to 96 hours post-fertilization (hpf). UROD is the fifth enzyme in heme biosynthesis. The UROD mutant is a model for hepatoerythropoietic porphyria (HEP). Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of HEP.

title: Histone deacetylase 5 deficient nucleus accumbens response to cocaine
description: Analysis of nuclei accumbens (NAc) from histone deacetylase 5 (HDAC5) mutants treated with cocaine for 7 days. The NAc is a major brain reward region; loss of HDAC5 causes hypersensitive responses to chronic cocaine. Results provide insight into the role of histone deacetylation in drug addiction.

title: Dystrophin deficiency effect on cardiac muscles: time course
description: Analysis of cardiac muscles from 8-week and 10.5-month-old mdx animals that lack dystrophin. The mdx animal is a model for Duchenne muscular dystrophy. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying the pathogenesis of muscular dystrophy.

title: Deltamethrin and permethrin effect on the frontal cerebral cortex: dose response
description: Analysis of brain frontal cerebral cortices of animals treated with various doses of deltamethrin or permethrin, which are neurotoxic pyrethroids used as insecticides. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying pyrethroid-induced disruption of nervous system excitability.

title: Gentamicin effect on Saccharomyces cerevisiae
description: Analysis of Saccharomyces cerevisiae strain 4073 cultures treated with gentamicin. Gentamicin is an antibiotic used against gram-negative bacterial infections. Its usefulness is limited by nephrotoxicity. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying gentamicin's renal toxicity.

title: NeuroD1 deficiency effect on the pineal gland
description: Analysis of pineal glands of neonates lacking neurogenic differentiation factor 1 (NeuroD1, also referred to as BETA2). NeuroD1 is a member of the bHLH transcription factor family. Results provide insight into the role of NeuroD1 in the pineal gland.

title: c-Jun N-terminal kinase 1 depletion effect on livers of diet-induced obese animals
description: Analysis of c-Jun N-terminal kinase (JNK) 1 depleted livers of diet-induced obese (DIO) animals. The DIO animal is a model of mild obesity and insulin resistance. Results provide insight into the specific role of hepatic JNK1 in contributing to insulin resistance in DIO animals.

title: Histone deacetylase inhibitors effect on osteoblast differentiation
description: Analysis of MC3T3-E1 preosteoblasts treated with the histone deacetylase inhibitor (HDI) trichostatin A, MS-275, or valproic acid for 18 hours under osteogenic conditions. HDIs accelerate osteoblast maturation. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying osteoblast differentiation.

title: House dust mite extract effect on a bronchial epithelial cell line
description: Analysis of H292 bronchial epithelial cells exposed to house dust mite (HDM) extract. More than just a physical barrier, epithelium can produce mediators in response to pathogens and allergens. Results provide insight into the nature of the response of bronchial epithelial cells to HDM allergen.

title: Heat stress effect on an epithelial cell line
description: Analysis of HEp2 epithelial cells subjected to heat stress at temperatures of 37 to 40 degrees C. Results provide insight into the regulatory pathways that control the response to heat stress.

title: Macrophage response to interleukins 1 and 6
description: Analysis of cultured monocyte-derived macrophages (MDM) stimulated with interleukin (IL) 1 or IL-6 for 4 hours. Cytokines IL-1 and IL-6 are not only produced by macrophages but also affect the cells in an autocrine manner. Results provide insight into IL-1 and IL-6 responsive genes in MDMs.

title: Primordial ovarian follicle development
description: Analysis of ovaries with unassembled, primordial, and primary follicles. Abnormal primordial follicle development can cause pathologies such as premature ovarian failure. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying primordial follicle assembly and transition to primary follicles.

title: Kaposi's sarcoma-associated herpesvirus microRNA-K12-11 expression
description: Analysis of cells expressing microRNA (miR) K12-11 from Kaposi's sarcoma-associated herpesvirus. miR-K12-11 shares sequence homology with hsa-miR-155, a miRNA up-regulated in lymphomas and important in B cell development. Results provide insight into the biological activity of miR-K12-11.

title: Hedgehog-induced medulloblastoma model (MG-430A)
description: Analysis of medulloblastoma tumors formed in transgenics by expressing an activated form of Smoothened (Smo). Expression of the activated Smo transmembrane protein results in activation of Hh signaling. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying Hh-related tumorigenesis.

title: Hedgehog-induced medulloblastoma model (MG-430B)
description: Analysis of medulloblastoma tumors formed in transgenics by expressing an activated form of Smoothened (Smo). Expression of the activated Smo transmembrane protein results in activation of Hh signaling. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying Hh-related tumorigenesis.

title: PLAGL2 transcription factor deficiency effect on the embryonic small intestine
description: Analysis of small intestines from 18.5 days post conception embryos lacking the transcription factor Pleomorphic adenoma gene-like 2 (PLAGL2). Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying the defective lipid absorption observed in PlagL2-/- mutant intestine.

title: Interleukin-1 effect on epidermal keratinocytes: time course
description: Analysis of epidermal keratinocytes at various time points up to 48 hours post-interleukin-1 (IL-1) treatment. IL-1 is a proinflammatory and immunomodulatory cytokine that plays a role in inflammatory diseases of the skin. Results provide insight into gene products that mediate the effects of IL-1.

title: DNA methylation inhibitor effect on melanoma cell lines
description: Analysis of six melanoma cell lines treated with the DNA methylation inhibitor 5-aza-2'-deoxycytidine (5AzadC). Results provide insight into the role of epigenetic silencing by DNA methylation in the pathogenesis of melanoma.

title: Mmi1 RNA-binding protein mutant
description: Analysis of mmi1 mutant cells. Mmi1 binds to meiosis-specific mRNAs that contain the DSR region. DSR is a cis-acting element that allows selective removal of the meiosis-specific mRNAs during vegetative growth. Results provide insight into the molecular regulation of meiosis.

title: Cervical cancer response to chemoradiotherapy
description: Analysis of cervical cancer biopsy samples from patients receiving radiotherapy alone or radiotherapy plus concomitant chemotherapy with cisplatin (CRT). Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying the therapeutic response to CRT.

title: Cardiac hypertrophy to overt heart failure transition model
description: Analysis of left ventricle (LV) biopsies of hypertrophic hearts from homozygous hypertensive transgenics TGR(mRen-2) 27 (Ren-2) that either progressed to heart failure (HF) or remained compensated. Results provide insight into molecular changes that occur during the hypertrophy-to-HF transition.

title: Gonadotropin-releasing hormone effect on pituitary organ cultures
description: Analysis of pituitary organ cultures treated with 10 nM gonadotropin-releasing hormone (GnRH) for 6 hours. GnRH is a decapeptide hypothalamic hormone that acts upon GnRH receptors in the pituitary. Results provide insight into GnRH-responsive genes in pituitary organ cultures.

title: Bone morphogenetic protein 4 effect on a stem cell line
description: Analysis of C3H10T1/2 (10T1/2) stem cells committed to the adipocyte lineage by treatment with bone morphogenetic protein 4 (BMP-4), a member of the transforming growth factor-beta superfamily. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying adipocyte commitment in a stem cell line.

title: Early-early stage Duchenne muscular dystrophy: quadriceps
description: Analysis of skeletal muscles from 1.5 to 61 month old children with Duchenne muscular dystrophy (DMD). DMD is a degenerative skeletal muscle disease caused by mutations in the dystrophin gene. Results provide insight into the early phases of DMD pathogenesis and pathophysiology.

title: Age-related hearing loss model: cochlea
description: Analysis of cochleas of 7 and 36 week old DBA/2J animals. The DBA/2J animal suffers from age-related hearing loss (AHL), a progressive disease characterized by an age-associated loss of hair cells and spiral ganglion cells in the cochlea. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of AHL.

title: Small-cell lung carcinoma cell lines of varying sensitivity to a Bcl-2 antagonist
description: Analysis of small-cell lung carcinoma cell (SCLC) lines. Expression profiles compared to the cell lines' sensitivity to the Bcl-2 antagonist ABT-737 and chromosomal gains that include changes in Bcl-2 gene copy number. ABT-737 induces the regression of a fraction of SCLC solid tumors.

title: Saccharomyces cerevisiae response to shift from anaerobic to aerobic growth: time course
description: Analysis of Saccharomyces cerevisiae cultures at various time points up to 120 minutes following a shift from anaerobic to aerobic growth. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying the adaptive response of shifted yeast cells to oxidative stress.

title: Myc deficiency effect on the embryonic heart
description: Analysis of Myc-deficient hearts from embryonic day 13.5 transgenics. The E13.5 Myc-null embryos show normal ventricular size and structure, but decreased cardiac myocyte proliferation. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying Myc-induced cellular proliferation.

title: Quercetin effect on intestinal cell differentiation in vitro: time course
description: Analysis of post-confluent Caco-2 colon cancer cells up to 10 days after treatment with ascorbate-stabilized quercetin, a polyphenol antioxidant compound. Caco-2 cells differentiate after reaching confluency. Results provide insight into quercetin's role in cell-proliferation and -differentiation.

title: Dicer inactivation effect on the embryonic heart
description: Analysis of embryonic day 11.5 hearts inactivated for Dicer, an RNase III endonuclease essential for processing of pre-microRNAs (miRNAs) into the mature form. The mutants died from cardiac failure by E12.5. Results provide insight into the role of miRNA function during cardiac development.

title: Candida albicans effect on endothelial cell line
description: Analysis of HUVEC umbilical vein endothelial cells (EC) exposed to Candida albicans blastopsores. ECs actively participate in the innate defense against microbial pathogens. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying the endothelial stress response to Candida infection.

title: Saccharomyces cerevisiae response to oxidative stress: time course
description: Analysis of Saccharomyces cerevisiae cultures at various time points up to 120 minutes following treatment with the oxidant cumene hydroperoxide (CHP). Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying the response of the yeast S. cerevisiae to oxidative stress.

title: HOXB4 induction effect on embryoid bodies
description: Analysis of ES cell-derived embryoid bodies (EBs) following transcriptional induction of homeobox transcription factor HOXB4. HOXB4 induction increases production of hematopoietic progenitors within EBs. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying HOXB4-induced stem cell expansion.

title: Histone H3 lysine 9 demethylase depletion effect on embryonic stem cells
description: Analysis of embryonic stem (ES) cells following depletion of the histone H3 Lys 9 demethylase genes, Jmjd1a and Jmjd2c. Pluripotent ES cells possess the ability to self-renew indefinitely. Results provide insight into the role of Jmjd1a and Jmjd2c in the maintenance of self-renewal in ES cells.

title: rrf-3 and eri-1 mutants: larvae
description: Analysis of L4 larvae mutant for RRF-3 or ERI-1. RRF-3 and ERI-1 encode proteins required for the accumulation of endogenous secondary siRNAs. Results provide insight into the transcriptional effects caused by the loss of the RRF-3 and ERI-1 proteins and provide further insight into their functions.

title: Corpus luteum response to prostaglandin F2alpha
description: Analysis of corpus lutea (CLs) of animals treated with prostaglandin F2alpha (PGF2alpha). The CL is a transient endocrine gland that produces progesterone, a hormone needed to maintain pregnancy. Results provide insight into the mechanisms underlying the regression of CL mediated by PGF2alpha.

title: Matrix metalloproteinase mutant airway epithelial cells response to Pseudomonas aeruginosa infection: time course
description: Analysis of cultured airway epithelial cells (AEC) from matrix metalloproteinase (MMP) -7 or -10 mutants after P. aeruginosa infection. MMP-7 and MMP-10 are induced by acute P. aeruginosa pulmonary infection. Results provide insight into the roles of the MMPs in the host response to Pseudomonas.

title: Encapsulated Streptococcus pneumoniae strains effect on pharyngeal epithelial cell line
description: Analysis of pharyngeal epithelial cells exposed to various encapsulated strains of Streptococcus pneumoniae. Nasopharynx colonization by S. pneumoniae is mediated by adherence to the respiratory epithelium. Results provide insight into the capsule-dependent host response to pneumococcal adherence.

title: Imatinib effect on K562 leukemia cell line (I)
description: Analysis of K562 leukemia cells treated with 1 uM imatinib for 24 hours. Imatinib is a highly selective and potent growth-inhibitor of BCR/ABL1 expressing cells such as K562. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying BCR/ABL1-mediated leukemogenesis.

title: Imatinib effect on K562 leukemia cell line (II)
