description: Analysis of K562 leukemia cells treated with 1 uM imatinib for 24 hours. Imatinib is a highly selective and potent growth-inhibitor of BCR/ABL1 expressing cells such as K562. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying BCR/ABL1-mediated leukemogenesis.

title: Imatinib effect on K562 leukemia cell line (III)
description: Analysis of K562 leukemia cells treated with 1 uM imatinib for 24 hours. Imatinib is a highly selective and potent growth-inhibitor of BCR/ABL1 expressing cells such as K562. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying BCR/ABL1-mediated leukemogenesis.

title: Imatinib effect on K562 leukemia cell line (IV)
description: Analysis of K562 leukemia cells treated with 1 uM imatinib for 24 hours. Imatinib is a highly selective and potent growth-inhibitor of BCR/ABL1 expressing cells such as K562. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying BCR/ABL1-mediated leukemogenesis.

title: Imatinib effect on K562 leukemia cell line (V)
description: Analysis of K562 leukemia cells treated with 1 uM imatinib for 24 hours. Imatinib is a highly selective and potent growth-inhibitor of BCR/ABL1 expressing cells such as K562. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying BCR/ABL1-mediated leukemogenesis.

title: Imatinib effect on K562 leukemia cell line (VI)
description: Analysis of K562 leukemia cells treated with 1 uM imatinib for 24 hours. Imatinib is a highly selective and potent growth-inhibitor of BCR/ABL1 expressing cells such as K562. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying BCR/ABL1-mediated leukemogenesis.

title: Imatinib effect on K562 leukemia cell line (VII)
description: Analysis of K562 leukemia cells treated with 1 uM imatinib for 24 hours. Imatinib is a highly selective and potent growth-inhibitor of BCR/ABL1 expressing cells such as K562. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying BCR/ABL1-mediated leukemogenesis.

title: Imatinib effect on K562 leukemia cell line (VIII)
description: Analysis of K562 leukemia cells treated with 1 uM imatinib for 24 hours. Imatinib is a highly selective and potent growth-inhibitor of BCR/ABL1 expressing cells such as K562. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying BCR/ABL1-mediated leukemogenesis.

title: Male and female lungs response to hantavirus infection: time course
description: Analysis of male and female lungs at various time points up to 40 days post-infection with Seoul hantavirus. Males and females differ in their susceptibility to several RNA and DNA viruses. Results provide insight into the influence of gender in the response to Seoul hantavirus infections.

title: Fibroblast cell line response to two and three dimensional collagen-glycosaminoglycan culture environments
description: Analysis of IMR-90 fibroblasts cultured in a two- or a three-dimensional collagen-glycosaminoglycan (GAG) environment. The 3-D presentation of collagen-GAG stimulates increased fibroblast remodeling activity. Results provide insight into molecular changes elicited by the 3-D collagen-GAG interface.

title: Various normal tissues
description: Analysis of a range of various normal tissues in mouse, a model organism for the study of development, genetics, behavior, and disease.

title: Cigarette smoking effect on the buccal epithelium
description: Analysis of buccal epithelia from cigarette smokers. Cigarette smoke creates a field of injury in epithelial cells lining the respiratory tract. Results extend the concept of a smoking-induced field of injury beyond intrathoracic (bronchial) epithelia to extrathoracic epithelia that line the mouth.

title: LIGHT overexpressing T cells and a high fat diet effect on the liver
description: Analysis of livers of Lck-LIGHT transgenics fed a high fat diet. Lck-LIGHT animals overexpress LIGHT, a tumor necrosis factor cytokine family member, in T cells and develop hyperlipidemia. Results provide insight into the role of T cells and liver in regulating lipid homeostasis mediated by LIGHT.

title: Acute myeloid leukemia
description: Comparison of leukemic blasts from 26 acute myeloid leukemia (AML) patients with normal hematopoietic cells at a variety of different stages of maturation from 38 healthy donors. Results provide insight into the possible clinical significance of those genes with AML-specific expression changes.

title: Transcription factor Sp3 deficiency effect on the embryonic heart
description: Analysis of hearts from embryonic day 12.5 C57Bl/6 mutants deficient for the zinc finger transcription factor Sp3. C57Bl/6 animals lacking Sp3 die before birth. Results provide insight into the role of Sp3 in the development of the embryonic heart.

title: Methylibium petroleiphilum PM1 response to methyl-tert-butyl ether
description: Analysis of Methylibium petroleiphilum PM1 cultures grown on methyl-tert-butyl ether (MTBE) or ethanol. M. petroleiphilum is an aerobic MTBE-degrading bacterium. The water pollutant MTBE is an additive that increases a fuel's oxygen content. Ethanol is an alternative oxygenate substituted for MTBE.

title: Endometriosis: endometrial endothelial cells
description: Analysis of cultured endometrial endothelial cells derived from the eutopic endometria of patients with endometriosis. Results provide insight into the role of aberrant angiogenesis in the pathogenesis of endometriosis.

title: Ribosomal protein null mutants
description: Analysis of several Saccharomyces cerevisiae mutants each deficient in one of various ribosomal proteins. S. cerevisiae contains many duplicated genes encoding ribosomal proteins. Results provide insight into the unique role of each member of a pair of ribosomal protein paralogs.

title: Multipotent stromal cell expansion in vitro
description: Temporal analysis of cultures of multipotent stromal cells (MSCs) from bone marrow aspirates from 3 donors. On day 2, the MSCs are in transition from lag phase to log phase; on day 7, they are in stationary phase. Results provide insight into the molecular changes in MSCs during in vitro expansion.

title: Estrogen effect on estrogen receptors alpha and beta single knockouts: aorta
description: Analysis of estrogen receptor alpha or beta null aortas of ovariectomized animals treated with estrogen. Estrogen is important in vascular tone regulation and in cardiovascular disease pathophysiology. Results provide insight into the mechanisms mediating the effects of estrogen in blood vessels.

title: Primary hepatocytes and HepG2 liver cells response to various fluoroquinolones
description: Analysis of primary hepatocytes (PHs) and HepG2 liver cells treated with various fluoroquinolones. PHs are used in drug metabolism research, and HepG2 cells are surrogates for PHs. Results provide insight into the differences in the response of PHs and HepG2 cells to xenobiotics.

title: Various brain tumors
description: Analysis of 12 primary brain tumor biopsies with some variation in their histological diagnoses. These results, together with those obtained from miRNA profiling by real-time PCR, provide insight into the relationship between endogenous fluctuations in miRNA and mRNA expression levels.

title: Benzothiadiazole effect on Oryza sativa leaves
description: Analysis of leaves of Oryza sativa plants treated with benzothiadiazole (BTH). BTH is a functional analog of salicylic acid and enhances the resistance of rice to the fungal pathogen Rhizoctonia solani. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying BTH-induced disease resistance.

title: Keloid fibroblast response to hydrocortisone in vitro
description: Analysis of keloid fibroblasts (FBs) treated with 1.5uM hydrocortisone (HC). Keloids are benign dermal tumors that form during protracted wound healing. HC at 1.5uM inhibits collagen and elastin synthesis in normal scar FBs but not in keloid FBs. Results provide insight into keloid pathogenesis.

title: Alcohol sensitivity model
description: Analysis of alcohol resistant and sensitive strains.  Strains generated by artificial selection for alcohol sensitivity over multiple generations. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of alcohol sensitivity.

title: Neutrophil response to aerobic exercise
description: Analysis of neutrophils from healthy males before and after 30 minutes of aerobic exercise. The number of circulating neutrophils increases after exercise. Results provide insight into the molecular response of these immune cells to exercise.

title: Hypertension models: resistance arteries
description: Analysis of small diameter branches of the saphenous artery from spontaneously hypertensive (SHR) and adrenocorticotropic hormone (ACTH)-induced hypertensive animals. The saphenous artery is a resistance artery. Results provide insight molecular mechanisms contributing to hypertension.

title: Age-related aortic vasculopathy model
description: Analysis of thoracic aortas (TAs) of Fischer 344/Brown Norway F1 hybrids (F344xBN) at 3 to 28 months of age. Age is a risk factor for vascular disease. The TAs of F344xBN animals exhibit age-related pathologies. Results provide insight into the mechanisms underlying age-mediated vascular pathology.

title: High fat diet effect on the skeletal muscle: time course
description: Analysis of skeletal muscles of C57BL/6J animals fed a low or high fat diet for 3 or 28 days. Oversupply of lipid to skeletal muscle can result in insulin resistance, a characteristic of metabolic syndrome (MS). Results provide insight into the molecular events underlying the early onset of MS.

title: Cadmium effect on the testis: time course
description: Analysis of testes of animals treated with cadmium chloride for 8 or 20 hours. Cadmium is an environmental pollutant that adversely affects the male reproductive system. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the toxic effect of cadmium on the male reproductive system.

title: Prefrontal cortex during a 24 hour (12 hour light:12 hour dark) cycle
description: Analysis of prefrontal cortices from C57BL/6J animals at 4 Zeitgeber time (ZT) points, 3 and 9 hrs after lights on (ZT3 and ZT9) and 3 and 9 hs after lights off (ZT15 and ZT21). The prefrontal cortex is important in regulating sleep and mood. Results provide insight into genes with diurnal rhythms.

title: not1-2 spt3 double mutant
description: Analysis of not1-2 spt3 double mutant cells. NOT1 encodes the scaffold subunit of the Ccr4-Not transcription factor complex. SPT3 encodes a transcription factor. The temperature sensitive not1-2 mutant exhibits transcriptional defects that are suppressed by the deletion of SPT3.

title: Allergic nasal epithelium response to house dust mite allergen in vitro
description: Analysis of cultured nasal epithelia prepared from healthy and allergic individuals following exposure to house dust mite (HDM) extract in vitro. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying the allergic response of the nasal epithelia to allergens.

title: Skeletal muscle during a 24-hour (12 hour light:12 hour dark) cycle
description: Analysis of gastrocnemius muscles of Wistar animals during a 24-hour period, from zeitgeber time (ZT) 0.25 to ZT 23.75. Results provide insight into baseline patterns of gene expression in normal skeletal muscle within the 24 hour circadian cycle.

title: Liver during a 24-hour (12 hour light:12 hour dark) cycle
description: Analysis of livers of Wistar animals during a 24-hour period, from zeitgeber time (ZT) 0.25 to ZT 23.75. Results provide insight into baseline patterns of gene expression in normal liver within the 24 hour circadian cycle.

title: Gram-positive and gram-negative sepsis: leukocytes
description: Analysis of leukocytes from patients with gram-positive or gram negative sepsis. Results provide insight into the specificity of the host response to gram-positive and gram negative sepsis.

title: Iron overload effect on cardiac and skeletal muscles
description: Analysis of cardiac and skeletal muscles of animals fed a high-iron diet to induce iron overload. The cardiac muscle is a tissue affected by iron overload. Result provides insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying the pathological effect of iron overload on muscle cells.

title: Trim24 deficient hepatocellular carcinoma tumors
description: Analysis of hepatocellular carcinoma (HCC) tumors from animals lacking Trim24 (Tif1alpha). Trim24 is a ligand-dependent nuclear receptor transcriptional co-regulator. Animals lacking Trim24 develop HCC. Results provide insight into the potential role of Trim24 as a liver-specific tumor suppressor.

title: Leukotriene B4 effect on monocytes: time course
description: Analysis of primary monocytes treated for up 16 hours with leukotriene B4 (LTB4) in vitro. LTB4 is a mediator of inflammation. Monocytes express the cell surface receptors BLT1 and BLT2 that mediate the action of LTB4. Results provide insight into the transcriptional response of monocytes to LTB4.

title: Tretinoin effect on promyelocytic leukemia cell line
description: Analysis of promyelocytic leukemia HL60 cells treated with tretinoin (all-trans retinoic acid; ATRA) or vehicle. ATRA induces terminal differentiation or growth arrest in HL60 cells. Results suggest a 90-gene expression signature for this cell culture model of hematopoietic differentiation.

title: Noncancerous hepatic tissues from hepatocellular carcinoma patients with and without venous metastasis
description: Analysis of noncancerous hepatic tissues surrounding tumors from hepatocellular carcinoma (HCC) patients with and without venous metastasis. Results provide insight into the role of the hepatic microenvironment in HCC metastasis.

title: Endometriosis
description: Analysis of ectopic endometrial tissues implanted in the peritoneal cavity of 11 subjects. The growth of endometrial tissue outside of the uterus is called endometriosis. Results provide insight into the molecular pathology of endometriosis.

title: Zinc effect on malignant and non-malignant prostate cell lines: time course
description: Analysis of malignant PC-3 and non-malignant HPR-1 prostate cells treated for up to 6 hours with zinc. Zinc exposure induces apoptosis in PC-3 cells, but not in HPR-1 cells. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying zinc-induced prostatic cell apoptosis.

title: Inflammatory breast cancer: stroma
description: Analysis of stromata surrounding tumors from patients with inflammatory breast cancer (IBC) and invasive non-IBC. This is part of a study that also examines the expression profiles of tumors. Results provide insight into the contribution of the tumor stroma component to the pathogenesis of IBC.

title: Inflammatory breast cancer: tumor
description: Analysis of tumor epithelia from patients with inflammatory breast cancer (IBC) and invasive non-IBC. This is part of a study that also examines the expression profiles of stromata surrounding tumors. Results provide insight into the contribution of the tumor component to the pathogenesis of IBC.

title: Rb null mutant embryonic fibroblast response to cisplatin
description: Analysis of retinoblastoma (Rb) deficient embryonic fibroblasts treated with cisplatin. Rb is a tumor suppressor gene. Cisplatin is a genotoxic chemotherapeutic agent. Results provide insight into the role of Rb in the response of embryonic fibroblasts to cisplatin-induced cytotoxicity.

title: Skeletal muscles of postmenopausal women with and without hormone replacement
description: Analysis of skeletal muscles of postmenopausal women treated with hormone replacement therapy (HRT) or with a placebo. Menopause is accompanied by age-associated changes in muscle structure and function. Results provide insight into the effect of HRT and estrogen deprivation on skeletal muscles.

title: Non-small cell lung carcinoma cell line response to cisplatin
description: Analysis of cisplatin-resistant A549 lung adenocarcinoma cell line treated with cisplatin, a chemotherapy drug. Its cytotoxic effects are likely due to the DNA damage it induces in cells. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying the response of A549 to cisplatin insult.

title: Caloric restriction effect on the aged heart and adipose tissue
description: Analysis of hearts and white adipose tissues of 28 month old male animals fed a calorie restricted diet since 4 months of age. Sustained caloric restriction (CR) extends lifespan in animal models. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of CR-induced lifespan extension.

title: Liver response to a high cholesterol diet and phenobarbital
description: Analysis of livers from animals treated with phenobarbital or fed a high cholesterol diet for 7 days. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying the effects of these exogenous sources on cholesterol homeostasis and drug metabolism.

title: Insulin-resistant polycystic ovary syndrome: muscle
description: Analysis of vastus lateralis muscles from women with insulin-resistant polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS). Insulin resistance in skeletal muscles is a risk factor for the development of type 2 diabetes in women with PCOS. Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of insulin resistance in PCOS.

title: Cimicifuga racemosa extract effect on breast cancer cell line MCF-7
description: Analysis of MCF-7 breast cancer cells treated with a Cimicifuga racemosa extract. Extracts from the C. racemosa rhizome are used as an herbal alternative to hormone replacement therapy for alleviation of postmenopausal disorders. Results provide insight into the extract's molecular mode of action.

title: Stat3 deficiency effect on pulmonary alveolar type II epithelial cells
description: Analysis of type II alveolar cells lacking signal transducer and activator of transcription 3 (Stat3). STAT3 mediates gene expression in response to numerous growth factors and cytokines, playing an important role in many cellular processes. Results provide insight into the role of Stat3 in lung.

title: Suprachiasmatic nucleus response to a light pulse
description: Analysis of suprachiasmatic nuclei (SCNs) of animals exposed to a 30 minute light pulse 1 hour after lights off. Circadian rhythms in mammals are driven by a clock located in the SCN. Results provide insight into the molecular events governing the response of the SCN to photic input.

title: Alpha 2B-adrenoceptor deficient embryo and its placenta
description: Analysis of placentas of embryonic day E10.5 mutant embryos lacking alpha 2B-adrenoceptor (Adra2b). Adra2b-/- deficient embryos develop a defect in fetal and maternal vessel formation in the placenta labyrinth at E10.5. Results provide insight into the role of Adra2b in placental development.

title: Cirrhotic liver response to the antiangiongenic agent Sunitinib
description: Analysis of cirrhotic livers from animals treated with antioangeogenic agent Sunitinib. In cirrhosis, pathological processes such as inflammation and pathological angiogenesis are closely integrated. Results provide insight into the utility of targeting angiogenesis in the treatment of cirrhosis.

title: Hypothalamic hamartoma and central precocious puberty
description: Analysis of hypothalamic hamartomas (HHs) from patients with or without central precious puberty (CPP). HHs are congenital lesions composed of neurons and astroglia often associated with CPP. Results provide insight into the mechanisms that initiate normal puberty.

title: Prostate cancer cell line response to dihydrotestosterone: time course
description: Analysis of LNCaP prostate cancer cells treated with the androgen dihydrotestosterone (DHT). DHT binds to androgen receptor (AR), a ligand dependent transcription factor that plays a key role in prostate cancer. Results provide insight into mechanisms underlying AR-dependent prostate cancer growth.

title: Hypoxia effect on cultured aortic smooth muscle cells
description: Analysis of aortic smooth muscle cells incubated for 16 hrs or 48 hrs under hypoxic conditions (1% or 3%O2). Smooth muscle cell proliferation and survival are modulated by hypoxia. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying oxygen regulation of arterial smooth muscle cells.

title: Various normal tissues
description: Analysis of various normal tissues. Results provide insight into housekeeping and tissue-specific genes.

title: Chronic hypoxia effect on the developing brain
description: Analysis of brain cortices and hypothalami of developing animals subjected to chronic consistent hypoxia (CCH) or chronic intermittent hypoxia (CIH). Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying the long-lasting pathological effects of hypoxia on postnatal brain development.

title: Heart failure: peripheral blood mononuclear cells
description: Analysis of peripheral blood mononuclear cells from chronic heart failure (CHF) patients with ischemic or non-ischemic cardiomyopathy (ICM or NICM). Results provide insight into diagnostic/prognostic markers and CHF gene expression profiles.

title: Letrozole effect on breast cancer tumors
description: Analysis of breast cancer tumors following treatment with letrozole for 14 days. The aromatase inhibitor letrozole is an anti-estrogen drug used to treat postmenopausal women with breast cancer. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanism of action of letrozole in breast cancer.

title: Cardiomyocyte response to biomechanical stretch in vitro
description: Analysis of neonatal ventricular cardiomyocytes subjected to both biomechanical stretch stress and pharmacological (i.e., phenylephrine, PE) induction of hypertrophy. Results provide insight into how mechanical stress is sensed and transduced in cardiomyocytes on the molecular level.

title: Cerebral malaria model
description: Analysis of C57BL/6 and CBA/CaH animals infected with Plasmodium berghei ANKA to induce experimental cerebral malaria (ECM). CM is a complication of P. falciparum infection. ECM in B6 and CBA displays many features of human CM. Results provide insight into the development of treatments for human CM.

title: Ulcerative colitis
description: Analysis of colonic mucosa samples with or without signs of inflammation from patients with ulcerative colitis (UC), a type of inflammatory bowel disease (IBD). Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms contributing to the development of inflammation in UC.

title: Rhizobial bacteroids from determinate soybean root nodules
description: Analysis of bacteroids harvested from soybean nodules at 21 days postinoculation (dpi), a timepoint of maximal nitrogen-fixation activity.  Free-living cells grown in aerobic or microaerobic culture also examined. Results provide insight into the genetic basis underlying the conversion to symbiosis.

title: Rhizobial bacteroids from determinate soybean root nodules: time course
description: Analysis of soybean nodules at 10, 13, 21, and 31 days postinoculation, having relative symbiotic nitrogen-fixation activities of 9, 95, 100, and 61%, respectively. Results provide insight into genes expressed early and late in bacteroid development.

title: Transcription factor sigma54-deficient rhizobial bacteroids from determinate soybean root nodules
description: Comparison of sigma54-deficient mutant strain N50-97 bacteroids with wild type bacteroids, both at 21 days postinoculation. The mutants are able to elicit soybean nodules but unable to carry out symbiotic nitrogen fixation. Results provide insight into the sigma 54 regulon in symbiosis.

title: Stress factor RpoS regulon in exponential-phase bacteria
description: Analysis of rpoS knockout mutants of bacteria K-12 strain MG1655 cells in exponential phase. RpoS, an alternative sigma factor and a stress response regulator, is a major regulator of genes required for stationary phase adaptation. Results provide insight into the role of RpoS in exponential phase.

title: Radioresistant tumor response to ionizing radiation
description: Analysis of nu61 radioresistant tumors following exposure to ionizing radiation. Nu61 tumors derived from the radiosensitive squamous cell carcinoma cell line SCC61. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of acquired tumor radioresistance.

title: Radioresistant tumor response to ionizing radiation: time course
description: Analysis of nu61 radioresistant tumors 5 and 24 hours following exposure to ionizing radiation. Nu61 tumors derived from the radiosensitive squamous cell carcinoma cell line SCC61. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of acquired tumor radioresistance.

title: Radioresistant tumor response to interferons
description: Analysis of nu61 radioresistant tumors following treatment with a mixture of interferons (IFNs) alpha, beta, and gamma. Nu61 tumors derived from the radiosensitive squamous cell carcinoma cell line SCC61. Results provide insight into the role of the IFN signaling pathway in tumor radioresistance.

title: Diesel exhaust inhalation effect on peripheral blood mononuclear cells: time course
description: Analysis of peripheral blood mononuclear cells from individuals exposed to diesel exhaust (DE), a major source of urban fine particulate matter (FPM). Exposure to ambient FPM is associated with cardiovascular disease. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying such health effects.

title: Parkinson's disease: substantia nigra (HG-U133A)
description: Analysis of medial and lateral substantia nigras (SNs) from post-mortem brain samples obtained from individuals with sporadic Parkinson's disease (PD). The SN exhibits extensive tissue damage in PD. Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of PD.

title: Parkinson's disease: substantia nigra (HG-U133B)
description: Analysis of medial and lateral substantia nigras (SNs) from post-mortem brain samples obtained from individuals with sporadic Parkinson's disease (PD). The SN exhibits extensive tissue damage in PD. Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of PD.

title: CA1 and CA3 hippocampal slice cultures response to oxidative stress: time course
description: Anlaysis of CA1 and CA3 hippocampal slice cultures for up to 12 hours following treatment with duroquinone to induce oxidative stress (OS). Neurons in the CA1 region are sensitive to OS, while those in CA3 are resistant. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of this difference.

title: Hearts from low and high capacity runners with and without exercise training
description: Analysis of hearts from low (LCRs) and high capacity runners (HCRs) with or without exercise training. Aerobic capacity is a strong predictor of cardiovascular mortality. Results provide insight into the molecular basis for the difference in inborn aerobic capacity in the LCRs and HCRs.

title: Neonatal lung response to cigarette smoke
description: Analysis of lungs from 2 week old animals exposed to cigarette smoke (CS) daily since birth. During infancy, exposure of humans to CS is associated with decreased lung function and increased incidences of respiratory illnesses. Results provide insight into the neonatal pulmonary response to CS.

title: Quercetin effect on the colonic mucosa
description: Analysis of distal colonic mucosa scraping from animals fed a diet supplemented with quercetin. Quercetin is one of the major flavonoids found in fruits and vegetables and is a component of dietary supplements for humans. Results provide insight into the effect of quercetin on the distal colon.

title: Moderate physical exercise training effect on the heart
description: Analysis of left heart ventricles of animals subjected to a moderate physical exercise regimen that induces cardioprotection. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of this cardioprotective effect.

title: Brown adipose tissue response to fasting
description: Analysis of brown (BATs) and white adipose tissues (WATs) and livers of animals after a 24 hour fast. WAT stores and releases fat in response to nutritional needs, while BAT dissipates fat to produce heat. Results provide insight into the role of BAT in the adaptation to food deprivation.

title: Triclosan-ciprofloxacin cross-resistant Staphylococcus aureus mutant response to triclosan
description: Analysis of Staphylococcus aureus JJ5 mutant strain treated with triclosan. JJ5 is a triclosan-ciprofloxacin cross-resistant strain. Triclosan resistance correlates with ciprofloxacin resistance in several bacteria. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of triclosan resistance in JJ5.

title: Antifungal compound sampangine effect on Saccharomyces cerevisiea
description: Analysis of Saccharomyces cerevisiae cells treated with the antifungal compound sampangine. Sampangine exhibits strong inhibitory activity against opportunistic fungal pathogens such as Candida albicans. Using S. cerevisiae as a model, results provide insight into sampangine's mechanism of action.

title: Metastatic breast cancer cell line response to restored miR-335 expression
description: Analysis of breast cancer LM2 cells transfected with a vector expressing microRNA miR-335. LM2 is metastatic to lung. miR-335 expression is lost as breast cancer cells develop metastatic potential. Restoring miR-335 expression inhibits metastatic cell invasion of lung cancer cells.

title: Breast cancer: histologically normal breast epithelium
description: Analysis of histologically normal breast epithelia of breast cancer patients. Results provide insight into the molecular abnormalities in normal appearing breast epithelium in breast cancer and the roles these abnormalities play in carcinogenesis.

title: Lithium-induced lifespan extension model
description: Analysis of Caenorhabditis elegans worms 48 hours following treatment with lithium. Chronic lithium treatment increased the lifespan of this organism. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of lithium’s effect on lifespan.

title: Colorectal mucosae from various regions of the large intestine
description: Analysis of colorectal mucosae from various regions of the normal large intestine. Results provide insight into the range of variation of gene expression in normal tissues.

title: Various tissues
description: Analysis of 22 different tissues from 10 to 12 week old C57BL/6 animals. Results provide insights into the practice of using housekeeping genes as reference genes.

title: Insectide chlorpyrifos effect on the brain: dose response
description: Analysis of brain frontal lobes of animals treated with chlorpyrifos (CPF) at doses up to 30 mg/kg. Subtoxic exposure to CPF, an organophosphorus insecticide, has long-term adverse effects on brain development. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying these effects.

title: Cerebral malaria model: time course
description: Analysis of brains of C57/B6 and Balb/C animals for up to 6 days following infection with Plasmodium berghei ANKA. Experimental infection of animals with P. berghei ANKA is a model for cerebral malaria (CM). C57/B6 animals are susceptible to cerebral malaria (CM), Balb/C animals are resistant.

title: Staphylococcus aureus response to berberine chloride
description: Analysis of Staphylococcus aureus strain ATCC25923 cells exposed to berberine chloride (BBR) for 45 minutes. BBR is a plant alkaloid that exhibits antimicrobial activities against S. aureus. Results provide insight into mechanisms underlying the response of S. aureus to BBR.

title: GL7 determinant in various B-cell lines
description: Analysis of B-cell lines representing myeloma and Burkitt's lymphoma and exhibiting varied GL7 epitope expression. GL7high B-cells have higher functional activity for producing antibodies and presenting antigens. Results identify a candidate gene responsible for the biosynthesis of the GL7 epitope.

title: Hepatocyte growth factor effect on Met receptor-knockout primary hepatocytes: time course
description: Analysis of Met-deficient hepatocytes treated with HGF for up to 24 hours. HGF/Met signaling controls invasive growth and metastasis in a variety of cancers, including hepatocellular carcinoma. Results identify a Met-dependent gene expression signature that may help elucidate the oncogenic process.

title: Suppressor of cytokine signaling 3 deficiency effect on the regenerating liver
description: Analysis of regenerating livers of animals bearing a hepatocyte-specific Suppressor of cytokine signaling 3 gene (SOCS3) knockout. SOCS3 down-regulates several signaling pathways in multiple cell types. Results provide insight into the role of SOCS3 in liver regeneration.

title: Renal inner medullary collecting duct cells
description: Analysis of inner medullary collecting duct (IMCD) cells isolated from the renal inner medulla. The IMCD is the terminal portion of the kidney's collecting duct system. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying aquaporin-2 regulation and osmotic water permeability in the IMCD.

title: Beta-galactoside alpha-2,6-sialyltransferase deficient mammary tumors
description: Analysis of mammary tumors from animals lacking beta-galactoside alpha-2,6-sialyltransferase (ST6Gal-I). Increased ST6Gal-I expression is reported in several carcinomas including breast carcinoma. Results provide insight into the role of ST6Gal-I in tumor progression.

title: Sorbate effect on Bacillus subtilis: time course
description: Analysis of Bacillus subtilis culture samples taken at various time points following the addition of 3mM potassium sorbate. Sorbic acid is a food preservative that inhibits the growth of bacteria, yeast, and molds. Results provide insight into the response of B. subtilis to sorbic acid stress.

title: Diabetes model: heart
description: Analysis of heart left ventricles of diabetic animals. Diabetes induced by streptozotocin treatment. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying diabetes-induced cardiac dysfunction.

title: Male contraceptive agent Gamendazole effect on the testis: time course
description: Analysis of testes of males treated with gamendazole for up to 24 hours. Gamendazole is a nonhormonal, nonsteroidal, oral indazole carboxylic acid contraceptive agent for males. The gamendazole analog lonidamine was also examined. Results provide insight into the mechanism of action of gamendazole.

title: Dasatinib resistant and sensitive prostatic cancer cell lines
description: Analysis of 16 prostatic cancer cell lines treated with anti-tumor agent dasatinib. The cell lines display sensitivity or resistance to dasatinib.  Results used to define a gene expression profile associated with sensitivity to dasatinib.

title: Inherited cryptorchidism model: fetal gubernaculum
description: Analysis of gubernaculum of cryptorchid (orl) fetuses at various gestational days up to GD20. The orl strain is at high risk for cryptorchidism, or undescended testis, one of the most common congenital anomalies in humans. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying cryptorchidism.

title: Inherited cryptorchidism model: fetal testis
description: Analysis of testis of cryptorchid (orl) fetuses at at various gestational days up to GD19. The orl strain is at high risk for cryptorchidism, or undescended testis, one of the most common congenital anomalies in humans. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying cryptorchidism.

title: Rheumatoid arthritis-related cartilage destruction model: chondrocytes
description: Analysis of chondrocytes treated with a supernatant from SV40 T-antigen immortalized human synovial fibroblasts derived from a patient with rheumatoid arthritis (RA). Results provide insight into the molecular mechanism underlying RA-related cartilage destruction.

title: Reversine effect on myoblast cell line
description: Analysis of C2C12 myoblast cells treated with reversine. Reversine induces dedifferentiation of C2C12 myoblasts and the subsequent redifferentiation to become multipotent mesenchymal progenitor cells. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying reversine's effects.

title: Methotrexate resistant colon cancer cell line
description: Analysis of HT29 derived colon cancer cells resistant to the anticancer drug methotrexate (MTX). Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms contributing to MTX resistance.

title: Cochlea response to mitochondrial DNA mutations
description: Analysis of cochleas of animals carrying a mutator allele of the mitochondrial (mt) Polg DNA polymerase. Accumulation of mtDNA mutations is associated with age-related hearing loss. Results provide insight into the role of mtDNA mutations in the pathogenesis of age-related hearing loss.

title: Preovulatory ovaries: time course
description: Analysis of fish preovulatory ovaries collected during late vitellogenesis, post-vitellogenesis and oocyte maturation. In fish, the post-vitellogenic period is critical for completion of the oogenetic process. Results provide insight into molecular events occurring during the preovulatory period.

title: Transcription factor AP-2 gamma mutation effect on the embryonic skin
description: Analysis of back skin from embryonic day 16.5 animals bearing a mutation in transcription factor AP-2 gamma. The E16.5 AP-2 gamma mutants display abnormal epidermal stratification. Results provide insight into the role of AP-2 gamma in skin development.

title: Treacher Collins Syndrome gene heterozygous mutation effect on embryos
description: Analysis of embryos heterozygous mutant for the Treacher Collins Syndrome (TCS) gene (TCOF1). TCS is a congenital disorder of craniofacial development arising from mutations in TCOF1. Results provide insight into the molecular pathogenesis of TCS.

title: Homeodomain transcription factor EMX2 deficiency effect on the embryonic urogenital epithelium
description: Analysis of urogenital epithelia from embryonic day 10.5 animals lacking the homeodomain transcription factor EMX2. Emx2 null mutants show severe urogenital malformations and die soon after birth due to the absence of kidneys. Results provide insight into the role of EMX2 in urogenital development.

title: Pseudomonas aeruginosa non-mucoid and mucoid strains
description: Analysis of a non-mucoid Pseudomonas aeruginosa strain and a mucoid strain from a cystic fibrosis (CF) patient. P. aeruginosa is an opportunistic pathogen associated with chronic pulmonary infections in CF patients. Non-mucoidity is associated with early stages of CF, mucoidity with late stages.

title: NF-kappaB and phosphotidylinositol 3-kinase inhibitor treated monocytes infected with the human cytomegalovirus
description: Analysis of monocytes treated with an NF-kappaB or a phosphatidylinositol 3-kinase (PI3K) inhibitor and then infected with the human cytomegalovirus (HCMV). Results provide insight into the role of NF-kappaB and PI3K in the activation of monocytes to a proinflammatory state after an HCMV infection.

title: pRb p107 double deficient skin
description: Analysis of skin grafts lacking pRb, p107, or both genes. pRb and p107 belong to the retinoblastoma family important in cell cycle regulation. Results provide insight into the role of p107 in epidermal tumor development when pRb is absent.

title: Confluent and sub-confluent umbilical vein endothelial cell cultures
description: Analysis of umbilical vein endothelial cells grown to sub-confluency or confluency. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying endothelial barrier formation.

title: Transcription factor Ctip2 deficiency effect on brain striata
description: Analysis of brain striata from neonates lacking the transcription factor Ctip2. Ctip2 is expressed by striatal medium spiny neurons (MSN), which are critical in motor control and selectively lost in Huntington's disease. Results provide insight into the role of Ctip2 in MSN differentiation.

title: Lung metastatic breast cancer cell line response to metadherin depletion
description: Analysis of LM2 breast cancer cells depleted for metadherin (MTDH), a cell surface protein in breast tumors that mediates lung metastasis. LM2 cells were grown alone or on a monolayer of lung microvascular endothelial cells. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying MTDH action.

title: Estrogen effect on myometrium of ovariectomized females: time course
description: Analysis of myometria of ovariectomized animals following treatment with estradiol for 6 or 24 hours. Estrogen reduces the increased uterine sympathetic nerve density induced by ovariectomy. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying estrogen-modulated sympathetic innervation.

title: Acute physiologic hyperinsulinemia effect on the skeletal muscle: time course
description: Analysis of skeletal muscles from normal, healthy glucose-tolerant individuals exposed to acute physiological hyperinsulinemia for up to 4 hours. Results suggest a low-grade inflammatory response which may provide insight into the etiology of insulin resistance in type 2 diabetes and obesity.

title: Young and aged skeletal muscles response to long-term vigorous endurance exercise
description: Analysis of skeletal muscles from young and aged individuals undergoing vigorous endurance exercise training for over 4 years. Results provide insight into the effects of endurance exercise on age-related insulin resistance and mitochondrial dysfunction.

title: Chemokine receptor CXCR7 deficiency effect on neonatal semilunar valves
description: Analysis of semilunar valves from neonates lacking the chemokine receptor CXCR7. Most animals lacking CXCR7 die at birth with ventricular septal defects and semilunar heart valve malformation. Results provide insight into the role of CXCR7 in heart valve development.

title: Methoxyacetic acid effect on testis: time course
description: Analysis of testes of males exposed to methoxyacetic acid (MAA) for up to 24 hours. MAA is an in vivo metabolite of ethylene glycol monomethoxy ether, a solvent in industrial and household applications. Results provide insight into the mechanisms underlying the disruption of spermatogenesis by MAA.

title: Photoreceptor degeneration model: retina
description: Analysis of retinas from adult protocadherin 21 (prCAD) mutants. The prCAD mutant is a model for inherited photoreceptor degeneration. prCAD is required for the assembly and integrity of the photoreceptor outer segment. Results compared with those from light damaged retinas (GDS3187).

title: Retina response to acute visible light exposure
description: Analysis of retinas from dark adapted animals following acute exposure to visible light to induce photoreceptor death. Results compared with those from retinas of prCAD mutants, a model for photoreceptor degeneration (GDS3186).

title: Leaf response to paraquat: time course
description: Analysis of Ler ecotype rosette leaves for up to 4 hours following treatment with paraquat. Paraquat is an herbicide that acts as a terminal oxidant of photosystem I. In light paraquat reduces oxygen to the superoxide radical, which subsequently dismutates to hydrogen peroxide.

title: Follicle stimulating hormone suppression effect on the maturing testis
description: Analysis of maturing testes from animals suppressed for follicle stimulating hormone (FSH) activity from age 14 to 18 days.  FSH activity suppressed by treatment with an antibody to FSH (FSHAb). Results provide insight into the role of FSH in Sertoli and male germ cell development.

title: Macrophage response to lipopolysaccharide and interleukin-10 co-treatment: time course
description: Analysis of interleukin-10 (IL-10)-deficient macrophages at various time points up to 30 minutes following co-stimulation with lipopolysaccharide (LPS) and IL-10. LPS elicits an inflammatory response. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying the anti-inflammatory effect of IL-10.

title: Natural killer cell response to interleukin-2 treatment: time course
description: Analysis of resting natural killer (NK) cells and NK cells activated with interleukin-2 (IL-2) for up to 24 hours.  The effector function of NK cells is enhanced by cytokines such as IL-2. Results provide insight into the molecular events in NK cell activation.

title: Rheumatoid arthritis: synovial macrophages
description: Analysis of synovial fluid macrophages from 5 patients with rheumatoid arthritis (RA). The chronic inflammation and progressive joint destruction observed in RA are mediated in part by macrophages. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying RA pathogenesis.

title: Monocyte-derived dendritic cell response to VAF347
description: Analysis of immature monocyte-derived dendritic cells following activation with anti-CD40 antibodies for 8 hours in the presence of VAF347. VAF347 is a low molecular weight compound that inhibits allergic lung inflammation in vivo. Results provide insight into the mechanism of action of VAF347.

title: Medroxyprogesterone acetate effect on the pregnant cervix
description: Analysis of embryonic day 15 (E15) pregnant cervices treated with medroxyprogesterone acetate (MPA). The use of progestational agents such as MPA reduces the incidence of pre-term birth. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying this effect.

title: Hexose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase deficiency effect on skeletal muscles
description: Analysis of skeletal muscles from animals lacking hexose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase (H6PD). H6PD null animals develop severe skeletal myopathy characterized by switching of Type II to Type I fibers. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the myopathy induced by the absence of H6PD.

title: Non-thermal low intensity pulsed ultrasound effect on leukemia cell line
description: Analysis of leukemia U937 cells exposed to non-thermal low intensity pulsed ultrasound (LIPUS) for 6 hours to induce apoptosis. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying the apoptotic response to nonthermal LIPUS.

title: Transcriptional coactivator PGC-1beta hypomorphic mutation effect on the liver
description: Analysis of livers of animals bearing a hypomorphic PGC-1beta mutation. PGC-1beta is a transcriptional coactivator that stimulates mitochondrial biogenesis and respiration of cells. Results provide insight into the function of PGC-1beta in the liver.

title: Abf1 DNA-binding mutant
description: Analysis of temperature sensitive Abf1 mutant cells subjected to a temperature of 37 degrees C to dissociate the mutant protein from its DNA binding sites. Results provide insight into the contribution of this general regulatory factor to transcription genome-wide.

title: Anti-Mullerian hormone effect on ovary
description: Analysis of postnatal day 4 ovaries cultured with anti-Mullerian hormone (AMH) for 10 days. AMH is an extracellular signaling molecule that inhibits the primordial to primary follicle transition in ovary. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying primordial follicle development.

title: Monocyte to macrophage differentiation
description: Analysis of monocytes following up to 168 hours of adherence-induced differentiation. Monocytes differentiate into macrophages, which are critical in the pathogenesis of many diseases. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying monocyte to macrophage differentiation.

title: Chronic loneliness effect on peripheral blood leukocytes
description: Analysis of leukocytes from individuals experiencing chronically high levels of subjective social isolation (loneliness). Social environment is known to influence human health. Results provide insight into transcriptional alterations in the immune system induced by chronic social isolation.

title: Integrin alpha7 overexpression effect on skeletal muscle
description: Analysis of skeletal muscle from transgenic females overexpressing integrin alpha7. Enhancement of alpha7 integrin levels alleviates pathology in a Duchenne muscular dystrophy murine model. Results provide insight into effects of increased integrin alpha7 on skeletal muscle transcription in vivo.

title: Airway epithelial cells response to Sendai virus infection in vitro
description: Analysis of primary culture tracheal epithelial cells following infection with Sendai virus (SeV), a common paramyxovirus.Respiratory paramyxoviral infections are a leading cause of serious respiratory disease. Results provide insight into the role of epithelial cells in antiviral defense.

title: Gingival epithelial cell line response to oral pathogen infections
description: Analysis of gingival epithelial HIGK cells infected with Aggregatibacter actinomycetemcomitans or Porphyromonas gingivalis. A. actinomycetemcomitans and P. gingivalis cause periodontal infections. Results provide insight into differences in epithelial cell responses to these pathogens.

title: 13-cis retinoic acid effect on SEB-1 sebocyte cell line
description: Analysis of cultured sebaceous gland cells (SEB-1 sebocytes) treated with 13-cis retinoic acid (13-cis RA, isotretinoin), a potent acne treatment agent that reduces the size and secretion of sebaceous glands. Results provide insight into the molecular basis for 13-cis RA's acne-clearing effect.

title: Whole seedling roots response to salinity stress: time course
description: Analysis of whole roots from 5-day-old Columbia seedlings subjected to 140 mM NaCl for up to 32 hours. High salinity is an important agricultural contaminant with complex effects on root physiology. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying the salt stress response in whole root.

title: Estradiol effect on breast cancer cell line expressing estrogen receptor: time course
description: Analysis of estrogen receptor (ER)-positive MCF7 breast cancer cells up to 48 hours following treatment with estradiol (E2). ERs facilitate the transcriptional effects of hormones. These results, together with ChIP-PET results, suggest potential correlations between ER binding and gene regulation.

title: 13-cis retinoic acid effect on skin
description: Analysis of upper back skin biopsies of acne patients treated with 13-cis retinoic acid (13-cis RA, isotretinoin), a potent acne treatment agent that reduces the size and secretion of sebaceous glands. Results provide insight into the molecular basis for 13-cis RA's acne-clearing effect.

title: YAP overexpression effect on MCF10A mammary epithelial cell line
description: Analysis of MCF10A mammary epithelial cells overexpressing the transcriptional coactivator YAP.  The Hippo pathway impinges on YAP in mammals to coordinate cell proliferation and apoptosis. Results provide insight into molecular components of the Hippo pathway in mammalian cells.

title: Liver response to human and chimpanzee diets
description: Analysis of livers from NMR-1 females fed human and chimpanzee diets for 2 weeks. Human diet is markedly different from the diets of closely related primate species.  Results provide insight into the influence of different diets on gene expression patterns.

title: Cytotoxic T cell line response to interleukin-2: time course
description: Analysis of cytotoxic T cell line (CTLL-2) at various time points up to 24 hours following interleukin-2 cytokine (IL-2) stimulation. IL-2 regulates T cell proliferation and differentiation. Results provide insight into the expression patterns of IL-2 responsive genes.

title: Interleukin-13 effect on esophageal epithelial cells from eosinophilic esophagitis patients
description: Analysis of primary esophageal epithelial cells from eosinophilic esophagitis (EE) patients following 100ng/mL interleukin-13 (IL-13) stimulation. The T-helper type 2 cytokine IL-13 plays a pivotal role in eosinophilic inflammation. Results provide insight into the role of IL-13 in EE pathogenesis.

title: Heart left ventricle and diaphragm comparison
description: Analysis of normal heart left ventricle and diaphragm of young-adult Sprague Dawley males. Concurrent rhythmic contractions of the diaphragm and heart are needed to sustain life. Results provide insight into transcriptional strategies for ensuring long-term energy supplies in these two muscles.

title: Selenate effect on roots
description: Analysis of roots from 10-day-old plants grown with selenate, the major form of bioavailable selenium (Se) in soil. Plants have the capacity to attenuate the toxic effects of Se.  Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying Se-stress responses and Se tolerance mechanisms in plants.

title: Interleukin-22 effect on colon cultures
description: Analysis of C57BL/6 colon cultures treated with 10 ng/ml of interleukin-22 (IL-22) for 24 hours. IL-22, a member of the IL-10 family of cytokines, can induce a marked antimicrobial response in vitro. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of IL-22 induced host defense mechanisms.

title: Social isolation stress-induced aggression model
description: Analysis of heads of Canton-S males subjected to social isolation (single-housed). Social experience with conspecifics is an environmental influence on aggressiveness common to many species. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the effect of social experience on aggressiveness.

title: Apelin knockout effect on the heart
description: Analysis of hearts from Apelin knockouts (KO) subjected to pressure overload by aortic banding (AB). Banded Apelin KOs develop severe and progressive heart failure. Results provide insight into the role of Apelin in maintaining cardiovascular homeostasis on pressure overload.

title: Transgenic and conventional cultivar comparison
description: Analysis of the first trifoliate leaves of two transgenic and three conventional soybean cultivars. To date, the possibility that transgene expression could lead to unintended effects remains a debated issue. Results provide insight into the overall molecular changes in transgenic soybean cultivars.

title: Fungal pathogen Phakopsora pachyrhizi effect on leaves: time course
description: Analysis of leaves up to 48 hours post-inoculation with Phakopsora pachyrhizi isolates, Hawaii 94-1 (HW94-1) and Taiwan 72-1 (TW72-1). HW94-1 produces a resistant reaction in the host, TW72-1 a susceptible reaction. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of resistance to a fungal pathogen.

title: Lipochitooligosaccharide effect on first trifoliolate leaf
description: Analysis of first trifoliolate leaf from cv. OAC Bayfield plants treated with Bradyrhizobium japonicum lipochitooligosaccharide (LCO, Nod factor).  Foliar application of LCO can induce changes in hormone level and enzymatic activity. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of these effects.

title: Brain response to human and chimpanzee diets
description: Analysis of brains from NMR1 females fed human and chimpanzee diets for 2 weeks. The human diet is markedly different from the diets of closely related primate species.  Results provide insight into the influence of different diets on gene expression patterns in brain.

title: Cervical cancer tumorigenesis
description: Analysis of cervical cancer (CC) primary tumors and cell lines. Chromosomal amplification is a common cellular mechanism of gene activation in tumorigenesis; chromosome 20 is a commonly gained chromosome in CC. Results provide insight into the potential role of chromosome 20 gain in CC progression.

title: Leaf response to fungal pathogen Phakopsora pachyrhizi
description: Analysis of 3-week-old cv. 5601 T plants (V2 growth stage) inoculated with Phakopsora pachyrhizi. This fungal pathogen is the causal agent of Asian soybean rust (ASR), a potentially devastating disease affecting crops. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the host response to ASR.

title: Early maturation-stage seed compartments
description: Analysis of LCM-captured compartments from seeds containing early maturation-stage embryos. Whole seeds at early maturation-stage also examined. The various compartments play distinct roles in seed formation. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms involved in seed development.

title: Globular-stage seed compartments
description: Analysis of LCM-captured compartments from seeds containing globular-stage embryos. Whole seeds at globular-stage and young trifoliate leaves also examined. The various compartments play distinct roles in seed formation. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms involved in seed development.

title: Heart-stage seed compartments
description: Analysis of LCM-captured compartments from seeds containing heart-stage embryos. Whole seeds at heart-stage and young trifoliate leaves also examined. The various compartments play distinct roles in seed formation. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms involved in seed development.

title: Scarlet Runner Bean globular-stage embryo
description: Analysis of LCM-captured globular-stage embryo regions (embryo proper and suspensor). The suspensor helps to transport materials between embryo and seed coat. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms involved in early embryo development.

title: Cotyledon-stage seed compartments
description: Analysis of LCM-captured compartments from cv. Asgrow A3237 seeds containing cotyledon-stage embryos. Whole seeds at cotyledon-stage also examined. The various compartments play distinct roles in seed formation. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms involved in seed development.

title: Effect of host quantitative resistance during Phytophthora sojae infection: time course
description: Analysis of hypocotyls from 8 cultivars, varying in quantitative resistance, up to 120 hours following infection with oomycete pathogen Phytophthora sojae. Mock inoculations spiked with 2-16% P. sojae RNA. Results identify host and pathogen genes differentially expressed during P. sojae infection.

title: Selenate effect on shoots
description: Analysis of shoots from 10-day-old plants grown with selenate, the major form of bioavailable selenium (Se) in soil. Plants have the capacity to attenuate the toxic effects of Se.  Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying Se-stress responses and Se tolerance mechanisms in plants.

title: Phytophthora sojae infection effect on hypocotyl sections: time course
description: Analysis of various hypocotyl sections from resistant and susceptible cultivars up to 120 hours following infection with Phytophthora sojae, an oomycete pathogen that causes root rot. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the different host responses to an oomycete pathogen.

title: S288C cell response to pterostilbene
description: Analysis of strain S288C cells subjected to pterostilbene at the IC50 concentration (70uM) for one generation (3h). Pterostilbene, an analog of resveratrol, is a phytoalexin exhibiting potent antifungal activity. Results provide insight into the molecular pathways affected by pterostilbene.

title: Comparison of tobramycin-treated PA14 biofilm/CFBE and planktonic cultures
description: Analysis of PA14 biofilms grown on cystic fibrosis bronchial epithelial (CFBE) cells and PA14 planktonic cultures treated with tobramycin, a CF antibiotic treatment. Results provide insight into P14 infection in the context of CFBEs and suggest P14's response to tobramycin is growth mode-dependent.

title: Young adult response to Pseudomonas aeruginosa PA14: time course
description: Analysis of strain fer-15(b26);fem-1(hc17) young adults exposed for up to 8 hrs to pathogenic Pseudomonas aeruginosa strain PA14, less pathogenic PA14 mutant gacA, and E. coli strain OP50 (normal food source). Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the response to a bacterial pathogen.

title: MAP kinase PMK-1 and transcription factor DAF-16 deletion mutants
description: Analysis of daf-2(e1368) loss-of-function mutant and daf-2(e1368);pmk-1(km25) and daf-2(e1368);daf-16(mgDf47) double mutants.  PMK-1 and DAF-16 confer enhanced pathogen resistance on daf-2 mutants relative to wild-type. Results suggest DAF-16 and PMK-1 upregulate distinct genes to promote immunity.

title: LIM homeobox Lhx8 deficiency effect on newborn ovaries
description: Wild type newborn ovary RNA was compared to newborn ovary RNA from Lhx8 deficient (-/-) or Nobox deficient (-/-) mice. Results indicate that Lxh8 is a critical factor for maintenance and differentiation of ooyctes during early embryogenesis and it acts in part by down-regulating the Nobox pathway.

title: Held out wing mutant embryos
description: Analysis of mutant embryos lacking both maternal and zygotic Held out wing (HOW), an RNA-binding protein (RBP) highly expressed in the mesoderm during early embryogenesis. how mutant embryos exhibit aberrant mesoderm spreading. Results provide insight into the role of HOW in mesoderm development.

title: Metaphase II stage oocytes matured in vivo
description: Analysis of young, untreated metaphase II (MII) oocytes. Results provide insight into the baseline of genes expressed in in vivo matured oocytes and into the molecular mechanisms underlying biological processes such as oogenesis, folliculogenesis, fertilization, and embryonic development.

title: Cigarette smoking effect on lung adenocarcinoma
description: Analysis of different tumor stage adenocarcinoma and paired normal lung tissues of current, former and never smokers. To date, tobacco smoking is responsible for over 90% of lung cancers. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of lung carcinogenesis induced by smoking.

title: Monocyte-derived macrophage response to decoy receptor 3
description: Analysis of monocyte-derived macrophages (MDMs) treated with decoy receptor 3 (DcR3) recombinant fusion protein. DcR3, a TNF receptor superfamily member, is up-regulated in tumors from diverse lineages. Results provide insight into the role of DcR3 in tumor-associated macrophage (TAM) development.

title: Liver response to Pacific ciguatoxin-1: time course
description: Analysis of adult male C57/BL6 livers exposed to a symptomatic dose of the marine neurotoxin Pacific ciguatoxin-1 (P-CTX-1) for up to 24 hours. Ciguatoxins (CTX) are polyether neurotoxins that target voltage-gated sodium channels. Results provide insight into the hepatic molecular response to CTX.

title: Intestinal tissue xenograft response to pathogen Shigella flexneri infection in vivo
description: Analysis of human intestinal xenotransplants infected with Shigella flexneri (virulent wild-type M90T, virulent mxiE mutant, and avirulent BS176 strains). Virulent S. flexneri are highly contagious enteric pathogens. Results provide insight into the intestinal innate immune response to infection.

title: Pediatric malignant germ cell tumors: yolk sac tumors and seminomas
description: Analysis of yolk sac tumors (YSTs) and seminomas, the two principal histological variants of pediatric malignant germ cell tumors (MGCTs). Seminomas and YSTs are presumed to arise from the same progenitor cell. Results provide insight into the molecular basis for the divergence of pediatric MGCTs.

title: Madin-Darby canine kidney type II cell line response to hepatocyte growth factor
description: Analysis of MDCK cells exposed to hepatocyte growth factor (HGF), a MAPK pathway activator. MDCK cells also exposed to HGF plus MAPK inhibitors. Epithelial organs such as kidney develop via tubulogenesis, a process induced by MAPK activation. Results provide insight into HGF-induced tubulogenesis.

title: Colon epithelial biopsies of ulcerative colitis patients
description: Analysis of inflamed and un-inflamed colon epithelial biopsies of 67 ulcerative colitis (UC) patients from different anatomical locations of the gastrointestinal (GI) tract. Results provide insight into the regional variation of gene expression in UC patients and the pathogenesis of UC.

title: Chromophobe renal cell carcinoma and oncocytoma
description: Comparison of chromophobe renal cell carcinoma (RCC) and benign oncocytoma tumor samples. Malignant chromophobe RCC and benign oncocytoma share  morphologic features. Results provide insight into the molecular differences between the two types of tumors.

title: Tuberous sclerosis complex hamartomas
description: Analysis of tuberous sclerosis complex (TSC) skin hamartomas (angiofibromas and periungual fibromas) with normal-appearing skin from the same patients. Hamartomas overgrow epithelial and mesenchymal cells in TSC skin. Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of TSC hamartomas.

title: Liver transplantation tolerance: peripheral blood mononuclear cells
description: Analysis of peripheral blood mononuclear cells from operationally tolerant liver transplant patients. Operationally tolerant patients are fully immunocompetent but accept grafts without chronic immunosuppression. Results identify a molecular signature for operational tolerance.

title: Estradiol effect on breast cancer cell line: time course
description: Analysis of MCF-7 breast cancer cells treated with estradiol for 3 or 6 hours. Results combined with ChIP experiments to identify estrogen receptor alpha binding sites and estradiol target genes in breast cancer cells.

title: Antimalarial drug chloroquine effect on PfCRT mutant parasite lines
description: Analysis of Plasmodium falciparum chloroquine-resistant transporter (PfCRT) mutants exposed to a low dose of chloroquine (CQ) for 3 h. The clones have different degrees of CQ resistance (CQR). Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the PfCRT effect on parasite susceptibility to CQ.

title: Estrogen effect on breast cancer cell line: time course
description: Analysis of MCF-7 breast cancer cells treated with estrogen for up to 12 hours. Results used in conjunction with estrogen receptor and RNA polymerase II binding data to provide insight into the mechanisms underlying estrogen-regulated gene expression in breast cancer.

title: Fibroblast pseudopodia response to lysophosphatidic acid
description: Analysis of pseudopodia from NIH/3T3 cells extending protrusions in response to LPA, a chemotactic stimulus. Asymmetric distribution of RNAs establishes polarity in multiple cell types. Results provide insight into RNAs that localize in cell protrusions in response to migratory stimuli.

title: Fibroblast pseudopodia response to fibronectin
description: Analysis of pseudopodia from NIH/3T3 cells extending protrusions in response to fibronectin, a haptotactic stimulus. Asymmetric distribution of RNAs establishes polarity in multiple cell types. Results provide insight into RNAs that localize in cell protrusions in response to migratory stimuli.

title: Prostate cancer progression at the cellular level
description: Analysis of LCM-captured epithelial cell populations representing prostate cancer progression from benign epithelium to metastatic disease. Stromal cell populations also examined. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying the different aspects of prostate cancer progression.

title: Interleukin-6 effect on skeletal muscle tissue: time course
description: Analysis of interleukin-6 (IL-6) infused skeletal muscle (SKM) biopsies at time points up to 6hr. IL-6, a cytokine secreted from skeletal muscle during exercise, works in both an autocrine and paracrine manner. Results provide insight into IL-6-induced expression of other secreted factors in SKM.

title: Myelomonocytic lymphoma U937 cell line response to mild hyperthermia
description: Analysis of myelomonocytic lymphoma U937 cells subjected to mild hyperthermia. Mild hyperthermia alone does not induce apoptosis but it does show a synergism with radiotherapy and anti-cancer drugs. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying cellular responses to mild hyperthermia.

title: Preinvasive and invasive cervical squamous cell carcinomas
description: Analysis of LCM-harvested high-grade squamous intraepithelial lesions (HSIL) and invasive squamous cell carcinomas (SCC) from cervices. If left untreated, a subset of the HSILs will progress to SCCs. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying cervical cancer progression.

title: Calcium-signaling effects on blastocyts
description: Analysis of blastocysts receiving reduced (CFW) or excess (20-p) Ca2+ signalling events. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying the differential effect of the CFW and 20-p treatments on the ability of blastocysts to implant or develop post-implantation.

title: CTCF depletion effect in oocytes
description: Analysis of germinal vesicle (GV) oocytes depleted for maternal stores of CTCF by RNA interference (RNAi). Depletion of CTCF, an 11 zinc-finger DNA-binding protein, causes meiotic defects in the egg. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of this observation.

title: Age-associated aneuploidy model
description: Analysis of germinal vesicle (GV)-intact oocytes and metaphase II (MII) eggs obtained from young and old females. An increased incidence of aneuploidy is observed with increasing maternal age. Results provide insight into the molecular basis underlying the age-associated increase in aneuploidy.

title: Transition from anaerobic photosynthesis to aerobic respiration: time course
description: Analysis of the facultative photosynthetic anaerobe Rhodobacter sphaeroides at various time points during the transition from anaerobic-light to aerobic-dark growth conditions. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying the transition from one homeostatic state to another.

title: Stage III serous ovarian adenocarcinomas
description: Analysis of stage III ovarian serous papillary adenocarcinomas from 5-year survivors and deceased patients. Ovarian carcinoma is often not detected until an advanced stage.  Results provide insight into gene expression patterns associated with survival that could have prognostic relevance.

title: Peripheral blood monocyte response to Francisella tularensis infections
description: Analysis of blood monocytes infected with Francisella tularensis tularensis Schu S4 (virulent) or subsp. novicida (less virulent). F. tularensis causes the disease tularemia. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms that enable Francisella to dampen or subvert the host immune response.

title: SOX transcription factor overexpression in embryonic stem cells
description: Analysis of CA1 and CA2 embryonic stem cell (ESC) lines over-expressing transcription factor SOX7 or SOX17, producing extraembryonic endoderm and definitive endoderm progenitors, respectively. Results provide insight into the roles of SOX7 and SOX17 as regulators of endoderm differentiation in ESCs.

title: Cytogenetically normal acute myeloid leukemia_training set (HG-U133B)
description: Analysis of mononuclear cells from bone marrow or peripheral blood from a training set of 163 adult patients with cytogenetically normal acute myeloid leukemia (CN-AML). Patients with CN-AML show heterogeneous treatment outcomes. Results provide insight into a prognostic gene signature for CN-AML.

title: Cigarette smoking effect on the nasal epithelium
description: Analysis of nasal epithelia from cigarette smokers. Cigarette smoke creates a field of injury in epithelial cells lining the respiratory tract. Results extend the concept of a smoking-induced field of injury beyond intrathoracic (bronchial) epithelia to extrathoracic epithelia that line the nose.

title: Cytogenetically normal acute myeloid leukemia_training set (HG-U133A)
description: Analysis of mononuclear cells from bone marrow or peripheral blood from a training set of 163 adult patients with cytogenetically normal acute myeloid leukemia (CN-AML). Patients with CN-AML show heterogeneous treatment outcomes. Results provide insight into a prognostic gene signature for CN-AML.

title: Tibolone hormone effect on postmenopausal endometrium
description: Comparison of endometria after short-term treatment with tibolone, estradiol (E2), or E2 + medroxyprogesterone acetate (E2 + MPA) in healthy postmenopausal women undergoing hysterectomy. A synthetic steroid, Tibolone is used as an alternative for estrogen or estrogen/progesterone hormone therapy.

title: Estradiol effect on breast cancer cell line in the absence of protein synthesis
description: Analysis of MCF-7 breast cancer cells treated with estradiol (E2) and cycloheximide, an inhibitor of protein synthesis (PS). Primary E2 targets are regulated by E2 in the absence of de novo PS. Results provide insight into mechanisms underlying primary and secondary E2 target gene regulation.

title: Leptin deficiency effect on lungs
description: Analysis of lungs from leptin-deficient (ob/ob) mutants treated with saline or leptin. Leptin deficiency results in low lung volumes and an attenuated chemical control of breathing. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms by which leptin alters respiratory system structure and function.

title: Sickle cell disease: platelets
description: Analysis of platelets from patients with sickle cell disease. Sickle cell disease patients exhibit increased activation of platelets. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of platelet dysfunction in sickle cell disease.

title: Thyroid carcinoma models
description: Analysis of 2, 6, and 10 month old transgenic (Tg) thyroids expressing RET/PTC3 fusion gene or E7 human papillomavirus 16 oncoprotein. The two Tg populations with different initiating mutations both develop thyroid carcinoma. Results provide insight into the different steps leading to carcinoma.

title: Lmx1b knockout effect on embryonic proximal hindlimb buds
description: Analysis of embryonic (e11.5) proximal hindlimb bud tissues deficient for transcription factor Lmx1b. In the developing limb, dorsal-ventral patterning is controlled by LMX1B, expressed in the dorsal mesenchyme. Results provide insight into the Lmx1b-dependent genes in the developing limb bud.

title: c-Myc transgenic model of lung adenocarcinomas
description: Analysis of cancerous lungs of transgenics overexpressing the c-Myc proto-oncogene in their alveolar epithelia. This overexpression results in bronchiolo-alveolar carcinoma and papillary adenocarcinoma. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms by which c-Myc effects tumorigenesis.

title: Beta-catenin deficiency model: kidney
description: Analysis of embryonic (E12.5) kidneys with beta-catenin deficiency targeted to the ureteric bud cell lineage. Inactivation of beta-catenin leads to abnormal ureteric branching and causes renal aplasia or dysplasia. Results provide insight into the role of beta-catenin during ureteric morphogenesis.

title: Na+/H+ exchanger 3 deficiency effect on the colon
description: Analysis of mutant colons lacking Na+/H+ exchanger 3 (NHE3). NHE3 provides a major route for intestinal Na+ absorption. NHE3 deficient animals develop colitis restricted to the distal colonic mucosa. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of colitis development induced by NHE3 deficiency.

title: Stromal cells and invasive breast cancer development
description: Analysis of epithelium and stroma cells in normal and invasive breast cancer tissues. Information on the role that stroma tissues have on the growth and progression of cancer is limited.Results provide insights into the molecular basis of cancer invasion and metastasis.

title: Cytogenetically normal acute myeloid leukemia_test set
description: Analysis of mononuclear cells from bone marrow or peripheral blood from a test set of adult patients with cytogenetically normal acute myeloid leukemia (CN-AML). CN-AML patients show heterogeneous treatment outcomes. Results provide insight into the prognostic value of a gene signature for CN-AML.

title: Methotrexate-resistant HT29 colon adenocarcinoma cell line
description: Analysis of HT29 colon cancer cells sensitive or resistant to methotrexate (MTX). MTX is used in the treatment of cancer. Chemotherapy effectiveness in cancer cells is compromised by development of drug resistance. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms associated with drug resistance.

title: Transcription factor paired box 3 knockin embryos: palate
description: Analysis of E14.5 palatal shelves of knockin mutants expressing developmentally-regulated transcription factor Pax3 beyond the time at which it is normally shut off. Cleft palate observed in newborns persistently expressing Pax3. Results provide insight into the role of Pax3 in palate development.

title: Wine fermentation effect on yeast: time course
description: Analysis of Saccharomyces cerevisiae, strain Vin13, subjected to ethanol levels up to 10% during a 15-day wine fermentation. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying the adaptive response of yeast to the long-term environmental stresses present during alcoholic fermentation.

title: Porphyromonas gingivalis SerB mutant infection effect on immortalized gingival epithelial cells
description: Analysis of immortalized gingival keratinocytes (HIGKs) infected with a Porphyromonas gingivalis SerB mutant strain. SerB mutants are deficient in internalization and survival in HIGKs. Results provide insight into the role of SerB in the interaction between P. gingivalis and HIGKs.

title: Skin carcinogenesis model
description: Analysis of papillomas initiated by DMBA/TPA treatment of epidermal keratinocytes deficient for activating transcriptional factor 2 (ATF2).  ATF2 mutant animals show increased susceptibility to papillomas relative to the WT counterparts. Results provide insight into the role of ATF2 in skin cancer.

title: Curcumin effect on oxidatively stressed monocyte cell line: time course
description: Analysis of U937 monoctyes exposed to oxidative stress then treated for 4 or 18 hrs with curcumin, a dietary polyphenol. Curcumin restores oxidative stress impaired histone deacetylase-2 activity and corticosteroid efficacy in vitro. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of these effects.

title: Evi-1 deficiency effect on hematopoietic stem cells
description: Analysis of hematopoietic stem cells lacking the ecotropic viral integration site-1 (Evi-1) gene. Evi-1 is an oncogene associated with myeloid leukemia. Results provide insight into the role of Evi-1 in normal hematopoiesis.

title: FHL2 deficiency effect on spontaneously immortalized embryonic fibroblasts
description: Analysis of spontaneously immortalized embryonic fibroblasts (EFs) lacking the LIM-only protein FHL2. FHL2 deficiency results in reduced proliferative capacity of spontaneously immortalized EFs. Results provide insight into the role of FLH2 in cell cycle and cell proliferation.

title: Various mental disorders: postmortem brains
description: Analysis of postmortem prefrontal cortices from subjects with bipolar disorder, depression, and schizophrenia. Results provide insight into the molecular pathophysiology of these mental disorders.

title: Helicobacter pylori infection effect on a gastric epithelial progenitor cell line
description: Analysis of a gastric epithelial progenitor (mGEP) cell line infected with two Helicobacter pylori strains: chronic atrophic gastritis (ChAG)-associated Kx1 and gastric cancer-associated Kx2. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the ChAG-to-cancer transition induced by H. pylori.

title: Type 2 diabetes: cultured myotubes
description: Analysis of cultured myotubes from obese patients with type 2 diabetes. Cultured human myotubes display the morphological, metabolic and biochemical properties of adult skeletal muscle. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying insulin resistance in skeletal muscle.

title: STAT5 depleted pro-B cell line response to IL-3: time course (MG-U74A)
