description: Analysis of STAT5A and STAT5B depleted proB Ba/F3-beta cells stimulated with IL-3 for 0.5 or 2 hours. STAT5A and STAT5B are members of the family of signal transducers and activators of transcription. Results identify IL-3 inducible STAT5 target genes.

title: STAT5 depleted pro-B cell line response to IL-3: time course (MG-U74B)
description: Analysis of STAT5A and STAT5B depleted pro-B Ba/F3-beta cells stimulated with IL-3 for 0.5 or 2 hours. STAT5A and STAT5B are members of the family of signal transducers and activators of transcription. Results identify IL-3 inducible STAT5 target genes.

title: STAT5 depleted pro-B cell line response to IL-3: time course (MG-U74C)
description: Analysis of STAT5A and STAT5B depleted pro-B Ba/F3-beta cells stimulated with IL-3 for 0.5 or 2 hours. STAT5A and STAT5B are members of the family of signal transducers and activators of transcription. Results identify IL-3 inducible STAT5 target genes.

title: Juvenile hormone III effect on adult female insects
description: Analysis of whole bodies of yellow white (y, w) adult female insects topically treated with exogenous juvenile hormone (JH) III. JH can modulate immunity in insects. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying JH regulation of innate immunity in insects.

title: Bronchopulmonary dysplasia: premature newborn umbilical cords
description: Analysis of umbilical cord tissues from extremely low gestational age newborns, between 23 to 27 weeks gestational age, some of who subsequently developed the chronic lung disorder bronchopulmonary dysplasia (BPD).  Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying BPD pathogenesis.

title: High dietary fat effect on small intestine: time course
description: Analysis of small intestines of male C57BL/6J rodents fed a powdered high-fat purified diet for up to 8 weeks. Diet contributes to obesity and insulin resistance (IR) development. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying dietary fat-induced obesity and IR pathogenesis.

title: Chlamydia pneumoniae infection effect on HL epithelial cells: time course
description: Analysis of the HL epithelial cell line at various time points up to 72 hours following Chlamydia pneumoniae infection. C. pneumonia is a common cause of respiratory infections such as pneumonia. Results provide insight into host-cell phenomena that are affected at the different stages of infection.

title: Fibroblast growth factor-23 transgenic model
description: Analysis of kidneys from C57Bl transgenics expressing human fibroblast growth factor-23 (FGF23). FGF23 is a circulating protein that causes decreased renal inorganic phosphate (Pi) reabsorption. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying the regulation of Pi homeostasis by FGF23.

title: Argyrin A effect on MCF7 breast cancer cells: time course
description: Temporal analysis of MCF7 breast adenocarcinoma cells treated with argyrin A, a proteasome inhibitor that induces apoptosis by stabilizing cyclin kinase inhibitor p27kip1. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms that make argyrin A-induced cell death dependent upon p27kip1 expression.

title: Ovaries from a high-fertility line
description: Analysis of ovaries from high-fertility FL1 animals. FL1 animals exhibit an increase in ovulation number. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of this increase in ovulation number.

title: Zinc inhalation effect on the heart: dose response
description: Analysis of hearts of animals after subchronic exposure to zinc via nose only inhalation of aerosolized zinc sulfate (10, 30 or 100 ug zinc/m3), for 5 hours/day, 3 days/week for 16 weeks. Results provide insight into the effect of inhalation of zinc at environmentally relevant levels on the heart.

title: Iron enriched and deficient diets effect on the liver
description: Analysis of livers of C57BL/6 and DBA/2 animals fed an iron enriched or deficient diet. Iron induces the production of hepcidin, a hepatic peptide hormone that regulates systemic iron homeostasis. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms regulating hepcidin expression.

title: Retina response to optic nerve injury: time course
description: Temporal analysis of retinas of animals following intraorbital optic nerve transection (IONT) or intraorbital nerve crush (IONC). Optic nerve injury, which is more severe with IONT than IONC, triggers retinal ganglion cell death. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of this degeneration.

title: Visual cortex during the critical period for ocular dominance (MG-U74A)
description: Analysis of visual cortices before the critical period for ocular dominance plasticity opens [postnatal day 14 (P14)], at the peak sensitivity of the critical period (P28), and after the critical period (P60). Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms associated with the critical period.

title: Visual cortex during the critical period for ocular dominance (MG-U74B)
description: Analysis of visual cortices before the critical period for ocular dominance plasticity opens [postnatal day 14 (P14)], at the peak sensitivity of the critical period (P28), and after the critical period (P60). Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms associated with the critical period.

title: Norflurazon effect on whole seedlings
description: Analysis of 5-day-old, light-grown gun1-9 and gun5 mutant whole seedlings treated with  norflurazon, an inhibitor of chloroplast development. GUN1 and GUN5 are involved in plastid-to-nucleus retrograde signaling. Results provide insight into nuclear genes under the control of retrograde pathways.

title: Visual cortex during the critical period for ocular dominance (MG-U74C)
description: Analysis of visual cortices before the critical period for ocular dominance plasticity opens [postnatal day 14 (P14)], at the peak sensitivity of the critical period (P28), and after the critical period (P60). Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms associated with the critical period.

title: Chronic stress effect on peripheral blood monocytes
description: Analysis of peripheral blood monocytes from individuals experiencing chronic stress due to being caregivers of family members with malignant brain cancer. Chronic stressors increase vulnerability to medical illness. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying this phenomenon.

title: Cyclooxygenase-2 inhibitor celecoxib effect on colorectal adenocarcinoma
description: Analysis of colorectal adenocarcinomas resected from patients treated with celecoxib for 7 days. Celecoxib is a cycooxygenase-2 inibitor that exhibits anti-cancer activity. Results provide insight into the mechanism of action of celecoxib in vivo.

title: Transcription factor STAT5b deficiency effect on the colon
description: Analysis of colons of animals lacking the Signal Transducers and Activators of Transcription member STAT5b. STAT5b mutants are more susceptible to experimental colitis, associated with intestinal barrier function defects. Results provide insight into the role of STAT5b in colonic barrier function.

title: Heart failure progression model: non-infarcted ventricular tissue
description: Analysis of non-infarcted left ventricular tissues from animals at various time points up to 14 days following myocardial infarction (MI). MI induced by ligating the left coronary artery. Results provide insight into the molecular pathogenesis of heart failure.

title: Chromatin remodeling component BAF250a deficiency effect on embryonic stem cells in vitro
description: Analysis of embryonic stem (ES) cells deleted for BAF250a in vitro. BAF250 is a component of the BAF chromatin remodeling complex. Results provide insight into the role of BAF250a in ES cell self-renewal and differentiation.

title: Bisphenol A effect on nonmalignant breast epithelial cell aspirates from breast cancer patients
description: Analysis of random periareolar fine-needle aspirates collected from unafflicted, contralateral breast tissue of breast cancer patients and treated with bisphenol A (BPA). BPA is a prevalent xenoestrogen. Results provide insight into early molecular events induced by BPA in susceptible breast tissue.

title: Newborn intestinal tissues response to Shigella flexineri infection
description: Analysis of intestinal tissues from  4- or 7-day-old animals infected with Shigella flexineri strains for 2 or 4 hr. Animals >1 wk old are no longer susceptible to infection by Shigella. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the switch from disease susceptibility to resistance.

title: Bronchial epithelial cells response to interleukin-22 and interleukin-17
description: Analysis of bronchial epithelial cells treated with interleukin (IL)-22, IL-17, or both.  IL-17 receptor mutant lungs are susceptible to Klebsiella pneumonia infections. IL-22 induces antimicrobial peptide expression. Results provide insight into the extent of IL-22 and IL-17's role in host defense.

title: Brassinazole effect on arf2 mutant seedlings
description: Analysis of etiolated, auxin response factor 2 (arf2) mutant seedlings grown on brassinazole, a type of brassinosteroid hormone (BR). ARF2 is required for normal BR response. Results provide insight into the convergence of the brassinosteroid and auxin signalling pathways at the molecular level.

title: Aquaporin-11 deficiency effect on the kidney
description: Analysis of kidneys of 1 week old animals lacking aquaporin-11 (AQP11). AQP11 null mutants develop polycystic kidneys. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of cyst formation in kidneys of AQP11 mutants.

title: Rosiglitazone effect on kidneys
description: Analysis of kidneys from lean and obese animals fed a diet supplemented with rosiglitazone for 12 weeks. Rosiglitazone is a thiazolidinedione drug used to treat diabetes. Results provide insight into the mechanism of action of rosiglitazone.

title: Dent disease model: renal proximal tubules
description: Analysis of renal proximal tubules dissected from CLCN5 deficient animals, a model for Dent disease. Clcn5 is a chloride/protein exchanger expressed in renal tubules. Results provide insight into the molecular pathophysiology of Dent disease.

title: Utrophin overexpression effect on dystrophin-deficient mdx skeletal muscles
description: Analysis of skeletal muscles from dystrophin-deficient mdx trangenics engineered to overexpress utrophin, a dystrophin-related protein. Dystrophin mutations result in Duchenne muscular dystrophy. mdx trangenics overexpressing utrophin display improved muscle function.

title: Staphylococcal superantigen toxins effect on peripheral blood mononuclear cells
description: Analysis of peripheral blood mononuclear cells treated with the recombinant staphylococcal superantigen (SAg) toxin SEI or SEB. SEI is located in the enterotoxin gene cluster (egc). Antibodies against non-egc SAgs are common in the healthy population, while those against egc SAgs are rare.

title: Cephaloridine effect on the kidney: dose response
description: Analysis of kidneys of animals treated with various doses of cephaloridine (CER). CER is a cephalosporin antibiotic used for studying cephalosporin antibiotic-induced renal tubule damage. Results provide insight into the mechanisms underlying cephalosporin antibiotic-induced nephrotoxicity.

title: Two distinct isogenic mesenchymal stem/stromal cell populations from umbilical cord blood (HG-U133A)
description: Comparison of UCB1 and UCB2 cells, two distinct isogenic mesenchymal stem/stromal cell (MSC) populations isolated from umbilical cord blood. UCB1 and UCB2 display phenotypic differences. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the phenotypic heterogeneity among MSC populations.

title: Two distinct isogenic mesenchymal stem/stromal cell populations from umbilical cord blood (HG-U133B)
description: Comparison of UCB1 and UCB2 cells, two distinct isogenic mesenchymal stem/stromal cell (MSC) populations isolated from umbilical cord blood. UCB1 and UCB2 display phenotypic differences. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the phenotypic heterogeneity among MSC populations.

title: Limb bud zone of polarizing activity
description: Analysis of zone of polarizing activity (ZPA) from limb buds of E10.5 embryos. The ZPA is a signaling center that is necessary for the normal anteroposterior patterning of the vertebrate limb. Results identify genes, beyond Sonic hedgehog (shh), expressed in the ZPA compared to the rest of the limb.

title: Dicer deficiency effect on embryonic stem cells
description: Analysis of embryonic stem (ES) cells homozygous or heterozygous null for Dicer, an RNase III endonuclease required for processing microRNAs. Loss of microRNA pathway components negatively affects ES cell differentiation. Results provide insight into the role of microRNAs in ES cell development.

title: Embryonic erythroid precursors
description: Analysis of primitive erythroid precursors and epithelial cells isolated from frozen sections of the embryonic day 9.5 yolk sac. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying embryonic erythropoiesis.

title: Nrf2 deficiency effect on the liver
description: Analysis of livers from animals lacking Nrf2, a transcription factor involved in the defense against oxidative stress. The liver is often exposed to oxidative stresses, such as those induced by viruses, toxins, and surgery. Results provide insight into the role of Nrf2 in liver regeneration.

title: Perfluorooctanoic acid effect on livers lacking PPAR-alpha
description: Analysis of PPAR-alpha null livers from animals treated with perfluorooctanoic acid (PFOA), a member of a class of industrial chemicals called peroxisome proliferator chemicals. PFOA exposure is linked to cancer. Results provide insight into the role of PPAR-alpha in mediating the effects of PFOA.

title: Amyotrophic lateral sclerosis model
description: Analysis of motor neurons of 60, 90, and 120 day old SOD1 G93A transgenics, a model for familial amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (ALS). ALS is an adult-onset neurodegenerative disease characterized by degeneration of upper and lower motor neurons. Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of ALS.

title: High doses of perfluorooctanoic acid effect on fetal liver and lung
description: Analysis of livers or lungs of fetuses dosed during gestation with up to 10 mg/(kg day) perfluorooctanoic acid (PFOA), an industrial chemical that induces growth deficits and mortality in murine neonates. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of PFOA-induced developmental toxicity.

title: Low doses of perfluorooctanoic acid effect on fetal liver and lung
description: Analysis of livers or lungs of fetuses dosed during gestation with up to 3 mg/(kg day) perfluorooctanoic acid (PFOA), an industrial chemical that induces growth deficits and mortality in murine neonates. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of PFOA-induced developmental toxicity.

title: Homocysteine effect on aortic smooth muscle cells in vitro
description: Analysis of cultured aortic smooth muscle cells grown for 14 days in the presence of 10 or 100 umol/L DL-homocysteine (Hcy). Elevated plasma levels of Hcy are a risk factor for atherosclerotic vascular disease. Results provide insight into the role of Hcy in atherosclerosis.

title: Pulmonary embolism model: right heart ventricles
description: Analysis of right ventricles (RV) of animals for up to 18 hours after injection with polystyrene microsphere beads to induce pulmonary embolism (PE). Animals injected with 1.3 or 2.0 million microspheres/100g body weight. Results provide insight into the mechanisms leading to RV failure after PE.

title: Protocadherin 12 deficiency effect on the placenta
description: Analysis of embryonic day 12.5 placentas from animals lacking protocadherin 12 (Pcdh12). Pcdh12 is a transmembrane adhesive protein with homophilic adhesive properties. Pcdh12 deficient placentas exhibit a reduction in size. Results provide insight into the function of Pcdh12.

title: Relaxation response practice effect on blood
description: Analysis of whole blood from long-term practitioners of daily relaxation response (RR) practice and those with short-term (8 wks) RR training. RR is a mind-body intervention that offsets the physiological effects caused by stress. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying the RR.

title: Untreated juvenile dermatomyositis muscle biopsies
description: Analysis of skeletal muscle biopsies from untreated girls with active symptoms of juvenile dermatomyositis (JDM) less than 2 months or greater than 2 months. Results provide insight into the impact of the duration of chronic inflammation on gene expression in muscle of untreated children with JDM.

title: Spleen CD11b+ cells response to Yersinia enterocolitica (Ye) YopH deletion mutant infection in vivo
description: Analysis of splenic CD11b+ cells from animals infected with wildtype Yersinia enterocolitica (Ye) or a YopH-deficient Ye mutant. YopH is a virulence factor that inhibits phagocytosis of Ye and promotes virulence of Ye. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of YopH-mediated immune evasion.

title: Endosperm and embryo fractions of developing and germinating seeds
description: Analysis of pericarp, endosperm and embryo seed tissue fractions of developing and germinating grains. Plant seeds prepare for germination during the seed maturation stage. Results provide insight into the transcriptome relationships between seed maturation and germination.

title: Cadmium exposure: time course
description: Analysis of animals treated with 100 uM cadmium for 4 or 24 hours. Cadmium is a environmental toxicant. Exposure to cadmium is associated with a variety of human diseases. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms involved in the defense against cadmium toxicity.

title: Frag1 cells response to ionic and non-ionic hyperosmotic stress
description: Analysis of bacterial Frag1 cells subjected to ionic (NaCl) and non-ionic (sucrose) hyperosmotic stress (HS). Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying the specificity of osmotic adjustment to ionic and non-ionic osmotica.

title: Activin deficiency effect on ovarian granulosa cells
description: Analysis of granulosa cells from animals deficient for all ovarian activins. Granulosa cells are associated with the developing oocyte. Results provide insight into the role of activins in ovarian growth, differentiation, and cancer.

title: Obese liver response to a short-term low-fat hypocaloric diet
description: Analysis of livers from middle-aged obese women on a low-fat hypocaloric diet for 8 weeks. The diet resulted in a mean weight loss of 5% of body weight. Results provide insight into the effect of a hypocaloric diet on the liver at the molecular level.

title: Conjugated linoleic acid isomers effect on intestinal cell line
description: Analysis of intestinal Caco-2 cells treated with conjugated linoleic acid (CLA) isomer trans-10, cis-12 CLA or cis-9, trans-11 CLA. CLA exerts isomer-specific effects on transepithelial calcium transport and cell growth in Caco-2 cells. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms of action.

title: Pickle mutant seedlings response to gibberellin inhibition
description: Analysis of pickle (pkl) mutant seedlings treated with the gibberellin (GA) inhibitor uniconazole.  PKL encodes a CHD3 chromatin remodeler that acts during germination to repress the expression of seed-associated genes. Repression of seed-associated traits is promoted in pkl mutant seedlings by GA.

title: Staphylococcus epidermidis SarZ mutant
description: Analysis of Staphylococcus epidermidis sarZ mutants deficient in biofilm formation. Biofilm-associated infections due to Staphylococcus epidermidis, a nosocomial pathogen, is a public health problem.  Results provide insight into the role of SarZ in biofilm formation and virulence in S. epidermidis.
platform_organism: Coxiella burnetii,Rickettsia rickettsii,Chlamydia muridarum,Chlamydophila pneumoniae AR39,Staphylococcus epidermidis RP62A,Staphylococcus epidermidis ATCC 12228,Staphylococcus aureus subsp. aureus MW2,Borrelia burgdorferi B31,Coxiella burnetii RSA 493,Chl

title: Rickettsia rickettsii virulent and avirulent strains
description: Comparison of the Rickettsia rickettsii virulent strain Sheila Smith and the avirulent strain Iowa. R. rickettsii is an obligate intracellular pathogen that causes Rocky Mountain spotted fever. Results provide insight in the molecular basis of virulence in R. rickettsii.
platform_organism: Coxiella burnetii,Rickettsia rickettsii,Chlamydia muridarum,Chlamydophila pneumoniae AR39,Staphylococcus epidermidis RP62A,Staphylococcus epidermidis ATCC 12228,Staphylococcus aureus subsp. aureus MW2,Borrelia burgdorferi B31,Coxiella burnetii RSA 493,Chl

title: Immature dendritic cell response to butanol fraction of Echinacea purpurea: time course
description: Analysis of immature dendritic cell lines (iDCs) treated with the butanol-fraction of stems and leaves of E. purpurea [BF/S+L/Ep] containing defined bioactive phytocompounds. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying the immune-modulatory activities induced by the phytocompounds.

title: Azaspiracid-1 effect on T lymphocyte cell line: time course and dose response
description: Analysis of T lymphocyte Jurkat cells treated with 1 or 10 nM azaspiracid-1 (AZA-1) for up to 24 hours. AZA-1 is a marine biotoxin reported to accumulate in shellfish and is associated with severe gastrointestinal intoxication. Results provide insight into the mechanism of action of AZA-1.

title: Dicer deficient embryonic stem cell response to miR-290 transfection
description: Analysis of undifferentiated Dicer deficient embryonic stem (ES) cells transfected with the siRNA-like form of miRNAs of the miR-290 cluster. Loss of miRNA pathway components negatively affects ES cell differentiation. Results provide insight into the role of miR-290 in ES cell differentiation.

title: Non-alcoholic steatohepatitis model
description: Analysis of livers from males fed a high polyunsaturated diet containing 70% corn oil to induce the development of non-alcoholic steatohepatitis (NASH). In NASH, steatosis is accompanied by inflammation, necrosis, apoptosis, and fibrosis. Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of NASH.

title: Osteosarcoma cell line response to activation of specific glucocorticoid receptor alpha isoforms: time course
description: Analysis of glucocorticoid receptor alpha (hGRalpha) isoform -A, -B, -C, or -D expressing osteosarcoma cells for up to 24 h after hGRalpha activation with dexomethasone. Cell apoptosis occurred in a GR isoform-selective manner. Results provide insight into the function of each isoform.

title: Azaspiracid-1 effect on T lymphocyte cell line: time course
description: Analysis of T lymphocyte Jurkat cells treated with 10 nM azaspiracid-1 (AZA-1) for up to 24 hours. AZA-1 is a marine biotoxin reported to accumulate in shellfish and is associated with severe gastrointestinal human intoxication. Results provide insight into the mechanism of action of AZA-1.

title: Macaca mulatta model of Helicobacter pylori infection: time course
description: Analysis of gastric mucosa from H. pylori specific pathogen free (SPF) rhesus monkeys infected with wildtype H. pylori strain J166 or its isogenic cag pathogenicity island (cag PAI) knockout mutant. Results provide insight into the role of cag PAI in the H. pylori host-pathogen interaction.

title: Vancomycin effect on the kidney: dose response
description: Analysis of kidneys of BALB/c females treated with vancomycin (VA) for up to 400 mg/kg delivered intraperitoneally or intravenously. VA, an antibiotic treatment against methicillin-resistant Staphylococcus aureus, is nephrotoxic. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of VA nephrotoxicity.

title: bHLH transcription factor Math2 overexpression effect on cultured brain cerebral cortical cells
description: Analysis of cultured brain cerebral cortical cells overexpressing Math2. Math2 is a bHLH transcription factor that is involved in neuronal differentiation and maturation. Results identify Math2 target genes.

title: Budding yeast response to heme deficiency
description: Analysis of Saccharomyces cerevisiae mutant cells lacking aminolevulinic acid (ALA) synthase. ALA synthase catalyzes the first step of heme biosynthesis. Heme uptake is induced by heme starvation in S. cerevisiae. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms regulating heme uptake.

title: Budding yeast response to hypoxia
description: Analysis of Saccharomyces cerevisiae wild type cells grown under reduced oxygen tension. Heme synthesis requires oxygen, and yeast grown anaerobically exhibit an increased uptake of hemin. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms regulating heme uptake.

title: Intralobular and interlobular mammary fibroblasts
description: Comparison of intralobular and interlobular fibroblasts isolated from breast tissues. Intralobular fibroblasts surround mammary gland epithelial cells, and interlobular fibroblasts surround intralobular fibroblasts. Results provide insight into the differences between the two fibroblast subtypes.

title: Aortic endothelial cell response to dominant negative PPAR gamma expression in vitro
description: Analysis of cultured endothelial cells expressing the dominant negative V290M PPAR gamma mutant protein. PPAR gamma exerts anti-inflammatory and antioxidant effects in the vascular endothelium. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of PPAR gamma's protective action in the vasculature.

title: Rice leaves response to blast fungus infection: time course
description: Analysis of leaves of rice cultivar Nipponbare 3 or 4 days following inoculation with the virulent Magnaporthe grisea FR13 isolate.  M. grisea causes blast.  Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the susceptibility of rice to blast.

title: Embryonic brain development
description: Analysis of brains at embryonic days (E) 9.5, 11.5, and 13.5. Mostly undifferentiated neural progenitor cells (NPCs) are present at E9.5, NPCs begin to differentiate into neurons at E11.5, and neurogenesis peaks at E13.5. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying neurogenesis.

title: Embryonic stem cell response to STAT3 overexpression in vitro (MG-U74A)
description: Analysis of cultured embryonic stem (ES) cells overexpressing the transcription factor STAT3. STAT3 is a downstream target of the LIF signaling cascade. LIF activation maintains ES cells in a pluripotent state. Results provide insight into the role of STAT3 in maintenance of ES cell pluripotency.

title: Embryonic stem cell response to STAT3 overexpression in vitro (MG-U74B)
description: Analysis of cultured embryonic stem (ES) cells overexpressing the transcription factor STAT3. STAT3 is a downstream target of the LIF signaling cascade. LIF activation maintains ES cells in a pluripotent state. Results provide insight into the role of STAT3 in maintenance of ES cell pluripotency.

title: Embryonic stem cell response to STAT3 overexpression in vitro (MG-U74C)
description: Analysis of cultured embryonic stem (ES) cells overexpressing the transcription factor STAT3. STAT3 is a downstream target of the LIF signaling cascade. LIF activation maintains ES cells in a pluripotent state. Results provide insight into the role of STAT3 in maintenance of ES cell pluripotency.

title: Lung development (Mu11K-A)
description: Analysis of lungs from embryonic day 12 to adulthood. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms governing normal lung development.

title: Lung development (Mu11K-B)
description: Analysis of lungs from embryonic day 12 to adulthood. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms governing normal lung development.

title: Nematode model of primary mitochondrial dysfunction: complex I mutants
description: Analysis of gas-1(fc21) electron transport chain complex I mutants.  The gas-1(fc21) mutation affects the 49 kD subunit of complex I, decreasing the rate of complex I-dependent oxidative phosphorylation. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying primary mitochondrial disease .

title: Nematode models of primary mitochondrial dysfunction: complex I, II, and III mutants
description: Analysis of 8 different electron transport chain (ETC) subunit mutants (3 missense and 5 RNAi-induced) in complexes I, II, and III. Results from this validation set provide insight into the contributions of individual complexes or subunits to primary mitochondrial dysfunction.

title: Murine model of primary mitochondrial dysfunction
description: Analysis of hepatocytes from Pdss2 liver-specific knockouts. The mutant livers are depleted for Coenzyme Q (CoQ), a critical component of the mitochondrial respiratory chain. Results from this mammalian model of primary mitochondrial dysfunction are compared to nematode models (GDS3452 and GDS3453).

title: Kras G12D heterozygous mutation effect on somatic cell line (MG-430A 2.0)
description: Analysis of MLP-29 liver cells bearing the heterozygous Kras G12D mutation. KRAS mutations are present at a high frequency in human cancers. Results identify a gene expression signature for the presence of the mutated Kras.

title: Kras G12D heterozygous mutation effect on somatic cell line (Sentrix MouseRef-8)
description: Analysis of MLP-29 liver cells bearing the heterozygous Kras G12D mutation. KRAS mutations are present at a high frequency in human cancers. Results identify a gene expression signature for the presence of the mutated Kras.

title: Frontotemporal lobar degeneration with ubiquitinated inclusions and progranulin mutations: various brain regions
description: Analysis of various brain regions of patients who suffered from frontotemporal lobar degeneration with ubiquitinated inclusions (FTLD-U). Presence of progranulin (GRN) mutations determined. GRN mutations are associated with FTLD-U. Results identify expression signatures for GRN subtypes of FTLD-U.

title: microRNA-140 overexpression effect on fibroblast cell line
description: Analysis of C3H10T1/2 fibroblast cells following microRNA-140 overexpression. MicroRNAs are short noncoding RNA molecules that regulate the expression of mRNAs. Results identify gene targets of microRNA-140.

title: microRNA-140 silencing effect on fibroblast cell line
description: Analysis of C3H10T1/2 fibroblast cells following microRNA-140 silencing. MicroRNAs are short noncoding RNA molecules that regulate the expression of mRNAs. Results identify gene targets of microRNA-140.

title: Sepsis effect on the skeletal muscle
description: Analysis of muscle biopsies from septic patients treated in the intensive care unit. Septic patients often develop multiple organ failure including persistent skeletal muscle dysfunction. Results provide insight into the molecular defects driving loss of muscle function and metabolic homeostasis.

title: SPT5 mutant embryos
description: Analysis of fog-sk8 mutant embryos containing a severe truncation of Spt5. Spt5 regulates transcription elongation. Results identify Spt5 target genes during development.

title: PPARalpha deficient heart response to chronic pressure overload
description: Analysis of heart left ventricles subjected to chronic pressure overload for 28 days to induce cardiac hypertrophy. PPARalpha mitigates cardiac hypertrophy. Results provide insight into processes and signalling pathways regulated by PPARalpha in hearts challenged by chronic pressure overload.

title: Gastrointestinal tract response to cytotoxic chemotherapy: time course
description: Analysis of the gastrointestinal tracts of animals up to 72 hours following treatment with the chemotherapy agent irinotecan to induce gastrointestinal mucositis (GM). GM is caused by the cytotoxic effects of cancer chemotherapy and radiotherapy. Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of GM.

title: Preeclampsia: first trimester placentas of pre-symptomatic women
description: Analysis of first trimester placenta tissues obtained by chorionic villus sampling from women destined to develop preeclampsia. Preeclampsia is a cause of maternal, fetal, and neonatal morbidity and mortality. Results provide insight into the molecular pathogenesis of preeclampsia.

title: Multifunctional protein 2 deficiency effect on the liver
description: Analysis of livers of 2 day old mutants lacking multifunctional protein 2 (Mfp2), an enzyme of the peroxisomal beta-oxidation pathway. Mfp2 deficiency results in extensive metabolic and pathological abnormalities starting in the postnatal period and leads to death by the age of 6 months.

title: Leukotriene D4 effect on monocytes
description: Analysis of monocytes following stimulation with leukotriene D4 (LTD4), a cysteinyl leukotriene (CysLT). CysLTs are mediators of innate immune responsiveness and chronic inflammatory diseases. Results provide insight into the signaling pathways involved in monocyte activation by cysLTs.

title: miR-122 overexpression effect on embryonic stem cells
description: Analysis of embryonic stem cells (ESCs) overexpressing wild-type miR-122. miR-122 is an endoderm specific microRNA. Results provide insight into the role of miR-122 in the differentiation of ESCs.

title: B-precursor acute lymphoblastic leukemia tumors sensitive and resistant to ionizing radiation
description: Analysis of B-precursor acute lymphoblastic (ALL) tumor cells exposed to ionizing radiation (IR) to induce DNA damage in vitro. Half of the tumors are sensitive to IR induced apoptosis. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the differences in response of B-precursor ALL to IR.

title: Barrett's esophagus
description: Analysis of Barrett's esophagus (BE), normal esophageal, and small intestinal biopsies. In BE, normal esophageal squamous epithelium transdifferentiates into  simple columnar epithelium resembling that of small intestine. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of this transdifferentiation.

title: Aiolos/OBF-1 double null mutation effect on bone marrow pre-BII cells
description: Analysis of bone marrow pre-BII cells from Aiolos/OBF-1 double null mutants. Aiolos is a chromatin regulator, OBF-1 a transcriptional activator. Small pre-BII to immature B cell transition is impaired in the double mutants. Results provide insight into the role of Aiolos and OBF-1 in pre-BII cells.

title: Limb girdle muscular dystrophy 2A (HG-U133A)
description: Analysis of skeletal muscles from patients with limb girdle muscular dystrophy 2A (LGMD2A). LGMD2A is a recessive genetic disorder caused by mutations in calpain 3 (CAPN3). Results provide insight into the molecular pathogenesis of LGMD2A.

title: Limb girdle muscular dystrophy 2A (HG-U133B)
description: Analysis of skeletal muscles from patients with limb girdle muscular dystrophy 2A (LGMD2A). LGMD2A is a recessive genetic disorder caused by mutations in calpain 3 (CAPN3). Results provide insight into the molecular pathogenesis of LGMD2A.

title: NF-E2-related factor 2 Nrf2 activation effect on the liver
description: Analysis of livers with hepatocyte-specific Keap1 deficiency. Keap1 represses transcription factor NF-E2-related factor 2 (Nrf2) signaling. Amplification of Nrf2 signaling inhibits acute inflammatory liver injury.  Results provide insight into the molecular basis of Nrf2-dependent cytoprotection.

title: Zinc finger protein Zelda deficiency effect on the embryo
description: Analysis of embryos lacking the zinc finger protein Zelda. Results provide insight into the role of Zelda in the transfer of control of embryogenesis to the zygotic genome during the process of maternal-to-zygotic transition.

title: 22q11 microdeletion syndrome model: prefrontal cortex
description: Analysis of prefrontal cortex of Df(16)A/+ animals.  Df(16)A/+ animals carry microdeletions  of about 1.3Mb in the locus syntenic to human 22q11.2. Individuals with 22q11.2 microdeletions show behavioral and cognitive deficits and are at high risk of developing schizophrenia.

title: 22q11 microdeletion syndrome model: hippocampus
description: Analysis of hippocampi of Df(16)A/+ animals.  Df(16)A/+ animals carry microdeletions of about 1.3Mb in the locus syntenic to human 22q11.2. Individuals with 22q11.2 microdeletions show behavioral and cognitive deficits and are at high risk of developing schizophrenia.

title: Sox10 depletion effect on Schwannoma cell line
description: Analysis of RT4D6 Schwannoma cells depleted for Sox10, an Sry-related HMG-Box transcription factor. Sox10 is important in the development of several cell lineages including neural crest stem cells and the derivative peripheral glial cells and melanocytes. Results identify Sox10 gene targets.

title: NOR1 gene and EWS/NOR1 fusion gene overexpression
description: Analysis of cells overexpressing NOR1 or the EWS/NOR1 fusion gene. NOR1 encodes an orphan nuclear receptor.  The EWS gene is involved in various malignancies by way of chromosomal translocations, and the EWS/NOR1 gene fusion is implicated in the pathogenesis of extraskeletal myxoid chondrosarcomas.

title: X-linked inhibitor of apoptosis XIAP depletion effect on a colorectal cancer cell line
description: Analysis of early and late passage HCT116 colon cancer cells depleted for X-linked inhibitor of apoptosis (XIAP). XIAP is overexpressed in the majority of NCI 60 cell lines compared to normal cells suggesting a potential role as a therapeutic target in a wide spectrum of malignancies.

title: Pulmonary microvascular endothelial cell response to hypoxia in vitro: time course
description: Analysis of pulmonary microvascular endothelial cells subjected to hypoxia for up to 48 hours. Pulmonary hypoxia is a common complication of chronic lung diseases leading to the development of pulmonary hypertension. Results provide insight into the molecular pathogenesis of pulmonary hypertension.

title: Insulin-like growth factor-I effect on breast cancer cell line: time course
description: Analysis of breast cancer MCF-7 cells stimulated with insulin-like growth factor-I (IGF-I) for 3 or 24 hours. High serum IGF-I levels are associated with an elevated risk of breast cancer. Results provide insight into the role of IGF-1 in the development and progression of breast cancer.

title: Zinc transporter SLC39A13 deficiency effect on chondrocytes
description: Analysis of chondrocytes lacking the zinc transporter SLC39A13. Zinc is an essential trace element that is abundant in connective tissues. Results provide insight into the role of zinc in connective tissues.

title: Transcription factor GATA4 deficiency effect on the jejunum
description: Analysis of jejuna of animals whose small intestinal epithelia lack the zinc finger transcription factor GATA4. These mutants exhibit impaired intestinal absorption of dietary fat and cholesterol. Results provide insight into the role of GATA4 in jejunal function.

title: Transcription factor CREB depletion effect on myeloid leukemic cell line
description: Analysis of myeloid leukemia K562 cells depleted for cAMP Response Element Binding Protein (CREB), a transcription factor. CREB is overexpressed in bone marrow samples of patients with acute leukemia. Results provides insight into the molecular mechanisms by which CREB contributes to acute leukemia.

title: Adipose tissue response to dihydrotestosterone: time course
description: Analysis of retroperitoneal adipose tissue samples from gonadectomized males and females following treatment with dihydrotestosterone (DHT) for up to 24 hours. Results provide insight into the role of DHT in the adipogenesis that occurs in retroperitoneal adipose tissues.

title: CD133 depletion effect on metastatic melanoma cell line
description: Analysis of metastatic melanoma FEMX-I cells depleted for CD133. CD133 is a cancer stem cell-associated antigen expressed in many malignancies such as melanoma. Results provide insight into the role of CD133 in cancer progression.

title: Deaf-1 deficiency and overexpression effect on cultured mammary epithelial cells
description: Analysis of cultured mammary epithelial cells lacking or overexpressing the transcription factor Deaf-1. Deaf-1 is involved in mammary gland development and breast cancer. Results identify target genes of Deaf-1.

title: Aire ectopic expression effect on pancreatic islet beta cells
description: Analysis of pancreatic islet beta cells ectopically expressing Aire. Aire promotes T cell tolerance by inducing the expression of genes encoding peripheral tissue antigens in medullary epithelial cells of the thymus. Results provide insight into the specificity of Aire's effect on transcription.

title: Senescent activated hepatic stellate cells
description: Analysis of activated hepatic stellate cells (HSCs) induced to senesce by treatment with a DNA-damaging agent. Upon activation in response to liver damage, HSCs proliferate and produce the extracellular matrix deposited in the fibrotic scar. Senescence of activated HSCs limits liver fibrosis.

title: Cigarette smoke of full flavor brand effect on bronchial epithelial cells in vitro: time course
description: Analysis of normal bronchial epithelial cells exposed to cigarette smoke from a typical full flavor brand for up to 24 hours. Results provide insight into the impact of cigarette smoke exposure at the molecular level.

title: Cigarette smoke of light flavor brand effect on bronchial epithelial cells in vitro: time course
description: Analysis of normal bronchial epithelial cells exposed to cigarette smoke from a typical light flavor brand for up to 24 hours. Results provide insight into the impact of cigarette smoke exposure at the molecular level.

title: Progerin expression in a hTERT-immortalized skin fibroblast cell line: time course
description: Analysis of skin fibroblasts induced to express GFP-progerin for up to 10 days. Progerin is a mutant form of lamin A and the causal agent of premature-ageing disease Hutchinson-Gilford Progeria Syndrome (HGPS). Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying this pathological effect.

title: Alveolar macrophages of cigarette smokers
description: Analysis of alveolar macrophages from cigarette smokers. Cigarette smoking is associated with increased lung cell turnover. Mononuclear phagocytes, such as macrophages, play an important role in the removal of apoptotic cells.

title: Interleukin-12 effect on peripheral blood mononuclear cells (HG-U133A)
description: Analysis of cultured peripheral blood mononuclear cells (PBMCs) stimulated with interleukin-12 (IL-12). PBMCs obtained from 7 donors. IL-12 plays a central role in adaptive and innate immunity. Results provide further insight into the effects of IL-12 on the immune response.

title: Interleukin-12 effect on peripheral blood mononuclear cells (HG-U133B)
description: Analysis of cultured peripheral blood mononuclear cells (PBMCs) stimulated with interleukin-12 (IL-12). PBMCs obtained from 7 donors. IL-12 plays a central role in adaptive and innate immunity. Results provide further insight into the effects of IL-12 on the immune response.

title: TREM-1 activation effect on monocytes in vitro
description: Analysis of cultured monocytes following TREM-1 activation by treatment with an antibody against TREM-1. TREM-1 is an immunoreceptor expressed on monocytes, macrophages, and neutrophils. Results provide insight into the cellular consequences of TREM-1 activation.

title: Cryptosporidium infection effect on intestinal epithelial cells in vitro
description: Analysis of cultured intestinal epithelial cells infected with Cryptosporidium hominis or parvum. Cryptosporidium parasites are pathogens of human intestinal epithelial cells. Results provide insight into the early pathogenesis of Cryptosporidium infection.

title: Synchronous and metachronous liver metastases from colorectal cancer
description: Analysis of synchronous and metachronous liver metastatic lesions from colorectal cancer (CC). The liver is a common site of metastases from CC. Synchronous metastatic lesions arise less than 6 months after the resection of the primary tumor, metachronous lesions arise 6 months after resection.

title: Seedling roots response to auxin and ethylene availability
description: Analysis of roots of aux1-7 seedlings treated with ethylene (ETH) and those of ein2-5 seedlings with auxin. Aux1-7 roots are defective in auxin influx but resistant to ETH. Ein2-5 roots are insensitive to ETH but responsive to auxin.  Results provide insight into auxin and ETH interactions in roots.

title: Spinal cord injury effect on the urinary bladder: time course
description: Analysis of bladders from Sprague-Dawley females for up to 25 days following spinal cord injury (SCI). Bladder wall tissue compliance increases within 2 weeks after SCI in this animal model. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the changes that the bladder undergoes after SCI.

title: Hormone-sensitive lipase deficient liver response to a high fat diet
description: Analysis of livers from hormone-sensitive lipase (HSL) null mutants fed a high fat diet. Decreased hepatic insulin sensitivity and elevation of plasma cholesterol are observed in this HSL-null animal model. Results provide insight into the mechanisms underlying these features.

title: Transcription factor Klf5 deficiency effect on embryonic stem cells
description: Analysis of embryonic stem cells (ESCs) lacking the transcription factor Klf5. Klf5 deficiency results in the failure of ESC derivation from cells of the inner cell mass and early embryonic lethality. Results provide insight into the role of Klf5 in blastocyst development and ESC self-renewal.

title: Claudin-1 overexpression effect on lung adenocarcinoma cell line
description: Analysis of lung adenocarcinoma CL1-5 cells overexpressing Claudin-1 (CLDN1), a component of tight junction complexes. Low CLDN1 expression in lung adenocarcinomas is associated with shorter overall survival. Results provide insight into the role of CLDN1 in the progression of lung adenocarcinoma.

title: HIV-1 infection effect on macrophages in vitro: time course
description: Analysis of cultured macrophages for up to 7 days after HIV-1 infection. Macrophages are targets of HIV-1 infection and constitute a viral reservoir that facilitates the spread of HIV-1 to other cells. Results provide insight into the signaling networks affected by HIV-1 infection in macrophages.

title: Furin deficiency effect on T-cells
description: Analysis of T-cells lacking the proprotein convertase furin. Proprotein convertases promote the proteolytic maturation of proproteins. Furin is induced in activated T-cells. Results provide insight into the function of furin in T-cells.

title: Embryonic stem cell-derived cardiomyocytes
description: Analysis of cardiomyocytes (CMs) derived from embryonic stem cells (ESCs). Under the appropriate conditions, ex vivo ESCs can differentiate into beating cardiomyocytes via an embryoid body (EB) intermediate. Results provide insight into the mechanisms underlying the differentiation of ESC into CMs.

title: Liposarcoma response to doxorubicin in vitro
description: Analysis of various types of liposarcomas treated with doxorubicin in vitro. While doxorubicin is an established chemotherapeutic for treating liposarcomas, the response to this drug is low. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the resistance of liposarcomas to doxorubicin.

title: Huntington's disease htt-171-82Q in vitro model: striatal neurons
description: Analysis of cultured primary striatal neurons expressing the N-terminal 171 residues of the Huntingtin protein along with 82 glutamine residues (htt-171-82Q), which is a pathological number of glutamines. Results provide insight into the molecular pathogenesis of Huntington's disease.

title: Nodular lymphocyte-predominant Hodgkin lymphoma: lymphocytic and histiocytic cells
description: Analysis of neoplastic lymphocytic and histiocytic cells (L&H) dissected from nodular lymphocyte-predominant Hodgkin lymphoma tumors (NLPHL). L&H cells represent less than 1 percent of cells in NLPHL tumors. Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of NLPHL.

title: Oncogenic NRAS depletion effect on melanoma cell lines: time course
description: Analysis of melanoma 224 and BL cells for up to 3 days after suppression of the mutant NRAS Q61R gene with siRNA siMut10 or siMut12. Activating mutations in NRAS gene is a common genetic event in malignant melanoma. Results provide insight into the role of NRAS in the pathogenesis of melanoma.

title: Chronic myelogenous leukemia response to imatinib: Philadelphia chromosome positive CD34+ cells
description: Analysis of Philadelphia chromosome-positive CD34+ cells of chronic myelogenous leukemia patients treated with imatinib. The anti-cancer drug imatinib is a selective bcr-abl tyrosine kinase inhibitor. Results provide insight into the molecular events affected by bcr-abl inhibition through imatinib.

title: Plasmacytoid dendritic cell response to transcription factor E2-2
description: Analysis of plasmocytoid dendritic cells (PDCs) heterozygous null for the transcription factor E2-2. Deletion of E2-2 blocked the development of PDCs but not of other lineages. Results provide insight into the role of E2-2 in the specification of the PDC lineage.

title: Resident liver stem cell lines
description: Analysis of the resident liver stem cell (RLSCs) lines MetE14/3 and WTE14/1. Results provide insight into the molecular phenotype of RLSCs.

title: Retina response to hypoxia and subsequent reoxygenation: time course
description: Analysis of retinas subjected to hypoxia for 6 hours and subsequent reoxygenation for up to 16 hours. Hypoxic preconditioning protects photoreceptors from light damage in animal model. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of this protective effect.

title: Lung response to aerosolized non-typeable Haemophilus influenza lysate: time course
description: Analysis of lungs exposed to aerosolized non-typeable Haemophilus influenza (NTHi) lysate for 2 or 4 hours. Aerosolized NTHi treatment induces lung inflammation but protects against fatal bacterial pneumonia in animal models. Results provide insight into molecular basis of NTHi's protective effect.

title: Non-migratory villous cytotrophoblasts and invasive extra-villous trophoblasts
description: Comparison of non-migratory villous cytotrophoblasts (CTBs) and invasive extra-villous trophoblasts.  Invasion of CTBs into uterine tissues is essential for placental development. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms regulating trophoblast invasion.

title: Hypoxia effect on a renal proximal tubule epithelial cell line
description: Analysis of cultured renal proximal tubule epithelial RPTEC cells subjected to hypoxia at 1% oxygen for 24 hours. Results identify hypoxia-controlled genes in epithelial cells.

title: Ovarian cancer and depression
description: Analysis of primary ovarian tumors from patients with high depressive symptoms. Results provide insight into the contribution of biobehavioral factors such as such as stress, depression, and social support to the molecular progression of cancer.

title: Skeletal muscle response to myostatin inhibition
description: Analysis of skeletal muscles of 4 to 5 month old males treated with an anti-myostatin antibody to inhibit myostatin activity. Myostatin null mutations lead to hypermuscularity. Results provide insight into the molecular effect of the post-developmental loss of myostatin activity on skeletal muscles.

title: KRAP deficiency effect on brown adipose tissues
description: Analysis of brown adipose tissues from animals lacking KRAP. KRAP null mutants exhibit increased metabolic rate, reduced adiposity, improved glucose tolerance, hypoinsulinemia, and hypoleptinemia. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the metabolic phenotype of KRAP deficient animals.

title: KRAP deficiency effect on the liver
description: Analysis of livers from animals lacking KRAP. KRAP null mutants exhibit increased metabolic rate, reduced adiposity, improved glucose tolerance, hypoinsulinemia, and hypoleptinemia. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the metabolic phenotype of KRAP deficient animals.

title: Pancreatic islet response to glucose in vitro: dose response
description: Analysis of pancreatic islets cultured for 18 hours in 2, 5, 10, or 30 mM glucose. Culture in 2 to 10 mM glucose improves beta cell survival and function, while concentrations above 10 mM are deleterious. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of this sensitivity to glucose concentrations.

title: PGC-1-related coactivator partial depletion
description: Analysis of U2OS cells partially depleted for the PGC-1-related coactivator PRC. Loss of PRC results in a severe reduction in respiratory energy production, the proliferation of structurally defective mitochondria, and a defect in cell cycle progression.

title: PGC-1-related coactivator depletion
description: Analysis of U2OS cells nearly completely depleted for the PGC-1-related coactivator PRC. Loss of PRC results in a severe reduction in respiratory energy production, the proliferation of structurally defective mitochondria, and a defect in cell cycle progression.

title: Caveolin-3 deficiency effect on virgin mammary glands
description: Analysis of caveolin-3 (Cav-3) deficient mammary glands from virgin females. Cav-3 deficient virgin mammary glands develop lobulo-alveolar hyperplasia, akin to the changes normally observed during pregnancy and lactation. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of this Cav-3 null phenotype.

title: Lymphatic endothelial cell response to Prox1 and NR2F2 depletion
description: Analysis of lymphatic endothelial cells (LECs) depleted for Prox1, NR2F2, or both regulators. LECs are derived from venous endothelial cells (VECs). Prox1 and NR2F2 regulate LEC and VEC development, respectively. Results provide insight into the role of NR2F2 and Prox1 in maintaining LEC phenotypes.

title: Polybrominated diphenyl ethers effect on adrenocortical carcinoma cell line
description: Analysis of H295R adrenocortical carcinoma cells treated with the hydroxylated polybrominated biphenyl ether (PBDE) 2-OH-BDE47 or 2-OH-BDE85. PBDEs are used as flame retardants in various products. The two PBDEs are cytotoxic. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of PBDE cytotoxicity.

title: Age and diet effect on canine skeletal muscles
description: Analysis of skeletal muscles from 1 and 12 year old female beagles fed an animal-protein based or plant-protein based diet for 12 months. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms in the skeletal muscle affected by age and diet.

title: Psoriasis
description: Analysis of lesional and non-lesional skins from patients with psoriasis. Psoriasis is an immune-mediated disease characterized by aberrant epidermal differentiation, surface scale formation, and marked cutaneous inflammation. Results provide insight into the molecular pathogenesis of psoriasis.

title: Spinocerebellar ataxia type 1 knock-in model: cerebellum
description: Analysis of cerebella from spinocerebellar ataxia type 1 (SCA1) knockin animals at an early symptomatic disease stage. SCA1 is a neurodegenerative disorder caused by expansion of a glutamine tract in ataxin-1. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of cerebellar pathogenesis in SCA1.

title: Spinocerebellar ataxia type 7 knock-in model: cerebellum
description: Analysis of cerebella from spinocerebellar ataxia type 7 (SCA7) knockin animals at an early symptomatic disease stage. SCA1 is a neurodegenerative disorder caused by expansion of a glutamine tract in ataxin-7. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of cerebellar pathogenesis in SCA7.

title: Human cytomegalovirus chemokine receptor U28 expression effect on fibroblast cell line
description: Analysis of fibroblast NIH-3T3 cells expressing the human cytomegalovirus (HCMV) chemokine receptor U28. HCMV proteins are present in malignancies such as colon cancer. U28 activates inflammatory and proliferative signaling pathways. Results provide insight into the role of U28 in oncogenesis.

title: Cigarette smoke-induced pulmonary emphysema model
description: Analysis of lungs of A/J animals exposed to cigarette smoke (CS) for up to 6 months. A/J animals chronically exposed to CS develop pulmonary emphysema (PE). Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying the initiation and development of PE.

title: Norovirus infection effect on macrophage cell line
description: Analysis of macrophage RAW264.7 cells infected with murine norovirus type 1.  Noroviruses cause non-bacterial gastroenteritis in humans. Results provide insight into the molecular pathogenesis of norovirus infections.

title: GLI1 transformed kidney epithelial cell line
description: Analysis of kidney epithelial RK3E cells transformed by the oncogenic transcription factor GLI1. Results compared with the gene expression profile of a subgroup of medulloblastomas that shows constitutive activation of the Sonic hedgehog pathway with expression of GLI1.

title: Caveolin-1 deficiency effect on hearts
description: Analysis of hearts lacking caveolin-1 (Cav1), the primary protein component of caveolae in non-muscle cells. Cav1 deficiency leads to cardiac hypertrophy and contractile dysfunction. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying cardiac hypertrophy induced by Cav1 deficiency.

title: Caveolin-3 deficiency effect on hearts
description: Analysis of hearts lacking caveolin-3 (Cav3), the primary protein component of caveolae in muscle cells. Cav3 deficiency leads to cardiac hypertrophy and contractile dysfunction. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying cardiac hypertrophy induced by Cav3 deficiency.

title: Monocytes and macrophages (RNG/MRC)
description: Comparison of monocytes and macrophages. Samples obtained from 86 patients with acute coronary syndrome. Results used as a reference to compare the performance of Affymetrix (GDS3554) and Illumina (GDS3555) arrays.

title: Monocytes and macrophages (Affymetrix)
description: Comparison of monocytes and macrophages. Samples obtained from patients with acute coronary syndrome. Results compared to the performance of Illumina arrays (GDS3555).  The result from two-color arrays (GDS3553) was used as a reference for the Illumina and Affymetrix arrays.

title: Monocytes and macrophages (Illumina)
description: Comparison of monocytes and macrophages. Samples obtained from patients with acute coronary syndrome. Results compared to the performance of Affymetrix arrays (GDS3554).  The result from two-color arrays (GDS3553) was used as a reference for the Illumina and Affymetrix arrays.

title: Torcetrapib effect on adrenal carcinoma cell line
description: Analysis of H295 adrenal carcinoma cells treated with torcetrapib, an anti-cholesterol drug. Adverse side effects of torcetrapib treatment include changes in blood pressure, potassium, sodium, and aldosterone. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the off-target side effects.

title: ERG transcription factor depletion effect on endothelial cell
description: Analysis of endothelial HUVEC cells depleted for the ETS-related gene (ERG) product.  ERG is a member of the ETS family of transcription factors. Results provide insight into the role of ERG in the regulation of normal endothelial cell function.

title: Deferasirox effect on leukemia cell line: dose response
description: Analysis of leukemia K562 cells treated with 10 or 50 uM deferasirox. Deferasirox is an iron chelator taken orally to treat iron toxicity. Iron depletion by deferasirox inhibits cancer cell proliferation in vitro. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of this anti-proliferative effect.

title: Occupational benzene exposure: peripheral blood mononuclear cells (HG-U133A)
description: Analysis of peripheral blood mononuclear cells from shoe factory workers exposed to benzene. Benzene is a leukemogen. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms of benzene carcinogenicity.

title: Occupational benzene exposure: peripheral blood mononuclear cells (HG-U133B)
description: Analysis of peripheral blood mononuclear cells from shoe factory workers exposed to benzene. Benzene is a leukemogen. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms of benzene carcinogenicity.

title: Occupational benzene exposure: peripheral blood mononuclear cells (HumanRef-8)
description: Analysis of peripheral blood mononuclear cells from shoe factory workers exposed to benzene. Benzene is a leukemogen. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms of benzene carcinogenicity.

title: Azithromycin effect on Pseudomonas aeruginosa PAO1
description: Analysis of PAO1 cultures exposed to up to 2.0 ug/ml of the macrolide azithromycin (AZM) for 9 hours. Low-dose macrolides are effective therapy in patients with chronic lung infections such as those caused by P. aeruginosa. Results provide insight into mechanism of action of AZM against infection.

title: Rapid stimulation effect on an in vitro atrial (HL-1) myocyte model
description: Analysis of spontaneously contracting HL-1 atrial cells rapidly stimulated for 24 hr. The resulting electrical remodeling of the HL-1 cells resembles that seen in atrial fibrillation (AF)/atrial tachycardia (AT). Results provide insight into the molecular basis of early atrial myocyte remodeling.

title: RNA-binding protein khd4 deletion effect on a pathogenic basidiomycete fungus
description: Analysis of pathogenic basidiomycete fungus Ustilago maydis deficient for khd4. Deletion of RNA-binding protein khd4 leads to abnormal cell morphology, reduced mating, and virulence.  Results provide insight into the role of RNA-binding proteins in the pathogenic development of U. maydis.

title: Mutant transcription factor ThPOK effect on memory P14 T cells
description: Analysis of CD8 P14 memory cells from helper-deficient (hd/hd) animals harboring a mutation in the gene encoding ThPOK. Clonal expansion is significantly reduced in CD8 T cells lacking functional ThPOK. Results provide insight into the role of ThPOK in CD8 T cell response to acute viral infection.

title: VEGF-A effect on endothelial cell line: time course (HG-U133 Plus 2.0)
description: Analysis of umbilical vein endothelial cells (HUVEC) treated with VEGF-A for up to 150 minutes in vitro.  VEGF-A is a major trigger of vasculogenesis and physiologic angiogenesis. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying the vasculogenic and angiogenic activity of VEGF-A.

title: VEGF-A effect on endothelial cell line: time course (HG-U133A)
description: Analysis of umbilical vein endothelial cells (HUVEC) treated with VEGF-A or EGF for up to 6 hours. VEGF-A is a major trigger of vasculogenesis and angiogenesis. EGF is a general growth factor. Results provide insight into the mechanisms underlying the vasculogenic and angiogenic activity of VEGF-A.

title: VEGF-A effect on endothelial cell line: time course (HG-U133B)
description: Analysis of umbilical vein endothelial cells (HUVEC) treated with VEGF-A for up to 6 hours in vitro.  VEGF-A is a major trigger of vasculogenesis and physiologic angiogenesis. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying the vasculogenic and angiogenic activity of VEGF-A.

title: Jag1 expression effect on endometrial stromal cells
description: Analysis of endometrial stromal cells engineered to have an increased expression of Jag1. Jag1 is a Notch ligand. Results provide insight into the role of Notch signaling in endometrial cells.

title: Pseduomonas aeruginosa PAO1 response to subinhibitory colistin
description: Analysis of Pseduomonas aeruginosa PAO1 treated with colistin at a subinhibitory concentration (0.15 ug/ml). Colistin is an antimicrobial peptide against P. aeruginosa infection in cystic fibrosis lungs. Result provide insight into the adaptive response of P. aeruginosa to low doses of colistin.

title: Chlamydia pneumonia infection effect on dendritic cells
description: Analysis of monocyte-derived dendritic cells infected with Chlamydia pneumonia. C. pneumonia is a human respiratory pathogen associated with various chronic diseases such as asthma and atherosclerosis. Results provide insight into the host defense response to C. pneumonia infections.

title: Zfp36l2 deficiency effect on the fetal liver
description: Analysis of E14.5 fetal livers lacking Zfp36l2, a member of the tristetraprolin family of tandem CCCH zinc finger proteins. Knockout animals exhibit pancytopenia and decreased hematopoietic progenitor cells from fetal liver.  Results provide insight into the role of Zfp36l2 in hematopoiesis.

title: Aryl hydrocarbon receptor deficiency effect on Langerhan cells
description: Analysis of Langerhan cells (LCs) lacking the aryl hydrocarbon receptor (AhR). LCs are Ag-presenting cells of the epidermis. AhR is a ligand-activated transcription factor involved in low molecular mass chemical metabolism and cell differentiation. Results provide insight into the role of AhR in LC.

title: Diamond-Blackfan anaemia: fibroblasts
description: Analysis of fibroblasts from patients with Diamond-Blackfan anaemia (DBA). DBA is a rare inherited red cell hypoplasia characterized by a defect in the maturation of erythroid progenitors. Results provide insight into the involvement of non-hematopoietic tissues in DBA pathogenesis.

title: Cbfbeta deficiency effect on regulatory T cells
description: Analysis of regulatory T cells lacking Cbfbeta. Cbfbeta is a cofactor for the Runx family of transcription factors. Results provide insight into the role of the Runx1-Cbfbeta transcription complex in regulatory T cell function.

title: Beta-catenin depletion effect on multiple myeloma cell line
description: Analysis of multiple myeloma MM1.S cells depleted for beta-catenin. Beta-catenin is an effector of the Wnt signaling pathway. Results provide insight into the role of Wnt/beta-catenin signaling in the progression of multiple myeloma.

title: Fer-1 null mutants
description: Analysis of fer-1 loss of function C. elegans mutants. The fer-1 gene encodes a homolog for the human Dysferlin gene. Mutations in the human Dysferlin gene results in Limb Girdle Muscular Dystrophy 2B (LGMD2B). Results provide insight into the molecular pathogenesis of LGMD2B.

title: Pulmonary sarcoidosis
description: Analysis of lungs from patients with pulmonary sarcoidosis (PS). PS is characterized by the granulomatous inflammation of the lung. Results provide insight into the molecular pathogenesis of PS.

title: Anti-mitotic compound MT7 effect on immortalized cell line: time course
description: Analysis of HeLa cells treated for up to 12 hrs with MT7, an anti-mitotic compound from a combinatorial library. MT7 inhibits cell proliferation by arresting mitosis specifically and reversibly in various tumor cell lines of human origin. Results provide insight into the mechanism of action of MT7.

title: PTEN heterozygosity effect on Smoothened-active mouse model
description: Analysis of medulloblastoma (MB) tumors from mice heterozygous for PTEN. SmoA1 +; Pten +/- mice exhibited decreased survival, an increased incidence, and a shorter time to onset of symptoms, compared to SmoA1 +; Pten +/+ mice. Results provide insight into the role of PTEN in the pathogenesis of MB.

title: GR24 effect on strigolactone-deficient mutant seedlings
description: Analysis of ecotype Columbia, strigolactone (SL)-deficient mutant seedlings treated with GR24 (1uM), a synthetic SL analog. SLs regulate shoot branching. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying SL signaling.

title: Quinine effect on yeast eukaryotic model
description: Analysis of Saccharomyces cerevisiae cells subjected to anti-malaria drug quinine (QN) at concentration that exerted a very slight effect on cellular growth. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying QN action and the host response to the drug.

title: Ovarian normal surface epithelia and ovarian cancer epithelial cells
description: Comparison of normal ovarian surface epithelia (OSE) and ovarian cancer epithelial cells (CEPIs). CEPIs were isolated by laser capture microdissection from serous papillary ovarian adenocarcinomas. Results provide insight into the role of OSE in the development of ovarian adenocarcinoma.

title: Heat-shocked embryonic fibroblast response to lipopolysaccharide
description: Analysis of embryonic fibroblasts subjected to heat shock and then treated with lipolysaccharide (LPS). LPS induces the expression of inflammatory genes. Results provide insight into the mechanisms underlying the fever-mediated suppression of inflammatory gene expression.

title: Low-salt diet effect on the heart
description: Analysis of hearts from animals on a low-salt diet for two weeks. Reduced sodium intake inversely correlates with cardiac mortality in hypertensive patients. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the detrimental effect of low-salt diets on the heart.

title: Macrophage response to H1N1 and H5N1 influenza viral infections
description: Analysis of macrophages at 1, 3, and 6 hours post-infection with H1N1 or H5N1 viruses in vitro. The avian H5N1 virus is highly pathogenic, while the swine H1N1 virus is less so. Alveolar macrophages are targets of H5N1. Results provide insight into the host response to H1N1 and H5N1 infections.

title: Isoproterenol-induced cardiomyopathy and exercise-induced cardiac hypertrophy
description: Comparison of hearts of C57BL/6 males with isoproterenol-induced cardiomyopathy to those with exercise-induced cardiac hypertrophy. Results provide insight into the molecular differences between pathological and physiological cardiac hypertrophy models.

title: Increased cell membrane saturated fatty acid effect on Escherichia coli
description: Analysis of Escherichia coli cells treated with CHIR-090, an inhibitor of lipid A bioynthesis, to increase the ratio of saturated to unsaturated fatty acids (SFA:UFA) in the cell membrane. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms regulating membrane lipid homeostasis in E. coli.

title: p300 genetic reduction model of Rubinstein-Taybi syndrome: hippocampus
description: Analysis of hippocampi from heterozygous p300 deletion animals. A small percentage of cases of Rubinstein-Taybi syndrome (RSTS) is caused by p300 mutations. Results provide insight in the contribution of p300 to RSTS pathoetiology.

title: Eset depletion effect on embryonic stem cell
description: Analysis of embryonic stem (ES) cells following shRNA knock-down of Eset. Eset is a histone H3 lysine 9 (H3K9) methyltransferase critical for development of the inner cell mass (ICM) from which ES cells are derived. Results provide insight into the role of Eset in ES cell differentiation.

title: Endothelial cell response to estradiol in vitro
description: Analysis of cultured umbilical vein endothelial cells treated with 1 nmol/L estradiol for 24 hours. The incidence of coronary heart disease in women increases after menopause. Results provide insight into the response of the cardiovascular system to estrogens at the molecular level.

title: Obesity: adipocyte expression profile (HG-U95A)
description: Analysis of cultured abdominal subcutaneous mature adipocytes from 4 male and 5 female non-diabetic obese Pima Indians. The prevalence of obesity in Pima Indians is among the highest of any population. Results provide insight into the role of adipocytes in obesity and obesity-related inflammation.

title: Obesity: adipocyte expression profile (HG-U95Av2)
description: Analysis of cultured abdominal subcutaneous mature adipocytes from 5 male and 5 female non-diabetic obese Pima Indians. The prevalence of obesity in Pima Indians is among the highest of any population. Results provide insight into the role of adipocytes in obesity and obesity-related inflammation.

title: Renal cancer response to rapamycin analog CCI-779 treatment:
description: Expression profiling of peripheral blood mononuclear cells (PBMC) from patients with advanced renal cancer following treatment with the rapamycin analog CCI-779. Gene expression examined 8 and 16 weeks after treatment. Results identify potential gene markers of CCI-779 exposure.

title: Tamoxifen effect on endometrioid carcinomas
description: Analysis of endometrial epithelial cells from stage I or II endometrioid carcinomas after treatment with oestrogen or tamoxifen (TMX). Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the association of TMX treatment of breast cancer with an increased incidence of endometrial cancer.

title: Spared nerve injury model of peripheral neuropathic pain: dorsal horn of spinal cord
description: Analysis of adult and neonatal dorsal horns of spinal cords 7 days after spared nerve injury (SNI). SNI is a model for neuropathic pain (NP). Partial peripheral nerve injury in adults result in NP-like hypersensitivity, but not in neonates. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of NP.

title: Myeloid leukemia cell response to thrombopoietin receptor agonist SB-559457 in vitro
description: Analysis of primary cultured myeloid leukemia cells treated with recombinant human thrombopoietin or the thrombopoietin receptor agonist SB-559457 (SB). SB is toxic to leukemia cells. Results provide insight into the mechanism of action of SB.

title: Egr-1 deficiency effect on retina during eye development
description: Analysis of retinas of Egr-1 deficient animals at post-natal days 30 and 42. 42 day-old Egr-1 knockout animals have longer eyes and a more myopic refractive error compared to wild-types. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms regulating axial eye growth.

title: Liver response to perinatal exposure to 2,2',4,4'-tetrabromodiphenyl ether: dose response
description: Analysis of livers of animals exposed to low doses of 2,2',4,4'-tetrabromodiphenyl ether (BDE-47) from gestational day 15 to post-natal day 20. Polybrominated diphenyl ethers are flame-retardant chemicals used in consumer products. Results provide insight into the mechanisms of toxicity of BDE-47.

title: Syk depletion effect on breast epithelial cell line
description: Analysis of MCF10A breast epithelial cells depleted for Syk. Progressive loss of Syk mRNA occurs during breast tumor development. Results provide insight into Syk’s tumor suppressor function and role in normal breast development.

title: Nasopharyngeal carcinoma
description: Analysis of biopsies from patients with Epstein-Barr virus (EBV)-positive undifferentiated nasopharyngeal carcinoma (NPC). NPC is a common cancer in China and Southeast Asia. Results provide insight into the molecular pathogenesis of NPC.

title: Claudin16 deficiency effect on kidneys
description: Analysis of kidneys from animals deficient for Claudin16. Mutations in Caludin16 are associated with renal Ca2+ and Mg2+ wasting, nephrocalcinosis and progressive renal insufficiency in humans. Results provide insight into the role of Caludin16 in Ca2+ and Mg2+ homeostasis.

title: Luteolin effect on pro-inflammatory challenged microglial cell line
description: Analysis of lipopolysaccharide-activated microglial BV-2 cells treated with luteolin, a plant derived flavonoid. Luteolin possesses the ability to scavenge oxygen and nitrogen species, and exhibits anti-inflammatory activities. Results provide insight into the immuno-modulatory effects of luteolin.

title: Asthma exacerbation and convalescent phases: peripheral blood mononuclear cells
description: Analysis of peripheral blood mononuclear cells of children with acute asthma during exacerbation and at subsequent convalescence. Severe asthma exacerbations in children are associated with viral infection and occur among atopics. Results provide insight into the significance of these comorbidities.

title: Primary coenzyme Q deficient liver response to probucol (430 2.0)
description: Analysis of livers from B6.Alb/cre,Pdss2(loxP/loxP) animals following treatment with probucol, an antioxidant/antihyperlipidemic agent. Results used to evaluate the performance of Affymetrix 430 2.0 in comparison to Affymetrix Gene 1.0 ST, and Illumina Mouse WG-6.

title: Primary coenzyme Q deficient liver response to probucol (Gene 1.0 ST)
description: Analysis of livers from B6.Alb/cre,Pdss2(loxP/loxP) animals following treatment with probucol, an antioxidant/antihyperlipidemic agent. Results used to evaluate the performance of Affymetrix Gene 1.0 ST in comparison to Affymetrix 430 2.0, and Illumina Mouse WG-6.

title: Primary coenzyme Q deficient liver response to probucol (WG-6 2.0)
description: Analysis of livers from B6.Alb/cre,Pdss2(loxP/loxP) animals following treatment with probucol, an antioxidant/antihyperlipidemic agent. Results used to evaluate the performance of Illumina Mouse WG-6 in comparison to Affymetrix 430 2.0, and Affymetrix Gene 1.0 ST.

title: Huntington disease model: brain striatum (430 2.0)
description: Analysis of brain striata from YAC128 trangenic animals at 12 and 24 months of age. The YAC128 transgenic animal is a model for Huntington disease (HD). Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of HD.

title: Huntington disease model: brain striatum (Ref-6 V1)
description: Analysis of brain striata from YAC128 trangenic animals at 12 and 24 months of age. The YAC128 transgenic animal is a model for Huntington disease (HD). Results provide insight into the pathogenesis of HD.

title: Nrf2-deficient lung response to cigarette smoke: dose response and time course
description: Analysis of lungs from transcription factor Nrf2-deficient animals exposed to cigarette smoke (CS) at various doses and for various lengths of time with or without a subsequent recovery period. Results provide insight into the impact of Nrf2 in acute and subchronic smoking scenarios.

title: Heart regeneration in zebrafish
description: Analysis of hearts of zebrafish 1 to 7 days following partial heart amputation. Unlike mammals, zebrafish hearts display an extensive regenerative capacity. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of this regenerative capacity.

title: Neurotrophin-3 effect on ovaries in vitro
description: Analysis of 4 day old ovaries cultured in the presence of neurotrophin-3 (NT3) for 2 days.  Neurotrophins are growth factors involved in promoting cell survival and differentiation. Results provide insight into the role of NT3 in ovarian primordial follicle development.

title: Heart atrium and ventricle
description: Comparison of heart atrial appendages and ventricular free walls. Unlike ventricular muscle cells, atrial muscle cells produce the hormones atrial natriuretic factor and brain natriuretic peptide. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of this phenotypic difference.

title: Macrophage migration inhibitory factor depletion effect on kidney cell line
description: Analysis of HEK293 kidney cells depleted for the macrophage migration inhibitory factor (MIF). MIF depletion in HEK293 cells result in G(0)/G(1) cell cycle arrest. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying this cell cycle arrest.

title: Non-small lung cancer subtypes: adenocarcinoma and squamous cell carcinoma
