description: Analysis of HMEC-TR cells silenced for TIF1γ or Smad4 and treated with TGFβ. A strong EMT increase was observed in TIF1γ-silenced cells after TGFβ1 treatment;  Smad4 inactivation completely blocked this process. Results show the relationship between TIF1γ and Smad4 in TGF-β signaling and EMT.

title: Zinc finger transcription factor induced fulvestrant resistant MCF7-R73 breast cancer cell lines
description: Analysis of fulvestrant-sensitive MCF7-R73 cells retrovirally induced with various zinc finger transcription factors. Six unique ZF-TFs conferred stable fulvestrant-resistance. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying acquired fulvestrant-resistance in breast cancer cells.

title: Genetically engineered murine models of human breast cancer
description: Analysis eight well-characterized genetically engineered mouse (GEM) models of human breast cancer , including MMTV-H-Ras, -Her2/neu, -c-Myc, -PymT, -Wnt1 and C3(1)/SV40 T/t-antigen transgenic mice, BRCA1(fl/fl);p53(+/-);MMTV-cre knock-out mice and the p53(fl/fl);MMTV-cre transplant model.

title: Acquired paclitaxel-resistant MDA-MB-231 cancer cells response to bexarotene treatment
description: Analysis of acquired paclitaxel (PTX)-resistant MDA-MB-231 cells treated with bexarotene-PTX or PTX. Retinoid X receptor-selective agonist bexarotene was efficacious in treating chemo-resistant cancer cells. Results provide insight into bexarotene’s role in overcoming acquired drug resistance.

title: Breast lipotransfer white adipose tissue CD34+ cells
description: Analysis of white adipose tissue (WAT) CD34+ cells from breast lipotransfer aspirates and marrow-derived CD34+ cells from leukapheresis of normal patients. WAT is a rich reservoir of CD45-CD34+ endothelial progenitor cells (EPC). Results provide insight into role of WAT CD34+ cells in cancer growth.

title: GATA3 ectopic expression effect on MDA-MB-231 breast cancer cells
description: Analysis of MDA-MB-231 cells transduced with a lentivirus expressing GATA3. Luminal transcriptional regulator GATA3 reduces tumorigenicity and metastases of basal triple negative breast cancers (TNBC). Results provide insight into molecular basis of GATA3-mediated reduction of TNBC metastases.

title: Effect of full-term pregnancy or hormone treatment on inguinal left mammary gland
description: Analysis of mammary gland of metestrus Lewis females randomly assigned to 3 groups: control, pregnancy, or hormone (exogenous estrogen and progesterone). Full-term pregnancy or treatment with hormone reduces breast cancer risk. Results provide insight into molecular basis of the protective effect.

title: Trans-retinoic acid and hydrocortisone induction of Na+/I- symporter in MCF-7 breast cancer cells
description: Analysis of MCF7 cells induced to express endogenous Na+/I- symporter (NIS). NIS expression raises potential for radionuclide therapy of breast cancer. However, NIS expression in most breast cancers is low. Results provide insight into mechanisms underlying NIS modulation in breast cancer.

title: Lapatinib-resistant HER2-positive breast tumor cells
description: Analysis of BT474 (lapatinib-sensitive) and BT474-J4 (acquired lapatinib-resistance) HER2+ breast cancer cells treated with lapatinib, foretinib or both. Foretinib restored lapatinib-sensitivity in BT474-J4. Results provide insight into molecular basis of acquired lapatinib-resistance in BC cells.

title: Doxorubicin-resistant MCF-7/ADR breast cancer cells
description: Analysis of weakly tumorigenic parental MCF-7 cells and a multistep doxorubicin-selected MCF-7/ADR subline. Results provide insight into whether prolonged continuous selection of cells for drug resistance enriches for cancer stem-like cells.

title: Estrogen receptor-positive and -negative breast cancer tumors
description: Analysis of primary breast carcinoma tumors from estrogen receptor positive or negative (ER+/-) patients. ER+ tumors tend to metastasize to the bone while ER- tumors tend to induce visceral metastasis. Results provide insight into molecular basis of different metastatic phenotypes in breast cancer.

title: Variable breast cancer tumor sample collection methods
description: Analysis of breast tumor samples preserved using 2 different RNA stabilization methods (RNAlater or snap freezing) up to 3 hours post tumor excision. Results provide insight into the effects of tissue handling on RNA integrity and microarray measurements from resected breast cancers.

title: Proteasome inhibitor Bortezomib effect on MCF7 breast cancer cells
description: Analysis of MCF7 cells stimulated with bortezomib (velcade). Proteasome inhibition can regulate estrogen-induced transcription. Results provide insight into the mechanisms by which proteasome inhibition influences ERα function and may uncover improved strategies for the treatment of breast cancer.

title: Proteasome inhibitor Bortezomib or proteasome subunit knockdown effect on MCF7 breast cancer cells
description: Analysis of MCF7 cells stimulated with bortezomib or depleted of PSMB3 or PSMB5. Proteasome inhibition can regulate estrogen-induced transcription. Results provide insight into mechanisms by which proteasome inhibition influences ERα function and into improved strategies for breast cancer treatment

title: Cancer stem cell population in highly metastatic variants of MDA-MB-231 breast cancer cell line
description: Analysis of CD24-/CD44+/ESA+ cancer stem cells from MDA-MB-231 breast cancer (BC) cell line and its highly metastatic variants 231BoM-1833 and 231BrM-2a. The majority of BC deaths are attributed to metastatic disease. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of metastatic progression.

title: Breast cancer cell lines treated with methylated or unmethylated DNA oligos
description: Analysis of breast cancer cell lines BT-20 and Hs578T treated with methylated or un-methylated CpG DNA oligos: CDH13 and ODN 2006. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms triggered by methylated, but not by unmethylated DNA, that could be involved in tumour biology.

title: Anastrozole/Fulvestrant/Gefitinib neoadjuvant therapy of estrogen receptor positive breast cancer patients: tumor core biopsies
description: Analysis of pre and post (3 wk) tumor core biopsies of postmenopausal women with ER+, HER2- breast cancer (BC) in neoadjuvant trial of anastrozole and fulvestrant with/without gefitinib. Results provide insight into mechanisms of resistance and inhibition of hormone receptors targeted in BC therapy.

title: E2F transcription factor knockdown effect on Myc-induced mammary tumors
description: Analysis of MMTV-Myc tumors generated in an E2F wild-type, E2F1 null, E2F2 null or E2F3 heterozygous background. E2Fs are Myc transcriptional activators shown to regulate proliferation and apoptosis. Results provide insight into role of E2Fs in Myc-induced breast cancer.

title: Tamoxifen effect on SRC-1-deficient endocrine-resistant breast cancer cell line LY2
description: Analysis of endocrine-resistant LY2 breast cancer cells depleted of p160 steroid coactivator protein SRC-1 and treated with tamoxifen. SRC-1 is central to the development of the endocrine resistant phenotype. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of endocrine resistant breast cancer.

title: Mutant p53 depletion effect on MDA-468.shp53 breast tumor cell line
description: Analysis of MDA-468.shp53 cells cultured under 3D conditions in the presence of DOX.  These cells express a DOX-inducible shRNA targeting endogenous mutant p53. The p53-reduced cells have an invasive, highly disorganized appearance. Results provide insight into role of mutant p53 in breast cancer.

title: Human Epidermal Growth Factor Receptor 2-positive breast cancer MMTV-Her2/Neu murine model: primary and secondary mammary tumors
description: Analysis of primary MMTV-Neu mammary tumors and secondary tumors generated by lin- cell transplantation or by single tumor-initiating cell (TIC) transplantation. Results enable molecular comparisons between the primary and secondary tumors.

title: Saliva of pre-treatment pancreatic cancer patients
description: Analysis of saliva supernatant from pancreatic cancer patients and healthy subjects. Oral fluid (saliva) meets the demand for non-invasive, accessible, and highly efficient diagnostic medium. Results provide insight into salivary biomarkers for detection of pancreatic cancer.

title: Response of pancreatic and colorectal cancer cells to CD24 down-regulation by monoclonal antibody or small interfering RNA
description: Analysis of HT29 and Colo357 cancer cell lines following treatment with anti-CD24 mAbs, and HT29 cells after expression of 1 or 2 shRNA vectors directed at the CD24 gene. CD24 is overexpressed in a large variety of human malignancies. Results provide insight into the role of CD4 in carcinogenesis.

title: Pancreatic Tumor and Normal tissue samples
description: Analysis of tumor tissue and normal tissue in pancreatic cancer samples. The fresh frozen samples were obtained during surgical procedures. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying tumorigenesis.

title: ICF cohort: Whole-tissue pancreatic ductal adenocarcinoma
description: Analysis of pancreatic ductal adenocarcinoma (PDAC) tumors and matching normal pancreatic tissue from ICF pancreatic cancer patients. PDAC is an aggressive, rapidly disseminating, desmoplastic cancer with poor prognosis. Results provide insight into molecular processes involved in PDAC pathology.

title: Long-term heat-stress effect on skeletal muscle
description: Analysis of skeletal muscle from eight healthy men following a 10-week application of heat stress (8 hours/day, 4 days/week) on the quadriceps muscles without exercise training. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms involved in the muscular adaptation to heat stress.

title: Masitinib-gemcitabin effect on gemcitabine-refractory Mia Paca-2 pancreatic tumor cell line
description: Analysis of Mia Paca2 cells after treatment with masitinib combined with standard gemcitabine chemotherapy. Masitinib is a tyrosine kinase inhibitor of c-Kit, PDGFRα and β. Results provide insight into the therapeutic potential of masitinib in vitro on human pancreatic tumor cell lines.

title: Transforming growth factor beta effect on Panc-1 pancreatic adenocarcinoma cell line
description: Analysis of Panc-1 cells treated with TGFβ to induce epithelial-mesenchymal transition. During EMT, cancer cells lose epithelial specific proteins and gain mesenchymal proteins to acquire migratory/invasive phenotype essential for metastasis. Results provide insight into molecular basis of EMT.

title: KUCaP-2 xenograft model of castration-resistant prostate cancer: various stages
description: Analysis of KUCaP-2 xenograft tissues transplanted into mice and collected during androgen-dependent growth (AD), castration-induced regression nadir (ND), and castration-resistant regrowth (CR) stages. Results provide insight into molecular basis of castration-resistant prostate cancer development.

title: Prostate response to activated form of p110β isoform of PI3-kinase
description: Analysis of ventral prostate from transgenics expressing a constitutively activated p110β allele in prostate. Activation of the p110β isoform causes mouse prostatic intraepithelial neoplasia (mPIN). Results provide insight into ability of an activated allele of p110β to induce prostatic tumor.

title: Recurrent and non-recurrent prostate cancer primary tumors
description: Analysis of prostate cancer primary tumors of known disease recurrence status. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying recurrent and non-recurrent prostate cancer primary tumors.

title: Inactivation of wt-p53 function in hTERT immortalized prostate epithelial EP156T cells: time course
description: Temporal analysis of EP156T cells infected with a recombinant retrovirus encoding either p53R175H mutant (M cells), dominant-negative p53 peptide GSE56 (G cells) or control vector (C cells). Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying early stages of transformation.

title: Late passage LNCaP prostate tumor cells treated with androgen receptor shRNA or androgen R1881
description: Analysis of late passage (LP50) LNCaP cells treated with AR shRNA or control shRNA, grown in hormone-free media to deplete androgen, and treated with androgen R1881 or vehicle. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying acquired androgen independence of late passage LNCaP cells.

title: Reactive stroma of breast and prostate cancer
description: Analysis of stroma associated with prostate and breast invasive tumors. Stromal reaction (tumor-associated tissue remodeling) occurs in various cancers. Results provide insight into whether this stromal response is largely a generic phenomenon or whether it reflects tumor-specific properties.

title: Diabetogenic 3A9 T-cell transfer model of type I diabetes: pancreatic islets
description: Analysis of islet cells after injection of diabetogenic 3A9 CD4 T cells into nondiabetic B10.BR IP-HEL recipients, 8 to 24 hrs post-transfer. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying the T-cell entry induced state of receptivity of islets to subsequent immunological insults.

title: Diabetogenic BDC T-cell transfer model of type I diabetes: pancreatic islets
description: Analysis of pancreatic islets after injection of diabetogenic BDC CD4 T cells into nondiabetic NOD Rag1-/- recipients, 24 to 48 hrs post-transfer. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying the T-cell entry induced state of receptivity of islets to subsequent immunological insults.

title: Tumor suppressor PTEN re-expression effect on PTEN-null embryonic fibroblasts: time course
description: Analysis of Pten-null (PtenΔloxp/Δloxp) mouse embryonic fibroblasts (MEFs) carrying a tet-inducible PTEN transgene, up to 48 hrs after PTEN induction. Castration resistant prostate cancer (CRPC) is associated with PTEN loss. Results provide insight into molecular basis of PTEN regulation of CRPC.

title: Model for inflammatory signaling in prostate epithelium based on expression of a constitutively active version of IκB kinase 2 (IKK2ca)
description: Analysis of prostate epithelium (PE)-PTEN+/-IKK2ca/ca and PE-PTEN+/- lateral prostates. PE-PTEN+/-IKK2ca prostates exhibit loss of smooth muscle but fail to induce invasiveness. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanism of inflammation and tumor development in the transgenic prostates.

title: Androgen deprivation effect on prostate xenograft tumor LuCaP35
description: NOD/SCID mice with established LuCaP35 xenografts were castrated, and tumors were isolated 4 weeks later. Androgen deprivation regresses androgen-dependent disease, but relapse often occurs in an androgen-independent manner. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of castration resistance.

title: Hepatocyte growth factor treatment of prostate cancer DU145 cell line: time course
description: Analysis of DU145 prostate cancer cells treated with hepatocyte growth factor (HGF) for up to 24 hrs. HGF receptor c-MET is specifically expressed in immature prostate cells. Results provide insight into the role of immature cells in prostate cancer by analysis of the HGF/c-MET pathway.

title: Isoflavone and 3,3’-diindolylmethane effect on C4-2B prostate cancer cells
description: Analysis of C4-2B prostate cancer (PCa) cells treated with isoflavone (IsoF) and 3,3’- diindolylmethane (B-DIM) for up to 72 hours. IsoF and B-DIM inhibited the signal transductions in PCa signaling. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying PCa growth.

title: Genetic reprogramming of prostate cancer-associated stromal cells
description: Analysis of induced pluripotent stem cells (iPSCs) obtained from sorted CD90+ prostate cancer (CP)-associated stromal cells cultured and transfected with stem cell transcription factor POU5F1/LIN28/NANOG/SOX2 expression vectors. Results provide insight into the stemness of CP stromal-derived iPSCs.

title: Pten-null, K-ras-activated prostate cancer model
description: Analysis of prostate tumors from mutants with prostate-specific Pten loss and K-ras activation. In murine models, PTEN deletion alone fails to mimic end stage of human prostate cancer (PC). Results provide insight into cooperation between PTEN loss and RAS activation to promote EMT and metastasis.

title: Model of cerebral aging and Alzheimer's disease: temporal cortex
description: Analysis of temporal cortex of young adult, old healthy, and Alzheimer’s disease (AD-like) animals. AD-like animals presented ß-amyloid plaques and cortical atrophy, which are signs of AD in humans. Results provided insight into molecular basis of physiological versus pathological brain aging.

title: Endoplasmic reticulum stress effect on lymphoblastoid cells of unrelated individuals
description: Analysis of immortalized B cells from 60 unrelated individuals (grandparents in the HapMap CEPH-Utah pedigrees) treated in vitro with tunicamycin to induce ER stress.  ER stress induces the unfolded protein response (UPR). Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying UPR response.

title: Endoplasmic reticulum stress effect on lymphoblastoid cells of monozygotic twins
description: Analysis of immortalized B cells from MZ twin pairs (14 of European ancestry, 12 African American) treated in vitro with thapsigargin to induce ER stress.  ER stress induces the unfolded protein response (UPR). Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the UPR response within twin pairs.

title: Embryonic cranial neural crest and neural plate
description: Analysis of cranial neural folds/plates from Hamburger & Hamilton stage 8 (HH8) embryos. Neural crest cells are a transient stem cell-like population appearing during vertebrate embryonic development. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying generation of cranial neural crest.

title: PPAR-γ agonist pioglitazone effect on obese women with polycystic ovary syndrome: skeletal muscle
description: Analysis of skeletal muscle from obese women with polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS) before and after thiazolidinedione (TZD) pioglitazone treatment. TZDs improve metabolic disturbances in PCOS patients. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying the effect of TZD in PCOS.

title: Obese women with polycystic ovary syndrome and obese, healthy women: skeletal muscle
description: Analysis of skeletal muscle from obese women with polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS) and obese, healthy women. Results provide insight into whether pioglitazone ameliorates preexisting abnormalities in PCOS patients.

title: Amyloid precursor protein double mutant and amyloid precursor-like protein 2 deficiency effects on adult brain regions
description: Analysis of prefrontal cortices and hippocampi from C57BL/6 adults: APLP2-KO (APLP2-/-) or APPsα-DM (APPα/αAPLP2-/-). Amyloid precursor protein (APP) and AP-like protein 2 (APLP2) play key roles in Alzheimer pathogenesis. Results provide mechanistic insights into APP/APLP2-mediated functions.

title: Postmortem temporal cortex from Medical Research Council Cognitive Function and Ageing Study (MRC-CFAS) cohort: astrocytes
description: Analysis of GFAP+ astrocytes representing different Braak stages and ApoE genotypes, in post-mortem temporal cortex samples. Astrocytes synthesize ApoE, which is involved in the astrocytic clearance of aggregated β-amyloid plaques. Results provide insight into role of ApoE in Alzheimer's pathology.

title: Various stages of Alzheimer's disease: laser-captured hippocampal CA1 gray matter
description: Analysis of laser-captured hippocampal CA1 gray matter from FFPE hippocampal sections of subjects at varying stages (incipient, moderate, severe) of Alzheimer’s disease (AD). Results provide insight into gray matter-specific molecular mechanisms underlying AD.

title: Nasu-Hakola disease model: DAP12 knockdown THP-1 clones
description: Analysis of DAP12-deficient acute monocytic leukemia THP-1 cells that serve as a model of NHD, following treatment with 12-myristate 13-acetate (PMA).  PMA is a known inducer of morphological differentiation of THP-1 cells. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying NHD pathology.

title: Proteasomal inhibitor lactacystin effect on cortical neurons in vitro: time course (MG_U74A)
description: Analysis of cultured cortical neurons treated with 1uM lactacystin for up to 48 hr. Lactacystin induces neuronal apoptosis. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying proteasomal inhibition-induced neuronal death.

title: Proteasomal inhibitor lactacystin effect on cortical neurons in vitro: time course (MG_U74Av2)
description: Analysis of cultured cortical neurons treated with 1uM lactacystin for up to 48 hr. Lactacystin induces neuronal apoptosis. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying proteasomal inhibition-induced neuronal death.

title: Alzheimer's disease: induced pluripotent stem cells with Presenilin 2 mutation (N141)
description: Analysis of 2 iPSC clones with presenilin 2 (PS2) mutation N141, established by retroviral transduction of fibroblasts from a Familial Alzheimer’s disease (FAD) patient. PS2 mutations are causative factors for autosomal-dominant early-onset FAD. Results provide insight into molecular basis of FAD.

title: Perforin 1 polymorphism effect on male patients with primary progressive multiple sclerosis: peripheral blood mononuclear cells
description: Analysis of PBMCs from primary-progressive multiple sclerosis (PPMS) male patients carrying risk (GAA/AGA) or protective (AGA/AGA) perforin 1 (PRF1) haplotypes. Results provide insight into associations between PRF1 polymorphisms and male patients with MS, particularly male patients with PPMS.

title: High fat diet effect on prostate: ventral prostate lobe
description: Analysis of ventral prostate lobe from 8-week-old C57BL/6J males fed a high fat diet for 12 weeks. High fat diets are a risk factor for prostate cancer. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms by which high fat diet can promote carcinogenesis.

title: High fat diet effect on prostate: dorsolateral prostate lobe
description: Analysis of dorsolateral prostate lobe from 8-week-old C57BL/6J males fed a high fat diet for 12 weeks. High fat diets are a risk factor for prostate cancer. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms by which high fat diet can promote carcinogenesis.

title: Subcutaneous Interferon-beta-1b treatment in relapsing-remitting multiple sclerosis (U133 A): peripheral mononuclear blood cells
description: Temporal analysis of PBMCs collected from 25 German relapsing-remitting multiple sclerosis patients treated with recombinant interferon-beta-1b (rIFN-β-1b, 250 µg every other day) for 2 years. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms of IFN-b action.

title: Subcutaneous Interferon-beta-1b treatment in relapsing-remitting multiple sclerosis (U133 B): peripheral mononuclear blood cells
description: Temporal analysis of PBMCs collected from 25 German relapsing-remitting multiple sclerosis patients treated with recombinant interferon-beta-1b (rIFN-β-1b, 250 µg every other day) for 2 years. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms of IFN-b action.

title: Relapsing-remitting multiple sclerosis therapy of Interferon-β Betaferon or Rebif: peripheral mononuclear blood cells
description: Temporal analysis of PBMCs from relapsing-remitting multiple sclerosis (RRMS) patients treated with Interferon-β-1b (Betaferon) or IFNβ-1a (Rebif). Half of the patients developed neutralizing antibodies (NAB) to IFNβ. Results provide insight into molecular basis of IFNβ bioactivity in MS patient

title: Ataxin-1 deficiency effect on lung
description: Analysis of lung of Atxn1-/- C57BL/6J mice at P6. Alveolarization defects causing air space enlargement were apparent in paralog of ATXN1 (ATAXIN1-Like) knockouts (Atxn1L-/-) at late alveolar stage (P17-23). Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms mediating the alveolarization defect.

title: Ataxin-1-Like deficiency effect on lung
description: Analysis of lung of ATAXIN1-Like-/- (Atxn1L-/-) C57BL/6J mice at P6. Alveolarization defects causing air space enlargement were apparent in ATXN1L knockouts at late alveolar stage (P17-23). Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms mediating the alveolarization defect.

title: Identical twins discordant for Multiple sclerosis: CD4+ and CD8+ T cells
description: Analysis of CD4+ and CD8+ T lymphocytes sorted from PBMCs from 4 monozygotic twin pairs discordant for relapsing remitting Multiple sclerosis (RRMS). The affected twin was free of disease-modifying therapies. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying the etiopathogenesis of RRMS.

title: Non-phosphorylated FTY720 effect on immortalized microglia HMO6 cell line
description: Analysis of immortalized brain HMO6 microglia treated with FTY720-non-P, a non-phosphorylated form of FTY720 (a synthetic analog of sphingosine). Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms responsible for triggering FTY720-non-P-induced apoptosis of HMO6.

title: Multiple sclerosis patients with high serum semaphorin4A levels: peripheral blood cells
description: Analysis of peripheral blood from MS patients with high or low serum levels of transmembrane-type semaphorin Sema4A. MS patients with high Sema4A levels have more severe disabilities and are unresponsive to IFN-β treatment. Results provide insight into role of Sema4A in the pathogenesis of MS.

title: Alpha-synuclein deficiency effect on striatum and cerebellum: time course
description: Analysis of striatum and cerebellum from alpha-synuclein (SNCA) knockouts at 6 or 21 months of age. SNCA mutations result in impaired movement and depression/anxiety, manifesting in humans as Parkinson's disease (PD). Results provide molecular insights into physiological role of alpha-synuclein.

title: Parkinson's disease: post-mortem medullary regions
description: Analysis of 2 regions of PD medullas: dorsal motor nucleus of the vagus (DMNV) and inferior olivary nucleus (ION). A functional magnetic resonance imaging variant was used to identify brainstem regions targeted by (DMNV) and resistant to (ION) PD. Results provide insight into molecular basis of PD.

title: Dopaminergic transcription factors Ascl1, Lmx1a, Nurr1 combined  effect on embryonic fibroblasts
description: Analysis of induced dopaminergic (iDA) neurons generated from  E14.5 mouse embryonic fibroblasts (MEFs) reprogrammed by infection with lentiviruses expressing dopaminergic transcription factors Ascl1, Lmx1a and Nurr1. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of MEF to iDA reprogramming.

title: Parkinson's disease induced pluripotent stem cell model with triplication of the α-synuclein locus
description: Analysis of iPSC lines derived from a PD patient with SNCA triplication and an unaffected first-degree relative. Triplication of SNCA, encoding α-synuclein, causes an aggressive form of PD. Results provide insight into the mechanistic basis of neurodegeneration caused by α-synuclein dysfunction.

title: Dopaminergic neurotoxin MPTP-based Parkinson's disease risk model: brain regions
description: Analysis of caudate-putamen and pre-frontal cortex from transgenics, over-expressing either risk-associated synaptic acetylcholinesterase (AChE)-S variant or the protective soluble AChE-R variant, exposed to environmental risk factor MPTP. Results provide insights into the molecular basis of PD.

title: LNCap prostate cancer cell line response to loss of COnstitutive Photomorphogenic-1 and ETV1
description: Analysis of LNCap prostate cancer (PC) cells following siRNA-mediated knockdown of COP1 and ETV1. Ubiquitin ligase COP1 (RFWD2) negatively regulates proto-oncogene ETV1 which has been linked to PC. Results provide insight into the role of COP1 as a tumor suppressor in PC.

title: LNCap prostate cancer cell line response to loss of COnstitutive Photomorphogenic-1, ETV1 and c-JUN
description: Analysis of LNCap prostate cancer cells following siRNA-mediated knockdown of COP1, ETV1, and c-JUN. Ubiquitin ligase COP1 (RFWD2) negatively regulates the abundance of ETV1 and c-JUN, both of which have been linked to PC. Results provide insight into the role of COP1 as a tumor suppressor in PC.

title: Hepatitis C Virus infection effect on Huh7 hepatoma cells: time course
description: Analysis of Huh7 hepatoma cells infected with JFH-1 Hepatitis C Virus (HCV) at 6, 12, 18, 24, and 48 hours post-infection. HCV is a leading cause of chronic liver disease. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms that contribute to HCV-associated liver pathogenesis.

title: Nonhuman primate model of Lassa fever: liver
description: Temporal analysis of liver from macaques infected with virulent lymphocytic choriomeningitis virus (LCMV)-WE or with non-virulent LCMV-Armstrong. LCMV-WE-infected macaques develop viral hemorrhagic fever similar to human Lassa fever. Results provide insight into molecular basis of LCMV pathogenesis.

title: Conditional GBA1 deletion model of Type 1 Gaucher Disease: liver and spleen
description: Analysis of liver and spleen from mice with increasing severities of the type 1 Gaucher Disease (GD1) phenotype resulting from conditional glucocerebrosidase gene (GBA1) deletion in the hematopoietic and mesenchymal cell lineages. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of GD1 development.

title: Recombinant Interferon α effect on natural killer cells in vitro
description: Analysis of natural killer (NK) cells sorted from healthy donor peripheral blood mononuclear cells (PBMCs) stimulated for 6h in media containing 1 or 100 ng/ml recombinant interferon (IFN)-alpha-2b. Results provide insight into the effects of type I IFNs on NK cells.

title: Compendium of normal tissues
description: Analysis of 10 pathologically normal tissues (liver, kidney, heart, lung, brain, lymph node, spleen, jejunum, pancreas, and skeletal muscle) from each of four dogs. Results provide insight into normal tissue expression to facilitate disease study and comparative genomic analysis with other mammals.

title: GB virus C effect on hepatitis C virus (HCV)/human immunodeficiency virus (HIV) co-infected patients: liver
description: Analysis of liver biopsies from HCV/HIV co-infected patients who are positive for GB virus C (GBV-C) infection. GBV-C infection reduces HCV-related liver disease in HCV/HIV co-infection. Results provide insight into underlying molecular mechanisms that may be involved in the reduced liver disease.

title: Kupffer cell depletion effect on steatosis in the context of high-fat-diet-induced obesity
description: Analysis of liver from C57BL/6 males fed high fat diets (HFD) for 20 wks to induce obesity and hepatic steatosis, and injected with clodronate during the last week of HFD to deplete Kupffer cells (KCs) in liver. Results provide insight into role of KCs in regulation of hepatic triglyceride storage.

title: Chronic lymphocytic leukemia: peripheral blood B cells (HG-U133A)
description: Analysis of peripheral blood B cells isolated from 41 untreated chronic lymphocytic leukemia (CLL) patients and 11 age-matched control subjects. B-cell CLL is the most common type of leukemia, mainly affecting adults. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying CLL pathogenesis.

title: Chronic lymphocytic leukemia: peripheral blood B cells (HG-U133B)
description: Analysis of peripheral blood B cells isolated from 41 untreated chronic lymphocytic leukemia (CLL) patients and 11 age-matched control subjects. B-cell CLL is the most common type of leukemia, mainly affecting adults. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying CLL pathogenesis.

title: Mixed lineage leukemia fusion protein induction of acute leukemia: bone marrow cells
description: Analysis of bone marrow of C57BL6 mice injected with AAF4.MLL-transduced or AF4.MLL/MLL.AF4-transduced leukemic cells. MLL fusion proteins initiate malignant transformation leading to the development of acute leukemia. Results provide insight into the leukemogenic properties of MLL fusion proteins.

title: Pluripotent embryonic stem cells and multipotent adult germline stem cells in 129SV and Stra8-EGFP/Rosa26-LacZ strains
description: Analysis of multipotent adult germline stem cells (maGSCs) and embryonic stem cells (ESCs) from different genetic backgrounds and under differentiation-promoting conditions. Results enable expression pattern comparisons between maGSCs and ESCs.

title: Neonatal ovarian xenobiotic cultures
description: Analysis of ovaries from Swiss neonates cultured in media containing xenobiotics: 4-vinylcyclohexene diepoxide, methoxychlor, menadione. Non-renewing follicles are vulnerable to xenobiotic insult. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying xenobiotic-induced preantral ovotoxicity.

title: Effect of protease-resistant (PML-RAR)α on U937 cell line
description: Analysis of U937 cells transfected with GFP-(PML-RAR)α (PR) or GFP-PR2VR (cleavage-resistant mutant) and GFP-sorted at 6 and 9 hrs. Neutrophil elastase (NE) cleaves PR, the fusion protein that initiates acute promyelocytic leukemia. Results provide insight into leukemogenicity of NE-resistant PR.

title: Notch1 promoter deletion effect on Ikaros-deficient model of T-cell acute lymphoblastic leukemia: thymic lymphoma
description: Analysis of thymic tumors from Ikaros-deficient (IkL/L) mice with a Notch promoter/exon1 deletion. The deletion of Notch1 promoter results in oncogenic activation of Notch1 and significantly accelerates leukemogenesis. Results provide insight into role of Notch activation in pathogenesis of T-ALL.

title: Imatinib effect on Philadelphia chromosome positive acute lymphoblastic leukemia cells
description: Analysis of Ph+ ALL cell lines (BV-173, NALM-1, SUP-B15, and TOM1) treated with tyrosine kinase inhibitor (TKI) imatinib. Ph encodes oncogenic BCR-ABL1 tyrosine kinase, which defines a subset of ALL with an unfavorable prognosis. Results provide insight into TKI resistance mechanisms in Ph+ ALL.

title: Chronic lymphocytic leukemia: peripheral blood, bone marrow and lymph node matched samples
description: Analysis of purified CLL cells from 24 treatment-naive patients. Samples were obtained concurrently from peripheral blood (PB), bone marrow (BM) and/or lymph nodes (LN). Results provide insight into the role of the tissue microenvironment in the pathogenesis of CLL in vivo.

title: Imatinib treatment of chronic myeloid leukemia cell lines: KU-812, KCL-22 and JURL-MK1
description: Analysis of CML cell lines (KU-812, KCL-22, and JURL-MK1) treated with tyrosine kinase inhibitor imatinib. Imatinib inhibits oncogenic BCR-ABL1, a tyrosine kinase present in most CML patients. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying imatinib inhibition of CML.

title: Inhibitor of DNA Binding Protein 4 knockout effect on TCL1 model of chronic lymphocytic leukemia: CD19+ splenic B cells
description: Analysis of CD19+ splenic B cells from 1 month-old TCL1 transgenics deficient in inhibitor of DNA binding protein 4 (ID4+/−TCL1-tg). ID4 transcriptional silencing is an early event in human CLL. Results provide insight into the role of ID4 in CLL pathogenesis.

title: Hodgkin and non-Hodgkin lymphoma cell lines
description: Analysis of lymphoid cell lines of Hodgkin, non-Hodgkin, and acute leukemia origin. Aberrant NOTCH activity is involved in the pathogenesis of B cell-derived lymphomas. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of deregulated NOTCH activity.

title: All-trans-retinoic acid effect on transglutaminase 2-silenced, NB4 model of acute promyelocytic leukemia: time course
description: Analysis of stable TG2-knockdown NB4 APL cells induced to differentiate in the presence of all-trans-retinoic acid (ATRA) for up to 72 hrs. Silencing of TG2 delays the differentiation process of NB4 cells. Results provide insight into the role of TG2 in the ATRA-induced differentiation of NB4 cells.

title: Lysophosphatidic acid effect on RhoA GEF Exchange Factor NET1-deficient, AGS gastric adenocarcinoma cells
description: Analysis of AGS gastric cancer (GC) cells depleted of NET1, a guanine exchange factor (GEF) for RhoA, and treated with lysophosphatidic acid, a RhoA activator. NET1 is up-regulated in GC and drives its aggressive phenotype. Results provide insight into the role of NET1 in GC.

title: THP-1 macrophage-like cells response to W-Beijing Mycobacterium tuberculosis strains: time course
description: Temporal analysis of macrophage-like THP-1 cell line infected by Mycobacterium tuberculosis (Mtb) W-Beijing strains and H37Rv. Mtb W-Beijing sublineages are highly virulent, prevalent and genetically diverse. Results provide insight into host macrophage immune response to Mtb W-Beijing strains.

title: Malawian children with mild malaria following an episode of severe malaria: peripheral whole blood
description: Analysis of paired peripheral blood samples from 5 children who initially presented with severe malaria then 1 month later with mild malaria. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying mild versus severe disease presentations.

title: Thiostrepton effect on malaria parasite
description: Analysis of ring stage Plasmodium falciparum at 5 % parasitaemia treated with 2 uM thiostrepton, an antibiotic with antimalarial activity. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying parasite responses to the drug.

title: Oxidized low-density lipoprotein effect on LOX-1 overexpressing aortic endothelial cell line HAECT: time course
description: Analysis of oxidized-low-density lipoprotein receptor-1 (LOX-1)-overexpressing HAECT cells treated with OxLDL for up to 24 hrs. OxLDL is implicated as a proatherogenic factor. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying OxLDL-induced endothelial dysfunction and atherosclerosis.

title: Age effect on healthy composite bone marrow
description: Analysis of composite bone marrow (BM) from healthy children and adults. Normal BM constitutes a complex tissue of blood progenitor cells changing in composition with age. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms associated with changes in the total precursor B-cell compartment with age.

title: Chronic obstructive pulmonary disease in ex-smokers: sputum
description: Analysis of sputum from ex-smokers with moderate (stage 2) or severe (stages 3, 4) chronic obstructive pulmonary disease  (COPD). Induced sputum contains inflammatory cells, predominantly neutrophils and macrophages. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying COPD progression.

title: Tolerant renal transplant recipients: peripheral whole blood
description: Analysis of whole blood from tolerant renal transplant recipients (i.e., with stable graft function and receiving no immunosuppressive drugs for >1 year) and from recipients stable on immunosuppressive drugs. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying renal transplant tolerance.

title: Scleroderma-associated pulmonary hypertension: peripheral blood mononuclear cells
description: Analysis of PBMCs from scleroderma patients with pulmonary arterial hypertension (PAH). PAH is a common, potentially fatal complication of chronic systemic scleroderma. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying scleroderma-related PAH.

title: Intravenous corticosteroid therapy effect on children with severe ulcerative colitis: peripheral blood
description: Analysis of peripheral blood from pediatric patients with severe ulcerative colitis (UC) on day 3 of intravenous corticosteroid (IVCS) therapy. Individual response to IVCS is variable. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying response to IVCS in pediatric UC.

title: Infant biliary atresia: liver
description: Analysis of liver wedge biopsies from infants at diagnosis of biliary atresia (BA). The biopsies underwent histological scoring and were classified as inflammation or fibrosis. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying stages of BA disease at diagnosis.

title: Methotrexate effect on SPARKS CHARMS juvenile idiopathic arthritis cohort: peripheral blood mononuclear cells
description: Analysis of PBMC from 11 patients with juvenile idiopathic arthritis (JIA) following 6 months of methotrexate (MTX) therapy. Individual response to MTX is variable. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying response to MTX in JIA.

title: Pituitary gonadotrope tumors
description: Analysis of gonadotrope/null cell tumors and normal pituitaries from autopsy samples. Pituitary gonadotrope tumors cause significant morbidity, hormonal deficits, and are more common in men. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms involved in pituitary tumorigenesis and progression.

title: Subcutaneous and visceral adipose tissue from lean or obese children
description: Analysis of subcutaneous and visceral adipose tissue (VAT) from lean and obese pre-pubertal children. The inflammatory environment of VAT may promote insulin resistance and type 2 diabetes. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying the inflammatory milieu of VAT in children.

title: Mixed lineage leukemia gene rearrangements in acute myeloid leukemia: bone marrow mononuclear cells
description: Analysis of bone marrow cells from AML cases representing MLL chromosomal translocation (tMLL) or partial tandem duplication (MLL-PTD). Rearrangements of MLL at chromosome 11q23 are commonly involved in acute leukemia. Results provide insight into molecular heterogeneity between MLL-PTD and tMLL.

title: Acute myeloid leukemia with CEBPA mutations [AMLSG cohort]: mononuclear cells
description: Analysis of mononuclear cells from bone marrow of untreated AML patients with CCAAT/enhancer binding protein alpha double mutation (CEBPAdm) or single mutation (CEBPAsm). Favorable outcome is observed in AML patients with CEBPAdm. Results provide insight into molecular basis of AML classification.

title: Early and advanced idiopathic pulmonary fibrosis: whole lung
description: Analysis of whole lung biopsy or explant from early and advanced idiopathic pulmonary fibrosis (IPF) patients. IPF is a fatal subtype of pulmonary fibrosis difficult to diagnose. Results provide insight into developing a diagnostic model for IPF.

title: BCL6 corepressor somatic mutation in acute myeloid leukemia with normal karyotype: Ficoll-enriched mononuclear cells
description: Analysis of mononuclear cells from normal karyotype, acute myeloid leukemia (CN-AML) patients with BCL6 corepressor (BCOR) mutation. CN-AML BCOR mutations are associated with oculo-facio-cardiodental genetic syndrome and poor outcome. Results provide insight into role of BCOR in CN-AML pathogenesis.

title: Uveal melanoma
description: Analysis of 29 uveal melanomas isolated from male and female patients. Uveal melanoma is an aggressive intraocular tumor cancer that metastasizes to the liver in ~50% of patients, with high lethality. Results provide insight into molecular pathways involved in uveal melanoma metastatic progression.

title: Clear-cell renal cell carcinoma tumors and tumorgrafts deficient for tumor suppressor BAP1 or PBRM1
description: Analysis of BAP1- and PBRM1-deficient ccRCC primary tumors, tumors growing in immunodeficient mice (tumorgrafts), and matched normal kidney cortices. BAP1 loss, but not PBRM1 loss, is associated with high-grade tumors. Results provide insight into molecular classification of RCC subtypes.

title: Chronic lymphocytic leukemia response to antisense Bcl-2 inhibitor SPC2996: peripheral blood
description: Temporal analysis of peripheral blood from 18 relapsed CLL patients treated with a maximum of 6 doses (0.2-6mg/kg) of SPC2996, an antisense molecule targeting the mRNA of Bcl-2 oncoprotein. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the immunostimulatory effects of SPC2996 in CLL.

title: Core binding factor-acute myeloid leukemia patients: mononuclear cells
description: Analysis of mononuclear cells isolated from untreated, CBF-AML patients representing t(8;21) and inv(16)/t(16;16) karyotypes. The CBF-AML samples exhibited differential sensitivity to treatment with ABT-737 and BV6. Results provide insight into molecular basis of sensitivity to inhibitor treatment.

title: Effect of Tet2 loss in bone marrow progenitors
description: Analysis of sorted bone marrow progenitor populations (LSK, CMP, GMP) deficient in ten-eleven translocation 2 (TET2).  Tet2 loss causes increased hematopoietic stem cell self-renewal and myeloid transformation. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying myeloid malignancies.

title: 3-Deazaneplanocin A effect on multiple myeloma cells
description: Analysis of MM cell lines (KMS18, MM.1S, NCI-H929, OPM-2) exposed to 500nM 3-Deazaneplanocin A (DZNep). DZNep potently inhibited growth and induced apoptosis in the NCI-H929 and MM.1S cell lines. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying DZNep-induced apoptosis in MM cells.

title: Small-molecule DOT1L inhibitor EPZ004777 effect on mixed lineage leukemia cells: time course
description: Temporal analysis of mixed lineage leukemia (MLL)-rearranged cell lines MV4-11 and MOLM-13 treated with EPZ004777, a potent inhibitor of DOT1L histone methyl transferase. EPZ004777 induces differentiation and apoptosis in MLL-rearranged cells. Results provide insight into role of DOT1L in MLL cells.

title: Inhibition of Notch signaling in T cell acute lymphoblastic leukemia cell lines
description: Analysis of T-ALL cell lines treated with γ-secretase inhibitor (GSI) to block Notch signaling. Cell lines include parental cells and cells transduced with ICN (a GSI-independent form of activated Notch1) or with c-Myc (a downstream Notch1 target). Results provide insight into Notch1 role in T-ALL.

title: All-trans retinoic acid effect on retinoic acid receptor α-deficient F9 teratocarcinoma cells
description: Analysis of F9 teratocarcinoma cells depleted of retinoic acid receptor (RAR)α and treated with all trans retinoic acid (atRA) in the presence of cycloheximide. RARα translocation events are associated with acute promyelocytic leukemia (APL). Results provide insight into the role of RARα in APL.

title: Histone methyltransferase H3K79 Dot1l deletion effect on MLL-AF9 leukemia cells: time course
description: Analysis of Mixed Lineage Leukemia (MLL)-AF9 leukemia cells after loss of Dot1l for up to 7 days. Loss of Dot1l leads to decreased growth, differentiation, and apoptosis of MLL-AF9 cells. Results provide insight into role of Dot1l in MLL-rearranged leukemia.

title: NCI-60 cancer cell line panel
description: Analysis of cell lines from 9 different cancer tissue of origin types (Breast, Central Nervous System, Colon, Leukemia, Melanoma, Non-Small Cell Lung, Ovarian, Prostate, and Renal) from the NCI-60 panel. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying the various cancer types.

title: MLL-rearranged infant acute lymphoblastic leukemia in vitro resistant to prednisolone
description: Analysis of primary MLL-rearranged ALL samples (>90% leukemic blasts) from untreated infants. In vitro prednisolone sensitivity was assessed by a 4day cytotoxicity (MTT) assay. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of glucocorticoid resistance in MLL-rearranged infant ALL patients.

title: Leukemia-specific fusion gene ETV6/RUNX1 knockdown effect on ETV6/RUNX1-positive, B-cell precursor acute lymphoblastic leukemia cell lines
description: Analysis of ETV6/RUNX1 (E/R) fusion gene-positive, BCP ALL cell lines (AT2 and REH) following E/R knockdown. E/R (also known as TEL/AML1) is the most frequent gene fusion in childhood ALL. Results provide insight into role of E/R gene fusion in leukemia propagation and maintenance.

title: Acute myeloid leukemia CD34+CD38- cell population
description: Analysis of CD34+CD38- and CD34+CD38+ cell fractions isolated from 5 acute myeloid leukemia (AML) patients. AML CD34+CD38- cells are enriched leukemic stem cells (LSC) that maintain the propagation of the disease. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms that maintain and characterize LSC.

title: Gfi1b overexpression in a pro-B Abelson leukemia virus transformed cell line
description: Analysis of Abelson murine leukemia virus (AMuLV) pro-B cell line expressing Gfi1b-estrogen receptor fusion protein. Targeted disruption of transcription factor Gfi1b severly impacts B cell development in vivo. Results provide insight into the role of Gfi1b in normal B cell development.

title: Notch1 overexpression model of T-cell acute lymphoblastic leukemia: double positive CD4+/8+ cells
description: Analysis of DP (CD4+/8+) cells from an intracellular Notch1 (Notch1-IC)-induced T-ALL model that recapitulates most features of human T-ALL. T-ALL malignancy is driven by oncogenic activation of NOTCH1 signaling. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of Notch1-driven leukemogenesis.

title: ATP effect on acute myeloid leukemia lymphoblasts
description: Analysis of lymphoblasts from 12 acute myeloid leukemia (AML) patients cultured for 24hrs with ATP. Extracellular nucleotide ATP inhibits proliferation and accumulation of AML cells. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying the inhibitory activity of ATP on leukemic cells.

title: DNA methyltransferase Dnmt1 knockout effect on leukemia stem cells and bulk leukemia cells
description: Analysis of Dnmt1 haploinsufficient leukemia stem cells (leukemic granulocytemacrophage progenitors; L-GMPs) and bulk leukemia cells from a model of MLL-AF9-induced acute myeloid leukemia (AML). Dnmt1 haploinsufficiency delays progression of AML. Results provide insight into role of Dnmt1 in AML.

title: Prolonged cardiothoracic surgery effect on diaphragm
description: Analysis of paired diaphragm biopsies from 5 patients during cardiothoracic surgery: the 1st as soon as diaphragm was exposed, the 2nd as late in surgery as possible (4.9 ± 1.8 hrs between biopsies). Results provide insight into diaphragm muscle biology after prolonged cardiothoracic procedures.

title: Polycomb histone methyltransferase Ezh2-deficient hearts: right ventricle and interventricular septum
description: Analysis of right ventricle and interventricular septum from Ezh2-deficient adults. Loss of Ezh2 leads to cardiac hypertrophy and fibrosis. Results provide insight into the role of Ezh2 in postnatal organ homeostasis.

title: Protein kinase C (PKC)ζ knockout response to chronic angiotensin treatment in vivo: heart
description: Analysis of heart from PKCζ-deficient males subjected to continuous infusion of angiotensin II for 14 days. PKCζ knockouts do not develop cardiac hypertrophy (CH) upon chronic challenge with angiotensin II. Results provide insight into the role of PKCζ in CH.

title: Sex effect on acute coxsackievirus B3-induced myocarditis: heart
description: Analysis of heart from CVB3-infected males during acute myocarditis (day 10 postinfection). Myocarditis and DCM, often caused by viral infections, occur more frequently in men than in women. Results provided insight into molecular basis of  progression from acute CVB3 myocarditis to DCM in males.

title: Inherited dilated cardiomyopathy patient-specific induced pluripotent stem cells
description: Analysis of iPSCs derived from skin fibroblasts of Dilated Cardiomyopathy (DCM) family members carrying point mutation R173W in the sarcomeric protein cardiac troponin T (TNNT2) gene. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying familial dilated cardiomyopathy.

title: Foregut endoderm and combined heart mesoderm and head tissue from E8.5 embryos
description: Analysis of foregut endoderm and mesoderm/ectoderm from early somite-stage embryos. Foregut definitive endoderm is the precursor of many tissues such as liver, pancreas, oesophagus. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying early development of the foregut definitive endoderm.

title: Diabetic ischemic heart failure patients: non-infarcted left ventricle
description: Analysis of left ventricle cardiac biopsies taken from the vital, non-infarcted zone of diabetic patients with ischemic heart failure (HF). Increased morbidity and mortality are associated with ischemic HF in diabetic patients. Results provide insight into the underlying pathogenetic mechanisms.

title: One-Twenty-Two-1 knockout effect on hematopoietic stem cells
description: Analysis of Lin- Sca-1+ c-Kit+ (LSK) cells, which include the hematopoietic stem cell (HSC) population, sorted from bone marrow of Ott1 knockouts. HSCs lacking Ott1 are unable to maintain quiescence during proliferative stress. Results provide insight into the role of Ott1 in stress hematopoiesis.

title: Heart, kidney and lung during juvenile growth
description: Analysis of heart, kidney, and lung from C57BL/6 males at 1, 4,  8 weeks of age. Mammalian somatic growth is rapid in early postnatal life but slows and eventually ceases in multiple tissues. Results provide insight into molecular events common to multiple tissues that regulate growth deceleration.

title: Iroquois homeobox Irx3 and Irx5 deletion effect on embryonic heart
description: Analysis of E12.5 hearts deficient in both of the Iroquois homeodomain transcription factors, Irx3 and Irx5. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying cooperative and antagonistic roles for Irx3 and Irx5 in cardiac morphogenesis.

title: Single nucleotide polymorphism rs1333049 from the 9p21.3 coronary artery disease risk locus: normal heart
description: Analysis of left ventricular heart from donors with no previous history of heart disease. Results provide insight into associations between 9p21.3 (rs1333049) genotype and transcripts in cardiovascular tissue.

title: Pancreatic-specific PPAR-beta deletion effect on pancreatic beta-cells
description: Analysis of β-cells harboring a pancreatic-specific deletion of peroxisome proliferator-activated receptor (PPAR)-β. The pancreas-specific KO animals developed chronic hyperinsulinemia due to increased beta-cell mass and insulin secretion. Results provide insight into role of PPAR-β in pancreas.

title: Escherichia coli O157:H7 response  to cinnamaldehyde: time course
description: Analysis of E. coli O157:H7 exposed to cinnamaldehyde (CIN) for up to 4 hours. CIN is a natural antimicrobial effective against many foodborne pathogens including Escherichia coli O157:H7. Results provide insight into molecular processes underlying CIN-induced transient inhibition of E. coli.

title: Small molecule KY02111 effect on induced pluripotent stem cell line IMR90-1: time course
description: Analysis of IMR90-1 iPSCs cultured in cardiac differentiation medium containing serum for 3 days, then treated with KY02111 for up to 24 hrs. KY02111 promotes differentiation of PSCs to cardiomyocytes. Results provide insight into molecular basis of KY02111-induced cardiac differentiation of PSCs.

title: Low-dose ionizing radiation effect on breast tissue: two inbred strains
description: Analysis of mammary gland from BALB/c and C57BL/6 females exposed to low dose (LD) ionizing radiation. The two inbred strains differ in their genetic susceptibility to radiation-induced mammary cancer. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying mammary cancer susceptibility.

title: Dopamine β-hydroxylase knockout effect on embryonic heart
description: Analysis of adrenergic-deficient (Dbh-/-) E10.5 hearts. Adrenergic hormones are essential for early heart development. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms that mediate adrenergic actions in early heart development.

title: Vesicular acetylcholine transporter knockdown effect on heart
description: Analysis of heart from vesicular acetylcholine transporter (VAChT)-deficient C57BL/6 males. The VAChT KD animals have a systemic decrease in ACh release and cardiac dysfunction. Results provide insight into potential molecular changes in the heart induced by decreased cholinergic neurotransmission.

title: Head muscle progenitors and trunk muscle progenitors: developmental time course
description: Analysis of pharyngeal mesoderm (PM) myogenic progenitors and trunk myogenic progenitors from E9.5 - E11.5 embryos. During embryogenesis, certain heart and craniofacial muscles arise from PM progenitors. Results provide insight into role of PM regulatory network in myogenesis and cardiogenesis.

title: Human hepatocytes from xenogeneic host livers
description: Analysis of hepatocytes isolated from chimeric mouse livers repopulated with human hepatocytes (c-heps) or from normal human livers (h-heps). Results provide insight into the potential use of chimeric mice as a relevant model for human liver biomedical experiments.

title: Cardiac transcription factors Tbx5, Gata4 and Myocardin effect on 10T1/2-tTA fibroblast cell line
description: Analysis of 10T1/2-tTA fibroblasts infected with different combinations of cardiac transcription factors (TFs) Tbx5, Gata4, and Myocardin lentiviruses and induced with doxycycline for 14 days. Results provide insight into the specific roles of these TFs in activating cardiac gene programs.

title: Pancreatic ductal adenocarcinoma surgery patients: circulating tumor cells
description: Analysis of circulating tumor cells (CTC) from patients who underwent surgery for PDAC. Most cancer deaths are caused by metastases, resulting from CTCs that detach from the primary cancer and survive in distant organs. Results provide insight into molecular characterization of CTC motility in PDAC.

title: Long-term octreotide treatment of neuroendocrine tumor cell line CNDT2.5
description: Analysis of ileum neuroendocrine tumor (NET) cell line CNDT2.5 treated with octreotide for up to 16 months. Somatostain analog octreotide is used to treat NET patients. Results provided insight into molecular basis of successful octreotide therapy or the development of drug resistance in NETs.

title: Raf kinase inhibitor 1 knockout effect on C57BL/6 pancreas
description: Analysis of pancreas from Raf kinase inhibitor 1 (Rkip1) knockouts. Rkip1-/- mice exhibit a larger pancreas and increased beta cell mass and pancreatic insulin content. Results provide insight into the role of Rkip1 in regulation of pancreatic beta cell function and proliferation.

title: Interleukin 1β effect on insulinoma cell line overexpressing pancreatic duodenum homeobox 1: time course
description: Analysis of pancreatic duodenum homeobox 1 (Pdx1)-overexpressing, INS-1ab insulinoma cell line exposed to Interleukin 1b (IL-1β) cytokine for up to 24 hrs.   Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying Pdx1-driven potentiation of beta cell sensitivity to IL-1β.

title: Interleukin-2 null effect on the regulatory T cell-deficient scurfy model of autoimmune disease: CD4+ T-cells
description: Analysis of CD4+ T cells purified from pooled peripheral lymph nodes of scurfy (Sf) mice deficient in interleukin-2. Sf.Il2-/- mice develop liver inflammation, but not inflammation of skin and lung, seen in Sf mice. Results provide insight into role of IL2 in multiorgan inflammation in Sf mice.

title: B7x effect on CD8 T cell-mediated diabetes model AI4αβ: pancreatic CD8 T cells
description: Analysis of pancreatic AI4αβ CD8 T cells isolated from Rip-B7xAI4αβ (overexpressing B7x in the β cells) and AI4αβ (lacking B7x) mice. B7x inhibits CD8 T cell-induced diabetes. Results provide insight into the molecular basis for abrogation of diabetes by B7x overexpression in β cells.

title: Sox9+ pancreatic cells: developmental time course
description: Analysis of GFP positive cells from Sox9-EGFP pancreas isolated by FACS at various developmental stages: e10.5, e15.5, p23. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying differentiatiation of Sox9+ embryonic pancreatic progenitors into adult ductal cells or the endocrine lineage.

title: Pancreatic ductal adenocarcinoma tumor and adjacent non-tumor tissue
description: Analysis of 45 matching pairs of pancreatic ductal adenocarcinoma (PDAC) tumor and adjacent non-tumor tissue. Results provide insight into tumor markers with prognostic significance and molecular mechanisms underlying PDAC.

title: Type 2 diabetic and hyperglycemic pancreatic islets
description: Analysis of pancreatic islets from type 2 diabetes (T2D) and non-diabetic cadaver donors. Glycemic control (HbA1c) levels also measured from the same individuals (normoglycemic: HbA1c < 6%; hyperglycemic: HbA1c ≥ 6%). Results provided insight into molecular basis of islet dysfunction in T2D.

title: Cyclooxygenase-2 overexpression or deletion effect on the K-ras/Pten pancreatic ductal adenocarcinoma murine model
description: Analysis of PDACs from mutants with pancreatic-specific Pten loss (Pten +/-) and K-ras activation (K-rasG12D) and either COX-2 over-expression (Cox-2 COE) or knockout (Cox-2 KO) under regulation of the Pdx-1 promoter. Results provide insight into the role of COX-2 in pancreatic cancer development.

title: Dietary saturated fat effect on small intestine
description: Analysis of small intestine divided into 3 equal parts along the proximal to distal axis (SI 1, SI 2, SI 3) from C57Bl/6J males fed high-fat diets varying in polyunsaturated/saturated fatty acid ratios (P/S). Results provide insight into role of dietary fat type on development of metabolic syndrome.

title: Non-obese diabetic (NOD) and disease-resistant NOD.NOR-Chr4 models: splenic B cells
description: Analysis of anti-IgM-F(ab’)2 fragment-stimulated, splenic B cells from non-obese diabetic (NOD) or NR4 (NOD background with Chromosome 4, type 1 diabetes (T1D)-resistance alleles) females. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying NOD and NR4 diabetogenic activity.

title: Transcription factor MIST1-null and MIST1-induced pancreas
description: Analysis of pancreas from C57BL/6 adults with Mist1-null phenotype rescued by tamoxifen-induced Mist1 expression. Embryonic knockout of Mist1 leads to acinar cell dysfunction, disrupting pancreatic function. Results provide insight into the role of Mist1 in regulating mature acinar properties.

title: Gamma secretase inhibitor MRK-003 effect on pancreatic ductal adenocarcinoma tumor xenografts
description: Analysis of 9 individual patient-derived, pancreatic ductal adenocarcinoma (PDAC) xenografts treated with GSI MRK-003. MRK-003 monotherapy significantly reduced tumor volume in 5 of 9 xenografts. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of MRK-003-mediated attenuation of PDAC.

title: Xenograft tumors generated from iKras p53 null pancreatic ductal adenocarcinoma cell lines
description: Analysis of xenograft tumors generated from independent iKras p53L/+ PDAC cell lines. Cultured parental lines also examined. Doxycycline treatment induced expression of oncogenic KrasG12D. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying KrasG12D-mediated PDAC tumor maintenance.

title: Diet-induced model of obesity: mesenteric adipose tissue surrounding pancreas
description: Analysis of adipose depot surrounding pancreas from cafeteria diet fed Wistar males. In obesity, β-cell mass increases in response to rising insulin demand; this β-cell plasticity is essential to avoid hyperglycemia onset. Results provide insight into molecular basis of β-cell mass adaptation.

title: Quadriceps muscle from cancer patients before and after surgery: sequential biopsies
description: Analysis of paired muscle biopsies (i.e., pre-resection baseline and 8 month post-resection follow-up, disease-free/weight-stable for previous 2 months) from upper gastrointestinal cancer patients. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying cancer-associated muscle wasting.

title: Gli transcriptional repressor Gli3T effect on epithelioid carcinoma cell line Panc-1
description: Analysis of epithelioid carcinoma Panc1 cells expressing Gli3T, a transcriptional repressor of Gli. Gli transcription factors are essential for Kras initiation of pancreatic tumorigenesis. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying pancreatic epithelial transformation.

title: Pancreatic CD45+ immune cells from NOD model of type 1 diabetes
description: Analysis of pancreatic CD45+ cells from 10 week-old NOD females MRI-scanned to noninvasively visualize effects of pancreatic-islet inflammation. All NOD juveniles develop insulitis but vary highly in their progression to diabetes. Results provide insight into molecular basis of disease progression.

title: Transcription factor pancreatic and duodenal homeobox 1 deficiency effect on proximal small intestine
description: Analysis of mature proximal small intestine with intestinal epithelium-specific pancreatic and duodenal homeobox 1 (Pdx1) inactivation. Pdx1 is essential for regulating pancreatic development and maintaining proper islet function. Results provide insight into role of Pdx1 in duodenum.

title: E-cadherin/CDH1 intron2 protein isoform overexpression in Mkn28 gastric tubular adenocarcinoma cell line
description: Analysis of MKN28 cell line (E-cadherin positive) overexpressing E-cadherin isoform CDH1a. CDH1a overexpression promotes mild MKN28 aggregation and increases invasion. Results provide insight into role of CDH1a as a negative modulator of canonical E-cadherin function in cancer cells.

title: Barrett esophagus: endoscopic biopsies
description: Analysis of endoscopic biopsies of Barrett's esophagus (BE), normal adjacent epithelia gastric cardia, and normal squamous esophagus. BE is a metaplastic condition and precursor to esophageal adenocarcinoma. Results provide insight molecular mechanisms underlying early stages of BE.

title: Inbred lines with different prion disease incubation times: whole brain
description: Analysis of brain from uninfected inbred lines with previously characterized, different prion incubation times. Prion diseases exhibit a long, clinically-silent incubation period, determined in part by genetic background. Results provide insight into molecular basis of different incubation times.

title: Cellular prion protein knockout effect on developing hippocampus
description: Analysis of hippocampi from cellular prion protein (PrPC)-deficient, FVB newborns (4.5-day-old) and adults (3-mo-old). PrPc protein is widely expressed throughout the CNS; mice lacking PrP are resistant to prion infection. Results provide insight into the influence of PrPC on the developing CNS.

title: Cerebral Palsy: skeletal muscle biopsies
description: Analysis of gracilis and semitendinosus muscle biopsies from pediatric cerebral palsy (CP) patients. Muscles from CP patients are spastic and form contractures limiting range of motion and joint function. Results provide insight into molecular basis of skeletal muscle response to CP.

title: Endogenous Cushing's Syndrome bone biopsies: pre- and post-surgery
description: Analysis of bone biopsies from Cushing’s syndrome (CS) patients, before and mean 3 months after surgical treatment. Excess GC-induced bone loss is a serious complication in patients with endogenous CS. Results provide insight molecular mechanisms by which excess GCs influence bone metabolism.

title: Chlamydia muridarum genital tract infection model: CD4 T cells
description: Anaysis of Chlamydia-specific CD4 T cell clones that terminate Chlamydia replication in epithelial cells via an iNOS-dependent or iNOS-independent mechanism. Results provide insight into two independent and redundant T cell mechanisms for clearing C. muridarum genital tract infections.

title: Zaire ebolavirus infection of macrophage: time course
description: Analysis of primary macrophages from three donors (D1, D2, D3) up to 6 hrs after in vitro exposure to purified Zaire ebolavirus (ZEBOV) virions. ZEBOV is the etiological agent of Ebola Hemorrhagic Fever (EHF). Results provide insight into the initial response of macrophages exposed to Ebola virions.

title: Host response to uninfected Ixodes scapularis nymphal tick attachment: time course
description: Analysis of ear bite-site biopsies from BALB/c hosts up to 12 hours after post nymphal tick infestation. Tick saliva facilitates and enhances viral infection. Results provide insight into immunomodulation at tick-host interface induced by tick saliva that facilitates tick-born virus transmission.

title: Two types of HIV-associated neurocognitive impairment: brain regions
description: Analysis of basal ganglia, frontal cortex, and white matter from HIV patients with HIV-associated dementia (HAD) or HAD plus HIV encephalitis (HIVE). Results provide insight into molecular events of neurological impairment and inflammation associated with HIV infection in different brain regions.

title: Co-expression of tyrosine kinase receptors HER2 and HER3 in mammary epithelial cells MCF10A grown in three-dimensional cultures
description: Analysis of MCF10A mammary epithelial cells expressing HER2, HER3, or HER2/HER3 heterodimer. Co-expression of HER2 and HER3 induced migration and invasion of MCF10A cells. Results provide insight into the role of HER2 and HER3 in breast cancer.

title: Epidermal growth factor effect on HER2-overexpressing mammary epithelial MCF10A cells: time course
description: Analysis of MCF10A and HER2-overexpressing MCF10A cells  grown on Matrigel in the absence or presence of epidermal growth factor (EGF). MCF10A-HER2 cells exhibited autonomous growth, independent of growth factors. Results provide insight into molecular bases underlying the growth autonomy confer

title: AP1510, TGFα  or heregulin ligand effect on MCF10 mammary epithelial cells expressing HER2-FKBP-HA chimeric receptors
description: Analysis of mammary epithelial MCF10A/HER2/FKBP/HA cells treated with AP1510 to induce the chimeric HER2-FKBP molecule to homodimerize, or with TGFα or heregulin to induce heterodimerization with EGFR or HER3. Results provide insight into signaling events following HER2 receptor dimerization.

title: Mammary epithelial cell line 184A1 response to dual-pulse epidermal growth factor stimulation: time course
description: Analysis of 184A1 mammary epithelial cells pulsed once or twice with epidermal growth factor (EGF). Normal cells require continuous exposure to growth factors to cross a restriction point and commit to cell-cycle progression. Results provide insight into molecular events regulating S phase entry.

title: CD4CD45Rbhi T-cell transfer colitis model: time course
description: Temporal analysis of colon tissue from RAG-1-/- C57BL/6 males injected with CD4+CD45RBhigh T cells from healthy wild type C57BL/6 males to induce colitis. T cells critically regulate clinical inflammatory bowel diseases (IBD). Results provide insight into the molecular basis of colitis development.

title: Natural and induced Foxp3+ regulatory T cells and Foxp3-deficient induced regulatory T cells
description: Analysis of 3 subsets of sorted Tregs: natural (nTreg), induced (iTreg), and iTregs that lost Foxp3 expression (ex-iTreg), from spleens and mesenteric lymph nodes of BALB/c Rag1-/- mice treated with WT nTregs and WT iTregs. Results provide insight into molecular relationships among the Treg subsets.

title: Intestinal mucosa response to active and inactive ulcerative colitis: colon biopsies
description: Analysis of colonic biopsies from patients with histologically active or inactive UC and from healthy, non-inflammatory controls. UC is a chronic inflammatory disease with periods of active disease followed by remission. Results provide insight into molecular events associated with UC remission.

title: Metalloprotease ADAMTS-12 deficiency effect on DSS-induced colitis: distal colon
description: Analysis of distal colon from dextran sodium sulfate (DSS)-treated, Adamts12 knockouts. Metalloprotease ADAMTS-12 deficient mice exhibit more severe inflammation from DSS challenge compared with their wild-type littermates. Results provide insight into the role of ADAMTS-12 in inflammation.

title: Azoxymethane/dextran sulfate sodium-induced ulcerative colitis-associated colorectal cancer model: time course
description: Temporal analysis of colon from AOM/DSS-induced model of ulcerative colitis-associated colorectal cancer (UC-CRC). Nonresolving inflammation is associated with increased incidence of CRC. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying the development from colitis to colorectal cancer.

title: DSS-induced colitis model response to L-arginine supplementation
description: Analysis of colon from dextran sulfate sodium (DSS)-treated C57BL/6 males following L-arginine supplementation. L-Arg supplementation improves clinical parameters of DSS-induced colitis. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying the clinical benefit of L-Arg supplementation.

title: Normal colonic lamina propria macrophage and dendritic cell populations
description: Analysis of sorted, steady-state colonic cells subdivided into 4 populations: 2 DC subsets and 2 MP subsets based on CD11c and F4/80 expression. DCs and MPs are important for immunological homeostasis in colon. Results provide insight into molecular characterization of colonic MP and DC populations.

title: Effect of macrophage-specific peroxisome proliferator-activated receptor-gamma deficiency on induced inflammatory bowel disease
description: Analysis of colon from macrophage PPARγ-deficient C57BL/6 mice and control littermates following dextran sulfate sodium challenge to induce colitis. Deficiency of PPARγ in macrophages worsens colitis severity. Results provide insight into molecular basis of the effects of macrophage PPARγ in IBD.

title: DSS-induced colitis model response to enhanced siRNA targeting of Tumor necrosis factor α
description: Analysis of distal colon from dextran sulfate sodium-treated C57BL/6 females after administration of chemically modified siRNA against TNFα, a proinflammatory cytokine involved in inflammatory bowel disease (IBD). Results provide insight into functionally enhanced siRNA targeting of TNFα in IBD.

title: Intestinal epithelium response to ursodeoxycholic acid
description: Analysis of normal colon epithelium of C57BL/6J females fed a standard diet containing 0.4% ursodeoxycholic acid (UDCA). UDCA mitigates colon carcinogenesis in humans and in animal models. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying the anticarcinogenic action of UDCA.

title: Activated Autoimmune Regulator (AIRE)-deficient, CD8+CD28low regulatory T lymphocytes
description: Analysis of AIRE-deficient, CD8+CD28low regulatory T (Treg) cells stimulated with allogeneic antigen-presenting cells (APC) and anti-CD3 antibody. Results provide insight into the role of AIRE in the function of regulatory T-cell populations, which are central to the prevention of immunopathology.

title: Entamoeba histolytica infected sigmoid colon
description: Analysis of colon biopsies from individuals during acute E. histolytica diarrhea (day 1) versus convalescence (day 60) post metronidazole treatment. The E. histolytica pathogen causes diarrhea and colitis. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying amebic colitis pathology.

title: Histone/protein deacetylase (HDAC) 6-deficient CD4+CD25+ T-regulatory cells
description: Analysis of CD4+CD25+ T-regulatory cells (Treg) from HDAC6-deficient C57BL6 mice. Foxp3+ Tregs are key to immune homeostasis and express multiple HDACs.  Results provide insight into the role of the HDAC6 isoform in the suppressive functions of Foxp3+ Tregs.

title: Ts65Dn aneuploidy model of Down syndrome: skeletal muscle
description: Analysis of soleus muscle, in the basal state, from five-month-old Ts65Dn Down syndrome (DS) males. Ts65Dn DS model exhibits muscle weakness in vivo. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying DS-associated muscle dysfunction.

title: CD43+/41+/235+ iPSC-derived progenitor cells with germ-line trisomy 21
description: Analysis of sorted CD43+/41+/235+ progenitors generated from trisomy 21 (T21) induced pluripotent stem cell (iPSC) lines. Down syndrome (DS, trisomy 21) affects many tissues, including blood, particularly during embryogenesis. Results provide insight into T21 effect on embryonic hematopoiesis.

title: Ozone effect on G-protein double-null mutant leaves: time course
description: Analysis of leaves from G-protein double mutant gpa1-4/agb1-2 plants with null mutations in the α- and β-subunits that were exposed to 125 ppb ozone for up to 2 days. Results provide insight into the role of G-protein signaling pathways in plant response to ozone exposure.

title: Colorectal cancer tumors
description: Analysis of primary colorectal cancer (CRC) tumors. CRC is a heterogeneous disease. Results provide insight into stratifying CRC tumor samples into subtypes and tailoring treatments for the CRC subtypes.

title: High and low chromosomal instability phenotypes in stage II and III colorectal cancers
description: Analysis of specimens from consecutive stage II and stage III colorectal cancer (CRC) patients with high or low chromosomal instability (CIN) phenotype. CIN-high CRC showed poorer outcome than CIN-low CRC. Results provide insight into molecular biomarkers to distinguish between the CIN phenotypes.

title: Patient-derived colorectal cancer explants
description: Analysis of patient-derived colorectal cancer explants (PDCCE), generated by direct transplantation of human colorectal cancer (CRC) tissues into NOD-SCID mice, and matched patient CRC primary tumors. Results provide insight into the degree to which PDCCEs represent their primary human counterparts.

title: Colorectal cancer tumors
description: Analysis of paired colorectal cancer (CRC) tumors and adjacent non-cancerous tissues. Colorectal cancer is a worldwide public health problem. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying CRC carcinogenesis.

title: Saracatinib-sensitive versus -resistant, PIK3CA mutant colorectal cancer xenografts
description: Analysis of patient-derived colorectal cancer (CRC) xenografts with a PIK3CA mutation with enhanced sensitivity to Src inhibitor saracatinib. Dysregulation of Src and PI3K (phosphoinositide 3-kinase) signaling pathways is common in CRC. Results provide insight into CRC model response to saracatinib.

title: p53 mutations in microsatellite-stable, stage III colorectal cancer
description: Analysis of Stage III CRCs exhibiting microsatellite-stable (MSS) and mutant p53 phenotypic features. p53 mutations are associated with higher Stage III MSS CRC mortality than p53 wild-type phenotypes. Results provide further insight into the prognostic value of p53 mutations in Stage III MSS CRCs.

title: CD133-positive and CD133-negative colon cancer cells
description: Analysis of CD133-positive and CD133-negative colorectal cancer cells and CAFs isolated from the same stage II patient specimen. CD133+ colon cancer cells exhibit enhanced tumorigenicity over CD133- cells. Results provide insight into molecular basis of the enhanced tumorigenicity of CD133+ cells.

title: Ls174T colon cancer cell line response to Wnt signaling inhibition
description: Analysis of Ls174T colon cancer cells following doxycyclin-induction of a dominant-negative Tcf4 transgene, or a shRNA against β-catenin, to block the Wnt signal transduction pathway. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms downstream of a defined signal transduction pathway.

title: Hepatitis B virus (HBV)-associated acute liver failure (ALF) patients: liver explant
