description: Analysis of explanted livers of 4 patients with HBV-associated ALF who underwent liver transplantation. Liver has inherent regenerative capacity via hepatic stem/progenitor cells (HSPC) when hepatic loss is massive. Results provide insight into role of HSPC in liver regeneration associated with ALF.

title: Leukemia inhibitory factor effect on Sin3a-silenced MCF7 breast cancer cell line
description: Analysis of SIN3 transcription regulator homolog A (Sin3a)-depleted MCF7 cells stimulated with LIF cytokine to activate signal transducer and activator of transcription 3 (STAT3). STAT3 transcription factor is a potent oncogene. Results provide insight into role of Sin3a in mediating STAT3 activity.

title: Alcoholic hepatitis
description: Analysis of alcoholic hepatitis (AH) livers. AH is a severe form of alcoholic liver disease characterized by hepatocellular damage, steatosis and pericellular fibrosis. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying AH pathogenesis.

title: Primary hepatocyte response to interferon-α or interleukin 28B: time course
description: Analysis of primary hepatocytes up to 24 hrs after treatment with cytokines: interferon (IFN)-α or interleukin 28B (IL28B, a type III IFN). Members of type III IFN system possess antiviral activities against Hepatitis C Virus (HCV). Results provide insight into role of III IFNs in HCV infection.

title: Ribavirin effect on uninfected hepatoma Huh7.5.1 cells
description: Analysis of uninfected hepatoma Huh7.5.1 cells treated with ribavirin. In the combination treatment for hepatitis C virus (HCV), ribavirin potentiates the anti-HCV effect of pegylated interferon (PEG-IFN). Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying ribavirin action.

title: Hepatitis C virus permissive cell lines Huh7.5 and HRP1 and non-permissive parent cell line Huh7
description: Analysis of hepatocyte cell line Huh7, non-permissive to hepatitis C virus (HCV) replication, and permissive cell lines Huh7.5 and HRP1. Results provide insight into host factors lost in cells permissive for HCV replication.

title: Unresectable colorectal cancer primary or metastatic lesions: training set
description: Analysis of primary or metastatic lesions from patients with unresectable colorectal cancer (CRC) prior to FOLFOX6 therapy (oxaliplatin, 5-fluorouracil, leucovorin regimen). Results provide insight into molecular signatures that predict responders to FOLFOX therapy for unresectable CRC.

title: Niemann-Pick Type C disease brain: time course
description: Analysis of brain across 6 age groups of Npc1−/− Balb/c females with Niemann-Pick Type C (NPC) disease. NPC is a neurodegenerative, lysosomal disorder caused by Npc1 or Npc2 gene dysfunction. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying NPC progression.

title: External beam radiation therapy effect on prostate cancer patients: peripheral white blood cells
description: Analysis of peripheral blood from men with non-metastatic prostate cancer (PC) on days 1, 7, 14, 21, 42 of external beam radiation therapy (EBRT), and at 30 days post-EBRT. Fatigue is a common side effect of EBRT. Results provide insight into molecular basis of fatigue in men with PC during EBRT.

title: Unresectable colorectal cancer primary or metastatic lesions: test  set
description: Analysis of primary or metastatic lesions from patients with unresectable colorectal cancer (CRC) prior to FOLFOX6 therapy (oxaliplatin, 5-fluorouracil, leucovorin regimen). Results provide insight into molecular signatures that predict responders to FOLFOX therapy for unresectable CRC.

title: 5-aza-2’-deoxycytidine effect on colorectal cancer cell lines
description: Analysis of colorectal cancer (CRC) cell lines treated with 5-aza-2’-deoxycytidine (5-aza-dC). 5-aza-dC, a DNA methylation inhibitor, was used to reactivate silenced genes in the CRC cell lines. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying epigenetic alterations in CRC.

title: Activated diabetogenic CD8+ G9C8 clone cells and transgenic NOD/LtJ CD8 T cells
description: Analysis of diabetogenic CD8+ G9C8 clone cells and transgenic NOD CD8 T cells. The clone and transgenic T cells display differences in their ability to kill β cells and induce disease in vivo. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of such differences between the two sets of CD8 T cells.

title: Polycystic ovary syndrome: granulosa cells
description: Analysis of granulosa cells from ovarian aspirates from polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS) women undergoing in vitro fertilization. PCOS is an endocrine disorder associated with greater risk for infertility, diabetes and cardiovascular diseases. Results provide insight into molecular basis of PCOS.

title: Fibroblast-derived induced pluripotent stem cells harboring pathogenic leucine-rich repeat kinase 2 mutation
description: Analysis of IPSCs generated from LRRK2 (Gly2019Ser) mutation-bearing patient fibroblasts by cell reprogramming. The LRRK2 (G2019S) mutation causes familial Parkinson's disease (PD). Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying PD.

title: H9 hESC-derived neural stem cells harboring pathogenic leucine-rich repeat kinase 2 mutation
description: Analysis of LRRK2 (Gly2019Ser) mutant neural stem cells (NSC) treated with LRRK2 kinase specific inhibitor LRRK2-IN-1. The LRRK2 (G2019S) mutation causes familial Parkinson's disease. Results provide insight into molecular basis of progressive degeneration of NSCs caused by pathogenic LRRK2.

title: Cell lines derived from metastatic lung adenocarcinoma model
description: Analysis of KrasG12D;p53-/- cell lines derived from primary lung tumors or from metastases (liver, lymph node). Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying changes in extracellular matrix (ECM)-adhesion in metastatic progression.

title: Endothelial progenitor cells from cord blood and adult peripheral blood
description: Analysis of outgrown endothelial progenitor cells (EPC) isolated from 2 different sources: cord blood or adult peripheral blood. EPC from these different anatomic locations possess unique biological properties. Results provide insight into the underlying molecular mechanisms of these properties.

title: Facioscapulohumeral muscular dystrophy: bicep and deltoid muscles
description: Analysis of biceps and deltoids of facioscapulohumeral muscular dystrophy (FSHD) subjects and their unaffected first-degree relatives. FSHD is progressive neuromuscular disorder affecting biceps more severely than deltoid muscles. Results provide insight into molecular basis of FSHD pathogenesis.

title: Primary mammary epithelial cells response to heat-inactivated Escherichia coli or Staphylococcus aureus: time course
description: Analysis of mammary epithelial cells (MECs) challenged with heat-killed particles of E. coli or S. aureus for up to 24 hrs. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying the pathogen-specific disease patterns.

title: Biallelic CEBPA-mutated acute myeloid leukemia with multilineage dysplasia: peripheral blood mononuclear cells
description: Analysis of PBMCs from biallelic CEBPA (encoding CCAAT/enhancer binding protein)-mutated, acute myeloid leukemia (AML) patients with or without multilineage dysplasia (MLD). Cases without CEBPA mutations also examined.  Results provide insight into the classification of CEBPA-mutated AML patients.

title: Nitric oxide generator DETA-NONOate effect on in vitro neuronal injury model: time course
description: Analysis of primary cortical neurons treated with nitric oxide (NO) generator DETA-NONOate for up to 24 hrs. High doses of NO, often observed in neurodegenerative disease pathogenesis, cause neuronal death. Results provide insight into molecular events contributing to NO-induced neuronal injury.

title: Infantile-onset Pompe response to recombinant human lysosomal acid alpha-glucosidase (rhGAA) treatment: quadriceps
description: Analysis of quadriceps biopsies from infantile-onset Pompe disease patients treated with recombinant human lysosomal acid alpha-glucosidase (rhGAA, Myozyme) for up to 52 weeks. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying the response to therapy (positive vs. poor clinical outcome).

title: Infantile-onset Pompe disease: biceps
description: Analysis of biceps biopsies from untreated patients with infantile-onset Pompe. Pompe disease is a genetic disorder resulting from lysosomal acid alpha-glucosidase (GAA) deficiency; the severest form affects infants. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of infantile-onset Pompe disease.

title: cAMP agonist forskolin effect on INS-1 insulinoma cell line: time course
description: Analysis of insulinoma cells after short-term (2hr) and long-term (16hr) stimulation with cAMP agonist forskolin. Incretin hormone GLP-1 enhances islet cell survival via cAMP pathway induction in beta cells. Results provide insight into mechanisms by which GLP-1 promotes pancreatic islet viability.

title: Dietary fatty acid composition effect on vastus lateralis muscle
description: Analysis of skeletal muscle (SM) from insulin resistant men 4 hrs after consumption of meals high in saturated FA (SFA), monounsaturated FA (MUFA), or polyunsaturated FA (PUFA). Results provide insight into mechanisms underlying effects of FA composition on SM FA handling and insulin sensitivity.

title: Long-term pioglitazone effect on triple transgenic model of Alzheimer's disease (3xTg-AD): hippocampus
description: Analysis of hippocampus from 10 month-old, triple-transgenic AD females treated with the thiazolidinedione pioglitazone (PIO) for 14 weeks. TZDs exert cognitive benefits early in the AD process. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying the neuroprotective role of PIO in AD.

title: Amyloid Precursor Protein APP family members: adult prefrontal cortex
description: Analysis of prefrontal cortex of adult wild-type, APP knockout, APLP2 knockout, and APPsα knockin (solely expressing the secreted APPsα ectodomain) males. β-amyloid accumulation is a key trigger for Alzheimer's disease. Results provide insight into physiological functions of APP family members.

title: Bacterial cell wall component MDP effect on HEK293 cells expressing Crohn's disease-associated NOD2 variant L1007fsinsC receptor: time course
description: Temporal analysis of HEK293 cells stably-expressing wildtype NOD2 receptor or variant NOD2L1007fsinsC and treated with muramyl dipeptide (MDP). MDP-induced NOD2 activation induces inflammatory and antibacterial factors. Results provide insight into molecular basis of NOD2-mediated immune response.

title: Inhaled corticotherapy effect on allergic asthma: bronchial biopsies
description: Analysis of bronchial biopsies from allergic asthma (AA) subjects following inhaled corticosteroids (ICS) therapy. ICS represent potent anti-inflammatory controller medications for the treatment of asthma. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying the pathophysiology of AA.

title: Allergic asthma: bronchial biopsies
description: Analysis of bronchial biopsies from allergic asthma (AA) subjects.  These results, together with those from GDS4417 (a study with similar specimen collection procedures, but different subjects, GeneChips, data processing), provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying AA pathophysiology.

title: Alveolar macrophage response to bacterial endotoxin lipopolysaccharide exposure in vivo
description: Analysis of alveolar macrophages purified from bilateral bronchoalveolar lavage after saline instillation into a lung segment followed by LPS instillation into the contralateral lung. Results provide insight into innate immune pathways activated in alveolar macrophages exposed to LPS in vivo.

title: Stem cell factor effect on bone marrow-derived mast cells
description: Analysis of bone marrow-derived mast cells (MC) treated with interleukin 3 (IL3) or IL3 + stem cell factor (SCF). MCs chronically exposed to SCF have a greatly reduced capacity to degranulate and to generate cytokines in response to antigen. Results provide insight into role of SCF in MC activation.

title: Dendritic cell responses to proinflammatory TNF cytokine or pathogenic Trypanosoma brucei antigens
description: Analysis of dendritic cells (DCs) treated with TNFa cytokine or T. brucei-derived, variant-specific surface glycoproteins (AnTat1.1 mfVSG or MiTat1.5 sVSG). Results provide insight into the partial maturation signatures of the differentially stimulated DCs.

title: Interleukin-25-induced pulmonary inflammation model: Type 2 myeloid cells and other inflammatory subsets
description: Analysis of inflammatory cell types from lungs of 4get females that received daily intra-tracheal injections of IL-25 for 4 days to induce antigen-independent type 2 inflammation. Results provide insight into role of IL-25 and its receptor in innate and adaptive pulmonary type 2 immune responses.

title: Lung epithelium response to fungal allergen Alternaria
description: Analysis of bronchial brushings of lung epithelium from C57BL/6 females after Alternaria challenge. Alternaria allergen is associated with severe asthma, including life-threatening exacerbations. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the acute innate airway response to Alternaria.

title: Acute Picornavirus-induced exacerbation in asthmatic children: nasal lavage cells
description: Analysis of paired nasal lavage samples obtained from asthmatic children during an acute Picornavirus-induced asthma exacerbation in vivo and 7-14 days later. Severe episodes can be life-threatening. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying virus-induced asthma exacerbations.

title: Severe asthma: circulating CD4+ and CD8+ T-cells
description: Analysis of circulating CD4+ and CD8+ T-cells from adult patients with severe or nonsevere asthma. CD4+ T cells contribute to the development and maintenance of an inflammatory response in asthmatic patients. Results provide insight into the role of CD8+ T cells in severe asthma.

title: Epidermolysis Bullosa Simplex: epidermis
description: Analysis of epidermal punch biopsies (with minimal dermis amounts) from six EBS patients. Most EBS cases are caused by defects in the genes encoding intermediate filament proteins keratin 5 (KRT5) and keratin 14 (KRT14). Results provide further insight into the molecular basis of EBS.

title: Niemann-Pick Type C disease liver: time course
description: Analysis of liver across 3 age groups of Npc1−/− Balb/c females with Niemann-Pick Type C (NPC) disease. NPC is a neurodegenerative, lysosomal disorder caused by Npc1 or Npc2 gene dysfunction. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying NPC progression.

title: Niemann-Pick Type C disease spleen: time course
description: Analysis of spleen across 3 age groups of Npc1−/− Balb/c females with Niemann-Pick Type C (NPC) disease. NPC is a neurodegenerative, lysosomal disorder caused by Npc1 or Npc2 gene dysfunction. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying NPC progression.

title: Serca2a effect on Dilated Cardiomyopathy iPSC-derived cardiomyocytes
description: Analysis of DCM iPSC-derived cardiomyocytes treated with sarcoplasmic reticulum Ca2+ adenosine triphosphatase (Serca2a). Serca2a treatment improved the function of these cardiomyocytes. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of Serca2a-mediated repair of DCM iPSC-derived cardiomyocytes.

title: Sex effect on chronic coxsackievirus B3-induced myocarditis: heart
description: Analysis of heart from CVB3-infected males during chronic myocarditis/dilated cardiomyopathy (DCM) (day 90 postinfection). Myocarditis and DCM, often caused by viral infections, occur more frequently in men than in women. Results provided insight into molecular basis of DCM progression in males.

title: Truncated CBF beta-SMMHC defective in high-affinity binding with RUNX1 effect on spleen cells
description: Analysis of spleen cells from animals expressing a truncated form of CBF beta-SMMHC lacking the RUNX1 high-affinity binding domain (HABD). The type I CBF beta-SMMHC fusion in acute myeloid leukemia (AML) patients lacks HABD. Results provide insight into the molecular pathogenesis of leukemia.

title: Anti-CD47 antibody dimer MABL (S-S diabody) effect on leukemia cell line: time course
description: Temporal analysis of MOLT-4 leukemia cells treated with 10 ug/mL anti-CD47 dimer MABL (S-S diabody). Cell surface antigen CD47 ligation induces apoptosis in B-chronic lymphocytic leukemia. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanism of CD47-mediated apoptosis in lymphoid malignant cells.

title: Mixed-lineage leukemia MLL translocation subgroups in pediatric acute myeloid leukemia
description: Analysis of mostly bone marrow cells from pediatric acute myeloid leukemia (AML) patients belonging to various mixed-lineage leukemia (MLL) translocation subgroups. AML with rearrangements involving the MLL gene, located on chromosome 11q23, are associated with poor clinical outcome.

title: Polycomb repressive complex 1 protein Bmi1 transduced CCE embryonic stem cells and differentiated embryoid body samples
description: Analysis of Bmi1 transduced CCE embryonic stem cells (ESC) and CCE ESC differentiated by embryoid body assay. Bmi1 is essential for maintaining the pool of adult stem cells. Results provide insight into role of Bmi1 in ESC-derived hematopoietic cell transition from pluripotency to differentiation.

title: Chronic lymphocytic leukemia with chromosomal deletion 11q: peripheral blood CD19+ cells
description: Analysis of CD19+cells from peripheral blood of chronic lymphocytic leukemia (CLL) patients with interstitial deletions on the long arm of chromosome 11 (del11q).  Del11q is associated with progressive and aggressive CLL. Results provide insight into the molecular pathogenesis of CLL with del11q.

title: NF-kB inactivation effect on T-ALL1 cell lines
description: Analysis of T cell acute lymphoblastic leukemia (T-ALL) cell lines treated with a peptide that inhibits the activity of IKK, an activator of NF-kB.  NF-kB pathway is downstream of oncogenic Notch1 in T-ALL. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of Notch-induced NF-kB activation in T-ALL.

title: Simian immunodeficiency virus encephalitis model of HIV-associated dementia: hippocampus
description: Analysis of hippocampus from simian immunodeficiency virus (SIV) encephalitis and control monkeys. Rhesus SIV encephalitis closely models human HIV-associated dementia (HAD) occurring in patients with advanced HIV. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying HAD cognitive deficits.

title: Aging effect on hippocampal regions critical for memory and cognition
description: Analysis of hippocampal cornu ammonis and dentate gyrus from young and aged female simians. Aging rhesus monkeys develop Metabolic Syndrome (MetS) symptoms and age-related cognitive decline similar to humans. Results provide insight into MetS-associated brain dysfunction in aging.

title: Rift Valley Fever virus ZH548 infection effect on BALB/cByJ and MBT/Pas embryonic fibroblasts
description: Analysis of fibroblasts from BALB/cByJ or MBT/Pas animals infected with Rift Valley Fever virus (RVFV). RVFV is an arthropod-borne virus that primarily infects ruminants but can infect humans. Results provided insight into the role of genetic variation among hosts and their susceptibility to RVFV.

title: IL-10+CD8 T cell response to coronavirus infection
description: Analysis of IL-10+CD8 and IL-10−CD8 T cells from C57Bl/6 Vert-X animals infected with the neurotropic coronavirus J2.2-V-1. IL-10 is a potent anti-inflammatory cytokine. Results provide insight into the role of IL-10+CD8 T cells in the immune response to coronavirus-induced encephalitis.

title: Multiple sclerosis: brain lesions
description: Analysis of histologically characterized multiple sclerosis (MS) brain lesions. MS is an inflammatory autoimmune disease which progresses to demyelination of the brain and spinal cord. Results provide insight into molecular events during MS pathogenesis.

title: Peripheral blood monocyte CD16 + and Cd16- subsets from healthy donors
description: Analysis of peripheral blood monocyte (Mo) CD16 (FcγRIII) subsets CD16- and CD16+. Increase in circulating CD16+ Mo have been reported in inflammatory pathologies (sepsis/HIV infection). Results provide insight into developmental and functional relationship between CD16+ and CD16- Mo subsets.

title: HIV-associated nephropathy model: kidney
description: Analysis of kidney from TgFVB transgenic mouse model of Human Immunodeficiency Virus-Associated Nephropathy (HIVAN). HIVAN is characterized by rapid progressive kidney dysfunction and prominent tubular damage. Results provide insight into molecular mechanism underlying HIVAN-related tubular disease.

title: AIDS-related lymphomas
description: Analysis of tumors from HIV+ male patients with AIDS-related lymphomas (ARL). HIV+ individuals have an increased risk of developing an aggressive B-cell Non-Hodgkin Lymphoma relative to HIV- persons. Results identify a signature for ARL subtypes and provide insight into pathogenetic events in ARL.

title: Classic Hodgkins lymphoma diagnostic lymph-node biopsies
description: Analysis of diagnostic lymph-node biopsies from classic Hodgkins lymphoma HIV- patients before ABVD chemotherapy. Results identify gene expression signatures that correlate with treatment outcomes.

title: Simian Immunodeficiency Virus infection effect on lymph nodes of Sooty mangabeys and Rhesus macaques
description: Temporal analysis of lymph nodes of SIVsmm infected Sooty mangabeys (SM) and SIVmac239 infected Rhesus macaques (RM). SIVsmm is non-pathogenic to host SM but origin of pathogens (HIV-2/SIVmac) to humans and RM. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the differences in host responses.

title: West Nile virus infection effect on retinal pigment epithelium cells
description: Analysis of primary retinal pigment epithelial (RPE) cells and RPE ARPE-19 cells infected with West Nile virus (WNV). WNV infection can lead to ocular pathologies such as chorioretinitis, uveitis, or optic neuritis. Results provide insight into the molecular response of RPE cells to WNV infection.

title: Monocyte-derived dendritic cells co-infected with HIV-GFP(G) and SIV-VLP(G)
description: Analysis of MDDCs exposed to GFP-encoding HIV-1 pseudotyped with vesicular stomatitis virus protein G (VSV-G) [HIV-GFP(G)], VSV-G-pseudotyped SIVmac239 virus-like particles [SIV-VLP(G)], or both. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms udnerlying DC activation after HIV-1 infection.

title: Programmed Death-1-expressing CD8 T cells in healthy adult peripheral blood
description: Analysis of PD-1hi, PD-1lo, and naive CD8+CD3+ T cells FACS-sorted from peripheral blood of healthy adults. PD-1, a member of the CD28 family of immune modulators, is highly expressed on chronic virus-specific CD8 T cells. Results provide insight into PD-1-expressing CD8 T cells in healthy adults.

title: Highly Active Antiretroviral Therapy (HAART) interruption effect on HIV patients: jejunal mucosa
description: Analysis of gut biopsies from HIV+ patients following interruption of HAART. Gut-associated lymphoid tissue (GALT) is a critical host-pathogen interaction site in HIV infection. Results provide insight into molecular basis of host response to viral rebound in GALT following HAART interruption.

title: Model of HIV-associated pulmonary arterial hypertension: right superior lobe of lung
description: Analysis of lung from 3 month old, human immunodeficiency virus (HIV)-transgenic F344 males. The HIV-transgenics display pulmonary hypertension and pulmonary artery remodeling. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying HIV-PAH onset and progression.

title: Pathogenic Simian Immunodeficiency Virus infection in Rhesus macaques: colorectal tissue
description: Analysis of colorectal biopsies from SIV-infected Rhesus macaques (RM) and Sooty mangabeys (SM). Unlike AIDS-susceptible RMs, natural hosts such as SMs do not progress to AIDS. Results provide insight into molecular basis of immune activation following pathogenic immunodeficiency virus infections.

title: Antiretroviral therapy effect on brain of patients with HIV-associated neurocognitive disorders
description: Analysis of postmortem brain of ART-treated, HIV-1-associated neurocognitive disorders (HAND) patients. ART reduces morbidity and mortality in HIV infection, but HAND persist despite treatment. Results provide insight into ART effectiveness in brain and into molecular signatures of HAND under ART.

title: HIV infection effect on interferon alpha 2-treated monocyte-derived macrophages: time course
description: Temporal analysis of macrophages pretreated for 18hrs with interferon alpha 2 (IFNα2) then infected with HIV-1 (Bal strain). IFN treatment prior to in vitro HIV infection inhibits virus replication. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying this modulation of viral replication.

title: Protein kinase HIPK2 overexpression effect on Human Embryonic Kidney cells
description: Analysis of HEK293 cells transfected with homeo-domain interacting protein kinase 2 (HIPK2) and HIPK2-DN mutant. HIPK2 mediates renal fibrosis in 3 mouse models of renal fibrosis (Tg26, UUO, folic-acidinduced renal fibrosis). Results provide further insight into role of HIPK2 in kidney fibrosis.

title: Transgenic model Tg26 of HIV-Associated Nephropathy: kidney cortex
description: Analysis of kidney cortices from HIV-1 transgenic, FVB/N males and females (Tg26). Tg26 models the renal pathologic changes observed in human disease and is used to study HIV-associated nephropathy (HIVAN) pathogenesis. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying HIVAN.

title: Programmed Death 1 antibody effect on pathogenic Simian Immunodeficiency Virus infection: peripheral blood mononuclear cells
description: Analysis of PBMCs from SIVmac251-infected (12 wks) rhesus macaques (RMs) treated with an antibody against Programmed Death-1 (PD-1) for 14 days. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms by which PD-1 blockade enhances survival of SIV-infected RMs.

title: Rapamycin-resistant diffuse large B-cell lymphoma cell lines
description: Analysis of diffuse large B-cell lymphoma (DLBCL) cell lines resistant to rapamycin, the prototypical mTOR (mammalian Target Of Rapamycin) inhibitor. The mTOR pathway is constitutively activated in DLBCL. Results provide insight into mechanisms of resistance to mTOR inhibition in DLBCL.

title: Rhesus macaque type-I interferon agonist effect on peripheral whole blood of SIV-infected Sooty mangabeys: time course
description: Temporal analysis of whole blood from 8 naturally SIV-infected SMs treated with recombinant RM IFNalpha2-IgFc (rmIFNα2) for 16 weeks. SIV infection of SMs is typically non-pathogenic. Results provide insight into effects of experimentally-augmented IFN-I signaling in chronically SIV-infected SMs.

title: Pandemic and seasonal influenza A H1N1 infection of differentiated type I-like alveolar epithelial cells in vitro
description: Analysis of type I-like alveolar epithelial cells infected with pandemic influenza H1N1 (pdmH1N1) or seasonal H1N1. Type I alveolar epithelial cells are a key target cell in pdmH1N1 pneumonia. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying host responses induced by H1N1 infections.

title: Severe pandemic H1N1 influenza effect on peripheral blood: time course
description: Temporal analysis of peripheral blood from patients with severe pdm(H1N1) influenza, bilateral chest infiltrates, and in need of mechanical ventilation, but without significant co-morbidity. Results provide insight into molecular basis of immune responses in patients with severe pdmH1N1 infection.

title: Methicillin-resistant and methicillin-sensitive control strains
description: Analysis of methicillin-resistant Staphylococcus aureus (MRSA) ATCC 33591 and methicillin-sensitive (MSSA) ATCC 25923; commonly used positive and negative control strains. Results provide comparison of representative MRSA and MSSA strains and insight into mechanisms of S. aureus drug resistance.

title: Host immune response of bacterial infected nematode stimulated with small molecule
description: Analysis of bacterial infected C. elegans treated with 70 μM RPW-24 or DMSO. In a C.elegans-bacterial infection assay screening small molecules, RPW-24 was identified as a putative antimicrobial agent. Results provide insight into C. elegans conserved immune response to bacterial infection.

title: Antibiotic-resistant Small Colony Variant
description: Analysis of Pseudomonas aeruginosa PA01 (ATCC 15692) Small Colony Variant (SCV). SCVs are slow-growing bacteria that often show increased resistance to antibiotics and cause infection. Results provide insight into mechanisms governing acquisition and reversion of antibiotic resistance in bacteria.

title: Artificial medium mimicking cystic fibrosis lung sputum
description: Analysis of Pseudomonas aeruginosa UCBPP-PA14 grown on artificial-sputum medium (ASMDM), MOPS-glucose medium and Luria broth; early exponential and stationary phases. ASMDM mimics cystic fibrosis lung environment.

title: Lubiprostone effect on cystic fibrosis small intestine phenotype
description: Analysis of small intestine from Cftr null and wild type mice treated with fluid secretion activator lubiprostone. Cystic fibrosis (CF) mice display CF trait of impaired mucus turnover. Results provide insight into response of CF intestine to lubiprostone treatment.

title: Cystic fibrosis bronchial epithelial cells exposure to Pseudomonas aeruginosa PA01 biofilms
description: Analysis of cystic fibrosis (CF) bronchial epithelial CFBE41o- cells exposed to Pseudomonas aeruginosa PA01 biofilms. Cells overexpressing 508del-CFTR and cells rescued with wild type CFTR were examined. CFTR mutations enhance the inflammatory response in the lung to PA01 infection.

title: Lung epithelial cells response to lipopolysaccharide exposure
description: Analysis of laser-microdissected airway epithelial cells from snap-frozen lung 0 and 2 days after lipopolysaccharide (LPS) exposure. Inhalation of LPS can lead to chronic lung diseases like cystic fibrosis and asthma. Results provide insight into inflammatory mediators modulated by LPS exposure.

title: KinB and RpoN deletion effects on alginate overproduction
description: Analysis of Pseudomonas aeruginosa PAO1 mucoid kinB mutant and nonmucoid kinB rpoN double mutant. Deletion of the sensor kinase KinB  results in alginate overproduction, a trait associated with chronic endobronchial infections in cystic fibrosis. Sigma Factor RpoN is required for mucoid induction.

title: Cystic fibrosis transmembrane conductance regulator expression in airway epithelial cells
description: Analysis of Calu-3 airway epithelial cells transfected with miR-138 mimic or SIN3A siRNA. MicroRNA-138 regulates Cystic fibrosis transmembrane conductance regulator (CFTR) expression through its interactions with the transcriptional regulatory protein SIN3A.

title: Caseous tuberculosis granulomas comparison with normal lung parenchyma
description: Analysis of caseous pulmonary tuberculosis (TB) granulomas. TB progression involves caseous granuloma development that cavitates, releasing infectious Mycobacterium tuberculosis bacilli. Results provide insight into TB etiology and pathogen-mediated dysregulation of host lipid metabolism.

title: Early lung immune response in tuberculosis: time course
description: Analysis of Mycobacterium tuberculosis (Mt)-infected lung 0 to 21 days after infection. TB immunity is associated with IFNγ lung T helper cell type 1 (Th1) accumulation and Mt-infected macrophage activation. Results provide insight into immune events that occur prior to Th1 accumulation in TB lung.

title: High grade astrocytoma patient survival: brain tumor
description: Analysis of surgical brain tumors from high grade astrocytoma (HGA) patients with known clinical outcomes. Increased expression of immune function-related genes was positively correlated with longer survival. Results provide insight into molecular profiles associated with long-term survival in HGA.

title: Nrf2-deficient type II lung epithelial cell response to antioxidant supplementation
description: Analysis of Nrf2 deficient lung epithelial cells treated with the antioxidant glutathione (GSH). GSH rescues cells from prooxidant-induced lung injury associated with Nrf2 deficiency. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms by which Nrf2 regulates cellular protection and proliferation.

title: Inflamed vascular epithelial cells response to apple extract enriched for procyanidins
description: Analysis of inflamed vascular endothelial cells treated with an apple extract enriched for procyanidins of low molecular weight. Results provide insight into possible protective effects induced by the plant derived procyanidins on the endothelial cells.

title: Oxidative stress effect on ATF4 knockout embryonic neurons
description: Analysis of bZip transcription factor activating transcription factor 4 (ATF4)-deficient, embryonic neurons treated with homocysteate (HCA), a glutamate analog that induces oxidative stress. Results provide insight into the role of ATF4 in oxidative stress-induced cell death.

title: Coronary artery disease response to exercise: CD133+ cells
description: Analysis of CD133+ endothelial progenitor cells of coronary artey disease (CAD) patients after 3 months of exercise. Bone marrow derived progenitor cells with endothelial differentiation potential are fewer in CAD. Results provide insight into the impact of exercise on CD133+ cells of CAD patients.

title: Erk5 activation effect on endothelial cells
description: Analysis of umbilical vein endothelial cells (ECs) transfected with MEK5D, a constitutively active mutant kinase, to activate Erk5.  The MEK5/Erk5 MAPK pathway is activated by laminar shear stress in ECs. Results provide insight into the role of the MEK5/Erk5 pathway in endothelial function.

title: BRCA1 depletion effect on HeLa cells
description: Analysis of HeLa cells depleted for BRCA1. BRCA1, the breast and ovarian cancer specific tumor suppressor, is a transcriptional regulator.  Results identify transcriptional targets of BRCA1.

title: Carboplatin effect on epithelial ovarian cancer cell line: time course
description: Analysis of 36M2 epithelial ovarian cancer cells (EOC) treated with 100 uM carboplatin for up to 36 hours. Gene expression profile compared to those from ovarian cells of patients with unfavorable and favorable outcomes. Results provide insight into the mechanism of drug resistance in EOC.

title: Tobacco smoke effect on the placenta
description: Analysis of placentas of women who smoked during pregnancy. Smoking increases the risk of preterm delivery and complications such as placental previa and abruption. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of smoke-induced placental abnormalities.

title: Rheumatoid arthritis: peripheral blood mononuclear cells
description: Analysis of peripheral blood mononuclear cells of rheumatoid arthritis (RA) patients. Results provide insight into the molecular pathogenesis and pathophysiology of RA.

title: Myelodysplastic syndrome: CD34+ hematopoietic stem cells
description: Analysis of bone marrow CD34+ hematopoietic stem cells of myelodysplastic syndrome (MDS) patients. MDS is a group of clonal hematopoietic stem cell malignancies characterized by ineffective hematopoiesis. Results provide insight into the molecular pathogenesis of MDS.

title: Atopic dermatitis
description: Analysis of non-lesional epidermal samples from individuals with atopic dermatitis (AD).  AD is characterized by dry eczematous skin lesions, a relapsing and often chronic course, and an intense intractable pruritus. Results provide insight into the molecular pathogenesis of AD.

title: Sebacic acid supplemented diet effect on db/db liver
description: Analysis of livers of db/db animals fed a diet supplemented with sebacic acid (SA) for 6 weeks. SA supplementation improves fasting plasma glucose, HbA1c and glucose tolerance in this model of type 2 diabetes. Results provide insight into the mechanism of action of SA.

title: DNA methyltransferase triple knockout nuclear transfer-trophoblastic stem cells
description: Analysis of Dnmt1/3a/3b-TKO ntTS cells, wildtype ntTS cells, and cell types representing the three blastocyst-derived lineages: epiblast (ES cells), trophectoderm (TS cells), and primitive endoderm (XEN cells, PE cells). Results provide insight into role of DNA methylation in early embryogenesis.

title: WHO 2008-classified acute myeloid leukemia subgroups (Analysis I): bone marrow mononuclear cells
description: Analysis of BMMCs from untreated patients diagnosed as AML-MLD-sole (AML with myelodysplasia-related changes solely because of multilineage dysplasia) or AML-NOS (AML-not otherwise specified) according to WHO 2008 guidelines. Results provide insight into the relevance of MLD for AML classification.

title: WHO 2008-classified acute myeloid leukemia subgroups (Analysis II): bone marrow mononuclear cells
description: Analysis of BMMCs from untreated patients with AML-MRC (AML with myelodysplasia-related changes) and from the combined group AML-NOS plus AML-MLD-sole on the basis of cytogenetics or a myelodysplastic syndrome (MDS) history. Results provide insight into the relevance of MLD for AML classification.

title: Systemic Lupus Erythematosus: mononuclear cells
description: Analysis of freshly isolated lymphocyte (CD4+ T cells and CD19+ B cells) and CD33+ myeloid subsets from the blood of Systemic Lupus Erythematosus (SLE) patients. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying SLE pathogenesis.

title: Lupus nephritis model response to sirolimus-induced mTOR inhibition (Mu11KsubA)
description: Analysis of kidney from sirolimus-treated NZB/W F1 females at 36 and 42 weeks of age. Sirolimus, a mammalian target of rapamycin (mTOR) inhibitor, has been efficacious in the NZB/W model of lupus nephritis. Results provide insight into role of the mTOR pathway in autoimmune lupus nephritis.

title: CD3+ T cell response to stimulation with CD3/CD28 or nitric oxide
description: Analysis of healthy T cells stimulated with CD3/CD28 (a Ca2+ fluxing inducer) or NO (a key trigger of mitochondrial hyperpolarization (MHP)). Enhanced Ca2+ fluxing and MHP underlie aberrant T-cell activation in SLE. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of T cell dysfunction in lupus.

title: Pristane-induced plasmacytoma tumor model: time course
description: Analysis of mesentery from BALB/c, DBA, and BALB/DBA animals up to 18 days after intraperitoneal injection of pristane (TMPD). TMPD induces B-cell plasmacytoma (PCT) in 60% of BALB/c animals, but DBA animals remain tumor-free. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of PCT susceptibility.

title: Aged, lupus-prone MRL/Faslpr model: splenic CD4 T cells
description: Analysis of CD4 T cells isolated from spleens of aged (16-24 wks) MRL/Faslpr females and sorted into 3 populations: CD62Lhi/PSGL1hi, CD62Llo/PSGL1hi, and CD62Llo/PSGL1lo. MRL/Faslpr animals exhibit lupus disease traits from 12-16 wks.  Results provide insight into molecular basis of lupus onset.

title: NZM2410-derived lupus susceptibility locus Sle2c1: peritoneal cavity B cells
description: Analysis of peritoneal cavity B cells (B1a) and splenic B (sB) cells from B6.Sle2c1 mice. Sle2 induces expansion of the B1a cell compartment, a B cell defect consistently associated with lupus. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying susceptibility to lupus in the NZM2410 model.

title: Quiescent systemic lupus erythematosus: peripheral blood B cells
description: Analysis of B cells sorted from the peripheral blood of patients with quiescent lupus (inactive > 6 months). B cell activation and production of a wide variety of autoantibodies appear central to lupus development. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying systemic lupus.

title: NZB/W model of systemic lupus erythematosus: renal macrophages
description: Analysis of F4/80hi renal macrophages isolated at an early stage of lupus, during lupus nephritis, and after induction of remission. The infiltrating F4/80hi cells are associated with renal damage. Results provide insight into mechanisms by which F4/80hi macrophages contribute to lupus nephritis.

title: Systemic lupus erythematosus and arthritides: synovial biopsies
description: Analysis of synovial biopsies obtained by needle arthroscopy from affected knees of patients with systemic lupus erythematosus (SLE), rheumatoid arthritis (RA), or osteoarthritis (OA). Results provide insight into distinct molecular mechanisms underlying SLE arthritis relative to those of OA and RA.

title: Australian patient cohort: gastric adenocarcinoma
description: Analysis of 70 primary gastric tumors representing 3 subtypes (invasive, metabolic, and proliferative) from the Australian patient cohort (AU-2). Gastric adenocarcinomas show sizable heterogeneity between patients. Results provide insight into molecular characterization of gastric cancer subtypes.

title: Wild-type embryonic stem cell rescue of mdx model of Duchenne muscular dystrophy: skeletal muscle
description: Analysis of pectoralis muscle from 4 month-old, wildtype/mdx chimeric males.  Chimeras were created by injecting WT ESCs into mdx mutant blastocysts; injected blastocysts developed in the uterus of pseudopregnant females. Results provide insight into molecular basis of WT ESC rescue of mdx mice.

title: Cmah knockout effect on mdx model of Duchenne Muscular Dystrophy (DMD): skeletal muscle
description: Analysis of muscle from mdx males with a human-specific deletion in the Cmah (cytidine monophosphate-sialic acid hydroxylase) gene. Cmah-/-mdx mice show increased disease severity that better approximates DMD in humans. Results provide insight into the contributions of glycosylation defects to DMD.

title: Chronic hypoxia effect on dmDys model of Duchenne Muscular Dystrophy: single whole animal
description: Analysis of 3-5 day-old dystrophin-deficient animals exposed to chronic hypoxia (CH) for 2 weeks. Respiratory muscle necrosis in late-stage DMD is associated with respiratory insufficiency and CH. Results provide insight into the effects of CH on dystrophin-deficient muscle in vivo.

title: Primary chronic lymphocytic leukemia cell response to purine nucleoside analog LMP-420
description: Analysis of chronic lymphocytic leukemia (CLL) patient cells cultured with LMP-420 (2 uM) for 24 hr. LMP-420 is an anti-inflammatory agent that induces CLL cell apoptosis in vitro without impairing normal immune cells. Results provide insight into the mechanism of action of LMP-420 in CLL.

title: Dexamethasone effect on glucocorticoid-resistant and -sensitive lymphoblastic leukemia cell lines
description: Analysis of glucocorticoid (GC)-resistant and -sensitive derivatives of the CEM-C7H2 T-ALL cell line following 6hrs of dexamethasone treatment. GC drugs are a central component of childhood ALL therapy. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying the anti-leukemic effects of GC.

title: Growth factor independence 1 knockout effect on LSK hematopoietic stem bone marrow cells
description: Analysis of Lin-Sca1+ckit+Flt3- (LSKFlt3-) hematopoietic stem cells (HSC) depleted of growth factor independence 1 (Gfi1). Transcriptional repressor Gfi1 restricts HSC proliferation and is essential to self-renewal. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying Gfi1 effects in HSCs.

title: Transcription factor c-JUN knockout effect on B lymphoid cells
description: Analysis of B lymphoid cells depleted of activating protein 1 (AP-1) transcription factor c-JUN. c-JUN is involved in BCR-ABL oncogene-induced transformation and leukemogenesis. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying c-JUN modulation of leukemogenesis.

title: Pediatric acute leukemia patients with early relapse: white blood cells
description: Analysis of WBCs from pediatric B cell precursor (BCP) acute lymphoblastic leukemia (ALL) patients with early, late, or no relapse. For patients with relapsed BCP-ALL, early relapses fare worse than later relapses. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of early relapses in BCP-ALL.

title: Early differentiating TG2a embryonic stem cells expressing cell surface 5T4 oncofetal glycoprotein
description: Analysis of differentiating E14 TG2a ESCs with cell surface expression of 5T4. The upregulation of 5T4 expression is associated with loss of pluripotency in ES cells. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying the balance between pluripotency and differentiation in ES cells.

title: HIV infection and Antiretroviral Therapy effects on mitochondria in various tissues
description: Analysis of PBMCs, muscle, adipose tissue from human immunodeficiency virus (HIV)-positive adults receiving nucleoside reverse transcriptase inhibitor (NRTI)-based ART. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying the divergent effects of HIV infection and ART on mitochondria in fat.

title: Bronchial epithelial cell response to influenza virus, viral RNA and interferon-beta: time course
description: Analysis of HBECs treated with IFNβ, wild-type H1N1 influenza (PR8), mutant ΔNS1 virus (PR8 with a deleted NS1 gene), viral RNA (purified directly from PR8), up to 18 hr post-treatment. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms mediating influenza-host interactions in H1N1 infection.

title: Choroid plexus epithelial cells response to Streptococcus suis infection
description: Analysis of porcine choroid plexus epithelial cells (PCPEC) infected with virulent Streptococcus suis serotype 2 and isogenic capsular mutant 10cps{delta}EF. The S. suis capsule is critical to its pathogenicity. Results provide insight into choroid plexus cellular response to S. suis meningitis infe

title: Peripheral blood response to Salmonella in animals with different Salmonella shedding levels
description: Analysis of peripheral blood from Salmonella enterica serovar Typhimurium (ST)-inoculated animals differing in Salmonella shedding phenotype at 0 and 2 days post-inoculation (dpi) . Fecal shedding of asymptomatic, Salmonella-carriers can lead to foodborne illness.

title: Cystic fibrosis: trachea, bronchus and distal lung
description: Analysis of trachea, bronchus and distal lung from newborn pigs with cystic fibrosis transmembrane conductance regulator (CFTR) gene mutations. Cystic fibrosis (CF) pigs develop lung disease. Results provide insight into CF lung disease pathogenesis.

title: Cystic fibrosis: trachea
description: Analysis of trachea from newborn pigs with cystic fibrosis transmembrane conductance regulator (CFTR) mutation; CFTR-/- pigs spontaneously develop hallmark features of CF lung disease. Results provide insight into Cystic fibrosis lung disease pathogenesis.

title: Chronological clonal isolates from sputum or throat samples of cystic fibrosis patients
description: Analysis of clonal isolates collected from three patients with cystic fibrosis (CF).  The isolates were collected between 3 months to 8 years after colonization, representing upwards of 39,000 in vivo generations. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of long-term infection of CF lung.

title: Diel and circadian effects on adult female heads and bodies: time course
description: Analysis of heads and bodies of mated, non-blood-fed, adult females maintained under a 12hr:12hr light:dark (LD) cycle or constant dark (DD) conditions; samples were collected every 4hr for 48 hr. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms under circadian and LD cycle control.

title: Balanced and unbalanced chromosomal translocations: lymphoblastoid cell lines
description: Analysis of lymphoblastoid cell lines established from individuals with the t(11;22)(q23;q11)-balanced translocation (carriers) or the +der(22)t(11;22)(q23;q11) karyotype (Emanuel syndrome patients). Results provide insight into the effect of balanced chromosomal rearrangements on the transcriptome.

title: Systemic juvenile idiopathic arthritis and non-systemic JIA subtypes: peripheral blood mononuclear cells
description: Analysis of PBMCs from patients with systemic juvenile idiopathic arthritis (sJIA) or non-sJIA. sJIA patients have significantly increased expansion of  immature PBMC subpopulations,  including CD34+ cells. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying sJIA pathogenesis.

title: Transforming growth factor-beta effect on Hepatocellular carcinoma Huh-7 cell line
description: Analysis of Hepatocellular carcinoma (HCC) Huh-7 cells stimulated with transforming growth factor-beta (TGF-β). HCC cell line Huh-7 has intact WNT pathway components. Results provide insight into the role of TGF-β in regulating WNT pathway activity in HCC cells.

title: Pediatric age-specific host response to septic shock: whole blood
description: Analysis of whole blood from children (up to 10 years old) within 24hrs of PICU admission for septic shock. Sepsis therapies useful in adults and older children may have little effect in immunologically immature younger patients. Results provide insight into age-specific host response to sepsis.

title: Stratification of pediatric septic shock patients: whole blood
description: Analysis of whole blood from children (up to 10 years old) within 24hrs of PICU admission for septic shock. Heterogeneous clinical phenotypes stratify the septic shock patients. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying these septic shock subgroups.

title: Effect of lifestyle on Moroccan Amazighs: peripheral blood leukocytes
description: Analysis of leukocytes from regionally distinct groups of Moroccan Amazighs leading diverse lifestyles: nomadic, rural, and urban. The Amazighs represent a genetically relatively homogeneous population. Results provide insight into effect of environment on immune function and disease susceptibility.

title: Acute myeloid leukemia fusion oncogene-transduced granulocyte monocyte precursors
description: Analysis of granulocyte monocyte precursors (GMPs) transduced with GFP alone or with AML-fusion oncogenes MOZ-TIF2 or NUP98-HOXA9 or AML1-ETO. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying transformation and self-renewal downstream of multiple AML-associated oncogenes.

title: Notch-on and Notch-off effects on T-lymphoblastic leukemia cell line CUTLL1: time course
description: Analysis of Notch1-dependent TLL cell line CUTLL1 treated with γ-secretase-inhibitor (GSI) to block Notch signaling, subjected to GSI washout to induce Notch1 reactivation, and incubated up to 4hr with translational inhibitor cycloheximide. Results provide insight into Notch1 function in TLL.

title: Early T-cell precursor acute lymphoblastic leukemia
description: Analysis of tumor cells from pediatric patients with early T-cell precursor acute lymphoblastic leukemia (ETP ALL). The ETP ALL subtype has a poor prognosis when treated with standard chemotherapy. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying ETP ALL.

title: PICALM-MLLT10 positive acute leukemia: mononuclear cells
description: Analysis of mononuclear cells from PICALM-MLLT10-positive T-cell acute lymphoblastic leukemia (T-ALL) patients (2 cases with histone methyltransferase gene EZH2 mutations) and PICALM-MLLT10-negative T-ALL patients. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying the leukemia subtypes.

title: Glycogen synthase kinase 3 α knockdown in acute myeloid leukemia  cell lines
description: Analysis of AML cell lines infected with shRNAs against glycogen synthase kinase 3 α and β isoforms (GSK-3α, GSK-3β). GSK-3 is a multifunctional serine threonine kinase; specific loss of GSK-3α induces differentiation in AML. Results provide insight into the role of GSK-3α in AML.

title: Post myocardial infarction heart: left ventricle
description: Analysis of remote, non-ischemic, regions of the left ventricle from animals that underwent permanent ligation of the left coronary artery to induce myocardial infarction (MI). Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying cardiac remodeling following MI.

title: Conventionalization of germ-free C57BL/6 males: time course
description: Temporal analysis of colon, ileum, and jejunum from conventionalized males (i.e., germfree mice colonized with total fecal microbiota of their conventionally born and raised siblings). Results provide insight into molecular basis of innate and adaptive immune responses during conventionalization.

title: CD-1 neuronal stem cell response to microRNA-128 mimic
description: Analysis of E14.5 brain-derived, neuronal stem cell cultures transfected with a miR-128 mimic. miR-128, a brain-specific miRNA,  represses Nonsense-Mediated mRNA Decay, thereby controlling numerous transcripts in neural cells. Results provide insight into role of miR-128 in neuron differentiation.

title: Fetal brain response to maternal immune activation induced by lipopolysaccharide
description: Analysis of fetal brains following maternal immune activation (MIA) induced by treating pregnant dams with lipopolysaccharide. MIA is a risk factor for the development of schizophrenia and autism. Results provide insight into the effect of MIA on the fetal brain at the molecular level.

title: 16p11.2 copy number variation models: various brain regions
description: Analysis of brain regions of C57BL/6N:129Sv animals harboring a df/+ deletion or dp/+ duplication in the chromosomal region corresponding to 16p11.2 in humans. Recurrent copy number variations (CNVs) of human 16p11.2 are associated with a variety of developmental/neurocognitive syndromes.

title: Autistic children and their father’s age: peripheral blood lymphocytes
description: Analysis of peripheral blood lymphocytes of autistic and non-autistic children. Correlation among gene expression changes, paternal age, and autism examined.

title: Rough attenuated Brucella suis strain infection effect on macrophage cell line: time course
description: Analysis of J774.A1 macrophage cells for up to 48 hours following infection with S1330-smooth virulent or VTRS1-rough attenuated Brucella suis strain. S1330 prevents macrophage cell death while VTRS1 induces it. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of VTRS1-induced macrophage cell death.

title: MyD88 and TRIF deficient spleen response to septic peritonitis
description: Analysis of spleens of MyD88 and TRIF double null mutants following surgical induction of septic peritonitis. MyD88 and TRIF are involved in innate immune responses that combat bacterial infections. Results provide insight into the role of MyD88 and TRIF in the pathogenesis of septic peritonitis.

title: Tuberous sclerosis complex 1 deficient CD4 T cell response to T cell receptor stimulation
description: Analysis of Tuberous sclerosis complex 1 (Tsc1) deficient CD4 T cells after T cell receptor stimulation using anti-CD3-CD28. Tsc1 is an mTOR signaling modulator involved in naive T cell quiescence and immune homeostasis regulation. Results provide insight into the role of Tsc1 in T cell quiescence.

title: Mammary gland cells of different genetic predispositions for somatic cell score response to S. aureus and E. coli: time course
description: Mammary gland epithelial cells of cows with favorable somatic cell score (SCS) QTL allele Q and unfavorable allele q after S. aureus or E.coli exposure for up to 24 hours. SCS is an indicator of milk quality and udder health. Results provide insight into molecular basis of mastitis susceptibility.

title: Phagocytic receptor Eater depleted hemocyte-derived cell line response to phagocytosed bacteria: time course
description: Analysis of phagocytic receptor Eater depleted hemocyte-derived S2 cells after phagocytosing bacteria for up to 180 minutes. Results provide insight into the role of Eater in the transcriptional regulation of genes that are induced after bacterial binding and phagocytosis.

title: MOZ-TIF2 fusion oncogene-associated leukemic stem cells
description: Analysis of leukemic stem cells (LSCs), with granulocyte monocyte precursor (GMP) surface phenotype, from a MOZ-TIF2 model of leukemia (L-GMPs) and their normal GMP counterparts. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying the evolution and maintenance of LSCs in leukemogenesis.

title: Transcription factor Otx2 knockout effect on fourth ventricular choroid plexus
description: Analysis of fourth ventricular choroid plexus tissue from Otx2 knockout mice at E13. Choroid plexuses (ChPs) are main regulators of cerebrospinal fluid composition in developing brain. Results provide insight into role of transcription factor Otx2 in development and maintenance of ChP cells.

title: Runt homology domain expression effect on hematopoietic stem cells
description: Analysis of c-Kit+Sca-1+Lin- hematopoietic stem cells (HSCs) lacking Runx1 or expressing the runt homology domain, RUNX1 (41-214). RUNX1(41-214) expression induces myelodysplastic syndrome (MDS) in mice. Results provide insight into molecular basis of MDS progression induced by RUNX1 (41-214).

title: bHLH transcription factor Mesogenin1 ectopic expression effect on embryoid bodies: time course
description: Analysis of embryoid bodies following induction of ectopic Msgn1 expression for up to 48 hours. Msgn1, a bHLH transcription factor, is a target of Wnt3a, a signaling protein that functions in the segmentation clock and the determination front during somitogenesis.

title: Homeobox transcription factor Dlx5 deficiency effect on embryonic otic vesicle
description: Analysis of otic vesicles from E10 and E10.5 embryos deficient for Dlx5. Dlx5 is a homeobox transcription factor that plays a key role in the development of many organ systems. Results provide insight into the role of Dlx5 in the regulation of early inner ear development.

title: Atopic Dermatitis response to narrow-band UVB treatment
description: Analysis of lesional and non-lesional skin biopsies from Atopic Dermatitis patients following NB-UVB phototherapy. Results identify a set of biomarkers of disease response to NB-UVB phototherapy.

title: Polycomb group protein CBX2 deficiency effect on XY and XX embryonic gonads
description: Analysis of E11.5 XY and  XX embryonic gonads deficient for the Polycomb group protein CBX2. Animals lacking CBX2 exhibit defects in gonadal, adrenal and splenic development. Results provide insight into role of Cbx2 in gonadal sex differentiation.

title: Zinc finger transcription factor Fezf1 deficiency effect on main olfactory epithelial cells
description: Analysis of E.18 olfactory cells lacking Fezf1, a zinc finger transcription factor. Olfactory cells isolated from the main olfactory epithelium. Results provide insight into the role of Fezf1 in olfactory system development and sensory neuron identity.

title: Neurofibromin inactivation effect on triceps muscle
description: Analysis of triceps muscles of 3 month old animals inactivated for the neurofibromin Nf1 gene in the early limb bud mesenchyme.  This inactivation results in muscular dystrophy. Results provide insight into the role of Nf1 in skeletal muscle development.

title: Large RS-like factor SON knockdown effect in HeLa cervical cancer cell line
description: Analysis of HeLa cells depleted of SON, a large Ser/Arg (SR)-related protein localized in nuclear speckles. SON depletion severely impairs spindle pole separation, microtubule dynamics, and genome integrity. Results provide insight into the role of SON in cell-cycle progression.

title: Model of β-catenin overexpression in embryonic kidney
description: Analysis of β-catGOF-UB (β-catenin Gain of Function-Ureteric Bud) mutant kidneys from E12.5 embryos. The β-catGOF-UB mutants display severe renal malformations.  Results provide insight into the role of β-catenin in renal dysplasia.

title: Inositol 1,4,5-trisphosphate receptor type 1 and type 3 double knockouts: embryonic heart
description: Analysis of heart from E9.25 embryos double-mutant for intracellular Ca2+ release channels IP3R type 1 and type 3 (IP3R1-/-IP3R3-/-). The double-mutants show hypoplasia of the outflow region in fetal heart. Results provide insight into a redundant role for IP3R1 and IP3R2 during cardiogenesis.

title: Childhood cerebral adrenoleukodystrophy patient-specific iPSC model
description: Analysis of induced pluripotent stem cells (iPSC) derived from childhood cerebral adrenoleukodystrophy (CCALD) patient dermal fibroblasts. Inflammatory brain demyelination is observed in CCALD patients. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying CCALD pathogenesis.

title: Wild type embryonic lens development
description: Analysis of lens from ICR embryos at 3 key developmental stages in the transition from E10.5 lens placode invagination to E12.5 lens primary fiber cell differentiation and matched whole embryo body (WB, minus ocular tissue) controls. Results provide insight into molecular basis of lens development.

title: Wild type embryonic tooth germ tissue
description: Analysis of laser capture microdissected tooth germ tissue from ICR E13.5 embryos and matched whole embryo body (WB, without tooth germ) controls representing stages E11.5, E12.5, and E13.5. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying tooth development.

title: Fibroblast growth factor receptor 3 depletion effect on bladder cancer cell line RT112
description: Analysis of bladder cancer cell line RT112 subjected to doxycycline-inducible, shRNA knockdown of FGFR3. Knockdown of FGFR3 in RT112 cells significantly attenuates tumor growth in vitro and in vivo. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying FGFR3-driven bladder cancer.

title: RhoGTP dissociation inhibitor 2 effect on UM-UC-3 bladder cancer cells
description: Analysis of UM-UC-3 bladder carcinoma cells (low RhoGDI2-expressing and highly metastatic) stably transfected with GFP-RhoGDI2. RhoGDI2 is a metastasis suppressor protein. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of RhoGD12-mediated blockage of prometastatic inflammatory host response.

title: High-risk bladder cancer
description: Analysis of bladder cancer specimens from a high-risk population of patients who underwent radical cystectomy (Memorial Sloan-Kettering Cancer Center cohort). Results provide insight into the prediction of survival in high-risk urothelial carcinoma of the urinary bladder.

title: Strain PAO1 response to natural quorum sensing inhibitor protoanemonin
description: Analysis of laboratory strain PAO1 treated with 125μM protoanemonin (4-methylenebut-2-en-4-olide), a natural quorum sensing (QS) inhibitor. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying protoanemonin inhibition of QS in P. aeruginosa.

title: Anti-IL-17 monclonal antibody ixekizumab effect on chronic psoriasis
description: Analysis of psoriatic skin biopsies from patients treated with 150mg of subcutaneous anti-IL-17 mAb ixekizumab (previously LY2439821) at weeks 0 and 2. IL-17 blockade resulted in a high-grade clinical improvement in psoriasis. Results provide insight into the role of IL-17 in disease pathogenesis.

title: Pimecrolimus and betamethasone valerate effects on lesional skin of actopic dermatitis
description: Analysis of skin biopsies from AD patients treated with pimecrolimus on 1 upper limb and betamethasone (BM) on the other upper limb. BM is clinically more effective but does not restore the skin barrier, compared to pimecrolimus. Results provide insight into mechanisms of action of both substances.

title: Endothelial cells from P8 neonatal retina [MG_U74Av2]
description: Analysis of FACS-sorted, GFP-positive endothelial cells from retinas of postnatal day 8 (P8) homozygous Tie2-GFP transgenics. Deregulated retinal angiogenesis causes vision loss in many ocular diseases. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying intraretinal angiogenesis.

title: Endothelial cells from P8 neonatal retina [MG_U74Bv2]
description: Analysis of FACS-sorted, GFP-positive endothelial cells from retinas of postnatal day 8 (P8) homozygous Tie2-GFP transgenics. Deregulated retinal angiogenesis causes vision loss in many ocular diseases. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying intraretinal angiogenesis.

title: Endothelial cells from P8 neonatal retina [MG_U74Cv2]
description: Analysis of FACS-sorted, GFP-positive endothelial cells from retinas of postnatal day 8 (P8) homozygous Tie2-GFP transgenics. Deregulated retinal angiogenesis causes vision loss in many ocular diseases. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying intraretinal angiogenesis.

title: Primary central nervous system lymphoma patients: brain tumor
description: Analysis of brain tumor tissue from primary central nervous system lymphoma (PCNSL) patients. PCNSL is an extranodal form of non-Hodgkin lymphoma that arises in the craniospinal axis. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying survival in patients with PCNSL.

title: MYC oncogene overexpression and silencing effect in medulloblastoma DAOY cells
description: Analysis of medulloblastoma (MB)-derived cell lines genetically manipulated to either overexpress or silence the MYC oncogene. MYC overexpression and/or amplification is associated with poor clinical outcome. Results provide insight into transcriptional targets mediating the effects of MYC in MB.

title: Primary and secondary brain tumors: glioblastomas, astrocytomas and oligodendrogliomas
description: Analysis of primary glioblastomas (GBM), astrocytomas, oligodendrogliomas and secondary GBM brain tumors. MNK1 kinase upregulation observed in primary GBM brain tumors. Results identifiy signaling pathways differentially regulated in gliomas.

title: Glioblastoma cell lines: LN018, LN215, LN229, LN319 and BS149
description: Analysis of 5 glioblastoma cell lines (LN018, LN215, LN229, LN319 and BS149). Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying glioblastoma multiforme and other aggressive brain cancers.

title: Sporadic medulloblastomas
description: Analysis of sporadic medulloblastomas (MB), tumor grade IV from pediatric patients. Medulloblastoma is a highly malignant brain tumor occurring predominantly in children. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying the pathogenesis of MB.

title: Glioblastoma brain tumors
description: Analysis of glioblastoma (GBM) tumors from different regions of the brain from patients of various ages. Mutations in H3F3A and IDH1 define distinct epigenetic and biological subgroups of GBM. Results provide insight into heterogeneity of GBM and oncogenic pathways leading to gliomagenesis.

title: Medulloblastomas in children
description: Analysis of medulloblastomas from children ages 3 to 16 years. Medulloblastoma is a malignant childhood brain tumor comprising four discrete subgroups. Results provide insights into pathogenesis of medulloblastoma and highlight targets for therapeutic development.

title: Transcription factor OTX2 oncogene silencing effect on D425 medulloblastoma cell line: time course
description: Analysis of D425 medulloblastoma (MB) cells with doxycyline inducible shRNA against OTX2, sampled 0 to 96 hrs after induction in 3 independent time courses (TC). OTX2 is implicated as an oncogene in childhood MB. Results provide insight into role of OTX2 in medulloblastoma.

title: Glioblastoma multiforme and oligodendroglial glioma: neurospheres
description: Analysis of primary neurosphere cultures of glioblastoma (GBM) or oligodendroglial (ODG) tumors from 6 patients. Patient-derived glioma-propagating cells (GPC) contain karyotypic and gene expression profiles that are found in the primary tumor.

title: U373MG glioblastoma cell line response to 3 anti-cancer 1,2,3,4-tetrahydroisoquinoline alkaloids
description: Analysis of U373MG glioblastoma cells treated 24 hrs with DMSO or IC50 concentrations of anti-cancer compounds ecteinascidin-770 (ET-770), ET-770 derivative (ET-770-DR) or renieramycin M (RM). Results provide insight into pathways responsible for cytotoxic effects of compounds on glioblastoma.

title: Extracellular matrix protein cysteine rich 61 (CCN1) effect on LN229 glioma cells
description: Analysis of LN229 glioma cells with doxycycline-inducible expression of Cyr61 (CCN1), induced for 24h with doxycycline. CCN1 expression may reduce efficacy of oncolytic HSV-1 brain cancer therapy. Results provide insight into CCN1-mediated oncolytic HSV-1 inhibition.

title: Parkin expression in parkin-deficient U87MG glioma cells
description: Analysis of U87MG glioma cells stably expressing parkin or vector alone. Parkin expression is dramatically reduced in glioma cells. Parkin mutations are a major cause of parkinsonism. Results provide insight into tumor suppressor function of parkin in brain tumors.

title: Pediatric glioblastoma brain tumors: histone H3.3 mutations
description: Analysis of pediatric glioblastoma (GBM) tumors with mutations in H3F3A gene. Mutation of key residues in histone H3.3 are specific to GBM and highly prevalent in children and young adults. Results indicate that defects in chromatin architecture underlie pediatric GBM pathogenesis.

title: MYC-driven medulloblastoma model
description: Analysis of Myc/DNp53-infected tumors derived from stem cells or progenitors, uninfected stem cells, and patched tumor cells. Cerebellar stem cells expressing Myc and mutant Trp53 generate tumors similar to MYC-driven medulloblastoma (MB). Results provide insight into transformation to MB tumor.

title: Isolates from burn wound patients
description: Analysis of three different P. aeruginosa strains isolated from burn wound patients and the same strains using two infection models (a plant model and a murine tumor model). Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying P. aeruginosa infections.

title: Isolates from chronically-infected burn wound and cystic fibrosis patients
description: Analysis of P. aeruginosa strains isolated from chronically-infected lungs of cystic fibrosis (CF) patients, burn wounds, and a burn wound strain infected-murine tumor model. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying chronic biofilm-associated P. aeruginosa infections.

title: Fetal liver hematopoietic stem cells heterozygous for CREB binding protein
description: Analysis of HSCs sorted fromCrebbp+/− day 14 fetal livers. Crebbp+/− mice inevitably develop myelodysplastic syndromes (MDS) and myeloproliferative neoplasms (MPN) within 9 to 12 months of age. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying deregulation of HSC in MDS/MPN.

title: Sonic Hedgehog inhibitor cyclopamine effect on co-culture of mesenchymal stem cells and umbilical vein endothelial cells
description: Analysis of a co-culture of 92% human mesenchymal stem cells (hMSC) and 8% human umbilical vein endothelial cells (huvEC) treated with the Sonic Hedgehog morphogen inhibitor cyclopamine. The co-culture of hMSC and huvEC supports the formation of a primitive three dimensional vascular network.

title: TGF-beta receptor type II knockdown effect on embryonic palatal tissue
description: Analysis of palatal tissues from E14.5 animals depleted for f TGF-beta receptor type II in cranial neural crest cells. Palatal fusion takes place at E14.5. Results provide insight into the role of TGF-beta signaling in palate development.

title: Cerebellar neuronal cell response to thyroid hormone: time course
description: Analysis of cerebellar neuronal cells for up to 48 hours following treatment with thyroid hormone in vitro. Results provide insight into the role of thyroid hormone in the post-natal development of the cerebellum.

title: MYBL1 transcription factor knockout effect on testes
description: Analysis of testis from 14 and 17 day old Mybl1 repro9/repro9 mutants. Mybl1 is highly transcribed in spermatocytes after meiotic entry. Repro9 mutants exhibit male infertility due to arrest of meiosis pachytene stage. Results provide insight in the role of MYBL1 in the regulation of male meiosis.

title: Heterozygous null CREB binding protein mutant response to environmental enrichment: hippocampus
description: Analysis of hippocampi of heterozygous CREB-binding protein null (CBP) mutants following environmental enrichment (EE). EE was reported to be beneficial for a number of cognitive disorders. Results provide insight into the role of CBP in EE-induced neurogenesis and cognitive enhancement.

title: Ras/MEK inhibition effect on IFN-alpha treated cancer cell line: time course
description: Analysis of HT1080 cells treated with IFN-alpha, the Ras/MEK inhibitor U0126, or both for 6 or 12 hours. SKOV3 cells treated with IFN-alpha for 6 hours examined. HT1080 is moderately resistant to the anti-viral effects of IFN-alpha. MEK inhibition increases the sensitivity of HT1080 to IFN-alpha.

title: Notch1 signaling inhibition effect on aortic valve interstitial cells
description: Analysis of aortic valve interstitial cells treated with the Notch1 signaling inhibitor DAPT. NOTCH1 mutations are associated with aortic valve malformations and adult-onset calcification. Results provide insight into the role of Notch in the pathogenesis of calcific aortic valve disease.

title: Turner syndrome amniocyte derived-induced pluripotent stem cells
description: Analysis of induced pluripotent stem cells (iPSCs) derived from monosomy X (Turner syndrome (TS)) amniocytes. TS derived-iPSCs facilitate modeling of aneuploidy-related abnormal early development. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying aneuploid syndromes.

title: Lmna G609G knock-in model of Hutchinson-Gilford Progeria Syndrome: liver
description: Analysis of liver from Lmna Gly609Gly knock-in C57BL/6 females. These mice accumulate progerin and manifest the main clinical features of human Hutchinson-Gilford progeria syndrome (HGPS). Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying HGPS.

title: Nonlesional atopic dermatitis skin
description: Analysis of paired samples of nonlesional atopic dermatitis (ANL) and lesional atopic dermatitis (AL) skin lesions compared with normal skin. ANL skin is characterized by terminal differentiation defects. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms that characterize ANL skin.

title: FHH.Pkhd1 model of autosomal recessive polycystic kidney disease
description: Analysis of kidneys from 30 day-old males representing SD, FHH, PCK, and FHH.Pkhd1 strains. The FHH.Pkhd1 strain carries the PCK Pkhd1 mutation but is resistant to the development of ARPKD. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms that modulate ARPKD disease progression and severity.

title: Transcription factor Trps1 GATA-domain deletion effect on embryonic whisker pads
description: Analysis of whisker pads from E12.5 embryos in which the GATA domain of Trps1 has been deleted. Trps1∆gt/∆gt mutants have fewer pelage follicles and lack vibrissae follicles postnatally. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying vibrissa follicle morphogenesis.

title: Segmental monosomy
description: Analysis of adult females representing segmental deficiencies (Df), both as single Df/+ genotypes and in pairwise Df combinations. Aneuploidies such as segmental monosomy are associated with developmental abnormalities. Results provide insight into the effects of aneuploidies on the transcriptome.

title: SmoA1 and SmoA2 models of medulloblastoma: postnatal day 5 brain
description: Analysis of cerebella from Smoothened (Smo)A1 and SmoA2 mutants. The SmoA1 and SmoA2 mutations both cause medulloblastoma but have markedly different effects on cerebellar development. Results provide insight into the molecular basis of the oncogenic and developmental effects of the Smo variants.

title: Wing disc response to Epidermal Growth Factor Receptor signaling perturbations
description: Analysis of third instar wing disc from EGFR dominant negative (71B-Gal4; UAS EgfrDN) and EGFR activated (71B-GAL4; UAS EgfrACT) larvae. Aberrant signaling of highly conserved EGFR pathway is implicated in a number of diseases. Results provide insight into the identity of new EGFR-responsive genes.

title: Acute myeloid leukemia cell lines with high Ecotropic Viral Integration site 1 expression
description: Analysis of acute myeloid leukemia (AML) cell lines with high or low Ecotropic viral integration site 1 (EVI1) expression. High EVI1 levels predict adverse outcome in chemotherapy-resistant AML patients. Results provide insight into novel molecular targets in AML with high EVI1 expression.

title: Transcription factor Nrf2 gain-of-function model: postnatal day 2.5 whole skin
description: Analysis of whole skin from female, K5cre-caNrf2 transgenics at P2.5.  Nrf2 activation induced epidermal thickening and hyperkeratosis resembling human skin disease lamellar ichthyosis. Results provide insight into the role of Nrf2 as a regulator of protective functions of the epidermis.

title: Larval brains and imaginal discs with centrosome loss or amplification
description: Analysis of 3rd instar larval brains and imaginal discs that lack centrosomes (DSas-4 and DSas-6) or have too many centrosomes (SakOE). Centrosome defects are common to many cancers. Results provide insight into the effects of centrosome loss or amplification on cell physiology.

title: Acute myeloid leukemia with mutated nucleophosmin: bone marrow blasts (training set)
description: Analysis of AML blasts displaying aberrant cytoplasmic localization of nucleophosmin (NPMc+ AML) but negative for AML-associated chromosomal translocations. Results provide insight into putative predictors of NPM status.

title: Acute myeloid leukemia with mutated nucleophosmin: bone marrow blasts (test set)
description: Analysis of AML blasts displaying aberrant cytoplasmic localization of nucleophosmin (NPMc+ AML) but negative for AML-associated chromosomal translocations. Results provide insight into the validity of the putative predictors of NPM status identified by the training set.

title: Models of Neuronal Migration Defects: time course
description: Analysis of brains from 4 models of human neuronal migration defects (Lis1, Dcx, Ywhae, Ndel) at 3 developmental stages. Neuronal migration defects (NMDs) are an important cause of severe epilepsy and mental retardation. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying the NMDs.

title: Gonadal development: ovaries and testes
description: Analysis of gonads from fetal, neonatal and adult C57BL/6 males and females. Events during meiosis I prophase are critical for correct segregation of chromosomes. Defects in these events may contribute to infertility. Results provide insight into molecular mechanisms underlying meiosis I prophase.

title: Dicer1 deletion effect on bone marrow granulocyte-macrophage progenitors
description: Analysis of bone marrow-derived GMPs from Dicer1-deficient, C57BL/6 females. Dicer1 encodes an RNaseIII enzyme critical for miRNA biogenesis. Dicer1-deficient GMPs are defective in myeloid development in vitro. Results provide insight into the role of miRNAs in myeloid-lineage specification.

title: Ascorbic acid effect on Mc3T3 osteoblasts
